WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.579
Scholastic audio presents...

00:00:17.579 --> 00:00:19.260
Wings of Fire.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:19.920
Book 15.

00:00:20.399 --> 00:00:24.600
The Flames of Hope. by 2 E.T. Sutherland.

00:00:24.719 --> 00:00:27.179
Read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:51.299 --> 00:00:57.060
The Lost Continent Prophecy.

00:00:57.179 --> 00:01:02.159
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire, to

00:01:02.159 --> 00:01:05.040
the land across the sea, where dragons

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:08.340
are poisoned, and dragons are dying, and

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:09.599
no one can ever be free.

00:01:09.659 --> 00:01:13.200
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

00:01:13.260 --> 00:01:15.780
A secret hides within their book.

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:20.280
A secret buried far below may save those

00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:21.239
brave enough to look.

00:01:21.299 --> 00:01:25.620
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

00:01:25.620 --> 00:01:28.260
to the dragons who flee from the hive

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:32.879
face a great evil with talons united, or

00:01:32.879 --> 00:01:34.439
none of the tribes will survive.

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:49.260
Prologue.

00:01:49.379 --> 00:01:52.379
The problem with belonging to a village

00:01:52.379 --> 00:01:54.840
that worshipped a big, ominous hole in

00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:56.879
the ground is that holes in the ground

00:01:56.879 --> 00:01:59.400
tended to be very cryptic about their

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:00.239
mystical instructions.

00:02:00.299 --> 00:02:03.719
Messages from the deep didn't arrive all

00:02:03.719 --> 00:02:06.659
that often, luckily, and they arrived

00:02:06.659 --> 00:02:09.060
even less often once the leaders decided

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:11.460
to abandon the Guardian of the Abyss.

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:15.419
After all, if no one ever visited him, and

00:02:15.419 --> 00:02:17.879
there were no more ceremonies, how could

00:02:17.879 --> 00:02:18.300
he?

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:21.060
Or the abyss, if you believed that part

00:02:21.060 --> 00:02:21.360
of it?

00:02:21.419 --> 00:02:23.099
Demand anything.

00:02:23.159 --> 00:02:27.840
Instead, pretend it's not there, forbid

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:30.599
any mention of it, ignore the whispers

00:02:30.599 --> 00:02:31.319
and the shadows.

00:02:31.379 --> 00:02:33.900
And maybe everyone would eventually

00:02:33.900 --> 00:02:36.300
forget about the big ominous hole that

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:37.800
had ruled the village for centuries.

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:40.500
That was the leader's plan.

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:44.340
In principle, Raven agreed with the

00:02:44.340 --> 00:02:44.759
leaders.

00:02:44.819 --> 00:02:47.759
She agreed that the abyss was creepy, and

00:02:47.759 --> 00:02:49.620
that it was weird to worship a giant hole

00:02:49.620 --> 00:02:51.960
in the ground, and that it wasn't great

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:53.699
to let that hole take a person to keep

00:02:53.699 --> 00:02:55.020
for itself every 10 years.

00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:59.400
But it's tradition was not a good enough

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:00.599
reason to go along with it.

00:03:00.659 --> 00:03:04.379
Even after 1000s of years, maybe

00:03:04.379 --> 00:03:06.180
especially after 1000s of years.

00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:10.139
If it had really been that long, that

00:03:10.139 --> 00:03:12.180
meant 100s of humans had been swallowed

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:12.900
up by the Abyss.

00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:15.900
The great and wonderful ancestor who had

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:18.719
agreed to this in the 1st place was long

00:03:18.719 --> 00:03:21.419
long gone, and maybe he hadn't never done

00:03:21.419 --> 00:03:23.460
the math on how much sacrifice would be

00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:23.759
involved.

00:03:23.819 --> 00:03:27.180
That still felt a little blasphemous.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:29.580
Their ancestor had saved them all.

00:03:29.639 --> 00:03:31.860
He was perfect, and could do no wrong.

00:03:31.979 --> 00:03:34.979
But maybe he could have made a better

00:03:34.979 --> 00:03:37.379
deal with the abyss, was all Raven was

00:03:37.379 --> 00:03:37.680
suggesting.

00:03:37.740 --> 00:03:42.060
So yes, she agreed with the leaders.

00:03:42.120 --> 00:03:44.580
It was time to stop feeding the abyss.

00:03:44.639 --> 00:03:47.219
It was definitely time to stop giving it

00:03:47.219 --> 00:03:47.879
new guardians.

00:03:47.939 --> 00:03:50.699
Vol could be the last one ever.

00:03:50.759 --> 00:03:54.360
But abandoning the abyss, and the whole

00:03:54.360 --> 00:03:56.400
practice of abyss worship was one thing.

00:03:56.460 --> 00:04:00.120
Abandoning Vol himself was too hard and

00:04:00.120 --> 00:04:00.599
too sad.

00:04:00.659 --> 00:04:04.379
Once upon a time, Vol had been a normal

00:04:04.379 --> 00:04:04.800
person.

00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:09.000
He'd been mole, silly big brother, funny

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:11.699
charming, really good at climbing sheer

00:04:11.699 --> 00:04:12.360
rock faces.

00:04:12.419 --> 00:04:15.599
It wasn't his fault that a green tentacle

00:04:15.599 --> 00:04:17.879
had reached out of the abyss, and dragged

00:04:17.879 --> 00:04:19.920
him in during the Guardian ceremony 4

00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:20.279
years ago.

00:04:20.339 --> 00:04:23.459
No one could ever predict who the Abyss

00:04:23.459 --> 00:04:23.819
would choose.

00:04:23.879 --> 00:04:28.199
If Raven were a sinister chasm looking

00:04:28.199 --> 00:04:30.899
for someone's brain to steal, she would

00:04:30.899 --> 00:04:33.180
have picked quartz, who played ball

00:04:33.180 --> 00:04:35.399
kicking games all day long, and was

00:04:35.399 --> 00:04:36.720
extremely boring.

00:04:36.839 --> 00:04:40.439
Court could have become guardian and sat

00:04:40.439 --> 00:04:42.660
beside the abyss all day, staring into

00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:43.079
space.

00:04:43.139 --> 00:04:44.939
And it wouldn't be all that different

00:04:44.939 --> 00:04:45.959
from how he was before.

00:04:46.019 --> 00:04:49.199
Raven could have gone on with her life

00:04:49.199 --> 00:04:51.899
just fine if everyone decided to give up

00:04:51.899 --> 00:04:52.500
on courts.

00:04:52.620 --> 00:04:54.060
She thought.

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:55.379
Probably.

00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:57.899
Even that idea made her feel a little

00:04:57.899 --> 00:04:58.560
sick inside.

00:04:58.680 --> 00:05:00.720
But Vol?

00:05:00.839 --> 00:05:03.540
If there were a tiny part of him that was

00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:07.379
still himself in there, she didn't want

00:05:07.379 --> 00:05:07.860
him to be alone.

00:05:07.920 --> 00:05:10.740
She didn't want him to think she'd left

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:12.300
him, like everyone else.

00:05:12.360 --> 00:05:16.079
Mole was the only one still allowed to

00:05:16.079 --> 00:05:17.519
visit him to bring him food.

00:05:17.579 --> 00:05:20.759
The leaders couldn't condemn Bull to

00:05:20.759 --> 00:05:21.420
starving to death.

00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:23.939
But no one else was supposed to go near

00:05:23.939 --> 00:05:24.240
him.

00:05:24.300 --> 00:05:27.720
At first, a few had tried to talk him

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:29.879
into leaving the abyss, and coming back

00:05:29.879 --> 00:05:32.399
to the village, and that had gone very

00:05:32.399 --> 00:05:33.180
poorly.

00:05:33.240 --> 00:05:36.300
The leaders didn't want anyone else to

00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:38.220
risk getting thrown into the chasm.

00:05:38.279 --> 00:05:41.819
So when Raven visited Vole, she had to do

00:05:41.819 --> 00:05:42.420
it in secret.

00:05:42.480 --> 00:05:46.740
Which meant she had absolutely no one to

00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:48.540
tell when the guardian gave her his

00:05:48.540 --> 00:05:49.800
terrifying instructions.

00:05:49.860 --> 00:05:52.319
Find the dragon.

00:05:52.379 --> 00:05:54.060
Bring it here.

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:57.600
Or everyone you know will die.

00:05:57.660 --> 00:06:03.300
So, all right, 1st question, what

00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:04.199
dragon?

00:06:04.259 --> 00:06:05.759
Any dragon?

00:06:05.819 --> 00:06:08.879
Was Raven supposed to somehow find a

00:06:08.879 --> 00:06:10.860
specific particular dragon somewhere?

00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:13.740
Deduce that that was the one the Abyss

00:06:13.740 --> 00:06:14.759
wanted, and then...

00:06:15.959 --> 00:06:16.379
What?

00:06:16.439 --> 00:06:19.079
Tie it up and haul it all the way down to

00:06:19.079 --> 00:06:20.220
the abyss?

00:06:20.279 --> 00:06:22.319
Did the Abyss think she had superpowers?

00:06:22.379 --> 00:06:26.819
How was a human supposed to make a dragon

00:06:26.819 --> 00:06:27.480
go anywhere?

00:06:27.540 --> 00:06:30.720
And again, what dragon?

00:06:30.779 --> 00:06:35.220
Saying, the dragon sounded nastily

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:35.759
specific.

00:06:35.819 --> 00:06:40.079
The abyss wasn't like, bring me a dragon

00:06:40.079 --> 00:06:41.699
as in, anyone will do.

00:06:41.819 --> 00:06:46.199
But if it did want a particular dragon, it

00:06:46.199 --> 00:06:47.459
needed to give her something to work

00:06:47.459 --> 00:06:47.699
with.

00:06:47.759 --> 00:06:50.100
A color for starters would be great.

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:51.779
How many wings?

00:06:51.839 --> 00:06:53.040
Big or small?

00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:55.139
Alive or dead?

00:06:55.199 --> 00:06:57.660
Ha, ha, ha.

00:06:57.720 --> 00:07:00.300
As if Raven could kill a dragon, whether

00:07:00.300 --> 00:07:02.100
the Abyss wanted her to or not.

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:06.300
In any case, the Abyss had not deigned to

00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:07.379
answer any of these questions.

00:07:07.439 --> 00:07:11.399
Voll had continued to stare intently over

00:07:11.399 --> 00:07:14.100
the edge into darkness, ignoring her.

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:17.879
So after days of useless thinking and a

00:07:17.879 --> 00:07:20.759
few unsuccessful experiments, Raven had

00:07:20.759 --> 00:07:21.959
done the only possible thing.

00:07:22.019 --> 00:07:25.259
She'd dragged Mole into her problem.

00:07:25.379 --> 00:07:28.379
She found him alone at one of the cave

00:07:28.379 --> 00:07:31.079
lakes, knocked him over, and sat on him

00:07:31.079 --> 00:07:31.920
before he could run away.

00:07:31.980 --> 00:07:35.100
Don't be mad, she started.

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:37.019
God, no.

00:07:37.079 --> 00:07:39.120
Mole gripped his face with his hands.

00:07:39.180 --> 00:07:40.860
Raven!

00:07:40.920 --> 00:07:42.959
How about don't do things that make

00:07:42.959 --> 00:07:43.740
people mad?

00:07:43.860 --> 00:07:47.160
I didn't do this, she protested.

00:07:47.220 --> 00:07:48.060
I swear.

00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:48.779
I mean.

00:07:48.959 --> 00:07:51.120
She squinted up at the ceiling.

00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:54.779
That is, I did a thing that might make

00:07:54.779 --> 00:07:57.060
you mad, but the actual problem I have to

00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:58.620
tell you about is not my fault.

00:07:58.680 --> 00:07:59.759
Seriously.

00:07:59.759 --> 00:08:02.639
Can you tell me one without telling me

00:08:02.639 --> 00:08:03.000
the other?

00:08:03.060 --> 00:08:04.199
he asked.

00:08:04.259 --> 00:08:06.180
She thought for a minute.

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:09.060
Mole lay still on the stone floor

00:08:09.060 --> 00:08:09.779
underneath her.

00:08:09.839 --> 00:08:13.199
His fishing net dropped nearby, his arms

00:08:13.199 --> 00:08:14.100
propped behind his head.

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:17.939
He was a little judgmental, and too much

00:08:17.939 --> 00:08:18.959
of a rule follower.

00:08:19.019 --> 00:08:22.199
But he was smart, and still usually the

00:08:22.199 --> 00:08:23.819
most agreeable person Raven knew.

00:08:23.879 --> 00:08:27.000
Hypothetically, she said.

00:08:27.060 --> 00:08:29.639
If you really needed to get a dragon from

00:08:29.639 --> 00:08:31.439
one place to another, how would you do

00:08:31.439 --> 00:08:31.620
it?

00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:34.259
He stared into her eyes.

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:37.559
Finally, he said, What?

00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:40.860
Imagine there's a dragon, she said.

00:08:40.919 --> 00:08:43.439
And you need it to go somewhere pretty

00:08:43.439 --> 00:08:46.319
specific, and you would prefer to not get

00:08:46.319 --> 00:08:47.039
eaten on the way?

00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:48.120
What would you do?

00:08:48.179 --> 00:08:49.980
Specifically.

00:08:50.039 --> 00:08:52.679
Raven, he said.

00:08:52.740 --> 00:08:57.419
When you say somewhere pretty specific, do

00:08:57.419 --> 00:08:58.980
you mean the abyss?

00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:02.100
Who said anything about the abyss?

00:09:02.220 --> 00:09:03.059
She flailed.

00:09:03.120 --> 00:09:04.259
I didn't.

00:09:04.320 --> 00:09:05.340
Why did you?

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:06.059
Nobody said.

00:09:06.179 --> 00:09:07.259
Hey, wait.

00:09:07.320 --> 00:09:09.179
What happened to the rules?

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:10.799
You said abyss, not me.

00:09:10.860 --> 00:09:11.820
It wasn't me this time.

00:09:11.879 --> 00:09:13.799
The rules.

00:09:13.919 --> 00:09:16.559
Nobody mentions the abyss.

00:09:16.679 --> 00:09:19.139
Nobody goes near the Abyss.

00:09:19.200 --> 00:09:22.080
Everyone pretends the Abyss does not

00:09:22.080 --> 00:09:22.679
exist anymore.

00:09:22.740 --> 00:09:27.000
Everyone acts like they hear absolutely 0

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:30.179
whispers and feel 0 weirdness coming from

00:09:30.179 --> 00:09:32.220
the creepy, big, dark hole.

00:09:32.279 --> 00:09:35.759
Mole rubbed his face again and gently

00:09:35.759 --> 00:09:36.480
pushed her off him.

00:09:36.539 --> 00:09:39.539
He sat up and buried his hands in his

00:09:39.539 --> 00:09:39.899
hair.

00:09:39.960 --> 00:09:42.659
If you're talking about what I think

00:09:42.659 --> 00:09:45.179
you're talking about, Vol said the same

00:09:45.179 --> 00:09:45.600
thing to me.

00:09:45.659 --> 00:09:47.759
He did?

00:09:47.820 --> 00:09:49.919
Raven poked him in the arm.

00:09:49.980 --> 00:09:51.539
Why didn't you tell me?

00:09:51.600 --> 00:09:53.279
Why would I?

00:09:53.340 --> 00:09:55.259
We're not supposed to talk about the

00:09:55.259 --> 00:09:55.919
abyss, remember?

00:09:55.980 --> 00:09:58.980
I'm not even allowed to mention Vol.

00:09:59.039 --> 00:10:01.740
How could I tell anyone he's given me a

00:10:01.740 --> 00:10:03.059
weird abyss message?

00:10:03.120 --> 00:10:05.639
You definitely shouldn't somehow know

00:10:05.639 --> 00:10:06.659
about it already.

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:08.220
He sighed.

00:10:08.279 --> 00:10:09.779
Raven.

00:10:09.840 --> 00:10:11.580
How did you?

00:10:11.879 --> 00:10:13.379
He trailed off.

00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:17.460
I visit him sometimes, she mumbled.

00:10:17.580 --> 00:10:20.159
She pulled one of the knives out of her

00:10:20.159 --> 00:10:22.379
boots and stabbed it into a crack in the

00:10:22.379 --> 00:10:22.559
floor.

00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:24.840
I don't get too close.

00:10:24.899 --> 00:10:28.259
I just... sit nearby and talk to him.

00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:32.100
When she looked up, she was startled by

00:10:32.100 --> 00:10:33.000
Mole's expression.

00:10:33.059 --> 00:10:34.799
It wasn't mad at all.

00:10:34.860 --> 00:10:37.860
He looked like he was about to burst into

00:10:37.860 --> 00:10:38.220
tears.

00:10:38.340 --> 00:10:40.740
Don't be weird about it.

00:10:40.799 --> 00:10:41.820
She cried.

00:10:41.879 --> 00:10:43.200
I feel bad for him.

00:10:43.259 --> 00:10:45.480
I know he's not really there anymore, but

00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:47.639
I still kind of keep waiting to see if he

00:10:47.639 --> 00:10:47.879
is.

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:49.200
I can't help it.

00:10:49.259 --> 00:10:50.460
I'm an idiot.

00:10:50.580 --> 00:10:51.360
I know that.

00:10:51.419 --> 00:10:53.279
You are.

00:10:53.340 --> 00:10:56.700
But so am I, Mole admitted.

00:10:56.759 --> 00:10:59.759
So he gave you the same message.

00:10:59.820 --> 00:11:03.539
Find a dragon, bring it to the abyss?

00:11:03.659 --> 00:11:06.240
Raven sighed as he nodded.

00:11:06.299 --> 00:11:09.179
How can we possibly do that, Mole?

00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:11.580
Do you think we have to?

00:11:11.639 --> 00:11:13.799
Could we ignore him?

00:11:13.860 --> 00:11:18.059
My message ended on a pretty clear, or

00:11:18.059 --> 00:11:20.759
everyone you know will die, note, she

00:11:20.759 --> 00:11:24.360
said, which also wasn't very specific, but

00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:26.279
I can imagine how a possessed guardian

00:11:26.279 --> 00:11:28.559
and an abyss full of green tentacles

00:11:28.559 --> 00:11:29.759
might go about killing everyone.

00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:33.720
On the other hand, I don't want to make

00:11:33.720 --> 00:11:34.919
the dragons mad either.

00:11:34.980 --> 00:11:36.120
Mole said.

00:11:36.179 --> 00:11:38.940
I'm guessing we need one from that big

00:11:38.940 --> 00:11:40.559
group that settled in the caves last

00:11:40.559 --> 00:11:40.799
month.

00:11:40.860 --> 00:11:44.220
But if we somehow did steal one of their

00:11:44.220 --> 00:11:46.799
dragons, wouldn't that make the rest all

00:11:46.799 --> 00:11:47.940
furious and vengeful?

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:49.740
I don't know about you.

00:11:49.799 --> 00:11:52.080
But I don't love the idea of living in a

00:11:52.080 --> 00:11:54.480
cave system with 100s of angry dragons.

00:11:54.539 --> 00:11:56.940
That sounds even worse than an angry

00:11:56.940 --> 00:11:57.600
abyss.

00:11:57.720 --> 00:12:00.720
So, we have to be clever about it.

00:12:00.779 --> 00:12:02.340
Raven suggested.

00:12:02.399 --> 00:12:05.100
I was thinking we skip over the problem

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:08.519
of which dragon it wants, and see whether

00:12:08.519 --> 00:12:10.259
we can get any dragon there.

00:12:10.320 --> 00:12:13.019
My 1st thought was to let one of them see

00:12:13.019 --> 00:12:15.179
me and hope it's hungry enough to chase

00:12:15.179 --> 00:12:16.019
me to the abyss.

00:12:16.139 --> 00:12:19.799
Oh, wow, Mole said.

00:12:19.860 --> 00:12:21.659
Terrible, terrible plan.

00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:23.100
I hated very much.

00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:26.399
More terrible than you realize, she

00:12:26.399 --> 00:12:26.700
said.

00:12:26.759 --> 00:12:30.240
Only like 2 or 3 of the dragons in that

00:12:30.240 --> 00:12:31.080
group are hunters.

00:12:31.200 --> 00:12:34.440
I can't get any of the colorful 4 wing

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:35.159
ones to chase me.

00:12:35.220 --> 00:12:37.620
You've tried?

00:12:37.620 --> 00:12:40.379
he said, looking at her aghast.

00:12:40.440 --> 00:12:43.259
Of course I've tried, she said.

00:12:43.320 --> 00:12:44.759
I've tried lots of things.

00:12:44.820 --> 00:12:46.620
I wouldn't bother you without trying

00:12:46.620 --> 00:12:48.240
everything I could think of first.

00:12:48.299 --> 00:12:51.120
The colorful dragons are not interested

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:52.019
in me at all.

00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:55.259
I can dance under their noses, and the

00:12:55.259 --> 00:12:56.580
worst they'll do is sniff me.

00:12:56.639 --> 00:12:59.820
I could get the big green Dobe one to

00:12:59.820 --> 00:13:01.080
chase me, but that's risky.

00:13:01.139 --> 00:13:03.120
He's really determined.

00:13:03.179 --> 00:13:05.700
I don't want him to accidentally find the

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:06.000
village.

00:13:06.059 --> 00:13:09.000
Right, he said.

00:13:09.059 --> 00:13:11.399
We should definitely avoid that.

00:13:11.460 --> 00:13:13.919
What have you tried so far?

00:13:13.919 --> 00:13:15.059
she asked.

00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:17.639
Um, he said.

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:19.080
Worrying?

00:13:19.139 --> 00:13:21.299
I've tried every variety of worrying.

00:13:21.360 --> 00:13:25.740
That's my best friend, she said, punching

00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:26.820
his shoulder affectionately.

00:13:26.879 --> 00:13:29.460
Doing the hard stuff so I don't have to.

00:13:29.580 --> 00:13:31.799
Ha, ha.

00:13:31.860 --> 00:13:34.139
What have you done besides volunteers

00:13:34.139 --> 00:13:34.919
dragon snack?

00:13:35.039 --> 00:13:36.539
She made a face.

00:13:36.600 --> 00:13:38.519
I looked for treasure.

00:13:38.580 --> 00:13:40.799
Dragons like shiny things right?

00:13:40.860 --> 00:13:42.720
That's what the storybooks say.

00:13:42.779 --> 00:13:45.960
I thought maybe if I made like a trail of

00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:48.539
diamonds, some dragon might follow it all

00:13:48.539 --> 00:13:49.679
the way to the abyss.

00:13:49.740 --> 00:13:51.720
That's...

00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:53.700
A lot of diamonds.

00:13:53.759 --> 00:13:55.200
I know.

00:13:55.259 --> 00:13:57.960
There's no way I can surreptitiously

00:13:57.960 --> 00:13:58.740
gather that much treasure.

00:13:58.860 --> 00:14:04.139
I tried prying one teeny tiny diamond out

00:14:04.139 --> 00:14:06.480
of the wall in the Salvation Tunnel, and

00:14:06.480 --> 00:14:09.000
mom caught me, and I got in so much

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:09.659
trouble.

00:14:09.720 --> 00:14:11.279
You have no idea.

00:14:11.399 --> 00:14:15.779
The week I didn't see you, he gasped, and

00:14:15.779 --> 00:14:16.679
she shrugged.

00:14:16.740 --> 00:14:18.059
He knew her parents.

00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:20.759
Solitary confinement was their usual

00:14:20.759 --> 00:14:21.600
punishment for everything.

00:14:21.720 --> 00:14:24.840
So, what else can we do?

00:14:24.899 --> 00:14:26.580
Any ideas?

00:14:26.639 --> 00:14:27.899
She asked.

00:14:27.960 --> 00:14:31.019
There's that flower juice the doctors use

00:14:31.019 --> 00:14:32.519
to make people sleep during surgeries.

00:14:32.580 --> 00:14:36.059
What if I somehow got a lot of that and

00:14:36.059 --> 00:14:36.960
gave it to a dragon?

00:14:37.019 --> 00:14:41.220
Maybe you could trick a dragon into

00:14:41.220 --> 00:14:44.100
eating something so it fell asleep, Mole

00:14:44.100 --> 00:14:44.759
said pensively.

00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:47.879
But then you'd have to figure out how to

00:14:47.879 --> 00:14:51.120
move a giant sleeping dragon, Raven.

00:14:51.179 --> 00:14:53.159
Yes, all right.

00:14:53.220 --> 00:14:55.740
That's where the plan fell apart in my

00:14:55.740 --> 00:14:57.120
head too, she said.

00:14:57.179 --> 00:14:59.279
Unless...

00:14:59.279 --> 00:15:01.019
Wheelbarrows?

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:02.519
Pulleys?

00:15:02.580 --> 00:15:04.740
Hypnotize the whole village and have them

00:15:04.740 --> 00:15:05.460
carry it for me?

00:15:05.519 --> 00:15:07.440
Okay, fine.

00:15:07.500 --> 00:15:08.340
Too hard.

00:15:08.399 --> 00:15:11.519
What about some kind of message for the

00:15:11.519 --> 00:15:12.179
dragons?

00:15:12.179 --> 00:15:13.259
he suggested.

00:15:13.320 --> 00:15:16.679
Like a drawing, a map to the abyss.

00:15:16.740 --> 00:15:19.139
With a picture of a big pile of treasure

00:15:19.139 --> 00:15:20.639
in the abyss.

00:15:20.759 --> 00:15:23.759
Raven laughed despite herself.

00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:27.120
We might end up luring the dumbest dragon

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:29.460
in the history of the world, she said.

00:15:29.519 --> 00:15:30.960
La, la, la.

00:15:31.019 --> 00:15:32.399
What's this lying here on the floor?

00:15:32.460 --> 00:15:35.159
A map to treasure.

00:15:35.220 --> 00:15:37.740
This doesn't seem suspicious at all.

00:15:37.799 --> 00:15:41.519
Off I go, dum dum, along this trail to

00:15:41.519 --> 00:15:42.960
get my pile of diamonds.

00:15:43.019 --> 00:15:44.820
This is completely normal.

00:15:44.879 --> 00:15:48.240
Your imaginary dragon sounds way too

00:15:48.240 --> 00:15:48.659
human.

00:15:48.720 --> 00:15:50.039
Mole protested.

00:15:50.100 --> 00:15:52.620
I'd be more worried that dragons would

00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:54.899
know what a map is, let alone how to

00:15:54.899 --> 00:15:55.320
follow one.

00:15:55.379 --> 00:15:59.039
You don't watch them enough, Raven

00:15:59.039 --> 00:15:59.580
pointed out.

00:15:59.639 --> 00:16:01.860
They are definitely smart enough to read

00:16:01.860 --> 00:16:04.500
maps, and too smart to fall for a fake

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:04.740
one.

00:16:04.799 --> 00:16:08.100
Next, you'll be telling me they have

00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:10.139
feelings like us too, he said.

00:16:10.200 --> 00:16:12.299
As though there are dragons who care

00:16:12.299 --> 00:16:13.379
about their brothers or something.

00:16:13.440 --> 00:16:16.080
He glanced sideways at her.

00:16:16.139 --> 00:16:18.960
Or dragons who would do anything for

00:16:18.960 --> 00:16:19.620
their best friends.

00:16:19.679 --> 00:16:23.100
Her hand stilled on her knife.

00:16:23.159 --> 00:16:24.480
Wait.

00:16:24.539 --> 00:16:27.059
Dragons with feelings?

00:16:27.120 --> 00:16:30.000
If any dragons had feelings.

00:16:30.059 --> 00:16:32.399
It was probably those rainbow colored

00:16:32.399 --> 00:16:33.539
butterfly looking ones.

00:16:33.600 --> 00:16:36.059
Maybe they did care about one another

00:16:36.059 --> 00:16:38.460
like humans did, more or less.

00:16:38.519 --> 00:16:41.220
And if so, maybe she could use that.

00:16:41.279 --> 00:16:44.159
Maybe this was how they could trick a

00:16:44.159 --> 00:16:44.639
dragon.

00:16:44.700 --> 00:16:47.340
By finding its most human weakness.

00:16:47.399 --> 00:16:52.200
Raven, Mole said, as she tucked her knife

00:16:52.200 --> 00:16:52.919
back into her boot.

00:16:53.039 --> 00:16:56.279
She met his eyes and smiled ruefully at

00:16:56.279 --> 00:16:56.519
him.

00:16:56.580 --> 00:17:00.299
He was wearing his rules are rules, and

00:17:00.299 --> 00:17:02.220
what am I going to do with you, face?

00:17:02.340 --> 00:17:04.619
Which usually meant a lecture was

00:17:04.619 --> 00:17:04.859
coming?

00:17:04.920 --> 00:17:09.180
But then he said, I know I should be mad

00:17:09.180 --> 00:17:11.579
you broke the rules to see Vol, but...

00:17:11.579 --> 00:17:13.140
Raven.

00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:15.839
I'm so glad I finally have someone I can

00:17:15.839 --> 00:17:16.859
talk to about this.

00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:20.700
She felt little cracks spreading across

00:17:20.700 --> 00:17:21.000
her heart.

00:17:21.059 --> 00:17:24.839
Mole had been all alone with this secret

00:17:24.839 --> 00:17:26.039
just like she had.

00:17:26.099 --> 00:17:29.279
He'd thought the fate of the village in

00:17:29.279 --> 00:17:31.979
everyone's lives rested entirely on his

00:17:31.979 --> 00:17:32.819
own thin shoulders.

00:17:32.940 --> 00:17:34.799
Poor mole.

00:17:34.859 --> 00:17:37.440
When he already had so much to deal with

00:17:37.440 --> 00:17:41.039
between being Voles, sole caretaker, and

00:17:41.039 --> 00:17:43.440
the only remaining son and heir of the

00:17:43.440 --> 00:17:43.980
leaders.

00:17:44.039 --> 00:17:47.759
She put one arm around him, and he rested

00:17:47.759 --> 00:17:48.480
his head against hers.

00:17:48.599 --> 00:17:51.900
We'll figure this out together, she

00:17:51.900 --> 00:17:52.319
promised.

00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:54.119
You don't have to do it alone.

00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:56.160
I have a new idea.

00:17:56.220 --> 00:18:00.299
Uh-oh, he said, and they both laughed.

00:18:00.359 --> 00:18:03.059
He reached across her and took her free

00:18:03.059 --> 00:18:03.900
hand in both of his.

00:18:04.019 --> 00:18:06.059
Raven.

00:18:06.119 --> 00:18:08.940
Why do you think the abyss is asking for

00:18:08.940 --> 00:18:09.720
a dragon now?

00:18:09.779 --> 00:18:11.339
After all this time.

00:18:11.460 --> 00:18:14.220
I don't know, she said.

00:18:14.339 --> 00:18:16.619
That seems like the dragon's problem, not

00:18:16.619 --> 00:18:16.859
mine.

00:18:16.920 --> 00:18:19.740
It's one of the things I've been worrying

00:18:19.740 --> 00:18:21.059
about, he said.

00:18:21.119 --> 00:18:24.660
Like, if the abyss is angry.

00:18:24.720 --> 00:18:27.779
Is it a good idea to give it a dragon?

00:18:27.900 --> 00:18:30.839
What is it going to do to the dragon?

00:18:30.900 --> 00:18:33.900
And if dragons have feelings like

00:18:33.900 --> 00:18:34.259
humans?

00:18:34.319 --> 00:18:36.000
Raven thought.

00:18:36.059 --> 00:18:39.779
Well, I wouldn't want to be given to a

00:18:39.779 --> 00:18:40.740
sinister abyss.

00:18:40.859 --> 00:18:43.920
Is this any better than the guardian

00:18:43.920 --> 00:18:44.519
ceremony?

00:18:44.640 --> 00:18:46.380
Mole said quietly.

00:18:46.440 --> 00:18:49.019
Do we have a choice?

00:18:49.019 --> 00:18:49.799
Raven asked.

00:18:49.859 --> 00:18:52.500
Won't the whole village be in danger if

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:53.819
we don't do what Volt says?

00:18:53.880 --> 00:18:55.799
Mole frowned.

00:18:55.859 --> 00:18:58.619
And Raven instinctively reached to rub

00:18:58.619 --> 00:19:00.240
his temple the way his brother used to.

00:19:00.299 --> 00:19:01.799
Listen.

00:19:01.920 --> 00:19:04.500
Whatever's going on with the abyss, and

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:05.160
the dragons?

00:19:05.220 --> 00:19:07.500
Maybe this will fix it, she said.

00:19:07.559 --> 00:19:10.200
Maybe this will make the abyss focus on

00:19:10.200 --> 00:19:12.059
the dragons, and leave us alone.

00:19:12.119 --> 00:19:13.200
Maybe.

00:19:13.440 --> 00:19:16.079
Her breath caught in her throat for a

00:19:16.079 --> 00:19:16.259
moment.

00:19:16.319 --> 00:19:18.180
Maybe.

00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:21.240
If we give it a dragon, it will give us

00:19:21.240 --> 00:19:21.960
back vole.

00:19:22.019 --> 00:19:23.819
The way he used to be.

00:19:23.940 --> 00:19:27.720
Mole sat up with a gasp and stared at

00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:27.900
her.

00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:29.759
Do you think so?

00:19:29.819 --> 00:19:31.859
I don't know.

00:19:31.980 --> 00:19:33.779
Don't get your hopes up.

00:19:33.839 --> 00:19:35.759
But we can ask, can't we?

00:19:35.819 --> 00:19:37.980
He nodded.

00:19:38.039 --> 00:19:39.839
His eyes drifting toward the lake.

00:19:39.900 --> 00:19:41.640
Right.

00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:44.519
And it's only one dragon.

00:19:44.579 --> 00:19:47.519
He let out a long breath.

00:19:47.579 --> 00:19:50.880
I hope we're doing the right thing.

00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:55.559
Part one.

00:19:55.619 --> 00:19:58.740
The land across the sea.

00:19:58.859 --> 00:20:01.980
Chapter one.

00:20:02.039 --> 00:20:05.099
Luna wanted to change the world.

00:20:05.160 --> 00:20:08.099
She knew what it should be like.

00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:12.000
She knew it could be more just and more

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:14.940
beautiful and more safe and more kind.

00:20:15.059 --> 00:20:18.240
A world where dragons loved whoever they

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:21.059
wanted to love, where they created art

00:20:21.059 --> 00:20:23.099
and took care of one another, and were

00:20:23.099 --> 00:20:24.720
happy instead of hurtful.

00:20:25.019 --> 00:20:27.900
Surely everyone wanted that world.

00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:30.240
So why couldn't it exist already?

00:20:30.299 --> 00:20:33.660
Luna knew exactly what she wanted to

00:20:33.660 --> 00:20:34.440
change and why.

00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:38.400
She just wasn't quite sure how yet.

00:20:38.460 --> 00:20:41.640
She wished the world was more like a

00:20:41.640 --> 00:20:43.980
weaving, where she could tear out the

00:20:43.980 --> 00:20:46.079
bits that were knotted wrong, or colors

00:20:46.079 --> 00:20:49.380
twisted in the wrong places, then reweave

00:20:49.380 --> 00:20:49.859
it all again.

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:53.160
Better and mend it and perfect.

00:20:53.220 --> 00:20:56.400
She knew how to fix a messed up

00:20:56.400 --> 00:20:57.000
tapestry.

00:20:57.059 --> 00:21:00.240
She had no idea where to start fixing a

00:21:00.240 --> 00:21:00.720
broken world.

00:21:00.779 --> 00:21:04.680
The problem was, there were so many

00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:07.019
things wrong, and they all needed

00:21:07.019 --> 00:21:07.559
fixing.

00:21:07.619 --> 00:21:10.619
And the other problem was how many

00:21:10.619 --> 00:21:12.180
dragons didn't seem to see that.

00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:15.420
A lot of dragons thought everything was

00:21:15.420 --> 00:21:15.660
fine.

00:21:15.720 --> 00:21:19.200
Even some of Luna's very favorite, most

00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:21.779
loved dragons didn't seem to care about

00:21:21.779 --> 00:21:23.039
all the wrong bad things.

00:21:23.099 --> 00:21:26.759
This had been baffling her all her life.

00:21:26.819 --> 00:21:29.579
She had started noticing the problems

00:21:29.579 --> 00:21:30.359
with her world.

00:21:30.420 --> 00:21:32.640
From the 1st moment her mothers had

00:21:32.640 --> 00:21:34.259
walked her through cicada hive.

00:21:34.319 --> 00:21:36.779
And even more clearly, during her

00:21:36.779 --> 00:21:38.579
earliest days of school at Silkworm

00:21:38.579 --> 00:21:38.819
Hall.

00:21:38.880 --> 00:21:41.220
How could anyone else miss them?

00:21:41.279 --> 00:21:45.720
For instance, it was wrong that the hive

00:21:45.720 --> 00:21:47.940
wings had cut down all the trees, and it

00:21:47.940 --> 00:21:51.779
was very, very, very wrong, that the hive

00:21:51.779 --> 00:21:53.819
wings had wiped out all the leaf wings.

00:21:53.880 --> 00:21:57.059
It was wrong that a silk wing couldn't

00:21:57.059 --> 00:21:59.880
choose her own life partner, her job, or

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:00.539
where she lived.

00:22:00.599 --> 00:22:04.019
It was awful that Luna's father had been

00:22:04.019 --> 00:22:05.759
taken away before she even hatched.

00:22:05.819 --> 00:22:09.480
And it was unfair that Queen Wasp got to

00:22:09.480 --> 00:22:11.039
decide everything that happened to the

00:22:11.039 --> 00:22:13.140
Silk Wings, and they couldn't say

00:22:13.140 --> 00:22:13.799
anything about it.

00:22:13.859 --> 00:22:17.279
A lot of dragons might argue that those

00:22:17.279 --> 00:22:20.400
things were fine, because Queen Wasp was

00:22:20.400 --> 00:22:22.200
the dragon in charge, and she said so.

00:22:22.259 --> 00:22:25.380
And also something, something war, and

00:22:25.380 --> 00:22:26.579
something, something danger.

00:22:26.640 --> 00:22:28.440
So that was how the world had to be.

00:22:28.500 --> 00:22:31.980
But even if you accepted all of that.

00:22:32.039 --> 00:22:34.019
Which Luna didn't.

00:22:34.140 --> 00:22:37.980
It was still obviously wrong, all wrong

00:22:37.980 --> 00:22:40.680
that hive wings could treat silk wings

00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:43.259
like tiny bugs under their talons.

00:22:43.319 --> 00:22:46.559
Silk wings were dragons too, just like

00:22:46.559 --> 00:22:47.099
them.

00:22:47.160 --> 00:22:49.680
Silk Wings didn't deserve to be stepped

00:22:49.680 --> 00:22:52.740
on, sneered at, poked without permission

00:22:52.740 --> 00:22:55.859
punished for no reason, or ignored.

00:22:55.920 --> 00:22:57.660
It made no sense.

00:22:57.720 --> 00:23:01.559
Why would a different wing shape, or a

00:23:01.559 --> 00:23:03.480
slightly different scale color, or

00:23:03.480 --> 00:23:04.140
antennae.

00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:06.480
Make one dragon superior and another

00:23:06.480 --> 00:23:07.380
dragon worth nothing.

00:23:07.440 --> 00:23:10.440
But how did you fix that?

00:23:10.500 --> 00:23:12.779
How could one dragon?

00:23:12.839 --> 00:23:15.420
Even a dragon who cared very much.

00:23:15.480 --> 00:23:18.059
Make a whole tribe change how they

00:23:18.059 --> 00:23:18.779
thought and behaved.

00:23:18.839 --> 00:23:21.960
How could she get into the heads of all

00:23:21.960 --> 00:23:24.779
those sneering hive wings and shake their

00:23:24.779 --> 00:23:26.880
brains around until they stopped being

00:23:26.880 --> 00:23:27.240
awful?

00:23:27.299 --> 00:23:30.720
She wanted them to see the better world

00:23:30.720 --> 00:23:31.619
she could picture.

00:23:31.680 --> 00:23:34.380
She wanted to stuff it into their

00:23:34.380 --> 00:23:37.559
eyeballs until every hive wing went, yes

00:23:37.559 --> 00:23:39.960
that world is way better than this one.

00:23:40.019 --> 00:23:41.700
Let's be like that instead.

00:23:41.759 --> 00:23:44.940
Luna wished she had magic.

00:23:45.000 --> 00:23:48.599
Magic would be so useful for problems

00:23:48.599 --> 00:23:49.079
like this.

00:23:49.140 --> 00:23:53.400
Even if it was a magic like clear sights

00:23:53.400 --> 00:23:54.480
seeing the future.

00:23:54.539 --> 00:23:57.480
Well, she'd find a way to make it

00:23:57.480 --> 00:23:57.839
useful.

00:23:57.960 --> 00:24:01.380
But proper magic, like spells and

00:24:01.380 --> 00:24:04.680
enchantments, and brain changers, like in

00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:06.180
the old dragon fairy tales.

00:24:06.240 --> 00:24:08.160
That's what she really wanted.

00:24:08.279 --> 00:24:10.980
Something to go, poof.

00:24:11.039 --> 00:24:13.680
Now you are all fair and kind, and

00:24:13.680 --> 00:24:15.660
incapable of cruelty or injustice.

00:24:15.779 --> 00:24:17.940
That's what she needed.

00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:21.119
But apparently, it didn't exist.

00:24:21.180 --> 00:24:25.200
Or if it had existed, once, in the

00:24:25.200 --> 00:24:26.039
distant kingdoms.

00:24:26.039 --> 00:24:28.079
Now it didn't work anymore.

00:24:28.140 --> 00:24:31.500
She traced her claw through the sand with

00:24:31.500 --> 00:24:31.859
a sigh.

00:24:31.980 --> 00:24:36.119
The sun was rising behind her, casting

00:24:36.119 --> 00:24:37.920
golden ripples across the ocean like

00:24:37.920 --> 00:24:39.180
trails of flame silk.

00:24:39.240 --> 00:24:42.960
On the other side of that ocean was

00:24:42.960 --> 00:24:44.579
Pantala, her home.

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:50.220
Her mother's, her tribe, blue, and sword

00:24:50.220 --> 00:24:50.579
tail.

00:24:50.640 --> 00:24:53.819
And they were all in trouble, and it was

00:24:53.819 --> 00:24:56.279
all a mess, and she didn't know how to

00:24:56.279 --> 00:24:57.720
begin untangling it.

00:24:57.779 --> 00:25:00.299
Before her metamorphosis.

00:25:00.359 --> 00:25:02.400
Luna had dreamed of flying.

00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:05.880
She dreamed of scattering the clouds with

00:25:05.880 --> 00:25:08.640
her new pale green wings, and she

00:25:08.640 --> 00:25:10.559
imagined sunshine pouring through her

00:25:10.559 --> 00:25:12.000
scales the higher she flew.

00:25:12.119 --> 00:25:15.720
She planned to weave tapestries with

00:25:15.720 --> 00:25:17.339
secret chrysalis messages in them.

00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:21.240
She imagined herself and swordtail at

00:25:21.240 --> 00:25:24.240
clandestine chrysalis meetings, whispering

00:25:24.240 --> 00:25:25.920
with other silk wings about how to change

00:25:25.920 --> 00:25:26.700
things together.

00:25:26.759 --> 00:25:31.019
But as it turned out, She couldn't simply

00:25:31.019 --> 00:25:31.680
be Luna.

00:25:31.740 --> 00:25:35.039
An ordinary silk wing, quietly changing

00:25:35.039 --> 00:25:37.019
the world alongside other silk wings.

00:25:37.079 --> 00:25:41.640
Now she had to be Luna, the flame silk

00:25:41.640 --> 00:25:45.000
Luna, who spun fire from her wrists.

00:25:45.119 --> 00:25:47.039
A flame silk.

00:25:47.160 --> 00:25:51.180
Rarest of all silk wings, chosen to save

00:25:51.180 --> 00:25:53.039
everyone somehow.

00:25:53.099 --> 00:25:55.740
To Queen Wasp.

00:25:55.799 --> 00:25:58.740
A flame silk was a valuable tool to be

00:25:58.740 --> 00:25:59.880
locked up and controlled.

00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:03.539
To the chrysalis, and the leaf wings.

00:26:03.599 --> 00:26:05.220
Flame silk was power.

00:26:05.339 --> 00:26:08.339
A weapon they could use to fight back.

00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:12.119
Luna didn't particularly like thinking of

00:26:12.119 --> 00:26:14.460
herself as a tool or a weapon.

00:26:14.519 --> 00:26:17.160
She had planned on changing the world in

00:26:17.160 --> 00:26:18.119
a silk wing way.

00:26:18.180 --> 00:26:21.059
Not in a setting your enemies on fire

00:26:21.059 --> 00:26:21.660
way.

00:26:21.660 --> 00:26:25.140
Setting your enemies on fire sounded

00:26:25.140 --> 00:26:25.619
fun.

00:26:25.680 --> 00:26:27.720
But it was actually extremely scary.

00:26:27.839 --> 00:26:30.299
Once you had a real dragon in front of

00:26:30.299 --> 00:26:32.400
you, who would really burn if you wanted

00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:32.880
them to.

00:26:32.940 --> 00:26:35.039
Not to mention?

00:26:35.220 --> 00:26:37.019
The 1st time she tried.

00:26:37.140 --> 00:26:39.539
Her flame silk got caught in a hurricane

00:26:39.539 --> 00:26:41.519
that then blew her to a whole other

00:26:41.519 --> 00:26:41.940
continent.

00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:45.180
So that wasn't the most auspicious start

00:26:45.180 --> 00:26:47.339
for the great and glorious flame silk

00:26:47.339 --> 00:26:48.119
savior, Luna.

00:26:48.180 --> 00:26:51.180
But she had to use this power now that

00:26:51.180 --> 00:26:52.859
she had it, didn't she?

00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:56.339
She'd been chosen by the universe, to be

00:26:56.339 --> 00:26:58.559
a dragon who could throw flaming lassos.

00:26:58.619 --> 00:27:02.160
She couldn't exactly be like, oh, no

00:27:02.160 --> 00:27:02.579
thank you.

00:27:02.640 --> 00:27:05.519
Someone else go set Queen Wasp Bonfire

00:27:05.519 --> 00:27:06.299
instead of me, please.

00:27:06.359 --> 00:27:08.519
This was fine.

00:27:08.579 --> 00:27:11.579
She just had to rethink her plans to

00:27:11.579 --> 00:27:12.240
change the world.

00:27:12.359 --> 00:27:14.640
Now that she was a little bit scarier

00:27:14.640 --> 00:27:17.700
than she used to be, now that she had a

00:27:17.700 --> 00:27:20.279
destiny, and maybe had to save the world

00:27:20.279 --> 00:27:21.900
all by herself with fire.

00:27:22.019 --> 00:27:26.099
I'm not all alone, though, even though I

00:27:26.099 --> 00:27:28.200
feel that way, without blue and sore

00:27:28.200 --> 00:27:28.500
tail.

00:27:28.559 --> 00:27:33.000
Today, she was returning to Pantala with

00:27:33.000 --> 00:27:36.599
9 other dragons, a human, and a mission.

00:27:36.660 --> 00:27:40.440
One of those dragons went galloping past

00:27:40.440 --> 00:27:43.019
charging into the water and plunging his

00:27:43.019 --> 00:27:43.740
head below the surface.

00:27:43.799 --> 00:27:46.920
His human stopped near the edge of the

00:27:46.920 --> 00:27:48.839
waves, crossed her arms inside.

00:27:48.900 --> 00:27:51.059
Did you see one?

00:27:51.119 --> 00:27:53.279
The rain wing called from the air

00:27:53.279 --> 00:27:54.359
swooping overhead.

00:27:54.420 --> 00:27:56.519
No, of course he didn't.

00:27:56.579 --> 00:27:58.140
Ren called back.

00:27:58.200 --> 00:28:01.440
Skye's head shot out of the water again

00:28:01.500 --> 00:28:04.440
and he shook himself vigorously, then

00:28:04.440 --> 00:28:06.839
stood with his snout tilted, as though he

00:28:06.839 --> 00:28:08.460
was waiting for water to drain out of his

00:28:08.460 --> 00:28:08.759
ears.

00:28:08.819 --> 00:28:12.779
False alarm, not a dolphin, he called to

00:28:12.779 --> 00:28:13.440
the rain wing.

00:28:13.500 --> 00:28:15.299
Just to confuse jellyfish.

00:28:15.359 --> 00:28:17.700
Pineapple.

00:28:17.819 --> 00:28:19.440
Luna reminded herself.

00:28:19.500 --> 00:28:21.480
Pineapple the rain wing.

00:28:21.539 --> 00:28:24.779
She was great at remembering faces

00:28:24.839 --> 00:28:27.119
because they were kind of like tapestries

00:28:27.119 --> 00:28:29.819
on dragon snouts, but usually she had

00:28:29.819 --> 00:28:30.539
trouble with names.

00:28:30.599 --> 00:28:34.019
This time, though, she was determined to

00:28:34.019 --> 00:28:36.000
memorize all the names of her traveling

00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:36.660
companions.

00:28:36.720 --> 00:28:40.140
It would help if pineapple could pick one

00:28:40.140 --> 00:28:42.059
color and stay that color.

00:28:42.119 --> 00:28:44.579
Because her trick of picturing him in a

00:28:44.579 --> 00:28:47.160
tapestry holding a pineapple didn't work

00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:49.079
if he kept looking completely different

00:28:49.079 --> 00:28:49.799
all the time.

00:28:49.859 --> 00:28:52.680
Not that I'm complaining.

00:28:52.799 --> 00:28:56.819
Having all these dragons to figure out, is

00:28:56.819 --> 00:28:58.500
much better than sitting on this beach by

00:28:58.500 --> 00:29:01.380
myself, staring wistfully at an ocean

00:29:01.380 --> 00:29:03.420
that's entirely too big.

00:29:03.480 --> 00:29:05.519
Are you still here?

00:29:05.579 --> 00:29:07.740
A voice demanded behind her.

00:29:07.799 --> 00:29:11.460
Luna smiled over her shoulder at Jerboa.

00:29:11.519 --> 00:29:14.220
We are leaving as soon as the ice wing

00:29:14.220 --> 00:29:14.640
arrives.

00:29:14.700 --> 00:29:16.380
She said reassuringly.

00:29:16.440 --> 00:29:19.259
Soon this beach will be so quiet, and

00:29:19.259 --> 00:29:20.400
you'll miss us so much.

00:29:20.460 --> 00:29:23.519
That sounds great.

00:29:23.640 --> 00:29:25.920
Treboa grumbled.

00:29:25.980 --> 00:29:28.380
Clomping up to sit beside Luna and

00:29:28.380 --> 00:29:29.519
scattering sand everywhere.

00:29:29.579 --> 00:29:32.940
I haven't talked to this many dragons in

00:29:32.940 --> 00:29:35.279
literally centuries.

00:29:35.339 --> 00:29:38.099
And now I remember why.

00:29:38.220 --> 00:29:42.900
Truboa always moved in an odd way, which

00:29:42.900 --> 00:29:45.059
at 1st Luna had thought was how all 2

00:29:45.059 --> 00:29:46.319
winged dragons walked.

00:29:46.380 --> 00:29:48.420
But now that she'd met a bunch more.

00:29:48.539 --> 00:29:50.519
She was pretty sure there was something

00:29:50.519 --> 00:29:53.099
different about Jaboa, as though she was

00:29:53.099 --> 00:29:55.740
secretly in pain, or her bones didn't fit

00:29:55.740 --> 00:29:56.519
together quite right.

00:29:56.519 --> 00:30:00.059
I, um, I made you something.

00:30:00.119 --> 00:30:02.160
Luna said tentatively.

00:30:02.220 --> 00:30:04.980
She handed your boa the leaf wrapped

00:30:04.980 --> 00:30:05.640
packet beside her.

00:30:05.700 --> 00:30:09.720
The sand wing furrowed her brow at it, as

00:30:09.720 --> 00:30:11.279
though every present she'd ever been

00:30:11.279 --> 00:30:12.779
given before had bitten her.

00:30:12.839 --> 00:30:14.819
It's just a little thing.

00:30:14.940 --> 00:30:17.819
It's terrible, Luna said in a rush.

00:30:17.940 --> 00:30:19.740
I don't have a loom here.

00:30:19.859 --> 00:30:21.960
So I couldn't weave you the tapestry I

00:30:21.960 --> 00:30:22.980
was imagining in my head.

00:30:23.039 --> 00:30:25.859
And then I thought, maybe I can create a

00:30:25.859 --> 00:30:27.180
new kind of art with my fire.

00:30:27.240 --> 00:30:30.240
So, I've been trying to carve pictures

00:30:30.240 --> 00:30:32.880
into wood with bits of flame silk, and

00:30:32.880 --> 00:30:33.839
it's harder than you'd think.

00:30:33.900 --> 00:30:37.079
So this is the best I was able to do so

00:30:37.079 --> 00:30:37.380
far.

00:30:37.440 --> 00:30:40.619
But it is still pretty awful, and you

00:30:40.619 --> 00:30:42.119
don't have to keep it if you don't want

00:30:42.119 --> 00:30:42.420
to.

00:30:42.480 --> 00:30:44.579
I just wanted to give you something to

00:30:44.579 --> 00:30:45.240
say thank you.

00:30:45.299 --> 00:30:47.819
Thank you for what?

00:30:47.940 --> 00:30:49.380
Treboa asked.

00:30:49.440 --> 00:30:52.259
For helping me get better, and for

00:30:52.259 --> 00:30:53.819
putting up with all of us in your space.

00:30:53.880 --> 00:30:56.039
You didn't have to come find me when I

00:30:56.039 --> 00:30:58.079
crashed here, Luna said.

00:30:58.140 --> 00:31:00.599
I know you could have stayed in your hut

00:31:00.599 --> 00:31:01.980
and kept out of all of this.

00:31:02.039 --> 00:31:05.519
Treboa didn't say very much about herself

00:31:05.519 --> 00:31:06.599
or her past.

00:31:06.660 --> 00:31:09.539
But she had clearly lived alone for a

00:31:09.539 --> 00:31:10.140
long time.

00:31:10.200 --> 00:31:13.440
And Luna got the sense that the sandwing

00:31:13.440 --> 00:31:14.819
both really wanted to connect with

00:31:14.819 --> 00:31:17.819
someone, and also got very overwhelmed

00:31:17.819 --> 00:31:19.859
very quickly by normal dragon

00:31:19.859 --> 00:31:20.519
interactions.

00:31:20.579 --> 00:31:22.259
That was a guess.

00:31:22.319 --> 00:31:25.200
Jerboa was not in the business of

00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:28.200
discussing her feelings, or making facial

00:31:28.200 --> 00:31:28.680
expressions.

00:31:28.680 --> 00:31:32.099
She mostly looked either bored or mildly

00:31:32.099 --> 00:31:32.640
annoyed.

00:31:32.700 --> 00:31:36.000
But Luna was familiar with the no

00:31:36.000 --> 00:31:37.200
feelings here, face.

00:31:37.319 --> 00:31:40.740
Her own was more of a, see, I'm smiling.

00:31:40.799 --> 00:31:42.240
I'm not causing any problems.

00:31:42.299 --> 00:31:43.740
Everything is totally fine.

00:31:43.799 --> 00:31:44.940
Face.

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.460
But it was still in the same genre of

00:31:47.460 --> 00:31:47.759
face.

00:31:47.880 --> 00:31:50.099
It's no problem.

00:31:50.220 --> 00:31:52.619
The Sandwing said brusquely.

00:31:52.680 --> 00:31:54.839
I figured I might as well do something

00:31:54.839 --> 00:31:55.319
useful.

00:31:55.440 --> 00:31:59.160
Treboa gingerly peeled the leaves off the

00:31:59.160 --> 00:31:59.460
gift.

00:31:59.519 --> 00:32:02.039
Revealing the soft white curve of

00:32:02.039 --> 00:32:03.000
driftwood underneath.

00:32:03.059 --> 00:32:06.119
Luna had burned the shape of 2 little

00:32:06.119 --> 00:32:07.019
dragons into it.

00:32:07.079 --> 00:32:10.140
Each sitting on their own continent on

00:32:10.140 --> 00:32:11.339
either side of the ocean.

00:32:11.339 --> 00:32:14.579
One had 4 wings, and the other had two.

00:32:14.640 --> 00:32:17.160
They were looking toward each other and

00:32:17.160 --> 00:32:17.640
waving.

00:32:17.700 --> 00:32:19.920
Well, they were supposed to be.

00:32:19.980 --> 00:32:22.859
The one with 4 wings looked like she was

00:32:22.859 --> 00:32:25.019
about to fall over backward, and the

00:32:25.019 --> 00:32:26.940
other one's face had come out all wrong

00:32:26.940 --> 00:32:28.799
so she looked like she was sneezing.

00:32:28.859 --> 00:32:33.119
Never mind, Luna said, trying to grab it

00:32:33.119 --> 00:32:34.619
out of Jerboa's talons.

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:37.799
It's an awful, weird looking art fail.

00:32:37.859 --> 00:32:38.460
Sorry.

00:32:38.519 --> 00:32:42.599
Stop that, Treboa said. batting her

00:32:42.599 --> 00:32:42.779
away.

00:32:42.839 --> 00:32:46.740
This is my weird looking art fail.

00:32:46.799 --> 00:32:47.880
Get your claws off it.

00:32:48.000 --> 00:32:51.660
When the world is all fixed, I'll make

00:32:51.660 --> 00:32:55.079
you a tapestry, Luna said, It'll be much

00:32:55.079 --> 00:32:56.640
better than this, I promise.

00:32:56.700 --> 00:33:00.359
Turboa squinted at the dark clouds that

00:33:00.359 --> 00:33:02.400
were huddled like suspicious high wing

00:33:02.400 --> 00:33:03.599
guards on the far horizon.

00:33:03.660 --> 00:33:08.039
When the world is all fixed, she echoed.

00:33:08.099 --> 00:33:09.420
Hmm.

00:33:09.539 --> 00:33:11.339
Don't get your hopes up.

00:33:11.400 --> 00:33:14.220
Every time you think you've fixed

00:33:14.220 --> 00:33:16.859
something, something else always goes

00:33:16.859 --> 00:33:17.039
wrong.

00:33:17.099 --> 00:33:19.200
That's the spirit.

00:33:19.319 --> 00:33:22.500
Kembley. the other Sandwing said, popping

00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:22.980
up behind her.

00:33:23.039 --> 00:33:25.140
Hey, I have an idea.

00:33:25.200 --> 00:33:27.720
Let's stop fixing things, and then maybe

00:33:27.720 --> 00:33:28.980
nothing else will go wrong.

00:33:29.099 --> 00:33:31.500
Treboa frowned at him.

00:33:31.559 --> 00:33:34.859
Uh-oh, Kibley said to Luna.

00:33:34.920 --> 00:33:37.019
I think I'm about to be called a

00:33:37.019 --> 00:33:38.460
preposterous whippersnapper.

00:33:38.519 --> 00:33:41.759
Tell your continent they can keep this

00:33:41.759 --> 00:33:42.059
one?

00:33:42.180 --> 00:33:44.759
Turboa said, flicking her tail at

00:33:44.759 --> 00:33:45.299
Kibley.

00:33:45.359 --> 00:33:48.720
Kibli grinnedadder, then turned to Luna

00:33:48.720 --> 00:33:49.019
again.

00:33:49.079 --> 00:33:51.539
Tsunami wants to show you something

00:33:51.539 --> 00:33:53.160
important, if you have a minute.

00:33:53.279 --> 00:33:56.160
He pointed out the beach to where the

00:33:56.160 --> 00:33:57.660
blue sea wing was sitting with cricket.

00:33:57.720 --> 00:34:02.039
Oh, sure, thanks, Luna said.

00:34:02.099 --> 00:34:05.339
Her scales always gave an odd little

00:34:05.339 --> 00:34:07.079
shiver when she saw cricket from a

00:34:07.079 --> 00:34:07.319
distance.

00:34:07.380 --> 00:34:10.920
Even though her brain knew this hive wing

00:34:10.920 --> 00:34:12.659
was safe, and had helped them.

00:34:12.719 --> 00:34:15.119
Her body still sent her an instinctive

00:34:15.119 --> 00:34:18.359
heap, run, hide, set it on fire.

00:34:18.480 --> 00:34:21.300
Reaction to the yellow and black dragon's

00:34:21.300 --> 00:34:21.539
face.

00:34:21.599 --> 00:34:24.360
There was a difference between knowing

00:34:24.360 --> 00:34:26.940
she should trust this dragon and feeling

00:34:26.940 --> 00:34:27.659
like she could.

00:34:27.719 --> 00:34:30.599
She knew Blue trusted her.

00:34:30.659 --> 00:34:33.059
But she'd only seen Cricket and Blue

00:34:33.059 --> 00:34:35.399
together for a moment before Luna was

00:34:35.399 --> 00:34:35.999
blown out to sea.

00:34:36.059 --> 00:34:39.719
And to be honest, Blue wasn't the most

00:34:39.719 --> 00:34:41.699
reliable truster of dragons.

00:34:41.760 --> 00:34:44.699
He would probably trust a giant hissing

00:34:44.699 --> 00:34:47.159
scorpion wielding knives, if it said

00:34:47.159 --> 00:34:48.059
something sympathetic.

00:34:48.119 --> 00:34:52.559
Also, there was a small part of Luna, that

00:34:52.559 --> 00:34:56.159
was really angry, that blue and sore tail

00:34:56.159 --> 00:34:58.260
had fallen into wasps' mind control

00:34:58.260 --> 00:35:00.719
clutches, but cricket hadn't.

00:35:00.780 --> 00:35:02.219
After all that.

00:35:02.340 --> 00:35:05.219
Why should this blissfully lucky hive

00:35:05.219 --> 00:35:06.659
wing get to escape yet again?

00:35:06.780 --> 00:35:09.480
But the dragons Luna loved didn't.

00:35:09.539 --> 00:35:11.099
It wasn't fair.

00:35:11.159 --> 00:35:13.619
She couldn't say that out loud.

00:35:13.679 --> 00:35:15.599
But it really wasn't.

00:35:15.659 --> 00:35:18.659
Luna, Tsunami said.

00:35:18.719 --> 00:35:20.940
Beckoning her closer, she approached.

00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:23.699
I'm going to share another Pyrean secret

00:35:23.699 --> 00:35:25.679
with you, because I think it will help

00:35:25.679 --> 00:35:28.320
and I think it's important, and you know

00:35:28.320 --> 00:35:28.619
what?

00:35:28.679 --> 00:35:29.519
It's my thing.

00:35:29.579 --> 00:35:32.159
Well, the Jade Mountain Academy's thing

00:35:32.159 --> 00:35:35.099
and I'm the headmaster, basically.

00:35:35.159 --> 00:35:36.360
And so I don't need any queen's

00:35:36.360 --> 00:35:37.679
permission is what I've decided.

00:35:37.739 --> 00:35:38.460
So there.

00:35:38.519 --> 00:35:41.219
Um, Luna said.

00:35:41.280 --> 00:35:42.300
Okay.

00:35:42.420 --> 00:35:46.320
Tsunami held out a star shaped sapphire

00:35:46.380 --> 00:35:48.420
that fit neatly in her cupped front

00:35:48.420 --> 00:35:49.019
talons.

00:35:49.079 --> 00:35:53.099
This is a dream visitor, she said.

00:35:53.159 --> 00:35:55.980
One of those animus touched magic objects

00:35:55.980 --> 00:35:56.519
you heard about?

00:35:56.579 --> 00:35:59.340
Luna's heart sped up.

00:35:59.400 --> 00:36:00.719
Magic.

00:36:00.780 --> 00:36:02.699
What does it do?

00:36:02.760 --> 00:36:03.900
She blurted.

00:36:03.960 --> 00:36:06.239
Please say it'll save my tribe.

00:36:06.300 --> 00:36:09.420
She glanced sideways at cricket.

00:36:09.480 --> 00:36:11.280
Who was unusually silent.

00:36:11.340 --> 00:36:14.219
Normally, the hive wing would have been

00:36:14.219 --> 00:36:15.659
the 1st one asking questions.

00:36:15.719 --> 00:36:18.659
But she was staring down at her claws

00:36:18.659 --> 00:36:20.039
half buried in the sand.

00:36:20.099 --> 00:36:22.800
She looked as though someone had said all

00:36:22.800 --> 00:36:24.000
her favorite books on fire.

00:36:24.059 --> 00:36:26.940
I've already let cricket use it.

00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:28.739
Tsunami explained.

00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:30.179
Why?

00:36:30.239 --> 00:36:32.099
Luna thought mutinously.

00:36:32.159 --> 00:36:34.260
Why her 1st and not me?

00:36:34.320 --> 00:36:35.579
How is that fair?

00:36:35.639 --> 00:36:37.500
When she's one of the bad guys.

00:36:37.619 --> 00:36:41.579
No, no, don't let anyone see you think

00:36:41.579 --> 00:36:41.760
that.

00:36:41.880 --> 00:36:43.139
I'm smiling.

00:36:43.199 --> 00:36:44.639
I'm not causing problems.

00:36:44.699 --> 00:36:45.480
Everything is fine.

00:36:45.539 --> 00:36:48.119
Tsunami went on.

00:36:48.179 --> 00:36:51.179
A dream visitor lets you step into the

00:36:51.179 --> 00:36:53.579
dreams of a sleeping dragon, no matter

00:36:53.579 --> 00:36:55.739
where they are, so long as it's someone

00:36:55.739 --> 00:36:56.280
you've seen before.

00:36:56.340 --> 00:36:59.400
I figured it's probably still nighttime

00:36:59.400 --> 00:37:00.239
in Pentala.

00:37:00.300 --> 00:37:02.519
And maybe there's someone there you want

00:37:02.519 --> 00:37:03.059
to check on?

00:37:03.119 --> 00:37:06.599
She carefully placed the Sapphire and

00:37:06.599 --> 00:37:07.500
Luna's talons.

00:37:07.559 --> 00:37:09.480
Luna's mind was spinning.

00:37:09.539 --> 00:37:11.940
She could actually see one of them

00:37:11.940 --> 00:37:12.179
again.

00:37:12.239 --> 00:37:13.619
Right now?

00:37:13.800 --> 00:37:17.820
It wasn't tribe saving magic, but it was

00:37:17.820 --> 00:37:18.780
still amazing.

00:37:18.840 --> 00:37:20.460
Who should she pick?

00:37:20.519 --> 00:37:22.679
Soretail or blue?

00:37:22.739 --> 00:37:24.659
Blue or sore tail?

00:37:24.719 --> 00:37:26.579
And then she realized.

00:37:26.699 --> 00:37:28.619
Did you visit Blue?

00:37:28.679 --> 00:37:30.480
She asked Cricket.

00:37:30.539 --> 00:37:32.639
The hive wing nodded.

00:37:32.699 --> 00:37:35.760
I tried, she said quietly.

00:37:35.820 --> 00:37:37.980
He couldn't really hear me, though.

00:37:38.039 --> 00:37:39.480
He was having a nightmare.

00:37:39.539 --> 00:37:40.980
About what?

00:37:41.039 --> 00:37:43.079
Luna asked sharply.

00:37:43.139 --> 00:37:45.719
That was her little brother.

00:37:45.780 --> 00:37:47.820
She should be the one worrying about his

00:37:47.820 --> 00:37:48.480
nightmares.

00:37:48.539 --> 00:37:52.139
A room full of silk wings, Cricket said.

00:37:52.199 --> 00:37:54.599
Plants growing out of the walls

00:37:54.599 --> 00:37:55.500
strangling them.

00:37:55.619 --> 00:37:57.239
It can't be real.

00:37:57.360 --> 00:37:58.500
Can it?

00:37:58.559 --> 00:38:00.719
She appealed to tsunami.

00:38:00.780 --> 00:38:03.300
I mean, was I seeing something he

00:38:03.300 --> 00:38:03.960
actually saw?

00:38:04.019 --> 00:38:06.960
Tsunami spread her wings.

00:38:07.079 --> 00:38:09.239
I don't know.

00:38:09.300 --> 00:38:12.300
We have dreams about real things and not

00:38:12.300 --> 00:38:14.579
real things and both mixed together all

00:38:14.579 --> 00:38:14.940
the time.

00:38:15.000 --> 00:38:19.260
Cricket sighed, took off her glasses and

00:38:19.260 --> 00:38:20.219
rubbed her eyes.

00:38:20.280 --> 00:38:23.400
I'll visit Sortail, Luna said.

00:38:23.460 --> 00:38:24.780
What do I have to do?

00:38:24.840 --> 00:38:28.199
Hold it up to your forehead. tsunami

00:38:28.199 --> 00:38:28.500
said.

00:38:28.559 --> 00:38:30.900
Close your eyes and concentrate on him.

00:38:31.019 --> 00:38:33.840
If it doesn't work, he might not be

00:38:33.840 --> 00:38:34.440
asleep right now.

00:38:34.500 --> 00:38:38.159
Or if he's having a nightmare, like blue

00:38:38.159 --> 00:38:40.440
you might see him, but he might not hear

00:38:40.440 --> 00:38:40.679
you.

00:38:40.739 --> 00:38:44.159
But if he's having a normal dream, you

00:38:44.159 --> 00:38:45.420
might be able to communicate with him.

00:38:45.480 --> 00:38:49.380
Luna's claws were trembling as she

00:38:49.380 --> 00:38:50.820
pressed the dream visitor to her

00:38:50.820 --> 00:38:51.179
forehead.

00:38:51.239 --> 00:38:54.420
It wasn't magic that could make all hive

00:38:54.420 --> 00:38:56.519
wings disappear, which would have been

00:38:56.519 --> 00:38:56.760
nice.

00:38:56.820 --> 00:39:00.360
But the chance to talk to Soortail, after

00:39:00.360 --> 00:39:03.239
all this time, was a magic she hadn't

00:39:03.239 --> 00:39:03.840
dared hope for.

00:39:03.900 --> 00:39:06.659
They'd never gone this long without

00:39:06.659 --> 00:39:07.380
talking to each other.

00:39:07.440 --> 00:39:10.380
Not since the day they 1st met 5 years

00:39:10.380 --> 00:39:10.619
ago.

00:39:10.679 --> 00:39:13.199
Swordtail.

00:39:13.320 --> 00:39:15.900
She whispered, closing her eyes.

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:19.019
She pictured his unexpectedly sweet

00:39:19.019 --> 00:39:19.440
face.

00:39:19.500 --> 00:39:23.639
Other dragons saw his mischief, his loud

00:39:23.639 --> 00:39:26.219
jokes, and his reckless arguments with

00:39:26.219 --> 00:39:27.059
guards or teachers.

00:39:27.119 --> 00:39:29.940
They might notice that he was strong and

00:39:29.940 --> 00:39:30.480
brave too.

00:39:30.599 --> 00:39:33.539
But hardly anyone seemed to see the true

00:39:33.539 --> 00:39:35.760
sore tail, under all his noisy

00:39:35.760 --> 00:39:36.239
silliness.

00:39:36.360 --> 00:39:38.820
It was like the red leaf.

00:39:38.880 --> 00:39:41.699
The secret chrysalis symbol hidden in the

00:39:41.699 --> 00:39:43.019
metamorphosis tapestries.

00:39:43.079 --> 00:39:44.760
You had to look for it.

00:39:44.820 --> 00:39:46.619
You had to know to care about it.

00:39:46.739 --> 00:39:50.400
Sortell understood about all the things

00:39:50.400 --> 00:39:52.380
Luna saw that were wrong.

00:39:52.440 --> 00:39:54.780
Even if he hadn't noticed them before.

00:39:54.840 --> 00:39:57.000
He understood immediately when she

00:39:57.000 --> 00:39:57.599
pointed them out.

00:39:57.659 --> 00:40:01.019
He was the absolute best at going from

00:40:01.019 --> 00:40:02.940
vaguely interested, to completely

00:40:02.940 --> 00:40:05.280
outraged in the span of a conversation.

00:40:05.340 --> 00:40:09.599
Sortell looked back into her eyes, and

00:40:09.599 --> 00:40:10.980
his whole face lit up.

00:40:11.039 --> 00:40:13.079
Three moons.

00:40:13.139 --> 00:40:16.500
She was really somewhere.

00:40:16.559 --> 00:40:19.800
Somewhere that wasn't a sunrise lit beach

00:40:19.800 --> 00:40:20.820
in the distant kingdoms.

00:40:20.940 --> 00:40:24.480
Somewhere dark, although a single bright

00:40:24.480 --> 00:40:26.400
light shone over Soretail's head.

00:40:26.400 --> 00:40:29.579
He was standing up on a pedestal, his

00:40:29.579 --> 00:40:32.159
wings spread behind him, his front talons

00:40:32.159 --> 00:40:32.760
outstretched.

00:40:32.820 --> 00:40:35.579
Sore tail, she cried.

00:40:35.639 --> 00:40:37.679
He didn't respond.

00:40:37.739 --> 00:40:40.739
His claws twitched like he wanted to

00:40:40.739 --> 00:40:42.539
reach for her, but he didn't move.

00:40:42.599 --> 00:40:46.260
Oh, she knew where they were now.

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:48.659
This was misbehavior's way.

00:40:48.719 --> 00:40:51.539
The place troublemakers like Swordtail

00:40:51.539 --> 00:40:53.460
were sent to be punished whenever they

00:40:53.460 --> 00:40:54.719
disobeyed hive wings.

00:40:54.780 --> 00:40:58.079
She walked up to the base of the pedestal

00:40:58.079 --> 00:41:00.059
and touched the letters carved in the

00:41:00.059 --> 00:41:00.300
stone.

00:41:00.360 --> 00:41:03.539
They looked like real words until she

00:41:03.539 --> 00:41:05.639
tried to read them, and then they went

00:41:05.639 --> 00:41:07.440
wobbly and slipped away from her brain.

00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:09.960
Like in a dream.

00:41:10.019 --> 00:41:13.320
Soretail, she said.

00:41:13.380 --> 00:41:14.639
This isn't real.

00:41:14.760 --> 00:41:17.039
You're not on misbehavior's way.

00:41:17.099 --> 00:41:18.840
This isn't even what it really looks

00:41:18.840 --> 00:41:19.139
like.

00:41:19.199 --> 00:41:21.840
She turned to look behind her.

00:41:21.900 --> 00:41:24.360
There were no other pedestals.

00:41:24.420 --> 00:41:25.380
No other prisoners.

00:41:25.440 --> 00:41:28.679
The stone paths rolled away into darkness

00:41:28.679 --> 00:41:31.800
and the darkness hummed, like it was full

00:41:31.800 --> 00:41:32.400
of bees.

00:41:32.460 --> 00:41:35.760
The light over Swordtail's head was wrong

00:41:35.760 --> 00:41:36.179
too.

00:41:36.239 --> 00:41:39.179
It was too bright, and she couldn't see a

00:41:39.179 --> 00:41:41.639
fixture or a ceiling, just the light

00:41:41.639 --> 00:41:42.780
blazing down on him.

00:41:42.840 --> 00:41:46.559
Sortail, get down from there right now

00:41:46.559 --> 00:41:47.579
she said.

00:41:47.639 --> 00:41:49.079
I don't know why you're dreaming about

00:41:49.079 --> 00:41:49.260
this.

00:41:49.320 --> 00:41:53.400
This is where I'm supposed to be, he said

00:41:53.400 --> 00:41:55.559
suddenly, sounding resigned and

00:41:55.559 --> 00:41:57.719
reasonable, which was not a very sore

00:41:57.719 --> 00:41:59.099
tail way to sound.

00:41:59.159 --> 00:42:00.659
I'm always here.

00:42:00.719 --> 00:42:01.559
Remember?

00:42:01.619 --> 00:42:03.179
You come and say with me?

00:42:03.239 --> 00:42:05.460
You should weave a hammock and live here

00:42:05.460 --> 00:42:07.380
because I'll probably be here more and

00:42:07.380 --> 00:42:08.219
more as we get older.

00:42:08.340 --> 00:42:11.460
Luna felt like she was about to cry.

00:42:11.519 --> 00:42:14.519
The 3 times he'd been punished like this

00:42:14.519 --> 00:42:14.760
before.

00:42:14.820 --> 00:42:17.159
She'd found a way to go sit with him for

00:42:17.159 --> 00:42:18.000
as long as she could.

00:42:18.059 --> 00:42:20.099
On misbehavior's way.

00:42:20.159 --> 00:42:22.619
The prisoners were temporarily paralyzed

00:42:22.619 --> 00:42:25.320
with a hive wing nerve toxin, so they

00:42:25.320 --> 00:42:26.159
couldn't move or speak.

00:42:26.219 --> 00:42:28.260
But they could still hear and see.

00:42:28.380 --> 00:42:32.159
So she'd read to him or sing, or tell him

00:42:32.159 --> 00:42:33.480
about the day he'd missed.

00:42:33.480 --> 00:42:35.940
You're not going to end up here again

00:42:35.940 --> 00:42:37.019
Luna said.

00:42:37.079 --> 00:42:39.119
I'm coming to set you free, swordtail.

00:42:39.239 --> 00:42:40.980
No, no.

00:42:41.039 --> 00:42:41.880
He said.

00:42:41.940 --> 00:42:43.559
I'm coming to rescue you.

00:42:43.619 --> 00:42:44.639
I'm helpful.

00:42:44.699 --> 00:42:45.900
That's what.

00:42:46.199 --> 00:42:47.340
Wait.

00:42:47.460 --> 00:42:49.320
Didn't I already?

00:42:49.500 --> 00:42:52.199
He trailed off, looking confused.

00:42:52.260 --> 00:42:54.780
You did, she said.

00:42:54.840 --> 00:42:58.800
Thortell, this is a dream, but I'm real.

00:42:58.860 --> 00:43:01.079
You can get off that pedestal.

00:43:01.139 --> 00:43:03.239
Get off it right now and come hug me.

00:43:03.300 --> 00:43:05.699
He thought for a moment.

00:43:05.760 --> 00:43:08.760
I like that idea much better than

00:43:08.760 --> 00:43:09.300
standing here.

00:43:09.360 --> 00:43:11.579
He broke his brow.

00:43:11.639 --> 00:43:12.780
Concentrating.

00:43:12.840 --> 00:43:15.659
Moving is tricky though.

00:43:15.719 --> 00:43:17.460
Not sure if everyone knows that.

00:43:17.519 --> 00:43:20.280
Hey, who's the boss of me?

00:43:20.340 --> 00:43:22.079
Are these my muscles or what?

00:43:22.139 --> 00:43:24.059
Don't I tell them what to do?

00:43:24.119 --> 00:43:27.420
Look at them, arguing back, not listening

00:43:27.420 --> 00:43:27.780
to me.

00:43:27.840 --> 00:43:31.260
Hey, do what I say, stupid talents.

00:43:31.320 --> 00:43:34.079
He glared at his claws, but they stayed

00:43:34.079 --> 00:43:35.159
frozen in place.

00:43:35.219 --> 00:43:37.139
All right, hang on.

00:43:37.199 --> 00:43:38.940
I'll fix this.

00:43:39.000 --> 00:43:40.559
I am the boss of me.

00:43:40.619 --> 00:43:43.320
Nobody else tells my talents what to do.

00:43:43.380 --> 00:43:45.659
Let's all not look at me for a minute

00:43:45.659 --> 00:43:47.219
while I yell at myself.

00:43:47.280 --> 00:43:49.320
Luna, talk about you instead.

00:43:49.440 --> 00:43:51.480
What do you mean, you're real?

00:43:51.599 --> 00:43:55.739
I'm in the distant kingdoms, using magic

00:43:55.739 --> 00:43:56.400
to talk to you.

00:43:56.460 --> 00:43:59.579
Luna spread her wings and flew up to

00:43:59.579 --> 00:43:59.820
him.

00:43:59.880 --> 00:44:02.820
This pedestal was also higher than the

00:44:02.820 --> 00:44:05.579
real ones on misbehavior's way, but it

00:44:05.579 --> 00:44:07.619
was only a dream, so she did not feel

00:44:07.619 --> 00:44:08.880
guilty about shoving him off.

00:44:08.940 --> 00:44:13.079
You're, he yelped, flapping around to

00:44:13.079 --> 00:44:13.739
break his fall.

00:44:13.800 --> 00:44:16.320
Hey, my wings can move.

00:44:16.380 --> 00:44:17.639
Check me out.

00:44:17.699 --> 00:44:20.219
Guess those ants for brains guards didn't

00:44:20.219 --> 00:44:21.599
stab me the right way this time.

00:44:21.719 --> 00:44:23.639
Swordtail.

00:44:23.699 --> 00:44:26.940
Luna took one of his talons and tugged

00:44:26.940 --> 00:44:27.539
him down to the ground.

00:44:27.659 --> 00:44:30.719
He settled his wings behind him, and

00:44:30.719 --> 00:44:32.880
looked down at their intertwined claws.

00:44:32.940 --> 00:44:36.119
A thread of silvery gray silk spun out of

00:44:36.119 --> 00:44:37.800
his wrist and wrapped around hers.

00:44:37.860 --> 00:44:40.500
Now she was crying.

00:44:40.559 --> 00:44:43.139
She wondered if she was crying in the

00:44:43.139 --> 00:44:45.360
real world too. sitting on that beach

00:44:45.360 --> 00:44:46.260
with tsunami.

00:44:46.320 --> 00:44:49.800
She let a thread of harmless flame silk

00:44:49.800 --> 00:44:52.320
the kind that shimmered gold, but didn't

00:44:52.320 --> 00:44:55.739
burn, spin out and wrap around his talons

00:44:55.739 --> 00:44:56.880
twining through his own silk.

00:44:56.940 --> 00:44:59.760
Listen, she said.

00:44:59.820 --> 00:45:02.820
I'm in the distant kingdoms, but I'm

00:45:02.820 --> 00:45:03.420
coming for you.

00:45:03.480 --> 00:45:06.420
I'm coming with sundew and cricket, and

00:45:06.420 --> 00:45:08.159
some other dragons, and we're going to

00:45:08.159 --> 00:45:08.760
save you, okay?

00:45:08.820 --> 00:45:10.380
Do you know where you are?

00:45:10.500 --> 00:45:12.840
I mean, really in real life?

00:45:12.900 --> 00:45:13.860
Not in this dream?

00:45:13.920 --> 00:45:18.420
Cicada hive, he said, blinking.

00:45:18.480 --> 00:45:21.420
Guarding silk wings until wasp has enough

00:45:21.420 --> 00:45:22.860
of her plant to infect them.

00:45:22.920 --> 00:45:24.960
He tried to laugh.

00:45:25.019 --> 00:45:27.420
Very boring job, actually.

00:45:27.480 --> 00:45:29.880
It's a bit like guarding a flower shop to

00:45:29.880 --> 00:45:31.320
make sure the orchids don't make a run

00:45:31.320 --> 00:45:31.619
for it.

00:45:31.679 --> 00:45:34.679
I can see why the hive wing guards were

00:45:34.679 --> 00:45:36.119
always so excited when I gave them

00:45:36.119 --> 00:45:36.840
something to chase.

00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:40.559
WASP sent you back to our own hive.

00:45:40.619 --> 00:45:41.880
Luna asked.

00:45:41.940 --> 00:45:44.519
So the silk wings you're guarding.

00:45:44.639 --> 00:45:45.960
Yeah.

00:45:46.019 --> 00:45:50.039
Everyone we know, he said with an awkward

00:45:50.039 --> 00:45:50.400
shrug.

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:52.380
Your moms are here.

00:45:52.440 --> 00:45:53.400
They're all right.

00:45:53.460 --> 00:45:55.260
What about Blue?

00:45:55.380 --> 00:45:56.159
She asked.

00:45:56.219 --> 00:46:01.079
Here too, he said, in a quieter voice.

00:46:01.199 --> 00:46:03.719
But not really, you know?

00:46:03.780 --> 00:46:06.539
It's like he's gone into a blue cocoon

00:46:06.539 --> 00:46:07.619
somewhere inside himself.

00:46:07.679 --> 00:46:10.320
I kind of wish I could do that too.

00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:14.340
I mean, I want to fight something, but I

00:46:14.340 --> 00:46:14.760
can't.

00:46:14.820 --> 00:46:17.039
I can't do anything with these stupid

00:46:17.039 --> 00:46:18.360
traitor talons.

00:46:18.480 --> 00:46:21.719
He looked down at their intertwined claws

00:46:21.719 --> 00:46:22.920
and took a deep breath.

00:46:23.039 --> 00:46:28.199
She, we, captured Io.

00:46:28.260 --> 00:46:29.699
So she's here too.

00:46:29.760 --> 00:46:32.159
She can't even look at me.

00:46:32.219 --> 00:46:34.079
It's not you.

00:46:34.139 --> 00:46:36.059
Luna said fiercely.

00:46:36.119 --> 00:46:39.239
Whatever Queen Wasp is making you do, it's

00:46:39.239 --> 00:46:40.440
not you, sore tail.

00:46:40.500 --> 00:46:41.519
Don't forget that.

00:46:41.579 --> 00:46:44.219
You're still in there, and we're going to

00:46:44.219 --> 00:46:45.000
get you away from her.

00:46:45.059 --> 00:46:46.320
I promise.

00:46:46.380 --> 00:46:50.159
I wish I were really talking to you, he

00:46:50.159 --> 00:46:50.400
said.

00:46:50.460 --> 00:46:53.519
These dreams always end with you being

00:46:53.519 --> 00:46:54.960
dragged away in chains made of

00:46:54.960 --> 00:46:55.260
lightning.

00:46:55.320 --> 00:46:59.219
You are really talking to me, you lummox

00:46:59.219 --> 00:47:01.559
Luna said, shaking his talons.

00:47:01.679 --> 00:47:04.139
She wrapped her wings around him and

00:47:04.139 --> 00:47:04.920
pulled him closer.

00:47:04.980 --> 00:47:08.400
With a sigh, he rested his head on her

00:47:08.400 --> 00:47:08.699
shoulder.

00:47:08.820 --> 00:47:11.039
Soretail.

00:47:11.099 --> 00:47:13.679
There's a dragon on this continent who's

00:47:13.679 --> 00:47:14.519
like clear sight.

00:47:14.639 --> 00:47:17.820
She told us this prophecy about Pentala

00:47:17.820 --> 00:47:19.019
and a buried secret.

00:47:19.139 --> 00:47:22.260
So we're coming to look for an abyss that

00:47:22.260 --> 00:47:23.579
we think is connected to the mind

00:47:23.579 --> 00:47:24.059
control.

00:47:24.119 --> 00:47:27.539
We're going to fly into the abyss, find a

00:47:27.539 --> 00:47:30.179
big obnoxious plant with a grudge, and

00:47:30.179 --> 00:47:32.340
then Sundu's going to kill it a lot until

00:47:32.340 --> 00:47:33.840
it's really, really dead.

00:47:33.960 --> 00:47:36.179
And then the mind control won't work

00:47:36.179 --> 00:47:37.619
anymore, and you'll be free.

00:47:37.679 --> 00:47:38.940
All right?

00:47:39.000 --> 00:47:40.920
Isn't that a great plan?

00:47:40.980 --> 00:47:42.780
Aye.

00:47:43.079 --> 00:47:46.320
Feel like I missed something, Swordtail

00:47:46.320 --> 00:47:46.559
said.

00:47:46.619 --> 00:47:48.539
Me too.

00:47:48.599 --> 00:47:50.760
It's very confusing, Luna agreed.

00:47:50.820 --> 00:47:52.380
But it's going to work.

00:47:52.440 --> 00:47:54.239
We're leaving the distant kingdoms

00:47:54.239 --> 00:47:54.599
today.

00:47:54.659 --> 00:47:56.460
So pay attention.

00:47:56.519 --> 00:48:00.059
And in a few days, you'll be like, oh wow

00:48:00.059 --> 00:48:00.659
they did it.

00:48:00.719 --> 00:48:03.000
The mind control doesn't work anymore.

00:48:03.059 --> 00:48:06.659
Let's go stab Queen Wasp in the face, and

00:48:06.659 --> 00:48:08.760
then find Luna, and hug her forever.

00:48:08.820 --> 00:48:11.159
He laughed.

00:48:11.219 --> 00:48:13.619
Shaking his head to clear the tears from

00:48:13.619 --> 00:48:13.920
his eyes.

00:48:13.980 --> 00:48:16.920
You do sound like real Luna.

00:48:16.980 --> 00:48:19.440
Where will I find you after you save us?

00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:23.340
The mosaic garden, Luna said. off the top

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:23.699
of her head.

00:48:23.760 --> 00:48:26.940
That hill, where you finally confessed

00:48:26.940 --> 00:48:28.800
your desperate love for me and said you

00:48:28.800 --> 00:48:29.460
couldn't live without me?

00:48:29.579 --> 00:48:34.440
Um, I believe my exact words were, hey

00:48:34.440 --> 00:48:36.119
Luna, want to be my girlfriend?

00:48:36.179 --> 00:48:37.920
He said with a grin.

00:48:37.920 --> 00:48:40.860
Yes, you're very lucky I can translate

00:48:40.860 --> 00:48:42.780
sword tail. she retorted.

00:48:42.840 --> 00:48:44.820
And let's see.

00:48:44.880 --> 00:48:48.000
I believe your romantic response was

00:48:48.000 --> 00:48:50.340
Soretail, did you sit on this box of

00:48:50.340 --> 00:48:51.000
honey drops?

00:48:51.059 --> 00:48:52.980
Why are they all squashed?

00:48:53.099 --> 00:48:56.460
And then I was like, Luna, pay attention

00:48:56.460 --> 00:48:57.659
to me.

00:48:57.719 --> 00:48:59.219
I am trying to make us an official

00:48:59.219 --> 00:48:59.579
couple.

00:48:59.639 --> 00:49:02.880
And you were like, yes, all right.

00:49:02.940 --> 00:49:04.079
Obviously, that's fine.

00:49:04.139 --> 00:49:06.420
Now go get us some more honey drops and

00:49:06.420 --> 00:49:07.800
don't sit on them this time.

00:49:07.860 --> 00:49:11.159
You do have a weird habit of squashing

00:49:11.159 --> 00:49:13.500
any candy you get your talons on, she

00:49:13.500 --> 00:49:15.719
pointed out, or your butt on, more

00:49:15.719 --> 00:49:16.199
accurately.

00:49:16.260 --> 00:49:19.980
I don't sit on candy on purpose, he

00:49:19.980 --> 00:49:20.519
objected.

00:49:20.579 --> 00:49:23.219
I certainly hope not, she said.

00:49:23.280 --> 00:49:25.019
That would be weird, sore tail.

00:49:25.079 --> 00:49:27.360
She nudged his snout with hers.

00:49:27.480 --> 00:49:29.039
But it's all right.

00:49:29.159 --> 00:49:30.179
I love you anyway.

00:49:30.239 --> 00:49:32.460
I love you too.

00:49:32.519 --> 00:49:34.679
He squeezed her talons.

00:49:34.739 --> 00:49:37.079
I think I'm about to wake up.

00:49:37.139 --> 00:49:40.920
Oh no, she said, starting to panic.

00:49:40.980 --> 00:49:42.000
Already?

00:49:42.059 --> 00:49:42.599
Wait.

00:49:42.659 --> 00:49:45.179
I don't have a choice, he said.

00:49:45.239 --> 00:49:46.860
She wants us for something.

00:49:46.920 --> 00:49:49.860
Luna, I'm all right, but...

00:49:49.860 --> 00:49:52.800
If you could come quickly, it would... it

00:49:52.800 --> 00:49:53.280
would be better.

00:49:53.400 --> 00:49:55.139
I will.

00:49:55.199 --> 00:49:55.860
I promise.

00:49:55.980 --> 00:49:59.159
Tell Blue we'll be there soon, she said.

00:49:59.219 --> 00:50:01.619
More silk was spinning out of her

00:50:01.619 --> 00:50:04.380
wrapping around his wrists, trying to

00:50:04.380 --> 00:50:04.920
keep him with her.

00:50:04.980 --> 00:50:07.500
Just hold on, sore tail.

00:50:07.619 --> 00:50:08.340
We're coming.

00:50:08.400 --> 00:50:09.059
We'll.

00:50:09.659 --> 00:50:10.980
But he was gone.

00:50:11.039 --> 00:50:13.619
Luna was back on the beach.

00:50:13.739 --> 00:50:16.619
Early morning light brushing the clouds

00:50:16.619 --> 00:50:17.340
pink overhead.

00:50:17.400 --> 00:50:21.480
Tears were rolling down her snout, and

00:50:21.480 --> 00:50:24.480
her talons held a cold sapphire, instead

00:50:24.480 --> 00:50:26.159
of sore tail's warm claws.

00:50:26.219 --> 00:50:30.239
Chapter 2.

00:50:30.480 --> 00:50:33.960
Part of Luna wanted to dive to the bottom

00:50:33.960 --> 00:50:36.360
of the ocean, and bury herself so deep

00:50:36.360 --> 00:50:38.760
that she would fall asleep, and never

00:50:38.760 --> 00:50:40.380
have to feel anything ever again.

00:50:40.440 --> 00:50:43.860
And part of Luna, wanted to throw the

00:50:43.860 --> 00:50:46.019
whole abyss mission out the window, and

00:50:46.019 --> 00:50:48.239
fly straight to Cicada Hive, and set

00:50:48.239 --> 00:50:51.059
everything on fire until she found sword

00:50:51.059 --> 00:50:51.420
tail.

00:50:51.480 --> 00:50:55.920
But by day 3 of their trip, all of Luna

00:50:55.920 --> 00:50:58.079
was focused on not screaming at her

00:50:58.079 --> 00:50:59.460
companions to fly faster.

00:50:59.519 --> 00:51:02.880
She did not think it had taken her this

00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:04.380
long to cross the ocean between the

00:51:04.380 --> 00:51:04.800
continents.

00:51:04.860 --> 00:51:08.219
Granted, she had been unconscious, and

00:51:08.219 --> 00:51:10.260
dragged along by a hurricane, but they

00:51:10.260 --> 00:51:11.460
could try a little harder.

00:51:12.119 --> 00:51:14.460
She tried to focus on the plan in her

00:51:14.460 --> 00:51:14.639
head.

00:51:14.699 --> 00:51:18.539
Find Penthalin humans, follow them to the

00:51:18.539 --> 00:51:19.139
abyss.

00:51:19.199 --> 00:51:21.119
Do... something.

00:51:21.179 --> 00:51:24.420
All right, most likely watch sundew do

00:51:24.420 --> 00:51:26.400
something, and then the important part.

00:51:26.460 --> 00:51:29.460
All the hive wings giving up and turning

00:51:29.460 --> 00:51:30.360
on Queen Wasp.

00:51:30.420 --> 00:51:33.659
Blue rescued from his nightmares, and

00:51:33.659 --> 00:51:35.579
Luna getting to hug sore tail for real

00:51:35.579 --> 00:51:38.039
and freedom for all the silk wings.

00:51:38.099 --> 00:51:41.760
There were some wobbly bits in the plan.

00:51:41.820 --> 00:51:44.400
Luna was trying not to think about the

00:51:44.400 --> 00:51:45.239
wobbly bits.

00:51:45.300 --> 00:51:47.760
Think about the happy ending instead.

00:51:47.820 --> 00:51:50.460
Think about how we're going to change

00:51:50.460 --> 00:51:50.820
everything.

00:51:50.880 --> 00:51:53.820
Think about the tapestries you'll be able

00:51:53.820 --> 00:51:55.260
to weave when this is all over.

00:51:55.320 --> 00:51:59.099
Luna did a twist roll in the air to catch

00:51:59.099 --> 00:52:02.219
a quick view of everyone. 10 dragons

00:52:02.219 --> 00:52:04.199
altogether, flying through the bright

00:52:04.199 --> 00:52:04.800
blue sky.

00:52:04.860 --> 00:52:08.519
Dragons from 10 different tribes.

00:52:08.579 --> 00:52:11.940
Not too long ago, she'd thought there

00:52:11.940 --> 00:52:13.679
were only 2 living tribes in the whole

00:52:13.679 --> 00:52:13.860
world.

00:52:13.920 --> 00:52:17.400
This is the kind of art I want to make

00:52:17.400 --> 00:52:18.300
she thought.

00:52:18.360 --> 00:52:21.599
A tapestry of all of us flying together.

00:52:21.659 --> 00:52:24.780
A tapestry that says, look how much

00:52:24.780 --> 00:52:26.579
bigger the world is than you thought it

00:52:26.579 --> 00:52:26.820
was.

00:52:26.880 --> 00:52:30.119
Look at how different we are, but we're

00:52:30.119 --> 00:52:31.019
all still dragons.

00:52:31.139 --> 00:52:33.900
Look at how dragons we don't even know.

00:52:33.960 --> 00:52:36.000
We'll fly across an ocean to help save

00:52:36.000 --> 00:52:36.539
us.

00:52:36.599 --> 00:52:39.300
Don't you want to be like these dragons?

00:52:39.360 --> 00:52:41.460
Don't you want to reach for different

00:52:41.460 --> 00:52:42.119
claws?

00:52:42.179 --> 00:52:44.400
Fly alongside different wings?

00:52:44.460 --> 00:52:46.860
Don't you want to do something brave and

00:52:46.860 --> 00:52:47.340
kind?

00:52:47.460 --> 00:52:49.079
Because someone has to.

00:52:49.139 --> 00:52:53.159
I'll call it talent united from the

00:52:53.159 --> 00:52:53.639
prophecy.

00:52:53.699 --> 00:52:55.800
After all of this is over.

00:52:55.920 --> 00:52:57.659
If we survive.

00:52:57.719 --> 00:53:01.380
Black wings fluttered in the corner of

00:53:01.380 --> 00:53:03.420
her eye, and Luna sighed.

00:53:03.539 --> 00:53:04.619
The good news?

00:53:04.679 --> 00:53:07.260
She was bringing a mini clear side back

00:53:07.260 --> 00:53:08.099
to Pentala with her.

00:53:08.159 --> 00:53:09.719
The bad news?

00:53:09.780 --> 00:53:12.719
Moon didn't have quite the personality

00:53:12.719 --> 00:53:14.639
Luna would have expected from a powerful

00:53:14.639 --> 00:53:15.119
seer.

00:53:15.179 --> 00:53:19.199
Luna had imagined more trances, more

00:53:19.199 --> 00:53:21.659
mystical declarations, and plenty of

00:53:21.659 --> 00:53:23.039
dramatic swooping about.

00:53:23.099 --> 00:53:25.199
If she were a seer.

00:53:25.260 --> 00:53:27.300
Luna would get out of every boring

00:53:27.300 --> 00:53:29.699
conversation by suddenly closing her eyes

00:53:29.699 --> 00:53:31.679
and announcing a need for silence.

00:53:31.739 --> 00:53:34.619
The future is speaking, and so forth.

00:53:34.679 --> 00:53:36.780
But on the plus side.

00:53:36.840 --> 00:53:40.440
Moon looked all cool and eerie, especially

00:53:40.440 --> 00:53:41.280
from a distance.

00:53:41.340 --> 00:53:43.380
And especially when she wasn't talking.

00:53:43.440 --> 00:53:46.320
She looked a lot like Clearsight did in

00:53:46.320 --> 00:53:48.659
the paintings, so that was a good start.

00:53:48.719 --> 00:53:51.960
Luna liked to imagine a scene where they

00:53:51.960 --> 00:53:54.539
all flew into a hive, pointed at Moon, and

00:53:54.539 --> 00:53:57.360
yelled, behold, the 2nd coming of clear

00:53:57.360 --> 00:53:57.719
sight.

00:53:57.840 --> 00:54:01.260
She says, actually, Queen Wasp is a jerk

00:54:01.260 --> 00:54:03.539
and silk wings are great, and should have

00:54:03.539 --> 00:54:05.400
their own queen, so there.

00:54:05.460 --> 00:54:09.179
And then all the hive wings would cry, oh

00:54:09.179 --> 00:54:11.519
no, we have been so wretched and wrong.

00:54:11.579 --> 00:54:13.860
Tell us how to be better dragons, Luna.

00:54:13.920 --> 00:54:16.019
Unfortunately.

00:54:16.139 --> 00:54:18.480
Moon was too nervous and twitchy to be a

00:54:18.480 --> 00:54:19.320
convincing prophet.

00:54:19.380 --> 00:54:21.840
The night wing would have to manage a

00:54:21.840 --> 00:54:24.780
much more imposing and inscutable face.

00:54:24.840 --> 00:54:27.420
If she wanted any hive wings to fall over

00:54:27.420 --> 00:54:29.280
at her talons, and renounce their

00:54:29.280 --> 00:54:29.880
horrible ways.

00:54:29.940 --> 00:54:33.599
In fact, after spending a few days with

00:54:33.599 --> 00:54:36.119
them, Luna had discovered that all the

00:54:36.119 --> 00:54:38.159
dragons who'd been chosen for the heroic

00:54:38.159 --> 00:54:40.800
quest of fulfilling Moon's prophecy were

00:54:40.800 --> 00:54:44.760
significantly less terrifying than she

00:54:44.760 --> 00:54:45.480
would have preferred.

00:54:45.539 --> 00:54:49.019
Apart from Zundu, who was impeccably

00:54:49.019 --> 00:54:50.159
terrifying at all times.

00:54:50.219 --> 00:54:54.119
Luna tilted her head up and sideways to

00:54:54.119 --> 00:54:56.159
study them each as they flew, one by

00:54:56.159 --> 00:54:56.460
one.

00:54:56.519 --> 00:55:01.380
Links, the ice wing, gleaming silver and

00:55:01.380 --> 00:55:03.480
blue, like diamonds slicing through the

00:55:03.480 --> 00:55:05.219
air, too smiley.

00:55:05.280 --> 00:55:09.179
Kibli, the sandwing, playing tag with a

00:55:09.179 --> 00:55:10.559
seagull to make moon laugh.

00:55:10.619 --> 00:55:13.260
Too hilarious, nowhere near series

00:55:13.260 --> 00:55:13.860
enough.

00:55:13.980 --> 00:55:17.519
Moon, the intimidating Nightwing

00:55:17.519 --> 00:55:18.059
herself.

00:55:18.119 --> 00:55:21.420
Too shy, lots of stammering, kind of

00:55:21.420 --> 00:55:22.619
spacy at weird moments.

00:55:22.739 --> 00:55:27.239
Cricket. too easily distracted, not a

00:55:27.239 --> 00:55:27.659
fighter.

00:55:27.719 --> 00:55:30.960
Plus, also a hive wing, and that still

00:55:30.960 --> 00:55:31.500
felt weird.

00:55:31.559 --> 00:55:35.219
She kept trying to fly next to Luna as

00:55:35.219 --> 00:55:37.019
though she wanted to talk about something

00:55:37.019 --> 00:55:39.059
but Luna could usually find a reason to

00:55:39.059 --> 00:55:41.639
fly with pineapple, or sky, or lynx

00:55:41.639 --> 00:55:41.940
instead.

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:44.400
Bullfrog.

00:55:44.400 --> 00:55:46.679
The mud wing was big and strong looking

00:55:46.679 --> 00:55:49.860
but he never said anything, not even when

00:55:49.860 --> 00:55:51.900
Kibley was off hunting, and there was a

00:55:51.900 --> 00:55:53.460
chance for other dragons to get a word in

00:55:53.460 --> 00:55:53.940
edgewise.

00:55:54.000 --> 00:55:57.119
If he had a personality or any sort of

00:55:57.119 --> 00:55:59.519
passion for anything, it was buried very

00:55:59.519 --> 00:56:01.619
deep, like a fossil.

00:56:01.679 --> 00:56:05.219
And Luna's favorite new Pyrea friend

00:56:05.219 --> 00:56:07.980
Pineapple the Rain Wing, was literally

00:56:07.980 --> 00:56:09.179
falling asleep while flying.

00:56:09.300 --> 00:56:10.320
Again.

00:56:10.440 --> 00:56:14.460
Pineapple, Luna called, flying up behind

00:56:14.460 --> 00:56:15.599
him and nudging his wing.

00:56:15.719 --> 00:56:19.500
He was iridescent gold and rose and cyan

00:56:19.500 --> 00:56:21.659
all over today, which was almost too

00:56:21.659 --> 00:56:23.099
pretty to look at straight on.

00:56:23.159 --> 00:56:26.099
Very up, he said.

00:56:26.159 --> 00:56:28.500
Startling away and tipping sideways.

00:56:28.559 --> 00:56:30.000
Definitely awake.

00:56:30.119 --> 00:56:33.659
It's the middle of the day, Luna pointed

00:56:33.659 --> 00:56:33.900
out.

00:56:33.960 --> 00:56:36.059
And we got so much sleep last night.

00:56:36.119 --> 00:56:37.619
How can you be tired?

00:56:37.679 --> 00:56:40.559
He shrugged, not at all embarrassed.

00:56:40.619 --> 00:56:43.860
This is when rain wings usually have our

00:56:43.860 --> 00:56:46.739
suntime naps, and there's so much sun out

00:56:46.739 --> 00:56:46.980
here.

00:56:47.039 --> 00:56:50.699
The confusing part is how all of you are

00:56:50.699 --> 00:56:51.179
still awake.

00:56:51.300 --> 00:56:55.079
He yawned, and then grinned at Luna, as

00:56:55.079 --> 00:56:56.940
she stifled a contagious yawn in

00:56:56.940 --> 00:56:57.659
response.

00:56:57.719 --> 00:57:00.780
There's an island coming up, Kibley

00:57:00.780 --> 00:57:01.079
said.

00:57:01.139 --> 00:57:03.360
He pulled out the map and consulted it

00:57:03.360 --> 00:57:05.460
tipping it to a line with the ocean

00:57:05.460 --> 00:57:05.760
below.

00:57:05.820 --> 00:57:07.920
We could rest for a bit.

00:57:07.980 --> 00:57:11.099
Arr, arr, arr.

00:57:11.159 --> 00:57:13.380
Luna didn't want to rest anymore.

00:57:13.440 --> 00:57:17.579
She'd spent forever resting on Jaboa's

00:57:17.579 --> 00:57:20.099
beach, waiting for Moon and Kibble to

00:57:20.099 --> 00:57:22.559
make a plan, waiting for the sea wings to

00:57:22.559 --> 00:57:25.139
swim to Pentala and back, waiting for the

00:57:25.139 --> 00:57:26.940
fleeing dragons from Pentala to get

00:57:26.940 --> 00:57:28.800
organized and figure out their next

00:57:28.800 --> 00:57:29.099
step.

00:57:29.159 --> 00:57:31.739
She couldn't wait 12nd longer.

00:57:31.860 --> 00:57:33.840
Swortail needed her now.

00:57:33.900 --> 00:57:37.019
She wanted to get to Blue and Sortell and

00:57:37.019 --> 00:57:37.739
save them at once.

00:57:37.860 --> 00:57:43.139
A short rest, maybe, tsunami said, soaring

00:57:43.139 --> 00:57:44.099
up beside Kibley.

00:57:44.219 --> 00:57:46.139
I want to make it to this island by

00:57:46.139 --> 00:57:46.739
nightfall.

00:57:46.800 --> 00:57:49.199
She pointed to another island.

00:57:49.260 --> 00:57:51.599
Three farther along the chain they were

00:57:51.599 --> 00:57:53.159
following, and Kibley nodded.

00:57:53.219 --> 00:57:55.440
Luna exhaled with relief.

00:57:55.500 --> 00:57:59.280
Tsunami was a pretty fierce and noisy sea

00:57:59.280 --> 00:58:02.099
wing, bigger than sundew, and maybe even

00:58:02.099 --> 00:58:03.119
scarier sometimes.

00:58:03.179 --> 00:58:05.940
She'd probably be useful against the hive

00:58:05.940 --> 00:58:06.420
wings.

00:58:06.480 --> 00:58:07.260
Luna thought.

00:58:07.320 --> 00:58:10.260
But the last dragon in their group was

00:58:10.260 --> 00:58:12.840
her direct opposite, Sky.

00:58:12.900 --> 00:58:15.960
The affable, pale orange sky wing with a

00:58:15.960 --> 00:58:16.500
human pet.

00:58:16.559 --> 00:58:19.559
Luna wished he had his tiny human's

00:58:19.559 --> 00:58:20.039
personality.

00:58:20.099 --> 00:58:22.920
Ren could probably take down a hive all

00:58:22.920 --> 00:58:25.320
by herself if she had fire and talons.

00:58:25.380 --> 00:58:28.139
Sky was more likely to bump into a hive

00:58:28.139 --> 00:58:30.119
and then apologized to its walls.

00:58:30.179 --> 00:58:32.940
He reminded her a little bit of her

00:58:32.940 --> 00:58:33.300
brother.

00:58:33.360 --> 00:58:34.019
Blue.

00:58:34.079 --> 00:58:36.659
Although Blue spent most of his time

00:58:36.659 --> 00:58:38.460
trying to imagine how other dragons

00:58:38.460 --> 00:58:38.820
felt.

00:58:38.880 --> 00:58:41.579
And Skye seemed mostly interested in how

00:58:41.579 --> 00:58:45.179
snails felt, or turtles, or dolphins.

00:58:45.239 --> 00:58:46.800
He was really sweet.

00:58:46.860 --> 00:58:49.920
They were all very lovely and funny and

00:58:49.920 --> 00:58:52.440
kind, and if Luna were organizing a

00:58:52.440 --> 00:58:54.179
dinner party, they'd be the perfect

00:58:54.179 --> 00:58:55.139
dragons to invite.

00:58:55.199 --> 00:58:58.079
But this wasn't a dinner party.

00:58:58.199 --> 00:59:01.980
It was an epic life or death battle, with

00:59:01.980 --> 00:59:04.800
an evil queen and her evil tribe, and

00:59:04.800 --> 00:59:07.320
also a vitally important rescue mission.

00:59:07.380 --> 00:59:10.619
With her own entire tribe's future at

00:59:10.619 --> 00:59:10.920
stake.

00:59:11.039 --> 00:59:14.159
How could 10 sweet dragons?

00:59:14.159 --> 00:59:17.880
Or, all right, 8 sweet dragons, into

00:59:17.880 --> 00:59:20.940
reasonably ferocious dragons, defeat the

00:59:20.940 --> 00:59:23.280
scariest queen and the scariest tribe in

00:59:23.280 --> 00:59:23.760
the whole world.

00:59:23.880 --> 00:59:27.000
Blue and Swordtail were counting on her.

00:59:27.059 --> 00:59:29.699
And this was the army she'd brought to

00:59:29.699 --> 00:59:30.000
save them?

00:59:30.119 --> 00:59:33.780
Luna fidgeted with her talons and glanced

00:59:33.780 --> 00:59:34.559
back over her shoulder.

00:59:34.619 --> 00:59:37.320
The distant kingdoms were so far behind

00:59:37.320 --> 00:59:39.420
them now, that there was nothing to see

00:59:39.420 --> 00:59:40.559
but sky and ocean.

00:59:40.619 --> 00:59:43.980
Maybe they should go back and ask for

00:59:43.980 --> 00:59:45.119
real armies again, though.

00:59:45.179 --> 00:59:48.599
Armies, with lots of soldiers and weapons

00:59:48.599 --> 00:59:50.460
that would be useful.

00:59:50.519 --> 00:59:54.420
A magic army would be even better.

00:59:54.480 --> 00:59:57.539
Luna imagined that tapestry for a

00:59:57.539 --> 00:59:57.719
moment.

00:59:57.780 --> 01:00:00.539
The whole top 3rd covered in wings

01:00:00.539 --> 01:00:03.480
dragons swarming down surrounded by

01:00:03.480 --> 01:00:06.059
lightning bolts, and enchanted swords

01:00:06.059 --> 01:00:08.760
with Queen Wasp, alone at the bottom

01:00:08.760 --> 01:00:12.300
making an uh-oh, very doomed face.

01:00:12.360 --> 01:00:15.719
Landing in Pantala with a magical army

01:00:15.719 --> 01:00:18.000
sounded like a much smarter idea than

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:19.920
flapping in with a talon full of cuddly

01:00:19.920 --> 01:00:21.179
dragons and a human.

01:00:21.239 --> 01:00:25.019
Don't worry, Moon said from her left.

01:00:25.079 --> 01:00:27.599
Some of us are more useful than we look.

01:00:27.659 --> 01:00:30.840
Luna pivoted to Squint Atter.

01:00:30.900 --> 01:00:33.239
Moon said things like that a lot.

01:00:33.300 --> 01:00:35.639
Things that sounded like she was talking

01:00:35.639 --> 01:00:37.320
back to the thoughts in Luna's head.

01:00:37.440 --> 01:00:40.079
Why would she suddenly swoop up and say

01:00:40.079 --> 01:00:42.119
something like that now, out of nowhere.

01:00:42.179 --> 01:00:45.539
Not me, Moon said quickly.

01:00:45.599 --> 01:00:48.780
I meant like Kibli, just for one

01:00:48.780 --> 01:00:49.079
example.

01:00:49.139 --> 01:00:51.960
She looked a little less nervous for a

01:00:51.960 --> 01:00:54.539
2nd as her eyes tracked the sand wings

01:00:54.539 --> 01:00:56.880
soaring down to the water, scooping up a

01:00:56.880 --> 01:00:59.340
floating coconut, and tossing it to sky

01:00:59.340 --> 01:01:01.380
who fumbled it through his talons and

01:01:01.380 --> 01:01:02.400
dropped it back in the ocean.

01:01:02.460 --> 01:01:06.000
He's actually kind of great at saving the

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:06.179
world.

01:01:06.239 --> 01:01:10.800
Kibli is her sore tail, Luna realized.

01:01:10.860 --> 01:01:13.739
She'd sort of guessed, from the way they

01:01:13.739 --> 01:01:15.539
looked at each other. and the way they

01:01:15.539 --> 01:01:17.039
slept side by side every night.

01:01:17.099 --> 01:01:19.800
Why are you telling me this?

01:01:19.860 --> 01:01:21.480
Luna asked Moon.

01:01:21.539 --> 01:01:23.579
Did you have a vision of what's going to

01:01:23.579 --> 01:01:24.840
happen to us in Pentala?

01:01:24.900 --> 01:01:28.079
She wished she could have a vision of the

01:01:28.079 --> 01:01:28.320
future.

01:01:28.380 --> 01:01:31.559
Imagine knowing the whole plan, how

01:01:31.559 --> 01:01:33.119
everything should turn out and how to get

01:01:33.119 --> 01:01:33.420
there.

01:01:33.480 --> 01:01:36.480
The whole tapestry of the future, spread

01:01:36.480 --> 01:01:37.079
out in her mind.

01:01:37.199 --> 01:01:38.880
That would be amazing.

01:01:38.940 --> 01:01:41.280
Sorry.

01:01:41.340 --> 01:01:42.539
Moon stammered.

01:01:42.599 --> 01:01:45.059
She pointed back the way Luna had been

01:01:45.059 --> 01:01:45.659
looking.

01:01:45.719 --> 01:01:48.659
I just, you looked like you were wishing

01:01:48.659 --> 01:01:49.559
you'd brought someone else.

01:01:49.679 --> 01:01:51.780
Or like maybe you want to go back?

01:01:51.840 --> 01:01:54.300
She took a deep breath.

01:01:54.360 --> 01:01:56.519
Sorry, never mind.

01:01:56.639 --> 01:01:59.400
No, no, I'm totally fine.

01:01:59.460 --> 01:02:00.599
Not worried at all.

01:02:00.659 --> 01:02:03.360
Luna blurted, before moon could swoop

01:02:03.360 --> 01:02:03.599
away.

01:02:03.659 --> 01:02:06.900
Still smiling, not causing problems.

01:02:07.019 --> 01:02:10.619
It's only that the closer we get, the

01:02:10.619 --> 01:02:13.019
more I remember how terrifying wasp is

01:02:13.019 --> 01:02:16.559
and the more I think, you know, wouldn't

01:02:16.559 --> 01:02:18.000
it be great if we had something big and

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:20.579
stabby, or magic, or both?

01:02:20.639 --> 01:02:24.000
Big stabby magic for stabbing hive wings

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:24.239
with?

01:02:24.300 --> 01:02:25.739
I know.

01:02:25.800 --> 01:02:28.019
Moon said sympathetically.

01:02:28.079 --> 01:02:31.019
But remember, we're not going to confront

01:02:31.019 --> 01:02:31.739
WASP.

01:02:31.800 --> 01:02:34.079
Our mission is to find out what's in the

01:02:34.079 --> 01:02:36.659
abyss that Queen Snowfall saw with her

01:02:36.659 --> 01:02:37.320
vision from the ring.

01:02:37.440 --> 01:02:39.960
And hopefully, it'll be a way to save

01:02:39.960 --> 01:02:43.260
your friends without needing any magic or

01:02:43.260 --> 01:02:44.579
um, stabbing.

01:02:44.639 --> 01:02:46.860
The other dragons.

01:02:46.920 --> 01:02:49.320
Especially Kibile and Moon, were

01:02:49.320 --> 01:02:51.420
convinced that this abyss would solve all

01:02:51.420 --> 01:02:52.019
their problems.

01:02:52.079 --> 01:02:55.980
But frankly, Luna had some concerns about

01:02:55.980 --> 01:02:58.860
what one might find at the bottom of a

01:02:58.860 --> 01:03:00.480
dark, ominous abyss.

01:03:00.480 --> 01:03:04.380
The word abyss kind of sounded like it

01:03:04.380 --> 01:03:05.940
came with guaranteed death and

01:03:05.940 --> 01:03:06.599
creepiness.

01:03:06.659 --> 01:03:09.659
She couldn't imagine anything abyss

01:03:09.659 --> 01:03:12.480
related that wouldn't require magic or

01:03:12.480 --> 01:03:13.980
stabbing to defeat.

01:03:14.039 --> 01:03:16.559
You haven't had any more specific

01:03:16.559 --> 01:03:17.340
visions?

01:03:17.400 --> 01:03:19.380
She asked Moon, hopefully.

01:03:19.440 --> 01:03:22.619
Clues about what's down there, hints

01:03:22.619 --> 01:03:23.639
about what we're supposed to do.

01:03:23.699 --> 01:03:27.059
Maybe the tiniest flash of me dancing on

01:03:27.059 --> 01:03:28.019
Wasp's grave?

01:03:28.079 --> 01:03:33.239
Nothing helpful, Moon said, with a rueful

01:03:33.239 --> 01:03:33.480
face.

01:03:33.539 --> 01:03:36.659
But then, she always looks like that.

01:03:36.719 --> 01:03:38.699
Luna thought grumpily.

01:03:38.760 --> 01:03:42.239
Moon has resting rueful face, like a

01:03:42.239 --> 01:03:45.780
permanent, oh, I'm so sorry, I can't help

01:03:45.780 --> 01:03:48.900
you even with all my amazing magic.

01:03:48.960 --> 01:03:51.599
I guess it only works on my problems

01:03:51.659 --> 01:03:52.920
expression.

01:03:52.980 --> 01:03:56.460
She glanced over at Moon again. and

01:03:56.460 --> 01:03:58.199
caught the little black dragon flinching

01:03:58.199 --> 01:04:00.300
as though something had jabbed her in the

01:04:00.300 --> 01:04:00.599
snout.

01:04:00.719 --> 01:04:03.239
We do have a little magic.

01:04:03.360 --> 01:04:06.179
Lynx interjected from above and to her

01:04:06.179 --> 01:04:06.420
right.

01:04:06.480 --> 01:04:09.300
She pointed to the silver bracelets on

01:04:09.300 --> 01:04:10.199
Sundew's wrists.

01:04:10.320 --> 01:04:12.719
When should we start using those?

01:04:12.780 --> 01:04:16.380
The wristbands gave Sundu the power to

01:04:16.380 --> 01:04:19.079
turn any or all of them invisible

01:04:19.079 --> 01:04:20.099
including herself.

01:04:20.159 --> 01:04:23.460
It was a small gift of magic from the ice

01:04:23.460 --> 01:04:26.280
wing queen, who was a flipping, terrifying

01:04:26.280 --> 01:04:27.719
dragon if you asked Luna.

01:04:27.840 --> 01:04:30.659
Snowfall could probably have defeated the

01:04:30.659 --> 01:04:32.639
hive wings just by staring coldly at

01:04:32.639 --> 01:04:32.940
them.

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:35.760
We're still at least 2 days from the

01:04:35.760 --> 01:04:37.559
coast of Pentala, by my estimate.

01:04:37.619 --> 01:04:39.059
Tsunami said.

01:04:39.119 --> 01:04:41.159
She glanced at Kibli's map again.

01:04:41.219 --> 01:04:42.960
Cricket, do you agree?

01:04:43.019 --> 01:04:44.760
Me?

01:04:44.820 --> 01:04:47.219
The bespectacled hive wing said

01:04:47.219 --> 01:04:47.880
startled.

01:04:47.940 --> 01:04:49.980
Oh, me, yes.

01:04:50.039 --> 01:04:50.820
Um, sorry.

01:04:50.940 --> 01:04:53.039
I was a little distracted when we left

01:04:53.039 --> 01:04:55.500
Pentala, and we were coming from farther

01:04:55.500 --> 01:04:57.659
north, but we don't want to aim for the

01:04:57.659 --> 01:04:59.039
poison jungle this time, right?

01:04:59.099 --> 01:05:01.139
We're thinking Dragonfly Bay?

01:05:01.199 --> 01:05:03.659
Also, we're moving faster now than we

01:05:03.659 --> 01:05:05.519
were with all the little and old leaf

01:05:05.519 --> 01:05:05.820
wings.

01:05:05.940 --> 01:05:09.480
But yes, right, 2 days, that sounds about

01:05:09.480 --> 01:05:10.019
right to me too.

01:05:10.079 --> 01:05:13.500
She added quickly, a tsunami frowned at

01:05:13.500 --> 01:05:13.679
her.

01:05:13.739 --> 01:05:16.679
The tiny human yelled something from

01:05:16.679 --> 01:05:19.380
Sky's back, but the wind whipped her itty

01:05:19.380 --> 01:05:20.280
bitty voice away.

01:05:20.340 --> 01:05:23.460
Ren says maybe we should start using them

01:05:23.460 --> 01:05:23.880
now then.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:25.739
Sky offered cheerfully.

01:05:25.800 --> 01:05:28.860
She says, better safe than super dead.

01:05:28.980 --> 01:05:29.760
What?

01:05:29.820 --> 01:05:31.019
Oh, sorry.

01:05:31.079 --> 01:05:34.260
He cleared his throat and said in a much

01:05:34.260 --> 01:05:37.440
deeper growlier voice, Danger could be

01:05:37.440 --> 01:05:38.760
lurking around every cloud.

01:05:38.820 --> 01:05:41.219
We could be murdered by zombie bug

01:05:41.219 --> 01:05:42.420
dragons at any moment.

01:05:42.480 --> 01:05:46.019
Then he spoiled the effect by bursting

01:05:46.019 --> 01:05:47.039
into helpless giggles.

01:05:47.099 --> 01:05:49.679
Pineapple grinned Adam.

01:05:49.739 --> 01:05:52.679
Most of the Pyrean dragons seemed sort of

01:05:52.679 --> 01:05:53.820
flummixed by Skye.

01:05:53.880 --> 01:05:56.820
The least sky wingish sky wing ever

01:05:56.820 --> 01:05:58.320
tsunami had called him.

01:05:58.440 --> 01:06:01.980
But pineapple found sky delightful, which

01:06:01.980 --> 01:06:04.019
made Luna like the rain wing even more.

01:06:04.079 --> 01:06:08.099
She's not wrong, Sundu pointed out.

01:06:08.159 --> 01:06:11.159
I like the idea of using the magic now

01:06:11.159 --> 01:06:12.239
Luna said.

01:06:12.300 --> 01:06:13.619
It won't run out, will it?

01:06:13.679 --> 01:06:15.300
We can use it as much as we want.

01:06:15.360 --> 01:06:17.340
That's right.

01:06:17.460 --> 01:06:19.440
Link said, nodding.

01:06:19.500 --> 01:06:21.900
Maybe we could start using it after our

01:06:21.900 --> 01:06:23.039
next rest stop, then?

01:06:23.099 --> 01:06:25.739
I'm not sure how much use it will be

01:06:25.739 --> 01:06:27.539
though, Kibley said seriously.

01:06:27.599 --> 01:06:30.539
I mean, even if we're all invisible.

01:06:30.599 --> 01:06:33.239
I'm pretty sure bullfrogs nonstop chatter

01:06:33.239 --> 01:06:34.019
is going to give us away.

01:06:34.079 --> 01:06:37.380
The silent mudwing swung his head

01:06:37.380 --> 01:06:39.780
ponderously around to give Kibli a

01:06:39.780 --> 01:06:40.320
puzzled look.

01:06:40.380 --> 01:06:42.300
Eh?

01:06:42.300 --> 01:06:43.019
he said.

01:06:43.079 --> 01:06:46.019
Yeah, that's what I'm talking about

01:06:46.019 --> 01:06:47.039
Kibley said.

01:06:47.099 --> 01:06:49.800
That nonstop yippyapping bullfrog.

01:06:49.860 --> 01:06:51.179
They're going to hear you coming from

01:06:51.179 --> 01:06:51.719
miles away.

01:06:51.780 --> 01:06:55.800
Sky snorted a laugh that nearly knocked

01:06:55.800 --> 01:06:56.760
Ren off his back.

01:06:56.820 --> 01:06:59.699
Bullfrog considered Kibley for a moment.

01:06:59.760 --> 01:07:03.599
Don't think so, he said after a while.

01:07:03.659 --> 01:07:06.420
I know it's going to be tough, Kibley

01:07:06.420 --> 01:07:08.340
said, but I'm afraid you'll have to be

01:07:08.340 --> 01:07:09.300
way quieter.

01:07:09.360 --> 01:07:12.900
Bullfrog turned his furrowed brow toward

01:07:12.900 --> 01:07:13.199
the others.

01:07:13.260 --> 01:07:16.139
I'm confused.

01:07:16.199 --> 01:07:19.019
Kibley is being ridiculous.

01:07:19.079 --> 01:07:20.400
Moon explained.

01:07:20.460 --> 01:07:22.739
He's trying to find someone to argue with

01:07:22.739 --> 01:07:24.719
him, since winter's not here to do it.

01:07:24.780 --> 01:07:28.380
Do I talk too much?

01:07:28.500 --> 01:07:31.679
Bullfrog asked pineapple. who was flying

01:07:31.679 --> 01:07:32.099
beside him.

01:07:32.159 --> 01:07:37.739
Do. I talk too much.

01:07:37.800 --> 01:07:40.980
I think that was the most words I've ever

01:07:40.980 --> 01:07:41.519
heard you say.

01:07:41.579 --> 01:07:43.260
Pineapple admitted.

01:07:43.320 --> 01:07:47.340
I'm sorry, Bullfrog, Kibley said, nudging

01:07:47.340 --> 01:07:47.699
his wing.

01:07:47.760 --> 01:07:49.440
I'm just kidding.

01:07:49.500 --> 01:07:51.480
You're the stealthiest dragon we have.

01:07:51.539 --> 01:07:52.739
I think you're awesome.

01:07:52.800 --> 01:07:54.719
Really?

01:07:54.780 --> 01:07:58.559
Bullfrog said, looking confused all over

01:07:58.559 --> 01:07:58.800
again.

01:07:58.920 --> 01:08:02.219
Kibble was not very much like blue in

01:08:02.219 --> 01:08:05.159
most ways, but sometimes Luna saw little

01:08:05.159 --> 01:08:06.900
things in the sand wing that reminded her

01:08:06.900 --> 01:08:07.260
of her brother.

01:08:07.320 --> 01:08:10.320
They both wanted to be liked so badly.

01:08:10.380 --> 01:08:13.079
They both wanted everyone they meant to

01:08:13.079 --> 01:08:14.699
feel warm and comfortable and happy

01:08:14.699 --> 01:08:15.239
around them.

01:08:15.300 --> 01:08:19.140
Kibli did it with jokes and banter, while

01:08:19.140 --> 01:08:21.420
Blue let other dragons push him around in

01:08:21.420 --> 01:08:22.260
order to keep the peace.

01:08:22.319 --> 01:08:25.559
That was something she loved about Blue

01:08:25.559 --> 01:08:27.239
that also drove her up a wall.

01:08:27.359 --> 01:08:30.779
Luna did not care 2 honey drops, whether

01:08:30.779 --> 01:08:32.279
any hive wings liked her.

01:08:32.340 --> 01:08:33.300
So what?

01:08:33.359 --> 01:08:36.599
They were mostly all terrible, the worst

01:08:36.599 --> 01:08:38.879
rude and superior and entitled and

01:08:38.879 --> 01:08:39.479
sneering.

01:08:39.539 --> 01:08:42.539
Why would she need any of them to think

01:08:42.539 --> 01:08:46.140
ah, yes, that Luna, what a lovely, quiet

01:08:46.140 --> 01:08:47.039
silk wing.

01:08:47.159 --> 01:08:49.020
No, no, no.

01:08:49.079 --> 01:08:52.560
She would much rather they thought, uh-oh

01:08:52.560 --> 01:08:53.579
here comes Luna.

01:08:53.640 --> 01:08:56.159
She's probably going to set us all on

01:08:56.159 --> 01:08:56.520
fire again.

01:08:56.579 --> 01:09:00.239
Especially, if that meant she never had

01:09:00.239 --> 01:09:02.520
to actually set anyone on fire.

01:09:02.579 --> 01:09:05.760
But blue was always friendly and polite

01:09:05.760 --> 01:09:06.420
to everyone.

01:09:06.479 --> 01:09:08.219
No matter how awful they were.

01:09:08.279 --> 01:09:11.219
That's why she'd never told him about the

01:09:11.219 --> 01:09:11.819
chrysalis.

01:09:11.880 --> 01:09:14.520
She had a feeling he'd be thoroughly

01:09:14.520 --> 01:09:16.800
confused by a secret group of silk wings

01:09:16.800 --> 01:09:19.079
who gathered to talk about fighting back

01:09:19.079 --> 01:09:20.159
against Queen Wasp.

01:09:20.279 --> 01:09:23.399
Fighting back wasn't in Blue's

01:09:23.399 --> 01:09:23.999
vocabulary.

01:09:24.060 --> 01:09:27.420
At least not until Luna turned out to be

01:09:27.420 --> 01:09:28.140
a flame silk.

01:09:28.199 --> 01:09:31.319
He'd been different when she came out of

01:09:31.319 --> 01:09:31.920
her cocoon.

01:09:31.979 --> 01:09:34.739
She hadn't been with him long enough to

01:09:34.739 --> 01:09:37.199
really see how different, but from the

01:09:37.199 --> 01:09:39.839
stories Cricket and Sundew told her, Blue

01:09:39.839 --> 01:09:41.939
had been through a lot while Luna was in

01:09:41.939 --> 01:09:42.899
her metamorphosis sleep.

01:09:42.960 --> 01:09:46.260
Kibley was a little bit like Swordtail

01:09:46.260 --> 01:09:46.439
too.

01:09:46.500 --> 01:09:48.840
Sortail was funny like Kibley.

01:09:48.960 --> 01:09:51.180
He also talked a lot when he was nervous

01:09:51.180 --> 01:09:52.560
like Kibley did.

01:09:52.619 --> 01:09:55.199
Sortail didn't need to be liked by

01:09:55.199 --> 01:09:55.680
everybody, though.

01:09:55.800 --> 01:09:59.159
He was happy to be loved by Luna and Blue

01:09:59.159 --> 01:10:00.600
and his sister Io.

01:10:00.659 --> 01:10:03.600
Everybody else could stuff termites up

01:10:03.600 --> 01:10:05.100
their noses if they didn't like him for

01:10:05.100 --> 01:10:05.699
all he cared.

01:10:05.760 --> 01:10:08.939
Luna wished she could talk to him again.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:11.880
She wanted to tell him about the dragons

01:10:11.880 --> 01:10:12.840
she was traveling with.

01:10:12.899 --> 01:10:16.619
What would he think of pineapple, or lynx

01:10:16.619 --> 01:10:17.159
or sky?

01:10:17.220 --> 01:10:20.220
Would he be able to trust cricket more

01:10:20.220 --> 01:10:20.520
than she did?

01:10:20.579 --> 01:10:23.819
Would he find Moon a little unsettling?

01:10:23.880 --> 01:10:26.520
Or would he feel sorry for her, and how

01:10:26.520 --> 01:10:27.300
shy she was?

01:10:27.359 --> 01:10:30.659
She was pretty sure he would like Kibli.

01:10:30.720 --> 01:10:33.960
She could imagine them annoying hive wing

01:10:33.960 --> 01:10:34.560
guards together.

01:10:34.619 --> 01:10:37.680
Luna had borrowed the dream visitor from

01:10:37.680 --> 01:10:40.319
tsunami whenever they'd stopped, but she

01:10:40.319 --> 01:10:42.060
hadn't been able to find Swordtail asleep

01:10:42.060 --> 01:10:42.239
again.

01:10:42.300 --> 01:10:46.020
She wondered what he was doing, or

01:10:46.020 --> 01:10:46.380
worse.

01:10:46.500 --> 01:10:48.659
What wasp was making him do.

01:10:48.720 --> 01:10:52.680
She couldn't bear to think of Wasp inside

01:10:52.680 --> 01:10:55.739
Soretail's head, or manipulating Blue's

01:10:55.739 --> 01:10:56.159
talons.

01:10:56.220 --> 01:10:59.579
She had to stop thinking about it, or she

01:10:59.579 --> 01:11:01.199
might have to dive into the ocean and

01:11:01.199 --> 01:11:02.640
scream for days.

01:11:02.699 --> 01:11:04.800
And the whales probably wouldn't like

01:11:04.800 --> 01:11:05.039
that.

01:11:05.100 --> 01:11:09.119
There's the island, Pineapple said.

01:11:09.180 --> 01:11:11.340
Flicking his tail toward the small blur

01:11:11.340 --> 01:11:13.619
of a white sand curve rising out of the

01:11:13.619 --> 01:11:14.399
ocean ahead of them.

01:11:14.460 --> 01:11:16.319
Thank the moons.

01:11:16.380 --> 01:11:18.180
I'm so ready to lie down.

01:11:18.300 --> 01:11:21.720
He grinned at Luna, and swooped ahead of

01:11:21.720 --> 01:11:21.899
everyone.

01:11:21.960 --> 01:11:25.140
Tsunami checked the position of the sun

01:11:25.140 --> 01:11:25.739
in the sky.

01:11:25.859 --> 01:11:27.779
Well, past midday.

01:11:27.840 --> 01:11:31.260
Luna knew from her internal clock, sighed

01:11:31.260 --> 01:11:33.539
and sped up to fly after him, shouting.

01:11:33.600 --> 01:11:35.579
Not for long, pineapple.

01:11:35.640 --> 01:11:37.020
Don't you dare fall asleep.

01:11:37.079 --> 01:11:39.239
I don't.

01:11:39.359 --> 01:11:41.520
Think.

01:11:41.640 --> 01:11:44.039
Bullfrog said slowly.

01:11:44.159 --> 01:11:46.800
That I talk too much.

01:11:46.859 --> 01:11:50.520
You don't, Moon reassured him.

01:11:50.579 --> 01:11:54.600
Kibley is the one who talks too much, Link

01:11:54.600 --> 01:11:55.319
said helpfully.

01:11:55.380 --> 01:11:58.199
You know, I feel like I've heard that

01:11:58.199 --> 01:11:58.920
somewhere before.

01:11:59.039 --> 01:12:01.500
Kibley said, tapping his chin.

01:12:01.560 --> 01:12:04.079
Race you to the beach bullfrog.

01:12:04.140 --> 01:12:06.600
He took off without waiting for an answer

01:12:06.600 --> 01:12:09.359
which was especially funny when Bullfrog

01:12:09.359 --> 01:12:10.859
just blinked after him in more

01:12:10.859 --> 01:12:11.579
confusion.

01:12:11.640 --> 01:12:13.619
Maybe tomorrow?

01:12:13.739 --> 01:12:16.920
Cricket said out of the blue, as though

01:12:16.920 --> 01:12:18.420
she'd been working out a question in her

01:12:18.420 --> 01:12:20.699
head, and missed the entire last half of

01:12:20.699 --> 01:12:21.180
the conversation.

01:12:21.239 --> 01:12:24.539
Starting tomorrow morning, we go into

01:12:24.539 --> 01:12:25.859
invisible stealth mode.

01:12:25.920 --> 01:12:27.420
What do you guys think?

01:12:27.479 --> 01:12:29.039
That makes sense, doesn't it?

01:12:29.100 --> 01:12:31.800
I agree, Moon said.

01:12:31.859 --> 01:12:33.720
Sure.

01:12:33.779 --> 01:12:37.140
I'll feel safer once we're invisible, Link

01:12:37.140 --> 01:12:38.340
said, nodding.

01:12:38.399 --> 01:12:41.100
Although, if we're all invisible.

01:12:41.159 --> 01:12:43.800
Pineapple really can't fall asleep while

01:12:43.800 --> 01:12:44.399
we're flying.

01:12:44.460 --> 01:12:47.220
Luna joked, or he'll drop into the ocean

01:12:47.220 --> 01:12:48.359
and we'll never find him.

01:12:48.420 --> 01:12:50.699
Up ahead of them.

01:12:50.760 --> 01:12:53.699
A dragon's scream sliced through the

01:12:53.699 --> 01:12:53.939
sky.

01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:58.260
Chapter 3.

01:12:58.560 --> 01:13:02.939
Luna froze in midair, her wings beating

01:13:02.939 --> 01:13:04.199
backward for a panicked moment.

01:13:04.260 --> 01:13:07.319
She turned instinctively toward sundew

01:13:07.319 --> 01:13:08.579
and saw links do the same.

01:13:08.640 --> 01:13:13.020
But Moon cried, Kibli, and shot away

01:13:13.020 --> 01:13:14.640
toward the island, leaving the rest of

01:13:14.640 --> 01:13:15.000
them behind.

01:13:15.060 --> 01:13:17.279
What was that?

01:13:17.399 --> 01:13:18.539
Sky yelped.

01:13:18.600 --> 01:13:21.960
I think it was pineapple, Lang said

01:13:21.960 --> 01:13:23.760
frantically, as Sundew yelled.

01:13:23.819 --> 01:13:24.960
Moon, wait.

01:13:25.079 --> 01:13:27.659
The little black dragon was too far ahead

01:13:27.659 --> 01:13:28.020
already.

01:13:28.079 --> 01:13:30.600
And now Luna could hear roaring coming

01:13:30.600 --> 01:13:31.500
from the distant beach.

01:13:31.560 --> 01:13:34.260
More than one dragon roaring.

01:13:34.380 --> 01:13:35.579
More than two.

01:13:35.699 --> 01:13:39.000
More than 4 A dozen unfamiliar voices.

01:13:39.060 --> 01:13:42.720
Too many dragons, roaring in fury and

01:13:42.720 --> 01:13:43.800
rage and pain.

01:13:43.859 --> 01:13:46.500
It's wasp, she said.

01:13:46.560 --> 01:13:48.720
Her throat closing over the words.

01:13:48.779 --> 01:13:50.279
She found us.

01:13:50.399 --> 01:13:51.960
She found us already.

01:13:52.020 --> 01:13:54.060
Everyone stay close.

01:13:54.180 --> 01:13:55.680
Sandu shouted.

01:13:55.739 --> 01:13:58.199
She vaulted to a higher wind current

01:13:58.199 --> 01:14:00.659
spread her wings, and held up the magic

01:14:00.659 --> 01:14:01.319
wristbands.

01:14:01.380 --> 01:14:04.199
What if we get separated while we're

01:14:04.199 --> 01:14:04.619
invisible?

01:14:04.739 --> 01:14:06.359
Cricket yelped.

01:14:06.420 --> 01:14:07.920
But Sundew was already touching the

01:14:07.920 --> 01:14:08.640
diamonds together.

01:14:08.699 --> 01:14:12.119
There was no time to answer, no time to

01:14:12.119 --> 01:14:12.539
make a plan.

01:14:12.600 --> 01:14:15.000
What were they supposed to do if they

01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:15.659
lost the others?

01:14:15.720 --> 01:14:18.300
Go on to the next island or go back?

01:14:18.359 --> 01:14:20.100
There was only one map.

01:14:20.159 --> 01:14:23.159
If something happened to sundo, or you

01:14:23.159 --> 01:14:25.319
got separated from the group, would you

01:14:25.319 --> 01:14:27.359
be an invisible dragon alone forever?

01:14:27.420 --> 01:14:31.020
Luna reached out in panic and found

01:14:31.020 --> 01:14:32.699
Lynx's talent doing the same.

01:14:32.760 --> 01:14:35.460
They clasped claws just as they both

01:14:35.460 --> 01:14:36.119
disappeared.

01:14:36.180 --> 01:14:39.420
It was so eerie.

01:14:39.479 --> 01:14:43.020
Feeling a cold talon in hers, when she

01:14:43.020 --> 01:14:44.340
couldn't see the dragon on the other end

01:14:44.340 --> 01:14:48.359
it was beyond eerie, to see empty air

01:14:48.359 --> 01:14:50.579
where her own wings and tail and claws

01:14:50.579 --> 01:14:50.880
should be.

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:55.439
Sundew, Sky and Wren, Bullfrog and

01:14:55.439 --> 01:14:58.260
Cricket, were all gone too, leaving only

01:14:58.260 --> 01:14:59.399
blue sky around them.

01:14:59.460 --> 01:15:02.880
Luna twisted in the air to look for moon

01:15:02.880 --> 01:15:05.399
tugging links along with her, but the

01:15:05.399 --> 01:15:06.600
night wing was nowhere to be seen.

01:15:06.720 --> 01:15:10.439
I think I got Moon before she was too far

01:15:10.439 --> 01:15:10.680
away.

01:15:10.800 --> 01:15:13.680
Sundu's voice said breathlessly.

01:15:13.739 --> 01:15:17.100
Luna felt a thick wing bump hers and a

01:15:17.100 --> 01:15:19.739
mumbled, oops, that she thought might be

01:15:19.739 --> 01:15:20.340
bullfrog.

01:15:20.399 --> 01:15:23.340
What about tsunami and Kibli and

01:15:23.340 --> 01:15:23.939
Pineapple?

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:25.319
Cricket's voice asked.

01:15:25.380 --> 01:15:27.119
Did you turn them invisible too?

01:15:27.180 --> 01:15:29.039
I couldn't.

01:15:29.100 --> 01:15:31.380
The magic can only cover dragons in my

01:15:31.380 --> 01:15:31.739
line of sight.

01:15:31.859 --> 01:15:33.239
Sundu answered.

01:15:33.300 --> 01:15:35.760
Her voice sounded like it was coming from

01:15:35.760 --> 01:15:37.560
the smoke thin wisps of clouds above

01:15:37.560 --> 01:15:37.800
them.

01:15:37.859 --> 01:15:41.579
So let's go save them, Luna said

01:15:41.579 --> 01:15:42.119
urgently.

01:15:42.180 --> 01:15:44.699
She wasn't sure if it was her own wings

01:15:44.699 --> 01:15:46.619
or lynxes moving them toward the island

01:15:46.619 --> 01:15:49.020
and the roaring and the screaming, but

01:15:49.020 --> 01:15:50.579
everyone else seemed to be behind them

01:15:50.579 --> 01:15:53.939
hovering, discussing, waiting, losing

01:15:53.939 --> 01:15:54.359
time.

01:15:54.420 --> 01:15:56.939
Come on, it must be hive wings

01:15:56.939 --> 01:15:57.420
attacking.

01:15:57.539 --> 01:15:58.500
We have to do something.

01:15:58.619 --> 01:16:00.359
How?

01:16:00.420 --> 01:16:01.140
Do what?

01:16:01.199 --> 01:16:03.420
Yelled the panicked thoughts flying

01:16:03.420 --> 01:16:03.960
around her brain.

01:16:04.020 --> 01:16:06.960
Right, Sundu cried.

01:16:07.020 --> 01:16:08.460
Yes, let's fight them.

01:16:08.520 --> 01:16:09.659
Finally.

01:16:09.720 --> 01:16:11.220
Won't they hear us?

01:16:11.279 --> 01:16:12.359
Even if they can't see us?

01:16:12.479 --> 01:16:13.619
Cricket asked.

01:16:13.680 --> 01:16:15.659
They can't hear us.

01:16:15.779 --> 01:16:18.539
Lynx answered Cricket, her voice

01:16:18.539 --> 01:16:20.579
startlingly close to Luna in the empty

01:16:20.579 --> 01:16:21.000
air.

01:16:21.000 --> 01:16:24.180
Queen Snowfall said only dragons inside

01:16:24.180 --> 01:16:25.920
the invisibility bubble can hear one

01:16:25.920 --> 01:16:26.100
another.

01:16:26.220 --> 01:16:29.520
But should we make a plan before we go

01:16:29.520 --> 01:16:30.180
charging in?

01:16:30.239 --> 01:16:32.399
Cricket said anxiously.

01:16:32.460 --> 01:16:35.760
There's no time for a plan, Luna cried.

01:16:35.819 --> 01:16:39.180
We have to fly over there and and

01:16:39.180 --> 01:16:41.460
invisibly smack all the hive wings in the

01:16:41.460 --> 01:16:41.640
head.

01:16:41.699 --> 01:16:44.819
Yes, Sundu agreed.

01:16:44.880 --> 01:16:46.859
Push them into the ocean, drop some

01:16:46.859 --> 01:16:48.060
sharks on them.

01:16:48.119 --> 01:16:51.300
Say pineapple and Kibli and tsunami, Luna

01:16:51.300 --> 01:16:51.659
added.

01:16:51.720 --> 01:16:54.779
And feed all the hive wings to fire

01:16:54.779 --> 01:16:55.739
ants.

01:16:55.800 --> 01:16:56.880
Sundoo yelled.

01:16:57.000 --> 01:16:58.920
Wait, wait, no.

01:16:58.979 --> 01:17:00.000
Cricket said.

01:17:00.060 --> 01:17:02.939
There was a whoosh of wind past Luna's

01:17:02.939 --> 01:17:04.979
scales, and then Sundu's voice called

01:17:04.979 --> 01:17:07.260
You'd better all be right behind me.

01:17:07.380 --> 01:17:09.119
But they're not.

01:17:09.180 --> 01:17:12.300
Everyone see that palm tree on the south

01:17:12.300 --> 01:17:12.960
end of the island.

01:17:13.079 --> 01:17:15.720
Lang shouted. her voice drowning out

01:17:15.720 --> 01:17:16.199
crickets.

01:17:16.260 --> 01:17:18.359
Regroup there if we get separated.

01:17:18.359 --> 01:17:21.119
Luna thought she could hear the human

01:17:21.119 --> 01:17:23.699
yippering something at sky, but then she

01:17:23.699 --> 01:17:24.899
and Links were flying fast.

01:17:24.960 --> 01:17:28.020
Wing beats in sync, and she lost track of

01:17:28.020 --> 01:17:28.619
where the others were.

01:17:28.739 --> 01:17:31.619
The only one she was sure of was links.

01:17:31.680 --> 01:17:34.319
Her strange ridged claws holding tight.

01:17:34.380 --> 01:17:37.079
Don't let go, Luna thought.

01:17:37.140 --> 01:17:38.939
Don't leave me alone up here.

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:42.359
The island was about as wide as cicada

01:17:42.359 --> 01:17:45.420
hive, and maybe twice as long, curved

01:17:45.420 --> 01:17:47.760
like a dragon tail, with a pair of huge

01:17:47.760 --> 01:17:49.680
boulders off the shore on the north end.

01:17:49.739 --> 01:17:52.439
The beach facing them rose quickly into a

01:17:52.439 --> 01:17:54.779
tangle of trees and cliff, blocking the

01:17:54.779 --> 01:17:55.979
view of the other side of the island.

01:17:56.100 --> 01:18:00.359
Lynx gasped softly, tightening her grip

01:18:00.359 --> 01:18:01.979
on Luna as they flew close enough to see

01:18:01.979 --> 01:18:03.479
the dragons battling on the beach.

01:18:03.539 --> 01:18:07.560
Hive wings swarmed across the white sand

01:18:07.560 --> 01:18:09.600
teeth and stingers flashing.

01:18:09.659 --> 01:18:13.020
There had to be at least 20 of them, giant

01:18:13.020 --> 01:18:15.180
and deadly as a horde of murder hornets.

01:18:15.239 --> 01:18:18.539
Luna's mind took an instinctive mental

01:18:18.539 --> 01:18:19.380
picture of the scene.

01:18:19.439 --> 01:18:21.600
Even though she knew she would never

01:18:21.600 --> 01:18:24.119
never, want to weave a tapestry this

01:18:24.119 --> 01:18:26.880
frightening. 20 hive wings.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:28.680
What are they doing all the way out

01:18:28.680 --> 01:18:28.859
here?

01:18:28.920 --> 01:18:32.100
Queen Wasp must have sent them to follow

01:18:32.100 --> 01:18:34.619
the escaping leaf wings, she said aloud.

01:18:34.680 --> 01:18:37.380
That means she could be inside all those

01:18:37.380 --> 01:18:38.159
dragons right now.

01:18:38.220 --> 01:18:40.739
Cricket's voice said hopelessly from

01:18:40.739 --> 01:18:41.159
above her.

01:18:41.220 --> 01:18:44.760
Tsunami's blue scales were easy to spot

01:18:44.760 --> 01:18:46.619
in the crowd, where the fighting was

01:18:46.619 --> 01:18:47.100
thickest.

01:18:47.159 --> 01:18:50.159
She roared and spun, slashing at the hive

01:18:50.159 --> 01:18:52.260
wings around her, and smacking others in

01:18:52.260 --> 01:18:53.460
the head with her powerful tail.

01:18:53.520 --> 01:18:56.880
Close to her, Kibli was surrounded by 5

01:18:56.880 --> 01:18:57.779
hive wings.

01:18:57.840 --> 01:19:01.079
His venomous tail was curved up, stabbing

01:19:01.079 --> 01:19:02.880
at his attackers as they darted in toward

01:19:02.880 --> 01:19:03.000
him.

01:19:03.060 --> 01:19:05.819
Luna saw him pull out one of the blow

01:19:05.819 --> 01:19:07.260
guns the rain wings had given them.

01:19:07.380 --> 01:19:10.199
But before he could aim it, a hive wing

01:19:10.199 --> 01:19:11.819
lunged at him and knocked it into the

01:19:11.819 --> 01:19:12.060
sand.

01:19:12.119 --> 01:19:15.000
They grappled, with their front claws

01:19:15.000 --> 01:19:17.220
locked, their teeth snapping at the air

01:19:17.220 --> 01:19:20.220
between them, both tails fainting jabs at

01:19:20.220 --> 01:19:20.520
the other.

01:19:20.579 --> 01:19:23.640
But someone had managed to use the

01:19:23.640 --> 01:19:24.300
blowguns.

01:19:24.359 --> 01:19:27.300
One hive wing was lying on the beach, eyes

01:19:27.300 --> 01:19:30.060
closed, with a dart in his neck, another

01:19:30.060 --> 01:19:32.880
one, near tsunami, suddenly clapped one

01:19:32.880 --> 01:19:35.159
tail into his cheek, staggered back, and

01:19:35.159 --> 01:19:35.640
collapsed.

01:19:35.760 --> 01:19:39.119
Luna squeezed Lynx's claws.

01:19:39.239 --> 01:19:42.300
I think pineapple did that, she cried.

01:19:42.359 --> 01:19:45.359
She'd never seen a rain wings camouflage

01:19:45.359 --> 01:19:46.260
power in action before.

01:19:46.319 --> 01:19:48.720
It was much more impressive than she'd

01:19:48.720 --> 01:19:48.960
expected.

01:19:49.020 --> 01:19:51.960
She couldn't see pineapple anywhere, but

01:19:51.960 --> 01:19:54.420
a moment later, a 3rd hive wing stumbled

01:19:54.420 --> 01:19:54.779
and went down.

01:19:54.840 --> 01:19:57.119
Do we attack?

01:19:57.180 --> 01:19:58.319
Links called.

01:19:58.380 --> 01:19:59.579
Sundo?

01:19:59.640 --> 01:20:00.239
Orders?

01:20:00.359 --> 01:20:02.819
First Priority is keeping Sky and Ren

01:20:02.819 --> 01:20:03.359
safe.

01:20:03.420 --> 01:20:04.439
Sundu answered.

01:20:04.500 --> 01:20:05.760
Skye, where are you?

01:20:05.880 --> 01:20:08.100
There was no response.

01:20:08.159 --> 01:20:11.699
Luna looked around, her heart racing, even

01:20:11.699 --> 01:20:12.779
though she knew she wouldn't see

01:20:12.779 --> 01:20:13.020
anything.

01:20:13.079 --> 01:20:16.619
Sky, Sundew shouted again.

01:20:16.680 --> 01:20:18.359
Come on, you twig brain?

01:20:18.420 --> 01:20:18.960
Where are you?

01:20:19.020 --> 01:20:23.279
Skye, if you can hear us, go hide.

01:20:23.340 --> 01:20:24.479
Link shouted.

01:20:24.539 --> 01:20:27.779
Luna could hear Sundu muttering curses

01:20:27.779 --> 01:20:30.060
but no sound from Sky or Wren.

01:20:30.119 --> 01:20:31.979
Had they lost them so quickly?

01:20:32.039 --> 01:20:35.699
What happens to the rest of the plan if

01:20:35.699 --> 01:20:36.659
we lose our little human?

01:20:36.779 --> 01:20:39.840
How will we find the abyss without her to

01:20:39.840 --> 01:20:41.579
help us talk to the Pentalon humans?

01:20:41.640 --> 01:20:45.359
Sandu, can't you make tsunami and Kibli

01:20:45.359 --> 01:20:45.899
invisible now?

01:20:45.960 --> 01:20:47.039
Cricket asked.

01:20:47.100 --> 01:20:50.579
I'd have to make us visible first, Sundu

01:20:50.579 --> 01:20:50.880
said.

01:20:50.939 --> 01:20:52.800
And I don't want the hive wings to know

01:20:52.800 --> 01:20:53.159
we're here.

01:20:53.220 --> 01:20:56.340
We can't risk them seeing Skye and Ren, or

01:20:56.340 --> 01:20:58.020
catching the rest of us and leaving those

01:20:58.020 --> 01:20:58.380
2 alone.

01:20:58.439 --> 01:21:00.720
Below them.

01:21:00.779 --> 01:21:03.359
A sudden burst of flame flared along the

01:21:03.359 --> 01:21:05.520
tail of the hive wing in Kibley's claws.

01:21:05.579 --> 01:21:08.220
The red and black dragon shrieked and

01:21:08.220 --> 01:21:10.619
flung herself away from him, rolling and

01:21:10.619 --> 01:21:11.880
rolling in the sand to put it out.

01:21:11.939 --> 01:21:14.159
Where did that come from?

01:21:14.220 --> 01:21:15.300
Moon?

01:21:15.420 --> 01:21:16.619
Luna wondered.

01:21:16.680 --> 01:21:17.939
Or bullfrog.

01:21:18.060 --> 01:21:20.520
Nightwings and Mudwings could both

01:21:20.520 --> 01:21:21.180
breathe fire.

01:21:21.239 --> 01:21:23.279
Maybe they were already down there

01:21:23.279 --> 01:21:24.659
fighting invisibly.

01:21:24.720 --> 01:21:26.699
I have fire too.

01:21:26.760 --> 01:21:30.300
She flexed her free claws, feeling the

01:21:30.300 --> 01:21:32.100
heat of the flame soak in her wrists.

01:21:32.159 --> 01:21:33.539
Should I use it?

01:21:33.600 --> 01:21:35.399
This is my chance, right?

01:21:35.460 --> 01:21:37.560
To use the weapon I was given?

01:21:37.619 --> 01:21:39.060
But.

01:21:39.899 --> 01:21:42.539
Can I really set other dragons on fire?

01:21:42.600 --> 01:21:45.899
During one of those long days of waiting

01:21:45.899 --> 01:21:47.819
on the beach in the distant kingdoms

01:21:47.819 --> 01:21:49.859
while Luna was practicing making

01:21:49.859 --> 01:21:51.600
different kinds of flame silk.

01:21:51.659 --> 01:21:54.000
Jerboa had touched one of the fiery

01:21:54.000 --> 01:21:56.220
threads, not realizing that it would burn

01:21:56.220 --> 01:21:56.460
her.

01:21:56.520 --> 01:21:59.579
She'd pretended that it didn't hurt very

01:21:59.579 --> 01:22:01.920
much, but Luna had felt guilty about it

01:22:01.920 --> 01:22:02.760
for days.

01:22:02.939 --> 01:22:05.520
She still felt haunted by the angry red

01:22:05.520 --> 01:22:07.020
mark on Jerboa's claw.

01:22:07.079 --> 01:22:10.140
I could throw ropes of fire at the hive

01:22:10.140 --> 01:22:10.560
wings.

01:22:10.619 --> 01:22:12.840
But what if I hit one of the invisible

01:22:12.840 --> 01:22:13.319
dragons?

01:22:13.380 --> 01:22:15.479
What if I hurt one of my friends?

01:22:15.539 --> 01:22:18.960
The other hive wings around Kibley were

01:22:18.960 --> 01:22:21.479
turning, shouting, searching the dunes

01:22:21.479 --> 01:22:22.619
for the source of the flames.

01:22:22.680 --> 01:22:26.159
Kibble bolted away from them, and threw

01:22:26.159 --> 01:22:28.199
himself at an orange speckled hive wing

01:22:28.199 --> 01:22:30.300
who was circling around behind tsunami.

01:22:30.359 --> 01:22:32.939
They slammed into a pile of seaweed and

01:22:32.939 --> 01:22:35.460
skidded sideways, clawing and roaring at

01:22:35.460 --> 01:22:35.699
each other.

01:22:35.760 --> 01:22:39.539
Bullfrog, get that dragon off Kibley

01:22:39.539 --> 01:22:40.560
Sundoo yelled.

01:22:40.619 --> 01:22:43.260
Lynx, get out your blowgun and hit as

01:22:43.260 --> 01:22:43.920
many as you can.

01:22:43.979 --> 01:22:45.420
I'll help tsunami.

01:22:45.479 --> 01:22:47.100
What about me?

01:22:47.220 --> 01:22:48.420
Luna asked.

01:22:48.479 --> 01:22:50.760
But her question was lost in a rush of

01:22:50.760 --> 01:22:51.420
wing beats.

01:22:51.539 --> 01:22:54.000
Links squeezed her talon and let go.

01:22:54.060 --> 01:22:57.659
Luna felt momentarily dizzy, untethered

01:22:57.659 --> 01:22:57.960
in the sky.

01:22:58.020 --> 01:23:01.199
I think Sundew still doesn't quite

01:23:01.199 --> 01:23:03.119
believe that silk wings and hive wings

01:23:03.119 --> 01:23:03.600
can be helpful.

01:23:03.659 --> 01:23:06.420
Cricket said quietly, from somewhere

01:23:06.420 --> 01:23:06.960
nearby.

01:23:07.020 --> 01:23:11.640
I can be, though, Luna protested, holding

01:23:11.640 --> 01:23:13.500
up her glowing wrists before she

01:23:13.500 --> 01:23:14.939
remembered that no one could see them.

01:23:15.000 --> 01:23:18.000
I could set a high wing on fire.

01:23:18.060 --> 01:23:21.600
I could. she added, although Cricket

01:23:21.600 --> 01:23:22.560
hadn't disagreed with her.

01:23:22.680 --> 01:23:25.859
Could you hurt another dragon like that?

01:23:25.920 --> 01:23:28.560
Blue's voice whispered in her head.

01:23:28.619 --> 01:23:32.939
But don't kill them, Cricket said, her

01:23:32.939 --> 01:23:34.020
voice rising with alarm.

01:23:34.079 --> 01:23:36.119
Remember, they're being controlled.

01:23:36.180 --> 01:23:37.439
This isn't their choice.

01:23:37.500 --> 01:23:40.680
That was a pretty hard thought to keep in

01:23:40.680 --> 01:23:43.680
mind as 2 hive wings slashed at tsunami's

01:23:43.680 --> 01:23:45.960
wings, one of them drawing blood, and

01:23:45.960 --> 01:23:47.399
another one jabbed his spear into

01:23:47.399 --> 01:23:48.239
Kibble's tail.

01:23:48.300 --> 01:23:51.479
Luna swooped lower, trying to find a good

01:23:51.479 --> 01:23:53.819
angle, trying to work up the courage to

01:23:53.819 --> 01:23:54.539
throw her silk.

01:23:54.600 --> 01:23:57.479
She was terrified of hitting tsunami, or

01:23:57.479 --> 01:23:58.319
Kibli too.

01:23:58.380 --> 01:24:00.420
They moved so fast as they fought.

01:24:00.479 --> 01:24:04.079
She also remembered the last time she'd

01:24:04.079 --> 01:24:05.939
tried to use her flame silk to fight hive

01:24:05.939 --> 01:24:06.300
wings.

01:24:06.359 --> 01:24:09.659
It had spiraled out of her control, caught

01:24:09.659 --> 01:24:11.579
a storm, and ended up carrying her all

01:24:11.579 --> 01:24:12.720
the way to Pyria.

01:24:12.779 --> 01:24:14.699
What if it happens again?

01:24:14.760 --> 01:24:17.699
What if I get blown away while I'm

01:24:17.699 --> 01:24:19.680
invisible and can't find my way back to

01:24:19.680 --> 01:24:19.979
everyone?

01:24:20.039 --> 01:24:24.060
She hesitated, pulling her front talons

01:24:24.060 --> 01:24:25.140
in close to her chest.

01:24:25.199 --> 01:24:28.199
The high wing on top of Kibley suddenly

01:24:28.199 --> 01:24:30.359
lurched sideways, as if something had

01:24:30.359 --> 01:24:31.319
rammed into his side.

01:24:31.380 --> 01:24:34.079
He yelled and slashed upward with his

01:24:34.079 --> 01:24:36.899
claws, and Luna saw blood droplets spray

01:24:36.899 --> 01:24:37.800
out from the empty air.

01:24:37.859 --> 01:24:41.039
Flames from nowhere engulfed the hive

01:24:41.039 --> 01:24:43.560
wing's tail, and he staggered, screaming

01:24:43.560 --> 01:24:44.399
into the sea.

01:24:44.460 --> 01:24:48.119
Kibley was up again, running back into

01:24:48.119 --> 01:24:49.979
the crowd of dragons around tsunami

01:24:49.979 --> 01:24:51.659
breathing his own fire now.

01:24:51.899 --> 01:24:54.659
As he ran, the seaweed underfoot began to

01:24:54.659 --> 01:24:56.520
slither around the hive wing's claws.

01:24:56.640 --> 01:24:59.819
Luna saw one yellow and black dragon trip

01:24:59.819 --> 01:25:01.500
and slam heavily into the sand.

01:25:01.560 --> 01:25:04.079
Another pair found themselves wound

01:25:04.079 --> 01:25:06.960
together, with long wet strands, and

01:25:06.960 --> 01:25:08.460
began shoving each other furiously.

01:25:08.520 --> 01:25:12.539
At the same time, Luna saw another hive

01:25:12.539 --> 01:25:14.699
wing yelp and fall sideways into the

01:25:14.699 --> 01:25:16.680
waves beside him, clutching his neck.

01:25:16.739 --> 01:25:20.399
Maybe we do have a chance, she thought

01:25:20.399 --> 01:25:21.840
with a rush of surprise.

01:25:21.899 --> 01:25:25.020
She landed on a tall boulder and looked

01:25:25.020 --> 01:25:26.699
down at the strange battle that covered

01:25:26.699 --> 01:25:26.939
the beach.

01:25:27.000 --> 01:25:30.359
Maybe we can win without even using my

01:25:30.359 --> 01:25:30.960
flame silk.

01:25:31.020 --> 01:25:32.760
Maybe I don't have to do anything.

01:25:32.819 --> 01:25:36.479
I mean, we have 3 dragons who can breathe

01:25:36.479 --> 01:25:36.779
fire.

01:25:36.840 --> 01:25:40.079
Sundu and her leaf speak, invisibility

01:25:40.079 --> 01:25:43.199
the tranquilizer darts, and a dragon who

01:25:43.199 --> 01:25:43.739
can see the future.

01:25:43.800 --> 01:25:47.760
Although, snakes and silkworms, moon, why

01:25:47.760 --> 01:25:49.500
didn't you see this coming?

01:25:49.619 --> 01:25:52.739
Maybe these kind, funny dragons can fight

01:25:52.739 --> 01:25:54.180
a bunch of scary hive wings.

01:25:54.239 --> 01:25:57.539
Something rustled in the trees above the

01:25:57.539 --> 01:26:00.239
beach, and a new dragon came gliding onto

01:26:00.239 --> 01:26:01.020
the sand.

01:26:01.079 --> 01:26:04.140
His talons touched down lightly, and he

01:26:04.140 --> 01:26:04.920
narrowed his eyes.

01:26:04.979 --> 01:26:08.039
There's another dragon here.

01:26:08.100 --> 01:26:09.659
He hissed.

01:26:09.720 --> 01:26:12.539
One we cannot see, possibly more.

01:26:12.659 --> 01:26:15.720
Luna's heart nearly stopped.

01:26:15.779 --> 01:26:19.140
The new dragon's wings were gold, dappled

01:26:19.140 --> 01:26:21.720
with lavender and gray, and long pale

01:26:21.720 --> 01:26:23.699
purple antennae were slowly unfurling

01:26:23.699 --> 01:26:24.119
from his head.

01:26:24.180 --> 01:26:26.460
That wasn't a hive wing.

01:26:26.520 --> 01:26:29.399
That was a silkwing, looking all peaceful

01:26:29.399 --> 01:26:31.979
and harmless, while Queen Wasp's voice

01:26:31.979 --> 01:26:33.600
slithered malevolently from his mouth.

01:26:33.659 --> 01:26:36.899
A shudder ran down Luna's spine.

01:26:36.960 --> 01:26:39.659
Sundew and Cricket had said that Wasp

01:26:39.659 --> 01:26:42.239
could control Silkwings now, but Luna had

01:26:42.239 --> 01:26:43.260
never seen it herself.

01:26:43.319 --> 01:26:45.420
She hadn't quite believed it until that

01:26:45.420 --> 01:26:45.720
moment.

01:26:45.779 --> 01:26:49.439
The silk wing on the beach twisted his

01:26:49.439 --> 01:26:51.600
neck around, and then slowly back in the

01:26:51.600 --> 01:26:52.020
other direction.

01:26:52.140 --> 01:26:54.420
What's he doing?

01:26:54.479 --> 01:26:56.520
Cricket whispered from the air above

01:26:56.520 --> 01:26:57.000
Luna.

01:26:57.060 --> 01:26:58.800
Why are his eyes closed?

01:26:58.920 --> 01:27:01.560
He's using his antennae.

01:27:01.619 --> 01:27:02.939
Luna realized.

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:05.220
They pick up movement and vibrations in

01:27:05.220 --> 01:27:05.460
the air.

01:27:05.579 --> 01:27:08.819
Like, from invisible dragons?

01:27:08.880 --> 01:27:10.560
Cricket said with alarm.

01:27:10.619 --> 01:27:14.220
Or camouflage to rain wings?

01:27:14.279 --> 01:27:16.619
Muna heard a small clattering sound.

01:27:16.680 --> 01:27:18.479
We have to stop him.

01:27:18.539 --> 01:27:21.539
Three moons, loading invisible darts into

01:27:21.539 --> 01:27:23.100
an invisible blowgun is impossible.

01:27:23.159 --> 01:27:24.359
Luna, help me.

01:27:24.420 --> 01:27:25.920
We have to knock out that silk wing.

01:27:26.039 --> 01:27:29.340
Luna fumbled for her own blowgun pouch

01:27:29.340 --> 01:27:31.439
but before she could get it out, the

01:27:31.439 --> 01:27:33.180
silkwing suddenly flew across the beach

01:27:33.180 --> 01:27:35.220
and launched himself at one of the sand

01:27:35.220 --> 01:27:37.079
dunes not far from her boulder.

01:27:37.140 --> 01:27:39.720
Two other hive wings spun and attacked

01:27:39.720 --> 01:27:41.039
the same spot in unison.

01:27:41.100 --> 01:27:44.819
They all moved in the creepy, synchronized

01:27:44.819 --> 01:27:46.560
way Cricket had told Luna about.

01:27:46.619 --> 01:27:49.079
But it was so much more horrifying to see

01:27:49.079 --> 01:27:49.800
it with her own eyes.

01:27:49.859 --> 01:27:52.380
They didn't seem like dragons anymore.

01:27:52.439 --> 01:27:55.260
They looked like knives that someone else

01:27:55.260 --> 01:27:56.340
was slashing through the air.

01:27:56.399 --> 01:28:00.060
There was a shriek beneath their claws

01:28:00.060 --> 01:28:01.680
and a bright green dragon with white

01:28:01.680 --> 01:28:03.899
wings suddenly appeared on the sand.

01:28:03.960 --> 01:28:06.600
It took Luna a moment to realize that it

01:28:06.600 --> 01:28:07.319
was pineapple.

01:28:07.380 --> 01:28:09.420
She had never seen him in those colors

01:28:09.420 --> 01:28:09.840
before.

01:28:09.899 --> 01:28:12.420
Pineapple, she cried.

01:28:12.539 --> 01:28:14.520
He couldn't hear her.

01:28:14.579 --> 01:28:17.699
A moment later, one of the high wings

01:28:17.699 --> 01:28:19.560
smacked a rock into the side of the rain

01:28:19.560 --> 01:28:20.220
wings head.

01:28:20.279 --> 01:28:22.140
Pineapple went limp.

01:28:22.199 --> 01:28:25.020
His white spotted wings splayed awkwardly

01:28:25.020 --> 01:28:26.939
under the talons of his attackers.

01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:29.100
Bloody claw marks were scored along his

01:28:29.100 --> 01:28:29.699
underbelly.

01:28:29.760 --> 01:28:32.279
But she could see his chest still rising

01:28:32.279 --> 01:28:32.699
and falling.

01:28:32.760 --> 01:28:34.739
What do we do?

01:28:34.800 --> 01:28:36.000
How do we rescue him?

01:28:36.060 --> 01:28:40.800
There's someone else we can't see, said

01:28:40.800 --> 01:28:44.100
the Silkwing, lifting his head again, one

01:28:44.100 --> 01:28:44.939
with fire.

01:28:45.060 --> 01:28:49.739
He paused, and then smiled, a slow

01:28:49.739 --> 01:28:50.579
malevolent smile.

01:28:50.699 --> 01:28:54.300
A lost flame silk, perhaps.

01:28:54.420 --> 01:28:57.539
Luna.

01:28:57.659 --> 01:28:58.979
Little flame silk.

01:28:59.039 --> 01:29:00.180
Are you here?

01:29:00.239 --> 01:29:04.920
Luna felt a sick yawning pit open up in

01:29:04.920 --> 01:29:05.460
her stomach.

01:29:05.520 --> 01:29:08.640
It was bone chilling to think that Wasp

01:29:08.640 --> 01:29:09.300
knew her name.

01:29:09.359 --> 01:29:12.180
To know that Wasp had spent time thinking

01:29:12.180 --> 01:29:13.020
about her at all.

01:29:13.079 --> 01:29:15.000
Even though she was invisible.

01:29:15.060 --> 01:29:17.819
Luna felt as though Wasp was glaring

01:29:17.819 --> 01:29:20.039
straight at her through the Silk Wings

01:29:20.039 --> 01:29:21.119
maggot white eyes.

01:29:21.180 --> 01:29:23.520
Everyone freeze.

01:29:23.579 --> 01:29:26.220
Sundew shouted, from somewhere along the

01:29:26.220 --> 01:29:26.460
beach.

01:29:26.520 --> 01:29:29.159
Cricket says that Silkwings can sense

01:29:29.159 --> 01:29:29.640
movement.

01:29:29.699 --> 01:29:30.960
Don't let him find you.

01:29:31.020 --> 01:29:34.079
Luna didn't need to be told twice.

01:29:34.140 --> 01:29:36.659
She wasn't sure she could move anyway.

01:29:36.720 --> 01:29:39.899
She kept her wings tight to her body

01:29:39.899 --> 01:29:42.300
claws gripping the rock, hardly daring to

01:29:42.300 --> 01:29:42.659
breathe.

01:29:42.720 --> 01:29:45.840
The silk wing took a step toward her

01:29:45.840 --> 01:29:47.579
Antenny twitching.

01:29:47.640 --> 01:29:50.579
Beyond him, Kibley was sinking under the

01:29:50.579 --> 01:29:53.340
attack of 3 hive wings, and Luna couldn't

01:29:53.340 --> 01:29:55.439
even see tsunami in the wave of dragons

01:29:55.439 --> 01:29:55.800
around her.

01:29:55.859 --> 01:29:57.779
Another step.

01:29:57.899 --> 01:30:01.079
Luna's eyes were riveted on the enemy's

01:30:01.079 --> 01:30:03.899
antenna as they tested the air. pivoting

01:30:03.899 --> 01:30:06.899
slowly in her direction, like mesmerizing

01:30:06.899 --> 01:30:07.560
cobras.

01:30:07.619 --> 01:30:10.619
He was going to find her.

01:30:10.680 --> 01:30:13.979
Wasp was going to catch her and take her

01:30:13.979 --> 01:30:16.500
mind and control her like these brain

01:30:16.500 --> 01:30:17.520
washed dragons.

01:30:17.579 --> 01:30:20.220
And Luna would end up as an empty shell

01:30:20.220 --> 01:30:22.739
spitting flame soak for a monster for the

01:30:22.739 --> 01:30:23.279
rest of her life.

01:30:23.399 --> 01:30:27.180
A blast of fire suddenly hit the silk

01:30:27.180 --> 01:30:29.880
wings left side, or almost did.

01:30:29.939 --> 01:30:32.279
He whipped out of the way at the last

01:30:32.279 --> 01:30:35.819
moment, and in one liquid motion, whirled

01:30:35.819 --> 01:30:38.220
and pounced on a spot of empty air, that

01:30:38.220 --> 01:30:39.479
was not so empty after all.

01:30:39.539 --> 01:30:43.979
Here, the silk wing commanded, and 10

01:30:43.979 --> 01:30:45.479
hive wings descended at once.

01:30:45.539 --> 01:30:48.659
Luna pressed her claws to her face to

01:30:48.659 --> 01:30:49.920
stop herself from screaming.

01:30:49.979 --> 01:30:52.560
Silvery threads were pouring from the

01:30:52.560 --> 01:30:54.899
silk wing's wrists, winding around the

01:30:54.899 --> 01:30:57.659
empty air in the unmistakable shape of a

01:30:57.659 --> 01:30:58.439
struggling dragon.

01:30:58.500 --> 01:31:02.039
Flames burst from the invisible dragon

01:31:02.039 --> 01:31:04.380
searing the closest threads to ash.

01:31:04.439 --> 01:31:06.960
But if they set all the silk on fire

01:31:06.960 --> 01:31:09.479
it'll burn their scales too, Luna

01:31:09.479 --> 01:31:09.779
thought.

01:31:09.840 --> 01:31:10.859
Can I?

01:31:11.460 --> 01:31:14.279
If I burn the silk wing, I have to use my

01:31:14.279 --> 01:31:15.539
flame silk to stop him.

01:31:15.960 --> 01:31:18.060
But it was all happening so fast.

01:31:18.119 --> 01:31:22.140
One of the hive wings stepped forward, and

01:31:22.140 --> 01:31:24.180
long black stingers slid from under her

01:31:24.180 --> 01:31:24.539
claws.

01:31:24.659 --> 01:31:27.239
She stabbed them into the air where the

01:31:27.239 --> 01:31:28.319
dragon's neck should be.

01:31:28.380 --> 01:31:31.560
The silvery threads sagged and went

01:31:31.560 --> 01:31:31.800
still.

01:31:31.859 --> 01:31:35.460
With a grim smile, the silkwings spun

01:31:35.460 --> 01:31:38.039
more and more silk, until the invisible

01:31:38.039 --> 01:31:40.079
unconscious dragon was wound up like a

01:31:40.079 --> 01:31:41.100
spider's lunch.

01:31:41.159 --> 01:31:44.819
And from the size and the fire, now Luna

01:31:44.819 --> 01:31:45.659
could guess who it was.

01:31:45.720 --> 01:31:48.420
The hive wings had captured Moon.

01:31:48.539 --> 01:31:52.680
Chapter 4.

01:31:52.979 --> 01:31:56.939
We can still beat them, Luna thought

01:31:56.939 --> 01:31:57.539
desperately.

01:31:57.600 --> 01:31:58.619
It's not over.

01:31:58.680 --> 01:32:02.159
But when she looked along the beach, She

01:32:02.159 --> 01:32:04.079
saw that tsunami lay unconscious on the

01:32:04.079 --> 01:32:04.319
sand.

01:32:04.380 --> 01:32:07.439
Another hive wing with long claw stingers

01:32:07.439 --> 01:32:10.680
stood over her, toxin, and blue sea wing

01:32:10.680 --> 01:32:12.239
blood dripping from the sharp points.

01:32:12.300 --> 01:32:16.439
Behind them, 5 hive wings had finally

01:32:16.439 --> 01:32:18.119
managed to ping Kibley down.

01:32:18.180 --> 01:32:21.300
He thrashed furiously, but even his tail

01:32:21.300 --> 01:32:22.979
was trapped under heavy red talons.

01:32:23.039 --> 01:32:26.279
The hive wing who had paralyzed tsunami

01:32:26.279 --> 01:32:28.859
stepped over, and sank her stingers into

01:32:28.859 --> 01:32:29.460
his neck as well.

01:32:29.520 --> 01:32:31.380
Barely a moment later.

01:32:31.439 --> 01:32:32.760
He was still.

01:32:32.880 --> 01:32:34.680
Sundew.

01:32:34.739 --> 01:32:37.260
Lynx's voice said from somewhere near

01:32:37.260 --> 01:32:37.979
Kibley.

01:32:38.039 --> 01:32:40.920
Sandu answered.

01:32:40.979 --> 01:32:43.560
As the Silkwings head snapped up.

01:32:43.619 --> 01:32:45.779
The antenna quivering suspiciously.

01:32:45.840 --> 01:32:48.960
Silence fell over the beach.

01:32:49.020 --> 01:32:52.439
All the hive wings seemed to be frozen in

01:32:52.439 --> 01:32:55.739
place, forced motionless by the queen in

01:32:55.739 --> 01:32:56.039
their heads.

01:32:56.100 --> 01:32:58.500
Only the silkwing moved.

01:32:58.619 --> 01:33:01.020
Stepping carefully around the fallen

01:33:01.020 --> 01:33:03.899
dragons, avoiding the seaweed, and

01:33:03.899 --> 01:33:05.699
studying the talon prints in the sand.

01:33:05.760 --> 01:33:07.680
To Luna.

01:33:07.739 --> 01:33:09.779
He seemed like a hollow shell of a

01:33:09.779 --> 01:33:10.199
dragon.

01:33:10.260 --> 01:33:12.899
Nothing but a weapon for Queen Wasp to

01:33:12.899 --> 01:33:13.500
use against them.

01:33:13.560 --> 01:33:15.899
Who was he before?

01:33:15.960 --> 01:33:18.420
Which hive did he live in?

01:33:18.479 --> 01:33:20.520
Was he in the chrysalis?

01:33:20.579 --> 01:33:22.979
Does he know what's happening to him

01:33:22.979 --> 01:33:23.220
now?

01:33:23.279 --> 01:33:27.000
What kind of dragons are these?

01:33:27.060 --> 01:33:29.340
The silk wing hissed.

01:33:29.399 --> 01:33:32.880
He walked slowly around tsunami and Kibli

01:33:32.880 --> 01:33:35.340
pausing to study Kibli's tale with an

01:33:35.340 --> 01:33:36.600
expression Luna couldn't read.

01:33:36.659 --> 01:33:40.079
I remember dragons like this.

01:33:40.199 --> 01:33:43.500
He murmured, in a voice that suddenly

01:33:43.500 --> 01:33:44.760
wasn't wasps anymore.

01:33:44.819 --> 01:33:46.800
It didn't seem like his own, though.

01:33:46.859 --> 01:33:49.859
His movement seemed even weirder and more

01:33:49.859 --> 01:33:52.560
unnatural, as though Dragon Wings didn't

01:33:52.560 --> 01:33:53.520
fit quite right on him.

01:33:53.579 --> 01:33:56.340
His head pivoted to glare at pineapple.

01:33:56.399 --> 01:34:01.020
And those, he spat, the ones that change

01:34:01.020 --> 01:34:02.819
color, I remember those.

01:34:02.939 --> 01:34:06.060
He lifted one of his claws to tap the

01:34:06.060 --> 01:34:08.340
side of his snout, then shifted his

01:34:08.340 --> 01:34:09.779
narrow gaze to the moon bundle.

01:34:09.899 --> 01:34:13.199
I don't recall invisible dragons who

01:34:13.199 --> 01:34:15.000
stayed invisible when unconscious

01:34:15.000 --> 01:34:15.119
though.

01:34:15.239 --> 01:34:18.420
Will I be able to control them?

01:34:18.539 --> 01:34:20.760
Wasp's voice demanded.

01:34:20.819 --> 01:34:23.279
Will the breath of evil work on them?

01:34:23.340 --> 01:34:27.060
She paused, and then the Silkwing hissed

01:34:27.060 --> 01:34:27.600
softly.

01:34:27.659 --> 01:34:30.539
There's one way to find out.

01:34:30.600 --> 01:34:33.239
He murmured, in the other voice.

01:34:33.300 --> 01:34:36.600
A soft moan came from one of the

01:34:36.600 --> 01:34:37.739
collapsed dragons.

01:34:37.800 --> 01:34:40.680
Red and black scales rippled as the hive

01:34:40.680 --> 01:34:43.260
wing tried to sit up, shivering with pain

01:34:43.260 --> 01:34:44.340
from the burns on her tail.

01:34:44.460 --> 01:34:46.979
Luna guessed she was the one who'd been

01:34:46.979 --> 01:34:47.699
fighting Kibley.

01:34:47.760 --> 01:34:50.939
The hive wing pressed her front talons to

01:34:50.939 --> 01:34:51.840
her forehead for a long moment.

01:34:51.899 --> 01:34:54.899
Then she glanced at the dark scorch marks

01:34:54.899 --> 01:34:56.100
across her tail and winced.

01:34:56.220 --> 01:34:58.619
Where are we?

01:34:58.739 --> 01:35:01.199
She asked the soldier closest tour.

01:35:01.319 --> 01:35:04.199
He stared into the distance with those

01:35:04.199 --> 01:35:06.600
white marble eyes, unmoving and

01:35:06.600 --> 01:35:07.199
unresponsive.

01:35:07.319 --> 01:35:11.399
The hive wing scanned the beach, hive

01:35:11.399 --> 01:35:13.500
wing bodies lying half in and half out of

01:35:13.500 --> 01:35:15.659
the waves, or collapsed on the sand

01:35:15.659 --> 01:35:18.600
others standing frozen, at attention.

01:35:18.659 --> 01:35:21.060
Three unconscious prisoners who looked

01:35:21.060 --> 01:35:22.979
nothing like any Pentalon dragon.

01:35:23.039 --> 01:35:26.279
One mystery dragon shaped bundle of silk

01:35:26.279 --> 01:35:29.640
and the ominous silk wing, still stalking

01:35:29.640 --> 01:35:30.840
around the sand and muttering to

01:35:30.840 --> 01:35:31.140
himself.

01:35:31.199 --> 01:35:35.159
And the island itself, so vastly

01:35:35.159 --> 01:35:36.659
different from the hives or the

01:35:36.659 --> 01:35:37.260
savannah.

01:35:37.319 --> 01:35:40.140
The hive wing blinked, bewildered.

01:35:40.199 --> 01:35:43.500
Luna wondered how long these hive wings

01:35:43.500 --> 01:35:46.140
had been under Wasp's mind control, and

01:35:46.140 --> 01:35:47.579
if they had any memory of what they'd

01:35:47.579 --> 01:35:48.000
done for her.

01:35:48.000 --> 01:35:51.060
She wondered why Wasp had released this

01:35:51.060 --> 01:35:53.039
one now, but not any of the others.

01:35:53.100 --> 01:35:56.039
Are we in the distant kingdoms?

01:35:56.100 --> 01:35:57.479
The hive wing asked.

01:35:57.539 --> 01:35:59.520
But once again, the soldier did not

01:35:59.520 --> 01:36:00.060
respond.

01:36:00.119 --> 01:36:03.539
The silkwing, however, came gliding

01:36:03.539 --> 01:36:05.220
across the sand to loom over her.

01:36:05.279 --> 01:36:08.460
Were there any other dragons here?

01:36:08.520 --> 01:36:11.760
This old wing snapped, back in Wasp's

01:36:11.760 --> 01:36:11.880
voice.

01:36:12.000 --> 01:36:13.979
The high wing looked confused.

01:36:14.039 --> 01:36:16.380
And Luna thought, there was a flash of

01:36:16.380 --> 01:36:17.460
contempt on her face too.

01:36:17.520 --> 01:36:20.819
She's never had a silk wing talk to her

01:36:20.819 --> 01:36:21.119
like that.

01:36:21.180 --> 01:36:23.520
How would I know?

01:36:23.579 --> 01:36:24.720
the hive wing demanded.

01:36:24.840 --> 01:36:27.899
The Silkwing gazed coldly down at her.

01:36:27.960 --> 01:36:30.000
What is your name?

01:36:30.119 --> 01:36:32.100
Earwig?

01:36:32.159 --> 01:36:34.079
The high wing answered sullenly.

01:36:34.140 --> 01:36:35.640
Earwig.

01:36:35.699 --> 01:36:39.060
Ah, yes, of Setsy Hive.

01:36:39.119 --> 01:36:40.979
I'm inside your brothers now.

01:36:41.039 --> 01:36:43.319
I could have them kill each other so

01:36:43.319 --> 01:36:43.859
easily.

01:36:43.920 --> 01:36:46.619
Or perhaps this one could rip off the

01:36:46.619 --> 01:36:47.340
other's ears.

01:36:47.399 --> 01:36:49.140
That would be entertaining.

01:36:49.260 --> 01:36:51.600
Perhaps if you ever want to see them

01:36:51.600 --> 01:36:51.840
again.

01:36:51.899 --> 01:36:54.420
You could try addressing your queen with

01:36:54.420 --> 01:36:55.079
more respect.

01:36:55.140 --> 01:36:59.579
Earwig stared up at him, her wings slack

01:36:59.579 --> 01:37:00.300
with astonishment.

01:37:00.359 --> 01:37:04.619
Use your brain, hissed the silkwing.

01:37:04.680 --> 01:37:07.079
There were 2 dragons we could see and 2

01:37:07.079 --> 01:37:07.619
we could not.

01:37:07.680 --> 01:37:09.479
Did you sense any others?

01:37:09.539 --> 01:37:12.000
Luna held her breath.

01:37:12.060 --> 01:37:16.979
Nah, no, your majesty, earwig said.

01:37:17.039 --> 01:37:20.220
I mean, I wasn't really in myself.

01:37:20.279 --> 01:37:23.279
And there was a lot, um, happening.

01:37:23.340 --> 01:37:26.579
The silkwing made an impatient movement

01:37:26.579 --> 01:37:29.159
that scattered sand across earwigs burns

01:37:29.159 --> 01:37:30.300
and she winced again.

01:37:30.359 --> 01:37:33.600
But I don't think so, she added quickly.

01:37:33.659 --> 01:37:37.380
Did you notice any flame silk?

01:37:37.500 --> 01:37:39.239
The Silkwing demanded?

01:37:39.300 --> 01:37:42.479
An odd, brief struggle seemed to cross

01:37:42.479 --> 01:37:45.300
his face, and then, in the other voice he

01:37:45.300 --> 01:37:45.720
spat.

01:37:45.779 --> 01:37:48.600
Or any plants acting strangely?

01:37:48.659 --> 01:37:51.359
Plants acting strangely?

01:37:51.420 --> 01:37:54.840
Earwig blinked several times, and glanced

01:37:54.840 --> 01:37:55.979
at the palm trees up the beach.

01:37:56.039 --> 01:37:58.199
No?

01:37:58.380 --> 01:38:01.859
She didn't notice the seaweed.

01:38:01.920 --> 01:38:03.600
Luna thought with relief.

01:38:03.659 --> 01:38:06.359
Queen Wasp must have been so busy

01:38:06.359 --> 01:38:08.760
controlling the silk wing that she didn't

01:38:08.760 --> 01:38:09.359
notice it either.

01:38:09.420 --> 01:38:13.920
Or, There are 2 minds fighting inside the

01:38:13.920 --> 01:38:14.579
silkwing.

01:38:14.640 --> 01:38:17.460
And maybe even if Queen Wasp did notice.

01:38:17.520 --> 01:38:19.800
She's decided not to tell the other one

01:38:19.800 --> 01:38:20.819
for some reason.

01:38:20.880 --> 01:38:24.840
The silkwing peered up at the clouds, and

01:38:24.840 --> 01:38:26.939
then around at the sand, radiating

01:38:26.939 --> 01:38:27.479
suspicion.

01:38:27.600 --> 01:38:29.880
Sundew!

01:38:29.939 --> 01:38:31.199
He yelled suddenly.

01:38:31.260 --> 01:38:33.600
Sundew, are you here?

01:38:33.720 --> 01:38:35.399
Silence.

01:38:35.520 --> 01:38:38.399
The sun shone brightly in an empty blue

01:38:38.399 --> 01:38:38.699
sky.

01:38:38.819 --> 01:38:41.399
Luna could hear birds fluttering in the

01:38:41.399 --> 01:38:42.960
trees, but no dragons.

01:38:43.020 --> 01:38:45.779
Nothing but earwigs labored breathing.

01:38:45.840 --> 01:38:48.300
What if the others left?

01:38:48.420 --> 01:38:49.979
And I'm the only one still here.

01:38:50.039 --> 01:38:52.500
Her heart sped up.

01:38:52.560 --> 01:38:54.720
And she tried to think calmer thoughts

01:38:54.720 --> 01:38:57.600
but in the emptiness, it was hard to

01:38:57.600 --> 01:38:59.340
believe she hadn't been abandoned there

01:38:59.340 --> 01:39:02.159
alone on her rock, with enemies all

01:39:02.159 --> 01:39:02.579
around her.

01:39:02.640 --> 01:39:07.140
Sundew, the silkwing said.

01:39:07.260 --> 01:39:10.260
Almost charmingly, except that his face

01:39:10.260 --> 01:39:12.060
didn't even try to make an expression.

01:39:12.119 --> 01:39:14.279
We're not finished with each other.

01:39:14.340 --> 01:39:15.899
I know it.

01:39:15.960 --> 01:39:16.439
You know it.

01:39:16.500 --> 01:39:19.199
Why not come on out and face me.

01:39:19.260 --> 01:39:21.779
Another long pause.

01:39:21.840 --> 01:39:25.260
Don't you want to see your mother again?

01:39:25.319 --> 01:39:28.859
The silkwing taunted the empty air, he

01:39:28.859 --> 01:39:29.399
smirked.

01:39:29.460 --> 01:39:30.600
All right.

01:39:30.659 --> 01:39:31.920
Perhaps not her.

01:39:31.979 --> 01:39:32.819
I don't blame you.

01:39:32.880 --> 01:39:36.479
I'd chop that branch off too, if it was

01:39:36.479 --> 01:39:37.199
related to me.

01:39:37.260 --> 01:39:39.420
But what about your queen?

01:39:39.539 --> 01:39:42.420
Or that little blue silk wing you went to

01:39:42.420 --> 01:39:44.399
so much trouble to steal from me?

01:39:44.460 --> 01:39:46.979
Blue.

01:39:47.039 --> 01:39:48.420
Luna's heart thudded.

01:39:48.539 --> 01:39:50.039
Blue, blue.

01:39:50.159 --> 01:39:52.800
Blue, trapped in wasps' talons.

01:39:52.920 --> 01:39:56.520
The silk wing turned toward her, and Luna

01:39:56.520 --> 01:39:58.319
feared that she must have moved at the

01:39:58.319 --> 01:40:00.720
thought of blue, that a flinch, or

01:40:00.720 --> 01:40:02.220
indrawn breath had given her way.

01:40:02.279 --> 01:40:05.579
But it crossed to the silk bundle and

01:40:05.579 --> 01:40:06.840
prodded it, frowning.

01:40:06.899 --> 01:40:09.000
This isn't you?

01:40:09.060 --> 01:40:11.220
Leaf wings don't breathe fire.

01:40:11.340 --> 01:40:14.880
And that wasn't flame silk, so it's not

01:40:14.880 --> 01:40:15.779
my Luna either.

01:40:15.840 --> 01:40:19.380
But if they're not with Sundoo, why are

01:40:19.380 --> 01:40:20.760
these dragons here now?

01:40:20.760 --> 01:40:24.000
Earwig looked around at the other frozen

01:40:24.000 --> 01:40:24.600
soldiers.

01:40:24.659 --> 01:40:25.739
Then back at him.

01:40:25.800 --> 01:40:28.199
Ah, are you asking me?

01:40:28.260 --> 01:40:30.600
He gave her disgusted look.

01:40:30.659 --> 01:40:32.760
Do you know the answer?

01:40:32.819 --> 01:40:35.100
No, she said.

01:40:35.159 --> 01:40:36.600
I don't know anything.

01:40:36.659 --> 01:40:39.300
I don't know who Sundu is, or why we

01:40:39.300 --> 01:40:41.100
fought these mystery mutant dragons.

01:40:41.159 --> 01:40:42.720
I'm not even sure where we are.

01:40:42.779 --> 01:40:46.199
She tried to stand up, but a look of

01:40:46.199 --> 01:40:48.479
agony crossed her face as her tail moved

01:40:48.479 --> 01:40:50.340
and she collapsed to the sand again.

01:40:50.460 --> 01:40:53.520
The silkwing jabbed one of the

01:40:53.520 --> 01:40:55.260
unconscious hive wings in the face with

01:40:55.260 --> 01:40:55.920
his claw.

01:40:55.979 --> 01:40:58.920
When that got no reaction, he leaned down

01:40:58.920 --> 01:41:00.840
and sniffed the air around the dragon's

01:41:00.840 --> 01:41:04.079
snout, then squinted, until he spotted

01:41:04.079 --> 01:41:05.699
the tiny dart jutting out between their

01:41:05.699 --> 01:41:06.119
scales.

01:41:06.180 --> 01:41:11.699
Not dead then, said Wasp's voice.

01:41:11.760 --> 01:41:14.939
But utterly useless to me like this.

01:41:15.000 --> 01:41:17.100
The silk wings straightened.

01:41:17.220 --> 01:41:19.859
The rest of you will have to carry our

01:41:19.859 --> 01:41:22.140
prisoners back to Wasp Hive.

01:41:22.199 --> 01:41:24.119
All of them?

01:41:24.180 --> 01:41:25.439
Right now?

01:41:25.439 --> 01:41:27.119
Earwig asked.

01:41:27.180 --> 01:41:28.560
Shouldn't we rest?

01:41:28.619 --> 01:41:31.020
My wings feel like we've been flying for

01:41:31.020 --> 01:41:31.380
days.

01:41:31.439 --> 01:41:33.060
Is it a long way back?

01:41:33.119 --> 01:41:36.300
If they have to carry a whole dragon, even

01:41:36.300 --> 01:41:39.180
these tiny ones, even with 3 hive wings

01:41:39.180 --> 01:41:40.979
to a prisoner, they're going to get tired

01:41:40.979 --> 01:41:41.819
fast.

01:41:41.880 --> 01:41:44.039
It is unpleasant.

01:41:44.159 --> 01:41:46.619
To converse with a dragon who talks so

01:41:46.619 --> 01:41:46.859
much.

01:41:46.979 --> 01:41:49.319
Wasp remarked.

01:41:49.500 --> 01:41:52.680
Earwig closed her mouth and rubbed her

01:41:52.680 --> 01:41:53.340
forehead again.

01:41:53.399 --> 01:41:57.000
You will stay here, and wait for these

01:41:57.000 --> 01:41:58.020
dragons to wake up.

01:41:58.140 --> 01:42:02.100
Wasp said, waving the silk wings talons

01:42:02.100 --> 01:42:04.020
at the Vord tranquilized hive wings.

01:42:04.079 --> 01:42:07.680
Then you will all return to Wasp Hive.

01:42:07.739 --> 01:42:11.640
He snapped his tail, and the other hive

01:42:11.640 --> 01:42:14.100
wings began to move in silent unison

01:42:14.100 --> 01:42:17.039
splitting up to circle the prisoners, and

01:42:17.039 --> 01:42:18.479
dragging vines from the trees.

01:42:18.539 --> 01:42:21.960
Wait, Earwig said.

01:42:22.020 --> 01:42:23.880
I don't want to be stuck here alone.

01:42:23.939 --> 01:42:25.079
What if you're right?

01:42:25.140 --> 01:42:26.939
And there are other dragons lurking

01:42:26.939 --> 01:42:27.899
about.

01:42:27.960 --> 01:42:28.500
She shivered.

01:42:28.560 --> 01:42:31.439
Can't you jump back into me so I can go

01:42:31.439 --> 01:42:31.800
with you?

01:42:31.859 --> 01:42:33.659
Just make me like them again.

01:42:33.720 --> 01:42:37.380
She pointed to the white eyed dragons who

01:42:37.380 --> 01:42:39.659
were lashing long vines around tsunami.

01:42:39.720 --> 01:42:43.079
Luna would have gasped if she could have

01:42:43.079 --> 01:42:43.380
moved.

01:42:43.439 --> 01:42:47.880
Earwig, was asking for Wasp to take over

01:42:47.880 --> 01:42:48.180
her mind.

01:42:48.239 --> 01:42:51.359
She was inviting the evil queen back into

01:42:51.359 --> 01:42:51.720
her head.

01:42:51.779 --> 01:42:54.300
How can she want that?

01:42:54.359 --> 01:42:56.279
No.

01:42:56.340 --> 01:42:59.340
Wasp didn't even turn the silk wing to

01:42:59.340 --> 01:43:00.359
look at earwig again.

01:43:00.420 --> 01:43:02.520
You are in too much pain.

01:43:02.579 --> 01:43:05.159
It will distract me from the many claws I

01:43:05.159 --> 01:43:06.300
am working with right now.

01:43:06.359 --> 01:43:08.399
But I don't know how to get back.

01:43:08.460 --> 01:43:09.779
None of us do.

01:43:09.840 --> 01:43:11.279
Irwig cried.

01:43:11.340 --> 01:43:14.159
You can't fly us all the way out into the

01:43:14.159 --> 01:43:15.779
middle of the ocean and leave us to die.

01:43:15.840 --> 01:43:20.579
This conversation is boring me, Wasp

01:43:20.579 --> 01:43:20.880
said.

01:43:20.939 --> 01:43:23.340
Let me be clear so it can be over.

01:43:23.399 --> 01:43:25.859
I do not care what happens to you.

01:43:25.920 --> 01:43:30.119
Luna noticed that your wig looked lost

01:43:30.119 --> 01:43:32.520
but not terribly surprised by this.

01:43:32.579 --> 01:43:36.000
The silkwing made a commanding gesture at

01:43:36.000 --> 01:43:38.460
the marble eyed hive wings, and they bent

01:43:38.460 --> 01:43:39.300
toward their captives.

01:43:39.359 --> 01:43:43.199
As Kibli was lifted into his net of vines

01:43:43.199 --> 01:43:46.079
his head lolled, and the pouch around his

01:43:46.079 --> 01:43:47.939
neck slid off into the sand with a

01:43:47.939 --> 01:43:49.079
soft...

01:43:49.140 --> 01:43:52.260
A panicked cry tried to claw its way out

01:43:52.260 --> 01:43:54.479
of Luna's throat, and she had to tense

01:43:54.479 --> 01:43:56.279
every muscle in her body to keep it from

01:43:56.279 --> 01:43:56.640
escaping.

01:43:56.699 --> 01:44:00.779
She'd forgotten, that Kibley was the one

01:44:00.779 --> 01:44:02.159
carrying the map in his pouch.

01:44:02.279 --> 01:44:05.039
The map she and Sundu and the others

01:44:05.039 --> 01:44:06.840
needed to get home to Pentala.

01:44:06.899 --> 01:44:09.960
The map that could lead WASP and her army

01:44:09.960 --> 01:44:10.739
to Pyria.

01:44:10.800 --> 01:44:15.180
The map that must never, ever fall into

01:44:15.180 --> 01:44:16.199
wasps' talons.

01:44:16.260 --> 01:44:17.760
Don't find it.

01:44:17.819 --> 01:44:19.199
Luna prayed.

01:44:19.260 --> 01:44:20.460
Leave it lying there.

01:44:20.520 --> 01:44:22.020
Don't even notice it.

01:44:22.079 --> 01:44:24.720
The silkwing turned.

01:44:24.779 --> 01:44:29.699
With agonizing slowness, and stared down

01:44:29.699 --> 01:44:30.779
the pouch.

01:44:30.840 --> 01:44:34.979
Chapter 5.

01:44:35.279 --> 01:44:38.699
Please, Luna prayed.

01:44:38.760 --> 01:44:39.779
Please ignore it.

01:44:39.840 --> 01:44:41.520
Please don't find the map.

01:44:41.579 --> 01:44:45.000
The silkwing nudged the pouch with one

01:44:45.000 --> 01:44:45.359
claw.

01:44:45.420 --> 01:44:48.659
It lay flat on the sand, like a deflated

01:44:48.659 --> 01:44:49.979
leather sack.

01:44:50.039 --> 01:44:51.479
He reached to pick it up.

01:44:51.539 --> 01:44:55.560
It had this in it, earwigs said out of

01:44:55.560 --> 01:44:55.800
the blue.

01:44:55.920 --> 01:44:58.979
She held up Kibley's blowgun, which had

01:44:58.979 --> 01:45:00.119
fallen near her talons.

01:45:00.180 --> 01:45:03.000
She shook it a few times, and one of the

01:45:03.000 --> 01:45:03.899
darts slid out.

01:45:03.960 --> 01:45:06.899
I think he was trying to jab me.

01:45:06.960 --> 01:45:09.479
Her claw flicked the dart.

01:45:09.539 --> 01:45:11.819
Aha.

01:45:11.880 --> 01:45:14.880
Wasp said, through the silk wing.

01:45:15.000 --> 01:45:17.819
The trick they used on your unconscious

01:45:17.819 --> 01:45:19.199
comrades, I assume.

01:45:19.319 --> 01:45:23.340
The Silkwing turned to tsunami and yanked

01:45:23.340 --> 01:45:25.260
the Seawing's pouch off her neck to peer

01:45:25.260 --> 01:45:25.560
inside.

01:45:25.680 --> 01:45:27.119
Yes.

01:45:27.180 --> 01:45:29.399
They all seem to have them.

01:45:29.460 --> 01:45:32.819
So it's a weapon they made, not a natural

01:45:32.819 --> 01:45:33.779
dragon power.

01:45:33.840 --> 01:45:35.399
Interesting.

01:45:35.460 --> 01:45:39.180
He shook tsunami's pouch, and the dream

01:45:39.180 --> 01:45:41.279
visitor Sapphire tumbled out along with a

01:45:41.279 --> 01:45:41.760
blowgun.

01:45:41.819 --> 01:45:43.979
Luna's heart sank.

01:45:44.039 --> 01:45:46.619
She knew that it was better to lose the

01:45:46.619 --> 01:45:47.880
dream visitor than the map.

01:45:47.939 --> 01:45:50.819
WASP could do much worse damage with the

01:45:50.819 --> 01:45:51.420
map.

01:45:51.479 --> 01:45:54.420
And yet, losing the only way to contact

01:45:54.420 --> 01:45:56.819
SwordTail felt like having all her

01:45:56.819 --> 01:45:58.859
favorite tapestries torn to shreds.

01:45:58.859 --> 01:46:02.220
The Silkwing held it up to his nose and

01:46:02.220 --> 01:46:03.060
squinted at it.

01:46:03.119 --> 01:46:05.880
Strange thing to carry around.

01:46:06.000 --> 01:46:09.659
He said in one voice, and then went on in

01:46:09.659 --> 01:46:10.619
wasp's voice.

01:46:10.680 --> 01:46:14.579
A gift for me from the distant kingdoms.

01:46:14.640 --> 01:46:15.899
How thoughtful.

01:46:15.960 --> 01:46:19.439
He tucked it back into Tsunami's pouch

01:46:19.439 --> 01:46:22.140
which he draped over his own head, then

01:46:22.140 --> 01:46:23.399
beckoned the other dragons with his

01:46:23.399 --> 01:46:23.640
tail.

01:46:23.699 --> 01:46:25.800
Time to go.

01:46:26.039 --> 01:46:28.739
They flared open their wings in unison

01:46:28.739 --> 01:46:30.119
and lifted into the sky.

01:46:30.180 --> 01:46:34.380
Kibli, tsunami, pineapple, and invisible

01:46:34.380 --> 01:46:37.079
moon hung between them, wrapped in vines

01:46:37.079 --> 01:46:39.119
breathing, but otherwise still.

01:46:39.239 --> 01:46:41.520
Luna couldn't believe it.

01:46:41.579 --> 01:46:43.920
They'd been arguing and joking and

01:46:43.920 --> 01:46:46.199
laughing with her only moments ago, and

01:46:46.199 --> 01:46:48.180
now, they were wasps prisoners.

01:46:48.239 --> 01:46:50.460
It's all falling apart.

01:46:50.520 --> 01:46:53.939
We haven't even reached Pentala yet, and

01:46:53.939 --> 01:46:54.899
everything is already lost.

01:46:54.960 --> 01:46:58.859
She watched helplessly as their wing

01:46:58.859 --> 01:47:00.539
beats faded into the distance.

01:47:00.600 --> 01:47:04.380
Earwig slumped on the beach, staring out

01:47:04.380 --> 01:47:04.739
of the ocean.

01:47:04.800 --> 01:47:08.460
She was alone, with the 4 unconscious

01:47:08.460 --> 01:47:09.060
hive wings.

01:47:09.119 --> 01:47:12.180
The sand all around her was churned up by

01:47:12.180 --> 01:47:15.119
the battle, grooved with claw marks, and

01:47:15.119 --> 01:47:16.079
splattered with blood.

01:47:16.140 --> 01:47:19.680
I can move now, Luna thought.

01:47:19.739 --> 01:47:22.319
But it was hard to convince her petrified

01:47:22.319 --> 01:47:22.979
limbs.

01:47:23.039 --> 01:47:24.840
The silk wing is gone.

01:47:24.899 --> 01:47:26.640
Earwig won't notice me.

01:47:26.760 --> 01:47:29.100
I can go to the palm tree and hope to

01:47:29.100 --> 01:47:29.760
find the others there.

01:47:29.819 --> 01:47:33.359
Should she try to grab Kibley's pouch

01:47:33.359 --> 01:47:33.720
first?

01:47:33.779 --> 01:47:36.180
What if earwig spotted it floating away?

01:47:36.239 --> 01:47:38.819
Earwig sighed?

01:47:38.880 --> 01:47:42.479
Long and tragic, and then, as if she'd

01:47:42.479 --> 01:47:44.579
heard Luna's thoughts, she dragged

01:47:44.579 --> 01:47:46.380
herself over to Kibley's pouch and picked

01:47:46.380 --> 01:47:46.800
it up.

01:47:46.859 --> 01:47:50.520
No, Luna cried inside her head.

01:47:50.579 --> 01:47:51.539
No, no, no.

01:47:51.659 --> 01:47:54.720
Earwig opens the pouch and peeked

01:47:54.720 --> 01:47:54.960
inside.

01:47:55.079 --> 01:47:57.539
With a barely curious expression.

01:47:57.600 --> 01:47:59.640
She slid out the map and unfolded it.

01:47:59.699 --> 01:48:01.619
Her eyes went wide.

01:48:01.739 --> 01:48:04.859
She started to jump to her feet, let out

01:48:04.859 --> 01:48:06.840
a yelp of pain, and toppled over again.

01:48:06.899 --> 01:48:09.060
Wasp!

01:48:09.119 --> 01:48:09.899
she shouted.

01:48:09.960 --> 01:48:10.680
Come back.

01:48:10.800 --> 01:48:12.539
Your majesty, I found...

01:48:12.539 --> 01:48:13.560
Flip.

01:48:13.619 --> 01:48:16.739
With the tiny sound of a dart, zipping

01:48:16.739 --> 01:48:17.279
through the air.

01:48:17.340 --> 01:48:20.760
Earwig's eyes rolled back in her head, and

01:48:20.760 --> 01:48:22.199
she flopped over with a thud.

01:48:22.319 --> 01:48:27.239
Whew. said Lynx's voice, loud and clear

01:48:27.239 --> 01:48:27.899
in the silence.

01:48:27.960 --> 01:48:30.420
Nice shot.

01:48:30.539 --> 01:48:33.779
Bullfrog's deep voice came from the mess

01:48:33.779 --> 01:48:35.699
of sandy talon prints near where

01:48:35.699 --> 01:48:38.159
pineapple had fallen, not far from Luna.

01:48:38.220 --> 01:48:40.619
She couldn't believe he'd been that close

01:48:40.619 --> 01:48:42.779
to her, and so silent that whole time.

01:48:42.840 --> 01:48:46.079
Well, maybe she could believe the silent

01:48:46.079 --> 01:48:46.260
part.

01:48:46.380 --> 01:48:48.600
Are we all here?

01:48:48.659 --> 01:48:51.359
Sundu asked, from the far side of the

01:48:51.359 --> 01:48:51.960
battleground.

01:48:52.020 --> 01:48:54.899
I am, Cricket's voice answered.

01:48:54.960 --> 01:49:00.420
Yes, said Bullfrog, and here, said Lynx.

01:49:00.479 --> 01:49:03.420
Me too, Luna managed.

01:49:03.479 --> 01:49:05.340
What are we going to do?

01:49:05.399 --> 01:49:06.659
Cricket asked.

01:49:06.720 --> 01:49:09.060
Her voice overlapping with links, saying

01:49:09.060 --> 01:49:10.380
that was awful.

01:49:10.439 --> 01:49:12.060
I felt like I couldn't do anything.

01:49:12.119 --> 01:49:14.399
Poor pineapple.

01:49:14.460 --> 01:49:15.539
Luna said.

01:49:15.600 --> 01:49:18.239
She pressed her talons to her snout, and

01:49:18.239 --> 01:49:19.920
took a deep breath to stop her tears.

01:49:19.979 --> 01:49:22.680
I can't believe a silk wing.

01:49:22.739 --> 01:49:23.939
She trailed off.

01:49:24.060 --> 01:49:26.460
Was that terrifying?

01:49:26.520 --> 01:49:28.680
Me neither, Sundu growled.

01:49:28.739 --> 01:49:30.960
Ren, Sky, where are you?

01:49:31.020 --> 01:49:34.619
Will the mind control work on the Pyrean

01:49:34.619 --> 01:49:35.039
dragons?

01:49:35.100 --> 01:49:35.939
Cricket asked.

01:49:36.000 --> 01:49:38.579
That's the 1st thing wasp will do, don't

01:49:38.579 --> 01:49:38.760
you think?

01:49:38.819 --> 01:49:41.100
Inject them with her hive mind toxin?

01:49:41.159 --> 01:49:43.859
No, because we're going to get them back

01:49:43.859 --> 01:49:44.880
before that happens.

01:49:44.939 --> 01:49:46.680
Sundew said firmly.

01:49:46.739 --> 01:49:48.239
Skye.

01:49:48.300 --> 01:49:51.119
Can we revisible ourselves now?

01:49:51.180 --> 01:49:52.319
Cricket asked.

01:49:52.380 --> 01:49:55.800
If I make us visible, Moon will be too

01:49:55.800 --> 01:49:57.000
Sundew said.

01:49:57.060 --> 01:49:58.920
And then they'll know she's another clear

01:49:58.920 --> 01:49:59.399
sight.

01:49:59.520 --> 01:50:02.340
But I might have to anyway, if we can't

01:50:02.340 --> 01:50:03.479
find Skye and Ren.

01:50:03.539 --> 01:50:05.760
Skye, Wren!

01:50:05.880 --> 01:50:07.619
Yes, what?

01:50:07.739 --> 01:50:10.619
The little human's voice demanded, as

01:50:10.619 --> 01:50:12.659
wing beats descended from the clouds.

01:50:12.720 --> 01:50:15.119
Four talon prints appeared in a puff of

01:50:15.119 --> 01:50:18.239
sand, followed by a spray of moor sand as

01:50:18.239 --> 01:50:19.619
guys shook out his wings.

01:50:19.619 --> 01:50:21.720
What are you shouting our names for?

01:50:21.779 --> 01:50:23.699
Ach, Sky, quit that.

01:50:23.760 --> 01:50:24.899
You're getting sand in my mouth.

01:50:24.960 --> 01:50:27.180
Where did you go?

01:50:27.239 --> 01:50:29.100
Sundu said irritably.

01:50:29.159 --> 01:50:30.420
We were worried about you.

01:50:30.479 --> 01:50:33.300
I mean, not me specifically, but somebody

01:50:33.300 --> 01:50:33.960
probably was.

01:50:34.020 --> 01:50:37.140
We went to the palm tree to wait for you

01:50:37.140 --> 01:50:38.279
Ran answered.

01:50:38.399 --> 01:50:41.399
I told you, I'm not sending sky into any

01:50:41.399 --> 01:50:43.800
battles with creepy bug dragon zombies.

01:50:43.859 --> 01:50:45.239
No offense, Cricket.

01:50:45.300 --> 01:50:46.859
Why?

01:50:46.920 --> 01:50:49.140
I'm not cricket started.

01:50:49.199 --> 01:50:51.659
But we could see most of what happened

01:50:51.659 --> 01:50:54.779
Ren went on, and it didn't look great.

01:50:54.840 --> 01:50:58.619
It was so horrible.

01:50:58.680 --> 01:51:01.020
Sky's voice added mournfully.

01:51:01.079 --> 01:51:03.359
I did not like those dragons.

01:51:03.420 --> 01:51:04.739
Is pineapple all right?

01:51:04.800 --> 01:51:06.060
Where did they take them?

01:51:06.180 --> 01:51:08.579
I thought we weren't going to fight any

01:51:08.579 --> 01:51:09.359
hive wings?

01:51:09.420 --> 01:51:10.380
Ren added.

01:51:10.439 --> 01:51:13.619
I thought our very specific plan was to

01:51:13.619 --> 01:51:16.199
stay far away from any dragons who might

01:51:16.199 --> 01:51:18.060
end up mind controlling us or hurting

01:51:18.060 --> 01:51:18.359
Skye.

01:51:18.479 --> 01:51:21.000
Or stealing our friends.

01:51:21.060 --> 01:51:22.199
Sky added.

01:51:22.260 --> 01:51:25.739
We didn't go looking for them, Sundew

01:51:25.739 --> 01:51:26.100
barked.

01:51:26.159 --> 01:51:27.000
They attacked us.

01:51:27.060 --> 01:51:28.439
We couldn't not fight back.

01:51:28.500 --> 01:51:31.319
I know, Ren said.

01:51:31.380 --> 01:51:32.399
Just...

01:51:32.399 --> 01:51:34.739
Sky's not that kind of dragon.

01:51:34.800 --> 01:51:37.140
Battles like that, scare him.

01:51:37.199 --> 01:51:39.840
I beg your pardon?

01:51:39.899 --> 01:51:42.779
Sky said, ripples appearing in the sand

01:51:42.779 --> 01:51:44.279
from his ruffling wings.

01:51:44.279 --> 01:51:45.659
I'm not scared.

01:51:45.720 --> 01:51:49.020
I mean, my heart is going really fast, and

01:51:49.020 --> 01:51:51.840
my stomach is flippy wobbly, and I wish I

01:51:51.840 --> 01:51:53.640
had a giant turtle shell that I could

01:51:53.640 --> 01:51:55.920
crawl into and stay there and never see

01:51:55.920 --> 01:51:59.220
those dragons again, but mostly, I am

01:51:59.220 --> 01:52:01.380
worried about pineapple, and our other

01:52:01.380 --> 01:52:01.680
friends.

01:52:01.739 --> 01:52:06.060
They're still alive, Luna reassured him.

01:52:06.180 --> 01:52:07.979
They were all unconscious.

01:52:08.039 --> 01:52:10.380
They're being taken to Wasp Hive, where

01:52:10.380 --> 01:52:11.220
the queen lives.

01:52:11.279 --> 01:52:14.460
WASP prefers capturing dragons to killing

01:52:14.460 --> 01:52:14.640
them.

01:52:14.699 --> 01:52:16.079
Cricket explained.

01:52:16.140 --> 01:52:18.119
They're more useful to her as new

01:52:18.119 --> 01:52:19.800
soldiers to control than his corpses.

01:52:19.859 --> 01:52:22.560
Ah, Ren said.

01:52:22.619 --> 01:52:24.180
I don't like those options.

01:52:24.239 --> 01:52:25.319
No, thank you.

01:52:25.380 --> 01:52:28.020
We should follow them, shouldn't we?

01:52:28.079 --> 01:52:29.159
Luna asked.

01:52:29.220 --> 01:52:31.560
A 100000000 knows?

01:52:31.680 --> 01:52:32.699
Ren cried.

01:52:32.760 --> 01:52:33.479
Follow them?

01:52:33.539 --> 01:52:34.800
What did I just say?

01:52:34.859 --> 01:52:37.260
Of course we have to follow them.

01:52:37.380 --> 01:52:38.819
Sundu said.

01:52:38.880 --> 01:52:41.100
We stay at a distance until we can

01:52:41.100 --> 01:52:42.720
tranquilize or dart the silk wing.

01:52:42.779 --> 01:52:44.159
Maybe while they're sleeping.

01:52:44.279 --> 01:52:46.439
Then we can sneak in and rescue

01:52:46.439 --> 01:52:46.619
everyone.

01:52:46.739 --> 01:52:50.579
I'm not sure WASP is going to let them

01:52:50.579 --> 01:52:52.500
sleep until they're inside her hive.

01:52:52.560 --> 01:52:54.779
Cricket said slowly.

01:52:54.840 --> 01:52:58.020
She can drive the dragons she's inside

01:52:58.020 --> 01:52:59.520
beyond the point of exhaustion.

01:52:59.579 --> 01:53:02.399
I think that's how she got them this far

01:53:02.399 --> 01:53:03.359
out here without the map.

01:53:03.420 --> 01:53:06.239
I don't think she could get them all the

01:53:06.239 --> 01:53:08.880
way to Pyria, but she can probably fly

01:53:08.880 --> 01:53:10.739
them back to her hive without letting

01:53:10.739 --> 01:53:11.220
them rest.

01:53:11.279 --> 01:53:16.859
So, if we try to follow them, links added

01:53:16.859 --> 01:53:19.140
we might end up over open water, with

01:53:19.140 --> 01:53:20.819
nowhere to rest when we need to.

01:53:20.880 --> 01:53:23.640
So, what's the alternative?

01:53:23.760 --> 01:53:25.260
Sundu cried.

01:53:25.319 --> 01:53:27.600
We can't let them take 4 dragons from

01:53:27.600 --> 01:53:28.140
us.

01:53:28.439 --> 01:53:30.600
From the plumes of sand around her

01:53:30.600 --> 01:53:30.779
voice.

01:53:30.899 --> 01:53:33.659
Luna guessed the invisible leaf wing was

01:53:33.659 --> 01:53:34.319
lashing her tail.

01:53:34.380 --> 01:53:38.399
They'd rescue us if they were here, Luna

01:53:38.399 --> 01:53:38.819
agreed.

01:53:38.880 --> 01:53:41.460
You know Tsunami and Kibbly wouldn't even

01:53:41.460 --> 01:53:42.060
stop to think.

01:53:42.119 --> 01:53:45.840
Um, I'm in favor of stopping to think

01:53:45.840 --> 01:53:47.819
before doing dangerous things.

01:53:47.939 --> 01:53:49.680
Links interjected.

01:53:49.739 --> 01:53:51.119
Me too.

01:53:51.239 --> 01:53:52.439
Cricket agreed.

01:53:52.500 --> 01:53:55.140
And remember, our goal is to get to the

01:53:55.140 --> 01:53:57.300
abyss and fulfill Moon's prophecy.

01:53:57.359 --> 01:53:59.699
Don't we think that's the way to defeat

01:53:59.699 --> 01:54:00.779
WASP and the other mind?

01:54:00.840 --> 01:54:03.479
So it's actually the best way to rescue

01:54:03.479 --> 01:54:03.840
our friends?

01:54:03.899 --> 01:54:06.960
Better than throwing ourselves at an army

01:54:06.960 --> 01:54:08.699
of creepy bug dragons, yes.

01:54:08.760 --> 01:54:10.439
Ren chimed in.

01:54:10.619 --> 01:54:13.079
But we can't fulfill the prophecy without

01:54:13.079 --> 01:54:13.439
them.

01:54:13.560 --> 01:54:15.000
Luna protested.

01:54:15.060 --> 01:54:16.619
Talons United.

01:54:16.739 --> 01:54:18.539
That means all 10 of us.

01:54:18.600 --> 01:54:20.880
And Moon is the only one who can tell us

01:54:20.880 --> 01:54:21.359
what to do.

01:54:21.420 --> 01:54:24.479
We need to follow the prophecy exactly

01:54:24.479 --> 01:54:25.739
and we're already failing.

01:54:25.800 --> 01:54:28.500
You can't make a tapestry with half your

01:54:28.500 --> 01:54:29.159
silk missing.

01:54:29.220 --> 01:54:30.840
She thought anxiously.

01:54:30.899 --> 01:54:35.880
Actually, Bullfrog's voice said slowly.

01:54:36.000 --> 01:54:40.079
Clay says, prophecies aren't like

01:54:40.079 --> 01:54:41.340
instructions.

01:54:41.399 --> 01:54:45.180
And they aren't messages saying, this

01:54:45.180 --> 01:54:46.500
will definitely happen.

01:54:46.560 --> 01:54:52.199
He says, prophecy can give you a hint in

01:54:52.199 --> 01:54:53.159
the right direction.

01:54:53.220 --> 01:54:56.880
But you have to choose what you do with

01:54:56.880 --> 01:54:57.060
it.

01:54:57.119 --> 01:55:00.659
Everyone fell silent for a long moment.

01:55:00.779 --> 01:55:03.779
Luna was so startled by the length of

01:55:03.779 --> 01:55:06.180
bullfrog's speech, that it took her a

01:55:06.180 --> 01:55:07.800
moment to process the meaning of it.

01:55:07.800 --> 01:55:09.840
Wait.

01:55:09.899 --> 01:55:12.779
So prophecies don't tell the future?

01:55:12.840 --> 01:55:13.680
she asked.

01:55:13.739 --> 01:55:16.020
Who's clay?

01:55:16.079 --> 01:55:17.699
Cricket asked at the same time.

01:55:17.760 --> 01:55:21.359
A mud wing, who was in a prophecy not too

01:55:21.359 --> 01:55:21.720
long ago.

01:55:21.840 --> 01:55:23.579
Links explained.

01:55:23.640 --> 01:55:25.260
He has saved Pyria.

01:55:25.319 --> 01:55:28.800
But our prophecies told us what would

01:55:28.800 --> 01:55:30.359
happen, Luna argued.

01:55:30.420 --> 01:55:32.819
I mean, the ones in Clearsight's book?

01:55:32.880 --> 01:55:35.100
They were like instructions.

01:55:35.159 --> 01:55:37.140
They were exactly instructions.

01:55:37.199 --> 01:55:40.199
Maybe, Cricket said.

01:55:40.260 --> 01:55:42.840
We don't know for sure because we never

01:55:42.840 --> 01:55:44.399
lived in a time Clearsight actually

01:55:44.399 --> 01:55:44.939
predicted.

01:55:45.060 --> 01:55:50.520
All I'm saying, Bullfrog cut in, his

01:55:50.520 --> 01:55:51.779
voice deep and implacable.

01:55:51.840 --> 01:55:54.539
Is that we're the ones who make the

01:55:54.539 --> 01:55:55.319
prophecy happen?

01:55:55.380 --> 01:55:57.840
Not the other way around.

01:55:57.899 --> 01:56:01.500
I'm confused, said Luna.

01:56:01.560 --> 01:56:03.600
I still think we need all 10 of us.

01:56:03.720 --> 01:56:07.619
I think I get it, Sundu said.

01:56:07.680 --> 01:56:09.659
You're saying the future is up to us.

01:56:09.720 --> 01:56:11.699
Whatever happens next?

01:56:11.760 --> 01:56:14.760
It's because of what we decide to do, not

01:56:14.760 --> 01:56:16.560
because of some mystical force pointing

01:56:16.560 --> 01:56:18.239
us here, or plopping us there.

01:56:18.300 --> 01:56:22.979
So we could decide to save our friends

01:56:22.979 --> 01:56:23.460
couldn't we?

01:56:23.520 --> 01:56:25.020
Luna said.

01:56:25.079 --> 01:56:25.920
Shouldn't we?

01:56:25.979 --> 01:56:28.979
Let's vote, Sundu said.

01:56:29.100 --> 01:56:31.319
All in favor of chasing the hive wings

01:56:31.319 --> 01:56:33.060
right now to rescue Moon and the others?

01:56:33.119 --> 01:56:35.819
Me, Luna said.

01:56:35.880 --> 01:56:38.579
Me too, Skye said.

01:56:38.640 --> 01:56:40.739
Ouch, Ren, no kicking.

01:56:40.800 --> 01:56:41.819
Bad pet human.

01:56:41.939 --> 01:56:43.380
And me.

01:56:43.439 --> 01:56:44.760
Sundu said.

01:56:44.819 --> 01:56:46.739
Who thinks we should stick with the

01:56:46.739 --> 01:56:48.659
original plan and go find the abyss.

01:56:48.720 --> 01:56:50.159
Me?

01:56:50.279 --> 01:56:52.140
Cricket and Bullfrog said together.

01:56:52.199 --> 01:56:54.960
Me too.

01:56:55.020 --> 01:56:56.340
Lynx agreed.

01:56:56.399 --> 01:56:58.859
So it's a tie.

01:56:58.979 --> 01:57:01.020
Sundoo said with a sigh.

01:57:01.079 --> 01:57:04.500
Said Wren's little human voice.

01:57:04.560 --> 01:57:06.180
I'm here too.

01:57:06.239 --> 01:57:07.800
And I vote for the original plan.

01:57:07.920 --> 01:57:10.619
I'd rather take Skye to a creepy abyss

01:57:10.619 --> 01:57:12.899
than into a swarm of creepy murder bug

01:57:12.899 --> 01:57:15.180
dragons, R, Skye, stop.

01:57:15.300 --> 01:57:18.359
There was a thump, and a large dent

01:57:18.359 --> 01:57:20.399
appeared in the beach, where Skye had

01:57:20.399 --> 01:57:22.800
apparently flung himself down, followed

01:57:22.800 --> 01:57:24.840
by a lot of sand flying, and crabs

01:57:24.840 --> 01:57:26.640
scuttling about as he had a rolling

01:57:26.640 --> 01:57:27.060
tantrum.

01:57:27.119 --> 01:57:30.180
Little human footprints landed on the

01:57:30.180 --> 01:57:32.460
sand and darted out of the way, then

01:57:32.460 --> 01:57:33.000
stopped again.

01:57:33.060 --> 01:57:35.939
Luna could easily picture Wen with her

01:57:35.939 --> 01:57:38.340
hands on her hips, glaring at the mess I

01:57:38.340 --> 01:57:38.640
was making.

01:57:38.699 --> 01:57:41.340
Well, this is very mature.

01:57:41.399 --> 01:57:43.439
Rand's voice said crossly.

01:57:43.500 --> 01:57:45.659
Sky.

01:57:45.720 --> 01:57:47.579
I know how you feel, Lang said.

01:57:47.640 --> 01:57:49.680
My heart says rescue them too.

01:57:49.739 --> 01:57:52.199
But my head says, we'll only get

01:57:52.199 --> 01:57:54.539
ourselves caught or worse, and the most

01:57:54.539 --> 01:57:56.640
logical way to save them is to get to the

01:57:56.640 --> 01:57:57.180
abyss.

01:57:57.300 --> 01:57:59.340
If we can defeat the other mind.

01:57:59.460 --> 01:58:01.859
WASP won't have an army to control

01:58:01.859 --> 01:58:03.359
anymore, right?

01:58:03.420 --> 01:58:04.979
That's our theory.

01:58:05.039 --> 01:58:08.100
And we can't risk losing you or Ren.

01:58:08.159 --> 01:58:09.300
Cricket agreed.

01:58:09.359 --> 01:58:11.760
You're the only ones who can help us talk

01:58:11.760 --> 01:58:13.260
to the humans to find the abyss.

01:58:13.380 --> 01:58:16.260
No, Sky cried.

01:58:16.319 --> 01:58:18.960
Ren, you can't just save me in the

01:58:18.960 --> 01:58:20.460
kingdom of sand, even when it was

01:58:20.460 --> 01:58:20.819
dangerous.

01:58:20.880 --> 01:58:22.739
That's what we do for friends.

01:58:22.859 --> 01:58:25.380
And I finally have dragon friends.

01:58:25.439 --> 01:58:27.720
Dragon friends who need saving.

01:58:27.720 --> 01:58:30.359
All right, this is what we're going to

01:58:30.359 --> 01:58:30.600
do.

01:58:30.659 --> 01:58:33.840
Sundu said, with such authority that

01:58:33.840 --> 01:58:36.300
everyone went quiet, and Skye stopped

01:58:36.300 --> 01:58:37.619
invisibly thrashing around.

01:58:37.680 --> 01:58:40.859
Links and I will go try to rescue them.

01:58:40.920 --> 01:58:43.859
If it seems impossible, we won't risk it

01:58:43.859 --> 01:58:46.260
but we'll take as many darts as we can

01:58:46.260 --> 01:58:47.520
and see what we can do.

01:58:47.579 --> 01:58:50.579
Meanwhile, the rest of you keep following

01:58:50.579 --> 01:58:52.680
the map to Pentala and wait for us

01:58:52.680 --> 01:58:52.920
there.

01:58:52.979 --> 01:58:55.619
If we don't catch up with you in 2 days

01:58:55.619 --> 01:58:57.659
go look for the abyss without us.

01:58:57.720 --> 01:58:59.699
Just us?

01:58:59.760 --> 01:59:01.680
Luna said softly.

01:59:01.739 --> 01:59:06.600
Her, Cricket, Sky and Ren, and Bullfrog.

01:59:06.659 --> 01:59:09.239
No tsunami or sundew to do the fighting.

01:59:09.300 --> 01:59:11.399
No moon to tell the future.

01:59:11.460 --> 01:59:15.300
No clever Kibli plans, no reassuring

01:59:15.300 --> 01:59:16.979
links, smiles, or pineapple

01:59:16.979 --> 01:59:17.579
cheerfulness.

01:59:17.579 --> 01:59:20.399
Don't worry, Sundew said.

01:59:20.460 --> 01:59:21.960
Will be there.

01:59:22.020 --> 01:59:24.539
Luna wanted to believe that.

01:59:24.600 --> 01:59:28.020
But if anything went wrong, the 5 of them

01:59:28.020 --> 01:59:29.880
would have to face the abyss alone.

01:59:29.939 --> 01:59:33.779
The last words of the prophecy echoed in

01:59:33.779 --> 01:59:34.079
her head.

01:59:34.140 --> 01:59:38.220
Face a great evil with talons united.

01:59:38.279 --> 01:59:41.460
Or none of the tribes will survive.

01:59:41.520 --> 01:59:46.199
Chapter 6.

01:59:46.260 --> 01:59:49.619
Luna was not surprised that it was

01:59:49.619 --> 01:59:50.039
raining.

01:59:50.100 --> 01:59:52.859
It was the rainy season on Penthala.

01:59:52.920 --> 01:59:55.140
She was used to the drumming sound of

01:59:55.140 --> 01:59:57.119
raindrops on hive walls and silk

01:59:57.119 --> 01:59:57.659
ceilings.

01:59:57.720 --> 02:00:01.859
She was not, used to the damp, chilly air

02:00:01.859 --> 02:00:03.720
spraying her no matter where she tried to

02:00:03.720 --> 02:00:04.140
sit, though.

02:00:04.199 --> 02:00:07.319
This cave was not designed for dragons to

02:00:07.319 --> 02:00:09.659
live in during storms, especially if

02:00:09.659 --> 02:00:11.939
those dragons had nothing to do, except

02:00:11.939 --> 02:00:14.100
anxiously watch the sky outside for

02:00:14.100 --> 02:00:14.880
missing friends.

02:00:14.880 --> 02:00:18.300
Of course, she knew those friends would

02:00:18.300 --> 02:00:18.840
be invisible.

02:00:18.960 --> 02:00:20.460
So she wouldn't see them coming.

02:00:20.520 --> 02:00:22.920
But she couldn't stop sitting near the

02:00:22.920 --> 02:00:25.260
mouth of the cave, and staring out at the

02:00:25.260 --> 02:00:26.159
thunderstorm anyway.

02:00:26.220 --> 02:00:30.119
I can make a tapestry of this, Luna

02:00:30.119 --> 02:00:30.420
thought.

02:00:30.539 --> 02:00:33.359
Endless rain, an empty beach.

02:00:33.420 --> 02:00:36.539
A sky that's all clouds and no dragons.

02:00:36.600 --> 02:00:39.840
Or maybe I'd weave shapes away off in the

02:00:39.840 --> 02:00:43.020
distance, blurred by lines of silver, silk

02:00:43.020 --> 02:00:46.319
raindrops, but still there, like faraway

02:00:46.319 --> 02:00:47.699
hope, coming toward us.

02:00:47.760 --> 02:00:50.939
I would love some hope.

02:00:51.000 --> 02:00:53.880
Even far away hope, right now.

02:00:53.939 --> 02:00:56.159
Luna?

02:00:56.220 --> 02:00:59.220
Cricket's voice said, her talon prints

02:00:59.220 --> 02:01:00.420
approaching through the wet sand.

02:01:00.479 --> 02:01:01.800
Are you there?

02:01:01.920 --> 02:01:03.720
For a moment.

02:01:03.779 --> 02:01:06.180
Luna considered pretending she wasn't.

02:01:06.239 --> 02:01:08.819
If she held really still and didn't

02:01:08.819 --> 02:01:11.039
breathe, Maybe cricket would walk away

02:01:11.039 --> 02:01:13.260
and Luna wouldn't have to muster the

02:01:13.260 --> 02:01:15.539
energy for a conversation, or more

02:01:15.539 --> 02:01:17.880
importantly, for a conversation where she

02:01:17.880 --> 02:01:19.680
had to act like she trusted this hive

02:01:19.680 --> 02:01:22.380
wing, like it was fine that Luna was

02:01:22.380 --> 02:01:24.659
stuck in a cave with her, instead of with

02:01:24.659 --> 02:01:26.520
any of the dragons she really wanted to

02:01:26.520 --> 02:01:26.819
be with.

02:01:26.880 --> 02:01:29.279
She would know though.

02:01:29.340 --> 02:01:31.979
And Luna couldn't bring herself to hurt

02:01:31.979 --> 02:01:34.319
cricket's feelings, especially when she

02:01:34.319 --> 02:01:36.060
remembered the way Blue looked at her.

02:01:36.119 --> 02:01:39.060
I'm here, Luna said.

02:01:39.119 --> 02:01:41.640
Just waiting.

02:01:41.760 --> 02:01:44.880
Again, stuck in one place.

02:01:44.939 --> 02:01:47.279
No idea what to do or how to help

02:01:47.279 --> 02:01:47.699
anyone.

02:01:47.760 --> 02:01:50.579
Maybe they're hiding out from the rain.

02:01:50.699 --> 02:01:53.939
Cricket said, accidentally bumping one of

02:01:53.939 --> 02:01:54.300
her wings.

02:01:54.359 --> 02:01:57.300
Maybe they're worried about the lightning

02:01:57.300 --> 02:01:59.220
and they'll be here as soon as the storm

02:01:59.220 --> 02:01:59.579
lets up.

02:01:59.640 --> 02:02:02.640
Maybe, Luna said.

02:02:02.699 --> 02:02:04.859
More to let Cricket know she was still

02:02:04.859 --> 02:02:06.600
there and listening than because she

02:02:06.600 --> 02:02:06.960
agreed.

02:02:07.020 --> 02:02:10.020
Sundu and Lynx should have been there

02:02:10.020 --> 02:02:10.619
yesterday.

02:02:10.680 --> 02:02:13.680
They'd agreed to wait for them at the

02:02:13.680 --> 02:02:15.300
cave that connected to the Flame Hill

02:02:15.300 --> 02:02:17.640
Cavern, the one where Luna had been blown

02:02:17.640 --> 02:02:18.479
away by the storm.

02:02:18.539 --> 02:02:21.539
A whole extra day they'd been waiting.

02:02:21.600 --> 02:02:24.539
With no sign of the leaf wing or the ice

02:02:24.539 --> 02:02:24.899
wing.

02:02:25.020 --> 02:02:27.659
Have they been captured too?

02:02:27.720 --> 02:02:32.579
It would be so, so bad for sundew to fall

02:02:32.579 --> 02:02:34.319
into the clutches of Queen Wasp.

02:02:34.380 --> 02:02:37.739
With sundews, leaf speak power.

02:02:37.800 --> 02:02:40.140
The other mind could grow the breath of

02:02:40.140 --> 02:02:42.359
evil plant from one edge of the continent

02:02:42.359 --> 02:02:44.039
to the other in a matter of weeks.

02:02:44.100 --> 02:02:46.319
Don't think about that.

02:02:46.380 --> 02:02:47.880
She's fine.

02:02:47.939 --> 02:02:49.500
I'm sure she's all right.

02:02:49.560 --> 02:02:50.760
They'll be here soon.

02:02:50.819 --> 02:02:52.680
Keep smiling.

02:02:52.739 --> 02:02:54.119
No problems here.

02:02:54.180 --> 02:02:57.119
Except no one could see her face.

02:02:57.239 --> 02:03:00.300
So she didn't have to pretend, smile.

02:03:00.359 --> 02:03:02.579
The one upside of being invisible.

02:03:02.699 --> 02:03:05.939
Luna kind of wished she could spin

02:03:05.939 --> 02:03:08.399
herself another cocoon, and go back into

02:03:08.399 --> 02:03:08.939
it for a while.

02:03:09.000 --> 02:03:11.279
This happened to her sometimes.

02:03:11.340 --> 02:03:14.640
It felt as though she had her own rainy

02:03:14.640 --> 02:03:16.859
seasons and sunny seasons inside her

02:03:16.859 --> 02:03:17.039
head.

02:03:17.100 --> 02:03:18.720
Some days.

02:03:18.779 --> 02:03:21.359
She was full of light and endless energy

02:03:21.359 --> 02:03:24.479
and knowing what was right and ready to

02:03:24.479 --> 02:03:25.020
fix everything.

02:03:25.079 --> 02:03:30.000
But then, Sundays, a kind of fog wove

02:03:30.000 --> 02:03:32.100
through her thoughts, and she just wanted

02:03:32.100 --> 02:03:34.439
to crawl away from everyone and wrap

02:03:34.439 --> 02:03:37.319
herself in silk, and not be a dragon for

02:03:37.319 --> 02:03:37.619
a while.

02:03:37.680 --> 02:03:41.100
She thought she hid those days pretty

02:03:41.100 --> 02:03:41.340
well.

02:03:41.399 --> 02:03:44.520
She had a lot of practice at smiling

02:03:44.520 --> 02:03:46.800
through the fog, so her mothers wouldn't

02:03:46.800 --> 02:03:46.920
worry.

02:03:46.979 --> 02:03:49.380
She didn't mean to add to all the

02:03:49.380 --> 02:03:52.800
troubles everyone had, even Blue, who

02:03:52.800 --> 02:03:55.260
noticed so much, and tried so hard to

02:03:55.260 --> 02:03:57.600
understand everyone, usually couldn't

02:03:57.600 --> 02:03:59.220
tell when she was having a rainy season

02:03:59.220 --> 02:03:59.520
day.

02:03:59.579 --> 02:04:02.640
There wasn't always a clear reason for

02:04:02.640 --> 02:04:05.880
the sad feelings, or rather, in some ways

02:04:05.880 --> 02:04:07.140
there were always reasons.

02:04:07.199 --> 02:04:10.079
Teachers yelling at Luna and Blue in

02:04:10.079 --> 02:04:10.319
school.

02:04:10.380 --> 02:04:12.359
Sore tail in trouble again.

02:04:12.420 --> 02:04:16.439
Luna's mother silverspot, lying sadly in

02:04:16.439 --> 02:04:18.239
her hammock after another long day of

02:04:18.239 --> 02:04:20.159
cruelty from her hive wing mistress.

02:04:20.220 --> 02:04:23.939
All of them, too squashed flat by the

02:04:23.939 --> 02:04:26.640
meanness of others, and too exhausted to

02:04:26.640 --> 02:04:29.579
weave or make beautiful things, or dream

02:04:29.579 --> 02:04:30.239
of a better life.

02:04:30.300 --> 02:04:33.659
But this time, there was a very clear

02:04:33.659 --> 02:04:34.079
reason.

02:04:34.140 --> 02:04:37.680
And so the sadness felt even bigger, like

02:04:37.680 --> 02:04:39.000
she was letting down the whole world.

02:04:39.060 --> 02:04:44.279
Losing pineapple, moon, Kibli and tsunami

02:04:44.279 --> 02:04:46.800
not knowing where sundu and lynx were.

02:04:46.859 --> 02:04:49.920
Silkwings under Queen Wasp's Mind

02:04:49.920 --> 02:04:50.399
Control.

02:04:50.460 --> 02:04:53.399
Their mission failing before they'd even

02:04:53.399 --> 02:04:53.939
begun.

02:04:54.000 --> 02:04:56.819
And sore tail and blue.

02:04:56.939 --> 02:04:59.939
She really couldn't let herself think

02:04:59.939 --> 02:05:02.159
about sore tail and bloom, and how much

02:05:02.159 --> 02:05:04.439
they needed her. and how much she was

02:05:04.439 --> 02:05:05.460
failing to rescue them.

02:05:05.579 --> 02:05:09.479
Or else, the fog cocoon might wrap her up

02:05:09.479 --> 02:05:11.760
forever, and then she'd be no use to

02:05:11.760 --> 02:05:12.060
anyone.

02:05:12.119 --> 02:05:15.239
It also didn't help that she was still

02:05:15.239 --> 02:05:15.779
invisible.

02:05:15.840 --> 02:05:18.779
Each day that passed without seeing her

02:05:18.779 --> 02:05:21.960
own talons or her friends' faces, made

02:05:21.960 --> 02:05:24.000
Luna feel more and more unreal.

02:05:24.060 --> 02:05:26.640
As though she didn't really exist.

02:05:26.699 --> 02:05:28.199
Or maybe they didn't.

02:05:28.260 --> 02:05:30.359
Or maybe nothing did.

02:05:30.420 --> 02:05:33.119
She felt like she could dissolve into the

02:05:33.119 --> 02:05:35.520
clouds, and no one would notice or care.

02:05:35.579 --> 02:05:38.520
Sore Tail would.

02:05:38.579 --> 02:05:40.140
He would care so much.

02:05:40.199 --> 02:05:43.140
He needs me to be real so I can rescue

02:05:43.140 --> 02:05:43.380
him.

02:05:43.439 --> 02:05:46.859
My whole tribe needs me to rescue them.

02:05:46.979 --> 02:05:48.840
Come on, Luna.

02:05:48.899 --> 02:05:50.399
Sit up and keep going.

02:05:50.460 --> 02:05:54.060
Luna pulled back her shoulders and

02:05:54.060 --> 02:05:56.699
fluffed her damp wings, at least being

02:05:56.699 --> 02:05:58.920
this cold and wet, meant that she must

02:05:58.920 --> 02:05:59.819
still exist, right?

02:05:59.880 --> 02:06:03.420
Also, being invisible was useful for

02:06:03.420 --> 02:06:05.699
gathering food, without being spotted by

02:06:05.699 --> 02:06:06.960
the patrols that were constantly

02:06:06.960 --> 02:06:07.439
overhead.

02:06:07.500 --> 02:06:10.739
The patrols were still mostly hive

02:06:10.739 --> 02:06:11.159
wings.

02:06:11.220 --> 02:06:13.979
Luna had been afraid that mind controlled

02:06:13.979 --> 02:06:15.720
silk wings would be everywhere when they

02:06:15.720 --> 02:06:18.239
reached Pentala, but she hadn't seen very

02:06:18.239 --> 02:06:18.779
many so far.

02:06:18.840 --> 02:06:22.199
She knew some of them were in the hives

02:06:22.199 --> 02:06:24.779
imprisoned until wasp had more breath of

02:06:24.779 --> 02:06:25.859
evil to infect them with.

02:06:25.920 --> 02:06:29.220
With poor blue and sore tail forced to

02:06:29.220 --> 02:06:29.640
guard them.

02:06:29.699 --> 02:06:31.800
Shouldn't I go to them?

02:06:31.859 --> 02:06:34.380
If this abyss plan is falling apart

02:06:34.380 --> 02:06:34.800
anyway?

02:06:34.859 --> 02:06:37.439
Shouldn't I fly to Cicada Hive and try to

02:06:37.439 --> 02:06:37.739
save them?

02:06:37.800 --> 02:06:39.479
How though?

02:06:39.539 --> 02:06:41.819
I have all this fire.

02:06:41.880 --> 02:06:43.680
But I don't know what to do with it.

02:06:43.739 --> 02:06:46.920
Flame silk can't get wasp out of their

02:06:46.920 --> 02:06:48.840
heads, and what else do I have?

02:06:48.899 --> 02:06:52.199
Isn't it weird being invisible for this

02:06:52.199 --> 02:06:52.439
long?

02:06:52.500 --> 02:06:54.119
Cricket said.

02:06:54.180 --> 02:06:56.399
Her voice more subdued than usual.

02:06:56.460 --> 02:06:58.380
When it's quiet?

02:06:58.500 --> 02:07:00.300
I have these moments where I suddenly

02:07:00.300 --> 02:07:00.960
feel all alone.

02:07:01.079 --> 02:07:04.439
As though everyone else is gone and I'm a

02:07:04.439 --> 02:07:06.600
ghost, floating around with no body.

02:07:06.720 --> 02:07:08.819
Do you ever feel like that?

02:07:08.939 --> 02:07:12.960
Um, Luna said reluctantly.

02:07:13.079 --> 02:07:14.579
Maybe a little.

02:07:14.699 --> 02:07:18.119
She hesitated, but her curiosity won

02:07:18.119 --> 02:07:18.359
out.

02:07:18.420 --> 02:07:21.779
What do you do when you feel that way?

02:07:21.840 --> 02:07:24.840
I come looking for you.

02:07:24.960 --> 02:07:27.119
Cricket's voice said wryly.

02:07:27.180 --> 02:07:30.600
I mean, Sky and Bullfrog and Wren help

02:07:30.600 --> 02:07:30.899
too.

02:07:30.960 --> 02:07:33.239
But you're the most real to me for some

02:07:33.239 --> 02:07:33.420
reason.

02:07:33.479 --> 02:07:35.880
Maybe because we're both from here.

02:07:35.939 --> 02:07:39.539
Hmm, Luna answered.

02:07:39.600 --> 02:07:41.880
She wasn't sure quite what to say to

02:07:41.880 --> 02:07:42.060
that.

02:07:42.119 --> 02:07:45.359
Cricket's disembodied voice was easier to

02:07:45.359 --> 02:07:48.359
talk to than cricket's hive wing face, but

02:07:48.359 --> 02:07:49.739
she didn't exactly find it comforting.

02:07:49.800 --> 02:07:53.039
And sometimes, cricket went on.

02:07:53.100 --> 02:07:56.399
I close my eyes, and try to focus on what

02:07:56.399 --> 02:07:56.819
I can feel.

02:07:56.880 --> 02:08:00.239
Like, my claws feel wet sand sifting

02:08:00.239 --> 02:08:00.479
around them.

02:08:00.539 --> 02:08:03.119
My wings lift in the wind from the sea.

02:08:03.180 --> 02:08:04.680
I'm still here.

02:08:04.800 --> 02:08:06.060
I really exist.

02:08:06.119 --> 02:08:09.960
I'm in this dragon body in this world, you

02:08:09.960 --> 02:08:10.199
know?

02:08:10.260 --> 02:08:12.119
Does that make sense?

02:08:12.239 --> 02:08:16.140
Luna took a deep breath and tried to

02:08:16.140 --> 02:08:17.699
inhabit her senses beyond sight.

02:08:17.760 --> 02:08:20.159
My scales are real.

02:08:20.220 --> 02:08:22.260
My talons are real.

02:08:22.380 --> 02:08:24.239
I am still here.

02:08:24.300 --> 02:08:28.500
That does help, she said after a moment.

02:08:28.560 --> 02:08:32.640
Also, if I were a ghost, I hope I would

02:08:32.640 --> 02:08:34.260
pick a better place to haunt than this

02:08:34.260 --> 02:08:35.699
damp, fishy smelling cave.

02:08:35.760 --> 02:08:38.460
Cricket laughed.

02:08:38.520 --> 02:08:40.619
I would haunt a library, she said

02:08:40.619 --> 02:08:43.260
although it would be very frustrating to

02:08:43.260 --> 02:08:45.000
only read books over other dragons

02:08:45.000 --> 02:08:45.479
shoulders.

02:08:45.539 --> 02:08:48.239
I'd haunt an art museum.

02:08:48.300 --> 02:08:50.340
Luna said dreamily.

02:08:50.460 --> 02:08:53.039
If she weren't real, she could look at

02:08:53.039 --> 02:08:55.739
beautiful things all day long and avoid

02:08:55.739 --> 02:08:57.840
mean dragons without feeling guilty about

02:08:57.840 --> 02:09:00.000
all the dragons who needed her, and all

02:09:00.000 --> 02:09:01.800
the tasks she should be accomplishing.

02:09:01.859 --> 02:09:04.020
But I am real.

02:09:04.079 --> 02:09:07.560
I'm really Luna, and I can't let myself

02:09:07.560 --> 02:09:08.279
drift away.

02:09:08.340 --> 02:09:11.520
Do you think Earwig made it back to

02:09:11.520 --> 02:09:11.819
shore?

02:09:11.880 --> 02:09:13.380
Cricket asked.

02:09:13.439 --> 02:09:16.199
Grooves in the sand appeared as she drew

02:09:16.199 --> 02:09:17.220
shapes with her claws.

02:09:17.279 --> 02:09:19.920
She'd had a fight with Sundu about the

02:09:19.920 --> 02:09:22.199
unconscious hive wing soldiers back on

02:09:22.199 --> 02:09:22.500
the island.

02:09:22.560 --> 02:09:25.920
We can help them, Cricket had argued.

02:09:25.979 --> 02:09:27.840
Ewig is lost out here.

02:09:27.899 --> 02:09:29.880
All 5 of these hive wings are.

02:09:30.000 --> 02:09:32.460
We could draw her a map on a leaf or

02:09:32.460 --> 02:09:34.619
something, just showing the safe island

02:09:34.619 --> 02:09:36.479
trail from here back to Pentala?

02:09:36.539 --> 02:09:38.819
It wouldn't be the whole map, just enough

02:09:38.819 --> 02:09:39.899
to get her home.

02:09:39.960 --> 02:09:43.140
So that Queen Wasp can have 5 more

02:09:43.140 --> 02:09:45.060
dragons for her army if we run into them

02:09:45.060 --> 02:09:45.300
again.

02:09:45.359 --> 02:09:47.460
Sundew had demanded.

02:09:47.579 --> 02:09:49.859
Why not leave them stuck out here where

02:09:49.859 --> 02:09:50.579
they can't hurt us?

02:09:50.640 --> 02:09:54.479
Because they're still dragons, Cricket

02:09:54.479 --> 02:09:55.140
pointed out.

02:09:55.199 --> 02:09:57.359
They didn't choose to come here or attack

02:09:57.359 --> 02:09:57.840
us.

02:09:57.899 --> 02:10:00.779
They're going to wake up scared, wishing

02:10:00.779 --> 02:10:02.579
they could go home, and we could help

02:10:02.579 --> 02:10:02.939
them.

02:10:03.000 --> 02:10:04.560
Sundo.

02:10:04.619 --> 02:10:06.779
We have to go now or we'll lose the

02:10:06.779 --> 02:10:06.960
trail.

02:10:07.079 --> 02:10:08.579
Links had said.

02:10:08.640 --> 02:10:10.920
Breathing little ice crystals into the

02:10:10.920 --> 02:10:11.640
air from above them.

02:10:11.760 --> 02:10:14.579
We don't have time to argue.

02:10:14.640 --> 02:10:16.260
Fine.

02:10:16.319 --> 02:10:17.399
Do what you like.

02:10:17.460 --> 02:10:19.319
Sundewad said to Cricket.

02:10:19.380 --> 02:10:21.899
I think it's a mistake, but if you want

02:10:21.899 --> 02:10:23.100
to take the time, go ahead.

02:10:23.159 --> 02:10:26.640
And then she and Links were gone, leaving

02:10:26.640 --> 02:10:27.840
the map with Luna.

02:10:27.960 --> 02:10:30.600
Luna wasn't sure who was right.

02:10:30.659 --> 02:10:34.319
Her instinct was to trust Sundoo, but

02:10:34.319 --> 02:10:35.880
Crickets said Blue would want to help the

02:10:35.880 --> 02:10:38.939
hive wings, and that, unfortunately, was

02:10:38.939 --> 02:10:39.479
definitely true.

02:10:39.600 --> 02:10:42.779
Luna knew her little brother would never

02:10:42.779 --> 02:10:45.300
fly away and leave them lost like that.

02:10:45.359 --> 02:10:48.539
So Luna had used her flaying silk to

02:10:48.539 --> 02:10:50.520
carefully burn a copy of the map onto a

02:10:50.520 --> 02:10:51.300
wide leaf.

02:10:51.359 --> 02:10:53.520
Just the part of it that would get the

02:10:53.520 --> 02:10:54.420
hive wings back home.

02:10:54.479 --> 02:10:56.880
She'd added crickets note.

02:10:57.000 --> 02:10:59.939
This is the way back to Pentala.

02:11:00.000 --> 02:11:00.840
Good luck.

02:11:00.899 --> 02:11:03.359
Friends who want you to be free.

02:11:03.420 --> 02:11:06.960
Then they left it in the sand under one

02:11:06.960 --> 02:11:08.340
of earwig's talons.

02:11:08.399 --> 02:11:10.859
Luna hoped they'd done the right thing.

02:11:10.920 --> 02:11:13.920
She hoped earwig would remember that

02:11:13.920 --> 02:11:15.659
someone had tried to help her when Queen

02:11:15.659 --> 02:11:16.920
Wasp had left her to die.

02:11:16.979 --> 02:11:20.760
Una realized, she'd been thinking for too

02:11:20.760 --> 02:11:22.979
long, and hadn't answered cricket's

02:11:22.979 --> 02:11:23.579
question.

02:11:23.640 --> 02:11:26.220
I'm sure she did, she said.

02:11:26.279 --> 02:11:28.020
Cricket?

02:11:28.079 --> 02:11:30.239
Do you really think there are good hive

02:11:30.239 --> 02:11:30.659
wings?

02:11:30.720 --> 02:11:32.880
Ones who would help us if they could?

02:11:32.939 --> 02:11:36.600
She was glad she couldn't see the look on

02:11:36.600 --> 02:11:37.380
Cricket's face.

02:11:37.439 --> 02:11:39.659
Luna had been thinking about this

02:11:39.659 --> 02:11:41.819
question for days, and couldn't believe

02:11:41.819 --> 02:11:43.260
she'd actually blurted it out.

02:11:43.319 --> 02:11:46.920
There was a long pause, and then Cricket

02:11:46.920 --> 02:11:47.640
said softly.

02:11:47.699 --> 02:11:49.800
I hope so.

02:11:49.859 --> 02:11:53.399
There's Katie did for one, and my dad, I

02:11:53.399 --> 02:11:53.579
think.

02:11:53.640 --> 02:11:56.520
I haven't met him yet, but maybe Scarab

02:11:56.520 --> 02:11:56.880
liked him.

02:11:56.939 --> 02:11:59.939
I hope he turns out to be good once he's

02:11:59.939 --> 02:12:01.319
free from wasps clutches.

02:12:01.380 --> 02:12:04.500
But I guess I can't promise what any of

02:12:04.500 --> 02:12:05.819
them will be like then.

02:12:05.880 --> 02:12:08.159
I only know which side I want to be on.

02:12:08.279 --> 02:12:10.979
And it's with you, and blue.

02:12:11.039 --> 02:12:15.539
We need all the allies we can get, Luna

02:12:15.539 --> 02:12:16.260
reminded herself.

02:12:16.319 --> 02:12:18.840
She never did anything to help us

02:12:18.840 --> 02:12:19.140
before.

02:12:19.260 --> 02:12:22.140
But she's only a dragonette, like us.

02:12:22.199 --> 02:12:25.020
Maybe this was her 1st chance.

02:12:25.079 --> 02:12:27.180
Maybe she felt like me.

02:12:27.239 --> 02:12:30.239
Like she wanted to change things, but

02:12:30.239 --> 02:12:30.779
didn't know how.

02:12:30.840 --> 02:12:34.680
What if you had to choose between saving

02:12:34.680 --> 02:12:38.220
blue or, like, all the hive wings, Luna

02:12:38.220 --> 02:12:42.060
asked, or your family, Blue, in a

02:12:42.060 --> 02:12:43.560
heartbeat, Cricket said.

02:12:43.680 --> 02:12:45.239
I promise, Luna.

02:12:45.300 --> 02:12:47.699
Blue is my favorite dragon in all the

02:12:47.699 --> 02:12:48.060
world.

02:12:48.180 --> 02:12:49.739
My very favorite.

02:12:49.800 --> 02:12:52.319
I didn't know dragons like him existed.

02:12:52.380 --> 02:12:54.420
If it seems like I don't miss him

02:12:54.420 --> 02:12:54.659
enough.

02:12:54.720 --> 02:12:56.939
It's because I'm trying so hard not to

02:12:56.939 --> 02:12:57.600
cry all the time.

02:12:57.659 --> 02:13:00.060
It feels like my wings have been cut

02:13:00.060 --> 02:13:00.300
off.

02:13:00.420 --> 02:13:02.579
But I know I have to keep going.

02:13:02.640 --> 02:13:06.060
Even on whatever stumps are left, because

02:13:06.060 --> 02:13:07.619
I'm not going to let this happen to him.

02:13:07.680 --> 02:13:11.220
Luna hadn't been quite ready for sharing

02:13:11.220 --> 02:13:12.180
all their feelings.

02:13:12.239 --> 02:13:15.300
She hadn't expected a hive wing of all

02:13:15.300 --> 02:13:18.359
dragons to just open up her chest, pull

02:13:18.359 --> 02:13:20.279
out all the pieces of her heart, and

02:13:20.279 --> 02:13:21.840
scatter them around on the sand like

02:13:21.840 --> 02:13:22.079
that.

02:13:22.079 --> 02:13:25.380
She wanted to stuff them back in, and

02:13:25.380 --> 02:13:27.659
wrap cricket in silk, so she'd have to

02:13:27.659 --> 02:13:29.880
act normal again, and they could pretend

02:13:29.880 --> 02:13:31.500
nobody here was on the verge of crying.

02:13:31.560 --> 02:13:34.380
To her enormous relief.

02:13:34.439 --> 02:13:36.840
Scuffling noises came from farther back

02:13:36.840 --> 02:13:37.500
in the cave.

02:13:37.560 --> 02:13:40.619
Luna turned toward the sound, and saw

02:13:40.619 --> 02:13:42.720
damp little human footprints come padding

02:13:42.720 --> 02:13:43.140
over the rocks.

02:13:43.260 --> 02:13:47.039
I think I found something, Wren's voice

02:13:47.039 --> 02:13:47.819
said breathlessly.

02:13:47.880 --> 02:13:49.859
Maybe a way to find the humans here.

02:13:49.920 --> 02:13:53.640
A flurry of sand and raindrops erupted

02:13:53.640 --> 02:13:54.479
from where cricket was sitting.

02:13:54.539 --> 02:13:55.680
Really?

02:13:55.739 --> 02:13:57.300
The hive wing cried.

02:13:57.359 --> 02:13:58.140
Did you see them?

02:13:58.199 --> 02:13:59.159
What were they doing?

02:13:59.220 --> 02:14:00.239
Did they have books with them?

02:14:00.300 --> 02:14:04.439
I didn't see any people yet, Ren said, but

02:14:04.439 --> 02:14:06.479
I found a human sized torch that was

02:14:06.479 --> 02:14:07.260
burned at one end.

02:14:07.319 --> 02:14:09.899
It's in this huge cave that has at least

02:14:09.899 --> 02:14:12.300
2 passageways out of it, the dragon's

02:14:12.300 --> 02:14:12.899
wouldn't fit into.

02:14:12.960 --> 02:14:15.960
I figured I'd search them, but I wanted

02:14:15.960 --> 02:14:16.920
to let Sky know first.

02:14:16.979 --> 02:14:19.979
I think he's on the beach, looking for

02:14:19.979 --> 02:14:22.380
turtles with bullfrog, Luna said.

02:14:22.439 --> 02:14:25.500
Oh, Skye, Ren said with a laugh.

02:14:25.560 --> 02:14:28.260
How did he bamboozle bullfrog into that?

02:14:28.380 --> 02:14:31.500
While Wren went out into the rain to find

02:14:31.500 --> 02:14:31.920
the others.

02:14:31.979 --> 02:14:34.439
Luna tried to focus on shaking off the

02:14:34.439 --> 02:14:35.579
fog in her head.

02:14:35.640 --> 02:14:38.760
They had something to do finally, besides

02:14:38.760 --> 02:14:39.479
sit and wait.

02:14:39.539 --> 02:14:43.380
The group needed her up energy, the let's

02:14:43.380 --> 02:14:44.819
do it, let's change things.

02:14:44.880 --> 02:14:46.979
Let's make a difference, Luna.

02:14:47.100 --> 02:14:48.420
Come on.

02:14:48.479 --> 02:14:50.100
I know I'm in there somewhere.

02:14:50.159 --> 02:14:53.520
Invisible wings came into the cave

02:14:53.520 --> 02:14:56.220
shaking off waterfalls of wet droplets.

02:14:56.279 --> 02:14:58.920
Ren's voice squeaked indignantly, and

02:14:58.920 --> 02:15:00.960
said something stern to sky in their part

02:15:00.960 --> 02:15:02.579
human, part dragon language.

02:15:02.640 --> 02:15:05.880
I hope we see a human, cricket said.

02:15:05.939 --> 02:15:07.979
Sundew said she saw one down here once.

02:15:08.100 --> 02:15:10.319
I wonder if it was in the same cavern.

02:15:10.439 --> 02:15:13.439
Ren's footprints pattered over to the

02:15:13.439 --> 02:15:15.180
spot where they'd burned a fire the last

02:15:15.180 --> 02:15:17.640
2 nights, and one of the long sticks

02:15:17.640 --> 02:15:18.539
floated up into the air.

02:15:18.600 --> 02:15:20.880
Luna or Bullfrog?

02:15:20.939 --> 02:15:21.899
Could you light this for me?

02:15:21.960 --> 02:15:24.420
I'll do it, Luna said.

02:15:24.479 --> 02:15:27.300
She put one talon on the free end of the

02:15:27.300 --> 02:15:30.300
stick, and let a coil of gold fire spiral

02:15:30.300 --> 02:15:31.920
out of her wrist to wind around the

02:15:31.920 --> 02:15:32.100
wood.

02:15:32.220 --> 02:15:35.159
The silk burned in a thin thread for a

02:15:35.159 --> 02:15:37.800
moment, and then it spread upward, until

02:15:37.800 --> 02:15:39.420
the end of the torch was alight with

02:15:39.420 --> 02:15:40.439
orange flame.

02:15:40.859 --> 02:15:43.020
Thanks, Luna, Ren said.

02:15:43.079 --> 02:15:45.060
All right, you can all follow me.

02:15:45.119 --> 02:15:47.880
But if we see any humans, don't scare

02:15:47.880 --> 02:15:48.539
them.

02:15:48.600 --> 02:15:50.699
I mean, I know they won't be able to see

02:15:50.699 --> 02:15:53.159
or hear us, but don't like, set anything

02:15:53.159 --> 02:15:54.960
on fire or try to pick them up.

02:15:55.020 --> 02:15:58.560
Or say, dump an ocean's worth of water on

02:15:58.560 --> 02:16:00.060
their heads by accident.

02:16:00.119 --> 02:16:03.899
Do you know what by accident even means?

02:16:04.020 --> 02:16:04.920
Sky demanded.

02:16:04.979 --> 02:16:07.680
The torch moved away to the back of the

02:16:07.680 --> 02:16:10.380
cave and Skye's voice followed, the 2 of

02:16:10.380 --> 02:16:11.579
them arguing affectionately.

02:16:11.640 --> 02:16:15.180
They sound like me and sore tail, Luna

02:16:15.180 --> 02:16:15.539
thought.

02:16:15.600 --> 02:16:18.600
For 3 years now, she'd been part of a

02:16:18.600 --> 02:16:19.020
pair.

02:16:19.079 --> 02:16:22.500
Luna and Sword Tail, Sore Tail and Luna

02:16:22.500 --> 02:16:25.199
She felt so strange and untethered

02:16:25.199 --> 02:16:27.720
without him, like threads of loose silk

02:16:27.720 --> 02:16:29.819
tied to a loom, but left out of the

02:16:29.819 --> 02:16:30.600
tapestry.

02:16:30.779 --> 02:16:33.719
The floating torch led them on a winding

02:16:33.719 --> 02:16:36.180
path. deeper into the dark underground

02:16:36.180 --> 02:16:39.239
labyrinth, until finally, it stopped near

02:16:39.239 --> 02:16:41.100
an archway where the tunnel opened into a

02:16:41.100 --> 02:16:41.879
bigger cave.

02:16:42.360 --> 02:16:45.000
All right, everyone, shh.

02:16:45.059 --> 02:16:47.579
Wren's voice said, from the area of the

02:16:47.579 --> 02:16:47.939
torch.

02:16:48.000 --> 02:16:49.680
Why?

02:16:49.739 --> 02:16:51.659
Sky demanded at full volume.

02:16:51.719 --> 02:16:54.179
We are not seeable and not hearable

02:16:54.179 --> 02:16:54.599
aren't we?

02:16:54.659 --> 02:16:55.979
La, la, la.

02:16:56.040 --> 02:16:57.840
I could sing all day, and it wouldn't

02:16:57.840 --> 02:16:58.200
bother anybody.

02:16:58.260 --> 02:17:02.280
Except us, Ren said.

02:17:02.340 --> 02:17:05.819
It would bother me and sh because I'm

02:17:05.819 --> 02:17:06.600
talking, that's why.

02:17:06.659 --> 02:17:08.520
This is the cave.

02:17:08.579 --> 02:17:11.399
I'm going to leave my torch here, so the

02:17:11.399 --> 02:17:13.620
humans don't see us coming, just in case

02:17:13.620 --> 02:17:14.700
there are any in there now.

02:17:14.760 --> 02:17:17.819
The burning stick floated over to the

02:17:17.819 --> 02:17:20.159
wall, and Wren tucked the end into a

02:17:20.159 --> 02:17:20.940
notch in the rocks.

02:17:21.000 --> 02:17:24.000
Make sure you don't disturb anything, in

02:17:24.000 --> 02:17:25.559
case they come back and notice and it

02:17:25.559 --> 02:17:26.100
scares them off.

02:17:26.159 --> 02:17:30.540
Are they really that smart?

02:17:30.600 --> 02:17:33.719
Bullfrog's voice asked skeptically.

02:17:33.780 --> 02:17:36.659
Luna could hear the frown in Wren's

02:17:36.659 --> 02:17:36.899
voice.

02:17:36.959 --> 02:17:38.519
Bullfrog?

02:17:38.579 --> 02:17:40.500
You do remember that I'm one of them

02:17:40.500 --> 02:17:40.920
right?

02:17:40.979 --> 02:17:43.319
The little human retorted.

02:17:43.379 --> 02:17:45.179
Right.

02:17:45.239 --> 02:17:46.620
Just...

02:17:46.620 --> 02:17:48.899
Thought you were...

02:17:49.020 --> 02:17:50.760
Different.

02:17:50.879 --> 02:17:51.479
Sorry.

02:17:51.540 --> 02:17:53.340
He ended in a mumble.

02:17:53.399 --> 02:17:57.180
She is special, but it turns out humans

02:17:57.180 --> 02:17:58.200
are pretty smart.

02:17:58.260 --> 02:18:01.739
Skye said suddenly, almost as smart as

02:18:01.739 --> 02:18:02.159
turtles.

02:18:02.280 --> 02:18:04.680
Not helping Skye.

02:18:04.739 --> 02:18:07.559
Their voices had moved off into the

02:18:07.559 --> 02:18:07.920
cave.

02:18:07.979 --> 02:18:10.500
So Luna stepped forward cautiously

02:18:10.500 --> 02:18:12.719
feeling the brush of cricket's tail ahead

02:18:12.719 --> 02:18:12.959
of her.

02:18:13.020 --> 02:18:16.680
It was a vast space, larger than the cave

02:18:16.680 --> 02:18:17.879
that opened onto the beach.

02:18:17.940 --> 02:18:20.040
Bigger even than the marketplace in

02:18:20.040 --> 02:18:20.879
Cicada Hive.

02:18:20.940 --> 02:18:24.000
Rock formations jutted from the floor and

02:18:24.000 --> 02:18:26.940
ceiling, like dragon teeth, some of them

02:18:26.940 --> 02:18:29.159
spiraled together into twisting columns

02:18:29.159 --> 02:18:32.340
dim sunlight, and trickles of rain

02:18:32.340 --> 02:18:34.260
spilled in from a few cracks in the roof

02:18:34.260 --> 02:18:37.799
water falling down the craggy walls, to a

02:18:37.799 --> 02:18:39.059
shallow pool on the far side.

02:18:39.120 --> 02:18:43.139
Luna tucked the space into her memory, the

02:18:43.139 --> 02:18:43.979
way she usually did.

02:18:44.040 --> 02:18:46.260
By imagining it as a tapestry.

02:18:46.379 --> 02:18:49.259
She pictured the silk colors she would

02:18:49.259 --> 02:18:51.659
use for the shades of gray shadows and

02:18:51.659 --> 02:18:54.539
golden spills of light, and how the sizes

02:18:54.539 --> 02:18:56.399
of the stalactites would give a sense of

02:18:56.399 --> 02:18:57.779
how far back the cave went.

02:18:57.840 --> 02:19:01.500
She kept her talons, and poured flame

02:19:01.500 --> 02:19:03.780
silk into them, choosing the kind that

02:19:03.780 --> 02:19:04.620
glowed without burning.

02:19:04.680 --> 02:19:07.200
Her father had told her about different

02:19:07.200 --> 02:19:09.299
kinds of flame silk in the brief half day

02:19:09.299 --> 02:19:10.139
she had had with him.

02:19:10.200 --> 02:19:13.319
He hadn't tartered very much, but she'd

02:19:13.319 --> 02:19:14.819
had way too much time to practice while

02:19:14.819 --> 02:19:17.280
she sat on the beach with Treboa, and by

02:19:17.280 --> 02:19:19.559
now, she could spend 5 different kinds of

02:19:19.559 --> 02:19:20.459
flame silk thread.

02:19:20.520 --> 02:19:24.000
The silk lit the area around her with a

02:19:24.000 --> 02:19:26.159
golden glow, so she could see more

02:19:26.159 --> 02:19:27.479
clearly into the shadows.

02:19:27.540 --> 02:19:29.940
It wasn't visible to the others, though

02:19:29.940 --> 02:19:32.040
or to any humans in the cave.

02:19:32.100 --> 02:19:34.200
Not unless she lit something else on

02:19:34.200 --> 02:19:34.500
fire.

02:19:34.620 --> 02:19:37.319
Here's the torch I found.

02:19:37.379 --> 02:19:39.839
Ren called from a ledge halfway up the

02:19:39.839 --> 02:19:40.859
wall to Luna's right.

02:19:40.920 --> 02:19:43.799
A stick, with a charred end waved in the

02:19:43.799 --> 02:19:43.979
air.

02:19:44.040 --> 02:19:46.860
Frayed bits of black thread clung to the

02:19:46.860 --> 02:19:48.840
wood, as though it had once had something

02:19:48.840 --> 02:19:50.340
wrapped around it to burn.

02:19:50.459 --> 02:19:53.459
And see, it's near this opening, which

02:19:53.459 --> 02:19:54.299
leads to a tunnel.

02:19:54.360 --> 02:19:56.100
I'm going to go in and see what I can

02:19:56.100 --> 02:19:56.340
find.

02:19:56.399 --> 02:19:58.440
You all look for more clues out here.

02:19:58.500 --> 02:20:01.020
Is that a good idea?

02:20:01.079 --> 02:20:03.120
Sky asked nervously.

02:20:03.180 --> 02:20:06.120
Couldn't I come with you if I squished?

02:20:06.180 --> 02:20:08.760
You're not an octopus.

02:20:08.819 --> 02:20:10.979
You big worry wart, Ren said.

02:20:11.040 --> 02:20:12.120
There's no way.

02:20:12.360 --> 02:20:15.420
Luna left them to their arguing and

02:20:15.420 --> 02:20:18.059
wandered deeper into the cave, peeking

02:20:18.059 --> 02:20:19.200
into all the dark corners.

02:20:19.260 --> 02:20:22.079
She could see why Wren was curious about

02:20:22.079 --> 02:20:22.440
this place.

02:20:22.500 --> 02:20:25.139
There were holes and possible tunnels

02:20:25.139 --> 02:20:27.600
everywhere, just the right size for the

02:20:27.600 --> 02:20:29.040
small, soft species.

02:20:29.100 --> 02:20:31.739
It would be easy for something Wren's

02:20:31.739 --> 02:20:33.659
size to vanish into the wall if a dragon

02:20:33.659 --> 02:20:34.079
came in.

02:20:34.139 --> 02:20:37.860
What if the abyss is down a human sized

02:20:37.860 --> 02:20:38.399
tunnel?

02:20:38.459 --> 02:20:39.780
Luna worried?

02:20:39.840 --> 02:20:42.840
What if it's buried in stone too deep for

02:20:42.840 --> 02:20:43.739
dragons to reach?

02:20:43.799 --> 02:20:47.040
She'd come to the far back wall of the

02:20:47.040 --> 02:20:49.620
cave. and was trying to peer into one of

02:20:49.620 --> 02:20:51.780
the little holes when she heard a faint

02:20:51.780 --> 02:20:52.620
rustling overhead.

02:20:52.680 --> 02:20:55.979
Luna stepped back and held up her flame

02:20:55.979 --> 02:20:58.319
silk, trying to see onto the shelf of

02:20:58.319 --> 02:20:59.100
rock above her.

02:20:59.159 --> 02:21:02.219
Farther up, nearer one of the slants of

02:21:02.219 --> 02:21:03.840
sunlight, something moved.

02:21:03.959 --> 02:21:07.620
It felt like the sudden fright of finding

02:21:07.620 --> 02:21:09.840
a spider pressed into a crack you thought

02:21:09.840 --> 02:21:11.159
was just a line in the wall.

02:21:11.280 --> 02:21:14.219
Luna gasped, and nearly stepped on her

02:21:14.219 --> 02:21:15.600
own tail as she tripped backward.

02:21:15.659 --> 02:21:17.639
On a ledge.

02:21:17.700 --> 02:21:20.879
Way up by the light, lying flat against

02:21:20.879 --> 02:21:23.700
the rocks, was a pale, soft looking

02:21:23.700 --> 02:21:26.340
creature with a thatch of dark fur on its

02:21:26.340 --> 02:21:26.579
head.

02:21:26.639 --> 02:21:30.719
They had found their 1st pentalin human.

02:21:30.840 --> 02:21:35.399
Chapter 7.

02:21:35.520 --> 02:21:39.059
The invisible dragons were crowded so

02:21:39.059 --> 02:21:41.159
close around the strange human's ledge

02:21:41.159 --> 02:21:43.500
the bullfrog kept stepping on Luna's

02:21:43.500 --> 02:21:43.920
talons.

02:21:44.040 --> 02:21:48.479
This is amazing, cricket said, for the

02:21:48.479 --> 02:21:49.559
900th time.

02:21:49.620 --> 02:21:51.659
It's not running away or anything.

02:21:51.719 --> 02:21:53.819
We can watch it for as long as we want.

02:21:53.879 --> 02:21:55.440
Look at how cute it is.

02:21:55.500 --> 02:21:57.180
Isn't it so cute?

02:21:57.239 --> 02:21:58.920
Don't worry, Ren, you're cute too.

02:21:58.979 --> 02:22:03.540
I most certainly am not, Ren's voice said

02:22:03.540 --> 02:22:04.739
from up near the human.

02:22:04.799 --> 02:22:07.200
She'd ordered Sky to lift her onto an

02:22:07.200 --> 02:22:08.700
outcropping so she could study the

02:22:08.700 --> 02:22:08.940
stranger.

02:22:09.059 --> 02:22:10.860
What is it doing?

02:22:10.920 --> 02:22:12.180
Cricket asked.

02:22:12.239 --> 02:22:13.020
Is it reading?

02:22:13.079 --> 02:22:14.639
It's looking at something, isn't it?

02:22:14.700 --> 02:22:17.639
Please try not to lose your mind when I

02:22:17.639 --> 02:22:18.120
tell you this?

02:22:18.239 --> 02:22:19.319
Ren said.

02:22:19.379 --> 02:22:21.479
This human seems to be comparing a

02:22:21.479 --> 02:22:24.059
regular book to a dragon sized book.

02:22:24.120 --> 02:22:27.659
Cricket gave a muffled gasp, and Luna

02:22:27.659 --> 02:22:29.219
felt her wings fluttering in the air.

02:22:29.280 --> 02:22:32.459
Or are reading both of them at the same

02:22:32.459 --> 02:22:33.239
time or something?

02:22:33.299 --> 02:22:36.600
But I don't think that's possible, Ren

02:22:36.600 --> 02:22:36.959
said.

02:22:37.079 --> 02:22:40.020
I mean, they're looking very closely at

02:22:40.020 --> 02:22:42.000
the pictures in the Dragon book, but I

02:22:42.000 --> 02:22:43.319
don't think they can actually read it.

02:22:43.440 --> 02:22:46.379
Where did it get a dragon book?

02:22:46.440 --> 02:22:47.700
Cricket burst out.

02:22:47.760 --> 02:22:49.260
Which book is it?

02:22:49.319 --> 02:22:51.360
What's the human sized book about?

02:22:51.479 --> 02:22:54.959
I have no idea, ran answered.

02:22:55.020 --> 02:22:57.479
A far away sound came from beyond the

02:22:57.479 --> 02:22:58.079
rock wall.

02:22:58.139 --> 02:23:00.479
And the strange human suddenly sat up and

02:23:00.479 --> 02:23:01.260
turned toward it.

02:23:01.319 --> 02:23:02.760
The sound came again.

02:23:02.819 --> 02:23:05.940
With something that looked astonishingly

02:23:05.940 --> 02:23:07.260
like a dragon's sigh.

02:23:07.379 --> 02:23:09.659
The human folded its books into a covered

02:23:09.659 --> 02:23:11.940
sort of parcel, tucked that safely

02:23:11.940 --> 02:23:14.399
between 2 dry rocks, and then darted

02:23:14.399 --> 02:23:16.200
through a small hole that Luna hadn't

02:23:16.200 --> 02:23:16.500
even noticed.

02:23:16.559 --> 02:23:18.420
Oh, no!

02:23:18.479 --> 02:23:19.559
Cricket yelped.

02:23:19.620 --> 02:23:20.520
Why did it leave?

02:23:20.639 --> 02:23:23.819
I think someone was calling them, Ren

02:23:23.819 --> 02:23:24.299
said.

02:23:24.360 --> 02:23:26.159
I'm going to follow and see where they

02:23:26.159 --> 02:23:26.399
go.

02:23:26.459 --> 02:23:27.299
Back soon.

02:23:27.360 --> 02:23:30.239
There was a little thump as she leaped to

02:23:30.239 --> 02:23:32.219
the human's ledge, and then she was gone

02:23:32.219 --> 02:23:32.639
too.

02:23:32.760 --> 02:23:34.799
Ren?

02:23:34.860 --> 02:23:36.420
Sky called nervously.

02:23:36.479 --> 02:23:37.739
But she didn't respond.

02:23:37.799 --> 02:23:41.100
Luna heard snuffling noises up by the

02:23:41.100 --> 02:23:43.319
human's tunnel as though Sky was trying

02:23:43.319 --> 02:23:44.819
to squash his snout into it.

02:23:44.879 --> 02:23:47.459
Can we look at the books the human left

02:23:47.459 --> 02:23:47.819
behind?

02:23:47.879 --> 02:23:49.020
Cricket asked.

02:23:49.079 --> 02:23:50.940
We shouldn't.

02:23:51.000 --> 02:23:53.459
We might damage them, Luna said.

02:23:53.520 --> 02:23:55.739
Ren said not to touch anything in case

02:23:55.739 --> 02:23:56.399
they notice.

02:23:56.459 --> 02:23:56.879
Remember?

02:23:56.940 --> 02:23:59.700
Cricket made a frustrated noise.

02:23:59.760 --> 02:24:02.219
But she said...

02:24:02.280 --> 02:24:02.819
You're right.

02:24:02.879 --> 02:24:05.280
Maybe Ren can get them out for us when

02:24:05.280 --> 02:24:05.760
she comes back.

02:24:05.819 --> 02:24:10.020
Ren was gone for a long, long time.

02:24:10.079 --> 02:24:12.899
Bullfrog eventually went out to find food

02:24:12.899 --> 02:24:15.239
for everyone, and Luna paced around the

02:24:15.239 --> 02:24:16.680
cavern until she knew every corner.

02:24:16.739 --> 02:24:19.260
She bumped into sky several times.

02:24:19.319 --> 02:24:21.120
He appeared to be doing the same thing.

02:24:21.180 --> 02:24:23.399
Maybe cricket was too.

02:24:23.459 --> 02:24:25.799
But if so, she was better at dodging

02:24:25.799 --> 02:24:26.040
them.

02:24:26.100 --> 02:24:29.520
It is so weird to think Blue might have

02:24:29.520 --> 02:24:32.219
found his someone, and she's a hive wing

02:24:32.219 --> 02:24:34.799
who overshares and is obsessed with

02:24:34.799 --> 02:24:35.520
humans and books.

02:24:35.579 --> 02:24:38.040
Not exactly who I would have pictured him

02:24:38.040 --> 02:24:38.459
with.

02:24:38.520 --> 02:24:41.459
How would I even make a wedding tapestry

02:24:41.459 --> 02:24:41.760
for them?

02:24:41.819 --> 02:24:43.860
Their colors would totally clash.

02:24:43.920 --> 02:24:48.059
No, they wouldn't, she admitted.

02:24:48.120 --> 02:24:50.040
She couldn't lie to herself about

02:24:50.040 --> 02:24:50.459
weaving.

02:24:50.579 --> 02:24:55.139
Azure blue, lavender violet, orange gold

02:24:55.139 --> 02:24:55.680
and black.

02:24:55.739 --> 02:24:59.040
Fine, I bet they'd be really pretty.

02:24:59.100 --> 02:25:02.280
She suddenly had a startling thought.

02:25:02.340 --> 02:25:06.360
What if we somehow saved the world, but

02:25:06.360 --> 02:25:08.579
never find sundo, or the magic

02:25:08.579 --> 02:25:09.299
wristbands?

02:25:09.360 --> 02:25:11.639
What if we're stuck invisible forever?

02:25:11.700 --> 02:25:15.239
Blue and Sortail would have to learn to

02:25:15.239 --> 02:25:16.920
live with invisible girlfriends.

02:25:16.979 --> 02:25:19.379
That might be easier, actually.

02:25:19.440 --> 02:25:21.959
No one would judge blue and cricket for

02:25:21.959 --> 02:25:24.540
liking each other across tribes, and I

02:25:24.540 --> 02:25:26.760
wouldn't have to think, back, hive wing

02:25:26.760 --> 02:25:28.079
every time I saw her.

02:25:28.139 --> 02:25:31.620
If I had met her as a voice and never saw

02:25:31.620 --> 02:25:33.659
her scales, would I like her better?

02:25:33.719 --> 02:25:36.899
She thought about the day she'd met Sore

02:25:36.899 --> 02:25:37.200
Tail.

02:25:37.260 --> 02:25:39.899
I'd have fallen for him no matter what he

02:25:39.899 --> 02:25:42.000
looked like, or which tribe he was from

02:25:42.000 --> 02:25:42.659
wouldn't I?

02:25:42.780 --> 02:25:45.959
It had been her 1st day at Silkworm

02:25:45.959 --> 02:25:46.319
Hall.

02:25:46.379 --> 02:25:48.600
And it had started as a sunny season

02:25:48.600 --> 02:25:49.440
morning in her mind.

02:25:49.500 --> 02:25:52.559
She'd been so excited to finally go to

02:25:52.559 --> 02:25:54.899
school, where she could learn to read and

02:25:54.899 --> 02:25:57.420
weave, and how laws worked, and why

02:25:57.420 --> 02:25:59.879
things just have to be this way, Luna.

02:25:59.940 --> 02:26:02.340
And how to make big old main dragons

02:26:02.340 --> 02:26:03.000
listen to you.

02:26:03.059 --> 02:26:06.120
But everything started to go wrong at the

02:26:06.120 --> 02:26:07.020
entrance to the hive.

02:26:07.079 --> 02:26:09.540
When the guards there had roughly clamped

02:26:09.540 --> 02:26:12.059
on her metal wrist cuff inscribed with

02:26:12.059 --> 02:26:12.600
the name of the school.

02:26:12.659 --> 02:26:16.079
It had been so unexpectedly heavy that

02:26:16.079 --> 02:26:18.479
she'd yelped, and the hive wing putting

02:26:18.479 --> 02:26:19.680
it on had sneered at her.

02:26:19.739 --> 02:26:23.100
Too bad we're Silkworm Hall, getting a

02:26:23.100 --> 02:26:25.739
whining little caterpillar like you, he'd

02:26:25.739 --> 02:26:26.219
hissed.

02:26:26.280 --> 02:26:28.260
I'm not whining.

02:26:28.319 --> 02:26:31.319
Luna had huffed, ignoring blue when he

02:26:31.319 --> 02:26:32.159
nudged her in the side.

02:26:32.280 --> 02:26:34.500
I don't think it's supposed to be this

02:26:34.500 --> 02:26:34.860
heavy.

02:26:34.920 --> 02:26:36.479
It is.

02:26:36.540 --> 02:26:38.280
The hive wing had snapped.

02:26:38.340 --> 02:26:39.059
Move along.

02:26:39.120 --> 02:26:43.139
Don't let the fog in, Luna had ordered

02:26:43.139 --> 02:26:43.500
herself.

02:26:43.559 --> 02:26:46.319
Don't let one mean dragon ruin your day.

02:26:46.379 --> 02:26:49.799
But the dragons who ran Solgorum Hall

02:26:49.799 --> 02:26:50.579
weren't any kinder.

02:26:50.639 --> 02:26:53.879
Some of the teachers were silk wings, but

02:26:53.879 --> 02:26:55.799
the administration was all hive wings.

02:26:55.860 --> 02:26:58.200
There were prickly guards at the doors

02:26:58.200 --> 02:27:00.719
and the walls were thick, with no windows

02:27:00.719 --> 02:27:01.739
and no sunlight at all.

02:27:01.799 --> 02:27:04.799
Students crowded the narrow corridors

02:27:04.799 --> 02:27:06.000
quiet and listless.

02:27:06.059 --> 02:27:09.059
She was separated from blue and given a

02:27:09.059 --> 02:27:09.540
different schedule.

02:27:09.600 --> 02:27:13.379
Teachers snapped at her to sit, be quiet

02:27:13.379 --> 02:27:16.500
stop asking questions, fold in her tail

02:27:16.500 --> 02:27:18.959
eat silently, wait for permission to

02:27:18.959 --> 02:27:20.819
speak, which never came.

02:27:20.879 --> 02:27:25.020
By recess, Luna was in the grip of one of

02:27:25.020 --> 02:27:27.180
the worst sadnesses she'd ever felt.

02:27:27.180 --> 02:27:30.239
She knew she couldn't let herself cry at

02:27:30.239 --> 02:27:30.659
school.

02:27:30.719 --> 02:27:33.059
And if she escaped out the front gates

02:27:33.059 --> 02:27:35.159
and ran back to the safety of the webs

02:27:35.159 --> 02:27:36.840
she'd only be in worse trouble later.

02:27:36.899 --> 02:27:40.139
But her wrist hurt, and her heart hurt

02:27:40.139 --> 02:27:42.000
and she did know how she would make it

02:27:42.000 --> 02:27:42.959
through the rest of the day.

02:27:43.020 --> 02:27:47.100
Recess, apparently meant standing or

02:27:47.100 --> 02:27:48.899
marching around an open balcony on the

02:27:48.899 --> 02:27:50.159
side of Cicada Hive.

02:27:50.159 --> 02:27:52.799
It was boring, but at least there was

02:27:52.799 --> 02:27:54.299
sunlight and wind.

02:27:54.360 --> 02:27:56.700
Luna tried to breathe in all the air she

02:27:56.700 --> 02:27:57.840
could fit into her lungs.

02:27:57.899 --> 02:28:01.200
Bit close to the edge there, aren't you?

02:28:01.319 --> 02:28:03.420
An older voice growled.

02:28:03.479 --> 02:28:06.180
She turned and saw one of the high wing

02:28:06.180 --> 02:28:08.040
guards approaching a student, who was

02:28:08.040 --> 02:28:09.059
looking out at the savannah.

02:28:09.120 --> 02:28:11.700
The little silk wing was not all that

02:28:11.700 --> 02:28:13.020
close to the balcony railing.

02:28:13.139 --> 02:28:15.180
And he blinked up at the hive wing and

02:28:15.180 --> 02:28:15.540
confusion.

02:28:15.600 --> 02:28:17.520
Me?

02:28:17.579 --> 02:28:18.600
he squeaked.

02:28:18.659 --> 02:28:21.540
His scales were light pink and lime green

02:28:21.540 --> 02:28:23.879
with hints of darker rose inside his wing

02:28:23.879 --> 02:28:24.299
buds.

02:28:24.360 --> 02:28:26.459
Luna had math class with him.

02:28:26.520 --> 02:28:29.219
Glider, if she remembered right.

02:28:29.280 --> 02:28:32.219
Seems a little dangerous worm.

02:28:32.280 --> 02:28:35.459
The hive wing smirked, looming over the

02:28:35.459 --> 02:28:38.399
wingless dragonette, he inched back, and

02:28:38.399 --> 02:28:39.299
she stepped closer.

02:28:39.360 --> 02:28:41.879
The balcony edge was a few steps behind

02:28:41.879 --> 02:28:42.360
him now.

02:28:42.420 --> 02:28:45.600
Without any wings, you could tip right

02:28:45.600 --> 02:28:48.780
over, and just think how far you'd have

02:28:48.780 --> 02:28:49.139
to fall.

02:28:49.200 --> 02:28:52.079
All that time to contemplate the giant

02:28:52.079 --> 02:28:53.940
splat you'll make at the end.

02:28:54.000 --> 02:28:58.079
I don't, don't, I didn't mean to.

02:28:58.559 --> 02:28:59.940
Can I please go inside now?

02:29:00.000 --> 02:29:01.920
Glider stammered.

02:29:01.979 --> 02:29:04.680
He risked a glance over his shoulder as

02:29:04.680 --> 02:29:05.520
she crowded him back.

02:29:05.579 --> 02:29:08.639
The balcony railing was only as high as

02:29:08.639 --> 02:29:09.959
the student's wing buds.

02:29:10.020 --> 02:29:12.540
It looked like it had been built as an

02:29:12.540 --> 02:29:13.079
afterthought.

02:29:13.200 --> 02:29:15.059
Oh, right.

02:29:15.120 --> 02:29:17.760
Silkwing dragonettes have no wings.

02:29:17.819 --> 02:29:19.920
We should pretend we care about their

02:29:19.920 --> 02:29:22.260
safety, but don't waste too much tree

02:29:22.260 --> 02:29:24.059
stuff on this since we don't really.

02:29:24.120 --> 02:29:26.700
It would not be hard to fall over it.

02:29:26.760 --> 02:29:28.920
Or be pushed over it.

02:29:29.040 --> 02:29:33.299
We lose at least one dragonette every

02:29:33.299 --> 02:29:36.899
year, the hive wing said, in a fake sad

02:29:36.899 --> 02:29:37.440
voice.

02:29:37.500 --> 02:29:40.620
Poor little brainless worms who aren't

02:29:40.620 --> 02:29:42.360
careful enough.

02:29:42.420 --> 02:29:45.719
She took another step, and glider

02:29:45.719 --> 02:29:46.500
squeaked with fear.

02:29:46.559 --> 02:29:48.059
Stop that.

02:29:48.180 --> 02:29:49.559
Luna said.

02:29:49.620 --> 02:29:52.139
She was startled to hear her own voice

02:29:52.139 --> 02:29:54.239
lancing through the silk fog around her.

02:29:54.299 --> 02:29:56.639
It felt like bright little flames of

02:29:56.639 --> 02:29:58.559
anger were burning holes in her sadness.

02:29:58.620 --> 02:30:01.139
Why are you being so mean?

02:30:01.200 --> 02:30:03.120
You're scaring him just to be awful?

02:30:03.239 --> 02:30:06.239
Most of the other silkwing students

02:30:06.239 --> 02:30:08.819
stared at her with wide, terrified eyes.

02:30:08.879 --> 02:30:10.799
The hive wing flicked her tail.

02:30:10.920 --> 02:30:13.200
We are dangerous looking stinger gleamed

02:30:13.200 --> 02:30:15.299
and turned her head slowly to glare at

02:30:15.299 --> 02:30:15.719
Luna.

02:30:15.780 --> 02:30:18.600
A worm with a voice.

02:30:18.659 --> 02:30:20.819
Hissed the guard.

02:30:20.879 --> 02:30:21.959
Gross.

02:30:22.020 --> 02:30:24.479
No one has ever taught you your place

02:30:24.479 --> 02:30:24.840
have they?

02:30:24.899 --> 02:30:28.079
Has anyone ever taught you basic

02:30:28.079 --> 02:30:28.559
decency?

02:30:28.620 --> 02:30:30.000
Luna demanded.

02:30:30.120 --> 02:30:32.159
How to be a dragon with a heart?

02:30:32.219 --> 02:30:34.559
Or were all your classes about acting

02:30:34.559 --> 02:30:36.719
like a pile of poisonous sludge to anyone

02:30:36.719 --> 02:30:37.440
smaller than you?

02:30:37.500 --> 02:30:41.040
There were audible gasps from the rest of

02:30:41.040 --> 02:30:43.680
the class, who started edging away as

02:30:43.680 --> 02:30:45.000
fast as they could sidle.

02:30:45.059 --> 02:30:47.819
The hive wing stepped toward her and

02:30:47.819 --> 02:30:49.379
raised her tail menacingly.

02:30:49.440 --> 02:30:52.379
Glider slipped away from the railing and

02:30:52.379 --> 02:30:54.540
bolted back into the school, but the

02:30:54.540 --> 02:30:55.260
guard didn't notice.

02:30:55.319 --> 02:30:58.739
Now the little worms end up on

02:30:58.739 --> 02:30:59.940
misbehaviors way.

02:31:00.000 --> 02:31:01.920
The hive wing snarled.

02:31:01.979 --> 02:31:04.739
But I get to paralyze you with my tail

02:31:04.739 --> 02:31:06.299
toxin first.

02:31:06.360 --> 02:31:07.799
I hear it's quite painful.

02:31:07.860 --> 02:31:10.920
Oh, no!

02:31:10.979 --> 02:31:13.979
shouted a voice on the far side of the

02:31:13.979 --> 02:31:14.340
balcony.

02:31:14.399 --> 02:31:16.860
Everyone hustled out of the way as the

02:31:16.860 --> 02:31:17.819
guard whirled around.

02:31:17.879 --> 02:31:20.700
The shouting dragonette was a little bit

02:31:20.700 --> 02:31:21.540
older than Luna.

02:31:21.600 --> 02:31:24.420
He was dark blue, with several small

02:31:24.420 --> 02:31:27.180
white triangular scales and larger orange

02:31:27.180 --> 02:31:28.020
splotches.

02:31:28.079 --> 02:31:31.200
And he was standing on the railing of the

02:31:31.200 --> 02:31:31.620
balcony.

02:31:31.739 --> 02:31:35.760
I got you close to the edge, he yelled.

02:31:35.819 --> 02:31:37.319
I wasn't careful enough.

02:31:37.440 --> 02:31:40.979
I was just wandering around, exactly like

02:31:40.979 --> 02:31:43.260
a worm with no brains, and suddenly I

02:31:43.260 --> 02:31:45.000
ended up here on this railing.

02:31:45.059 --> 02:31:47.159
Oh no, the horror.

02:31:47.219 --> 02:31:49.379
I'm probably going to go splat.

02:31:49.440 --> 02:31:51.360
I'm such a brainless worm.

02:31:51.420 --> 02:31:52.860
Tragic day.

02:31:52.920 --> 02:31:54.239
Poor world.

02:31:54.299 --> 02:31:56.340
What are you going to do without sword

02:31:56.340 --> 02:31:56.700
tail?

02:31:56.819 --> 02:32:00.180
The hive wing guard goggled at him.

02:32:00.239 --> 02:32:02.340
Luna could not imagine what her own face

02:32:02.340 --> 02:32:02.760
was doing.

02:32:02.819 --> 02:32:06.659
If only someone had warned me about going

02:32:06.659 --> 02:32:08.520
Splat!

02:32:08.639 --> 02:32:10.440
The dragon had howled.

02:32:10.500 --> 02:32:13.260
If only some brilliant hive wing had

02:32:13.260 --> 02:32:15.600
reminded me I have no wings and should be

02:32:15.600 --> 02:32:16.680
careful in tall places.

02:32:16.739 --> 02:32:20.159
Alas, alack, woe and despair.

02:32:20.219 --> 02:32:22.799
Get down from there.

02:32:22.860 --> 02:32:25.379
The hive wing snapped furiously.

02:32:25.440 --> 02:32:27.360
Get down right now.

02:32:27.420 --> 02:32:30.840
Luna saw a strange flare of something in

02:32:30.840 --> 02:32:31.680
the hive wing's eyes.

02:32:31.739 --> 02:32:34.860
And she suddenly realized that the guard

02:32:34.860 --> 02:32:36.899
was never intending to push glider over

02:32:36.899 --> 02:32:37.260
the edge.

02:32:37.319 --> 02:32:40.440
The hivewing wanted to scare them and

02:32:40.440 --> 02:32:41.579
prove her power over them.

02:32:41.700 --> 02:32:45.000
But if any of them actually fell, she'd

02:32:45.000 --> 02:32:46.200
be in big trouble.

02:32:46.260 --> 02:32:48.899
Get down from here?

02:32:48.959 --> 02:32:51.600
Swordell echoed, looking thoroughly

02:32:51.600 --> 02:32:52.200
befuddled.

02:32:52.260 --> 02:32:53.819
But how?

02:32:53.879 --> 02:32:55.200
Which way do I go?

02:32:55.260 --> 02:32:58.079
I'm much too stupid to figure this out

02:32:58.079 --> 02:32:58.319
myself.

02:32:58.379 --> 02:33:01.920
He took a wobbling step along the railing

02:33:01.920 --> 02:33:03.840
and flailed around as though he couldn't

02:33:03.840 --> 02:33:04.379
get his balance.

02:33:04.500 --> 02:33:08.399
The hive wing charged over and yanked him

02:33:08.399 --> 02:33:09.479
onto the safety of the floor.

02:33:09.540 --> 02:33:11.639
What are you playing at?

02:33:11.700 --> 02:33:13.200
She snarled.

02:33:13.260 --> 02:33:15.299
You're going straight to the headmaster

02:33:15.299 --> 02:33:18.059
and you too. she barked, pointing at

02:33:18.059 --> 02:33:18.479
Luna.

02:33:18.540 --> 02:33:22.079
I know you know the way, the hive wing

02:33:22.079 --> 02:33:23.879
added, scowling at sword tail.

02:33:23.940 --> 02:33:27.299
I do, Sortail said cheerfully.

02:33:27.360 --> 02:33:29.940
He sauntered over and bumped Luna's side

02:33:29.940 --> 02:33:30.420
with a grin.

02:33:30.479 --> 02:33:32.579
Come along, troublemaker.

02:33:32.700 --> 02:33:36.059
Luna glanced around the balcony, but

02:33:36.059 --> 02:33:37.860
everyone else was studiously avoiding her

02:33:37.860 --> 02:33:38.219
gaze.

02:33:38.280 --> 02:33:40.979
Why hadn't any of them stuck up for

02:33:40.979 --> 02:33:42.959
Glider or tried to stop the guards

02:33:42.959 --> 02:33:43.739
bullying?

02:33:43.799 --> 02:33:45.299
Were they all too scared?

02:33:45.360 --> 02:33:48.959
The dark blue dragonette led the way into

02:33:48.959 --> 02:33:51.420
the school and down a couple of levels

02:33:51.420 --> 02:33:53.520
then stopped in a deserted corridor and

02:33:53.520 --> 02:33:55.319
sat down, beaming at her.

02:33:55.379 --> 02:33:58.440
That was wild, he said.

02:33:58.500 --> 02:33:59.940
You are boggers.

02:34:00.000 --> 02:34:01.620
Me?

02:34:01.680 --> 02:34:04.020
Luna protested, but she couldn't help

02:34:04.020 --> 02:34:04.620
smiling back.

02:34:04.680 --> 02:34:07.620
You're the one who nearly ended up a silk

02:34:07.620 --> 02:34:09.059
wing pancake on the savannah.

02:34:09.120 --> 02:34:11.280
I'm surprised she didn't shove you over

02:34:11.280 --> 02:34:12.540
the way you were carrying on.

02:34:12.600 --> 02:34:15.899
They're getting used to me, he said with

02:34:15.899 --> 02:34:16.319
a shrug.

02:34:16.379 --> 02:34:19.559
Yelling at a guard on your 1st day

02:34:19.559 --> 02:34:19.799
though?

02:34:19.860 --> 02:34:22.020
What's the plan for day two?

02:34:22.079 --> 02:34:23.879
Drawing trees all over the walls?

02:34:23.940 --> 02:34:25.260
No, wait.

02:34:25.319 --> 02:34:27.360
Announcing at lunch that you're starting

02:34:27.360 --> 02:34:29.219
a rebellion against Queen Wasp?

02:34:29.340 --> 02:34:32.219
He must have seen something in her face

02:34:32.219 --> 02:34:34.979
because he added quickly, I'm just

02:34:34.979 --> 02:34:35.340
kidding.

02:34:35.399 --> 02:34:35.940
Don't do that.

02:34:36.000 --> 02:34:38.579
I mean, save it for day 5 at least.

02:34:38.639 --> 02:34:42.959
Luna giggled, and realized this was the

02:34:42.959 --> 02:34:44.819
lightest she'd felt since stepping into

02:34:44.819 --> 02:34:45.780
Silkworm Hall.

02:34:45.840 --> 02:34:49.200
I'm pretty sure announcing your rebellion

02:34:49.200 --> 02:34:51.479
isn't the best way to start, she said.

02:34:51.540 --> 02:34:53.579
Mine will be stealthier than that.

02:34:53.639 --> 02:34:57.000
In fact, I just recruited you. and you

02:34:57.000 --> 02:34:57.659
didn't even notice.

02:34:57.780 --> 02:34:59.700
Really?

02:34:59.760 --> 02:35:00.600
he said.

02:35:00.659 --> 02:35:02.819
I'm leading a secret rebellion now?

02:35:02.879 --> 02:35:06.719
No, no, I'm leading it, she said.

02:35:06.780 --> 02:35:08.520
You're the comic relief.

02:35:08.579 --> 02:35:09.719
He laughed.

02:35:09.780 --> 02:35:11.219
That sounds about right.

02:35:11.280 --> 02:35:13.139
I'm SwordTail, by the way.

02:35:13.200 --> 02:35:15.840
Oh, I know, she said.

02:35:15.899 --> 02:35:18.420
The one this poor world would miss so

02:35:18.420 --> 02:35:18.840
terribly.

02:35:18.899 --> 02:35:20.520
Very dramatic.

02:35:20.579 --> 02:35:21.959
I'm Luna.

02:35:22.020 --> 02:35:24.780
It is thrilling to meet you, Luna.

02:35:24.899 --> 02:35:26.700
Sortail dipped his head.

02:35:26.760 --> 02:35:29.219
I'm so excited there's finally someone

02:35:29.219 --> 02:35:31.319
here who might cause even half as much

02:35:31.319 --> 02:35:31.920
trouble as I do.

02:35:31.979 --> 02:35:35.760
Speaking of which, I guess we'd better

02:35:35.760 --> 02:35:38.399
get to the headmaster, Luna said with a

02:35:38.399 --> 02:35:38.639
sigh.

02:35:38.639 --> 02:35:41.579
Let's not and say we did.

02:35:41.700 --> 02:35:43.319
Swordell suggested.

02:35:43.379 --> 02:35:45.780
The guards never check if we actually

02:35:45.780 --> 02:35:46.440
make it there.

02:35:46.500 --> 02:35:48.299
They just want us out from under their

02:35:48.299 --> 02:35:48.780
own claws.

02:35:48.840 --> 02:35:50.879
Have you seen the art room yet?

02:35:50.940 --> 02:35:53.159
The art room?

02:35:53.280 --> 02:35:56.159
Luna echoed, her spirits floating up to

02:35:56.159 --> 02:35:56.579
the ceiling.

02:35:56.639 --> 02:35:59.639
It's the best part of the day, he said.

02:35:59.700 --> 02:36:01.680
I thought you might like something to

02:36:01.680 --> 02:36:02.219
look forward to.

02:36:02.280 --> 02:36:05.819
Yes, please, she said.

02:36:05.879 --> 02:36:08.520
She followed him around the corner, and

02:36:08.520 --> 02:36:10.260
threw a wide doorway into a huge room

02:36:10.260 --> 02:36:12.180
that was covered in weavings.

02:36:12.239 --> 02:36:15.120
Looms were set up all over the space.

02:36:15.180 --> 02:36:17.340
Most of them with partly finished

02:36:17.340 --> 02:36:20.100
projects, waving little rainbow and white

02:36:20.100 --> 02:36:21.180
tendrils at her.

02:36:21.239 --> 02:36:24.059
There were still no windows, but one

02:36:24.059 --> 02:36:25.739
entire wall was covered with a giant

02:36:25.739 --> 02:36:29.159
woven skyscape, bright blue, with golden

02:36:29.159 --> 02:36:31.860
clouds and sunlight, and 100s of dragons

02:36:31.860 --> 02:36:34.860
in flight, most of them silk wings, Luna

02:36:34.860 --> 02:36:35.280
noticed.

02:36:35.340 --> 02:36:39.180
She stepped closer to the skyscape, hardly

02:36:39.180 --> 02:36:40.319
able to breathe.

02:36:40.379 --> 02:36:42.719
This was what she wanted to do with her

02:36:42.719 --> 02:36:42.959
life.

02:36:43.020 --> 02:36:45.840
Make things so beautiful, they could fix

02:36:45.840 --> 02:36:46.799
a dragon's heart.

02:36:46.860 --> 02:36:49.860
She wanted to use her own talons and silk

02:36:49.860 --> 02:36:52.260
to weave tapestries as powerful as

02:36:52.260 --> 02:36:52.739
sunshine.

02:36:52.799 --> 02:36:56.100
She wanted her art to reach into other

02:36:56.100 --> 02:36:59.100
dragons and lift the clouds away, to give

02:36:59.100 --> 02:37:00.719
them a reason to spread their wings and

02:37:00.719 --> 02:37:01.260
keep flying.

02:37:01.379 --> 02:37:04.979
This tapestry was the world as it could

02:37:04.979 --> 02:37:05.219
be.

02:37:05.280 --> 02:37:07.979
All these silk wings were free.

02:37:08.040 --> 02:37:09.420
Luna knew it.

02:37:09.479 --> 02:37:11.399
She felt it all through her scales.

02:37:11.459 --> 02:37:14.219
Maybe the hive wings couldn't tell when

02:37:14.219 --> 02:37:16.620
they looked at it, but Luna knew this was

02:37:16.620 --> 02:37:17.760
the world she dreamed of.

02:37:17.879 --> 02:37:22.139
Miss Clorin did that, Sortell said.

02:37:22.260 --> 02:37:25.200
She's the art teacher, and a silk wing

02:37:25.200 --> 02:37:25.440
obviously.

02:37:25.500 --> 02:37:29.760
It's amazing, Luna said reverently.

02:37:29.819 --> 02:37:33.239
Almost as good as mine, Sortell said

02:37:33.239 --> 02:37:35.520
cuffing up his chest and strutting over

02:37:35.520 --> 02:37:37.979
to a display, where a small blue and

02:37:37.979 --> 02:37:39.000
orange tapestry hung.

02:37:39.059 --> 02:37:41.340
It looked as though a spider had gotten

02:37:41.340 --> 02:37:43.379
tangled in the threads and run amok

02:37:43.379 --> 02:37:45.899
leaving trails of white zigzags all over

02:37:45.899 --> 02:37:46.799
the blocky background.

02:37:46.860 --> 02:37:50.159
Oh, uh, Luna said.

02:37:50.219 --> 02:37:52.559
Very um...

02:37:53.340 --> 02:37:55.020
Would you believe there are people who

02:37:55.020 --> 02:37:55.799
can't read this?

02:37:55.860 --> 02:37:58.739
Sortel said, poking the zigzags.

02:37:58.799 --> 02:38:00.420
Luna squinted at it.

02:38:00.479 --> 02:38:02.340
Those are letters?

02:38:02.340 --> 02:38:03.120
she asked.

02:38:03.180 --> 02:38:07.379
It says sword tail, he declared

02:38:07.379 --> 02:38:08.219
indignantly.

02:38:08.280 --> 02:38:09.479
Very clearly.

02:38:09.600 --> 02:38:14.100
Of course, yes, clearly, she agreed.

02:38:14.159 --> 02:38:17.219
She touched one of the empty looms, her

02:38:17.219 --> 02:38:19.020
claws yearning to strum the chords.

02:38:19.079 --> 02:38:21.420
When can I start a weaving?

02:38:21.479 --> 02:38:24.360
Probably today, he said.

02:38:24.420 --> 02:38:26.040
It's one of our daily classes.

02:38:26.159 --> 02:38:28.500
Apparently weaving is one of the few

02:38:28.500 --> 02:38:30.600
things we're good for, so we'd better

02:38:30.600 --> 02:38:31.739
learn how to do it well.

02:38:31.799 --> 02:38:34.680
Lucky for us, Ms. Clorin is great.

02:38:34.739 --> 02:38:37.620
Don't tell any hive wings, or they'll

02:38:37.620 --> 02:38:38.459
probably take her away.

02:38:38.520 --> 02:38:41.219
Mustn't let those wingless dragonettes

02:38:41.219 --> 02:38:42.120
have any fun or joy.

02:38:42.239 --> 02:38:45.840
I hate that, Luna burst out.

02:38:45.899 --> 02:38:47.340
Why is it like that?

02:38:47.399 --> 02:38:49.500
Why do they want us to be miserable?

02:38:49.559 --> 02:38:52.139
Why can't we decide for ourselves where

02:38:52.139 --> 02:38:54.840
we go to school or what we study, or who

02:38:54.840 --> 02:38:56.940
our teachers are, or whether we have

02:38:56.940 --> 02:38:58.860
windows in our classrooms by all the

02:38:58.860 --> 02:38:59.219
moons?

02:38:59.280 --> 02:39:03.899
I don't know, he said, really looking at

02:39:03.899 --> 02:39:04.079
her.

02:39:04.139 --> 02:39:06.420
Because it's always been that way?

02:39:06.479 --> 02:39:09.059
Nope, she said.

02:39:09.180 --> 02:39:11.159
Not before the tree wars, it wasn't.

02:39:11.280 --> 02:39:12.959
Whoa.

02:39:13.079 --> 02:39:15.120
Didn't you start school today?

02:39:15.180 --> 02:39:16.020
he asked.

02:39:16.079 --> 02:39:17.940
How do you already know more history

02:39:17.940 --> 02:39:18.719
stuff than I do?

02:39:18.840 --> 02:39:21.959
I listen to my moms when they think I'm

02:39:21.959 --> 02:39:23.340
asleep, Luna said.

02:39:23.399 --> 02:39:26.579
Silkwings used to have our own queen and

02:39:26.579 --> 02:39:28.319
our own cities in the webs between the

02:39:28.319 --> 02:39:28.739
trees.

02:39:28.799 --> 02:39:31.559
Huh, he said.

02:39:31.620 --> 02:39:33.540
And then.

02:39:34.799 --> 02:39:37.500
And then Queen Wasp said we couldn't, and

02:39:37.500 --> 02:39:39.659
knocked down all the trees, and killed

02:39:39.659 --> 02:39:42.120
all the leaf wings, and told us we had to

02:39:42.120 --> 02:39:44.700
come live in these sunless termite mounds

02:39:44.700 --> 02:39:46.319
and do everything the hive wings say from

02:39:46.319 --> 02:39:48.659
now on, because of some stupid old book

02:39:48.659 --> 02:39:49.379
of prophecies.

02:39:49.440 --> 02:39:53.940
Ha, Swordtell said, you are going to be

02:39:53.940 --> 02:39:54.959
trouble, aren't you?

02:39:55.079 --> 02:39:58.379
I don't care if I am, Luna said.

02:39:58.440 --> 02:40:00.959
I think they need to know how awful they

02:40:00.959 --> 02:40:03.120
are, and we need to figure out how to fix

02:40:03.120 --> 02:40:03.899
everything.

02:40:03.959 --> 02:40:07.979
All right, he said, coming to lean

02:40:07.979 --> 02:40:10.079
against her empty loom, his dark blue

02:40:10.079 --> 02:40:10.920
eyes shining.

02:40:10.979 --> 02:40:12.719
All right, what?

02:40:12.719 --> 02:40:13.440
she said.

02:40:13.500 --> 02:40:15.059
All right.

02:40:15.120 --> 02:40:16.739
I'm in, he said.

02:40:16.799 --> 02:40:17.760
I'm with you.

02:40:17.819 --> 02:40:19.739
Sign me up for fixing everything.

02:40:19.799 --> 02:40:22.319
Thinking about it now.

02:40:22.379 --> 02:40:24.659
Made Luna's heart feel like it was made

02:40:24.659 --> 02:40:25.440
of flame silk.

02:40:25.559 --> 02:40:27.420
The brightest burning kind.

02:40:27.479 --> 02:40:30.420
Soretail was on her side from the moment

02:40:30.420 --> 02:40:30.959
they met.

02:40:31.020 --> 02:40:33.959
He always threw himself into danger to

02:40:33.959 --> 02:40:36.239
protect her, deflecting the punishment

02:40:36.239 --> 02:40:38.520
onto himself whenever she made a hive

02:40:38.520 --> 02:40:39.059
wing angry.

02:40:39.120 --> 02:40:42.360
His noise covered her tracks, and kept

02:40:42.360 --> 02:40:44.100
their attention while she found the

02:40:44.100 --> 02:40:44.819
chrysalis.

02:40:44.879 --> 02:40:47.340
That was why he'd ended up on

02:40:47.340 --> 02:40:50.159
misbehavior's way multiple times, and she

02:40:50.159 --> 02:40:50.579
never had.

02:40:50.639 --> 02:40:53.399
But he couldn't stand by her now.

02:40:53.459 --> 02:40:56.579
She was alone, and he was in danger.

02:40:56.700 --> 02:40:59.579
And I don't have time to be sad.

02:40:59.639 --> 02:41:02.639
I can't be an extra problem when our

02:41:02.639 --> 02:41:03.840
problems are so big already.

02:41:03.899 --> 02:41:06.360
Luna sighed.

02:41:06.420 --> 02:41:09.479
She could tell by her internal clock that

02:41:09.479 --> 02:41:10.979
it was well into nighttime when they

02:41:10.979 --> 02:41:12.719
finally heard the patter of footsteps

02:41:12.719 --> 02:41:13.200
returning.

02:41:13.260 --> 02:41:15.059
Red?

02:41:15.120 --> 02:41:16.079
Sky cried.

02:41:16.139 --> 02:41:18.600
Ren, Ren, Ren, are you all right?

02:41:18.659 --> 02:41:21.840
Of course I am, she answered from the

02:41:21.840 --> 02:41:22.620
human sledge.

02:41:22.680 --> 02:41:24.540
What could happen to me?

02:41:24.600 --> 02:41:26.819
I am invisible, which also means it's

02:41:26.819 --> 02:41:28.500
going to be tough to ask these humans for

02:41:28.500 --> 02:41:30.780
help, but it makes spying on them pretty

02:41:30.780 --> 02:41:31.139
easy.

02:41:31.260 --> 02:41:32.639
Help me down.

02:41:32.700 --> 02:41:36.059
Rens gets to quick map with water on the

02:41:36.059 --> 02:41:38.219
floor for them, showing the path that

02:41:38.219 --> 02:41:40.020
went from behind the wall, down through

02:41:40.020 --> 02:41:42.000
some tunnels, to a central human cave

02:41:42.000 --> 02:41:42.420
village.

02:41:42.540 --> 02:41:45.899
There are a lot of people there, Ren

02:41:45.899 --> 02:41:46.319
said.

02:41:46.379 --> 02:41:48.000
I think it's actually bigger than

02:41:48.000 --> 02:41:49.920
talisman, the village where I grew up

02:41:49.920 --> 02:41:52.440
although it's hard to tell because it's

02:41:52.440 --> 02:41:53.639
kind of like a rabbit warren.

02:41:53.760 --> 02:41:55.799
A bit like valor, sky.

02:41:55.860 --> 02:42:00.000
Oh, dear, Skye said, I hope the humans

02:42:00.000 --> 02:42:01.500
here are nicer than Ivy's dad.

02:42:01.559 --> 02:42:04.139
Luna had no idea what they were talking

02:42:04.139 --> 02:42:04.440
about.

02:42:04.500 --> 02:42:07.079
Did you see the abyss?

02:42:07.079 --> 02:42:07.680
she asked.

02:42:07.739 --> 02:42:09.479
No.

02:42:09.600 --> 02:42:11.520
Ren answered ruefully.

02:42:11.579 --> 02:42:14.040
And nobody mentioned one the whole time I

02:42:14.040 --> 02:42:14.639
was there either.

02:42:14.700 --> 02:42:17.639
These might not be the same humans Queen

02:42:17.639 --> 02:42:19.020
Snowfall saw in her vision.

02:42:19.139 --> 02:42:22.500
You mean, you think there are other

02:42:22.500 --> 02:42:23.639
humans in Pentala?

02:42:23.700 --> 02:42:24.659
Cricket asked.

02:42:24.719 --> 02:42:26.819
More cave villages?

02:42:26.879 --> 02:42:29.879
Probably, Ren said.

02:42:29.940 --> 02:42:32.100
We are kind of everywhere, if you look

02:42:32.100 --> 02:42:32.520
hard enough.

02:42:32.579 --> 02:42:35.459
I'll keep spying on these ones for now

02:42:35.459 --> 02:42:37.500
and see if they say anything about it.

02:42:37.559 --> 02:42:41.219
The one we saw is named Axolotl.

02:42:41.280 --> 02:42:42.959
She said the name in human.

02:42:43.079 --> 02:42:45.239
Luna wasn't sure what the dragon

02:42:45.239 --> 02:42:46.020
translation would be.

02:42:46.079 --> 02:42:49.739
Is it a boy human or girl human?

02:42:49.739 --> 02:42:50.819
Sky asked.

02:42:50.879 --> 02:42:52.319
Neither?

02:42:52.440 --> 02:42:53.340
Both?

02:42:53.399 --> 02:42:55.739
We'd have to ask them, Ren said.

02:42:55.799 --> 02:42:58.200
They use they and them pronouns.

02:42:58.200 --> 02:43:01.079
Like that traveling librarian we met, Skye

02:43:01.079 --> 02:43:01.620
remember?

02:43:01.680 --> 02:43:02.399
Sage.

02:43:02.459 --> 02:43:04.920
Oh, right, Skye said.

02:43:04.979 --> 02:43:08.280
What's in Axolotl?

02:43:08.340 --> 02:43:10.680
He managed the human word better than

02:43:10.680 --> 02:43:12.719
Luna would have, but it still sounded

02:43:12.719 --> 02:43:14.579
very weird coming from a dragon's mouth.

02:43:14.639 --> 02:43:18.239
It's kind of a cave salamander, Ren

02:43:18.239 --> 02:43:18.719
said.

02:43:18.780 --> 02:43:20.219
There were a few around the village.

02:43:20.280 --> 02:43:23.520
The creature she described didn't sound

02:43:23.520 --> 02:43:25.620
familiar to Luna, but after a moment of

02:43:25.620 --> 02:43:30.000
listening, Cricket said, oh, an exolotl

02:43:30.000 --> 02:43:31.379
in dragon.

02:43:31.440 --> 02:43:34.139
Luna still wasn't sure what that was, but

02:43:34.139 --> 02:43:37.079
Bullfrog made an, ah, yes, kind of

02:43:37.079 --> 02:43:37.440
noise.

02:43:37.500 --> 02:43:40.799
Did you figure out how Axolotl has a

02:43:40.799 --> 02:43:41.340
dragon book?

02:43:41.399 --> 02:43:42.479
Cricket asked.

02:43:42.540 --> 02:43:45.360
No, I think it's a secret from the other

02:43:45.360 --> 02:43:47.219
humans, Ren guessed.

02:43:47.280 --> 02:43:48.840
I'll follow them again tomorrow.

02:43:48.899 --> 02:43:51.360
Hopefully someone will mention an abyss

02:43:51.360 --> 02:43:51.719
eventually.

02:43:51.840 --> 02:43:55.200
The others decided to sleep in the cavern

02:43:55.200 --> 02:43:58.020
but Luna crept back out to the sea facing

02:43:58.020 --> 02:44:00.659
cave and spent the night there, despite

02:44:00.659 --> 02:44:01.680
the cold and wet.

02:44:01.979 --> 02:44:04.079
She wanted to be there in case their

02:44:04.079 --> 02:44:04.739
friends arrived.

02:44:04.799 --> 02:44:07.860
If finding Axolotl and the cave village

02:44:07.860 --> 02:44:09.659
meant they were one step closer to the

02:44:09.659 --> 02:44:12.540
abyss, then they really needed sundo, and

02:44:12.540 --> 02:44:14.579
ideally, moon and lynx and all the others

02:44:14.579 --> 02:44:14.879
too.

02:44:15.000 --> 02:44:17.459
She didn't sleep much.

02:44:17.520 --> 02:44:20.700
She kept jerking awake, thinking she'd

02:44:20.700 --> 02:44:22.920
heard sundew's voice, but it was only

02:44:22.920 --> 02:44:25.319
ever the waves on the beach, or rain

02:44:25.319 --> 02:44:26.280
dripping down the rocks.

02:44:26.399 --> 02:44:30.659
The next day and the next, Wren went back

02:44:30.659 --> 02:44:32.700
into the tunnels to study the Pentalon

02:44:32.700 --> 02:44:33.059
humans.

02:44:33.120 --> 02:44:36.299
Axolotl returned to their ledge twice in

02:44:36.299 --> 02:44:36.719
that time.

02:44:36.780 --> 02:44:39.360
It was fascinating to watch the little

02:44:39.360 --> 02:44:41.819
human sitting for so long, peering at the

02:44:41.819 --> 02:44:42.299
dragon book.

02:44:42.360 --> 02:44:45.239
Cricket pointed out that Axolotl was

02:44:45.239 --> 02:44:48.059
riding in the other human sized book, as

02:44:48.059 --> 02:44:48.780
if they were taking notes.

02:44:48.840 --> 02:44:52.020
I think they're trying to translate the

02:44:52.020 --> 02:44:54.059
dragon, she whispered to Luna.

02:44:54.180 --> 02:44:55.500
Isn't that brilliant?

02:44:55.559 --> 02:44:58.979
I knew our pental in humans would be just

02:44:58.979 --> 02:45:00.780
as clever as the ones in the distant

02:45:00.780 --> 02:45:01.200
kingdoms.

02:45:01.319 --> 02:45:04.319
Do you think Axolotl snuck into one of

02:45:04.319 --> 02:45:05.280
the hives to get that book?

02:45:05.340 --> 02:45:07.559
That would mean they're really brave

02:45:07.559 --> 02:45:07.799
too.

02:45:07.860 --> 02:45:10.139
I wonder what they think of dragons.

02:45:10.200 --> 02:45:11.579
Do you think they'll like us?

02:45:11.639 --> 02:45:13.739
On the 3rd day?

02:45:13.799 --> 02:45:16.319
Still, no sign of sunduin links.

02:45:16.379 --> 02:45:19.440
Axolotl arrived earlier than usual, and

02:45:19.440 --> 02:45:21.479
sat down with a sigh, looking tired.

02:45:21.540 --> 02:45:25.079
At least, Luna thought so, although they

02:45:25.079 --> 02:45:27.420
didn't have wings to droop, or a long

02:45:27.420 --> 02:45:29.879
listless tail, which were the signs that

02:45:29.879 --> 02:45:31.200
might have tipped off Luna's friends

02:45:31.200 --> 02:45:33.719
about her own emotional state if they'd

02:45:33.719 --> 02:45:34.319
been able to see her.

02:45:34.379 --> 02:45:37.680
At least invisibility meant she only had

02:45:37.680 --> 02:45:38.940
to keep her voice sounding happy.

02:45:39.000 --> 02:45:42.120
Ren had been eating breakfast with them

02:45:42.120 --> 02:45:45.120
but they all cautiously hid or wolfed

02:45:45.120 --> 02:45:46.860
down their food when they heard axolotl

02:45:46.860 --> 02:45:47.040
coming.

02:45:47.159 --> 02:45:50.159
Sky lifted Wren up to crouch on the ledge

02:45:50.159 --> 02:45:51.360
beside the curious human.

02:45:51.420 --> 02:45:54.360
Axolotl pulled out the dragon book and

02:45:54.360 --> 02:45:56.639
flipped it open again, trailing one of

02:45:56.639 --> 02:45:59.459
their long, thin appendages, like a claw

02:45:59.459 --> 02:46:01.920
but not in the least bit dangerous, down

02:46:01.920 --> 02:46:02.340
the page.

02:46:02.399 --> 02:46:06.299
It looks like a book about trees, Ren

02:46:06.299 --> 02:46:06.959
called down.

02:46:07.020 --> 02:46:10.379
Axolotl turned the page and she added

02:46:10.379 --> 02:46:11.459
Hang on.

02:46:11.520 --> 02:46:13.799
In this picture, the trees are burning.

02:46:13.860 --> 02:46:16.979
Maybe it's a history of the tree wars?

02:46:17.040 --> 02:46:18.000
Cricket guest.

02:46:18.120 --> 02:46:21.479
Our histories didn't have illustrations

02:46:21.479 --> 02:46:23.159
Luna said grumbly.

02:46:23.219 --> 02:46:25.440
Even our books couldn't have any pictures

02:46:25.440 --> 02:46:26.340
of trees in them.

02:46:26.399 --> 02:46:30.120
She edged as close as she could, craning

02:46:30.120 --> 02:46:32.459
to see, and felt cricket and sky doing

02:46:32.459 --> 02:46:33.659
the same on either side of her.

02:46:33.719 --> 02:46:37.799
All at once, she felt a weird tingling in

02:46:37.799 --> 02:46:40.079
her talons, as though one of the less

02:46:40.079 --> 02:46:42.600
flammable forms of flame silk was pulsing

02:46:42.600 --> 02:46:43.440
through her palms.

02:46:43.500 --> 02:46:46.260
She glanced down to make sure she hadn't

02:46:46.260 --> 02:46:48.059
unleashed some flame silk by accident.

02:46:48.180 --> 02:46:51.180
But no, her front claws were right there

02:46:51.180 --> 02:46:53.700
propped against the stone column she was

02:46:53.700 --> 02:46:55.799
leaning against, looking perfectly normal

02:46:55.799 --> 02:46:56.940
and not glowy.

02:46:57.059 --> 02:47:00.059
Wait, her claws.

02:47:00.120 --> 02:47:01.200
She could see them.

02:47:01.260 --> 02:47:04.260
Luna looked up into Cricket's startled

02:47:04.260 --> 02:47:04.620
eyes.

02:47:04.680 --> 02:47:07.200
Cricket's face, right there in front of

02:47:07.200 --> 02:47:07.319
her.

02:47:07.440 --> 02:47:11.639
And right at that moment, Axolotl raised

02:47:11.639 --> 02:47:14.340
their head and discovered Wren, suddenly

02:47:14.340 --> 02:47:16.739
crouching next to them out of nowhere, and

02:47:16.739 --> 02:47:19.620
4 dragons crowded around the ledge, gazing

02:47:19.620 --> 02:47:20.280
straight at them.

02:47:20.340 --> 02:47:24.120
Axolotl shrieked, leaped to their feet

02:47:24.120 --> 02:47:26.760
tripped over Wren, bonked into the wall

02:47:26.760 --> 02:47:29.639
pinwheeled backward, bounced off

02:47:29.639 --> 02:47:32.700
Bullfrog's nose, shrieked again, and made

02:47:32.700 --> 02:47:33.659
a run for the tunnels.

02:47:33.780 --> 02:47:37.020
Bullfrog calmly lunged over the rock

02:47:37.020 --> 02:47:39.420
shelf, and trapped the human under one

02:47:39.420 --> 02:47:40.860
big talon.

02:47:40.920 --> 02:47:41.760
Eck!

02:47:41.819 --> 02:47:43.559
Wren shouted at the mudwing.

02:47:43.620 --> 02:47:44.639
Stop that.

02:47:44.700 --> 02:47:45.180
Get off them.

02:47:45.299 --> 02:47:48.360
She ran over and grabbed Bullfrog's

02:47:48.360 --> 02:47:50.280
massive front leg, trying to yank it up.

02:47:50.340 --> 02:47:54.959
It's fun, Bullfrog said impassively.

02:47:55.020 --> 02:47:57.360
I'm not hurting it.

02:47:57.420 --> 02:48:00.719
That is a lot of yelling for someone

02:48:00.719 --> 02:48:03.420
who's not hurt, Skye said, covering his

02:48:03.420 --> 02:48:03.899
ears.

02:48:03.959 --> 02:48:07.620
Because they're scared, Ren snapped.

02:48:07.680 --> 02:48:08.579
Wouldn't you be?

02:48:08.700 --> 02:48:11.100
If a human and 4 dragons literally

02:48:11.100 --> 02:48:13.139
appeared out of thin air and then stepped

02:48:13.139 --> 02:48:13.500
on you?

02:48:13.559 --> 02:48:18.059
I'm not stepping on it, Bullfrog

02:48:18.059 --> 02:48:18.479
observed.

02:48:18.540 --> 02:48:21.959
I'm preventing it from leaving, that's

02:48:21.959 --> 02:48:22.139
all.

02:48:22.260 --> 02:48:25.020
Poor axolotl.

02:48:25.079 --> 02:48:26.639
Tell them we won't hurt them.

02:48:26.760 --> 02:48:29.280
Luna said to Ren, that we're friendly

02:48:29.280 --> 02:48:29.760
dragons.

02:48:29.879 --> 02:48:31.620
Two of us are vegetarians.

02:48:31.680 --> 02:48:34.500
I think that would be a lot more

02:48:34.500 --> 02:48:36.840
comforting without a giant carnivore

02:48:36.840 --> 02:48:39.299
standing on them, but I'll try, Ren

02:48:39.299 --> 02:48:39.719
said.

02:48:39.780 --> 02:48:42.840
She crouched next to Axolotl and said

02:48:42.840 --> 02:48:43.979
something in the human language.

02:48:44.040 --> 02:48:47.520
It took a moment for Axolotl to hear her

02:48:47.520 --> 02:48:49.979
over there yelling, but finally they went

02:48:49.979 --> 02:48:52.079
quiet, and their expression went from

02:48:52.079 --> 02:48:55.200
panicked, to panicked, but also curious.

02:48:55.260 --> 02:48:58.739
Ren kept talking rapidly, waving her

02:48:58.739 --> 02:48:59.700
hands at the dragons.

02:48:59.760 --> 02:49:04.500
Okay, now get off them, she said to

02:49:04.500 --> 02:49:06.659
Bullfrog in Dragon, shoving at the

02:49:06.659 --> 02:49:07.620
Mudwings talons.

02:49:07.680 --> 02:49:10.920
But then it might escape.

02:49:11.040 --> 02:49:13.200
Bullfrog said placidly.

02:49:13.260 --> 02:49:16.200
If they still want to do that, we let

02:49:16.200 --> 02:49:16.500
them.

02:49:16.559 --> 02:49:17.639
Ren said.

02:49:17.700 --> 02:49:19.860
She threw her shoulder under one of

02:49:19.860 --> 02:49:22.319
Bullfrog's claws and lifted it as much as

02:49:22.319 --> 02:49:22.620
she could.

02:49:22.680 --> 02:49:26.459
Underneath, Axolotl tried to wiggle

02:49:26.459 --> 02:49:26.819
free.

02:49:26.879 --> 02:49:30.059
Because Hugh Dragons are not actually

02:49:30.059 --> 02:49:33.120
monsters is the point I am trying to make

02:49:33.120 --> 02:49:35.399
and you are kind of making the opposite

02:49:35.399 --> 02:49:36.120
point right now.

02:49:36.239 --> 02:49:39.719
Bullfrog wrinkle just snout skeptically.

02:49:39.780 --> 02:49:41.340
Expressions.

02:49:41.399 --> 02:49:43.920
Luna hadn't realized how much she'd

02:49:43.920 --> 02:49:45.299
missed seeing facial expressions.

02:49:45.360 --> 02:49:48.719
But he lifted his talons and stepped back

02:49:48.719 --> 02:49:49.680
down to the cave floor.

02:49:49.739 --> 02:49:53.940
Axolotl sat up, feeling their limbs as

02:49:53.940 --> 02:49:55.139
though making sure everything was

02:49:55.139 --> 02:49:55.500
intact.

02:49:55.620 --> 02:49:58.620
They looked at Wren with wide, astonished

02:49:58.620 --> 02:50:00.479
eyes and burbled something.

02:50:00.540 --> 02:50:02.340
What did they say?

02:50:02.399 --> 02:50:03.239
What did they say?

02:50:03.299 --> 02:50:05.159
Cricket asked eagerly.

02:50:05.219 --> 02:50:08.459
They can't believe I can talk to dragons

02:50:08.459 --> 02:50:09.420
Ren said.

02:50:09.479 --> 02:50:11.040
They've always wanted to do that.

02:50:11.100 --> 02:50:12.959
They want to know what you're saying.

02:50:13.020 --> 02:50:16.500
Sky laughed and said something human

02:50:16.500 --> 02:50:17.040
sounding.

02:50:17.159 --> 02:50:21.360
Axolotl gasped, pointed at him, turned to

02:50:21.360 --> 02:50:23.819
Ren, waved their hands around, and

02:50:23.819 --> 02:50:24.840
pointed to sky again.

02:50:24.899 --> 02:50:27.000
Now what did they say?

02:50:27.059 --> 02:50:28.440
Cricket demanded.

02:50:28.500 --> 02:50:31.920
This is going to take a while, Ren

02:50:31.920 --> 02:50:33.840
observed, rubbing her forehead.

02:50:33.899 --> 02:50:36.059
Wait, Luna said.

02:50:36.120 --> 02:50:38.100
Why are we suddenly not invisible

02:50:38.100 --> 02:50:38.399
anymore?

02:50:38.459 --> 02:50:41.639
Maybe the magic wore off?

02:50:41.700 --> 02:50:42.780
Cricket guessed.

02:50:42.840 --> 02:50:45.719
I thought Lynx said that wouldn't happen

02:50:45.719 --> 02:50:46.739
Luna said.

02:50:46.799 --> 02:50:48.600
She jumped to her feet.

02:50:48.659 --> 02:50:51.180
Maybe Sundu made us all visible because

02:50:51.180 --> 02:50:51.719
she's here.

02:50:51.780 --> 02:50:52.860
I'll go check.

02:50:52.920 --> 02:50:56.459
Meanwhile, I will stay here and explain

02:50:56.459 --> 02:50:58.559
my entire life to yet another strange

02:50:58.559 --> 02:50:59.040
human.

02:50:59.100 --> 02:51:02.639
Ren said, sitting down next to Axolotl.

02:51:02.700 --> 02:51:06.000
Luna dashed back into the tunnels and

02:51:06.000 --> 02:51:07.979
raced through the winding rock corridors

02:51:07.979 --> 02:51:08.879
to the beach cave.

02:51:08.940 --> 02:51:10.860
Outside.

02:51:10.920 --> 02:51:12.180
It was pouring again.

02:51:12.239 --> 02:51:14.760
Curtains of rain billowing into the open

02:51:14.760 --> 02:51:15.479
space.

02:51:15.540 --> 02:51:18.659
Luna ran out into the storm and looked up

02:51:18.659 --> 02:51:21.659
at the sky, then whirled around, searching

02:51:21.659 --> 02:51:22.020
the beach.

02:51:22.079 --> 02:51:24.120
No sun do.

02:51:24.180 --> 02:51:25.559
No links.

02:51:25.620 --> 02:51:28.079
There was nobody there at all.

02:51:28.139 --> 02:51:32.760
Chapter 8.

02:51:32.879 --> 02:51:36.120
Axolotl says they've heard of a village

02:51:36.120 --> 02:51:37.799
that worships an abyss.

02:51:37.860 --> 02:51:40.559
Cricket said to Luna, when she returned

02:51:40.559 --> 02:51:42.899
to the Dragon Teeth Cavern, wet

02:51:42.899 --> 02:51:44.520
bedraggled, and disappointed.

02:51:44.579 --> 02:51:47.399
Cricket's eyes were glowing behind her

02:51:47.399 --> 02:51:49.319
spectacles, and she was practically

02:51:49.319 --> 02:51:50.579
bouncing on her talons.

02:51:50.639 --> 02:51:53.340
They said, they can guide us there.

02:51:53.399 --> 02:51:55.139
If we translate the dragon book for them

02:51:55.260 --> 02:51:57.299
Luna, isn't this wonderful?

02:51:57.360 --> 02:51:58.739
They're willing to help us.

02:51:58.860 --> 02:52:00.899
Maybe they'll like us so much.

02:52:00.959 --> 02:52:03.059
They'll want to be my best friend, just

02:52:03.059 --> 02:52:04.200
like Skye and Wren.

02:52:04.260 --> 02:52:06.479
And then we can learn each other's

02:52:06.479 --> 02:52:08.159
language and hang out all the time.

02:52:08.219 --> 02:52:12.000
I mean, after we save the world, and

02:52:12.000 --> 02:52:12.780
rescue Blue.

02:52:12.840 --> 02:52:15.840
She finished, her expression sobering.

02:52:15.899 --> 02:52:20.520
The human says, we can head for the abyss

02:52:20.520 --> 02:52:22.799
tomorrow, Bullfrog added.

02:52:22.920 --> 02:52:25.079
He was sitting by the entrance to the

02:52:25.079 --> 02:52:27.299
cavern, as far from the humans as

02:52:27.299 --> 02:52:29.940
possible, with a mildly grumpy look on

02:52:29.940 --> 02:52:30.239
his face.

02:52:30.299 --> 02:52:33.059
Lune guest he had been ordered over here

02:52:33.059 --> 02:52:35.760
by Ren, so he wouldn't scare Axolotl any

02:52:35.760 --> 02:52:36.600
more than he already had.

02:52:36.659 --> 02:52:40.200
Over by the ledge, Sky and Wren and

02:52:40.200 --> 02:52:42.840
Axolotl, were chatting away, like Silk

02:52:42.840 --> 02:52:44.520
Wings having a day off picnic in the

02:52:44.520 --> 02:52:45.180
mosaic garden.

02:52:45.299 --> 02:52:47.340
Tomorrow?

02:52:47.399 --> 02:52:48.780
Luna echoed.

02:52:48.840 --> 02:52:50.100
But we can't.

02:52:50.219 --> 02:52:51.899
We have to wait for the others.

02:52:51.959 --> 02:52:54.659
Bullfrog froed his browadder.

02:52:54.719 --> 02:52:57.420
Sundew said not to wait.

02:52:57.540 --> 02:53:01.079
And their days late, Cricket agreed.

02:53:01.139 --> 02:53:03.600
I wonder if maybe making us visible

02:53:03.600 --> 02:53:03.959
again?

02:53:04.020 --> 02:53:06.420
Was Sundew trying to tell us we should go

02:53:06.420 --> 02:53:07.260
on without them.

02:53:07.319 --> 02:53:09.600
She did say we should look for the abyss

02:53:09.600 --> 02:53:10.559
if they didn't show up.

02:53:10.620 --> 02:53:14.459
But we won't have any idea what to do if

02:53:14.459 --> 02:53:16.379
we find it, Luna said.

02:53:16.440 --> 02:53:19.379
She tried to keep her voice light, instead

02:53:19.379 --> 02:53:20.940
of letting the panic seep into it.

02:53:21.000 --> 02:53:23.579
She hoped her face looked reasonable

02:53:23.579 --> 02:53:25.799
rather than like a tapestry of worries.

02:53:25.860 --> 02:53:28.860
Other dragons, especially hive wings

02:53:28.860 --> 02:53:31.260
didn't like her panic voice or worry

02:53:31.260 --> 02:53:31.799
face.

02:53:31.860 --> 02:53:34.139
She'd noticed in her 6 years of life

02:53:34.139 --> 02:53:36.360
showing her nerves did not make them

02:53:36.360 --> 02:53:37.079
kinder to her.

02:53:37.139 --> 02:53:40.079
Too often, it made them more irritable

02:53:40.079 --> 02:53:41.819
and impatient instead.

02:53:41.879 --> 02:53:43.440
Not sore tail.

02:53:43.500 --> 02:53:45.899
Sortail is never impatient with me.

02:53:45.959 --> 02:53:47.280
And not blue.

02:53:47.340 --> 02:53:49.920
I can't even imagine what an irritable

02:53:49.920 --> 02:53:50.639
blue would look like.

02:53:50.700 --> 02:53:52.799
If they were here.

02:53:52.860 --> 02:53:55.079
They'd understand why I'm so worried.

02:53:55.139 --> 02:53:56.760
You're right.

02:53:56.819 --> 02:53:58.920
Cricket said unexpectedly.

02:53:58.979 --> 02:54:02.040
She poked one claw into a crack in the

02:54:02.040 --> 02:54:03.719
rock floor and wiggled it back and

02:54:03.719 --> 02:54:04.020
forth.

02:54:04.079 --> 02:54:07.500
In fact, Luna would have to say cricket

02:54:07.500 --> 02:54:09.600
definitely had a worry face on.

02:54:09.659 --> 02:54:12.600
She'd never seen a hive wing with a worry

02:54:12.600 --> 02:54:13.079
face before.

02:54:13.139 --> 02:54:16.620
I mean, I know exactly how you feel

02:54:16.620 --> 02:54:16.979
Luna.

02:54:17.040 --> 02:54:19.260
I didn't think I'd have to do any

02:54:19.260 --> 02:54:21.360
decision making or fighting while we had

02:54:21.360 --> 02:54:23.399
Sundu and tsunami and moon with us.

02:54:23.399 --> 02:54:25.860
I wouldn't send me to save the world.

02:54:25.979 --> 02:54:28.500
We have no idea what we're going to find

02:54:28.500 --> 02:54:30.360
down there, and it's completely

02:54:30.360 --> 02:54:31.020
terrifying.

02:54:31.079 --> 02:54:35.159
Bullfrog grunted, and they both turned to

02:54:35.159 --> 02:54:35.700
look at him.

02:54:35.760 --> 02:54:39.000
He paused for a long moment and then said

02:54:39.000 --> 02:54:40.620
Same.

02:54:40.680 --> 02:54:44.280
How come cricket doesn't mind spilling

02:54:44.280 --> 02:54:45.659
out all her worries and fears?

02:54:45.659 --> 02:54:47.879
In front of dragons, she hardly knows.

02:54:47.940 --> 02:54:50.100
That's not a hive wing thing?

02:54:50.159 --> 02:54:52.739
Is this what Blue likes about her?

02:54:52.799 --> 02:54:55.260
That she shares all her feelings before

02:54:55.260 --> 02:54:55.979
he has to guess?

02:54:56.040 --> 02:54:58.920
Here's what I tell myself.

02:54:58.979 --> 02:55:02.280
Cricket went on, touching one of Luna's

02:55:02.280 --> 02:55:03.059
talons lightly.

02:55:03.120 --> 02:55:05.219
We're going looking for the truth.

02:55:05.280 --> 02:55:06.959
That's something I can do.

02:55:07.079 --> 02:55:08.700
I can't discover things.

02:55:08.760 --> 02:55:10.559
Whatever is down there.

02:55:10.620 --> 02:55:12.959
Moon and Snowfall think we need to know

02:55:12.959 --> 02:55:13.319
about it.

02:55:13.440 --> 02:55:16.500
So that's all we're doing, at least in my

02:55:16.500 --> 02:55:19.440
head, flying into the abyss, finding

02:55:19.440 --> 02:55:21.120
answers, flying out again.

02:55:21.180 --> 02:55:24.120
What if the answers eat us?

02:55:24.120 --> 02:55:25.500
Luna asked.

02:55:25.559 --> 02:55:28.979
Then we hope the next dragons do better.

02:55:29.040 --> 02:55:30.120
Cricket said.

02:55:30.180 --> 02:55:33.180
Maybe we can leave a message for sun do

02:55:33.180 --> 02:55:34.920
and links, so they know where to look for

02:55:34.920 --> 02:55:35.100
us.

02:55:35.159 --> 02:55:38.459
But we can't just sit here, not when Blue

02:55:38.459 --> 02:55:39.899
needs us, right?

02:55:39.959 --> 02:55:43.559
When we have a next step that might take

02:55:43.559 --> 02:55:44.040
us to him?

02:55:44.159 --> 02:55:45.659
Don't we have to take it?

02:55:45.780 --> 02:55:48.420
Even if we can't see the end of the path

02:55:48.420 --> 02:55:48.659
yet?

02:55:48.719 --> 02:55:51.899
Luna covered her face with her talons.

02:55:51.959 --> 02:55:55.500
Cricket was right, which was very

02:55:55.500 --> 02:55:57.719
annoying, because Luna would have

02:55:57.719 --> 02:55:59.879
preferred nearly any other dragon to pull

02:55:59.879 --> 02:56:02.219
her back into her, let's do this state.

02:56:02.280 --> 02:56:04.500
But it was true.

02:56:04.559 --> 02:56:06.780
They couldn't stay here in this cave

02:56:06.780 --> 02:56:09.299
watching the rain, waiting for someone

02:56:09.299 --> 02:56:10.620
more heroic to show up.

02:56:10.680 --> 02:56:13.799
Blue and Soretail and all the other silk

02:56:13.799 --> 02:56:15.540
wings needed them to keep going.

02:56:15.600 --> 02:56:18.239
All right, she said.

02:56:18.299 --> 02:56:20.159
How do we leave a message?

02:56:20.219 --> 02:56:25.079
Ooh, let's think, Cricket said, bouncing

02:56:25.079 --> 02:56:25.500
to her feet.

02:56:25.559 --> 02:56:28.500
She picked up a rock, put it back down

02:56:28.500 --> 02:56:31.319
picked up another rock, tapped it on the

02:56:31.319 --> 02:56:33.120
floor, and scratched her head.

02:56:33.180 --> 02:56:35.100
What are you doing?

02:56:35.159 --> 02:56:36.120
Luna asked.

02:56:36.180 --> 02:56:37.680
Thinking.

02:56:37.799 --> 02:56:40.139
Cricket said, unselfconsciously.

02:56:40.200 --> 02:56:42.899
It has to be something sundew and links

02:56:42.899 --> 02:56:44.219
will find, but nobody else.

02:56:44.280 --> 02:56:46.680
We don't want patrolling hive wings to

02:56:46.680 --> 02:56:47.280
see it by accident.

02:56:47.340 --> 02:56:51.059
So, we can't paint on the wall of the

02:56:51.059 --> 02:56:52.620
cave, Luna said.

02:56:52.739 --> 02:56:55.079
Or a carve a giant arrow pointing

02:56:55.079 --> 02:56:57.180
wherever we're going, Cricket added.

02:56:57.239 --> 02:57:00.360
Because then anyone might find it, Luna

02:57:00.360 --> 02:57:00.840
finished.

02:57:00.959 --> 02:57:03.180
What should the message even say?

02:57:03.239 --> 02:57:04.559
Cricket wondered.

02:57:04.680 --> 02:57:06.659
Find a human and follow it?

02:57:06.719 --> 02:57:08.879
I wonder if there's something more

02:57:08.879 --> 02:57:09.899
specific we can write.

02:57:09.959 --> 02:57:12.479
I'll tell Ren to ask Axolotl.

02:57:12.540 --> 02:57:16.139
This was an obvious excuse for cricket to

02:57:16.139 --> 02:57:19.680
talk to, or at least near Axolotl again

02:57:19.680 --> 02:57:21.299
but Luna didn't stop her.

02:57:21.360 --> 02:57:24.600
She spun out a coil of glowing flame silk

02:57:24.600 --> 02:57:27.479
and held it in her palms, drying some of

02:57:27.479 --> 02:57:29.639
the leftover raindrops, and wondering if

02:57:29.639 --> 02:57:30.959
she could use it to hide a message

02:57:30.959 --> 02:57:31.500
somehow.

02:57:31.620 --> 02:57:34.799
They say it's not far from a giant lake

02:57:34.799 --> 02:57:35.399
in the south.

02:57:35.459 --> 02:57:38.579
Cricket said, bounding back to Luna with

02:57:38.579 --> 02:57:39.840
her spectacles askew.

02:57:39.899 --> 02:57:41.700
Must be Lake Scorpion, right?

02:57:41.760 --> 02:57:43.319
We can put that in the message.

02:57:43.379 --> 02:57:44.879
Did you have any more ideas?

02:57:44.940 --> 02:57:45.899
I haven't yet.

02:57:45.959 --> 02:57:46.799
Let's think.

02:57:46.860 --> 02:57:49.920
Bit noisy for thinking.

02:57:49.979 --> 02:57:52.620
Bullfrog observed placidly.

02:57:52.680 --> 02:57:55.260
Sorry, Cricket said it once.

02:57:55.319 --> 02:57:55.979
I'll shush.

02:57:56.100 --> 02:57:59.100
They thought quietly for a long moment.

02:57:59.159 --> 02:58:00.719
A code?

02:58:00.780 --> 02:58:01.799
Luna thought.

02:58:01.860 --> 02:58:04.920
A trail of scraps of flame silk, like

02:58:04.920 --> 02:58:06.000
bread crumbs to follow?

02:58:06.059 --> 02:58:08.219
Hmm.

02:58:08.340 --> 02:58:10.680
Bullfrog said after a long time.

02:58:10.739 --> 02:58:13.440
Leaf wings like...

02:58:13.440 --> 02:58:15.479
Plants.

02:58:15.540 --> 02:58:19.860
They do like plants, Muno cried, jumping

02:58:19.860 --> 02:58:22.440
to her feet, and hive wings barely notice

02:58:22.440 --> 02:58:22.620
them.

02:58:22.680 --> 02:58:24.239
We need a plant to help us.

02:58:24.360 --> 02:58:26.819
Bullfrogs squinted at her.

02:58:26.940 --> 02:58:30.059
A plan to what now?

02:58:30.120 --> 02:58:32.879
Sundew can talk to plants.

02:58:32.940 --> 02:58:35.340
Cricket explained, equally excited.

02:58:35.399 --> 02:58:37.979
If there is an unexpected plant in the

02:58:37.979 --> 02:58:38.940
caves, she'll notice.

02:58:38.940 --> 02:58:41.459
Then we bury the message near its roots

02:58:41.459 --> 02:58:43.379
and hope the plant tells Sun to about

02:58:43.379 --> 02:58:43.500
it.

02:58:43.559 --> 02:58:46.500
The plant.

02:58:46.620 --> 02:58:48.719
Bullfrog said slowly.

02:58:48.780 --> 02:58:50.399
Will.

02:58:50.399 --> 02:58:52.559
Tell Sundo?

02:58:52.559 --> 02:58:55.440
Something like that, Cricket said.

02:58:55.500 --> 02:58:58.920
Bullfrog looked skeptical, but he

02:58:58.920 --> 02:59:00.600
followed them out into the rain and stood

02:59:00.600 --> 02:59:02.579
guard, while they dug up a hearty looking

02:59:02.579 --> 02:59:04.559
violet from a cliff top overhead.

02:59:04.620 --> 02:59:07.920
Cricket's talons were gentle as she

02:59:07.920 --> 02:59:09.600
extricated it and all its roots.

02:59:09.659 --> 02:59:12.479
She cradled dirt around the flower's

02:59:12.479 --> 02:59:14.340
tendrils as they flew down to the cave

02:59:14.340 --> 02:59:16.319
and then they planted the little purple

02:59:16.319 --> 02:59:18.120
flower in the wet sand near the back

02:59:18.120 --> 02:59:18.420
wall.

02:59:18.479 --> 02:59:21.600
Poor thing, Cricket said.

02:59:21.659 --> 02:59:23.639
This water is too salty for it.

02:59:23.700 --> 02:59:25.200
I don't think it's going to like it

02:59:25.200 --> 02:59:25.379
here.

02:59:25.440 --> 02:59:28.440
Sundew will move it somewhere safe when

02:59:28.440 --> 02:59:30.120
she finds it, Luna said.

02:59:30.180 --> 02:59:31.379
She'll take care of it.

02:59:31.440 --> 02:59:33.059
Sorry, little flower.

02:59:33.120 --> 02:59:36.479
She touched one of the leaves lightly, and

02:59:36.479 --> 02:59:38.579
then she stepped back and brought forth a

02:59:38.579 --> 02:59:40.079
twist of burning flame silk.

02:59:40.139 --> 02:59:43.860
Sky and Wren had found a wide, flat piece

02:59:43.860 --> 02:59:46.020
of driftwood on the beach, and Luna

02:59:46.020 --> 02:59:47.940
burned their message into its smooth gray

02:59:47.940 --> 02:59:48.299
surface.

02:59:48.420 --> 02:59:51.420
Gone to find the abyss near Lake

02:59:51.420 --> 02:59:52.200
Scorpion.

02:59:52.260 --> 02:59:53.159
Meet us there.

02:59:53.219 --> 02:59:56.579
Then Cricket dug a hole near the flower's

02:59:56.579 --> 02:59:58.139
roots and buried the message.

02:59:58.200 --> 03:00:00.899
Luna felt like there should be more to

03:00:00.899 --> 03:00:01.260
say.

03:00:01.319 --> 03:00:04.139
As though the others had been gone a 1000

03:00:04.139 --> 03:00:06.239
years, and needed to be told about

03:00:06.239 --> 03:00:07.139
everything they'd missed.

03:00:07.200 --> 03:00:10.440
She wanted to tell them to hurry, to be

03:00:10.440 --> 03:00:13.559
careful, to avoid hive wings, and be kind

03:00:13.559 --> 03:00:14.639
to any humans they saw.

03:00:14.700 --> 03:00:16.559
But they knew all that.

03:00:16.620 --> 03:00:19.200
They would be here already, if they

03:00:19.200 --> 03:00:19.379
could.

03:00:19.440 --> 03:00:23.280
The next morning, Axolotl unexpectedly

03:00:23.280 --> 03:00:25.020
appeared with another human.

03:00:25.079 --> 03:00:27.540
This one wore an outer wrapping that was

03:00:27.540 --> 03:00:29.639
almost entirely made of stolen dragon

03:00:29.639 --> 03:00:30.180
silk.

03:00:30.239 --> 03:00:33.299
Orange and silver strips wound around the

03:00:33.299 --> 03:00:36.000
newcomer's pale brown limbs, and more

03:00:36.000 --> 03:00:37.620
were tied into its long dark hair.

03:00:37.680 --> 03:00:39.659
Like axolotl.

03:00:39.719 --> 03:00:41.639
This human looked like it rarely saw the

03:00:41.639 --> 03:00:41.879
sun.

03:00:41.940 --> 03:00:44.760
The glow of Luna's flame silk made it

03:00:44.760 --> 03:00:46.500
blink rapidly and shield its eyes.

03:00:46.620 --> 03:00:51.479
This is ocelot, Ren explained, after some

03:00:51.479 --> 03:00:52.979
back and forth chatter in human.

03:00:53.040 --> 03:00:55.440
She's offered to keep watch for our

03:00:55.440 --> 03:00:56.280
missing dragons.

03:00:56.340 --> 03:00:58.680
If we burn another message, she says

03:00:58.680 --> 03:00:59.639
she'll give it to them.

03:00:59.700 --> 03:01:01.559
She will?

03:01:01.620 --> 03:01:02.700
Cricket said.

03:01:02.760 --> 03:01:04.680
Isn't that really brave of her?

03:01:04.739 --> 03:01:06.659
Has she been around dragons before?

03:01:06.719 --> 03:01:10.379
Ren repeated the question in human, and

03:01:10.379 --> 03:01:11.459
ocelot laughed.

03:01:11.520 --> 03:01:14.280
She held up her arms, draped in dragon

03:01:14.280 --> 03:01:15.959
silk, and twirled as she answered.

03:01:16.079 --> 03:01:19.979
She says, she steals from dragons all the

03:01:19.979 --> 03:01:20.159
time.

03:01:20.280 --> 03:01:23.340
Ren translated, sounding amused.

03:01:23.399 --> 03:01:25.200
And she's not scared of them.

03:01:25.319 --> 03:01:26.459
I like her.

03:01:26.579 --> 03:01:29.219
Still, Luna said.

03:01:29.280 --> 03:01:32.280
Tell her to stay away from hive wings, and

03:01:32.280 --> 03:01:33.180
silk wings.

03:01:33.239 --> 03:01:35.219
Anyone who looks like me or Cricket.

03:01:35.280 --> 03:01:38.100
Only show herself to a green dragon or a

03:01:38.100 --> 03:01:38.639
white dragon.

03:01:38.700 --> 03:01:40.860
Sundew and lynx won't eat her.

03:01:40.920 --> 03:01:44.399
Tell her only trust dragons with 2 wings

03:01:44.399 --> 03:01:47.100
right now, not 4 Cricket agreed.

03:01:47.159 --> 03:01:50.399
Aren't there some leaf wings under wasps

03:01:50.399 --> 03:01:51.059
control too?

03:01:51.120 --> 03:01:52.260
Ren asked.

03:01:52.319 --> 03:01:53.760
Oh.

03:01:53.879 --> 03:01:55.139
Right.

03:01:55.200 --> 03:01:57.420
Luna's wings drooped.

03:01:57.479 --> 03:01:58.620
She'd forgotten about that.

03:01:58.680 --> 03:02:01.620
She'd forgotten that wasp had her claws

03:02:01.620 --> 03:02:03.840
sunk deep into even the fiercest tribal

03:02:03.840 --> 03:02:04.860
on Pentala.

03:02:04.920 --> 03:02:07.680
She felt a light pat on one of her claws

03:02:07.680 --> 03:02:11.040
and looked up to find Axolotl, giving her

03:02:11.040 --> 03:02:12.780
what she thought might be a reassuring

03:02:12.780 --> 03:02:13.139
expression.

03:02:13.260 --> 03:02:17.040
Axolotl says, it'll be all right, Ren

03:02:17.040 --> 03:02:17.459
said.

03:02:17.520 --> 03:02:19.079
Ocelot is smart.

03:02:19.139 --> 03:02:21.659
She'll know which dragons are safe, and

03:02:21.659 --> 03:02:22.440
who should get the message.

03:02:22.500 --> 03:02:26.040
Ren pointed to Skye's wings, and

03:02:26.040 --> 03:02:28.379
bullfrog's wings, and explained something

03:02:28.379 --> 03:02:29.879
at length in the human language.

03:02:29.940 --> 03:02:33.540
Luna burned the same message again on a

03:02:33.540 --> 03:02:35.819
new piece of driftwood, and tried to take

03:02:35.819 --> 03:02:37.620
comfort in the idea that they'd left a

03:02:37.620 --> 03:02:40.260
backup message, that sundew just had to

03:02:40.260 --> 03:02:42.719
find the flower or the human, the violet

03:02:42.719 --> 03:02:44.819
or ocelot, and she'd be able to follow

03:02:44.819 --> 03:02:45.180
them.

03:02:45.239 --> 03:02:47.100
But was it enough?

03:02:47.159 --> 03:02:48.899
Sundew.

03:02:48.959 --> 03:02:49.979
Where are you?

03:02:50.040 --> 03:02:54.659
It is very wet outside, Skye said.

03:02:54.719 --> 03:02:57.120
Bending depeared axolotl's layers of

03:02:57.120 --> 03:02:57.540
wrapping.

03:02:57.600 --> 03:03:00.840
Ren, this poor little human is going to

03:03:00.840 --> 03:03:02.819
get all slippery, and slide off my back

03:03:02.819 --> 03:03:05.399
if we try to fly right now, and sick.

03:03:05.459 --> 03:03:08.399
Don't fluffy mammals get sick if you get

03:03:08.399 --> 03:03:09.120
them too wet?

03:03:09.180 --> 03:03:10.379
What do we do?

03:03:10.440 --> 03:03:12.899
Can we wrap you both in waterproof leaves

03:03:12.899 --> 03:03:13.260
or something?

03:03:13.319 --> 03:03:16.379
He got a mischievous look in his eyes.

03:03:16.440 --> 03:03:19.139
Fancy umbrella leaf hats?

03:03:19.200 --> 03:03:23.100
You are a ridiculous dragon, Ren said

03:03:23.100 --> 03:03:23.700
sternly.

03:03:23.760 --> 03:03:25.319
We are not going outside.

03:03:25.379 --> 03:03:27.540
Axolotl knows a way through the caves

03:03:27.540 --> 03:03:29.340
that will get us most of the way there

03:03:29.340 --> 03:03:31.500
which is safer than trying to fly with

03:03:31.500 --> 03:03:33.299
dragons everywhere looking for us.

03:03:33.360 --> 03:03:35.879
Sky looked disappointed.

03:03:35.940 --> 03:03:38.639
And maybe a little nervous, Luna

03:03:38.639 --> 03:03:38.940
thought.

03:03:39.059 --> 03:03:42.299
We're going underground?

03:03:42.360 --> 03:03:47.520
Like, a lot farther underground, he

03:03:47.520 --> 03:03:47.940
said.

03:03:47.940 --> 03:03:51.540
I'm afraid that is where most people keep

03:03:51.540 --> 03:03:55.020
their dark, scary abysses, Ren said, with

03:03:55.020 --> 03:03:56.219
an affectionate grin.

03:03:56.280 --> 03:03:59.219
On the one talon, it was a relief that

03:03:59.219 --> 03:04:00.540
they didn't have to try to fly in the

03:04:00.540 --> 03:04:00.840
rain.

03:04:00.899 --> 03:04:02.040
On the other.

03:04:02.100 --> 03:04:04.620
Luna had never felt more claustrophobic

03:04:04.620 --> 03:04:06.540
as she followed Axolotl through the

03:04:06.540 --> 03:04:07.620
underground tunnels.

03:04:07.739 --> 03:04:10.979
She had figured out a way to wind glowing

03:04:10.979 --> 03:04:12.719
flame silk threads around her horns.

03:04:12.780 --> 03:04:15.540
They cast a circle of light that

03:04:15.540 --> 03:04:17.399
illuminated the stone pressing in all

03:04:17.399 --> 03:04:19.559
around the dragons, which was both

03:04:19.559 --> 03:04:21.360
comforting and unsettling.

03:04:21.420 --> 03:04:24.540
Most of the tunnels were so narrow that

03:04:24.540 --> 03:04:26.940
her antennae kept brushing the ceiling

03:04:26.940 --> 03:04:28.319
and she couldn't unfold her wings all the

03:04:28.319 --> 03:04:28.500
way.

03:04:28.620 --> 03:04:32.219
But axolotl strode forward confidently

03:04:32.219 --> 03:04:33.540
chatting with Ren.

03:04:33.600 --> 03:04:35.760
They seemed to know their way, even

03:04:35.760 --> 03:04:38.340
without any flame silk light, or Wren's

03:04:38.340 --> 03:04:38.700
torch.

03:04:38.760 --> 03:04:42.059
They kept one paw outstretched, lightly

03:04:42.059 --> 03:04:44.159
brushing the walls, and occasionally

03:04:44.159 --> 03:04:45.780
stopped to consult the notebook they had

03:04:45.780 --> 03:04:46.260
brought with them.

03:04:46.319 --> 03:04:50.219
Cricket also had Axolotl's dragon book

03:04:50.219 --> 03:04:51.719
tucked in the pouch with her blowgun

03:04:51.719 --> 03:04:52.139
darts.

03:04:52.260 --> 03:04:54.840
She'd promised to help translate it

03:04:54.840 --> 03:04:55.920
during their rest stops.

03:04:55.979 --> 03:04:58.739
Axolotl seemed like a human version of

03:04:58.739 --> 03:05:00.659
cricket in some ways, as far as

03:05:00.659 --> 03:05:01.680
Lunicatel.

03:05:01.739 --> 03:05:03.420
They were obsessed with the idea that

03:05:03.420 --> 03:05:05.819
dragons could read, and fascinated by

03:05:05.819 --> 03:05:07.559
what they might find in a dragon book

03:05:07.559 --> 03:05:10.020
exactly the way cricket had been obsessed

03:05:10.020 --> 03:05:11.819
with human books, ever since she found

03:05:11.819 --> 03:05:12.659
out about them.

03:05:13.079 --> 03:05:15.540
It's not just a history of the tree

03:05:15.540 --> 03:05:16.020
wars.

03:05:16.079 --> 03:05:18.899
She said to Luna, laid on their 3rd day

03:05:18.899 --> 03:05:20.700
of travel through the caves.

03:05:20.760 --> 03:05:22.739
As they navigated a slippery rock pile

03:05:22.739 --> 03:05:24.659
with a small chasm off to the left.

03:05:24.719 --> 03:05:26.879
A droplet of water splashed onto

03:05:26.879 --> 03:05:29.399
cricket's glasses, and she paused for a

03:05:29.399 --> 03:05:30.899
moment to wipe them dry on her pouch.

03:05:30.959 --> 03:05:33.780
Luna waited with her, and behind them

03:05:33.780 --> 03:05:35.399
Bullfrog stopped as well.

03:05:35.459 --> 03:05:38.459
Cricket set the spectacles back on her

03:05:38.459 --> 03:05:38.879
snout.

03:05:38.940 --> 03:05:42.959
It's a whole history of the world, she

03:05:42.959 --> 03:05:43.739
breathed.

03:05:43.799 --> 03:05:46.500
Books like this all vanished from my

03:05:46.500 --> 03:05:48.540
school library. especially if I ever

03:05:48.540 --> 03:05:49.319
happened to find one.

03:05:49.379 --> 03:05:51.959
The hive wing philosophy is that

03:05:51.959 --> 03:05:54.120
everything started with the tree wars, and

03:05:54.120 --> 03:05:56.040
you'd better not ask any questions about

03:05:56.040 --> 03:05:57.000
anything before that.

03:05:57.059 --> 03:06:00.600
Luna could imagine that had been a hard

03:06:00.600 --> 03:06:01.979
rule for cricket to follow.

03:06:02.040 --> 03:06:05.040
Is there anything in there about Silkwing

03:06:05.040 --> 03:06:06.840
villages before the tree wars?

03:06:06.899 --> 03:06:08.819
She asked, as they kept walking.

03:06:08.879 --> 03:06:12.840
Lots, Cricket said, with illustrations.

03:06:12.899 --> 03:06:14.459
They were beautiful.

03:06:14.520 --> 03:06:17.159
What about Pyrea?

03:06:17.219 --> 03:06:18.899
Bullfrog asked.

03:06:18.959 --> 03:06:20.100
Stuff about us.

03:06:20.159 --> 03:06:23.459
Yes, although the book calls you the

03:06:23.459 --> 03:06:26.100
distant kingdoms, like we always have, but

03:06:26.100 --> 03:06:27.780
there's a whole chapter about Clearsight

03:06:27.780 --> 03:06:30.540
and another that goes further back to the

03:06:30.540 --> 03:06:33.120
dragons that 1st came over here, and the

03:06:33.120 --> 03:06:34.200
whole legend of the hive.

03:06:34.319 --> 03:06:36.899
Luna shivered.

03:06:36.959 --> 03:06:40.079
The legend of the hive was her new least

03:06:40.079 --> 03:06:43.260
favorite story, and this shadowy K was

03:06:43.260 --> 03:06:45.059
not a great place to be reminded of it.

03:06:45.180 --> 03:06:48.360
She could too easily imagine clouds of

03:06:48.360 --> 03:06:50.819
mind controlled bats swarming their faces

03:06:50.819 --> 03:06:53.760
or hordes of cave centipedes scuttling

03:06:53.760 --> 03:06:54.360
over their claws.

03:06:54.479 --> 03:06:58.379
Up ahead, Sky and the 2 humans had made

03:06:58.379 --> 03:07:00.719
it past the chasm, and were resting near

03:07:00.719 --> 03:07:01.500
a pool in the rocks.

03:07:01.559 --> 03:07:04.739
Strands of a weird, sticky substance hung

03:07:04.739 --> 03:07:06.719
down from the ceiling, with a flying

03:07:06.719 --> 03:07:08.940
insect trapped in one of them, still

03:07:08.940 --> 03:07:09.840
flapping weekly.

03:07:09.899 --> 03:07:13.379
Lune gave the translucent goopy threads a

03:07:13.379 --> 03:07:15.899
wide berth as she approached the others.

03:07:15.959 --> 03:07:19.559
It's after dark, she said, sitting down

03:07:19.559 --> 03:07:20.340
beside Skye.

03:07:20.399 --> 03:07:22.020
Should we all sleep soon?

03:07:22.079 --> 03:07:23.639
Are the humans tired?

03:07:23.760 --> 03:07:26.819
Sky twisted to stare around the cave?

03:07:26.879 --> 03:07:29.280
With a befuddled expression, then looked

03:07:29.280 --> 03:07:29.760
back at her.

03:07:29.819 --> 03:07:32.579
How do you know it's after dark?

03:07:32.579 --> 03:07:33.420
he asked.

03:07:33.479 --> 03:07:36.059
I can't tell if we've been down here for

03:07:36.059 --> 03:07:37.799
2 minutes or 9 days.

03:07:37.860 --> 03:07:42.479
Oh, it's a silkwing thing, Luna said.

03:07:42.540 --> 03:07:44.520
We always know what time of day it is.

03:07:44.579 --> 03:07:47.459
It had taken her internal clock a little

03:07:47.459 --> 03:07:50.459
while to adjust when she landed in Pyria

03:07:50.459 --> 03:07:52.440
and then to adjust back once they reached

03:07:52.440 --> 03:07:55.559
Pantala, but by now, she felt properly

03:07:55.559 --> 03:07:56.520
synced up with the sky.

03:07:56.639 --> 03:08:01.979
Wow, very cool, Skye said with a smile.

03:08:02.040 --> 03:08:05.100
We can go a little farther if you can, Ren

03:08:05.100 --> 03:08:05.639
said.

03:08:05.700 --> 03:08:08.700
Axolotl says there's a drier cave, where

03:08:08.700 --> 03:08:10.200
we can make a fire and spend the night.

03:08:10.260 --> 03:08:13.319
All right, Luna said.

03:08:13.379 --> 03:08:15.299
And cricket and bullfrog agreed.

03:08:15.360 --> 03:08:19.319
They set off again, squeezing into yet

03:08:19.319 --> 03:08:21.420
another tunnel that seemed just barely

03:08:21.420 --> 03:08:22.379
big enough for dragons.

03:08:22.440 --> 03:08:25.139
Luna could feel cricket edging along

03:08:25.139 --> 03:08:26.940
behind her, and she turned her head

03:08:26.940 --> 03:08:28.860
slightly to see the hive wing.

03:08:28.920 --> 03:08:30.659
What else is in that book?

03:08:30.719 --> 03:08:33.719
She asked. hoping to distract herself

03:08:33.719 --> 03:08:35.940
from the tons of rock currently between

03:08:35.940 --> 03:08:36.899
her and the sky.

03:08:36.959 --> 03:08:38.940
Let's think.

03:08:39.000 --> 03:08:43.020
Well, I haven't read this part yet, but

03:08:43.020 --> 03:08:44.399
there's a short section on something

03:08:44.399 --> 03:08:46.079
called the scorching.

03:08:46.200 --> 03:08:47.639
Cricket answered.

03:08:47.700 --> 03:08:50.040
Behind them, Bullfrog grunted.

03:08:50.100 --> 03:08:52.860
Course there is, he said.

03:08:52.920 --> 03:08:55.620
It's in every boring history book.

03:08:55.799 --> 03:08:58.260
Not ours, Cricket said.

03:08:58.319 --> 03:08:59.579
I've never heard of it.

03:08:59.639 --> 03:09:00.840
Have you, Luna?

03:09:00.899 --> 03:09:02.700
Luna shook her head.

03:09:02.760 --> 03:09:04.200
Oh my goodness.

03:09:04.260 --> 03:09:05.940
Bullfrog, tell me everything.

03:09:06.000 --> 03:09:07.620
What do your books say about it?

03:09:07.680 --> 03:09:09.780
Not much.

03:09:09.840 --> 03:09:11.520
Bullfrog said.

03:09:11.579 --> 03:09:14.399
After a moment, he must have felt the

03:09:14.399 --> 03:09:16.200
waves of disapproval coming off cricket

03:09:16.200 --> 03:09:21.059
because he added, Um, it's how we got

03:09:21.059 --> 03:09:23.159
tribes and kingdoms and stuff.

03:09:23.219 --> 03:09:25.260
It is?

03:09:25.379 --> 03:09:26.639
Crickets said.

03:09:26.700 --> 03:09:27.420
What?

03:09:27.479 --> 03:09:27.959
How?

03:09:28.020 --> 03:09:30.180
Weren't there always kingdoms and

03:09:30.180 --> 03:09:30.540
tribes?

03:09:30.659 --> 03:09:33.600
Luna had reached the end of the tunnel

03:09:33.600 --> 03:09:36.180
and wiggled out onto a wider ledge that

03:09:36.180 --> 03:09:37.979
sloped down to a cave floor.

03:09:38.040 --> 03:09:40.739
She started to slide down it and bonked

03:09:40.739 --> 03:09:42.180
her head on a stalactite.

03:09:42.239 --> 03:09:46.200
Ow, she muttered, rubbing her forehead as

03:09:46.200 --> 03:09:47.520
she skidded to a stop at the bottom.

03:09:47.579 --> 03:09:50.879
Bullfrog and Cricket slid down next to

03:09:50.879 --> 03:09:53.100
her, and they started after the light of

03:09:53.100 --> 03:09:55.260
Ren's torch, already more than halfway

03:09:55.260 --> 03:09:55.920
across the cave.

03:09:55.979 --> 03:09:59.459
Bullfrog, Cricket prodded him.

03:09:59.520 --> 03:10:00.719
Say more things.

03:10:00.780 --> 03:10:05.819
Um, he said, sounding more stumped than

03:10:05.819 --> 03:10:06.299
annoyed.

03:10:06.360 --> 03:10:08.819
I don't remember much.

03:10:08.879 --> 03:10:12.120
Not my favorite subject. history.

03:10:12.180 --> 03:10:15.299
But, Cricket prompted.

03:10:15.360 --> 03:10:17.219
You do remember...

03:10:17.280 --> 03:10:18.719
What?

03:10:18.780 --> 03:10:22.139
I guess there were more scavengers back

03:10:22.139 --> 03:10:22.500
then?

03:10:22.500 --> 03:10:23.459
he said.

03:10:23.520 --> 03:10:25.200
Like.

03:10:25.620 --> 03:10:31.020
Over 5000 years ago, and no tribes.

03:10:31.139 --> 03:10:34.739
Dragons lived mostly on their own, I

03:10:34.739 --> 03:10:35.159
think.

03:10:35.159 --> 03:10:38.340
And then a scavenger made a dragon real

03:10:38.340 --> 03:10:39.360
mad.

03:10:39.479 --> 03:10:41.159
So the dragon ate him.

03:10:41.219 --> 03:10:43.739
And then the dragon burned a bunch of

03:10:43.739 --> 03:10:46.500
stuff and got some other dragons to eat a

03:10:46.500 --> 03:10:49.620
bunch more scavengers and burn a bunch

03:10:49.620 --> 03:10:50.280
more stuff.

03:10:50.399 --> 03:10:52.500
And then they made a kingdom.

03:10:52.620 --> 03:10:55.440
And that was the scorching.

03:10:55.500 --> 03:10:59.280
He thought for a moment, and then added

03:10:59.280 --> 03:11:00.899
yup.

03:11:00.959 --> 03:11:05.340
Wow, Luna said, those poor humans.

03:11:05.399 --> 03:11:08.040
Bullfrog scratched his head.

03:11:08.100 --> 03:11:10.860
I mean, he said.

03:11:10.920 --> 03:11:13.620
I think they started it?

03:11:13.680 --> 03:11:16.620
One human, you said.

03:11:16.739 --> 03:11:18.360
Luna pointed out.

03:11:18.420 --> 03:11:20.639
One human made a dragon mad.

03:11:20.700 --> 03:11:22.680
So the dragons ate and burned everybody

03:11:22.680 --> 03:11:22.979
else?

03:11:23.040 --> 03:11:25.200
That's kind of intense.

03:11:25.260 --> 03:11:28.379
I wonder what the human did, Cricket

03:11:28.379 --> 03:11:28.739
said.

03:11:28.799 --> 03:11:31.260
What could make a dragon that angry?

03:11:31.319 --> 03:11:33.120
Stealing treasure?

03:11:33.180 --> 03:11:36.000
Scaring away prey?

03:11:36.059 --> 03:11:38.639
Bullfrog guest, like.

03:11:38.639 --> 03:11:41.819
Really good prey.

03:11:41.879 --> 03:11:44.700
Probably cows.

03:11:44.760 --> 03:11:47.819
Maybe it killed someone the dragon cared

03:11:47.819 --> 03:11:48.120
about.

03:11:48.180 --> 03:11:49.260
Luna asked.

03:11:49.379 --> 03:11:50.940
Hmm.

03:11:51.000 --> 03:11:52.559
Bullfrog said.

03:11:52.620 --> 03:11:55.500
Pretty hard for a scavenger to kill a

03:11:55.500 --> 03:11:56.159
dragon.

03:11:56.219 --> 03:11:59.760
He paused for another moment, then added

03:11:59.760 --> 03:12:03.719
I guess one managed with Queen Oasis

03:12:03.719 --> 03:12:03.959
though.

03:12:04.020 --> 03:12:05.399
What?

03:12:05.459 --> 03:12:07.079
Cricket said avidly.

03:12:07.139 --> 03:12:07.860
Who?

03:12:07.920 --> 03:12:12.299
No, Bullfrog said. pointing at her.

03:12:12.420 --> 03:12:14.760
No, no, no.

03:12:14.819 --> 03:12:18.420
Not your walking history book, me.

03:12:18.479 --> 03:12:22.260
He hurried away to catch up to Ren and

03:12:22.260 --> 03:12:22.620
Skye.

03:12:22.680 --> 03:12:24.420
Any idea?

03:12:24.479 --> 03:12:26.219
Cricket asked Luna.

03:12:26.280 --> 03:12:28.379
Then sighed when Luna shook her head.

03:12:28.440 --> 03:12:30.899
Doesn't it drive you mad?

03:12:30.959 --> 03:12:33.420
All the things there are to know, and how

03:12:33.420 --> 03:12:35.280
much we don't know, and how hard it is to

03:12:35.280 --> 03:12:35.819
find things out?

03:12:35.879 --> 03:12:39.420
I guess, on the scale of all our problems

03:12:39.420 --> 03:12:41.340
that one doesn't bother me so much.

03:12:41.399 --> 03:12:43.020
Luna admitted.

03:12:43.079 --> 03:12:46.020
They reached the bottom of a sheer cliff

03:12:46.020 --> 03:12:48.120
and spread their wings to fly up to the

03:12:48.120 --> 03:12:50.579
top of it, where a sky had already lifted

03:12:50.579 --> 03:12:50.940
the humans.

03:12:51.000 --> 03:12:54.180
It would be nice to find a book called

03:12:54.180 --> 03:12:56.399
What's in the Abyss and what to do about

03:12:56.399 --> 03:12:58.319
it, though, wouldn't it?

03:12:58.440 --> 03:13:00.239
Cricket said wistfully.

03:13:00.299 --> 03:13:03.180
Yes, Luna agreed.

03:13:03.239 --> 03:13:05.819
And also, how to free your mind

03:13:05.819 --> 03:13:09.719
controlled friends. 101 ways to kill an

03:13:09.719 --> 03:13:12.420
evil queen, without, like, having to be

03:13:12.420 --> 03:13:14.819
all mean or violent about it, Cricket

03:13:14.819 --> 03:13:17.159
suggested, and Luna was surprised into

03:13:17.159 --> 03:13:17.520
laughing.

03:13:17.579 --> 03:13:19.979
Do you worry about that too?

03:13:20.100 --> 03:13:21.659
She asked Cricket.

03:13:21.780 --> 03:13:24.780
How to defeat bad guys without being bad

03:13:24.780 --> 03:13:25.200
guys?

03:13:25.260 --> 03:13:26.340
Cricket answered.

03:13:26.459 --> 03:13:28.379
All the time.

03:13:28.440 --> 03:13:30.600
Luna held out her talons.

03:13:30.659 --> 03:13:33.719
How do you use a gift like fire to win a

03:13:33.719 --> 03:13:35.459
war, but without hurting anyone?

03:13:35.520 --> 03:13:38.520
How to care about all dragons?

03:13:38.579 --> 03:13:39.540
The way Blue does?

03:13:39.659 --> 03:13:41.399
Cricket said as they landed.

03:13:41.459 --> 03:13:43.979
But fight them the way sundu would if

03:13:43.979 --> 03:13:44.520
they hurt someone?

03:13:44.579 --> 03:13:48.360
This was so, almost exactly the thought

03:13:48.360 --> 03:13:50.700
Luna had been having, that she reached

03:13:50.700 --> 03:13:52.139
out and grabbed Cricket's arm.

03:13:52.200 --> 03:13:55.860
Once, Luna and Sortail had been talking

03:13:55.860 --> 03:13:58.260
about the Salvation Wall, and he'd said

03:13:58.260 --> 03:14:00.059
the exact thing she'd been about to say.

03:14:00.120 --> 03:14:02.819
She'd gotten so excited, that she had

03:14:02.819 --> 03:14:05.459
jumped on him, yelling, my brain words

03:14:05.459 --> 03:14:06.540
words of my head.

03:14:06.780 --> 03:14:08.940
That had been their joke ever since.

03:14:09.059 --> 03:14:11.700
Whenever they agreed about something, one

03:14:11.700 --> 03:14:14.100
of them would declare, my brain words, or

03:14:14.100 --> 03:14:16.920
words of my head, and they'd both fall

03:14:16.920 --> 03:14:17.639
over laughing.

03:14:18.420 --> 03:14:21.239
She came within a breath of shouting, my

03:14:21.239 --> 03:14:23.639
brain words, at cricket, before

03:14:23.639 --> 03:14:25.379
remembering that was only for sword

03:14:25.379 --> 03:14:25.860
tail.

03:14:26.040 --> 03:14:27.959
And then she had to stand there for a

03:14:27.959 --> 03:14:31.139
moment, eyes closed, until she no longer

03:14:31.139 --> 03:14:32.639
felt like she'd been punched in the

03:14:32.639 --> 03:14:33.000
stomach.

03:14:33.000 --> 03:14:35.100
Are you all right?

03:14:35.159 --> 03:14:36.299
Cricket asked.

03:14:36.360 --> 03:14:40.139
Yep, Luna said, letting go over.

03:14:40.200 --> 03:14:42.059
Still smiling.

03:14:42.120 --> 03:14:43.139
No problems here.

03:14:43.200 --> 03:14:47.340
Yes, just what you said, exactly.

03:14:47.399 --> 03:14:50.819
But mostly, how to save blue and sore

03:14:50.819 --> 03:14:51.120
tail.

03:14:51.239 --> 03:14:54.360
She turned her wrist up to the ceiling

03:14:54.360 --> 03:14:57.420
again, to study the fire gold dots below

03:14:57.420 --> 03:14:57.899
her scales.

03:14:57.959 --> 03:15:02.280
I will set dragons on fire for them if I

03:15:02.280 --> 03:15:02.579
have to.

03:15:02.639 --> 03:15:05.399
Me too, Cricket said.

03:15:05.459 --> 03:15:08.280
Well, all right, no, I can't.

03:15:08.340 --> 03:15:09.120
But I will.

03:15:09.180 --> 03:15:10.680
I will.

03:15:10.860 --> 03:15:13.500
Throw books at anyone who's mean to them

03:15:13.500 --> 03:15:14.100
so there.

03:15:14.159 --> 03:15:16.920
Big heavy ones, so watch out, jerks.

03:15:16.979 --> 03:15:20.879
All right, Luna thought, hiding a smile.

03:15:20.940 --> 03:15:24.600
And for the 1st time she thought, Maybe I

03:15:24.600 --> 03:15:26.700
kind of get what Blue sees in this hive

03:15:26.700 --> 03:15:27.120
wing.

03:15:27.180 --> 03:15:30.360
Between those superpowers, will

03:15:30.360 --> 03:15:32.459
definitely get them back, she said.

03:15:32.520 --> 03:15:34.260
Today.

03:15:34.319 --> 03:15:36.659
Now, she mostly believed it.

03:15:36.719 --> 03:15:39.780
She could feel the rainy season fog

03:15:39.780 --> 03:15:42.000
fading, and little cracks of sunlight

03:15:42.000 --> 03:15:44.819
hope pushing through her brain. ironic

03:15:44.819 --> 03:15:46.799
considering she hadn't seen the actual

03:15:46.799 --> 03:15:47.520
sun in 3 days.

03:15:47.579 --> 03:15:50.819
They had been walking along the cliff top

03:15:50.819 --> 03:15:54.120
for a while, under a vast ceiling, studded

03:15:54.120 --> 03:15:57.000
with spires and glow worms, when Bullfrog

03:15:57.000 --> 03:15:59.459
suddenly stopped, Luna nearly stepped on

03:15:59.459 --> 03:15:59.760
his tail.

03:15:59.879 --> 03:16:04.979
He said, staring at the inky blackness

03:16:04.979 --> 03:16:06.540
beyond the flame silk glow.

03:16:06.600 --> 03:16:09.059
Luna and Cricket froze.

03:16:09.120 --> 03:16:12.059
Ahead of them, Sky and the humans did the

03:16:12.059 --> 03:16:12.239
same.

03:16:12.299 --> 03:16:15.659
Was that a flicker of wind in the silent

03:16:15.659 --> 03:16:16.020
cave?

03:16:16.079 --> 03:16:19.680
Luna's antennae unfurled instinctively

03:16:19.680 --> 03:16:22.020
checking for strange vibrations in the

03:16:22.020 --> 03:16:22.200
air.

03:16:28.260 --> 03:16:33.719
There was something.

03:16:33.780 --> 03:16:36.780
A very still distant sound.

03:16:36.840 --> 03:16:39.780
Like someone hidden in the spires

03:16:39.780 --> 03:16:43.200
overhead, just... breathing.

03:16:43.319 --> 03:16:47.219
And then, the hidden something shifted

03:16:47.219 --> 03:16:50.219
leaned forward, and began to glide on

03:16:50.219 --> 03:16:51.899
silent wings toward them.

03:16:51.959 --> 03:16:56.159
Chapter 9.

03:16:56.219 --> 03:16:58.559
The humans?

03:16:58.620 --> 03:17:01.620
Luna shouted, lunging past bullfrog.

03:17:01.680 --> 03:17:03.600
Sky protect the humans.

03:17:03.659 --> 03:17:06.540
There was a flurry of shrieks and wing

03:17:06.540 --> 03:17:09.180
beats. and muffled cries from Wren and

03:17:09.180 --> 03:17:11.579
Axolotl as Skye threw himself on top of

03:17:11.579 --> 03:17:13.379
both of them, covering them with his

03:17:13.379 --> 03:17:13.680
wings.

03:17:13.799 --> 03:17:17.459
Bullfrog rose up on his hind legs, front

03:17:17.459 --> 03:17:19.620
claws slashing at the air, hissing.

03:17:19.680 --> 03:17:23.280
A dark shape shot over their heads and

03:17:23.280 --> 03:17:24.360
smashed into cricket.

03:17:24.420 --> 03:17:26.760
She was thrown back against the stone

03:17:26.760 --> 03:17:28.260
wall with an awful thud.

03:17:28.319 --> 03:17:31.260
Luna whirled and raced over to her.

03:17:31.319 --> 03:17:34.440
As the light of her flame silk got closer

03:17:34.440 --> 03:17:36.899
she realized the dark shape was a

03:17:36.899 --> 03:17:37.319
dragon.

03:17:37.379 --> 03:17:42.059
A leaf wing, a large, furious leaf wing

03:17:42.059 --> 03:17:43.979
who now had cricket pinned to the floor

03:17:43.979 --> 03:17:45.780
with his talons around her neck.

03:17:45.840 --> 03:17:46.979
Stop!

03:17:47.040 --> 03:17:48.000
Luna yelled.

03:17:48.120 --> 03:17:49.500
Don't hurt her.

03:17:49.559 --> 03:17:50.100
She's with us.

03:17:50.159 --> 03:17:51.000
We're friends.

03:17:51.059 --> 03:17:52.260
We're all on the same side.

03:17:52.319 --> 03:17:54.299
By all this silk stop it.

03:17:54.360 --> 03:17:57.360
She rammed her shoulder into the leaf

03:17:57.360 --> 03:18:00.239
wing side, but he only lifted one wing to

03:18:00.239 --> 03:18:01.260
glance at her sternly.

03:18:01.319 --> 03:18:05.280
Have to make her unconscious, he said.

03:18:05.340 --> 03:18:07.319
A little out of breath as Cricket

03:18:07.319 --> 03:18:09.840
struggled and kicked at him to protect

03:18:09.840 --> 03:18:10.079
us.

03:18:10.139 --> 03:18:14.760
No, no, Luna said, understanding what was

03:18:14.760 --> 03:18:15.059
happening.

03:18:15.180 --> 03:18:18.059
She doesn't have Queen Wasp inside her.

03:18:18.120 --> 03:18:20.700
She's the one hive wing who isn't mind

03:18:20.700 --> 03:18:21.239
controlled.

03:18:21.299 --> 03:18:22.559
Haven't you heard about her?

03:18:22.620 --> 03:18:25.260
This is cricket, the one who stole the

03:18:25.260 --> 03:18:26.159
book of Clearsight.

03:18:26.280 --> 03:18:30.360
Hmm, he said. rings a bell.

03:18:30.479 --> 03:18:33.000
He glanced down at her without moving his

03:18:33.000 --> 03:18:33.600
talons.

03:18:33.659 --> 03:18:36.000
Better saved than sorry, though.

03:18:36.059 --> 03:18:40.920
You'd really better stop now, Bullfrog

03:18:40.920 --> 03:18:42.840
said, looming up behind Luna.

03:18:42.899 --> 03:18:45.959
Or I will have to do some hitting.

03:18:46.079 --> 03:18:49.200
The leaf wing looked skeptical.

03:18:49.260 --> 03:18:52.200
He was about the same size as the mudwing

03:18:52.200 --> 03:18:53.340
and then confused.

03:18:53.399 --> 03:18:56.579
He squinted at Bullfrog in the flame silk

03:18:56.579 --> 03:18:58.379
light, but didn't stop leaning on

03:18:58.379 --> 03:18:59.159
Cricket's throat.

03:18:59.219 --> 03:19:01.860
Her flailing was getting weaker, Luna

03:19:01.860 --> 03:19:03.600
noticed, with a touch of panic.

03:19:03.659 --> 03:19:06.420
What are you?

03:19:06.540 --> 03:19:08.639
The leaf wing asked bullfrog.

03:19:08.700 --> 03:19:12.180
We're friends of Sundoo, Luna blurted.

03:19:12.239 --> 03:19:14.879
Oh, really?

03:19:14.940 --> 03:19:16.559
Said the Leaf Wing.

03:19:16.620 --> 03:19:18.780
Immediately releasing cricket and taking

03:19:18.780 --> 03:19:21.719
a step back, Cricket rolled onto her side

03:19:21.719 --> 03:19:22.139
gasping.

03:19:22.319 --> 03:19:25.799
Should have mentioned that sooner. he

03:19:25.799 --> 03:19:27.840
said, looking down at the high wing

03:19:27.840 --> 03:19:28.500
reproachfully.

03:19:28.559 --> 03:19:30.840
When?

03:19:31.020 --> 03:19:32.760
Cricket managed to croak.

03:19:32.819 --> 03:19:35.100
The leaf wing rubbed his chin for a

03:19:35.100 --> 03:19:35.340
moment.

03:19:35.399 --> 03:19:37.500
Hmm, he said.

03:19:37.559 --> 03:19:40.319
Should wear a sign, maybe.

03:19:40.440 --> 03:19:42.719
Listing all our friends?

03:19:42.780 --> 03:19:43.920
Luna demanded.

03:19:43.979 --> 03:19:45.719
Who are you anyway?

03:19:45.780 --> 03:19:48.600
How do we know you don't have Queen Wasp

03:19:48.600 --> 03:19:49.020
inside you?

03:19:49.079 --> 03:19:52.500
He stared at her, and then sat down

03:19:52.500 --> 03:19:52.860
heavily.

03:19:52.920 --> 03:19:58.500
So it's true, he said, closing his eyes.

03:19:58.559 --> 03:20:02.520
The devastation on his face nearly sucked

03:20:02.520 --> 03:20:04.200
away all of Luna's anger at him.

03:20:04.319 --> 03:20:07.920
That she can infect leaf wings now?

03:20:07.979 --> 03:20:09.059
She said gently.

03:20:09.120 --> 03:20:10.379
Yes.

03:20:10.440 --> 03:20:12.180
And silk wings.

03:20:12.239 --> 03:20:16.559
Not us, though, Cricket said, with a

03:20:16.559 --> 03:20:18.120
faint wave of her wing at the group of

03:20:18.120 --> 03:20:18.299
them.

03:20:18.360 --> 03:20:19.860
Not just anyone.

03:20:19.920 --> 03:20:22.440
You have to be exposed to the breath of

03:20:22.440 --> 03:20:23.159
evil first.

03:20:23.280 --> 03:20:27.180
He still looked confused, so Luna added

03:20:27.180 --> 03:20:29.819
either by being stabbed with her tail

03:20:29.819 --> 03:20:31.920
venom, or breathing in the smoke from

03:20:31.920 --> 03:20:32.700
this awful plant.

03:20:32.760 --> 03:20:34.139
It's a long story.

03:20:34.200 --> 03:20:36.420
Why are you down here?

03:20:36.479 --> 03:20:37.680
Cricket asked.

03:20:37.739 --> 03:20:39.360
Why aren't you with the other leaf

03:20:39.360 --> 03:20:39.719
wings?

03:20:39.780 --> 03:20:45.600
Was on a mission, he said morosely, hid

03:20:45.600 --> 03:20:46.860
got stuck here.

03:20:46.979 --> 03:20:49.260
He pointed at bullfrog.

03:20:49.319 --> 03:20:51.180
What is that?

03:20:51.299 --> 03:20:54.959
Bullfrog looked as ruffled as Luna had

03:20:54.959 --> 03:20:55.379
ever seen him.

03:20:55.440 --> 03:20:59.399
I'm not a that, he said.

03:20:59.459 --> 03:21:01.260
I'm a mudwing.

03:21:01.319 --> 03:21:04.979
This is bullfrog, Luna explained.

03:21:05.040 --> 03:21:07.379
He came from the distant kingdoms to help

03:21:07.379 --> 03:21:09.180
us, and so did they.

03:21:09.239 --> 03:21:12.420
She pointed to where Skye was still lying

03:21:12.420 --> 03:21:13.559
flat on top of the humans.

03:21:13.680 --> 03:21:16.860
The noises coming from under his wings

03:21:16.860 --> 03:21:18.659
sounded decidedly grouchy now.

03:21:18.719 --> 03:21:22.079
Skye, you can let them out, she called.

03:21:22.139 --> 03:21:23.219
He won't eat them.

03:21:23.280 --> 03:21:25.020
You won't eat them, will you?

03:21:25.079 --> 03:21:27.299
Eat what?

03:21:27.420 --> 03:21:30.360
The leaf wing's eyes went as big as the

03:21:30.360 --> 03:21:33.180
moons, as the 2 humans scrambled out from

03:21:33.180 --> 03:21:34.139
under Sky's wings.

03:21:34.260 --> 03:21:36.360
You.

03:21:36.479 --> 03:21:38.940
You have an underground monkey.

03:21:39.000 --> 03:21:42.239
Two underground monkeys.

03:21:42.299 --> 03:21:43.799
Huh.

03:21:43.860 --> 03:21:47.819
Rather think you could spare one, don't

03:21:47.819 --> 03:21:47.940
you?

03:21:48.000 --> 03:21:51.540
Seems selfish not to share when we are so

03:21:51.540 --> 03:21:52.139
hungry.

03:21:52.200 --> 03:21:55.139
His teeth gleamed.

03:21:55.260 --> 03:21:58.500
They're not provisions, Luna cried.

03:21:58.559 --> 03:21:59.579
They're not for eating.

03:21:59.639 --> 03:22:02.340
We're not monkeys either.

03:22:02.399 --> 03:22:05.700
Wren added in Dragon, sauntering up and

03:22:05.700 --> 03:22:06.959
putting her paws on her hips.

03:22:07.020 --> 03:22:09.840
The leaf wing flapped his jaw for a while

03:22:09.840 --> 03:22:11.700
in a very gratifying way.

03:22:11.760 --> 03:22:14.760
It...

03:22:15.059 --> 03:22:17.100
You taught it to talk.

03:22:17.219 --> 03:22:19.079
He finally managed.

03:22:19.139 --> 03:22:21.479
How did you do that?

03:22:21.540 --> 03:22:23.700
Oh.

03:22:23.819 --> 03:22:26.040
Why did you do that?

03:22:26.100 --> 03:22:29.399
Oh, it was quite hard.

03:22:29.459 --> 03:22:31.739
Skye said. years of training.

03:22:31.799 --> 03:22:34.020
They're very clever mimics though.

03:22:34.079 --> 03:22:34.860
Watch this.

03:22:34.920 --> 03:22:36.600
Not funny Sky.

03:22:36.659 --> 03:22:41.100
Not funny, Skye, Ren said, at almost the

03:22:41.100 --> 03:22:41.879
exact same moment.

03:22:41.940 --> 03:22:43.920
She frowned at Skye.

03:22:43.979 --> 03:22:45.540
Then at the leaf wing.

03:22:45.600 --> 03:22:47.399
I'm not a parrot.

03:22:47.459 --> 03:22:49.920
I can speak dragon, and you shouldn't eat

03:22:49.920 --> 03:22:50.639
any humans.

03:22:50.700 --> 03:22:52.379
We're just as smart as you are.

03:22:52.440 --> 03:22:55.379
Ha, said the leaf wing.

03:22:55.440 --> 03:22:56.520
Ha!

03:22:56.579 --> 03:22:58.979
Huh.

03:22:59.040 --> 03:23:02.100
This is very odd.

03:23:02.219 --> 03:23:06.059
I think I should take you to Hemlock.

03:23:06.120 --> 03:23:08.280
He'll sort this out.

03:23:08.340 --> 03:23:11.940
He gave Axolotl a measuring look.

03:23:12.059 --> 03:23:13.739
What about that one?

03:23:13.799 --> 03:23:16.860
You sure I can't eat that one?

03:23:16.920 --> 03:23:19.979
You're thick, aren't you?

03:23:20.040 --> 03:23:20.940
Ren said.

03:23:21.000 --> 03:23:23.639
The Leaf Wing growled resentfully.

03:23:23.700 --> 03:23:26.819
Doesn't seem fair, he said.

03:23:26.879 --> 03:23:30.479
There's hardly anything I can eat down

03:23:30.479 --> 03:23:30.780
here.

03:23:30.840 --> 03:23:34.200
Now you're taking a whole species off the

03:23:34.200 --> 03:23:34.979
list.

03:23:35.159 --> 03:23:37.079
Rude, that is.

03:23:37.200 --> 03:23:41.520
I'm pretty sure it's more rude to eat

03:23:41.520 --> 03:23:43.559
something that can talk to you, Ren

03:23:43.559 --> 03:23:43.920
said.

03:23:43.979 --> 03:23:45.959
No earring.

03:23:46.020 --> 03:23:46.620
No.

03:23:46.680 --> 03:23:49.739
Axolotl suddenly shouted in dragon

03:23:49.739 --> 03:23:52.139
popping out from behind Sky's leg, and

03:23:52.139 --> 03:23:53.459
then immediately ducking bag.

03:23:53.520 --> 03:23:57.180
Sky collapsed in giggles, nearly landing

03:23:57.180 --> 03:23:58.620
on the small human, who looked

03:23:58.620 --> 03:23:59.219
affronted.

03:23:59.280 --> 03:24:01.860
The leaf wing blinked at them.

03:24:01.979 --> 03:24:04.020
What?

03:24:04.079 --> 03:24:08.399
They mean no eating, Ren said.

03:24:08.459 --> 03:24:10.079
Clearly try not to laugh.

03:24:10.139 --> 03:24:11.639
We're working on it.

03:24:11.700 --> 03:24:15.000
No eating, she growled at Axolotl.

03:24:15.059 --> 03:24:18.360
No eating. they growled back.

03:24:18.420 --> 03:24:20.700
In a pretty decent dragon accent, Luna

03:24:20.700 --> 03:24:21.180
thought.

03:24:21.239 --> 03:24:24.120
She'd noticed that Axolotl picked up

03:24:24.120 --> 03:24:25.620
written language more quickly than things

03:24:25.620 --> 03:24:25.979
they heard.

03:24:26.100 --> 03:24:28.860
Cricket had been looking at the book with

03:24:28.860 --> 03:24:31.379
them each night, and Axolotl was already

03:24:31.379 --> 03:24:33.479
recognizing several letters and a few

03:24:33.479 --> 03:24:33.659
words.

03:24:33.719 --> 03:24:36.540
If they actually had more time to sit and

03:24:36.540 --> 03:24:36.719
study.

03:24:36.780 --> 03:24:39.120
Axolotl might be able to communicate with

03:24:39.120 --> 03:24:41.879
dragons in writing. more or less within a

03:24:41.879 --> 03:24:42.239
month or so.

03:24:42.299 --> 03:24:46.020
Wait, Cricket said, struggling to her

03:24:46.020 --> 03:24:46.379
feet.

03:24:46.440 --> 03:24:48.059
Did you say hemlock?

03:24:48.120 --> 03:24:49.079
Sundu's dad?

03:24:49.139 --> 03:24:51.299
Are you with Bryony?

03:24:51.420 --> 03:24:53.159
and the silk wings that fled bloodworm

03:24:53.159 --> 03:24:53.520
hive?

03:24:53.579 --> 03:24:55.979
He blinked at her a few times.

03:24:56.100 --> 03:24:58.920
How do you know all that?

03:24:58.979 --> 03:25:02.159
A dragon in the distant kingdoms had a

03:25:02.159 --> 03:25:04.079
vision about all of you, Cricket

03:25:04.079 --> 03:25:04.559
explained.

03:25:04.620 --> 03:25:07.620
I don't think she mentioned you, though.

03:25:07.739 --> 03:25:11.100
The leaf wing drew himself up and looked

03:25:11.100 --> 03:25:11.459
annoyed.

03:25:11.520 --> 03:25:15.000
I'm pokeweed, he said.

03:25:15.059 --> 03:25:17.280
I'm essential to the mission.

03:25:17.399 --> 03:25:19.860
Pokweed.

03:25:19.920 --> 03:25:21.120
Cricket echoed.

03:25:21.180 --> 03:25:22.020
Huh.

03:25:22.079 --> 03:25:22.920
Nope.

03:25:23.040 --> 03:25:25.860
We are heading for a human settlement

03:25:25.860 --> 03:25:27.540
near an abyss, Luna said.

03:25:27.600 --> 03:25:29.159
This one is guiding us.

03:25:29.219 --> 03:25:33.059
She waved one wing at Axolotl, who was

03:25:33.059 --> 03:25:35.040
staying as close to Skye's side as

03:25:35.040 --> 03:25:37.260
possible, and making little muttery

03:25:37.260 --> 03:25:38.219
dragon like noises.

03:25:38.280 --> 03:25:40.559
Oh, what?

03:25:40.559 --> 03:25:42.180
Nero what?

03:25:42.239 --> 03:25:44.219
Pokweed scratched his head.

03:25:44.280 --> 03:25:46.079
An abyss?

03:25:46.139 --> 03:25:49.079
A really big dark chasm, Cricket told

03:25:49.079 --> 03:25:49.440
him.

03:25:49.500 --> 03:25:51.299
Have you seen one of those down here?

03:25:51.360 --> 03:25:54.600
Pokweed waved his wings around.

03:25:54.659 --> 03:25:59.159
Saw one big dark chasm, isn't it?

03:25:59.219 --> 03:26:03.299
This one would be bigger and darker and

03:26:03.299 --> 03:26:03.959
more...

03:26:03.959 --> 03:26:08.819
Down, Luna said, like way down.

03:26:08.879 --> 03:26:11.399
Seems weird.

03:26:11.520 --> 03:26:13.200
Pokweed said.

03:26:13.260 --> 03:26:15.120
Weird thing to look for.

03:26:15.180 --> 03:26:17.639
Unless it's for hiding.

03:26:17.700 --> 03:26:19.319
Is that what it's for?

03:26:19.440 --> 03:26:20.940
Hiding from WASP?

03:26:21.059 --> 03:26:23.760
No, Cricket said.

03:26:23.819 --> 03:26:25.319
I mean, we're not sure.

03:26:25.379 --> 03:26:27.479
We're hoping there's something in it that

03:26:27.479 --> 03:26:28.079
can stop her.

03:26:28.139 --> 03:26:29.940
Hmm.

03:26:30.059 --> 03:26:32.100
Even more weird.

03:26:32.159 --> 03:26:35.760
Pokweed shrugged and turned, waving one

03:26:35.760 --> 03:26:36.120
wing.

03:26:36.180 --> 03:26:38.579
You explain it to Hemlock.

03:26:38.700 --> 03:26:40.920
He won't believe me if I try.

03:26:41.040 --> 03:26:44.819
Ren and Axolotl chattered for a moment

03:26:44.819 --> 03:26:47.459
inhuman, then climbed on disguise back

03:26:47.459 --> 03:26:50.219
and they all flew after Pokweed, through

03:26:50.219 --> 03:26:51.420
the vast open cave.

03:26:51.479 --> 03:26:54.780
It was a bit hazardous, dodging the

03:26:54.780 --> 03:26:57.120
stalactites, but it was a relief to be

03:26:57.120 --> 03:26:59.760
flying again after 3 days of walking and

03:26:59.760 --> 03:27:00.899
climbing and sliding.

03:27:00.959 --> 03:27:03.840
Luna stretched her wings as wide as she

03:27:03.840 --> 03:27:05.280
could and shook out her tail.

03:27:05.340 --> 03:27:09.000
Pokweed had evidently ventured a long way

03:27:09.000 --> 03:27:10.500
from the rest of the group in search of

03:27:10.500 --> 03:27:10.739
food.

03:27:10.799 --> 03:27:13.260
Luna felt like they were following him

03:27:13.260 --> 03:27:14.100
for hours.

03:27:14.159 --> 03:27:16.860
Half the time they could fly, but for

03:27:16.860 --> 03:27:18.659
much of the journey, they had to crawl

03:27:18.659 --> 03:27:20.280
through tunnels or climb through

03:27:20.280 --> 03:27:21.659
passageways in the rock.

03:27:21.719 --> 03:27:25.680
Pokweed radiated a distinct air of slow

03:27:25.680 --> 03:27:26.879
and unimaginative.

03:27:26.940 --> 03:27:29.520
But if he'd been willing to explore this

03:27:29.520 --> 03:27:32.760
far alone and memorize the way back, Luna

03:27:32.760 --> 03:27:34.559
thought he must be braver and smarter

03:27:34.559 --> 03:27:35.159
than he seemed.

03:27:35.219 --> 03:27:39.059
He wasn't a very good listener though, at

03:27:39.059 --> 03:27:41.459
least not to silk wings, hive wings, or

03:27:41.459 --> 03:27:41.760
humans.

03:27:41.819 --> 03:27:44.159
Maybe he paid more attention when other

03:27:44.159 --> 03:27:45.120
leaf wings were talking.

03:27:45.180 --> 03:27:48.659
As they dropped down a shaft into a damp

03:27:48.659 --> 03:27:50.879
tunnel, Luna's antennae picked up

03:27:50.879 --> 03:27:53.159
movement, and murmuring vibrations ahead

03:27:53.159 --> 03:27:53.459
of them.

03:27:53.520 --> 03:27:54.899
From a distance.

03:27:54.959 --> 03:27:58.260
It sounded like wind in a forest, leaves

03:27:58.260 --> 03:27:59.879
brushing and whispering ahead of a

03:27:59.879 --> 03:28:00.180
storm.

03:28:00.239 --> 03:28:03.479
They emerged from the tunnel into a cave

03:28:03.479 --> 03:28:05.219
that surrounded an underground lake.

03:28:05.280 --> 03:28:08.219
Odd crystalline shapes jutted from the

03:28:08.219 --> 03:28:10.500
walls, like tapestries made of

03:28:10.500 --> 03:28:12.239
translucent gems instead of silk.

03:28:12.299 --> 03:28:15.540
Glow worms dotted the ceiling, like

03:28:15.540 --> 03:28:18.600
strange blue constellations, and a faint

03:28:18.600 --> 03:28:20.639
phosphorescent glow came from deep under

03:28:20.639 --> 03:28:21.659
the surface of the lake.

03:28:21.719 --> 03:28:23.879
But those were the only sources of

03:28:23.879 --> 03:28:24.059
light.

03:28:24.180 --> 03:28:28.079
The murmurs resolved into dragon voices

03:28:28.079 --> 03:28:30.780
hushed and flat, and echoing in the

03:28:30.780 --> 03:28:31.440
cavernous space.

03:28:31.500 --> 03:28:34.500
She couldn't see them all, but Luna's

03:28:34.500 --> 03:28:36.059
antennas sensed there were over a 100

03:28:36.059 --> 03:28:38.579
dragons in this cave alone, with more

03:28:38.579 --> 03:28:40.319
scattered in caves and tunnels that

03:28:40.319 --> 03:28:41.219
branched off this one.

03:28:41.280 --> 03:28:44.639
I'd weave this place with black silk

03:28:44.639 --> 03:28:45.000
thread.

03:28:45.120 --> 03:28:47.639
A tapestry all dark from far away.

03:28:47.700 --> 03:28:50.399
But with little circles of light in gold

03:28:50.399 --> 03:28:54.299
silk, and up close, around each gold silk

03:28:54.299 --> 03:28:57.120
circle, you'd find outlines of wings or

03:28:57.120 --> 03:29:00.540
tails or dragon faces, maybe in dark gray

03:29:00.540 --> 03:29:02.760
silk, hovering all around the lights.

03:29:02.819 --> 03:29:06.840
A quartet of small silkwing dragonettes

03:29:06.840 --> 03:29:08.700
was sitting near the tunnel on the shore

03:29:08.700 --> 03:29:10.739
of the lake, dabbling their talent

03:29:10.739 --> 03:29:11.760
listlessly in the water.

03:29:11.819 --> 03:29:14.819
They looked up as Pokweed stepped into

03:29:14.819 --> 03:29:17.340
the cave, and then they saw Luna, and

03:29:17.340 --> 03:29:18.239
their eyes went huge.

03:29:18.299 --> 03:29:20.280
Mommy!

03:29:20.340 --> 03:29:22.559
The little pink one shouted, leaping to

03:29:22.559 --> 03:29:22.920
her feet.

03:29:22.979 --> 03:29:25.620
Mommy, there's a dragon with fire on her

03:29:25.620 --> 03:29:25.860
head.

03:29:25.920 --> 03:29:28.200
Mommy, mommy, she has a fire hat.

03:29:28.260 --> 03:29:31.559
I want a fire hat, cried the small orange

03:29:31.559 --> 03:29:32.459
one beside her.

03:29:32.520 --> 03:29:36.120
Nobody ever lets me set a hat on fire and

03:29:36.120 --> 03:29:37.739
put it on my head, not fair.

03:29:37.860 --> 03:29:40.139
It's not a hat.

03:29:40.260 --> 03:29:42.959
The lime green one barked imperiously.

03:29:43.020 --> 03:29:45.120
It is obviously a crown.

03:29:45.180 --> 03:29:47.579
I bet she is a fire queen.

03:29:47.639 --> 03:29:51.540
The 4th dragonette, who was lavender with

03:29:51.540 --> 03:29:53.459
speckles of dark blue and turquoise

03:29:53.459 --> 03:29:56.100
bolted straight out to Luna's feet, sat

03:29:56.100 --> 03:29:57.719
down, and stared up at her.

03:29:57.780 --> 03:29:59.879
He looked a bit like her earliest

03:29:59.879 --> 03:30:02.159
memories of blue, between the colors of

03:30:02.159 --> 03:30:04.139
his scales, and his trusting expression.

03:30:04.260 --> 03:30:08.100
Um, Luna said, hello?

03:30:08.159 --> 03:30:09.780
Hi.

03:30:09.840 --> 03:30:12.059
The dragonette said softly.

03:30:12.120 --> 03:30:15.420
The reflection of the flame silk glowed

03:30:15.420 --> 03:30:16.620
in his awestruck eyes.

03:30:16.680 --> 03:30:19.860
Luna realized more dragonettes were

03:30:19.860 --> 03:30:22.139
cantering her way, all of them with

03:30:22.139 --> 03:30:23.700
similar bedazzled expressions.

03:30:23.760 --> 03:30:27.120
Behind them came several grown silk wings

03:30:27.120 --> 03:30:29.280
who looked more tired than anything else

03:30:29.280 --> 03:30:31.559
but at least a few looked happy to see

03:30:31.559 --> 03:30:32.520
her, she thought.

03:30:32.579 --> 03:30:36.959
Thank the moons, said one of the older

03:30:36.959 --> 03:30:39.180
dragons, clasping her front talons

03:30:39.180 --> 03:30:39.540
together.

03:30:39.600 --> 03:30:42.719
The last of the flame silk we brought

03:30:42.719 --> 03:30:44.280
with us faded days ago.

03:30:44.340 --> 03:30:48.299
And it's been so dark, said the Pink

03:30:48.299 --> 03:30:49.079
Dragonette.

03:30:49.139 --> 03:30:51.059
I do not like it's so dark.

03:30:51.180 --> 03:30:54.120
Yes, you do, said the orange one.

03:30:54.180 --> 03:30:57.000
You said yesterday that it wasn't so bad

03:30:57.000 --> 03:30:58.860
and you called me a Freddy slug.

03:30:58.920 --> 03:31:01.379
I'm the one who doesn't like the dark.

03:31:01.440 --> 03:31:03.959
If anyone's getting a fire hat, it should

03:31:03.959 --> 03:31:05.219
be me, because you're mean.

03:31:05.280 --> 03:31:08.700
You were mean first, shouted the pink

03:31:08.700 --> 03:31:09.420
dragonette.

03:31:09.479 --> 03:31:11.399
Mommy, tell him he's the mean one.

03:31:11.459 --> 03:31:14.040
The dark is whispery.

03:31:14.100 --> 03:31:17.459
Breathed the dragonette at Luna's feet

03:31:17.459 --> 03:31:19.079
inching a bit closer to her.

03:31:19.139 --> 03:31:21.899
She noticed that he had a little star

03:31:21.899 --> 03:31:24.479
shaped white scar on his forehead, over

03:31:24.479 --> 03:31:26.879
his left eye, and another on his shoulder

03:31:26.879 --> 03:31:28.620
near his right wing bud.

03:31:28.680 --> 03:31:31.620
Poor little dragon, she thought.

03:31:31.680 --> 03:31:32.879
What happened to you?

03:31:32.940 --> 03:31:36.600
He also wore 2 of the heavy wrist cuffs

03:31:36.600 --> 03:31:37.500
instead of just one.

03:31:37.559 --> 03:31:40.860
She gently lifted one of his talons to

03:31:40.860 --> 03:31:43.500
read the inscription on the cuff, Weaver

03:31:43.500 --> 03:31:43.860
Hall.

03:31:43.920 --> 03:31:45.479
That must be his school.

03:31:45.540 --> 03:31:48.719
The other said, construction apprentice.

03:31:48.780 --> 03:31:50.940
Apprentice.

03:31:51.000 --> 03:31:52.860
He can't be more than 2 years old.

03:31:52.920 --> 03:31:55.979
How could a dragon this tiny be part of a

03:31:55.979 --> 03:31:57.120
construction crew already?

03:31:57.180 --> 03:32:01.559
She knew, from Swordtail's stories, that

03:32:01.559 --> 03:32:03.360
it was a dangerous, exhausting job

03:32:03.360 --> 03:32:05.520
working with the tree stuff on the

03:32:05.520 --> 03:32:06.059
hives.

03:32:06.120 --> 03:32:08.579
Maybe that was how this little dragon had

03:32:08.579 --> 03:32:09.659
gotten his scars.

03:32:09.719 --> 03:32:13.200
He gazed up at her hopefully, as she set

03:32:13.200 --> 03:32:14.100
his talon down again.

03:32:14.159 --> 03:32:17.219
I have never met an actual flame silk

03:32:17.219 --> 03:32:20.340
said another dragon, who had wings, but

03:32:20.340 --> 03:32:21.659
didn't look much older than Luna.

03:32:21.719 --> 03:32:22.979
Did you really make that?

03:32:23.040 --> 03:32:25.799
I did, Luna said.

03:32:25.860 --> 03:32:27.719
Um, hi, I'm Luna.

03:32:27.780 --> 03:32:29.399
Luna.

03:32:29.459 --> 03:32:33.180
A pale yellow dragon limped forward, and

03:32:33.180 --> 03:32:34.979
the others stepped back respectfully to

03:32:34.979 --> 03:32:35.399
let her through.

03:32:35.459 --> 03:32:38.520
The ones Sore Tail and Blue were looking

03:32:38.520 --> 03:32:38.760
for?

03:32:38.819 --> 03:32:40.860
Tao?

03:32:40.920 --> 03:32:42.000
Cricket yelped.

03:32:42.059 --> 03:32:44.879
She bounded past Luna, and threw her

03:32:44.879 --> 03:32:46.739
wings around the startled yellow silk

03:32:46.739 --> 03:32:49.200
wing, the closest dragons in the crowd

03:32:49.200 --> 03:32:51.959
saw her hive wing scales, and jumped back

03:32:51.959 --> 03:32:52.559
hissing.

03:32:52.620 --> 03:32:54.780
Cricket?

03:32:54.840 --> 03:32:56.100
Tao cried.

03:32:56.159 --> 03:32:57.120
No way.

03:32:57.180 --> 03:32:58.559
How are you here?

03:32:58.620 --> 03:33:01.799
She turned to the other silk wings

03:33:01.799 --> 03:33:03.899
putting one wing protectively around

03:33:03.899 --> 03:33:04.379
cricket.

03:33:04.440 --> 03:33:07.799
This is the hive wing who found out the

03:33:07.799 --> 03:33:10.260
secret of the mind control, the one who

03:33:10.260 --> 03:33:11.940
told everyone the truth about the Book of

03:33:11.940 --> 03:33:12.540
Clearsight.

03:33:12.600 --> 03:33:15.360
Remember the paint on the posters in

03:33:15.360 --> 03:33:16.020
Jewel Hive?

03:33:16.079 --> 03:33:18.600
She's been fighting Queen Waspel longer

03:33:18.600 --> 03:33:19.200
than most of you.

03:33:19.260 --> 03:33:23.100
Luna felt a weird little stab of guilt

03:33:23.100 --> 03:33:25.739
that this silk wing was quicker to defend

03:33:25.739 --> 03:33:27.120
cricket than she had ever been.

03:33:27.180 --> 03:33:30.780
Then again, it was reassuring to see that

03:33:30.780 --> 03:33:32.819
Blue wasn't the only Silkwing who liked

03:33:32.819 --> 03:33:34.139
and trusted cricket.

03:33:34.200 --> 03:33:36.479
You've read the Book of Clearsight?

03:33:36.600 --> 03:33:38.819
One of the silk wings asked Cricket.

03:33:38.879 --> 03:33:42.120
Did you really see Queen Wasp stabbing

03:33:42.120 --> 03:33:43.139
eggs in the hatchery?

03:33:43.260 --> 03:33:44.280
asked another.

03:33:44.399 --> 03:33:47.159
She can't get inside your mind at all?

03:33:47.280 --> 03:33:51.360
All this excitement about us, Luna said

03:33:51.360 --> 03:33:52.260
ruefully to Cricket.

03:33:52.319 --> 03:33:55.379
And they haven't even seen the humans or

03:33:55.379 --> 03:33:56.700
the Pyria dragons yet.

03:33:56.760 --> 03:33:59.700
She looked down and saw that the

03:33:59.700 --> 03:34:02.399
dragonette at her feet had, in fact

03:34:02.399 --> 03:34:04.379
noticed sky and bullfrog.

03:34:04.379 --> 03:34:07.440
He had edged close enough to her that he

03:34:07.440 --> 03:34:10.020
was almost sitting on her talon, and he

03:34:10.020 --> 03:34:11.819
was now staring past her at the other 2

03:34:11.819 --> 03:34:14.159
dragons, who were hanging back in the

03:34:14.159 --> 03:34:15.059
shadows of the tunnel.

03:34:15.120 --> 03:34:18.659
What we really want to know is what's

03:34:18.659 --> 03:34:19.200
happening up there.

03:34:19.319 --> 03:34:22.680
Tao said, taking one of cricket's talons

03:34:22.680 --> 03:34:23.100
in her own.

03:34:23.219 --> 03:34:25.079
Is anyone else alive?

03:34:25.139 --> 03:34:27.120
What happened to the leaf wings?

03:34:27.180 --> 03:34:30.659
We have a lot to tell you, Cricket said.

03:34:30.719 --> 03:34:32.639
Is there someone in charge of everyone

03:34:32.639 --> 03:34:32.940
here?

03:34:33.000 --> 03:34:37.500
Depends on who you ask, Tao said, rolling

03:34:37.500 --> 03:34:37.860
her eyes.

03:34:37.920 --> 03:34:40.920
The leaf wings think they're in charge.

03:34:40.979 --> 03:34:43.739
Morpho keeps insisting he should make all

03:34:43.739 --> 03:34:44.219
the decisions.

03:34:44.280 --> 03:34:47.159
The bloodworm hive silk wings have their

03:34:47.159 --> 03:34:49.680
own chrysalis, which it turns out was way

03:34:49.680 --> 03:34:52.860
bigger than ours, and Lady Jewel and Lady

03:34:52.860 --> 03:34:54.000
Scarab are here too.

03:34:54.059 --> 03:34:57.059
But we don't have to listen to any hive

03:34:57.059 --> 03:34:57.659
wings anymore.

03:34:57.719 --> 03:35:00.840
A green gray dragon said mutinously.

03:35:00.899 --> 03:35:03.420
Now that they don't have their wide-eyed

03:35:03.420 --> 03:35:05.700
stinger clawed goons to push us around

03:35:05.700 --> 03:35:09.120
Lady Jewel is the reason we all escaped.

03:35:09.239 --> 03:35:11.040
Tao said stiffly.

03:35:11.100 --> 03:35:14.100
She's not our queen, but we don't have to

03:35:14.100 --> 03:35:14.879
be rotten to her.

03:35:15.000 --> 03:35:17.280
Chrysalis?

03:35:17.340 --> 03:35:18.600
Luna said hopefully.

03:35:18.659 --> 03:35:21.180
I was going to join the cicada hive

03:35:21.180 --> 03:35:22.799
chrysalis after my metamorphosis.

03:35:22.860 --> 03:35:24.000
Are any of them here?

03:35:24.120 --> 03:35:26.520
Tao shook her head.

03:35:26.579 --> 03:35:28.620
Sorry, little dragon.

03:35:28.680 --> 03:35:31.440
No one from Cicada Hive, as far as I

03:35:31.440 --> 03:35:31.620
know.

03:35:31.680 --> 03:35:35.579
Pokweed suddenly appeared, with 2 other

03:35:35.579 --> 03:35:37.920
leaf wings and a feather gray silk wing.

03:35:37.979 --> 03:35:40.200
Luna hadn't even realized he'd been

03:35:40.200 --> 03:35:40.860
gone.

03:35:40.920 --> 03:35:42.899
Oh, wow.

03:35:42.959 --> 03:35:45.659
Hello, said the smaller leaf wing.

03:35:45.719 --> 03:35:47.760
Visitors from the outside world.

03:35:47.819 --> 03:35:49.680
Please tell us you come with good news.

03:35:49.739 --> 03:35:51.120
I'm Bryany.

03:35:51.180 --> 03:35:53.399
This is Grayling, and this grumpy face is

03:35:53.399 --> 03:35:53.879
hemlock.

03:35:53.940 --> 03:35:56.100
Stern face.

03:35:56.219 --> 03:35:57.840
Hemlock corrected her.

03:35:57.899 --> 03:35:58.920
Not grumpy.

03:35:58.979 --> 03:36:01.139
This is an intimidating face.

03:36:01.200 --> 03:36:05.100
Pokweed says you know sundu, he said

03:36:05.100 --> 03:36:06.059
turning to Luna.

03:36:06.120 --> 03:36:07.440
Is she all right?

03:36:07.500 --> 03:36:09.120
She...

03:36:09.239 --> 03:36:10.920
Was when we left her.

03:36:10.979 --> 03:36:12.780
Luna said honestly.

03:36:12.840 --> 03:36:15.600
She was supposed to meet up with us a few

03:36:15.600 --> 03:36:17.219
days ago, but she didn't show.

03:36:17.280 --> 03:36:19.260
We left her a message.

03:36:19.319 --> 03:36:21.059
We were hoping she follows us here.

03:36:21.180 --> 03:36:24.059
We've been to the distant kingdoms

03:36:24.059 --> 03:36:25.079
Cricket said.

03:36:25.139 --> 03:36:28.440
We came back with dragons to help us, and

03:36:28.440 --> 03:36:31.139
underground monkeys who can talk, and a

03:36:31.139 --> 03:36:32.579
vision about an abyss that we have to

03:36:32.579 --> 03:36:32.819
find.

03:36:32.879 --> 03:36:36.360
Tao looked too astonished to speak.

03:36:36.420 --> 03:36:39.659
Bryony and Hemlock exchanged bewildered

03:36:39.659 --> 03:36:40.139
glances.

03:36:40.200 --> 03:36:44.700
Let's sit, Bryany said, waving to a

03:36:44.700 --> 03:36:46.139
circle of boulders nearby.

03:36:46.200 --> 03:36:47.819
We want to hear everything.

03:36:47.879 --> 03:36:51.239
Luna started to turn towards Sky and

03:36:51.239 --> 03:36:53.520
Bullfrog, but the little dragonette

03:36:53.520 --> 03:36:55.680
suddenly jumped forward and wrapped his

03:36:55.680 --> 03:36:57.180
tiny claws around her leg.

03:36:57.180 --> 03:36:59.639
He pressed his face into her scales and

03:36:59.639 --> 03:37:00.360
whispered something.

03:37:00.420 --> 03:37:03.540
Oh goodness, Luna said.

03:37:03.600 --> 03:37:07.020
Um, hey, cutie, can I have my leg back?

03:37:07.079 --> 03:37:10.860
Please let me stay with you, he mumbled.

03:37:10.920 --> 03:37:12.180
I'll be really good.

03:37:12.299 --> 03:37:13.440
I promise.

03:37:13.500 --> 03:37:16.139
I won't be any trouble, and I won't

03:37:16.139 --> 03:37:18.000
complain about anything, I promise

03:37:18.000 --> 03:37:18.360
promise.

03:37:18.420 --> 03:37:22.680
Luna felt a stab of sad, familiar

03:37:22.680 --> 03:37:23.159
sympathy.

03:37:23.219 --> 03:37:26.040
Won't someone be looking for you?

03:37:26.100 --> 03:37:28.799
she asked, touching the top of his head

03:37:28.799 --> 03:37:29.459
lightly.

03:37:29.520 --> 03:37:31.979
The dragonette shook his head.

03:37:31.979 --> 03:37:34.440
No, they are gone.

03:37:34.500 --> 03:37:39.000
Luna wondered if that meant dead, or

03:37:39.000 --> 03:37:41.399
captured by hive wings, or just out

03:37:41.399 --> 03:37:42.120
gathering food.

03:37:42.180 --> 03:37:45.120
It was hard to tell from the dragonette's

03:37:45.120 --> 03:37:45.540
quiet voice.

03:37:45.600 --> 03:37:48.719
She wondered if a dragonette with parents

03:37:48.719 --> 03:37:50.100
would have been forced onto a

03:37:50.100 --> 03:37:51.120
construction crew though.

03:37:51.180 --> 03:37:53.040
Poor little guy.

03:37:53.159 --> 03:37:58.379
It's only me, he said, in an even smaller

03:37:58.379 --> 03:37:59.100
voice.

03:37:59.159 --> 03:38:00.899
Just dusky.

03:38:00.959 --> 03:38:05.219
I can be really quiet, really, you won't

03:38:05.219 --> 03:38:05.940
even notice me.

03:38:06.000 --> 03:38:07.260
Please?

03:38:07.379 --> 03:38:10.680
He hesitated, then added softly.

03:38:10.799 --> 03:38:13.500
I don't want to be alone in the dark

03:38:13.500 --> 03:38:13.920
anymore.

03:38:13.979 --> 03:38:17.340
I'm afraid I'll get lost, and no one will

03:38:17.340 --> 03:38:18.360
ever find me.

03:38:18.420 --> 03:38:21.780
Luna thought about being a small dragon

03:38:21.840 --> 03:38:25.079
with no family, in a giant cave in the

03:38:25.079 --> 03:38:27.540
dark, because your home burned to ashes

03:38:27.540 --> 03:38:30.659
in the sky, hiding from monsters, who

03:38:30.659 --> 03:38:32.459
were suddenly even scarier than they had

03:38:32.459 --> 03:38:34.799
already been your whole life, because now

03:38:34.799 --> 03:38:36.600
you could be turned into one of them.

03:38:36.659 --> 03:38:39.899
She curved one of her wings around him.

03:38:39.959 --> 03:38:43.559
Of course you can stay with me, she said

03:38:43.559 --> 03:38:45.299
and it won't be dark.

03:38:45.360 --> 03:38:46.020
Don't worry.

03:38:46.079 --> 03:38:49.020
I can make lots and lots of flame silk.

03:38:49.079 --> 03:38:50.159
Here, look.

03:38:50.219 --> 03:38:52.920
I can make a kind that gives light, but

03:38:52.920 --> 03:38:53.399
won't burn you.

03:38:53.459 --> 03:38:55.139
Hold out your talons.

03:38:55.200 --> 03:38:59.940
Dusky warily held out one small talon, and

03:38:59.940 --> 03:39:01.739
she uncoiled a little thread of glowing

03:39:01.739 --> 03:39:02.700
silk into his palm.

03:39:02.819 --> 03:39:05.819
He brought it close to his eyes, took a

03:39:05.819 --> 03:39:08.040
deep breath, and then clutched it to his

03:39:08.040 --> 03:39:08.399
chest.

03:39:08.459 --> 03:39:11.340
Will it make the whisper stop?

03:39:11.399 --> 03:39:13.500
He asked softly.

03:39:13.559 --> 03:39:15.719
The whispers?

03:39:15.780 --> 03:39:16.920
Luna echoed.

03:39:16.979 --> 03:39:18.659
In the dark.

03:39:18.780 --> 03:39:20.280
Dusky said.

03:39:20.340 --> 03:39:23.399
There are whispers all the time in the

03:39:23.399 --> 03:39:23.700
dark.

03:39:23.760 --> 03:39:27.420
Luna felt a chill run all through her

03:39:27.420 --> 03:39:29.879
scales, like trickles of icy water.

03:39:29.940 --> 03:39:31.500
What?

03:39:31.620 --> 03:39:33.780
What do the whispers say?

03:39:33.840 --> 03:39:35.040
She asked.

03:39:35.100 --> 03:39:37.739
Although she wasn't sure she wanted to

03:39:37.739 --> 03:39:37.920
know.

03:39:37.979 --> 03:39:41.159
Dusky tipped his head up to look at her

03:39:41.159 --> 03:39:43.139
with large, dark eyes.

03:39:43.200 --> 03:39:47.399
His voice, when he finally spoke, was so

03:39:47.399 --> 03:39:49.739
faint that it seemed to come from the

03:39:49.739 --> 03:39:51.600
clustered shadows outside her light.

03:39:51.719 --> 03:39:57.239
They say, You're mine now, little

03:39:57.239 --> 03:39:58.139
dragon.

03:39:58.200 --> 03:40:02.100
Chapter 10.

03:40:02.340 --> 03:40:05.520
Luna slept poorly that night.

03:40:05.579 --> 03:40:08.700
In fact, she wasn't sure she slept

03:40:08.700 --> 03:40:09.540
properly at all.

03:40:09.600 --> 03:40:12.180
And in the morning, she didn't know if

03:40:12.180 --> 03:40:13.739
she'd really heard whispers all night

03:40:13.739 --> 03:40:15.540
long, or if she'd dreamed them.

03:40:15.600 --> 03:40:19.139
It probably didn't help to have a twitchy

03:40:19.139 --> 03:40:20.700
little dragonette curled up against her

03:40:20.700 --> 03:40:21.239
side.

03:40:21.299 --> 03:40:23.340
But she couldn't bring herself to send

03:40:23.340 --> 03:40:24.239
Dusky away.

03:40:24.299 --> 03:40:27.540
He'd looped the flame silk she gave him

03:40:27.540 --> 03:40:30.420
around his wrist, like a talisman, and he

03:40:30.420 --> 03:40:32.579
stayed so close to her, that she'd

03:40:32.579 --> 03:40:35.040
tripped over him 3 times on her way to

03:40:35.040 --> 03:40:36.899
the lake and back to her sleeping spot.

03:40:36.959 --> 03:40:39.059
He didn't say very much.

03:40:39.180 --> 03:40:41.579
But he did jerk awake several times

03:40:41.579 --> 03:40:44.280
during the night, startling her out of

03:40:44.280 --> 03:40:46.139
any almost sleep she might have been in.

03:40:46.200 --> 03:40:49.799
She had hoped that making so many coils

03:40:49.799 --> 03:40:51.899
of flame silk would have tired her out

03:40:51.899 --> 03:40:52.979
enough to sleep through anything.

03:40:53.040 --> 03:40:56.219
They'd spent hours sitting with Briony

03:40:56.219 --> 03:40:59.579
hemlock, Tao, Grayling, and Lady Jewel

03:40:59.579 --> 03:41:01.139
explaining everything that had happened

03:41:01.139 --> 03:41:03.299
in the poison jungle, and the distant

03:41:03.299 --> 03:41:03.780
kingdoms.

03:41:03.840 --> 03:41:06.239
The humans had fallen asleep before the

03:41:06.239 --> 03:41:07.139
end of the story.

03:41:07.200 --> 03:41:09.479
Both of them tucked protectively under

03:41:09.479 --> 03:41:10.319
Sky's wing.

03:41:10.379 --> 03:41:13.799
And that whole time, Luna had burned off

03:41:13.799 --> 03:41:16.139
wrist cuffs and made flame silk for the

03:41:16.139 --> 03:41:18.360
hidden silk wings, while Dusky sat on her

03:41:18.360 --> 03:41:18.780
tail.

03:41:18.840 --> 03:41:22.319
She'd decided to name the 5 kinds she

03:41:22.319 --> 03:41:24.360
could make and give the dragons options.

03:41:24.479 --> 03:41:27.840
The simplest ones she called gold silk

03:41:27.840 --> 03:41:30.540
which was much like the silvery silk most

03:41:30.540 --> 03:41:32.639
of her tribe could make, except that hers

03:41:32.639 --> 03:41:34.200
shimmered with a golden color.

03:41:34.260 --> 03:41:37.200
But it didn't glow or burn, and it could

03:41:37.200 --> 03:41:38.520
be used in normal tapestries.

03:41:38.579 --> 03:41:40.799
It wouldn't be much use to these dragons

03:41:40.799 --> 03:41:42.540
except for adding another color to

03:41:42.540 --> 03:41:43.500
anything they were weaving.

03:41:43.559 --> 03:41:48.120
The next kind she called firefly silk, it

03:41:48.120 --> 03:41:50.040
gave off a little bit of light, like

03:41:50.040 --> 03:41:52.440
holding a firefly in your talons, but it

03:41:52.440 --> 03:41:53.100
didn't burn.

03:41:53.340 --> 03:41:56.459
Then there was glow silk, the kind she'd

03:41:56.459 --> 03:41:57.420
given to Dusky.

03:41:57.479 --> 03:42:00.000
It felt a little warm, and it glowed

03:42:00.000 --> 03:42:02.819
brighter, closer to a normal fire, but

03:42:02.819 --> 03:42:03.600
anyone could hold it.

03:42:03.719 --> 03:42:07.079
When she demonstrated that kind, all the

03:42:07.079 --> 03:42:08.819
watching silk wings asked for some.

03:42:08.879 --> 03:42:11.520
They delightedly wound it around their

03:42:11.520 --> 03:42:12.420
own horns.

03:42:12.479 --> 03:42:14.280
A few wove it into necklaces or

03:42:14.280 --> 03:42:14.819
bracelets.

03:42:14.879 --> 03:42:18.360
As Luna was helping one little dragonette

03:42:18.360 --> 03:42:20.819
tie it around her ankle, she realized

03:42:20.819 --> 03:42:22.559
that Lady Jewel was hovering right over

03:42:22.559 --> 03:42:24.360
her shoulder, peering at it.

03:42:24.420 --> 03:42:27.540
I've never seen flame silk like that.

03:42:27.600 --> 03:42:28.979
The hive wing said.

03:42:29.100 --> 03:42:30.959
She held out one talon.

03:42:30.959 --> 03:42:32.040
May I?

03:42:32.100 --> 03:42:34.979
Luna felt a little flare of anger.

03:42:35.100 --> 03:42:37.500
This was one of Wasp's relatives.

03:42:37.559 --> 03:42:40.440
Jewel had happily ruled her hive with

03:42:40.440 --> 03:42:42.719
Wasps' power behind her, keeping

03:42:42.719 --> 03:42:45.000
Silkwings as servants, and enforcing

03:42:45.000 --> 03:42:46.440
Wasps' terrible rules.

03:42:46.440 --> 03:42:49.020
She'd never tried to make anything better

03:42:49.020 --> 03:42:50.159
for Silkwings before.

03:42:50.219 --> 03:42:53.280
And the only reason she was here now was

03:42:53.280 --> 03:42:55.260
because she knew WASP might try to mind

03:42:55.260 --> 03:42:56.459
control her if she were caught.

03:42:56.520 --> 03:43:00.180
Maybe Joel saw some of that in Luna's

03:43:00.180 --> 03:43:02.819
face, because she added more humbly.

03:43:02.879 --> 03:43:04.260
Please.

03:43:04.379 --> 03:43:08.459
Dal says she helped all her silk wings

03:43:08.459 --> 03:43:11.459
escape, Luna thought, and that she's not

03:43:11.459 --> 03:43:14.100
as bad as other hive wings, and that

03:43:14.100 --> 03:43:15.719
Queen Wasp took her children too.

03:43:15.780 --> 03:43:17.940
Tal trusts her.

03:43:18.000 --> 03:43:19.620
That doesn't mean I have to.

03:43:19.680 --> 03:43:21.899
But she doesn't have to be my enemy

03:43:21.899 --> 03:43:22.200
either.

03:43:22.260 --> 03:43:26.040
Luna gave her a small curl of the glow

03:43:26.040 --> 03:43:26.399
silk.

03:43:26.459 --> 03:43:28.200
Thank you.

03:43:28.260 --> 03:43:30.540
Jules said, peering at it.

03:43:30.600 --> 03:43:32.639
This is extraordinary.

03:43:32.700 --> 03:43:35.819
I thought there were only 2 kinds, one

03:43:35.819 --> 03:43:38.159
that neither glows nor burns, and one

03:43:38.159 --> 03:43:39.420
that burns like regular fire.

03:43:39.479 --> 03:43:42.719
But this kind would be so much safer for

03:43:42.719 --> 03:43:43.440
the lanterns.

03:43:43.500 --> 03:43:46.020
Can all flame silks make this?

03:43:46.079 --> 03:43:48.000
I don't know.

03:43:48.059 --> 03:43:49.200
Luna said.

03:43:49.260 --> 03:43:51.719
Your cousin keeps them all imprisoned in

03:43:51.719 --> 03:43:53.520
a cavern, where they spend their lives

03:43:53.520 --> 03:43:55.920
slaving to make her as much flame silk as

03:43:55.920 --> 03:43:57.780
they can, so I haven't had much

03:43:57.780 --> 03:43:59.340
opportunity to get to know any others.

03:43:59.399 --> 03:44:02.760
Jewel ducked her head, looking

03:44:02.760 --> 03:44:03.899
chastened.

03:44:03.959 --> 03:44:05.940
Right, she said.

03:44:06.000 --> 03:44:07.079
Of course.

03:44:07.139 --> 03:44:07.920
Sorry.

03:44:07.979 --> 03:44:10.920
But you can make the kind that burns

03:44:10.920 --> 03:44:11.219
too.

03:44:11.280 --> 03:44:12.659
Hemlock asked.

03:44:12.719 --> 03:44:16.319
I can make 2 burning kinds, Luna said.

03:44:16.379 --> 03:44:19.260
I call this one Blaze silk.

03:44:19.319 --> 03:44:20.760
I think it's what you'll find in most

03:44:20.760 --> 03:44:21.420
lanterns.

03:44:21.479 --> 03:44:25.200
She made a little curl of the thread that

03:44:25.200 --> 03:44:27.899
burned and glowed like a normal fire, and

03:44:27.899 --> 03:44:29.639
held it up over Dusky's head when he

03:44:29.639 --> 03:44:30.299
reached for it.

03:44:30.299 --> 03:44:32.940
No, little one, this will hurt you.

03:44:33.059 --> 03:44:37.200
Hemlock held out a stone jar, and Luna

03:44:37.200 --> 03:44:39.000
carefully slid the blaze silk into it.

03:44:39.059 --> 03:44:44.280
And this is the last kind, she said, which

03:44:44.280 --> 03:44:45.479
I wouldn't use very often.

03:44:45.479 --> 03:44:48.600
The thread that came from her wrist was

03:44:48.600 --> 03:44:51.180
so bright that everyone near her shielded

03:44:51.180 --> 03:44:51.540
their eyes.

03:44:51.659 --> 03:44:54.000
It looked like a bolt of lightning

03:44:54.000 --> 03:44:55.020
sizzling in her palm.

03:44:55.079 --> 03:44:58.559
I call it sun silk, she said.

03:44:58.620 --> 03:45:01.139
I can only make a little bit at a time.

03:45:01.200 --> 03:45:04.379
She shook her head as Hemlock produced

03:45:04.379 --> 03:45:05.459
another stone jar.

03:45:05.520 --> 03:45:07.559
It can burn through that too.

03:45:07.620 --> 03:45:09.239
I have to drown it.

03:45:09.299 --> 03:45:11.940
The dragons all moved aside.

03:45:12.000 --> 03:45:13.319
Even dusky.

03:45:13.379 --> 03:45:15.479
As she placed the silk lightly on a

03:45:15.479 --> 03:45:17.399
corner of her wing, and carried it down

03:45:17.399 --> 03:45:20.040
to the lake, where she held it under the

03:45:20.040 --> 03:45:21.299
water until the fire went out.

03:45:21.360 --> 03:45:25.200
Blaze silk is more useful, if you're

03:45:25.200 --> 03:45:27.360
trying to start a normal fire, she said

03:45:27.360 --> 03:45:29.280
returning to the circle of boulders.

03:45:29.340 --> 03:45:32.280
Do you want some of that or just glow

03:45:32.280 --> 03:45:32.639
silk?

03:45:32.700 --> 03:45:34.680
Both, please.

03:45:34.739 --> 03:45:36.420
Bryani answered.

03:45:36.479 --> 03:45:38.280
If we can start a fire and keep feeding

03:45:38.280 --> 03:45:40.559
it, it'll last beyond when the flame silk

03:45:40.559 --> 03:45:40.860
fades.

03:45:40.920 --> 03:45:43.739
Should have thought of that when we had

03:45:43.739 --> 03:45:44.819
Flame Soak before.

03:45:44.940 --> 03:45:46.739
Pokween muttered.

03:45:46.799 --> 03:45:49.200
We didn't think we'd be down here that

03:45:49.200 --> 03:45:49.799
long then.

03:45:49.920 --> 03:45:53.219
Bryany reminded him, which made all the

03:45:53.219 --> 03:45:55.260
faces of the dragons around them go very

03:45:55.260 --> 03:45:55.799
gloomy.

03:45:55.860 --> 03:45:59.399
The silk wings here were from Bloodworm

03:45:59.399 --> 03:46:02.280
Hive, Jewel Hive, and Mantis Hive.

03:46:02.340 --> 03:46:05.040
They knew Cinnabar had gone to warn the

03:46:05.040 --> 03:46:07.379
silk wings and other hives, but none of

03:46:07.379 --> 03:46:08.579
them had shown up in the caves.

03:46:08.639 --> 03:46:10.680
Nobody knew what that meant.

03:46:10.739 --> 03:46:13.200
Were they safely in hiding somewhere

03:46:13.200 --> 03:46:13.559
else?

03:46:13.559 --> 03:46:16.260
Or were they all captured by Queen Wasp?

03:46:16.319 --> 03:46:19.559
They'd seen silk wings flying in

03:46:19.559 --> 03:46:21.180
formation with hive wings on a few

03:46:21.180 --> 03:46:23.639
foraging expeditions, so they knew at

03:46:23.639 --> 03:46:24.959
least some of them had been captured.

03:46:25.020 --> 03:46:27.540
They hadn't known about the breath of

03:46:27.540 --> 03:46:29.819
evil plant, or the other mind, though.

03:46:29.879 --> 03:46:32.340
Luna could tell that several of them

03:46:32.340 --> 03:46:34.379
didn't really believe that there was

03:46:34.379 --> 03:46:36.180
another controlling malevolence out

03:46:36.180 --> 03:46:36.360
there.

03:46:36.420 --> 03:46:38.819
They thought it was still Queen Wasp.

03:46:38.940 --> 03:46:41.459
Despite cricket's strange story about the

03:46:41.459 --> 03:46:43.440
possessed leaf wing in the eye of the

03:46:43.440 --> 03:46:44.159
poison jungle.

03:46:44.219 --> 03:46:47.520
Everyone was fascinated by Moon's

03:46:47.520 --> 03:46:48.180
prophecy though.

03:46:48.239 --> 03:46:50.879
Luna saw a shiver of hope go through

03:46:50.879 --> 03:46:51.120
them.

03:46:51.180 --> 03:46:53.940
All these starving, homeless dragons

03:46:53.940 --> 03:46:56.399
suddenly sitting taller, and touching

03:46:56.399 --> 03:46:58.139
their glow silk or brushing their

03:46:58.139 --> 03:46:58.799
neighbor's wing.

03:46:58.860 --> 03:47:01.739
They'd lost their faith in the book of

03:47:01.739 --> 03:47:04.139
Clearsight, but not their belief in the

03:47:04.139 --> 03:47:05.040
magic of prophecies.

03:47:05.159 --> 03:47:09.360
I don't know about any abyss, Tao said

03:47:09.360 --> 03:47:12.540
but there is a colony of, what's the word

03:47:12.540 --> 03:47:12.959
you said?

03:47:13.079 --> 03:47:16.260
Humans, living not too far from here?

03:47:16.379 --> 03:47:18.719
I know a cave where they go to gather

03:47:18.719 --> 03:47:19.079
water.

03:47:19.139 --> 03:47:21.540
You do?

03:47:21.659 --> 03:47:23.579
Pokweed huffed.

03:47:23.639 --> 03:47:25.139
You never told me about it.

03:47:25.200 --> 03:47:29.940
Well, I was afraid you might eat them, Tao

03:47:29.940 --> 03:47:31.440
said, in a reasonable voice.

03:47:31.559 --> 03:47:34.379
Yes, exactly.

03:47:34.440 --> 03:47:36.299
Pokweed snapped.

03:47:36.360 --> 03:47:37.920
That was the whole point.

03:47:37.979 --> 03:47:41.459
And if you had, you'd be feeling very

03:47:41.459 --> 03:47:43.860
horrified right now, Tao pointed out.

03:47:43.979 --> 03:47:45.059
I would hope.

03:47:45.120 --> 03:47:50.040
Pokweed subsided, muttering, Wouldn't be

03:47:50.040 --> 03:47:51.059
quite so hungry, though.

03:47:51.120 --> 03:47:54.659
Several of the silk wings gave him a

03:47:54.659 --> 03:47:55.260
disgusted look.

03:47:55.319 --> 03:47:58.620
Wren and Axolotl were lucky that the 1st

03:47:58.620 --> 03:48:00.959
giant crowd of dragons they'd met were

03:48:00.959 --> 03:48:03.059
mostly from Pentala's vegetarian tribe.

03:48:03.120 --> 03:48:05.819
None of the silk wings had had any

03:48:05.819 --> 03:48:07.620
trouble accepting that humans were clever

03:48:07.620 --> 03:48:09.899
could communicate, and shouldn't be

03:48:09.899 --> 03:48:10.139
eaten.

03:48:10.200 --> 03:48:13.260
Of course, that was how they felt about

03:48:13.260 --> 03:48:15.959
zebras, wildebeests, lobsters, and

03:48:15.959 --> 03:48:16.739
meerkats too.

03:48:16.799 --> 03:48:19.500
As Guy pointed out to Wren with immense

03:48:19.500 --> 03:48:19.920
glee.

03:48:19.979 --> 03:48:23.399
Lady Jewel, on the other hand, had looked

03:48:23.399 --> 03:48:25.319
decidedly green around the gills when

03:48:25.319 --> 03:48:26.280
they introduced the humans.

03:48:26.340 --> 03:48:30.180
She kept staring at Wren and Axolotl, like

03:48:30.180 --> 03:48:31.620
she hoped they would suddenly throw off

03:48:31.620 --> 03:48:33.719
their mammal skins and turn out to be

03:48:33.719 --> 03:48:35.100
dragons in disguise after all.

03:48:35.159 --> 03:48:38.040
Can you take us there?

03:48:38.100 --> 03:48:39.420
To the human colony?

03:48:39.479 --> 03:48:41.399
Cricket asked Tal.

03:48:41.520 --> 03:48:42.899
Tao nodded.

03:48:42.959 --> 03:48:46.200
Tomorrow, she said, after you sleep.

03:48:46.260 --> 03:48:48.959
Are we near Lake Scorpion?

03:48:49.020 --> 03:48:49.979
Luna asked.

03:48:50.100 --> 03:48:52.559
Could you send some dragons to watch the

03:48:52.559 --> 03:48:52.979
sky there?

03:48:53.100 --> 03:48:55.260
In case sundew and links and the others

03:48:55.260 --> 03:48:56.040
come looking for us?

03:48:56.159 --> 03:48:57.540
Yes.

03:48:57.600 --> 03:48:59.579
Hemlock said immediately.

03:48:59.639 --> 03:49:00.959
I'll go myself.

03:49:01.020 --> 03:49:01.860
It's not far.

03:49:01.920 --> 03:49:05.040
We'll send some of the bloodworm hive

03:49:05.040 --> 03:49:07.079
chrysalis with you, Grayling said.

03:49:07.139 --> 03:49:08.280
It's a huge lake.

03:49:08.340 --> 03:49:10.559
You want dragons stationed all around it

03:49:10.559 --> 03:49:11.520
so you don't miss them.

03:49:11.579 --> 03:49:15.360
Hemlock flicked a glance at Bryony, her

03:49:15.360 --> 03:49:17.639
green tail crisscrossed with graylings

03:49:17.639 --> 03:49:18.479
and nodded.

03:49:18.540 --> 03:49:21.959
Luna's flame silk filled the caves with

03:49:21.959 --> 03:49:24.540
light and warmth, and a fire crackled in

03:49:24.540 --> 03:49:26.219
the center of the circle of boulders.

03:49:26.459 --> 03:49:28.139
It was noisier too.

03:49:28.200 --> 03:49:30.719
The light seemed to bring the dragons

03:49:30.719 --> 03:49:33.000
back to life, and the caves were full of

03:49:33.000 --> 03:49:34.139
voices.

03:49:34.200 --> 03:49:36.239
But were they all dragon voices?

03:49:36.299 --> 03:49:39.000
Was Luna just imagining it?

03:49:39.059 --> 03:49:41.639
Or could she hear the whisper that Dusky

03:49:41.639 --> 03:49:43.680
heard, threading underneath them all?

03:49:43.799 --> 03:49:46.620
Come to me, little dragon.

03:49:46.680 --> 03:49:48.299
You're mine.

03:49:48.360 --> 03:49:50.100
Find me.

03:49:50.159 --> 03:49:53.040
Around sunrise.

03:49:53.100 --> 03:49:56.159
Luna groggily opened her eyes and found a

03:49:56.159 --> 03:49:58.319
pale brown and gold silk wing crouched

03:49:58.319 --> 03:50:00.120
beside her, looking at dusky.

03:50:00.180 --> 03:50:03.059
The dragonette was finally truly asleep

03:50:03.059 --> 03:50:05.819
flopped out in the curve of Luna's side

03:50:05.819 --> 03:50:08.459
with his flame silk bracelet still curled

03:50:08.459 --> 03:50:09.180
close to his chest.

03:50:09.239 --> 03:50:11.280
Sorry.

03:50:11.340 --> 03:50:14.340
The brown silk wing whispered, when he

03:50:14.340 --> 03:50:15.299
saw Luna's eyes.

03:50:15.360 --> 03:50:17.219
I didn't mean to wake you.

03:50:17.280 --> 03:50:19.020
I'm Whitespeck.

03:50:19.079 --> 03:50:21.239
I just wanted to check on Dusky.

03:50:21.299 --> 03:50:23.399
Are you his family?

03:50:23.459 --> 03:50:24.719
Luna asked.

03:50:24.780 --> 03:50:27.959
He shook his head, his wings drooping.

03:50:28.079 --> 03:50:31.260
They're all dead, or missing.

03:50:31.319 --> 03:50:33.840
He said, even more softly.

03:50:33.959 --> 03:50:38.760
He hesitated, then said, Dusky's mother

03:50:38.760 --> 03:50:41.159
was shipped off to Vinegaroon Hive before

03:50:41.159 --> 03:50:42.600
Dusky even came out of his egg.

03:50:42.659 --> 03:50:46.319
And then Dusky's father died, in a tree

03:50:46.319 --> 03:50:48.479
stuffed construction accident a year ago

03:50:48.479 --> 03:50:49.860
when Dusky was one.

03:50:49.920 --> 03:50:53.579
Oh no, Luna breathed.

03:50:53.639 --> 03:50:57.120
But his wrist cuff said, White Speck

03:50:57.120 --> 03:50:57.540
sighed.

03:50:57.600 --> 03:51:00.840
Bloodworm hive's rules were very strict.

03:51:00.899 --> 03:51:03.659
One member of each household must be

03:51:03.659 --> 03:51:06.719
employed on Lady Bloodworm's pet projects

03:51:06.719 --> 03:51:09.780
even, if that household consists of only

03:51:09.780 --> 03:51:10.920
one small orphan.

03:51:10.979 --> 03:51:13.620
The day after his father died.

03:51:13.739 --> 03:51:15.959
They came and dragged him off to work on

03:51:15.959 --> 03:51:17.100
the same construction side.

03:51:17.159 --> 03:51:19.799
He has to split his time between there

03:51:19.799 --> 03:51:20.280
and school.

03:51:20.340 --> 03:51:24.239
That's awful, Luna whispered.

03:51:24.360 --> 03:51:27.840
It's why I joined the chrysalis, he

03:51:27.840 --> 03:51:28.139
said.

03:51:28.200 --> 03:51:30.299
Dusky's father was my friend.

03:51:30.360 --> 03:51:33.540
So, I've been trying to watch out for

03:51:33.540 --> 03:51:34.379
Dusky ever since.

03:51:34.440 --> 03:51:37.979
But I don't have a partner or anyone else

03:51:37.979 --> 03:51:38.280
to help.

03:51:38.399 --> 03:51:41.879
I was sent to Bloodworm Hive from Tetsi

03:51:41.879 --> 03:51:45.360
Hive, and left my whole family behind, and

03:51:45.360 --> 03:51:46.319
they won't let me adopt him.

03:51:46.379 --> 03:51:49.680
So, I can't do as much as I would like

03:51:49.680 --> 03:51:49.979
to.

03:51:50.040 --> 03:51:54.059
He paused. took a deep breath and added

03:51:54.059 --> 03:51:56.879
Sorry, too much information.

03:51:56.940 --> 03:52:01.379
No, I'm glad you told me, Luna said.

03:52:01.440 --> 03:52:03.120
I was wondering about him.

03:52:03.239 --> 03:52:05.459
But I didn't want to make him talk about

03:52:05.459 --> 03:52:06.540
it if he didn't want to.

03:52:06.600 --> 03:52:09.239
I'll get you both something to eat.

03:52:09.299 --> 03:52:11.940
White spec said, standing up.

03:52:12.000 --> 03:52:14.879
I'm all right, Luna said.

03:52:14.940 --> 03:52:17.399
She knew there wasn't much to go around

03:52:17.399 --> 03:52:19.799
and these dragons had been hungry a lot

03:52:19.799 --> 03:52:20.639
longer than she had.

03:52:20.700 --> 03:52:24.299
But if there's anything for Dusky, that

03:52:24.299 --> 03:52:24.719
would be great.

03:52:24.780 --> 03:52:26.040
Thank you.

03:52:26.159 --> 03:52:29.399
As they prepared to follow Tao to the

03:52:29.399 --> 03:52:30.059
human colony.

03:52:30.120 --> 03:52:32.579
Luna tried to talk Dusky into staying

03:52:32.579 --> 03:52:35.100
behind, but he clung to her and wouldn't

03:52:35.100 --> 03:52:35.340
let go.

03:52:35.399 --> 03:52:37.739
I think it's all right.

03:52:37.860 --> 03:52:40.680
Ren said, patting the little dragon on

03:52:40.680 --> 03:52:40.920
the head.

03:52:40.979 --> 03:52:44.579
He shied away from her hand, and buried

03:52:44.579 --> 03:52:46.319
his face in Luna's scales.

03:52:46.379 --> 03:52:48.420
The dragonette seemed to have no problem

03:52:48.420 --> 03:52:50.579
with any of the strange looking newcomers

03:52:50.579 --> 03:52:52.860
or cricket, but he was absolutely

03:52:52.860 --> 03:52:54.299
terrified of the humans.

03:52:54.360 --> 03:52:57.420
We are just going to look at the cave and

03:52:57.420 --> 03:52:58.500
see if we can find any people.

03:52:58.559 --> 03:53:00.059
No abyss today.

03:53:00.120 --> 03:53:02.100
He can come along for this fact finding

03:53:02.100 --> 03:53:02.280
part.

03:53:02.340 --> 03:53:04.200
Please.

03:53:04.319 --> 03:53:06.000
Please let me come with you.

03:53:06.120 --> 03:53:07.680
Desky asked.

03:53:07.739 --> 03:53:10.079
He gave Luna giant, sad eyes.

03:53:10.139 --> 03:53:12.299
I won't be any trouble.

03:53:12.360 --> 03:53:13.319
I promise.

03:53:13.440 --> 03:53:15.540
All right.

03:53:15.600 --> 03:53:16.979
Luna relented.

03:53:17.040 --> 03:53:18.719
She lifted him onto her back.

03:53:18.780 --> 03:53:21.059
But be really careful, okay?

03:53:21.120 --> 03:53:25.260
I will be the best, quietest dragon

03:53:25.260 --> 03:53:25.739
ever.

03:53:25.799 --> 03:53:29.639
I promise, promise. he said, snuggling

03:53:29.639 --> 03:53:30.120
into her neck.

03:53:30.180 --> 03:53:33.360
They found axolotl surrounded by

03:53:33.360 --> 03:53:35.520
dragonettes, who were arguing over who

03:53:35.520 --> 03:53:37.020
would get to keep the clever human as a

03:53:37.020 --> 03:53:37.260
pet.

03:53:37.319 --> 03:53:41.159
I saw them first, said the pink one.

03:53:41.219 --> 03:53:43.620
And look, they like me best.

03:53:43.739 --> 03:53:46.559
Axolotl held out their hand for her to

03:53:46.559 --> 03:53:47.040
sniff.

03:53:47.159 --> 03:53:49.860
Instead, she seized their hand in her

03:53:49.860 --> 03:53:52.079
talons, and yanked them down so she could

03:53:52.079 --> 03:53:52.979
climb onto their shoulders.

03:53:53.040 --> 03:53:56.940
Not fair, bellowed the orange one.

03:53:57.000 --> 03:53:58.319
Dad!

03:53:58.379 --> 03:54:00.059
I want a pet human.

03:54:00.120 --> 03:54:02.639
Nobody ever lets me adopt weird looking

03:54:02.639 --> 03:54:03.600
cave mammals.

03:54:03.659 --> 03:54:07.079
Um, no eating?

03:54:07.139 --> 03:54:09.479
Axolotl said cautiously.

03:54:09.540 --> 03:54:11.940
They patted the tail of the little pink

03:54:11.940 --> 03:54:13.559
one where it draped across their

03:54:13.559 --> 03:54:14.459
collarbone.

03:54:14.520 --> 03:54:17.579
Eee, look how clever they are.

03:54:17.639 --> 03:54:20.280
The pink one cried, wrapping her arms

03:54:20.280 --> 03:54:23.280
around Axolotl's head, and squishy.

03:54:23.340 --> 03:54:25.500
I just want to love them and cuddle them

03:54:25.500 --> 03:54:26.700
and smush them.

03:54:26.760 --> 03:54:29.879
Oh, dear, Ren said.

03:54:29.940 --> 03:54:31.979
I didn't realize I'd have to teach

03:54:31.979 --> 03:54:34.620
Axolotl how to say, no smooshing as

03:54:34.620 --> 03:54:34.799
well.

03:54:34.860 --> 03:54:38.459
She waded into the pile of squabbling

03:54:38.459 --> 03:54:40.680
dragonettes, and firmly peeled them off

03:54:40.680 --> 03:54:43.799
axolotl, who looked disheveled, bewildered

03:54:43.799 --> 03:54:45.180
and a little enchanted.

03:54:45.239 --> 03:54:47.100
Not a pet.

03:54:47.159 --> 03:54:49.379
She scolded the little dragons.

03:54:49.440 --> 03:54:52.860
Humans can be friends, but not pets.

03:54:52.920 --> 03:54:54.239
Friend.

03:54:54.360 --> 03:54:57.659
Axolotl cried in dragon, latching onto

03:54:57.659 --> 03:54:59.159
one of the words they'd been practicing.

03:54:59.280 --> 03:55:02.040
They crouched and clasped one of the pink

03:55:02.040 --> 03:55:03.360
dragonette's talons.

03:55:03.420 --> 03:55:06.840
Friend, Axolotl said again, with a

03:55:06.840 --> 03:55:07.079
smile.

03:55:07.200 --> 03:55:10.200
The pink dragonette beamed.

03:55:10.260 --> 03:55:13.260
Desky, look, this human likes me best of

03:55:13.260 --> 03:55:13.559
anyone.

03:55:13.620 --> 03:55:17.159
Dusky shivered, and buried his nose in

03:55:17.159 --> 03:55:17.879
Luna's neck.

03:55:18.000 --> 03:55:21.659
Probably because I am not a brat, like

03:55:21.659 --> 03:55:22.860
some dragons.

03:55:22.920 --> 03:55:25.559
The pink dragonette stuck out her tongue

03:55:25.559 --> 03:55:26.219
at the orange one.

03:55:26.340 --> 03:55:28.979
Aww.

03:55:29.100 --> 03:55:31.200
The orange one grumbled to Ren.

03:55:31.260 --> 03:55:32.340
But why?

03:55:32.399 --> 03:55:35.040
We want a fluffy human to play with.

03:55:35.100 --> 03:55:37.739
That one said you were his pet.

03:55:37.860 --> 03:55:41.219
He pointed at Guy, who did an extremely

03:55:41.219 --> 03:55:43.079
terrible job of trying to look innocent.

03:55:43.139 --> 03:55:46.620
Sky, Rand stamped her foot.

03:55:46.680 --> 03:55:50.040
Don't make that mad face, he protested.

03:55:50.100 --> 03:55:51.659
They would have tried to keep you

03:55:51.659 --> 03:55:52.020
otherwise.

03:55:52.079 --> 03:55:54.780
I wanted them to know we go together, you

03:55:54.780 --> 03:55:55.079
and me.

03:55:55.139 --> 03:55:58.680
You could have said best friends, Ren

03:55:58.680 --> 03:56:01.559
suggested, or that I saved your life like

03:56:01.559 --> 03:56:04.500
multiple times, or that nobody gets to

03:56:04.500 --> 03:56:06.959
keep any humans, by all the moons.

03:56:07.020 --> 03:56:07.860
I mean, really.

03:56:07.920 --> 03:56:11.700
No, humans for you.

03:56:11.760 --> 03:56:14.700
Sky said sternly to the dragonettes.

03:56:14.760 --> 03:56:17.700
Ooh, but I bet you could find some really

03:56:17.700 --> 03:56:19.260
cute cave snails.

03:56:19.379 --> 03:56:22.979
He lowered his voice and whispered, They'd

03:56:22.979 --> 03:56:25.260
probably be better behaved than she is

03:56:25.260 --> 03:56:25.680
anyway.

03:56:25.739 --> 03:56:30.780
You are so lucky you're cute, Ren said

03:56:30.780 --> 03:56:31.620
shaking her head.

03:56:31.680 --> 03:56:35.100
She said something to Axolotl, then added

03:56:35.100 --> 03:56:36.420
in dragon to Luna.

03:56:36.479 --> 03:56:39.540
Dusky kind of reminds me of Baby Sky.

03:56:39.600 --> 03:56:42.120
Totally different scales, but the sweet

03:56:42.120 --> 03:56:44.520
face, and Skye had no family either.

03:56:44.579 --> 03:56:48.719
Except you, Skye said, poking her

03:56:48.719 --> 03:56:49.739
affectionately with his tail.

03:56:49.799 --> 03:56:54.120
Well, you lucked into me, Ren said with a

03:56:54.120 --> 03:56:54.420
grin.

03:56:54.479 --> 03:56:57.899
Tal led them out of the main cave, and

03:56:57.899 --> 03:57:00.059
for a while, they climbed and walked

03:57:00.059 --> 03:57:01.620
through the winding rock passages.

03:57:01.680 --> 03:57:05.280
At one point in a high ceilinged cave

03:57:05.280 --> 03:57:08.100
Luna wondered why they weren't flying, and

03:57:08.100 --> 03:57:09.840
then she remembered noticing that one of

03:57:09.840 --> 03:57:11.520
Tao's wings looked different from the

03:57:11.520 --> 03:57:11.760
others.

03:57:11.819 --> 03:57:15.120
She wanted to ask how Tao had made it all

03:57:15.120 --> 03:57:17.520
the way here from Jewel Hive, but she

03:57:17.520 --> 03:57:19.139
wasn't sure if that was too nosy.

03:57:19.200 --> 03:57:21.840
Tao seemed like someone who was good at

03:57:21.840 --> 03:57:24.479
both solving her own problems and asking

03:57:24.479 --> 03:57:25.680
for help when she needed it.

03:57:25.739 --> 03:57:28.559
They had to splash through a long river

03:57:28.559 --> 03:57:29.159
for a while.

03:57:29.280 --> 03:57:32.219
Pale, eyeless fish darted between their

03:57:32.219 --> 03:57:32.700
claws.

03:57:32.819 --> 03:57:35.280
Cricket and Briny tried to catch one but

03:57:35.280 --> 03:57:38.399
failed, and then Bullfrog tried, succeeded

03:57:38.399 --> 03:57:41.340
and snarfed it down with a very self

03:57:40.379 --> 03:57:41.940
satisfied expression.

03:57:42.000 --> 03:57:45.659
The frigid water came up to Luna's wings

03:57:45.659 --> 03:57:47.340
ribald around her stomach, and

03:57:47.340 --> 03:57:49.500
occasionally splashed up her nose.

03:57:49.559 --> 03:57:52.559
Eventually, the river narrowed, and

03:57:52.559 --> 03:57:54.719
curved through a thin gap between 2 walls

03:57:54.719 --> 03:57:55.139
of rock.

03:57:55.200 --> 03:58:00.000
They squeezed through one by one, Tao, Sky

03:58:00.000 --> 03:58:03.420
with the humans, Luna with Dusky, Bryony

03:58:03.420 --> 03:58:03.959
and Cricket.

03:58:04.020 --> 03:58:06.479
It took more wiggling and squishing to

03:58:06.479 --> 03:58:08.879
get bullfrog through, but eventually he

03:58:08.879 --> 03:58:10.500
flopped into the shallow water on the

03:58:10.500 --> 03:58:12.659
other side with an oof of

03:58:12.659 --> 03:58:13.379
disgruntlement.

03:58:13.440 --> 03:58:15.600
This is it.

03:58:15.659 --> 03:58:16.920
Tao said.

03:58:16.979 --> 03:58:19.440
She flipped her tail at the cave below

03:58:19.440 --> 03:58:19.680
them.

03:58:19.739 --> 03:58:22.680
The river swept past their talons and

03:58:22.680 --> 03:58:25.139
over an edge, water falling down about

03:58:25.139 --> 03:58:27.659
the height of 2 dragons, into a wide

03:58:27.659 --> 03:58:28.200
rippling pool.

03:58:28.319 --> 03:58:31.440
Luna could see more pale fish flickering

03:58:31.440 --> 03:58:33.540
in the dark water, but she didn't see any

03:58:33.540 --> 03:58:33.840
humans.

03:58:33.899 --> 03:58:37.379
Cricket splashed out of the water and

03:58:37.379 --> 03:58:39.540
crouched to the edge of the rock, peering

03:58:39.540 --> 03:58:39.780
down.

03:58:39.840 --> 03:58:42.479
You've seen humans here?

03:58:42.540 --> 03:58:44.280
She asked Tal.

03:58:44.340 --> 03:58:46.500
A couple of times.

03:58:46.559 --> 03:58:47.700
Tao answered.

03:58:47.760 --> 03:58:48.959
Can't you smell them?

03:58:49.020 --> 03:58:52.260
Luna sniffed, but it was hard to separate

03:58:52.260 --> 03:58:54.840
out any new furry smells from the sense

03:58:54.840 --> 03:58:56.940
of wren and axolotl right beside her.

03:58:57.059 --> 03:58:59.159
There's something else.

03:58:59.280 --> 03:59:02.639
Tao turned to Bryony, who offered one of

03:59:02.639 --> 03:59:04.680
her wings to support Tao's shorter wing

03:59:04.680 --> 03:59:06.840
as they glided down to the cave below.

03:59:06.899 --> 03:59:09.840
Luna and the others followed as Tal

03:59:09.840 --> 03:59:11.879
stepped around the shore, to the far side

03:59:11.879 --> 03:59:14.040
of the pool and reached into the water.

03:59:14.100 --> 03:59:16.680
She pulled out a small contraption.

03:59:16.739 --> 03:59:19.799
It took Luna a moment to realize it was a

03:59:19.799 --> 03:59:20.520
sort of cage.

03:59:20.639 --> 03:59:23.879
It was designed so fish would swim in, but

03:59:23.879 --> 03:59:25.920
couldn't swim back out, and it currently

03:59:25.920 --> 03:59:27.540
held 3 squirming fish.

03:59:27.600 --> 03:59:29.700
Whoa.

03:59:29.819 --> 03:59:31.260
Cricket breathed.

03:59:31.319 --> 03:59:34.079
She hurried over to study it, blinking

03:59:34.079 --> 03:59:34.979
behind her spectacles.

03:59:35.040 --> 03:59:37.860
This, humans made this?

03:59:37.920 --> 03:59:41.940
Ren can make things like that, Skye said

03:59:41.940 --> 03:59:43.620
sounding hilariously defensive.

03:59:43.680 --> 03:59:45.239
She can make anything.

03:59:45.299 --> 03:59:47.760
She catches fish with weird inventions

03:59:47.760 --> 03:59:48.540
all the time.

03:59:48.600 --> 03:59:52.139
There are several of these, Tao said.

03:59:52.200 --> 03:59:53.879
She lowered it back into the water.

03:59:54.000 --> 03:59:57.899
I believe the humans come from there, she

03:59:57.899 --> 04:00:00.299
added, pointing to a hole higher up the

04:00:00.299 --> 04:00:00.540
wall.

04:00:00.600 --> 04:00:03.899
Now that she was looking, Luna could see

04:00:03.899 --> 04:00:06.000
an odd sort of path, descending from the

04:00:06.000 --> 04:00:08.159
hole to the shore of the lake, made of

04:00:08.159 --> 04:00:09.959
stairs, chiseled into the stone.

04:00:10.020 --> 04:00:13.680
Maybe Axolotl and I should stay here for

04:00:13.680 --> 04:00:14.579
the rest of the day.

04:00:14.639 --> 04:00:17.879
Ren suggested, so we can meet anyone who

04:00:17.879 --> 04:00:18.659
comes to the lake?

04:00:18.780 --> 04:00:21.299
Without a bunch of giant drooling dragon

04:00:21.299 --> 04:00:23.340
faces looming around to scare them off.

04:00:23.399 --> 04:00:25.860
Sky snorted huffily.

04:00:25.920 --> 04:00:28.559
A small scuffing noise came from behind

04:00:28.559 --> 04:00:28.920
them.

04:00:28.979 --> 04:00:32.040
Luna whirled around, accidentally

04:00:32.040 --> 04:00:34.620
splashing dusky, and stared into the dark

04:00:34.620 --> 04:00:35.520
corners of the cave.

04:00:35.639 --> 04:00:39.059
The stalagmites cast along shadows and

04:00:39.059 --> 04:00:41.159
the light from her glow silk, and for a

04:00:41.159 --> 04:00:42.959
moment, she thought she saw movement.

04:00:43.079 --> 04:00:44.520
There.

04:00:44.579 --> 04:00:46.319
No, there.

04:00:46.379 --> 04:00:47.399
No?

04:00:47.520 --> 04:00:49.739
Maybe it was nothing.

04:00:49.799 --> 04:00:52.620
And then something glinted overhead

04:00:52.620 --> 04:00:53.760
catching the light.

04:00:53.819 --> 04:00:56.700
She lifted her gaze, and locked eyes with

04:00:56.700 --> 04:00:59.760
a gaunt, shaggy, eerie thing.

04:00:59.819 --> 04:01:03.899
It saw her see it, but it stayed

04:01:03.899 --> 04:01:06.059
perfectly still, without a flicker of

04:01:06.059 --> 04:01:08.639
movement or muscle tension, as though it

04:01:08.639 --> 04:01:09.719
was not afraid of her at all.

04:01:09.780 --> 04:01:13.020
It was shaped like a human, she thought

04:01:13.020 --> 04:01:15.360
but it held itself in a weird, spider

04:01:15.360 --> 04:01:17.940
like way, knees and elbows bent at

04:01:17.940 --> 04:01:19.139
painful, sharp angles.

04:01:19.200 --> 04:01:22.680
Its arms were as thin as her antennae, and

04:01:22.680 --> 04:01:25.079
when it crouched, as it did now, its

04:01:25.079 --> 04:01:26.879
matted hair and beard brushed the

04:01:26.879 --> 04:01:27.059
ground.

04:01:27.180 --> 04:01:30.959
Its skin was as pale as the eyeless fish

04:01:30.959 --> 04:01:33.479
but less natural, as though all the blood

04:01:33.479 --> 04:01:34.620
had been sucked out of it.

04:01:34.680 --> 04:01:36.360
And its eyes.

04:01:36.420 --> 04:01:39.120
They seemed to be covered in a green film

04:01:39.120 --> 04:01:41.700
like algae, but they also seemed to be

04:01:41.700 --> 04:01:43.799
staring straight into Luna's soul.

04:01:43.860 --> 04:01:47.219
She couldn't help crying out in alarm and

04:01:47.219 --> 04:01:49.559
jumping back, stumbling farther into the

04:01:49.559 --> 04:01:49.799
pool.

04:01:49.860 --> 04:01:53.639
The human still did not flinch, but a

04:01:53.639 --> 04:01:56.340
crack opened in its hairy face, then

04:01:56.340 --> 04:01:59.100
widened to reveal rotting teeth, and

04:01:59.100 --> 04:02:00.659
something like a cruel imitation of a

04:02:00.659 --> 04:02:00.840
smile.

04:02:00.959 --> 04:02:03.299
What is it?

04:02:03.420 --> 04:02:05.700
Briony asked, splashing over next to

04:02:05.700 --> 04:02:05.940
her.

04:02:06.000 --> 04:02:09.120
Luna pointed, and all the dragons turned

04:02:09.120 --> 04:02:10.920
to look up at the strange creature on the

04:02:10.920 --> 04:02:11.219
ledge.

04:02:11.280 --> 04:02:14.639
Wren held out her hands and said

04:02:14.639 --> 04:02:16.260
something calm and soothing and human.

04:02:16.379 --> 04:02:19.680
When there was no reaction, she added in

04:02:19.680 --> 04:02:22.379
dragon, Do you understand this language

04:02:22.379 --> 04:02:23.040
instead?

04:02:23.100 --> 04:02:24.360
They won't hurt you.

04:02:24.420 --> 04:02:28.020
The creature lunged to its feet suddenly

04:02:28.020 --> 04:02:30.659
hissed at them, and bolted away through a

04:02:30.659 --> 04:02:31.319
crack in the wall.

04:02:31.379 --> 04:02:35.639
Chapter 11.

04:02:36.000 --> 04:02:39.420
That was so creepy.

04:02:39.479 --> 04:02:42.659
Bryney said. looking down at Wren and

04:02:42.659 --> 04:02:43.860
Axolotl with a shiver.

04:02:43.920 --> 04:02:46.440
I didn't know humans could be that

04:02:46.440 --> 04:02:47.040
creepy.

04:02:47.100 --> 04:02:48.719
Was?

04:02:48.840 --> 04:02:49.559
that a human?

04:02:49.620 --> 04:02:50.760
Cricket asked.

04:02:50.819 --> 04:02:51.540
For sure?

04:02:51.600 --> 04:02:53.760
Not some other weird thing we haven't

04:02:53.760 --> 04:02:54.239
discovered yet?

04:02:54.299 --> 04:02:58.319
I think he was human, Ren said.

04:02:58.379 --> 04:03:00.659
But I have no idea what was wrong with

04:03:00.659 --> 04:03:00.780
him.

04:03:00.840 --> 04:03:04.559
She said something to Axolotl and they

04:03:04.559 --> 04:03:06.540
raised their hands, looking equally

04:03:06.540 --> 04:03:07.020
puzzled.

04:03:07.079 --> 04:03:10.500
Dusky had his face buried in Luna's neck

04:03:10.500 --> 04:03:11.700
again, trembling.

04:03:11.760 --> 04:03:14.459
She rubbed her wings together uneasily

04:03:14.459 --> 04:03:17.040
then reached up and tugged the dragonette

04:03:17.040 --> 04:03:19.920
into her arms, partly to comfort him, and

04:03:19.920 --> 04:03:20.940
partly to comfort herself.

04:03:21.000 --> 04:03:24.899
She'd expected tiny wrens and daffodils

04:03:24.899 --> 04:03:28.739
and axolotls and ocelots, calm, smart

04:03:28.739 --> 04:03:29.459
little creatures.

04:03:29.520 --> 04:03:32.100
She'd never pictured an unsettling

04:03:32.100 --> 04:03:33.479
dangerous looking version of them.

04:03:33.540 --> 04:03:37.799
She felt her hope shiver, like thin glass

04:03:37.799 --> 04:03:39.180
that could shatter at any moment.

04:03:39.239 --> 04:03:41.819
Don't fall into the fog, Luna.

04:03:41.940 --> 04:03:43.559
Don't let the worry win.

04:03:43.620 --> 04:03:46.620
Humans are scary.

04:03:46.680 --> 04:03:48.959
Dusky whispered in Luna's ear.

04:03:49.020 --> 04:03:51.479
His breath smelled like the wild carrots

04:03:51.479 --> 04:03:52.440
he'd eaten for breakfast.

04:03:52.500 --> 04:03:55.920
Not all of them, she whispered back.

04:03:55.979 --> 04:03:59.879
Ren and Axolotl are friendly, and kind of

04:03:59.879 --> 04:04:00.840
cute, aren't they?

04:04:00.959 --> 04:04:05.459
I have bad dreams about humans, he said.

04:04:05.579 --> 04:04:07.799
So quietly she could barely hear him.

04:04:07.860 --> 04:04:11.760
Wait till you get your wings, she said

04:04:11.760 --> 04:04:12.959
patting his head.

04:04:13.020 --> 04:04:15.000
You won't be scared of anything then.

04:04:15.120 --> 04:04:18.000
I've only had mine for a little while, and

04:04:18.000 --> 04:04:18.840
look how tough I am.

04:04:18.899 --> 04:04:22.799
It's all right to be scared too, Cricket

04:04:22.799 --> 04:04:23.819
said unexpectedly.

04:04:23.879 --> 04:04:26.579
Luna hadn't even realized she was close

04:04:26.579 --> 04:04:27.299
enough to hear them.

04:04:27.360 --> 04:04:30.239
Cricket offered one of her talons to

04:04:30.239 --> 04:04:32.700
Dusky, and he touched his nose to it

04:04:32.700 --> 04:04:33.780
blinking up at her.

04:04:33.840 --> 04:04:37.200
Everyone gets scared sometimes, she said

04:04:37.200 --> 04:04:39.059
or sad, or worried.

04:04:39.120 --> 04:04:41.520
That thing scared me too, Dusky.

04:04:41.579 --> 04:04:43.920
You can always talk to one of us about it

04:04:43.920 --> 04:04:44.819
whenever you feel that way.

04:04:44.879 --> 04:04:46.920
What would that be like?

04:04:46.979 --> 04:04:48.360
Luna wondered.

04:04:48.420 --> 04:04:50.819
Telling someone anytime I felt sad.

04:04:50.879 --> 04:04:53.520
Is that normal for other dragons?

04:04:53.639 --> 04:04:56.040
Should we follow him?

04:04:56.100 --> 04:04:58.799
Ren asked, starting toward the ledge.

04:04:58.860 --> 04:05:01.079
No way.

04:05:01.139 --> 04:05:03.420
Sky objected instantly.

04:05:03.479 --> 04:05:05.340
I'm not letting you near that thing.

04:05:05.459 --> 04:05:08.399
It looked like it would eat you in a

04:05:08.399 --> 04:05:08.819
heartbeat.

04:05:08.879 --> 04:05:11.940
He made what he seemed to think was a

04:05:11.940 --> 04:05:14.040
stern, determined expression and glared

04:05:14.040 --> 04:05:14.940
down at her.

04:05:15.000 --> 04:05:17.459
I'm also not leaving you here alone.

04:05:17.520 --> 04:05:19.979
That thing could come back and get you.

04:05:20.040 --> 04:05:22.260
And so I am staying here to guard you, no

04:05:22.260 --> 04:05:23.040
matter what you say.

04:05:23.100 --> 04:05:25.799
Ren put her hands on her hips.

04:05:25.860 --> 04:05:28.680
No one is going to approach me if they

04:05:28.680 --> 04:05:30.780
see you looming around pretending to be

04:05:30.780 --> 04:05:31.620
scary, Skye.

04:05:31.680 --> 04:05:34.260
Well, good, he said.

04:05:34.319 --> 04:05:35.399
I am scary.

04:05:35.520 --> 04:05:36.959
They should think about that.

04:05:37.079 --> 04:05:40.260
What if all the Abyss worshipers look

04:05:40.260 --> 04:05:40.559
like that?

04:05:40.620 --> 04:05:43.319
Briony asked, flicking her tail

04:05:43.319 --> 04:05:43.799
worriedly.

04:05:43.920 --> 04:05:46.739
Maybe the abyss makes them creepy.

04:05:46.799 --> 04:05:50.700
Sky lunged forward and cupped his front

04:05:50.700 --> 04:05:52.979
talons around Wren, just as she was about

04:05:52.979 --> 04:05:54.299
to climb the wall to the ledge.

04:05:54.360 --> 04:05:58.319
Ren, he said, with desperate

04:05:58.319 --> 04:05:58.799
seriousness.

04:05:58.920 --> 04:06:02.219
If the abyss can do that to humans, you

04:06:02.219 --> 04:06:03.000
can't go there.

04:06:03.059 --> 04:06:05.700
I won't let you turn into a scary hair

04:06:05.700 --> 04:06:06.180
monster.

04:06:06.239 --> 04:06:10.200
She put one hand on his nearest claw and

04:06:10.200 --> 04:06:11.399
looked up at him for a long moment.

04:06:11.459 --> 04:06:13.739
Like they were communicating entire

04:06:13.739 --> 04:06:15.000
libraries with their eyes.

04:06:15.059 --> 04:06:18.840
Finally, Ren said, You'd better not.

04:06:18.899 --> 04:06:20.520
I like my hair the way it is.

04:06:20.579 --> 04:06:23.040
We could turn around.

04:06:23.100 --> 04:06:25.680
Skye said, hopefully, and go home.

04:06:25.739 --> 04:06:28.440
You wanted to help, Skye?

04:06:28.559 --> 04:06:31.319
She reminded him with a gentle nudge.

04:06:31.379 --> 04:06:34.440
Listen, you protect me from becoming a

04:06:34.440 --> 04:06:36.659
scary hair monster, and I'll protect you

04:06:36.659 --> 04:06:38.700
from becoming a wide-eyed murder zombie.

04:06:38.760 --> 04:06:39.600
Deal?

04:06:39.659 --> 04:06:40.920
He sighed.

04:06:40.979 --> 04:06:42.479
All right.

04:06:42.540 --> 04:06:45.360
But if there are any reckless heroics

04:06:45.360 --> 04:06:47.159
involved, it's my turn to do them.

04:06:47.219 --> 04:06:50.760
As they talked, Cricket had flown up to

04:06:50.760 --> 04:06:52.260
the ledge where the hair creature had

04:06:52.260 --> 04:06:52.739
been hiding.

04:06:52.799 --> 04:06:55.680
She paced along it, touching the rock

04:06:55.680 --> 04:06:57.239
wall and studying the shadows.

04:06:57.299 --> 04:07:00.899
There is a gap here that some of us might

04:07:00.899 --> 04:07:01.500
fit through.

04:07:01.559 --> 04:07:03.059
She said thoughtfully.

04:07:03.120 --> 04:07:04.739
Let's think.

04:07:04.799 --> 04:07:06.299
Should we try?

04:07:06.360 --> 04:07:07.620
Just to look?

04:07:07.739 --> 04:07:11.340
What if it leads to the abyss?

04:07:11.399 --> 04:07:12.780
Bullfrog asked.

04:07:12.840 --> 04:07:14.520
Then what do we do?

04:07:14.579 --> 04:07:18.479
Turn around, Skye said promptly.

04:07:18.600 --> 04:07:21.180
Go back to the cavern with all those nice

04:07:21.180 --> 04:07:23.459
rainbow dragons and have another bonfire

04:07:23.459 --> 04:07:23.760
party.

04:07:23.879 --> 04:07:26.280
Let's spend the night telling each other

04:07:26.280 --> 04:07:28.319
whatever the opposite of ghost stories

04:07:28.319 --> 04:07:32.579
are, like, once there was a turtle, and

04:07:32.579 --> 04:07:34.500
then it met another even cuter turtle.

04:07:34.559 --> 04:07:37.500
And then they had the absolute most

04:07:37.500 --> 04:07:39.540
adorable turtle babies, and they lived

04:07:39.540 --> 04:07:42.479
forever in a sunny place, and no one ever

04:07:42.479 --> 04:07:44.280
thought about eating them even once their

04:07:44.280 --> 04:07:44.940
whole lives.

04:07:45.000 --> 04:07:45.840
The end.

04:07:45.899 --> 04:07:48.299
I'll fly into the abyss.

04:07:48.420 --> 04:07:49.739
Bryany said.

04:07:49.799 --> 04:07:51.360
I do it right now.

04:07:51.420 --> 04:07:54.000
I want to know what's down there that's

04:07:54.000 --> 04:07:54.899
where the whole prophecy.

04:07:54.959 --> 04:07:58.079
Cricket rubbed her forehead and scrunched

04:07:58.079 --> 04:07:58.620
up her eyes.

04:07:58.680 --> 04:08:01.079
We have to, don't we?

04:08:01.139 --> 04:08:01.920
she said.

04:08:01.979 --> 04:08:05.940
A secret buried far below may save those

04:08:05.940 --> 04:08:07.739
brave enough to look.

04:08:07.799 --> 04:08:09.000
It's right there in the prophecy.

04:08:09.059 --> 04:08:10.260
We have to go look.

04:08:10.319 --> 04:08:15.000
But, Sundew, Luna said.

04:08:15.059 --> 04:08:18.120
And tsunami, and moon, and lynx and

04:08:18.120 --> 04:08:19.260
pineapple.

04:08:19.319 --> 04:08:20.399
How can we go without them?

04:08:20.459 --> 04:08:24.659
Face a great evil with talons united.

04:08:24.719 --> 04:08:27.239
That's in the prophecy too, isn't it?

04:08:27.299 --> 04:08:30.000
If we only have half the tribes

04:08:30.000 --> 04:08:30.659
represented?

04:08:30.719 --> 04:08:32.100
Aren't we doing it all wrong?

04:08:32.159 --> 04:08:36.059
That's true, Skye said, hopefully.

04:08:36.120 --> 04:08:38.459
We could give them a couple more days to

04:08:38.459 --> 04:08:39.719
find us, couldn't we?

04:08:39.780 --> 04:08:42.899
More sitting and waiting.

04:08:42.959 --> 04:08:44.760
Bullfrog grunted.

04:08:44.819 --> 04:08:46.319
No thanks.

04:08:46.379 --> 04:08:49.260
What if we look?

04:08:49.319 --> 04:08:52.440
Cricket suggested, but we don't face

04:08:52.440 --> 04:08:53.819
anything yet.

04:08:53.879 --> 04:08:56.100
We scouted out carefully first.

04:08:56.159 --> 04:08:59.579
I'll just go through this gab and pick

04:08:59.579 --> 04:09:00.780
around and come right back.

04:09:00.840 --> 04:09:02.879
I'll come with you.

04:09:03.000 --> 04:09:05.819
Luna heard herself say. to her own

04:09:05.819 --> 04:09:06.239
surprise.

04:09:06.299 --> 04:09:08.700
No, no, no.

04:09:08.760 --> 04:09:10.260
Dusky whispered.

04:09:10.319 --> 04:09:12.659
The dragonette was trembling so hard.

04:09:12.719 --> 04:09:15.180
Luna could feel the vibrations echoing in

04:09:15.180 --> 04:09:15.600
her bones.

04:09:15.659 --> 04:09:19.739
You stay with Tao, she said, unwrapping

04:09:19.739 --> 04:09:20.700
him from her shoulders.

04:09:20.760 --> 04:09:22.680
I'll come right back, all right?

04:09:22.739 --> 04:09:26.520
He made a sad little noise as she tucked

04:09:26.520 --> 04:09:28.680
him into Tao's arms, but he didn't argue

04:09:28.680 --> 04:09:28.920
with her.

04:09:28.979 --> 04:09:31.920
I hope I can make a weaving for him one

04:09:31.920 --> 04:09:32.219
day.

04:09:32.340 --> 04:09:33.600
Luna thought.

04:09:33.659 --> 04:09:35.159
Something comforting.

04:09:35.219 --> 04:09:37.860
Maybe of what he'll look like with wings

04:09:37.860 --> 04:09:40.139
to remind him of what he has to look

04:09:40.139 --> 04:09:40.559
forward to.

04:09:40.620 --> 04:09:44.520
It would have dusky in the center, flying

04:09:44.520 --> 04:09:47.219
looking happy instead of frightened, with

04:09:47.219 --> 04:09:49.799
dragons he trusts behind him, keeping him

04:09:49.799 --> 04:09:49.979
safe.

04:09:50.100 --> 04:09:53.399
Maybe I could put wren and axolotl in it

04:09:53.399 --> 04:09:55.799
waving from the ground, or flying with

04:09:55.799 --> 04:09:58.020
his friends, to remind him that some

04:09:58.020 --> 04:09:59.340
humans are safe and friendly.

04:09:59.399 --> 04:10:03.180
She felt her worry, sadness lift a little

04:10:03.180 --> 04:10:05.639
as she pictured the tapestry, and

04:10:05.639 --> 04:10:07.260
imagined the possible colors and

04:10:07.260 --> 04:10:07.739
composition.

04:10:07.799 --> 04:10:10.979
It distracted her enough to get her on to

04:10:10.979 --> 04:10:11.819
the ledge with cricket.

04:10:11.879 --> 04:10:14.579
And it helped squash down the fear enough

04:10:14.579 --> 04:10:16.319
so she could squeeze through the small

04:10:16.319 --> 04:10:18.600
gap right behind the hive wing.

04:10:18.659 --> 04:10:22.200
Her flame silk illuminated a long, dark

04:10:22.200 --> 04:10:24.120
tunnel, stretching away in either

04:10:24.120 --> 04:10:24.420
direction.

04:10:24.479 --> 04:10:27.299
The roof was low enough that Cricket and

04:10:27.299 --> 04:10:28.379
Luna both had to crouch.

04:10:28.440 --> 04:10:31.559
There was no sign of the hairy, hissing

04:10:31.559 --> 04:10:31.920
creature.

04:10:31.979 --> 04:10:33.780
Which way?

04:10:33.840 --> 04:10:34.979
Cricket whispered.

04:10:35.040 --> 04:10:37.680
Something glinted off to the left

04:10:37.680 --> 04:10:39.299
reflecting in the light of the flame

04:10:39.299 --> 04:10:39.719
silk.

04:10:39.840 --> 04:10:43.020
Luna pointed, and Cricket nodded, and

04:10:43.020 --> 04:10:45.299
they crept toward it, with cricket in the

04:10:45.299 --> 04:10:45.479
lead.

04:10:45.540 --> 04:10:48.600
The shiny thing turned out to be a

04:10:48.600 --> 04:10:51.840
diamond, several diamonds in fact, plus a

04:10:51.840 --> 04:10:54.360
few rubies and emeralds, embedded in the

04:10:54.360 --> 04:10:56.459
wall in a design that framed the archway

04:10:56.459 --> 04:10:57.120
into a new tunnel.

04:10:57.180 --> 04:11:00.239
Cricket brushed her claws over the

04:11:00.239 --> 04:11:00.659
design.

04:11:00.719 --> 04:11:03.600
Do these look like vines to you?

04:11:03.659 --> 04:11:05.520
She whispered to Luna.

04:11:05.579 --> 04:11:07.680
Luna nodded.

04:11:07.739 --> 04:11:10.860
Emerald vines, diamond flowers.

04:11:10.920 --> 04:11:13.440
Dark and blood red rubies throughout.

04:11:13.559 --> 04:11:16.680
I guess the humans made this.

04:11:16.739 --> 04:11:19.319
I wonder if that means the village is

04:11:19.319 --> 04:11:19.739
close.

04:11:19.799 --> 04:11:23.219
I don't see any humans down here, she

04:11:23.219 --> 04:11:23.940
added softly.

04:11:24.000 --> 04:11:26.100
But there's something on the wall in this

04:11:26.100 --> 04:11:26.520
tunnel.

04:11:26.579 --> 04:11:28.979
They went through the archway.

04:11:29.100 --> 04:11:31.979
In the light of Luna's flame silk, the

04:11:31.979 --> 04:11:33.239
stone walls came alive.

04:11:33.299 --> 04:11:35.700
Shapes flickering across them like

04:11:35.700 --> 04:11:36.600
darting shadows.

04:11:36.659 --> 04:11:39.600
She nearly yelped, thinking the hair

04:11:39.600 --> 04:11:41.700
creature was running toward them, but

04:11:41.700 --> 04:11:43.739
after the 1st moment of panic, she

04:11:43.739 --> 04:11:46.979
realized it was only paintings, paintings

04:11:46.979 --> 04:11:48.540
covered the tunnel walls on either side

04:11:48.540 --> 04:11:50.280
of them, and the ceiling as well.

04:11:50.340 --> 04:11:55.200
Pictures, Cricket said. in an awe struck

04:11:55.200 --> 04:11:57.299
voice, leaning closer to study them.

04:11:57.360 --> 04:11:59.520
It's a story, I think.

04:11:59.579 --> 04:12:02.100
The humans must have done these, right?

04:12:02.159 --> 04:12:04.020
There's so many of them.

04:12:04.139 --> 04:12:07.559
The walls and ceiling were covered in

04:12:07.559 --> 04:12:08.700
little drawings of humans.

04:12:08.760 --> 04:12:11.579
It was strange to see a story with this

04:12:11.579 --> 04:12:14.100
many humans in it, and no words to help

04:12:14.100 --> 04:12:16.260
figure out what was going on, and no

04:12:16.260 --> 04:12:18.360
dragons at all, as far as Luna could

04:12:18.360 --> 04:12:18.479
see.

04:12:18.600 --> 04:12:20.459
No, wait.

04:12:20.520 --> 04:12:21.780
There was one.

04:12:21.840 --> 04:12:24.120
A little farther along the passage.

04:12:24.180 --> 04:12:25.559
Tucked up near the ceiling.

04:12:25.620 --> 04:12:27.959
There was a drawing of a dragon curled in

04:12:27.959 --> 04:12:30.780
a cave, smoke rising from its nostrils.

04:12:30.840 --> 04:12:34.440
Luna followed the tunnel, watching the

04:12:34.440 --> 04:12:35.280
pictures as she went.

04:12:35.340 --> 04:12:38.520
The walls seemed to mirror each other, and

04:12:38.520 --> 04:12:40.500
were covered mostly with humans doing odd

04:12:40.500 --> 04:12:41.219
little human things.

04:12:41.280 --> 04:12:45.059
But here was the dragon again, this time

04:12:45.059 --> 04:12:46.920
flying low over a group of crouching

04:12:46.920 --> 04:12:49.799
stick figures, and farther along, here

04:12:49.799 --> 04:12:52.799
again, back in its cave, but now, with

04:12:52.799 --> 04:12:56.100
little bones scattered at its feet, Luna

04:12:56.100 --> 04:12:56.639
shuddered.

04:12:56.700 --> 04:12:59.159
The idea of eating any animals gave her

04:12:59.159 --> 04:13:01.559
the heebie-jeebies, eating animals that

04:13:01.559 --> 04:13:03.719
were smart and self aware, made it so

04:13:03.719 --> 04:13:04.079
much worse.

04:13:04.200 --> 04:13:07.559
These dragons didn't know who they were

04:13:07.559 --> 04:13:09.299
eating, she told herself.

04:13:09.360 --> 04:13:12.479
But to see a story like this, where

04:13:12.479 --> 04:13:14.940
dragons like her were the scary, dangerous

04:13:14.940 --> 04:13:15.299
villains.

04:13:15.360 --> 04:13:18.239
It made her feel strange and inside out

04:13:18.239 --> 04:13:20.219
like she didn't know who she really was.

04:13:20.280 --> 04:13:23.760
The drawings got more unsettling as they

04:13:23.760 --> 04:13:24.899
continued along the passage.

04:13:24.959 --> 04:13:27.360
More dragons appeared.

04:13:27.479 --> 04:13:29.879
Most of them chasing the tiny stick

04:13:29.879 --> 04:13:32.399
figures, and more bones filled the empty

04:13:32.399 --> 04:13:33.360
spaces on the wall.

04:13:33.360 --> 04:13:36.420
A few dragons had little human legs

04:13:36.420 --> 04:13:37.979
poking out of their mouths.

04:13:38.040 --> 04:13:41.159
Next, came several small human houses on

04:13:41.159 --> 04:13:43.500
fire, and a few small humans on fire

04:13:43.500 --> 04:13:43.860
too.

04:13:43.920 --> 04:13:48.299
My art won't be like this, Luna thought

04:13:48.299 --> 04:13:49.799
touching one of the paintings.

04:13:49.860 --> 04:13:52.680
Other dragons can do these kinds of

04:13:52.680 --> 04:13:53.340
stories.

04:13:53.399 --> 04:13:55.680
I want my tapestries to make dragons

04:13:55.680 --> 04:13:55.979
happy.

04:13:56.040 --> 04:13:59.520
I'll show dragons and humans side by side

04:13:59.520 --> 04:14:03.120
communicating, and living in peace, and

04:14:03.120 --> 04:14:05.159
maybe if enough dragons see it in a

04:14:05.159 --> 04:14:07.020
tapestry, they'll want to live it for

04:14:07.020 --> 04:14:07.500
real too.

04:14:07.559 --> 04:14:11.040
These aren't pental and dragons.

04:14:11.100 --> 04:14:12.899
Crooked said softly.

04:14:12.959 --> 04:14:14.280
Did you notice that?

04:14:14.340 --> 04:14:17.040
They all have 2 wings, and they're

04:14:17.040 --> 04:14:17.639
breathing fire.

04:14:17.700 --> 04:14:22.440
Oh, Luna said, studying the dragons more

04:14:22.440 --> 04:14:22.799
closely.

04:14:22.860 --> 04:14:25.500
She had to admit, that was smart of

04:14:25.500 --> 04:14:28.079
cricket to notice, and admitting that to

04:14:28.079 --> 04:14:30.899
herself made her realize she hadn't had

04:14:30.899 --> 04:14:32.459
any angry thoughts about cricket in a

04:14:32.459 --> 04:14:32.639
while.

04:14:32.700 --> 04:14:35.760
Somewhere along the way, she'd become

04:14:35.760 --> 04:14:38.819
cricket in Luna's mind, an individual

04:14:38.819 --> 04:14:41.459
dragon who was not so bad, instead of a

04:14:41.459 --> 04:14:43.500
hive wing, representative of her entire

04:14:43.500 --> 04:14:44.520
cruel tribe.

04:14:44.579 --> 04:14:46.200
You're right.

04:14:46.260 --> 04:14:47.700
What does that mean?

04:14:47.819 --> 04:14:50.459
How can there be drawings here?

04:14:50.520 --> 04:14:53.280
on Pentala, of Pyrean dragons.

04:14:53.340 --> 04:14:57.659
I think they're very old, Cricket said.

04:14:57.719 --> 04:15:00.180
Brushing one claw lightly over a small

04:15:00.180 --> 04:15:01.620
drawing of a shrieking human.

04:15:01.680 --> 04:15:04.379
Maybe they're from a time when the same

04:15:04.379 --> 04:15:06.479
dragons flew over both continents.

04:15:06.540 --> 04:15:07.860
Hmm.

04:15:07.979 --> 04:15:09.780
Luna said doubtfully.

04:15:09.840 --> 04:15:12.059
That didn't entirely make sense to her.

04:15:12.180 --> 04:15:14.940
If this continent used to have 2 winged

04:15:14.940 --> 04:15:17.459
dragons who breathed fire, why weren't

04:15:17.459 --> 04:15:17.940
they here anymore?

04:15:18.000 --> 04:15:21.059
More and more little squares on fire?

04:15:21.120 --> 04:15:22.680
Trees on fire?

04:15:22.739 --> 04:15:25.920
Painted flames covering wide swaths of

04:15:25.920 --> 04:15:28.139
the wall, with only a circle peeking out

04:15:28.139 --> 04:15:30.059
here and there that might have been a

04:15:30.059 --> 04:15:31.020
screaming human face.

04:15:31.079 --> 04:15:34.500
Luna really didn't love this story

04:15:34.500 --> 04:15:36.000
whatever was happening in it.

04:15:36.059 --> 04:15:39.180
Oh, Cricket yelped.

04:15:39.239 --> 04:15:41.879
She grabbed Luna's talon and pointed to

04:15:41.879 --> 04:15:42.719
the fire paintings.

04:15:42.780 --> 04:15:44.100
Luna.

04:15:44.219 --> 04:15:46.620
What if this is the thing Bullfrog was

04:15:46.620 --> 04:15:47.159
telling us about?

04:15:47.280 --> 04:15:49.440
The smoking?

04:15:49.500 --> 04:15:50.459
The burning.

04:15:50.520 --> 04:15:51.959
The scorching.

04:15:52.379 --> 04:15:53.879
Luna gasped.

04:15:53.940 --> 04:15:55.500
Could that be it?

04:15:55.559 --> 04:15:59.459
And this is how the human saw it, she

04:15:59.459 --> 04:16:00.000
cried.

04:16:00.059 --> 04:16:04.020
Lots of burning and death, Cricket said.

04:16:04.079 --> 04:16:06.420
Sounds kind of like how the dragon saw it

04:16:06.420 --> 04:16:06.899
too, actually.

04:16:06.959 --> 04:16:10.200
But wasn't the scorching 1000s of years

04:16:10.200 --> 04:16:10.500
ago?

04:16:10.559 --> 04:16:11.940
Luna asked.

04:16:12.000 --> 04:16:14.399
Maybe there have been humans down here

04:16:14.399 --> 04:16:14.940
all that time.

04:16:15.000 --> 04:16:16.319
Cricket said.

04:16:16.379 --> 04:16:18.899
Maybe this is how some of them survived

04:16:18.899 --> 04:16:20.940
by hiding in the caves and living

04:16:20.940 --> 04:16:21.479
underground.

04:16:21.540 --> 04:16:26.280
I wonder who this is, Luna said, pointing

04:16:26.280 --> 04:16:28.139
to a little figure all by himself in a

04:16:28.139 --> 04:16:30.239
space on the wall, with a circle of

04:16:30.239 --> 04:16:31.620
figures at a distance around him.

04:16:31.680 --> 04:16:34.739
He was slightly bigger than the others

04:16:34.739 --> 04:16:36.959
with a halo of light drawn around his

04:16:36.959 --> 04:16:39.239
head, and he was pointing toward the far

04:16:39.239 --> 04:16:41.159
end of the tunnel, the direction they

04:16:41.159 --> 04:16:41.700
were walking.

04:16:42.360 --> 04:16:45.000
A little ways on, she saw him again.

04:16:45.059 --> 04:16:48.479
Standing alone on a small crescent on top

04:16:48.479 --> 04:16:49.979
of what looked like waves.

04:16:50.040 --> 04:16:52.260
Lots of other humans were behind him

04:16:52.260 --> 04:16:55.620
following him, stuffed 10 apiece in their

04:16:55.620 --> 04:16:56.340
own crescents.

04:16:56.399 --> 04:16:58.860
She could tell it was the same figure

04:16:58.860 --> 04:17:01.680
even if he hadn't had the halo, because

04:17:01.680 --> 04:17:03.959
in both paintings, he was holding a green

04:17:03.959 --> 04:17:06.479
box and wearing thick black gloves.

04:17:06.540 --> 04:17:09.000
At least, she thought that's what it

04:17:09.000 --> 04:17:11.579
looked like, either that, or he had giant

04:17:11.579 --> 04:17:12.059
paws.

04:17:12.180 --> 04:17:14.639
Crossing the ocean.

04:17:14.700 --> 04:17:16.379
Cricket murmured.

04:17:16.440 --> 04:17:17.819
Darting along the wall.

04:17:17.940 --> 04:17:21.840
Coming to Pantala, and look, way along

04:17:21.840 --> 04:17:22.079
here.

04:17:22.139 --> 04:17:25.079
They've reached land again, and are going

04:17:25.079 --> 04:17:25.680
into a cave.

04:17:25.739 --> 04:17:29.340
She paused, and touched the painting

04:17:29.340 --> 04:17:32.100
lightly, then turned to look at Luna with

04:17:32.100 --> 04:17:32.579
worried eyes.

04:17:32.639 --> 04:17:35.340
Does it seem like there are a lot of

04:17:35.340 --> 04:17:36.780
plants painted around this cave?

04:17:36.840 --> 04:17:39.540
It did look very leafy.

04:17:39.600 --> 04:17:42.059
There were vines curling around the

04:17:42.059 --> 04:17:44.700
entrance, and under the human's feet, as

04:17:44.700 --> 04:17:46.139
they followed their hero into the mouth

04:17:46.139 --> 04:17:47.579
of the cave.

04:17:47.639 --> 04:17:49.739
The leaves and vines were streaked red

04:17:49.739 --> 04:17:51.840
and green, with little white flowers

04:17:51.840 --> 04:17:52.739
scattered around them.

04:17:52.799 --> 04:17:55.200
Muna knotted.

04:17:55.319 --> 04:17:58.440
Lots of one particular plant.

04:17:58.500 --> 04:17:59.940
She said slowly.

04:18:00.000 --> 04:18:03.000
Cricket let out a long breath.

04:18:03.059 --> 04:18:06.780
That's not just any plant, she said.

04:18:06.840 --> 04:18:08.819
I'm pretty sure that's the breath of

04:18:08.819 --> 04:18:09.180
evil.

04:18:09.239 --> 04:18:11.399
Luna!

04:18:11.459 --> 04:18:13.680
A little voice screamed from the tunnel

04:18:13.680 --> 04:18:14.459
behind them.

04:18:14.520 --> 04:18:16.260
Fire dragon, Luna.

04:18:16.319 --> 04:18:17.639
I'm here.

04:18:17.700 --> 04:18:20.579
Luna called, recognizing Dusky's voice

04:18:20.579 --> 04:18:21.659
with a jolt of alarm.

04:18:21.719 --> 04:18:23.879
She ran back along the painted tunnel.

04:18:23.940 --> 04:18:26.040
Dusky, stay there.

04:18:26.100 --> 04:18:26.520
I'm coming.

04:18:26.639 --> 04:18:28.139
Luna!

04:18:28.260 --> 04:18:29.399
He shrieked again.

04:18:29.459 --> 04:18:32.219
She flew through the archway and around

04:18:32.219 --> 04:18:33.840
the corner into the 1st tunnel.

04:18:33.899 --> 04:18:37.799
She saw Dusky's flame silk bracelet first

04:18:37.799 --> 04:18:40.200
glowing warmly in the dark passageway

04:18:40.200 --> 04:18:41.340
moving away from her.

04:18:41.399 --> 04:18:44.340
Then she saw the human holding Dusky.

04:18:44.399 --> 04:18:47.579
And a thick, twisted net Dusky was caught

04:18:47.579 --> 04:18:50.280
in, his little claws pinned to his sides

04:18:50.280 --> 04:18:53.639
and the other human, standing between her

04:18:53.639 --> 04:18:55.860
and the captured dragonette, holding a

04:18:55.860 --> 04:18:58.260
torch, and a sharp, gleaming knife.

04:18:58.379 --> 04:19:01.739
Neither human was the hairy, hissing

04:19:01.739 --> 04:19:04.020
creature, but they were not wren or

04:19:04.020 --> 04:19:04.979
axolotl either.

04:19:05.040 --> 04:19:08.280
These looked spiky and dangerous in their

04:19:08.280 --> 04:19:08.520
own way.

04:19:08.579 --> 04:19:11.459
The closer one had short, straight, dark

04:19:11.459 --> 04:19:14.100
hair, and black feathers woven into the

04:19:14.100 --> 04:19:15.899
leather of her outer wrappings.

04:19:15.959 --> 04:19:17.700
Her face was thinner and sharper than

04:19:17.700 --> 04:19:20.159
Wren's, and she had a tiny emerald

04:19:20.159 --> 04:19:21.420
embedded in the side of her nose.

04:19:21.479 --> 04:19:25.020
She called something to her partner, who

04:19:25.020 --> 04:19:26.760
wrapped his arms more firmly around the

04:19:26.760 --> 04:19:28.799
net and dusky, and took off running.

04:19:28.860 --> 04:19:31.440
No, Luna yelled.

04:19:31.500 --> 04:19:32.399
What are you doing?

04:19:32.459 --> 04:19:33.420
Stop.

04:19:33.479 --> 04:19:34.920
Ren, Ren, help.

04:19:34.979 --> 04:19:37.920
She ran full tilt toward them.

04:19:37.979 --> 04:19:40.139
But the feathered human flung down her

04:19:40.139 --> 04:19:42.659
torch in a blaze of flames, and darted

04:19:42.659 --> 04:19:43.200
after the other one.

04:19:43.260 --> 04:19:45.299
They were gone.

04:19:45.420 --> 04:19:47.819
And they'd taken Dusky with them.

04:19:47.879 --> 04:19:52.200
Chapter 12.

04:19:52.559 --> 04:19:54.899
Wren!

04:19:55.020 --> 04:19:57.479
Luna shouted again, as she reached the

04:19:57.479 --> 04:19:59.219
gap she'd squeezed through only a moment

04:19:59.219 --> 04:19:59.639
before.

04:19:59.700 --> 04:20:00.959
Help!

04:20:01.020 --> 04:20:02.700
There were humans here, and they took

04:20:02.700 --> 04:20:03.360
Dusky.

04:20:03.479 --> 04:20:06.059
She kicked aside the burning torch

04:20:06.059 --> 04:20:07.979
flinching at the stab of pain in her

04:20:07.979 --> 04:20:08.159
foot.

04:20:08.219 --> 04:20:12.059
Through the haze of panic around her, she

04:20:12.059 --> 04:20:14.700
heard Tao crying something like, he

04:20:14.700 --> 04:20:17.520
promised he would just look, Luna, I'm so

04:20:17.520 --> 04:20:17.700
sorry.

04:20:17.819 --> 04:20:18.959
They came out of nowhere.

04:20:19.020 --> 04:20:23.819
And bullfrog, grunting, it's too small.

04:20:23.879 --> 04:20:25.559
Can't get through.

04:20:25.680 --> 04:20:29.100
And Brian yelling, then get out of the

04:20:29.100 --> 04:20:30.540
way, you big thick crocodile.

04:20:30.659 --> 04:20:34.139
And Skye shouting, Ren, don't you dare.

04:20:34.200 --> 04:20:35.579
Wren, stop.

04:20:35.639 --> 04:20:36.600
It's not safe.

04:20:36.719 --> 04:20:40.079
And then Ren was there, in the passageway

04:20:40.079 --> 04:20:42.600
with her, seeing the look on Luna's face

04:20:42.600 --> 04:20:44.879
turning toward the sound of Dusky's

04:20:44.879 --> 04:20:47.159
shrieks, still echoing along the stone

04:20:47.159 --> 04:20:49.739
and running, and Luna ran with her.

04:20:49.799 --> 04:20:53.100
She thought she heard cricket's talon

04:20:53.100 --> 04:20:55.920
steps behind them, maybe Bryonies, but

04:20:55.920 --> 04:20:58.620
she didn't look back, only forward, at

04:20:58.620 --> 04:21:00.420
the distant light of Dusky's bracelet

04:21:00.420 --> 04:21:01.079
moving away from them.

04:21:01.200 --> 04:21:03.600
She wished she could run faster.

04:21:03.659 --> 04:21:06.780
But the 3rd time she ran headfirst into a

04:21:06.780 --> 04:21:09.000
stalactite, she forced herself to slow

04:21:09.000 --> 04:21:11.100
down and watch the passage ahead.

04:21:11.159 --> 04:21:13.559
She'd be no use to dusky if she knocked

04:21:13.559 --> 04:21:14.399
herself unconscious.

04:21:14.459 --> 04:21:17.219
What did the human say?

04:21:17.280 --> 04:21:20.280
Ren asked as they ran, why did they take

04:21:20.280 --> 04:21:20.520
him?

04:21:20.579 --> 04:21:23.819
I have no idea, Luna cried.

04:21:23.940 --> 04:21:26.819
They said, herbal cheapsqueak. and threw

04:21:26.819 --> 04:21:28.079
a net over him and ran away.

04:21:28.200 --> 04:21:30.299
Purple.

04:21:30.360 --> 04:21:32.040
Cheap, Ren muttered.

04:21:32.100 --> 04:21:33.239
Not literally.

04:21:33.299 --> 04:21:34.680
Luna interrupted.

04:21:34.739 --> 04:21:35.579
I don't know.

04:21:35.639 --> 04:21:37.979
It just sounded like squeaking to me.

04:21:38.040 --> 04:21:38.340
I sorry.

04:21:38.399 --> 04:21:41.639
I think one of them said, abyss.

04:21:41.760 --> 04:21:43.319
Cricket panted behind them.

04:21:43.379 --> 04:21:46.200
Luna remembered that the hive wing had

04:21:46.200 --> 04:21:48.479
been trying to study human with axolotl

04:21:48.479 --> 04:21:50.639
Wren, and Sky during their rest stops.

04:21:50.700 --> 04:21:52.559
Luna had been too tired to pay

04:21:52.559 --> 04:21:53.219
attention.

04:21:53.340 --> 04:21:54.959
She should have paid attention.

04:21:55.079 --> 04:21:57.600
She could at least have learned the word

04:21:57.600 --> 04:22:00.239
abyss, or maybe something actually useful

04:22:00.239 --> 04:22:03.719
like how to say, stop, or, don't you dare

04:22:03.719 --> 04:22:06.840
take that dragonette, or, I will give up

04:22:06.840 --> 04:22:09.299
vegetarianism just to eat you if you hurt

04:22:09.299 --> 04:22:10.079
that dragonette.

04:22:10.139 --> 04:22:15.000
It is weird, Ren said breathlessly, that

04:22:15.000 --> 04:22:17.520
they would grab a baby dragon with a big

04:22:17.520 --> 04:22:18.360
dragon right there.

04:22:18.479 --> 04:22:21.360
I mean, if they assume you're his mom

04:22:21.360 --> 04:22:24.239
they should guess, you'll chase them and

04:22:24.239 --> 04:22:25.139
probably eat them.

04:22:25.200 --> 04:22:28.319
And so if they were smart, they would

04:22:28.319 --> 04:22:30.180
drop him, and then they'd have a better

04:22:30.180 --> 04:22:31.079
chance of escaping.

04:22:31.139 --> 04:22:32.700
So it's...

04:22:32.700 --> 04:22:34.260
Weird is all.

04:22:34.379 --> 04:22:37.979
The tunnel zigged and zagged, and the

04:22:37.979 --> 04:22:39.420
humans kept turning off into other

04:22:39.420 --> 04:22:42.059
branches, and a few times, they nearly

04:22:42.059 --> 04:22:44.399
lost sight of Dusky's light at places

04:22:44.399 --> 04:22:47.219
where the path split, but then, it would

04:22:47.219 --> 04:22:47.760
always appear again.

04:22:47.819 --> 04:22:52.260
If the humans know these caves well, they

04:22:52.260 --> 04:22:53.700
should have been able to lose us by now.

04:22:53.760 --> 04:22:57.360
Ren pointed out, pausing to rest one hand

04:22:57.360 --> 04:22:59.280
against the wall, clutching her side.

04:22:59.340 --> 04:23:00.360
Sorry.

04:23:00.420 --> 04:23:01.799
Ow.

04:23:01.860 --> 04:23:02.940
I'll catch up.

04:23:03.000 --> 04:23:05.280
Luna crouched beside her.

04:23:05.340 --> 04:23:06.719
I'll carry you.

04:23:06.780 --> 04:23:08.639
If I catch them, I need you to

04:23:08.639 --> 04:23:09.420
communicate with them.

04:23:09.479 --> 04:23:12.659
Wren clambered onto Luna's bag without

04:23:12.659 --> 04:23:14.639
arguing, and they set off running again.

04:23:14.700 --> 04:23:17.520
The ground kept slanting downward.

04:23:17.579 --> 04:23:19.860
And each turn took them lower and lower

04:23:19.860 --> 04:23:20.459
into the earth.

04:23:20.520 --> 04:23:23.639
Luna wondered for a moment how they would

04:23:23.639 --> 04:23:24.659
ever get back to the others.

04:23:24.719 --> 04:23:27.600
Sky was going to kill her for taking Ren

04:23:27.600 --> 04:23:29.399
off to get lost in this underground

04:23:29.399 --> 04:23:30.000
labyrinth.

04:23:30.059 --> 04:23:32.579
Suddenly Luna realized.

04:23:32.639 --> 04:23:34.860
There was a faint green glow coming from

04:23:34.860 --> 04:23:35.340
up ahead.

04:23:35.399 --> 04:23:38.819
And maybe the sound of distant whispers

04:23:38.819 --> 04:23:39.120
too?

04:23:39.180 --> 04:23:42.059
It was hard to hear for sure over her

04:23:42.059 --> 04:23:44.520
running footsteps, but the glow became

04:23:44.520 --> 04:23:47.040
brighter as she ran closer, until she

04:23:47.040 --> 04:23:49.979
emerged into a sepulchral, echoing cavern

04:23:49.979 --> 04:23:52.559
and found herself on a plateau scattered

04:23:52.559 --> 04:23:53.040
with boulders.

04:23:53.100 --> 04:23:56.280
The plateau overlooked a jagged slash in

04:23:56.280 --> 04:23:58.860
the heart of the planet, a stab wound in

04:23:58.860 --> 04:24:01.680
the stone that plunged down and down and

04:24:01.680 --> 04:24:04.559
down, so far, it hurt Luna's eyes to look

04:24:04.559 --> 04:24:04.799
at it.

04:24:04.920 --> 04:24:06.659
The abyss.

04:24:06.780 --> 04:24:08.280
They'd found it.

04:24:08.399 --> 04:24:10.620
Luna had no doubt.

04:24:10.680 --> 04:24:13.379
There couldn't be any place deeper or

04:24:13.379 --> 04:24:15.420
creepier in the whole world.

04:24:15.479 --> 04:24:16.920
There couldn't be anywhere else where

04:24:16.920 --> 04:24:21.000
someone might stand and say, oh, this is

04:24:21.000 --> 04:24:22.979
much more of an abyss than that one.

04:24:23.100 --> 04:24:25.920
It felt like a place a prophecy would

04:24:25.920 --> 04:24:26.280
point to.

04:24:26.340 --> 04:24:28.739
It felt like it had been carved out of

04:24:28.739 --> 04:24:30.959
generations of dragons nightmares.

04:24:31.079 --> 04:24:33.059
And the humans were there.

04:24:33.120 --> 04:24:35.579
Standing near the edge with Dusky.

04:24:35.639 --> 04:24:39.000
As Luna spotted them, she realized the

04:24:39.000 --> 04:24:40.559
feathered one was crouching beside the

04:24:40.559 --> 04:24:42.719
baby dragon and sawing through the net

04:24:42.719 --> 04:24:43.260
with her knife.

04:24:43.319 --> 04:24:45.420
Don't hurt him.

04:24:46.200 --> 04:24:47.700
N cried, skidding to a stop.

04:24:47.760 --> 04:24:51.360
The one with the knife looked at her, then

04:24:51.360 --> 04:24:53.040
yelled something at the other one, who

04:24:53.040 --> 04:24:53.819
shook his head.

04:24:53.879 --> 04:24:56.100
She told him to run.

04:24:56.159 --> 04:24:58.500
Ren murmured to Luna.

04:24:58.559 --> 04:24:59.940
But he won't leave her.

04:25:00.000 --> 04:25:02.940
Luna, I think Dusky was bait.

04:25:03.059 --> 04:25:04.860
I think this is a trap.

04:25:04.920 --> 04:25:08.340
Luna jerked her head around, but there

04:25:08.340 --> 04:25:09.360
was no one else nearby.

04:25:09.420 --> 04:25:12.059
The glow from the abyss, and the light

04:25:12.059 --> 04:25:13.799
from her flame silk illuminated the

04:25:13.799 --> 04:25:14.280
plateau.

04:25:14.340 --> 04:25:17.459
No other humans, not even the hairy

04:25:17.459 --> 04:25:17.879
creature.

04:25:17.940 --> 04:25:20.819
No hidden nets, or anything that looked

04:25:20.819 --> 04:25:21.780
like it might trap her.

04:25:21.840 --> 04:25:24.540
If Cricket and Briony had been behind

04:25:24.540 --> 04:25:24.780
her.

04:25:24.840 --> 04:25:26.040
They hadn't caught up yet.

04:25:26.100 --> 04:25:29.219
It doesn't matter, she said.

04:25:29.280 --> 04:25:31.079
We have to get Dusky back.

04:25:31.139 --> 04:25:35.159
It made her sick with nerves to see him

04:25:35.159 --> 04:25:37.920
so close to that awful hole, knowing he

04:25:37.920 --> 04:25:40.200
had no wings, if the worst happened and

04:25:40.200 --> 04:25:40.620
he fell in.

04:25:40.680 --> 04:25:44.459
Wren slid off Luna's back and stepped

04:25:44.459 --> 04:25:46.799
toward the humans, holding her hands with

04:25:46.799 --> 04:25:47.639
palms out.

04:25:47.700 --> 04:25:50.459
She called to the menhuman, and both

04:25:50.459 --> 04:25:52.379
humans froze, staring at her.

04:25:52.440 --> 04:25:54.420
Here we go.

04:25:54.479 --> 04:25:56.399
Wren said with a sigh.

04:25:56.459 --> 04:25:59.340
Luna, look as fierce as you can.

04:25:59.399 --> 04:26:02.280
I'm going to try talking them down, but

04:26:02.280 --> 04:26:03.780
it'll help if you could look a bit more

04:26:03.780 --> 04:26:04.200
threatening.

04:26:04.260 --> 04:26:07.379
She took another step toward the humans

04:26:07.379 --> 04:26:09.840
and said something else, and the one in

04:26:09.840 --> 04:26:11.100
black feathers responded.

04:26:11.159 --> 04:26:13.979
Look fierce and scary.

04:26:14.040 --> 04:26:17.280
Luna fluffed up her wings, hoping that

04:26:17.280 --> 04:26:19.020
would make her look bigger, and frowned.

04:26:19.139 --> 04:26:22.319
She always found frowning dragons a

04:26:22.319 --> 04:26:22.979
little scary anyhow.

04:26:23.100 --> 04:26:24.360
What else could she do?

04:26:24.420 --> 04:26:26.340
Oh, right.

04:26:26.399 --> 04:26:28.020
My terrifying superpower.

04:26:28.139 --> 04:26:31.139
As the human said bristly sounding things

04:26:31.139 --> 04:26:34.319
back and forth, Luna lifted one talon and

04:26:34.319 --> 04:26:36.959
let a smoking thread of blaze silk spill

04:26:36.959 --> 04:26:40.020
into her palm, it wound into a ball, and

04:26:40.020 --> 04:26:41.700
she cupped the fire between her claws.

04:26:41.819 --> 04:26:44.459
She never tried throwing flame soap

04:26:44.459 --> 04:26:46.799
before, but maybe holding it menacingly

04:26:46.799 --> 04:26:47.280
would be enough.

04:26:47.340 --> 04:26:50.399
The feathered human looked around the

04:26:50.399 --> 04:26:51.780
plateau and shouted something.

04:26:51.840 --> 04:26:55.200
Her partner shook his head, and responded

04:26:55.200 --> 04:26:56.760
in a quiet, sad voice.

04:26:56.879 --> 04:26:58.979
What's happening?

04:26:59.040 --> 04:27:00.719
Luna asked Wren.

04:27:00.780 --> 04:27:02.520
Why aren't they giving Dusky back?

04:27:02.579 --> 04:27:06.360
They're waiting for someone, Ren said.

04:27:06.420 --> 04:27:09.659
They called him the Guardian of the Abyss

04:27:09.659 --> 04:27:12.479
but his name must be Vol because that's

04:27:12.479 --> 04:27:13.680
what that one just shouted.

04:27:13.739 --> 04:27:15.780
I think her name is Raven.

04:27:15.899 --> 04:27:18.420
She says the guardian told them to bring

04:27:18.420 --> 04:27:21.180
the abyss, a dragon, or the abyss told

04:27:21.180 --> 04:27:23.579
them, speaking through the guardian

04:27:23.579 --> 04:27:24.059
something like that.

04:27:24.120 --> 04:27:27.420
She listened to the conversation the

04:27:27.420 --> 04:27:28.620
other humans were having for a moment.

04:27:28.680 --> 04:27:31.500
Apparently he's always here.

04:27:31.559 --> 04:27:33.659
It's creepy that he's missing.

04:27:33.719 --> 04:27:35.280
He's never left before.

04:27:35.340 --> 04:27:37.200
They didn't even think he could.

04:27:37.260 --> 04:27:41.879
Luna felt a horrible chill, like Arctic

04:27:41.879 --> 04:27:43.559
spiders tiptoeing down her spine.

04:27:43.680 --> 04:27:47.159
The abyss talks to them, she said.

04:27:47.280 --> 04:27:50.520
It asks for things.

04:27:50.579 --> 04:27:52.440
Do they know what's down there?

04:27:52.500 --> 04:27:56.219
Ren spoke to the humans, and the one

04:27:56.219 --> 04:27:57.479
without feathers answered her.

04:27:57.540 --> 04:27:59.459
They don't know.

04:27:59.520 --> 04:28:01.260
Ren relayed to Luna.

04:28:01.319 --> 04:28:04.079
Only the guardian can go into the abyss.

04:28:04.139 --> 04:28:05.459
I'm not sure how.

04:28:05.520 --> 04:28:07.559
But they get instructions through him.

04:28:07.620 --> 04:28:09.899
Ren shook her head.

04:28:09.959 --> 04:28:13.620
I'd say it's all a made up cult thing, but

04:28:13.620 --> 04:28:15.719
since it's in your prophecy, then I guess

04:28:15.719 --> 04:28:17.340
there really might be something down

04:28:17.340 --> 04:28:17.520
there.

04:28:17.579 --> 04:28:20.219
The breath of evil.

04:28:20.280 --> 04:28:21.540
Luna thought.

04:28:21.600 --> 04:28:23.459
The source of the other mind.

04:28:23.579 --> 04:28:25.680
It has to be, doesn't it?

04:28:25.739 --> 04:28:29.399
Well, it can't have Dusky, she said

04:28:29.399 --> 04:28:29.879
firmly.

04:28:29.940 --> 04:28:31.139
Tell them no.

04:28:31.200 --> 04:28:33.840
Tell them I will set them on fire right

04:28:33.840 --> 04:28:36.000
now if they don't give him back.

04:28:36.120 --> 04:28:39.000
Ren put her hands on her hips.

04:28:39.059 --> 04:28:41.340
And whatever she said in human, it

04:28:41.340 --> 04:28:43.079
sounded very commanding to Luna.

04:28:43.139 --> 04:28:46.139
Raven and the other human looked at each

04:28:46.139 --> 04:28:48.420
other for a long moment, and then Raven

04:28:48.420 --> 04:28:51.120
sighed, knelt down and cut the rest of

04:28:51.120 --> 04:28:52.319
the net off Dusky.

04:28:52.379 --> 04:28:56.459
Luna, he yelped, as soon as his snout was

04:28:56.459 --> 04:28:56.639
free.

04:28:56.700 --> 04:28:59.100
He wriggled away from the robes as the

04:28:59.100 --> 04:29:01.500
humans stepped back and pelted across the

04:29:01.500 --> 04:29:02.459
plateau toward her.

04:29:02.520 --> 04:29:04.200
Dusky?

04:29:04.260 --> 04:29:05.760
Luna cried with relief.

04:29:05.819 --> 04:29:06.899
It's all right.

04:29:06.959 --> 04:29:07.680
We're here.

04:29:07.739 --> 04:29:11.340
She set down her ball of flame silk, and

04:29:11.340 --> 04:29:14.100
stepped forward, talons outstretched to

04:29:14.100 --> 04:29:14.940
catch him.

04:29:15.000 --> 04:29:18.000
But he was still a few steps away, when

04:29:18.000 --> 04:29:19.319
something dropped from the ceiling.

04:29:19.379 --> 04:29:21.899
Something that had been hiding among the

04:29:21.899 --> 04:29:24.659
stalactites overhead, waiting to pounce

04:29:24.659 --> 04:29:26.940
like a vicious predatory insect.

04:29:27.059 --> 04:29:30.899
Something hairy, and leggy, and hissing

04:29:30.899 --> 04:29:34.260
giving off a stench, almost as bad as

04:29:34.260 --> 04:29:36.239
Lady Scarab's weapon as it fell.

04:29:36.299 --> 04:29:39.840
The guardian of the Abyss landed on Dusky

04:29:39.840 --> 04:29:41.819
knocking the dragonette flat.

04:29:41.879 --> 04:29:44.280
He seized the little silkwing in his

04:29:44.280 --> 04:29:46.139
spindly arms and sprinted sideways

04:29:46.139 --> 04:29:48.659
darting away from Luna, while her brain

04:29:48.659 --> 04:29:51.479
was still screaming, creepy things

04:29:51.479 --> 04:29:52.260
falling from the sky.

04:29:52.379 --> 04:29:56.700
And then, before anyone could blink, or

04:29:56.700 --> 04:29:57.719
scream, or move.

04:29:57.780 --> 04:30:01.319
The terrifying human hurled himself, and

04:30:01.319 --> 04:30:03.659
the wingless dragonette, over the edge

04:30:03.659 --> 04:30:05.340
into the abyss.

04:30:05.459 --> 04:30:09.600
Part two.

04:30:09.719 --> 04:30:13.139
A secret buried far below.

04:30:13.260 --> 04:30:16.500
Chapter 13.

04:30:16.739 --> 04:30:19.020
Desky.

04:30:19.079 --> 04:30:20.579
Luna shrieked.

04:30:20.639 --> 04:30:22.620
No, no, no, no, no.

04:30:22.739 --> 04:30:24.239
This couldn't be happening.

04:30:24.299 --> 04:30:26.579
The little dragon couldn't be gone just

04:30:26.579 --> 04:30:26.879
like that.

04:30:26.940 --> 04:30:29.459
The abyss could not have him.

04:30:29.520 --> 04:30:32.040
She didn't stop to think.

04:30:32.100 --> 04:30:34.680
She ran to the edge and threw herself

04:30:34.680 --> 04:30:35.280
after them.

04:30:35.399 --> 04:30:37.440
I can catch them.

04:30:37.500 --> 04:30:39.719
I can save Dusky before they hit the

04:30:39.719 --> 04:30:40.079
bottom.

04:30:40.139 --> 04:30:41.040
I can get him back.

04:30:41.100 --> 04:30:43.260
Below her.

04:30:43.319 --> 04:30:45.659
She could see the tiny dark silhouette of

04:30:45.659 --> 04:30:47.940
the guardian falling, framed against the

04:30:47.940 --> 04:30:49.860
weird glow. behind her.

04:30:49.920 --> 04:30:52.319
She heard Wren shouting, but she couldn't

04:30:52.319 --> 04:30:53.579
make out anything the human was saying.

04:30:53.700 --> 04:30:56.879
I guess I am a dragon who can fly into

04:30:56.879 --> 04:30:58.020
the danger when I have to.

04:30:58.079 --> 04:31:00.000
She thought as she plummeted.

04:31:00.059 --> 04:31:01.379
I never knew for sure.

04:31:01.440 --> 04:31:04.319
Sortell always did it for me, before I

04:31:04.319 --> 04:31:04.680
ever could.

04:31:04.739 --> 04:31:07.020
Please be okay, Dusky.

04:31:07.079 --> 04:31:09.899
The flailing stick figure below her

04:31:09.899 --> 04:31:12.360
looked as far away as before, and the

04:31:12.360 --> 04:31:13.620
fall felt endless.

04:31:13.680 --> 04:31:16.260
Luna tried pumping her wings to descend

04:31:16.260 --> 04:31:18.120
faster, but it didn't seem to help.

04:31:18.180 --> 04:31:20.760
Why would the guardian do this?

04:31:20.879 --> 04:31:22.799
Why would he take Dusky?

04:31:22.860 --> 04:31:25.860
Why would the abyss want a baby dragon?

04:31:25.920 --> 04:31:28.440
The light was getting brighter.

04:31:28.559 --> 04:31:31.500
Bright enough to dazzle her eyes, and

04:31:31.500 --> 04:31:33.180
suddenly she couldn't see the human and

04:31:33.180 --> 04:31:33.719
dusky anymore.

04:31:33.780 --> 04:31:36.000
They were swallowed by the green glow

04:31:36.000 --> 04:31:38.399
which filled her field of vision

04:31:38.399 --> 04:31:41.879
shimmering fold of eerie light, consuming

04:31:41.879 --> 04:31:44.520
everything else, and blinding her, so she

04:31:44.520 --> 04:31:46.020
didn't know how much farther she had to

04:31:46.020 --> 04:31:46.260
fall.

04:31:46.319 --> 04:31:49.200
And then all at once, she was there.

04:31:49.260 --> 04:31:53.219
Luna had to swerve the last moment, to

04:31:53.219 --> 04:31:55.559
avoid landing in the morass of vines that

04:31:55.559 --> 04:31:56.700
carpeted the abyss floor.

04:31:56.760 --> 04:31:59.879
They were thick, and wound together like

04:31:59.879 --> 04:32:02.459
an angry nest of eels, and she thought

04:32:02.459 --> 04:32:04.379
the whole tangle might be dragons deep.

04:32:04.440 --> 04:32:07.139
The phosphorescent light came from the

04:32:07.139 --> 04:32:09.840
leaves, and from a moist, mossy coating

04:32:09.840 --> 04:32:10.920
on all the walls around her.

04:32:10.979 --> 04:32:13.680
It was bright enough here, that she

04:32:13.680 --> 04:32:15.299
wouldn't have needed the glow silk on her

04:32:15.299 --> 04:32:18.000
horns, but she was glad she had it, and

04:32:18.000 --> 04:32:19.319
its warm golden light.

04:32:19.379 --> 04:32:22.379
There was no sign of Dusky, or the

04:32:22.379 --> 04:32:23.159
wretched human.

04:32:23.280 --> 04:32:24.719
Tusky!

04:32:24.840 --> 04:32:25.680
Luna cried.

04:32:25.739 --> 04:32:26.879
Dusky.

04:32:26.940 --> 04:32:29.819
Maybe the vines had cushioned their fall

04:32:29.819 --> 04:32:31.979
but then, where were they now?

04:32:32.040 --> 04:32:34.620
How could they have vanished so quickly?

04:32:34.680 --> 04:32:35.819
Wait.

04:32:35.879 --> 04:32:36.899
There.

04:32:36.959 --> 04:32:39.479
There was a section of the tangle that

04:32:39.479 --> 04:32:40.500
looked partly crushed.

04:32:40.559 --> 04:32:42.600
This had to be where they had landed.

04:32:42.659 --> 04:32:45.540
Luna hovered as close as she dared and

04:32:45.540 --> 04:32:46.260
peered at it.

04:32:46.319 --> 04:32:48.899
She didn't want to land on or touch the

04:32:48.899 --> 04:32:49.319
vines.

04:32:49.440 --> 04:32:52.139
She could too easily imagine long

04:32:52.139 --> 04:32:54.479
tendrils, wrapping around her ankles

04:32:54.479 --> 04:32:57.180
dragging her down, so the plants could

04:32:57.180 --> 04:32:58.979
dissolve her into bone mulch.

04:32:59.100 --> 04:33:02.459
And she was pretty sure, this was the

04:33:02.459 --> 04:33:03.059
breath of evil.

04:33:03.180 --> 04:33:05.880
She'd never seen it in real life before

04:33:05.880 --> 04:33:08.459
but it looked like the plant in the cave

04:33:08.459 --> 04:33:10.680
paintings, and it matched the description

04:33:10.680 --> 04:33:13.020
from cricket and sundews stories.

04:33:13.080 --> 04:33:14.580
Muna!

04:33:14.639 --> 04:33:16.380
Dusky's voice shrieked.

04:33:16.500 --> 04:33:18.779
Luna whipped around.

04:33:18.840 --> 04:33:21.659
There was a trail across the vines if she

04:33:21.659 --> 04:33:22.139
squinted.

04:33:22.200 --> 04:33:24.720
The path of a small creature running full

04:33:24.720 --> 04:33:27.540
tilt, leaping from tangle to tangle like

04:33:27.540 --> 04:33:30.240
a fearless squirrel, and it led in the

04:33:30.240 --> 04:33:32.099
direction of Dusky's cry for help.

04:33:32.220 --> 04:33:35.819
She shot over the vines, swooping around

04:33:35.819 --> 04:33:37.020
the curves of the abyss.

04:33:37.139 --> 04:33:40.020
Maybe the abyss monster could fall faster

04:33:40.020 --> 04:33:41.759
than she could catch him, but he could

04:33:41.759 --> 04:33:43.860
not run her wings, especially while

04:33:43.860 --> 04:33:44.880
carrying a baby dragon.

04:33:45.000 --> 04:33:48.299
As it turned out though, he hadn't had to

04:33:48.299 --> 04:33:48.599
run far.

04:33:48.659 --> 04:33:51.779
The vines and the trail converged on a

04:33:51.779 --> 04:33:55.020
cave in the wall of the abyss, or rather

04:33:55.020 --> 04:33:57.900
the vines seemed to be exploding from it

04:33:57.900 --> 04:33:59.880
swarming out in both directions.

04:33:59.939 --> 04:34:03.119
The cave entrance was full of plants.

04:34:03.180 --> 04:34:05.700
But there was a gap near the top where a

04:34:05.700 --> 04:34:08.639
small dragon, or a human and a tiny

04:34:08.639 --> 04:34:10.080
dragon could fit through.

04:34:10.080 --> 04:34:13.380
Luna held her breath and dove toward the

04:34:13.380 --> 04:34:13.680
opening.

04:34:13.740 --> 04:34:16.740
Her wings and talons brushed the vines as

04:34:16.740 --> 04:34:18.720
she glided through, and she felt the

04:34:18.720 --> 04:34:21.299
tendrils shiver, as if a 1000000

04:34:21.299 --> 04:34:23.759
gleefully venomous wasps were waking up

04:34:23.759 --> 04:34:24.540
somewhere nearby.

04:34:24.599 --> 04:34:28.259
On the other side, there was a room.

04:34:28.319 --> 04:34:32.099
That is, it still felt like a cave.

04:34:32.159 --> 04:34:35.220
Stone walls, chili, dark.

04:34:35.340 --> 04:34:38.220
But it was the size and shape of a throne

04:34:38.220 --> 04:34:42.659
room, square, with 4 matching columns, and

04:34:42.659 --> 04:34:43.680
corners.

04:34:43.740 --> 04:34:46.680
And most importantly, a throne on the far

04:34:46.680 --> 04:34:49.799
end, up against a perfectly smooth, flat

04:34:49.799 --> 04:34:50.159
wall.

04:34:50.220 --> 04:34:54.060
The vines were coming from the thing on

04:34:54.060 --> 04:34:54.479
the throne.

04:34:54.540 --> 04:34:57.659
Luna tried to make the scene into a

04:34:57.659 --> 04:34:59.939
picture in her memory instinctively, the

04:34:59.939 --> 04:35:02.159
way she always did, but she couldn't.

04:35:02.220 --> 04:35:04.380
She couldn't figure it out.

04:35:04.439 --> 04:35:06.539
She couldn't get her brain to fit around

04:35:06.539 --> 04:35:07.799
what her eyes could see.

04:35:07.860 --> 04:35:12.959
Her 1st thought was, This would be such a

04:35:12.959 --> 04:35:14.279
disturbing tapestry.

04:35:14.340 --> 04:35:17.819
Her mind desperately wanted to see it as

04:35:17.819 --> 04:35:20.639
a tapestry instead, as a picture, not

04:35:20.639 --> 04:35:23.340
real, not really right in front of her.

04:35:23.580 --> 04:35:27.419
She'd expected a plant, and yes, there

04:35:27.419 --> 04:35:28.020
was a plant.

04:35:28.080 --> 04:35:31.380
A stem as thick as the columns rose from

04:35:31.380 --> 04:35:33.540
the earth below the throne, winding

04:35:33.540 --> 04:35:34.319
around the pedestal.

04:35:34.380 --> 04:35:37.259
But on the throne was a man.

04:35:37.380 --> 04:35:41.400
And sitting on his knees, captured

04:35:41.400 --> 04:35:43.319
between the thick black gloves on the

04:35:43.319 --> 04:35:45.720
human's hands, was a young dragon.

04:35:45.779 --> 04:35:49.139
For a horrible moment, Luna thought it

04:35:49.139 --> 04:35:49.739
was dusky.

04:35:49.799 --> 04:35:52.979
But as she flew closer, her light

04:35:52.979 --> 04:35:55.919
reflected off green and orange scales, and

04:35:55.919 --> 04:35:58.139
she saw that this dragonette had wings.

04:35:58.200 --> 04:36:01.319
It also could not possibly be alive.

04:36:01.380 --> 04:36:05.279
The plant was growing straight through

04:36:05.279 --> 04:36:06.599
the dragon's skull.

04:36:06.659 --> 04:36:10.919
Emerging, horrifyingly, from a split at

04:36:10.919 --> 04:36:13.380
the top of its head and then continuing

04:36:13.380 --> 04:36:14.880
on through the human's skull.

04:36:14.939 --> 04:36:18.599
Behind a human's head, the vines divided

04:36:18.599 --> 04:36:21.359
and cascaded away, like a parody of

04:36:21.359 --> 04:36:24.419
ocelot's hair, like tentacles, exploding

04:36:24.419 --> 04:36:25.019
outward.

04:36:25.080 --> 04:36:27.659
Some of them swarmed toward the cave

04:36:27.659 --> 04:36:30.299
opening, while 100s of others clambered

04:36:30.299 --> 04:36:32.759
up the walls and disappeared into cracks

04:36:32.759 --> 04:36:33.060
overhead.

04:36:33.119 --> 04:36:35.039
What?

04:36:35.159 --> 04:36:37.319
Luna breathed.

04:36:37.439 --> 04:36:40.799
At the foot of the throne, on the vines

04:36:40.799 --> 04:36:43.139
that covered the floor, a hairy shape

04:36:43.139 --> 04:36:45.539
twisted around to glare at her, in his

04:36:45.539 --> 04:36:48.179
arms, dusky flailed, whimpering.

04:36:48.240 --> 04:36:52.139
Dusky, Luna said, starting forward.

04:36:52.200 --> 04:36:54.299
Stay back.

04:36:54.360 --> 04:36:56.459
Hissed voice in dragon.

04:36:56.580 --> 04:36:58.740
The voice came from the guardian's

04:36:58.740 --> 04:36:59.099
mouth.

04:36:59.159 --> 04:37:01.919
It sounded like the possessed silkwing on

04:37:01.919 --> 04:37:03.419
the island where they'd been attacked.

04:37:03.479 --> 04:37:04.799
Luna froze.

04:37:04.860 --> 04:37:07.259
Who is talking to me?

04:37:07.319 --> 04:37:08.340
The other mind?

04:37:08.400 --> 04:37:10.139
Who are you?

04:37:10.200 --> 04:37:11.400
Luna said.

04:37:11.459 --> 04:37:14.220
She focused her gaze on the throne.

04:37:14.340 --> 04:37:16.439
On the grotesque tableau of the

04:37:16.439 --> 04:37:19.020
dragonette, man and plant fused

04:37:19.020 --> 04:37:19.439
together.

04:37:19.500 --> 04:37:22.259
Their blank, staring eyes seem to be

04:37:22.259 --> 04:37:22.860
fixed on her.

04:37:22.919 --> 04:37:26.099
Both the human and the dragon had a white

04:37:26.099 --> 04:37:28.559
film covering their eyeballs, with a

04:37:28.559 --> 04:37:30.539
shimmer of mossy green overlaying it.

04:37:30.599 --> 04:37:33.599
But they couldn't still be alive.

04:37:33.659 --> 04:37:36.840
They just absolutely could not be.

04:37:36.900 --> 04:37:40.259
I am the emperor of the world.

04:37:40.319 --> 04:37:43.919
You're so not, Luna said.

04:37:43.979 --> 04:37:46.139
How can you be emperor if no one even

04:37:46.139 --> 04:37:46.680
knows you exist?

04:37:46.740 --> 04:37:49.259
Hissing filled the room.

04:37:49.319 --> 04:37:52.020
Coming from the throne, into shivering

04:37:52.020 --> 04:37:54.419
plants, and the guardian of the abyss all

04:37:54.419 --> 04:37:54.959
at the same time.

04:37:55.020 --> 04:37:59.040
They will know, said the voice.

04:37:59.159 --> 04:38:01.200
They will all know soon.

04:38:01.259 --> 04:38:03.359
I am the ruler of everything.

04:38:03.419 --> 04:38:05.759
All of it is mine all.

04:38:05.880 --> 04:38:06.840
Okay.

04:38:06.900 --> 04:38:09.299
You're deranged and sinister.

04:38:09.360 --> 04:38:11.520
Got it, Luna interrupted.

04:38:11.580 --> 04:38:13.139
But who is talking right now?

04:38:13.200 --> 04:38:14.340
What is that?

04:38:14.459 --> 04:38:16.560
She pointed to the throne.

04:38:16.619 --> 04:38:18.419
What happened to that little dragon?

04:38:18.479 --> 04:38:21.779
There was an offended silence for a

04:38:21.779 --> 04:38:22.380
heartbeat.

04:38:22.439 --> 04:38:23.279
Two.

04:38:23.340 --> 04:38:24.599
Three.

04:38:24.659 --> 04:38:27.599
And then, with a wrestling, the voice

04:38:27.599 --> 04:38:28.439
finally answered.

04:38:28.560 --> 04:38:32.819
Give yourself to the vines, and we'll

04:38:32.819 --> 04:38:34.020
show you the whole story.

04:38:34.080 --> 04:38:36.419
Ha!

04:38:36.479 --> 04:38:37.380
Luna said.

04:38:37.439 --> 04:38:39.359
No, easy no.

04:38:39.419 --> 04:38:40.859
I will never let you take my mind.

04:38:40.919 --> 04:38:44.939
It's inevitable now, the voice said

04:38:44.939 --> 04:38:45.419
calmly.

04:38:45.479 --> 04:38:47.580
As soon as you entered this chamber

04:38:47.580 --> 04:38:50.520
eventually your wings will tire, and

04:38:50.520 --> 04:38:52.319
you'll drop from the air with exhaustion

04:38:52.319 --> 04:38:54.360
and then my vines will have you.

04:38:54.779 --> 04:38:57.179
Luna scoffed.

04:38:57.240 --> 04:38:58.619
I can leave whenever.

04:38:58.919 --> 04:39:01.079
She turned toward the cave entrance.

04:39:01.139 --> 04:39:04.560
It was entirely barricaded with vines.

04:39:04.619 --> 04:39:07.919
Muna shot over to the tangle that now

04:39:07.919 --> 04:39:08.699
blocked the exit.

04:39:08.819 --> 04:39:11.400
She nearly grabbed one of the vines to

04:39:11.400 --> 04:39:13.799
rip it away, but she pulled her talons

04:39:13.799 --> 04:39:15.360
back at the side of wicked thorns

04:39:15.360 --> 04:39:16.560
bristling along the edges.

04:39:16.619 --> 04:39:19.319
If they scratched her, would she

04:39:19.319 --> 04:39:20.819
instantly be lost to the other mind?

04:39:20.939 --> 04:39:23.219
Or would it happen if she touched the

04:39:23.219 --> 04:39:24.119
sticky sap?

04:39:24.119 --> 04:39:25.979
Or the jagged leaves?

04:39:26.040 --> 04:39:27.180
How did this work?

04:39:27.240 --> 04:39:29.400
Was it more dangerous here?

04:39:29.459 --> 04:39:32.099
This close to the roots, to its origin?

04:39:32.159 --> 04:39:34.439
How did you do this?

04:39:34.500 --> 04:39:35.700
Loonan demanded.

04:39:35.759 --> 04:39:38.519
I thought you needed a dragon with leaf

04:39:38.519 --> 04:39:39.659
speak to move the vines.

04:39:39.720 --> 04:39:42.720
Oh, I have one.

04:39:42.779 --> 04:39:46.139
Luna's gaze went to the mystery

04:39:46.139 --> 04:39:47.279
dragonette on the throne.

04:39:47.340 --> 04:39:49.200
Was it a leaf wing?

04:39:49.259 --> 04:39:51.299
But the orange scales.

04:39:51.360 --> 04:39:53.400
It didn't look like any tribe she'd seen

04:39:53.400 --> 04:39:53.759
so far.

04:39:53.819 --> 04:39:57.840
Unfortunately, my lizard is not strong

04:39:57.840 --> 04:39:59.340
enough for everything we want to do.

04:39:59.400 --> 04:40:02.880
Her leaf speak works for the vines close

04:40:02.880 --> 04:40:05.520
to us in the abyss, but not in the

04:40:05.520 --> 04:40:06.119
overworld.

04:40:06.240 --> 04:40:10.080
Which is why this fool was supposed to

04:40:10.080 --> 04:40:11.700
bring me sundew.

04:40:11.819 --> 04:40:13.500
The voice suddenly roared.

04:40:13.619 --> 04:40:16.979
At the foot of the throne, the guardian

04:40:16.979 --> 04:40:18.720
coward, baring his teeth.

04:40:18.779 --> 04:40:21.779
He whined something inhuman, and shook

04:40:21.779 --> 04:40:22.919
poor little dusky.

04:40:22.919 --> 04:40:27.060
That is obviously not the dragon I need.

04:40:27.180 --> 04:40:29.400
The voice abruptly cut off.

04:40:29.459 --> 04:40:32.819
There was an odd, strangled sound, and

04:40:32.819 --> 04:40:33.479
then it returned.

04:40:33.540 --> 04:40:35.580
Suddenly soft and whispery.

04:40:35.639 --> 04:40:38.520
But it's the dragon I want.

04:40:38.580 --> 04:40:42.000
A few of the vines slithered toward Dusky

04:40:42.000 --> 04:40:43.200
like curious snakes.

04:40:43.259 --> 04:40:45.540
The guardian took a step away from them

04:40:45.540 --> 04:40:47.220
and snarled something else.

04:40:47.340 --> 04:40:51.779
Pathetic. the voice said, back to its

04:40:51.779 --> 04:40:52.740
previous cadence.

04:40:52.860 --> 04:40:56.159
You're not much use to me either, Silkwing

04:40:56.159 --> 04:40:58.439
but I'll keep you just for fun.

04:40:58.500 --> 04:41:01.139
Maybe sundew will come looking for you.

04:41:01.259 --> 04:41:03.240
That would be convenient.

04:41:03.299 --> 04:41:06.959
I'm not afraid of you, Luna said.

04:41:07.020 --> 04:41:09.900
She turned her wrists upward and gestured

04:41:09.900 --> 04:41:10.860
at the vines all around.

04:41:10.919 --> 04:41:13.080
I'm a flame sulk.

04:41:13.139 --> 04:41:14.819
All I have to do is burn my way out.

04:41:14.880 --> 04:41:18.180
Maybe this is the reason I'm a flame

04:41:18.180 --> 04:41:18.540
silk.

04:41:18.659 --> 04:41:21.479
Maybe I'm supposed to use my sun silk to

04:41:21.479 --> 04:41:23.040
burn all these vines to ashes.

04:41:23.099 --> 04:41:25.680
Maybe this is always where I was supposed

04:41:25.680 --> 04:41:26.159
to end up.

04:41:26.279 --> 04:41:30.419
Oh, said the voice gleefully.

04:41:30.479 --> 04:41:33.180
Oh no, no, don't.

04:41:33.240 --> 04:41:34.259
Anything but that.

04:41:34.319 --> 04:41:36.659
Luna hesitated.

04:41:36.720 --> 04:41:38.939
Why did it sound so delighted?

04:41:39.060 --> 04:41:42.720
That would be just terrible.

04:41:42.779 --> 04:41:44.220
The voice went on.

04:41:44.279 --> 04:41:47.639
You fiendish monster.

04:41:47.700 --> 04:41:49.799
Because...

04:41:49.799 --> 04:41:50.819
Wait.

04:41:50.939 --> 04:41:53.580
Because burning it would release the same

04:41:53.580 --> 04:41:55.680
smoke that got the silk wings and leaf

04:41:55.680 --> 04:41:56.819
wings of the snarling river.

04:41:56.880 --> 04:41:58.319
It would be toxic.

04:41:58.439 --> 04:42:01.200
It would go straight into my brain, and

04:42:01.200 --> 04:42:02.099
if I burned too much.

04:42:02.159 --> 04:42:04.919
The smoke could rise and get the others

04:42:04.919 --> 04:42:06.240
beyond the abyss as well.

04:42:06.299 --> 04:42:09.119
She clasped her front talons together

04:42:09.119 --> 04:42:10.680
suddenly terrified.

04:42:10.740 --> 04:42:11.939
Cricket!

04:42:12.000 --> 04:42:14.459
Luna shouted at the blocked exit.

04:42:14.520 --> 04:42:15.840
Ren, Bryany.

04:42:15.959 --> 04:42:17.759
Oh, yes.

04:42:17.880 --> 04:42:21.180
Please do bring them closer.

04:42:21.240 --> 04:42:22.979
The voice chuckled.

04:42:23.040 --> 04:42:26.639
I would like all those pretty dragons to

04:42:26.639 --> 04:42:27.060
play with.

04:42:27.119 --> 04:42:29.819
And the sparky humans too.

04:42:29.880 --> 04:42:31.619
This guardian is the worst.

04:42:31.680 --> 04:42:33.720
It suddenly roared again.

04:42:33.779 --> 04:42:36.599
I demand another, and nobody listens.

04:42:36.659 --> 04:42:38.880
My worshipers have betrayed me.

04:42:38.939 --> 04:42:43.200
The guardian shrieked, dropped dusky, and

04:42:43.200 --> 04:42:45.180
threw his hairy arms over his head.

04:42:45.240 --> 04:42:48.840
Dusky scrambled away from him, and pelted

04:42:48.840 --> 04:42:50.220
across the vines that covered the floor.

04:42:50.279 --> 04:42:53.700
He stopped below Luna, and reached up

04:42:53.700 --> 04:42:55.799
toward her, with a heartbreaking look on

04:42:55.799 --> 04:42:56.400
his face.

04:42:56.700 --> 04:42:59.520
Muna, help me, he wailed.

04:42:59.580 --> 04:43:01.740
She swooped down to pick him up.

04:43:01.860 --> 04:43:06.360
But as her talons touched his, vines shot

04:43:06.360 --> 04:43:08.880
up from the tangle, snapping around her

04:43:08.880 --> 04:43:09.720
wrists and ankles.

04:43:09.779 --> 04:43:13.200
Dusky's eyes went blank, and he yanked

04:43:13.200 --> 04:43:15.299
her down toward him, and more vines

04:43:15.299 --> 04:43:18.000
surged up to ensnare her neck, her tail

04:43:18.000 --> 04:43:18.659
her wings.

04:43:18.720 --> 04:43:22.680
Luna tried to scream for help, but a vine

04:43:22.680 --> 04:43:24.659
looped around her snout and pinned it

04:43:24.659 --> 04:43:24.900
shut.

04:43:24.959 --> 04:43:28.860
She was trapped, like an insect in a

04:43:28.860 --> 04:43:32.340
spider web, and the spider was casting

04:43:32.340 --> 04:43:35.279
its poisonous haze across her mind, and

04:43:35.279 --> 04:43:37.919
all around her, the throne room faded

04:43:37.919 --> 04:43:38.159
away.

04:43:38.220 --> 04:43:42.900
Chapter 14.

04:43:43.080 --> 04:43:46.139
Luna opened her eyes.

04:43:46.200 --> 04:43:48.840
She was standing on the slope of a

04:43:48.840 --> 04:43:51.599
mountain, in bright daylight, surrounded

04:43:51.599 --> 04:43:52.439
by pine trees.

04:43:52.500 --> 04:43:53.819
What?

04:43:53.880 --> 04:43:57.180
She blinked, but the pine trees were

04:43:57.180 --> 04:43:57.540
still there.

04:43:57.599 --> 04:43:59.580
She held up her talons.

04:43:59.639 --> 04:44:01.500
They looked like hers.

04:44:01.560 --> 04:44:03.360
She felt like herself.

04:44:03.419 --> 04:44:06.540
She did not feel like she was drowning in

04:44:06.540 --> 04:44:07.139
evil vines.

04:44:07.259 --> 04:44:10.619
Is this an evil vine hallucination?

04:44:10.680 --> 04:44:13.560
It felt awfully real.

04:44:13.619 --> 04:44:15.900
If it is a hallucination.

04:44:15.959 --> 04:44:17.340
Why is it happening?

04:44:17.400 --> 04:44:19.259
For a moment.

04:44:19.319 --> 04:44:22.200
She stared at the trees, but they didn't

04:44:22.200 --> 04:44:23.819
seem to have any sinister intentions.

04:44:23.880 --> 04:44:27.060
They swayed gently, looking the very

04:44:27.060 --> 04:44:28.200
opposite of suspicious.

04:44:28.259 --> 04:44:31.979
Their whole aura radiated, nope, not

04:44:31.979 --> 04:44:33.119
interested in eating your brain.

04:44:33.240 --> 04:44:36.240
Something was sitting on her foot.

04:44:36.299 --> 04:44:38.639
Luna glanced down.

04:44:38.700 --> 04:44:40.200
It was dusky.

04:44:40.259 --> 04:44:43.680
But he had his eyes squeezed shut, and

04:44:43.680 --> 04:44:45.659
his little arms and tail clamped around

04:44:45.659 --> 04:44:46.020
her leg.

04:44:46.139 --> 04:44:50.159
He was so small, smaller even than most 2

04:44:50.159 --> 04:44:51.240
year old dragonettes.

04:44:51.299 --> 04:44:53.939
Any idea where we are?

04:44:54.000 --> 04:44:55.139
She asked him.

04:44:55.200 --> 04:44:57.779
He shook his head mutely.

04:44:57.840 --> 04:45:00.000
She thought about pointing out that he

04:45:00.000 --> 04:45:01.860
might have a better chance of guessing if

04:45:01.860 --> 04:45:03.659
he actually opened his eyes and looked

04:45:03.659 --> 04:45:05.880
but she decided he was already stressed

04:45:05.880 --> 04:45:06.180
enough.

04:45:06.240 --> 04:45:09.360
And this certainly didn't look like the

04:45:09.360 --> 04:45:10.439
Pentala they knew.

04:45:10.500 --> 04:45:13.799
It looked more like the dragon colony

04:45:13.799 --> 04:45:16.439
Luna had visited in Pyria, the one called

04:45:16.439 --> 04:45:19.560
Sanctuary, which was surrounded by pine

04:45:19.560 --> 04:45:20.400
forest like this.

04:45:20.520 --> 04:45:24.240
Except here, there were no dragons in any

04:45:24.240 --> 04:45:26.340
direction, as far as she could see.

04:45:26.459 --> 04:45:29.220
She spotted an overlook beyond the

04:45:29.220 --> 04:45:29.520
trees.

04:45:29.580 --> 04:45:32.939
Luna paced over to it, dragging Duske

04:45:32.939 --> 04:45:33.419
along with her.

04:45:33.479 --> 04:45:34.919
Which was not difficult.

04:45:34.979 --> 04:45:37.080
He seemed to weigh no more than a pine

04:45:37.080 --> 04:45:37.979
cone.

04:45:38.040 --> 04:45:40.259
They gazed down at the land below them.

04:45:40.380 --> 04:45:43.619
Muna had expected to see a continent

04:45:43.619 --> 04:45:44.700
choked with vines.

04:45:44.819 --> 04:45:47.099
She'd thought she'd find the breath of

04:45:47.099 --> 04:45:49.259
evil plant spreading from here to the

04:45:49.259 --> 04:45:49.740
horizon.

04:45:49.799 --> 04:45:52.319
She wouldn't have been surprised to

04:45:52.319 --> 04:45:54.599
discover that she'd been unconscious and

04:45:54.599 --> 04:45:57.299
mind controlled for years, and this was a

04:45:57.299 --> 04:45:59.220
future where the plan had won and taken

04:45:59.220 --> 04:45:59.819
over everything.

04:45:59.880 --> 04:46:03.900
But what she saw instead was far more

04:46:03.900 --> 04:46:04.560
mystifying.

04:46:04.619 --> 04:46:07.319
The landscape below her looked.

04:46:07.380 --> 04:46:09.779
Strangely organized.

04:46:09.840 --> 04:46:12.779
It was partitioned into squares and

04:46:12.779 --> 04:46:15.840
rectangles and ovals, with long, flat

04:46:15.840 --> 04:46:17.220
lines running between all of them.

04:46:17.279 --> 04:46:20.459
Many of the sections contained cubic

04:46:20.459 --> 04:46:23.880
structures, giant boxes with ornate roofs

04:46:23.880 --> 04:46:25.740
or taller, tower like things.

04:46:25.799 --> 04:46:30.900
It's like a hive, Luna realized, spotting

04:46:30.900 --> 04:46:32.520
an arrangement of roofs around an open

04:46:32.520 --> 04:46:34.080
square that might be a market.

04:46:34.139 --> 04:46:37.619
Except all the layers are spread out next

04:46:37.619 --> 04:46:40.020
to each other, instead of stacked on top

04:46:40.020 --> 04:46:40.560
of one another.

04:46:40.619 --> 04:46:43.979
Some of the areas were for growing food

04:46:43.979 --> 04:46:46.860
plants, as far as she could tell, like

04:46:46.860 --> 04:46:49.500
the hive greenhouses, but open to the air

04:46:49.500 --> 04:46:50.939
and much bigger.

04:46:51.000 --> 04:46:53.099
Those seem to be arranged around the

04:46:53.099 --> 04:46:55.740
outer edges, while the intersections were

04:46:55.740 --> 04:46:58.139
crammed with cubes and towers, and

04:46:58.139 --> 04:47:00.360
stepped temples, and stone paved

04:47:00.360 --> 04:47:01.020
courtyards.

04:47:01.080 --> 04:47:03.119
Dusky?

04:47:03.180 --> 04:47:05.520
Luna said, nudging him with her snout.

04:47:05.580 --> 04:47:07.080
What are we looking at?

04:47:07.139 --> 04:47:09.360
Does this look at all familiar to you?

04:47:09.419 --> 04:47:11.580
He shook his head again.

04:47:11.639 --> 04:47:14.040
Luna scanned the sky.

04:47:14.099 --> 04:47:16.439
I still don't see any dragons.

04:47:16.500 --> 04:47:17.939
Isn't that odd?

04:47:18.000 --> 04:47:20.520
Did they all live in the flattened out

04:47:20.520 --> 04:47:21.000
hives?

04:47:21.119 --> 04:47:24.419
She dropped her gaze again, and realized

04:47:24.419 --> 04:47:26.040
that there were shapes moving among the

04:47:26.040 --> 04:47:28.259
structures, and along the long, flat

04:47:28.259 --> 04:47:29.340
lines.

04:47:29.400 --> 04:47:31.619
They were so small from here that they

04:47:31.619 --> 04:47:33.299
looked more like ants than anything

04:47:33.299 --> 04:47:33.540
else.

04:47:33.599 --> 04:47:36.060
But she didn't think they were dragons.

04:47:36.119 --> 04:47:38.279
They didn't move like dragons.

04:47:38.340 --> 04:47:40.799
None of them were flying, and they

04:47:40.799 --> 04:47:41.639
weren't shaped right.

04:47:41.700 --> 04:47:45.060
She tried extending her antennae all the

04:47:45.060 --> 04:47:46.740
way to see if she could pick up any

04:47:46.740 --> 04:47:47.099
clues.

04:47:47.159 --> 04:47:50.040
The only vibrations in the sky overhead

04:47:50.040 --> 04:47:51.000
came from birds.

04:47:51.060 --> 04:47:54.240
The largest was a hawk, drifting lazily

04:47:54.240 --> 04:47:54.959
far above them.

04:47:55.080 --> 04:47:57.599
But somewhere nearby.

04:47:57.659 --> 04:47:59.880
Were those voices?

04:47:59.939 --> 04:48:02.400
They were pitched a little too high and

04:48:02.400 --> 04:48:04.319
fast, not dragons.

04:48:04.380 --> 04:48:05.880
Humans.

04:48:05.939 --> 04:48:09.900
Luna scooped Dusky into her arms and flew

04:48:09.900 --> 04:48:12.180
up into one of the trees, perching on a

04:48:12.180 --> 04:48:13.500
branch where the needles were thick

04:48:13.500 --> 04:48:15.419
enough to hide her from the ground.

04:48:15.479 --> 04:48:18.900
Not that she was afraid of the humans

04:48:18.900 --> 04:48:19.439
exactly.

04:48:19.500 --> 04:48:22.080
But after seeing the guardian, and the

04:48:22.080 --> 04:48:24.119
one on the throne, she thought she might

04:48:24.119 --> 04:48:26.220
want to keep her distance until she could

04:48:26.220 --> 04:48:27.840
tell which kind of humans these were.

04:48:27.900 --> 04:48:31.919
There were 4 of them, slouching and

04:48:31.919 --> 04:48:34.439
swaggering up the mountain, balking into

04:48:34.439 --> 04:48:36.720
one another, and shouting, and breaking

04:48:36.720 --> 04:48:38.580
twigs off the trees they passed.

04:48:38.639 --> 04:48:41.939
One of them stopped, picked up a rock, and

04:48:41.939 --> 04:48:43.319
hurled it at a nearby tree.

04:48:43.380 --> 04:48:46.380
When it thunked against the bark, he

04:48:46.380 --> 04:48:48.000
shouted, that's right.

04:48:48.060 --> 04:48:50.700
And then 2 of the others scrambled around

04:48:50.700 --> 04:48:52.020
to grab rocks and do the same.

04:48:52.080 --> 04:48:55.860
The last human rolled his eyes and sat

04:48:55.860 --> 04:48:57.959
down on one of the boulders, stretching

04:48:57.959 --> 04:48:58.439
out his legs.

04:48:58.500 --> 04:49:00.599
So impressive.

04:49:00.659 --> 04:49:03.479
He said, you can hit trees with rocks.

04:49:03.540 --> 04:49:05.459
Someone should make you all emperor.

04:49:05.520 --> 04:49:08.639
The 1st rock thrower grinned and strutted

04:49:08.639 --> 04:49:10.619
in a circle, holding out his arms to the

04:49:10.619 --> 04:49:11.340
watching trees.

04:49:11.400 --> 04:49:15.479
Not all of us, he said, just me, Emperor

04:49:15.479 --> 04:49:16.200
Coyote.

04:49:16.259 --> 04:49:17.819
Wait.

04:49:17.880 --> 04:49:20.759
A shock is zipped through Luna from snout

04:49:20.759 --> 04:49:21.180
to tail.

04:49:21.240 --> 04:49:22.979
I can understand them.

04:49:23.040 --> 04:49:25.560
They're speaking human, but I can

04:49:25.560 --> 04:49:26.040
understand them.

04:49:26.099 --> 04:49:29.520
This had to be a hallucination then.

04:49:29.580 --> 04:49:32.279
She hadn't magically learned human while

04:49:32.279 --> 04:49:33.779
flying around under the vine's mind

04:49:33.779 --> 04:49:34.200
control.

04:49:34.259 --> 04:49:37.439
Such a weird hallucination, though.

04:49:37.500 --> 04:49:42.360
I'd be a better emperor than you, shouted

04:49:42.360 --> 04:49:44.340
one of the other humans, leaping on the

04:49:44.340 --> 04:49:45.000
1st one's back.

04:49:45.060 --> 04:49:47.580
They tuzzled for a moment, yelling

04:49:47.580 --> 04:49:51.599
Emperor Coyote, and no, Emperor Argyle

04:49:51.599 --> 04:49:54.000
and ended up on the ground in a flailing

04:49:54.000 --> 04:49:54.900
pile of limbs.

04:49:54.959 --> 04:49:57.779
These humans were so loud.

04:49:57.840 --> 04:50:00.959
Luna had not seen any like these before.

04:50:01.020 --> 04:50:04.020
The other humans she'd met were careful

04:50:04.020 --> 04:50:06.479
and quiet, slipping around the edges of

04:50:06.479 --> 04:50:08.400
the world so they wouldn't get caught or

04:50:08.400 --> 04:50:11.580
eaten, even Wren, who seemed fearless

04:50:11.580 --> 04:50:14.220
still held herself in a watchful, cautious

04:50:14.220 --> 04:50:16.439
way, as though she might need to dart to

04:50:16.439 --> 04:50:18.599
safety, or fight off an attack at any

04:50:18.599 --> 04:50:18.779
moment.

04:50:18.840 --> 04:50:22.319
These 4, though, took up all the space

04:50:22.319 --> 04:50:24.659
and all the air, and filled it without

04:50:24.659 --> 04:50:25.979
hesitation.

04:50:26.040 --> 04:50:27.240
They never checked the sky.

04:50:27.360 --> 04:50:29.580
They never looked around to see if

04:50:29.580 --> 04:50:30.419
anything was coming for them.

04:50:30.479 --> 04:50:33.299
They acted like it had never occurred to

04:50:33.299 --> 04:50:34.560
them that something might eat them.

04:50:34.619 --> 04:50:37.619
As though dragons didn't even exist.

04:50:37.680 --> 04:50:39.959
Luna shivered.

04:50:40.020 --> 04:50:43.799
Do dragons exist in this strange place?

04:50:43.919 --> 04:50:45.180
She wondered.

04:50:45.240 --> 04:50:46.919
Why haven't I seen any?

04:50:47.040 --> 04:50:50.220
The one on the rock rolled his eyes at

04:50:50.220 --> 04:50:51.720
the scuffling humans on the ground.

04:50:51.779 --> 04:50:55.259
Very regal behavior, he said.

04:50:55.319 --> 04:50:58.619
The 1st one shoved his friend away and

04:50:58.619 --> 04:50:59.939
bounced back to his feet again.

04:51:00.000 --> 04:51:03.240
There are 3 empires, he said with a

04:51:03.240 --> 04:51:03.599
shrug.

04:51:03.659 --> 04:51:05.040
We can each have one.

04:51:05.159 --> 04:51:08.520
He waved at the other two. casually

04:51:08.520 --> 04:51:09.540
excluding the one on the rock.

04:51:09.599 --> 04:51:14.159
If this plan works, said his seated

04:51:14.159 --> 04:51:17.880
friend, coldly, Luna thought, then there

04:51:17.880 --> 04:51:20.400
will be only one empire left, and only

04:51:20.400 --> 04:51:22.680
one emperor over this whole continent.

04:51:22.740 --> 04:51:26.459
He stood up, brushing pine needles off

04:51:26.459 --> 04:51:28.319
the long, silky outer wrapping he was

04:51:28.319 --> 04:51:28.500
wearing.

04:51:28.560 --> 04:51:31.919
They all wore similar wrapping, Luna

04:51:31.919 --> 04:51:34.560
noticed, fancier, cleaner, and more

04:51:34.560 --> 04:51:36.540
elegant than anything the humans she knew

04:51:36.540 --> 04:51:36.840
wore.

04:51:36.900 --> 04:51:40.139
Little swirls of silver thread decorated

04:51:40.139 --> 04:51:42.000
the edges of the wrappings and delicate

04:51:42.000 --> 04:51:43.080
filigree patterns.

04:51:43.139 --> 04:51:45.840
These wrappings did not look like they

04:51:45.840 --> 04:51:47.520
would work very well for climbing trees

04:51:47.520 --> 04:51:48.000
in a hurry.

04:51:48.060 --> 04:51:53.400
This plan is ridiculous cottonmouth, said

04:51:53.400 --> 04:51:54.299
the bossy one.

04:51:54.360 --> 04:51:56.159
He started to lead the way up the slope

04:51:56.159 --> 04:51:56.459
again.

04:51:56.520 --> 04:51:58.979
Nobody's seen a dragon in at least a

04:51:58.979 --> 04:51:59.159
year.

04:51:59.220 --> 04:52:01.139
Nobody has any idea where they live.

04:52:01.200 --> 04:52:04.860
Luna barely stopped to gasp from escaping

04:52:04.860 --> 04:52:05.040
her.

04:52:05.099 --> 04:52:07.380
They're looking for dragons.

04:52:07.439 --> 04:52:10.139
Why haven't they seen one in a year?

04:52:10.200 --> 04:52:11.880
Where is everybody?

04:52:11.939 --> 04:52:15.900
She wanted to follow them, but she was a

04:52:15.900 --> 04:52:17.459
little nervous about what these humans

04:52:17.459 --> 04:52:18.240
would do if they saw her.

04:52:18.360 --> 04:52:21.479
She thought for a moment, then climbed

04:52:21.479 --> 04:52:23.220
higher up the tree and along a branch

04:52:23.220 --> 04:52:26.159
into the next one, with Dusky clinging to

04:52:26.159 --> 04:52:26.520
her neck.

04:52:26.580 --> 04:52:29.700
Her childhood in the webs around Cicada

04:52:29.700 --> 04:52:32.400
Hive meant she had no trouble clambering

04:52:32.400 --> 04:52:34.200
and leaping nimbly from one tree to the

04:52:34.200 --> 04:52:34.439
next.

04:52:34.500 --> 04:52:37.259
And the absolute racket the humans

04:52:37.259 --> 04:52:39.299
generated made it easy to follow them.

04:52:39.360 --> 04:52:42.119
She was pretty sure they wouldn't hear

04:52:42.119 --> 04:52:44.639
her, even if she slipped and crashed all

04:52:44.639 --> 04:52:45.659
the way to the forest floor.

04:52:45.720 --> 04:52:50.040
The humans hiked for a long time, arguing

04:52:50.040 --> 04:52:51.959
cheerfully about some kind of ball game

04:52:51.959 --> 04:52:54.840
before finally stopping to rest, not far

04:52:54.840 --> 04:52:55.979
from the mountain's peak.

04:52:56.040 --> 04:52:58.560
This was one of the shorter mountains in

04:52:58.560 --> 04:52:58.919
the range.

04:52:58.979 --> 04:53:00.479
Luna could now see.

04:53:00.540 --> 04:53:03.419
Much taller ones extended off to the

04:53:03.419 --> 04:53:03.659
north.

04:53:03.720 --> 04:53:06.540
Some with snow visible on the jagged

04:53:06.540 --> 04:53:08.040
claws they reached toward the sky.

04:53:08.099 --> 04:53:10.020
From here.

04:53:10.080 --> 04:53:12.659
She could also see more of the unfolded

04:53:12.659 --> 04:53:13.500
hives down below.

04:53:13.560 --> 04:53:15.840
They covered everything.

04:53:15.959 --> 04:53:19.200
Every spot of land seemed to be cordoned

04:53:19.200 --> 04:53:21.900
off, built on, growing something in

04:53:21.900 --> 04:53:24.240
straight lines or swarming with the

04:53:24.240 --> 04:53:25.139
little ant figures.

04:53:25.200 --> 04:53:27.540
Definitely not dragons.

04:53:27.599 --> 04:53:30.000
Luna was pretty sure they were humans.

04:53:30.060 --> 04:53:31.979
Human cities.

04:53:32.040 --> 04:53:37.020
Just out in the open, where anyone could

04:53:37.020 --> 04:53:39.299
swoop down and eat them, like a giant

04:53:39.299 --> 04:53:40.799
buffet set up for dragons.

04:53:40.860 --> 04:53:44.220
She wasn't even sure she was in Pyrea

04:53:44.220 --> 04:53:44.580
after all.

04:53:44.639 --> 04:53:47.279
She remembered a mountain range like this

04:53:47.279 --> 04:53:50.040
bisecting the continent, near sanctuary.

04:53:50.099 --> 04:53:52.979
But they'd flown over a vast desert to

04:53:52.979 --> 04:53:55.259
get to it, the whole kingdom of sand

04:53:55.259 --> 04:53:57.659
covering most of the territory west of

04:53:57.659 --> 04:53:58.080
the mountains.

04:53:58.139 --> 04:54:01.560
And yet, from up here, she couldn't see

04:54:01.560 --> 04:54:02.939
any sign of a desert to the west.

04:54:03.000 --> 04:54:05.939
She could see the sun slowly sinking

04:54:05.939 --> 04:54:08.099
toward the horizon, but everything in

04:54:08.099 --> 04:54:10.259
that direction was either green, or the

04:54:10.259 --> 04:54:11.939
gleaming white and gray stone of the

04:54:11.939 --> 04:54:12.659
human cities.

04:54:12.779 --> 04:54:16.080
We should get back to camp, said one of

04:54:16.080 --> 04:54:16.560
the humans.

04:54:16.619 --> 04:54:18.659
The 4 of them were sprawled around to

04:54:18.659 --> 04:54:20.700
clearing, leaning against the trees and

04:54:20.700 --> 04:54:22.200
eating snacks from the bags around their

04:54:22.200 --> 04:54:22.619
waists.

04:54:22.680 --> 04:54:25.500
There obviously aren't any dragons up

04:54:25.500 --> 04:54:27.479
here, like you predicted coyote.

04:54:27.540 --> 04:54:29.580
I know, right?

04:54:29.580 --> 04:54:31.139
said the bossy one.

04:54:31.200 --> 04:54:33.000
He tossed a net into his mouth and

04:54:33.000 --> 04:54:33.540
stretched.

04:54:33.599 --> 04:54:36.599
But we can say we checked it out, as the

04:54:36.599 --> 04:54:37.319
commander ordered.

04:54:37.380 --> 04:54:40.439
I wouldn't call this the most thorough

04:54:40.439 --> 04:54:41.580
scouting expedition.

04:54:41.639 --> 04:54:44.400
Cottonmouth said, in his flat

04:54:44.400 --> 04:54:45.180
disapproving voice.

04:54:45.299 --> 04:54:49.919
Feel free to carry on alone, Coyote said

04:54:49.919 --> 04:54:52.380
grandly, waving one hand at the rest of

04:54:52.380 --> 04:54:54.900
the mountain left above them, but I'm

04:54:54.900 --> 04:54:57.180
telling you, if there were a dragon, this

04:54:57.180 --> 04:54:59.159
close to the emperor city, we'd know

04:54:59.159 --> 04:54:59.459
about it.

04:54:59.520 --> 04:55:02.099
I bet they've run off to hide in the far

04:55:02.099 --> 04:55:02.639
north.

04:55:02.700 --> 04:55:05.220
Around the edges of the Diamond Empire.

04:55:05.279 --> 04:55:06.419
That's where they are.

04:55:06.479 --> 04:55:10.139
Fine with me, said one of the others.

04:55:10.200 --> 04:55:13.020
Maybe they'll eat the diamond army, and

04:55:13.020 --> 04:55:16.860
save us the trouble of fighting them. said

04:55:16.860 --> 04:55:17.279
his friend.

04:55:17.340 --> 04:55:19.680
I'm not scared of the diamond army.

04:55:19.740 --> 04:55:21.720
We smashed them the last time they tried

04:55:21.720 --> 04:55:22.439
to come through the pass.

04:55:22.500 --> 04:55:26.639
And they smashed us, the last time we

04:55:26.639 --> 04:55:28.139
tried to cross to their side.

04:55:28.200 --> 04:55:30.240
Cottonmouth pointed out.

04:55:30.299 --> 04:55:32.880
And they're stuck at the river border

04:55:32.880 --> 04:55:34.139
with Empress Jaguar.

04:55:34.200 --> 04:55:36.959
None of the empires can expand.

04:55:37.020 --> 04:55:40.080
We're all trapped, pushing and shoving

04:55:40.080 --> 04:55:42.360
each other back and forth, over the same

04:55:42.360 --> 04:55:43.560
few miles of territory.

04:55:43.619 --> 04:55:46.139
That's why we need a new advantage.

04:55:46.200 --> 04:55:49.020
That's what makes the emperor's plan so

04:55:49.020 --> 04:55:49.439
genius.

04:55:49.560 --> 04:55:52.979
You keep calling it the emperor's plan.

04:55:53.099 --> 04:55:54.720
Coyote scoffed.

04:55:54.779 --> 04:55:56.639
But everyone knows you're the one who

04:55:56.639 --> 04:55:57.720
slithered it into his ears.

04:55:57.840 --> 04:56:01.919
Blah, one of the others cried, throwing

04:56:01.919 --> 04:56:03.060
an orange at coyote.

04:56:03.119 --> 04:56:05.220
The human deftly snatched it out of the

04:56:05.220 --> 04:56:07.799
air, produced a knife from his boot, and

04:56:07.799 --> 04:56:08.520
started peeling it.

04:56:08.580 --> 04:56:11.700
The emperor is very wise.

04:56:11.819 --> 04:56:14.040
Cottonmouth said calmly.

04:56:14.099 --> 04:56:17.520
It is a credit to his wisdom that he

04:56:17.520 --> 04:56:19.919
listens to even his lowliest advisors.

04:56:19.979 --> 04:56:25.319
Well, I don't see how this genius plan is

04:56:25.319 --> 04:56:28.439
going to work if we can't find any

04:56:28.439 --> 04:56:31.740
dragons, said the 4th human, yawning.

04:56:31.799 --> 04:56:35.639
We will find them, Cottonmouth said.

04:56:35.700 --> 04:56:37.860
I am quite sure of that.

04:56:37.919 --> 04:56:42.299
And then, he looked up into the trees

04:56:42.299 --> 04:56:44.279
straight into Luna's eyes.

04:56:44.340 --> 04:56:48.779
Chapter 15.

04:56:49.200 --> 04:56:53.040
Luna squeaked and ducked back into the

04:56:53.040 --> 04:56:54.720
branches. her heart hammering.

04:56:54.840 --> 04:56:57.959
Dusky squeezed her neck so hard, she felt

04:56:57.959 --> 04:56:58.680
dizzy for a moment.

04:56:58.740 --> 04:57:01.020
What will they do to us?

04:57:01.080 --> 04:57:03.000
What do they want a dragon for?

04:57:03.060 --> 04:57:06.180
There was a moment of silence down below

04:57:06.180 --> 04:57:08.639
and then one of the humans laughed and

04:57:08.639 --> 04:57:10.799
said something mocking, imitating

04:57:10.799 --> 04:57:12.659
Cottonmouth's pretentious tone.

04:57:13.020 --> 04:57:15.180
Coyote and the other one laughed as well

04:57:15.180 --> 04:57:17.340
and Luna heard the sound of them getting

04:57:17.340 --> 04:57:18.959
up and bumping around noisily.

04:57:19.020 --> 04:57:22.799
She risked a peek through the needles, and

04:57:22.799 --> 04:57:24.599
saw that Cottonmouth was standing up as

04:57:24.599 --> 04:57:24.720
well.

04:57:24.840 --> 04:57:27.299
His gaze focused back on his companions.

04:57:27.360 --> 04:57:31.020
But surely he had seen her.

04:57:31.080 --> 04:57:33.240
Why hadn't he reacted?

04:57:33.240 --> 04:57:34.740
or told the others.

04:57:34.799 --> 04:57:38.819
Cheer up, Cottonmouth, Coyote said

04:57:38.819 --> 04:57:40.080
slapping him on the shoulder.

04:57:40.139 --> 04:57:42.959
I'm sure the emperor will let you chase

04:57:42.959 --> 04:57:45.000
imaginary dragons for the rest of your

04:57:45.000 --> 04:57:45.840
life if you want to.

04:57:45.900 --> 04:57:48.119
You can avoid the front line for years

04:57:48.119 --> 04:57:48.599
that way.

04:57:48.720 --> 04:57:53.459
That is not, Cottonmouth began frostily.

04:57:53.520 --> 04:57:55.799
Sure, sure.

04:57:55.860 --> 04:57:59.099
Coyote waved away his protests, and

04:57:59.099 --> 04:58:00.779
bounded off down the slope, with the

04:58:00.779 --> 04:58:01.979
other 2 close behind him.

04:58:02.040 --> 04:58:04.740
Race you back to camp, he shouted.

04:58:04.860 --> 04:58:07.560
And with another cacophony of crashing

04:58:07.560 --> 04:58:09.779
and hollering and noise, they were gone.

04:58:09.840 --> 04:58:13.200
Cottonmouth let out a soft, hissing

04:58:13.200 --> 04:58:14.340
breath and turned.

04:58:14.400 --> 04:58:16.619
Silently scanning the trees around him

04:58:16.619 --> 04:58:17.819
but not looking up.

04:58:17.819 --> 04:58:19.560
One human.

04:58:19.680 --> 04:58:22.439
Luna could take one human if she needed

04:58:22.439 --> 04:58:22.680
to.

04:58:22.740 --> 04:58:25.680
She had flame silk to defend herself

04:58:25.680 --> 04:58:26.040
with.

04:58:26.099 --> 04:58:28.860
What she really needed was answers.

04:58:28.919 --> 04:58:31.619
If she could understand human in this

04:58:31.619 --> 04:58:33.659
hallucination, could they understand

04:58:33.659 --> 04:58:34.319
dragon?

04:58:34.380 --> 04:58:36.000
Hello?

04:58:36.060 --> 04:58:37.020
She called.

04:58:37.080 --> 04:58:39.240
Cottonmouth didn't respond.

04:58:39.299 --> 04:58:41.819
He prowled away from the clearing

04:58:41.819 --> 04:58:43.979
stepping quietly over fallen branches.

04:58:44.040 --> 04:58:47.939
Luna gently tucked Dusky into a sturdy

04:58:47.939 --> 04:58:50.459
triangle of branches and whispered, stay.

04:58:50.520 --> 04:58:53.520
Then she spread her wings, and floated

04:58:53.520 --> 04:58:54.540
down from her hiding place.

04:58:54.659 --> 04:58:57.360
Hello, she called after him.

04:58:57.419 --> 04:59:00.900
Aren't I the thing you're looking for?

04:59:00.959 --> 04:59:04.500
He kept walking, as though he couldn't

04:59:04.500 --> 04:59:04.919
hear her at all.

04:59:04.979 --> 04:59:08.220
Even if he didn't understand dragon.

04:59:08.279 --> 04:59:09.119
Surely he could tell the difference

04:59:09.119 --> 04:59:11.459
between a dragon growl, and the other

04:59:11.459 --> 04:59:12.419
noises of the forest.

04:59:12.479 --> 04:59:15.659
She padded forward, and poked him in the

04:59:15.659 --> 04:59:16.560
back with one talon.

04:59:16.680 --> 04:59:18.779
Zero reaction.

04:59:18.840 --> 04:59:21.720
He didn't turn, didn't flinch, or jump.

04:59:21.779 --> 04:59:24.000
Can you not see me?

04:59:24.060 --> 04:59:26.040
Luna asked, or hear me?

04:59:26.099 --> 04:59:27.119
Really?

04:59:27.180 --> 04:59:29.580
She darted around in front of him and

04:59:29.580 --> 04:59:30.599
waved her wings.

04:59:30.659 --> 04:59:33.840
He walked straight through her.

04:59:33.900 --> 04:59:35.580
Yar!

04:59:35.639 --> 04:59:36.659
Luna shouted.

04:59:36.720 --> 04:59:40.200
It didn't hurt, but it was so weird.

04:59:40.259 --> 04:59:43.860
She held up her talons and examined them

04:59:43.860 --> 04:59:44.400
frantically.

04:59:44.459 --> 04:59:46.740
They were there.

04:59:46.799 --> 04:59:48.180
She could see them.

04:59:48.299 --> 04:59:50.880
And she could touch things like trees and

04:59:50.880 --> 04:59:51.419
dusky.

04:59:51.479 --> 04:59:54.360
So how did she not exist at all for this

04:59:54.360 --> 04:59:54.540
human?

04:59:54.599 --> 04:59:58.259
It was like being invisible, but a

04:59:58.259 --> 04:59:59.279
different kind of terrible.

04:59:59.340 --> 05:00:02.819
She hurried back to Desky and sat in the

05:00:02.819 --> 05:00:05.040
tree for a moment, cuddling him in her

05:00:05.040 --> 05:00:06.540
arms so at least something would be

05:00:06.540 --> 05:00:06.779
real.

05:00:06.840 --> 05:00:10.020
Dusky, where are we?

05:00:10.080 --> 05:00:11.099
Luna asked.

05:00:11.159 --> 05:00:12.479
Why is this happening?

05:00:12.540 --> 05:00:15.360
Dusky looked up at the sky.

05:00:15.419 --> 05:00:18.419
And when Luna followed his gaze, she saw

05:00:18.419 --> 05:00:20.819
a dark shadow, descending rapidly from

05:00:20.819 --> 05:00:21.419
the clouds.

05:00:21.479 --> 05:00:24.840
It rolled over them like fog, like the

05:00:24.840 --> 05:00:27.060
entire world blinking, and when it

05:00:27.060 --> 05:00:28.860
cleared, they were somewhere else

05:00:28.860 --> 05:00:29.159
entirely.

05:00:29.220 --> 05:00:33.180
It was still a mountain, but a higher

05:00:33.180 --> 05:00:35.939
colder one above the tree line, with

05:00:35.939 --> 05:00:37.919
scatterings of snow dusting several of

05:00:37.919 --> 05:00:38.520
the boulders.

05:00:38.580 --> 05:00:41.939
They materialized nearly on top of a

05:00:41.939 --> 05:00:45.000
mountain goat, but like cotton mouth, it

05:00:45.000 --> 05:00:46.979
stared right through them, chewing

05:00:46.979 --> 05:00:47.700
placidly.

05:00:48.060 --> 05:00:50.580
Humans were also scattered throughout the

05:00:50.580 --> 05:00:53.340
boulders, and for a moment, Luna thought

05:00:53.340 --> 05:00:55.020
they were all dead because they were

05:00:55.020 --> 05:00:55.860
lying so still.

05:00:55.919 --> 05:00:58.439
But then one raised his head briefly

05:00:58.439 --> 05:01:00.360
before ducking back down, and she

05:01:00.360 --> 05:01:01.860
realized they were hiding from

05:01:01.860 --> 05:01:02.099
something.

05:01:02.159 --> 05:01:04.319
Oh.

05:01:04.380 --> 05:01:06.959
Probably from the giant cave, they were

05:01:06.959 --> 05:01:10.200
all looking at, or rather, from the thing

05:01:10.200 --> 05:01:12.840
inside the giant cave, that was rumbling

05:01:12.840 --> 05:01:14.939
and growling and emitting trails of

05:01:14.939 --> 05:01:15.119
smoke.

05:01:15.180 --> 05:01:17.459
They found a dragon.

05:01:17.520 --> 05:01:20.040
I wonder if the dragon will be able to

05:01:20.040 --> 05:01:20.819
see or hear me.

05:01:20.880 --> 05:01:25.319
The growls grew louder, as the dragon in

05:01:25.319 --> 05:01:26.639
the cave approached the entrance.

05:01:26.700 --> 05:01:30.299
She poked her head out, yawned, and

05:01:30.299 --> 05:01:31.380
sniffed suspiciously.

05:01:31.439 --> 05:01:35.520
She wasn't a very big dragon, not very

05:01:35.520 --> 05:01:36.540
much bigger than Luna.

05:01:36.599 --> 05:01:39.599
She had 2 wings, and her scales were

05:01:39.599 --> 05:01:42.180
orange, with lemon yellow under scales.

05:01:42.240 --> 05:01:44.939
Small flames flickered in her mouth as

05:01:44.939 --> 05:01:45.659
she yawned.

05:01:45.720 --> 05:01:49.020
She seemed muted somehow, like an

05:01:49.020 --> 05:01:50.520
undercooked version of a dragon.

05:01:50.639 --> 05:01:54.299
I hope they don't hurt her, Luna thought

05:01:54.299 --> 05:01:56.400
anxiously, glancing at the humans.

05:01:56.459 --> 05:01:58.979
They were all holding sharp, pointy

05:01:58.979 --> 05:02:01.200
things, and looked very intent on

05:02:01.200 --> 05:02:01.380
something.

05:02:01.439 --> 05:02:05.040
Be careful, Luna called.

05:02:05.099 --> 05:02:07.020
Dragon, can you hear me?

05:02:07.080 --> 05:02:09.419
There are humans here, and I think

05:02:09.419 --> 05:02:10.200
they're planning something.

05:02:10.259 --> 05:02:13.500
But the dragon's eyes passed right over

05:02:13.500 --> 05:02:16.080
her, and nobody reacted to her voice

05:02:16.080 --> 05:02:17.159
except Dusky.

05:02:17.220 --> 05:02:19.619
He burrowed into her neck and whimpered.

05:02:19.680 --> 05:02:22.200
I told you humans are scary.

05:02:22.259 --> 05:02:25.979
The orange dragon stretched her wings and

05:02:25.979 --> 05:02:27.000
lifted up into the sky.

05:02:27.060 --> 05:02:30.119
She circled for a few heartbeats, while

05:02:30.119 --> 05:02:32.520
the humans stayed frozen, and then she

05:02:32.520 --> 05:02:34.860
flew off toward the east, lit by the

05:02:34.860 --> 05:02:35.639
rising sun.

05:02:35.700 --> 05:02:39.540
Now, one of the humans called in a low

05:02:39.540 --> 05:02:39.720
voice.

05:02:39.779 --> 05:02:43.080
The 3 humans nearest the cave, leaped out

05:02:43.080 --> 05:02:45.119
from their hiding places, and ran full

05:02:45.119 --> 05:02:47.099
tilt into the dark opening.

05:02:47.159 --> 05:02:49.319
Luna realized that one of them was

05:02:49.319 --> 05:02:49.979
coyote.

05:02:50.040 --> 05:02:52.860
But he looked older, more aligned and

05:02:52.860 --> 05:02:53.340
grizzled.

05:02:53.459 --> 05:02:56.400
Several long moments passed.

05:02:56.459 --> 05:02:59.220
The human who'd spoken climbed over his

05:02:59.220 --> 05:03:01.560
rock and darted closer to the cave

05:03:01.560 --> 05:03:04.500
staying near cover, and Luna saw that it

05:03:04.500 --> 05:03:05.340
was cottonmouth.

05:03:05.400 --> 05:03:08.759
He also looked older, with a new scar

05:03:08.759 --> 05:03:10.619
cross one temple and longer hair.

05:03:10.680 --> 05:03:13.200
The wrappings on these humans looked

05:03:13.200 --> 05:03:15.540
rougher too, like they'd been dragged

05:03:15.540 --> 05:03:18.060
through thorn bushes, with no silver

05:03:18.060 --> 05:03:19.020
filigrees this time.

05:03:19.080 --> 05:03:22.319
But Cottonmouth had new gold medallions

05:03:22.319 --> 05:03:24.540
on each shoulder of his cloak, and a

05:03:24.540 --> 05:03:26.159
bright green feather tied into his brown

05:03:26.159 --> 05:03:27.360
hair with gold thread.

05:03:27.479 --> 05:03:30.479
He stared at the cave, as though he could

05:03:30.479 --> 05:03:31.919
drag something out of it with the force

05:03:31.919 --> 05:03:33.180
of his eyeballs.

05:03:33.240 --> 05:03:37.200
And then, finally, the 3 humans came back

05:03:37.200 --> 05:03:37.860
out of the cave.

05:03:37.919 --> 05:03:41.220
Two had their swords drawn, watching the

05:03:41.220 --> 05:03:41.400
sky.

05:03:41.459 --> 05:03:45.180
Coyote walked between them. carrying a

05:03:45.180 --> 05:03:46.439
dragon egg in his arms.

05:03:46.500 --> 05:03:49.860
A slow smile spread across Cottonmouth's

05:03:49.860 --> 05:03:50.099
face.

05:03:50.159 --> 05:03:53.099
He waved another trio of humans forward

05:03:53.099 --> 05:03:55.979
carrying a box, and Coyote slid the egg

05:03:55.979 --> 05:03:57.180
into the padded interior.

05:03:57.240 --> 05:03:59.400
I knew it.

05:03:59.459 --> 05:04:02.580
Cottonmouth said, bending over the egg.

05:04:02.700 --> 05:04:05.400
He brushed his paws over the eggshell.

05:04:05.459 --> 05:04:07.020
Yeah, yeah.

05:04:07.080 --> 05:04:08.400
Coyote said.

05:04:08.459 --> 05:04:09.240
You were right.

05:04:09.299 --> 05:04:11.099
The emperor will be thrilled.

05:04:11.159 --> 05:04:14.159
How many eggs were in the nest?

05:04:14.220 --> 05:04:15.659
Cottonmouth asked.

05:04:15.720 --> 05:04:19.380
Three, answered one of the other humans

05:04:19.380 --> 05:04:21.840
missing the warning look coyote shot at

05:04:21.840 --> 05:04:22.020
him.

05:04:22.080 --> 05:04:24.479
Cottonmouth stood up and looked into

05:04:24.479 --> 05:04:25.439
Coyote's eyes.

05:04:25.560 --> 05:04:27.479
Go get the other two.

05:04:27.540 --> 05:04:30.540
Whoa, Coyote said.

05:04:30.599 --> 05:04:32.220
I thought the plan was to start with

05:04:32.220 --> 05:04:32.459
one.

05:04:32.580 --> 05:04:36.419
I want them all, Cottonmouth said.

05:04:36.479 --> 05:04:38.459
Go get them, now.

05:04:38.520 --> 05:04:41.759
But, sir, said the human on coyotes

05:04:41.759 --> 05:04:42.180
left.

05:04:42.240 --> 05:04:43.799
Won't that make the dragon angry?

05:04:43.860 --> 05:04:46.139
I thought the scholars said they might

05:04:46.139 --> 05:04:47.279
not miss one, but...

05:04:47.279 --> 05:04:49.979
Cottonmouth turned and stabbed him

05:04:49.979 --> 05:04:51.180
through the stomach in one swift

05:04:51.180 --> 05:04:51.599
movement.

05:04:51.659 --> 05:04:54.000
The human gurgled and fell over.

05:04:54.060 --> 05:04:57.360
Luna covered Dusky's eyes just a moment

05:04:57.360 --> 05:04:57.959
too late.

05:04:58.020 --> 05:05:00.419
She could feel him shuddering all through

05:05:00.419 --> 05:05:01.020
her scales.

05:05:01.080 --> 05:05:05.340
Fine, Coyote said, throwing up his

05:05:05.340 --> 05:05:05.580
hands.

05:05:05.639 --> 05:05:07.979
He turned and stalked back into the

05:05:07.979 --> 05:05:08.340
cave.

05:05:08.400 --> 05:05:11.580
Cottonmouth gestured, and 3 other humans

05:05:11.580 --> 05:05:13.619
ran after him, while the rest of the

05:05:13.619 --> 05:05:15.119
troop produced 2 more boxes.

05:05:15.180 --> 05:05:19.139
Luna closed her own eyes, as the 2

05:05:19.139 --> 05:05:21.060
remaining dragon eggs were lowered into

05:05:21.060 --> 05:05:21.540
the boxes.

05:05:21.599 --> 05:05:25.439
That poor orange dragon, she thought.

05:05:25.500 --> 05:05:28.139
She'll come back from hunting, and all

05:05:28.139 --> 05:05:28.979
her eggs will be gone.

05:05:29.040 --> 05:05:30.840
I wish I could save them.

05:05:30.959 --> 05:05:33.240
What are the humans going to do with

05:05:33.240 --> 05:05:33.419
them?

05:05:33.540 --> 05:05:36.540
Dusky, she whispered.

05:05:36.599 --> 05:05:39.000
I think this has something to do with the

05:05:39.000 --> 05:05:40.560
human and the dragonette we saw.

05:05:40.619 --> 05:05:43.080
But I don't understand how it's connected

05:05:43.080 --> 05:05:44.639
to the plant and the other mind.

05:05:44.700 --> 05:05:47.880
Maybe the shadow would take them to the

05:05:47.880 --> 05:05:49.740
next part of the story, if they kept

05:05:49.740 --> 05:05:50.099
watching.

05:05:50.159 --> 05:05:53.040
She took a deep breath and opened her

05:05:53.040 --> 05:05:53.400
eyes again.

05:05:53.459 --> 05:05:57.599
They were on an island beach now, their

05:05:57.599 --> 05:05:59.459
talons sinking into hot sand.

05:05:59.520 --> 05:06:02.400
The island was small, curving around a

05:06:02.400 --> 05:06:04.439
bright little bay, the water blue and

05:06:04.439 --> 05:06:04.979
shimmering.

05:06:05.040 --> 05:06:08.400
In the shallows, 2 dragon eggs rested in

05:06:08.400 --> 05:06:10.619
a rock pool, mostly underwater.

05:06:10.680 --> 05:06:14.880
Oh no, Luna whispered, pressing her claws

05:06:14.880 --> 05:06:15.540
to her snout.

05:06:15.599 --> 05:06:17.400
It was already too late.

05:06:17.520 --> 05:06:19.860
A group of humans were gathered around

05:06:19.860 --> 05:06:22.680
the rock pool, lifting the eggs into snug

05:06:22.680 --> 05:06:24.900
jars full of seawater and padded with

05:06:24.900 --> 05:06:25.319
kelp.

05:06:25.439 --> 05:06:28.439
Cottonmouth and Coyote were not with

05:06:28.439 --> 05:06:28.619
them.

05:06:28.680 --> 05:06:31.080
These humans looked slightly different.

05:06:31.139 --> 05:06:34.139
They wore sleek dark fur pelts over their

05:06:34.139 --> 05:06:36.540
seal brown skin, and their hair with

05:06:36.540 --> 05:06:37.680
shades of blue and green.

05:06:37.740 --> 05:06:41.340
One wore a simple silver headband, with a

05:06:41.340 --> 05:06:42.840
jaguar symbol in the center of her

05:06:42.840 --> 05:06:43.139
forehead.

05:06:43.200 --> 05:06:45.599
Quickly, she snapped.

05:06:45.659 --> 05:06:47.939
That sea dragon could return any minute.

05:06:48.000 --> 05:06:50.880
That's what all these warriors with

05:06:50.880 --> 05:06:51.779
spears are for.

05:06:51.840 --> 05:06:53.700
Grumbled the human next tour.

05:06:53.759 --> 05:06:56.220
There's no need to kill them if we don't

05:06:56.220 --> 05:06:58.380
have to, said the Jaguar lady.

05:06:58.439 --> 05:07:00.599
The empress said stealth.

05:07:00.659 --> 05:07:02.700
She said, don't let them know it was

05:07:02.700 --> 05:07:03.599
humans who took them.

05:07:03.659 --> 05:07:06.479
She pointed to the sand near the rock

05:07:06.479 --> 05:07:06.900
pool.

05:07:06.959 --> 05:07:09.599
Wipe away those footprints before we go.

05:07:09.659 --> 05:07:12.840
Luna thought this was fairly ridiculous.

05:07:12.900 --> 05:07:15.599
Surely any dragon could smell the heavy

05:07:15.599 --> 05:07:17.279
scent of human this many would leave

05:07:17.279 --> 05:07:19.560
behind, even hours later.

05:07:19.740 --> 05:07:22.500
Are the other empires being this

05:07:22.500 --> 05:07:22.979
careful?

05:07:23.040 --> 05:07:24.659
asked one of the humans.

05:07:24.720 --> 05:07:28.439
We don't know, said the leader grimly.

05:07:28.500 --> 05:07:30.659
The spies found out they're stealing

05:07:30.659 --> 05:07:32.400
dragon eggs, but not much else.

05:07:32.459 --> 05:07:35.099
We don't know if they've succeeded in

05:07:35.099 --> 05:07:37.439
taming the dragons after they hatch, or

05:07:37.439 --> 05:07:38.939
what else they might be trying to do with

05:07:38.939 --> 05:07:39.119
them.

05:07:39.180 --> 05:07:42.779
Stirring up trouble they can handle if

05:07:42.779 --> 05:07:44.700
you ask me, said one of the others.

05:07:44.759 --> 05:07:47.040
And then the shadow flickered down

05:07:47.040 --> 05:07:47.279
again.

05:07:47.340 --> 05:07:49.380
When it lifted.

05:07:49.439 --> 05:07:51.959
Luna and Dusky were in a rocky, sandy

05:07:51.959 --> 05:07:54.299
area at the base of a reddish stone

05:07:54.299 --> 05:07:54.720
cliff.

05:07:54.779 --> 05:07:56.459
Halfway up.

05:07:56.520 --> 05:07:59.040
A group of humans were hastily passing

05:07:59.040 --> 05:08:01.979
eggs out of a cave into boxes, then

05:08:01.979 --> 05:08:04.259
lowering them to the ground below, where

05:08:04.259 --> 05:08:06.360
an army of soldiers on horses waited.

05:08:06.419 --> 05:08:08.759
Cottonmouth and Coyote were there.

05:08:08.819 --> 05:08:12.479
Coyote scanned the sky, while Cottonmouth

05:08:12.479 --> 05:08:13.860
kept his eyes fixed on the eggs.

05:08:13.919 --> 05:08:16.319
If it hasn't worked yet.

05:08:16.380 --> 05:08:18.180
Coyote growled.

05:08:18.240 --> 05:08:19.259
Why do you keep trying?

05:08:19.319 --> 05:08:22.020
This is a pointless waste of soldiers and

05:08:22.020 --> 05:08:22.680
scientists.

05:08:22.740 --> 05:08:25.740
All we've gotten so far is mauled faces

05:08:25.740 --> 05:08:27.240
and burned out laboratories.

05:08:27.299 --> 05:08:30.779
I will figure out how to control them

05:08:30.779 --> 05:08:32.520
Cottonmouth said.

05:08:32.580 --> 05:08:35.340
There were 2 more feathers woven into his

05:08:35.340 --> 05:08:37.979
hair alongside new strands of gray.

05:08:38.040 --> 05:08:40.919
The grooves in his face were deeper now

05:08:40.919 --> 05:08:43.319
especially along his forehead and between

05:08:43.319 --> 05:08:44.220
his eyes.

05:08:44.279 --> 05:08:47.099
We have to scare them into submission.

05:08:47.159 --> 05:08:50.400
They will be my weapons once I break

05:08:50.400 --> 05:08:50.700
them.

05:08:50.759 --> 05:08:53.700
Coyote looked at him uneasily.

05:08:53.759 --> 05:08:56.819
You mean the emperor's weapons?

05:08:56.939 --> 05:09:01.139
Cottonmouth smiled tightly, leaning

05:09:01.139 --> 05:09:02.520
forward to watch the last of the eggs

05:09:02.520 --> 05:09:03.479
reach the ground.

05:09:03.540 --> 05:09:05.880
There were 6 of them this time.

05:09:05.939 --> 05:09:07.740
Luna saw with dismay.

05:09:07.799 --> 05:09:09.599
Let's go.

05:09:09.659 --> 05:09:11.340
Cottonmouth called.

05:09:11.400 --> 05:09:13.500
As soon as the boxes were lashed to their

05:09:13.500 --> 05:09:13.860
horses.

05:09:13.919 --> 05:09:16.740
He turned his own horse, and Coyote

05:09:16.740 --> 05:09:18.000
caught the reins to stop him.

05:09:18.060 --> 05:09:20.400
What about the soldiers still up there?

05:09:20.459 --> 05:09:21.900
Coyote asked.

05:09:21.959 --> 05:09:23.700
They can catch up.

05:09:23.759 --> 05:09:26.279
Cottonmouth said dismissively.

05:09:26.340 --> 05:09:28.919
He twitched the reins out of Coyote's

05:09:28.919 --> 05:09:30.659
hands and kicked his horse into a

05:09:30.659 --> 05:09:30.959
gallop.

05:09:31.020 --> 05:09:35.040
Coyote looked back at the figures, slowly

05:09:35.040 --> 05:09:37.200
inching down the cliff on the long

05:09:37.200 --> 05:09:38.159
dangling ropes.

05:09:38.220 --> 05:09:41.819
But after a moment, he sighed, turned his

05:09:41.819 --> 05:09:43.200
horse, and followed the others.

05:09:43.259 --> 05:09:47.639
So only Luna was left to see the dragon's

05:09:47.639 --> 05:09:47.880
return.

05:09:48.000 --> 05:09:52.200
This dragon was bigger, sandy tan flecked

05:09:52.200 --> 05:09:54.540
with black, and Luna thought she glimpsed

05:09:54.540 --> 05:09:56.700
a barb at the end of her tail, as the

05:09:56.700 --> 05:09:58.080
dragon swooped into her cave.

05:09:58.139 --> 05:10:01.860
She exploded out again a moment later

05:10:01.860 --> 05:10:03.419
roaring with fury.

05:10:03.479 --> 05:10:06.659
The last few soldiers on the cliff didn't

05:10:06.659 --> 05:10:07.200
stand a chance.

05:10:07.319 --> 05:10:10.799
Luna covered Dusky's eyes and closed her

05:10:10.799 --> 05:10:13.319
own as fire blasted from the dragon's

05:10:13.319 --> 05:10:13.500
mouth.

05:10:13.619 --> 05:10:17.279
The next moment, they were standing in a

05:10:17.279 --> 05:10:19.740
stone pyramid with a sand pit in the

05:10:19.740 --> 05:10:20.340
center of it.

05:10:20.400 --> 05:10:23.400
Windows high in the wall illuminated

05:10:23.400 --> 05:10:25.259
words painted in gold on the ceiling.

05:10:25.319 --> 05:10:28.080
The odd human letters rearranging into

05:10:28.080 --> 05:10:29.340
language in Luna's brain.

05:10:29.400 --> 05:10:32.159
Obedience, said one wall.

05:10:32.279 --> 05:10:35.279
Self preservation, said another.

05:10:35.580 --> 05:10:37.680
The emperor protects us all.

05:10:37.799 --> 05:10:41.580
Human soldiers lined the walls too

05:10:41.580 --> 05:10:44.580
bearing heavily padded leather armor and

05:10:44.580 --> 05:10:47.099
bristling with spikes and sharp weapons.

05:10:47.159 --> 05:10:50.099
In the center of the sand pit, a dragon

05:10:50.099 --> 05:10:52.139
egg was hatching, all alone.

05:10:52.200 --> 05:10:55.740
Luna could remember a few details about

05:10:55.740 --> 05:10:56.580
her own hatching.

05:10:56.639 --> 05:10:59.400
The gentle rocking of the silk hammock

05:10:59.400 --> 05:11:01.979
that cradled her egg, the talons that

05:11:01.979 --> 05:11:04.319
lifted her free of the eggshell, her

05:11:04.319 --> 05:11:06.779
mother's wings enfolding her, and a

05:11:06.779 --> 05:11:09.299
feeling of light, warmth, color

05:11:09.299 --> 05:11:10.500
security.

05:11:10.560 --> 05:11:12.959
There was none of that here.

05:11:13.020 --> 05:11:16.200
In this cold stone room full of spiky

05:11:16.200 --> 05:11:16.560
humans.

05:11:16.619 --> 05:11:20.700
One human stood close to the egg, but his

05:11:20.700 --> 05:11:22.919
face was shielded with a metal helmet, and

05:11:22.919 --> 05:11:25.560
armor plates covered his entire body, so

05:11:25.560 --> 05:11:27.000
Luna couldn't tell if it was cotton

05:11:27.000 --> 05:11:27.299
mouth.

05:11:27.360 --> 05:11:30.540
He held a long metal stick in his paws

05:11:30.540 --> 05:11:31.799
hovering over the egg.

05:11:31.860 --> 05:11:35.279
As the tiny hatching dragon pushed the

05:11:35.279 --> 05:11:37.860
shell aside and wobbled out onto the sand

05:11:37.860 --> 05:11:41.099
the human pounced, a wire circle at the

05:11:41.099 --> 05:11:42.659
end of the stick closed around the

05:11:42.659 --> 05:11:43.560
dragonette's neck.

05:11:43.680 --> 05:11:46.500
The dragonet squeaked with fear and

05:11:46.500 --> 05:11:47.040
surprise.

05:11:47.099 --> 05:11:49.380
It tried to turn, looking for a

05:11:49.380 --> 05:11:51.959
comforting figure, but the human used the

05:11:51.959 --> 05:11:53.099
stick to force it to the ground.

05:11:53.159 --> 05:11:57.840
I don't need to see this, Luna said, as

05:11:57.840 --> 05:12:00.060
Dusky buried his face in her neck again.

05:12:00.119 --> 05:12:02.520
She covered his ears, so he wouldn't have

05:12:02.520 --> 05:12:03.119
to hear it either.

05:12:03.180 --> 05:12:05.400
I don't want to see this.

05:12:05.459 --> 05:12:07.740
Show us something else, please.

05:12:07.860 --> 05:12:10.979
The human prodded the dragonette with a

05:12:10.979 --> 05:12:12.840
different stick, then shoved it back onto

05:12:12.840 --> 05:12:13.259
its feet.

05:12:13.319 --> 05:12:16.020
The dragonette staggered in the sand

05:12:16.020 --> 05:12:18.119
hissing, and snapped its teeth at the

05:12:18.119 --> 05:12:18.299
human.

05:12:18.419 --> 05:12:21.959
Brave little dragon, trying to fight back

05:12:21.959 --> 05:12:22.259
already.

05:12:22.319 --> 05:12:23.639
Luna thought.

05:12:23.700 --> 05:12:26.459
She remembered Coyote's words about

05:12:26.459 --> 05:12:29.639
mauled faces, and she hoped many humans

05:12:29.639 --> 05:12:31.680
here had been clawed by their small

05:12:31.680 --> 05:12:32.279
captives.

05:12:32.400 --> 05:12:35.639
But it was awful too, that the

05:12:35.639 --> 05:12:37.439
dragonettes climbed out of their shells

05:12:37.439 --> 05:12:39.360
directly into violence and pain.

05:12:39.419 --> 05:12:41.819
They shouldn't have had to use their

05:12:41.819 --> 05:12:42.840
teeth and claws yet.

05:12:42.900 --> 05:12:45.000
They should have had time to be taken

05:12:45.000 --> 05:12:46.139
care of first.

05:12:46.200 --> 05:12:49.139
Finally, the shadow flickered through.

05:12:49.200 --> 05:12:51.840
And now they were in a clinical box of a

05:12:51.840 --> 05:12:54.840
room, long and lined with tables on

05:12:54.840 --> 05:12:55.319
either side.

05:12:55.380 --> 05:12:59.279
On top of the tables were cages, each one

05:12:59.279 --> 05:13:00.479
with a dragon egg in it.

05:13:00.540 --> 05:13:02.700
Luna hissed in a breath.

05:13:02.759 --> 05:13:07.200
There were so many, 20 at least, with 10

05:13:07.200 --> 05:13:09.540
more cages containing broken eggshells

05:13:09.540 --> 05:13:11.220
where those dragonettes must have

05:13:11.220 --> 05:13:11.580
hatched.

05:13:11.639 --> 05:13:14.819
The door at the far end was flung open

05:13:14.819 --> 05:13:17.880
suddenly, and Cottonmouth stormed in, with

05:13:17.880 --> 05:13:19.380
a man behind him carrying another

05:13:19.380 --> 05:13:20.700
eggbox.

05:13:20.759 --> 05:13:24.720
In here, Cottonmouth said, throwing open

05:13:24.720 --> 05:13:25.439
one of the cages.

05:13:25.500 --> 05:13:28.979
I don't believe there was only one egg in

05:13:28.979 --> 05:13:29.459
that nest.

05:13:29.520 --> 05:13:31.259
That dragon was enormous.

05:13:31.319 --> 05:13:34.860
Biggest I've ever seen, the man said

05:13:34.860 --> 05:13:37.020
anxiously, unpacking the stuffing around

05:13:37.020 --> 05:13:37.319
the egg.

05:13:37.380 --> 05:13:40.500
How could a dragon that size have only

05:13:40.500 --> 05:13:41.279
one egg?

05:13:41.340 --> 05:13:43.319
Cottonmouth demanded?

05:13:43.380 --> 05:13:45.779
And why would it hide it so carefully?

05:13:45.840 --> 05:13:47.580
Are you lying to me?

05:13:47.639 --> 05:13:50.040
Did my stupid brother decide to leave the

05:13:50.040 --> 05:13:50.580
rest behind?

05:13:50.700 --> 05:13:52.740
I'm not lying.

05:13:52.860 --> 05:13:54.119
The man cried.

05:13:54.180 --> 05:13:57.599
He stopped short of touching the egg, and

05:13:57.599 --> 05:13:59.220
clasped his shaking hands together.

05:13:59.279 --> 05:14:01.139
I promise you sir.

05:14:01.200 --> 05:14:03.360
We had the hardest time getting to it.

05:14:03.419 --> 05:14:05.939
I promise, we wouldn't have risked being

05:14:05.939 --> 05:14:06.779
sent back.

05:14:06.840 --> 05:14:09.060
Cottonmouth snorted.

05:14:09.119 --> 05:14:11.220
That I can believe.

05:14:11.279 --> 05:14:14.639
Well, it had better be worth it then.

05:14:14.700 --> 05:14:17.220
He leaned closer to the shell.

05:14:17.279 --> 05:14:19.619
Glaring at the faint shimmer of orange

05:14:19.619 --> 05:14:20.639
scales underneath.

05:14:20.700 --> 05:14:23.099
At least it's a big one.

05:14:23.159 --> 05:14:26.400
When I break this dragon, it will burn

05:14:26.400 --> 05:14:28.680
the diamond empire's armies to ash for

05:14:28.680 --> 05:14:28.919
me.

05:14:28.979 --> 05:14:34.259
I heard the other man began, then broke

05:14:34.259 --> 05:14:35.099
off unhappily.

05:14:35.159 --> 05:14:36.419
What?

05:14:36.540 --> 05:14:38.220
Cottonmouth snapped.

05:14:38.279 --> 05:14:41.340
I heard the Diamond Empire, and the

05:14:41.340 --> 05:14:44.159
Jaguar Empire, are both trying to tame

05:14:44.159 --> 05:14:45.000
Dragons too.

05:14:45.060 --> 05:14:46.500
The man mumbled.

05:14:46.560 --> 05:14:49.259
Cottonmouth laughed bitterly.

05:14:49.319 --> 05:14:50.340
Yes.

05:14:50.400 --> 05:14:53.040
No one can keep a secret around here.

05:14:53.099 --> 05:14:56.099
But most of the dragons in their

05:14:56.099 --> 05:14:58.080
territories are those swimming ones.

05:14:58.139 --> 05:15:01.979
Can't breathe fire, according to the

05:15:01.979 --> 05:15:02.459
scholars.

05:15:02.520 --> 05:15:05.759
Our dragons will be the most dangerous

05:15:05.819 --> 05:15:07.860
once we get them to work.

05:15:07.919 --> 05:15:11.400
Get them to work, Luna thought.

05:15:11.459 --> 05:15:13.200
With a shiver of outrage.

05:15:13.259 --> 05:15:16.020
As though dragons are nothing more than

05:15:16.020 --> 05:15:19.319
defective looms, or broken carts, as if

05:15:19.319 --> 05:15:21.479
baby dragons just need a little prodding

05:15:21.479 --> 05:15:22.619
and fixing to be useful.

05:15:22.740 --> 05:15:27.119
The shadow again, this time casting them

05:15:27.119 --> 05:15:29.040
into darkness for long enough, though

05:15:29.040 --> 05:15:30.779
Luna wondered if that was the end of the

05:15:30.779 --> 05:15:31.439
human story.

05:15:31.500 --> 05:15:34.619
But at length, it lifted again.

05:15:34.680 --> 05:15:37.439
Now she was in a field of tall green

05:15:37.439 --> 05:15:37.919
plants.

05:15:37.979 --> 05:15:39.479
All around her.

05:15:39.540 --> 05:15:41.639
Humans picked interestingly small

05:15:41.639 --> 05:15:44.459
tomatoes and pea pods, filling baskets

05:15:44.459 --> 05:15:45.479
and chatting as they worked.

05:15:45.540 --> 05:15:49.500
The blue sky soared overhead, sunlit and

05:15:49.500 --> 05:15:49.919
peaceful.

05:15:49.979 --> 05:15:52.680
Dusky lifted his snout and took a deep

05:15:52.680 --> 05:15:52.979
breath.

05:15:53.040 --> 05:15:56.099
Through their scales, she could feel his

05:15:56.099 --> 05:15:58.740
heartbeat slow a little bit, despite all

05:15:58.740 --> 05:15:59.520
the humans around them.

05:15:59.580 --> 05:16:04.200
Then, a terrifying roar split the air.

05:16:04.259 --> 05:16:07.860
A wordless howl of fury that felt like

05:16:07.860 --> 05:16:10.139
all of Luna's worst days rolled together

05:16:10.139 --> 05:16:11.099
and set on fire.

05:16:11.159 --> 05:16:14.520
Three dragons burst out of the forest.

05:16:14.580 --> 05:16:16.560
They flew low to the ground.

05:16:16.619 --> 05:16:18.840
Close enough that Luna could smell the

05:16:18.840 --> 05:16:20.459
smoke rising from their snouts.

05:16:20.580 --> 05:16:23.220
Close enough that she could look into

05:16:23.220 --> 05:16:25.020
their eyes as they shot past.

05:16:25.139 --> 05:16:28.919
One of them was the dragon from the red

05:16:28.919 --> 05:16:31.500
stone cliff, whose 6 eggs had been

05:16:31.500 --> 05:16:31.919
stolen.

05:16:31.979 --> 05:16:35.279
The one in the lead was nearly 5 times

05:16:35.279 --> 05:16:38.759
that size, a huge orange dragon with

05:16:38.759 --> 05:16:41.639
rusty copper green underscales, lashing

05:16:41.639 --> 05:16:43.139
her enormous tail as she flew.

05:16:43.200 --> 05:16:47.279
The 3rd was a black dragon, speckled with

05:16:47.279 --> 05:16:48.060
red scales.

05:16:48.119 --> 05:16:49.860
His face was set with grim

05:16:49.860 --> 05:16:50.459
determination.

05:16:50.520 --> 05:16:54.720
The humans around Luna screamed, dropped

05:16:54.720 --> 05:16:56.819
their baskets, and fled toward the

05:16:56.819 --> 05:16:57.599
buildings in the distance.

05:16:57.659 --> 05:17:01.259
The dragons opened their mouths and set

05:17:01.259 --> 05:17:02.520
the fields ablaze.

05:17:02.580 --> 05:17:06.599
Luna clutched Dusky closer, but the

05:17:06.599 --> 05:17:07.919
flames burned around them without

05:17:07.919 --> 05:17:08.880
singeing their wings.

05:17:08.939 --> 05:17:12.419
The plant shriveled and turned to ash as

05:17:12.419 --> 05:17:15.360
the fire raged across the whole area, but

05:17:15.360 --> 05:17:17.220
Luna and Dusky stood unscathed.

05:17:17.279 --> 05:17:20.459
I knew it, Luna whispered.

05:17:20.520 --> 05:17:24.240
She looked up as the dragons circled, now

05:17:24.240 --> 05:17:26.040
breathing their fire on the closest human

05:17:26.040 --> 05:17:26.700
dwellings.

05:17:26.759 --> 05:17:29.099
Stealing the dragon eggs.

05:17:29.220 --> 05:17:31.979
That's what the humans did to make the

05:17:31.979 --> 05:17:32.819
dragon so mad.

05:17:32.880 --> 05:17:34.860
Dusky.

05:17:34.919 --> 05:17:37.979
This is the beginning of the scorching.

05:17:38.040 --> 05:17:42.360
Chapter 16.

05:17:42.599 --> 05:17:46.619
Luna was not sure why or how she was

05:17:46.619 --> 05:17:49.560
watching these slices of the past, but

05:17:49.560 --> 05:17:50.939
she could see how the story had changed

05:17:50.939 --> 05:17:53.340
over the 1000s of years that had passed

05:17:53.340 --> 05:17:54.180
since the scorching.

05:17:54.299 --> 05:17:57.479
Dragons had poured it into a myth.

05:17:57.599 --> 05:18:01.020
Covering it, like layers of tree stuff

05:18:01.020 --> 05:18:03.060
keeping the memory that a human had done

05:18:03.060 --> 05:18:05.759
something terrible, but wiping away the

05:18:05.759 --> 05:18:07.200
details of what had happened to their

05:18:07.200 --> 05:18:07.439
eggs.

05:18:07.500 --> 05:18:11.459
Perhaps over the years, dragons hadn't

05:18:11.459 --> 05:18:13.200
believed that humans could steal so many

05:18:13.200 --> 05:18:15.779
or that humans could have built a society

05:18:15.779 --> 05:18:18.599
this advanced, or that humans could be

05:18:18.599 --> 05:18:19.259
dangerous at all.

05:18:19.319 --> 05:18:22.259
And the humans had changed it too.

05:18:22.319 --> 05:18:24.720
If the story in the cave paintings was

05:18:24.720 --> 05:18:25.139
their version.

05:18:25.259 --> 05:18:28.139
Those paintings hadn't shown the cause of

05:18:28.139 --> 05:18:28.799
the scorching.

05:18:28.860 --> 05:18:32.040
They hadn't included any greedy humans

05:18:32.040 --> 05:18:34.919
stealing eggs, or torturing newly hatched

05:18:34.919 --> 05:18:35.639
dragons.

05:18:35.700 --> 05:18:38.159
In the human version, the dragons

05:18:38.159 --> 05:18:39.479
attacked them unprovoked.

05:18:39.540 --> 05:18:42.240
Luna remembered the little drawings of

05:18:42.240 --> 05:18:44.040
dragons eating humans and burning

05:18:44.040 --> 05:18:44.340
everything.

05:18:44.459 --> 05:18:47.099
The humans had painted themselves as

05:18:47.099 --> 05:18:49.919
victims, dragons as barbaric monsters.

05:18:49.979 --> 05:18:53.880
But it was the other way around, Luna

05:18:53.880 --> 05:18:54.720
thought angrily.

05:18:54.779 --> 05:18:56.520
Bullfrog was actually right.

05:18:56.580 --> 05:18:58.619
The humans did start it.

05:18:58.680 --> 05:19:01.380
The shadow rolled them into the next

05:19:01.380 --> 05:19:04.139
moment. leaving them standing atop a

05:19:04.139 --> 05:19:06.360
towering stepped temple, under the 3

05:19:06.360 --> 05:19:08.580
moons, in the center of a city that

05:19:08.580 --> 05:19:09.959
wasn't cotton mouths.

05:19:10.139 --> 05:19:12.360
Luna guessed they were on the other side

05:19:12.360 --> 05:19:14.880
of the mountains, somewhere in the north

05:19:14.880 --> 05:19:16.380
given the cold temperatures.

05:19:16.439 --> 05:19:19.319
The humans below them were heavy furs

05:19:19.319 --> 05:19:21.479
over snow white wool wrappings.

05:19:21.659 --> 05:19:23.700
They screamed in a different language

05:19:23.700 --> 05:19:26.220
from cotton mouths, but they burned just

05:19:26.220 --> 05:19:26.639
as quickly.

05:19:26.700 --> 05:19:30.240
This time there were 10 dragons attacking

05:19:30.240 --> 05:19:32.340
together, burning every corner of the

05:19:32.340 --> 05:19:33.180
city.

05:19:33.240 --> 05:19:36.000
And this time, Dusky didn't hide his

05:19:36.000 --> 05:19:36.240
face.

05:19:36.360 --> 05:19:39.419
He pushed his snout through Luna's talons

05:19:39.419 --> 05:19:40.860
peeking out to watch.

05:19:40.919 --> 05:19:43.979
I am glad they're burning those humans.

05:19:44.099 --> 05:19:46.380
He said softly but fiercely.

05:19:46.439 --> 05:19:50.279
I want them to burn every single human, so

05:19:50.279 --> 05:19:51.419
they're all gone forever.

05:19:51.479 --> 05:19:53.759
Dusky?

05:19:53.819 --> 05:19:55.500
This happened a long time ago.

05:19:55.560 --> 05:19:56.759
Luna said.

05:19:56.819 --> 05:20:00.060
And listen, I know you're upset about the

05:20:00.060 --> 05:20:00.720
dragon eggs.

05:20:00.779 --> 05:20:01.860
I am too.

05:20:01.919 --> 05:20:02.819
It's awful.

05:20:02.880 --> 05:20:05.340
But I still don't think killing every

05:20:05.340 --> 05:20:06.959
human would be the right response.

05:20:07.080 --> 05:20:09.599
I do, he said.

05:20:09.659 --> 05:20:10.979
They deserve it.

05:20:11.040 --> 05:20:13.380
Luna understood that.

05:20:13.439 --> 05:20:16.020
There were days she felt that way about

05:20:16.020 --> 05:20:16.799
the hive wings.

05:20:16.860 --> 05:20:20.340
When dragons, or humans, did something

05:20:20.340 --> 05:20:21.240
unforgivable.

05:20:21.299 --> 05:20:23.040
Shouldn't they be punished?

05:20:23.099 --> 05:20:25.139
Shouldn't the punishment be equally as

05:20:25.139 --> 05:20:25.619
terrible?

05:20:25.680 --> 05:20:28.740
After the hive wings tried to wipe out

05:20:28.740 --> 05:20:31.080
the leaf wings, didn't they deserve to be

05:20:31.080 --> 05:20:32.159
exterminated in response?

05:20:32.220 --> 05:20:35.340
And if the humans stole the dragon's

05:20:35.340 --> 05:20:37.380
children, shouldn't the dragons?

05:20:38.099 --> 05:20:39.540
Didn't it make sense to?

05:20:39.840 --> 05:20:42.299
But she couldn't finish that thought.

05:20:42.419 --> 05:20:44.819
She couldn't look down at the burning

05:20:44.819 --> 05:20:45.060
city.

05:20:45.119 --> 05:20:48.060
All these 100s of humans, and really

05:20:48.060 --> 05:20:49.799
believe it was right.

05:20:49.860 --> 05:20:52.439
Even after what she'd seen them do to the

05:20:52.439 --> 05:20:54.060
newly hatched Dragonette.

05:20:54.119 --> 05:20:57.720
She couldn't think of Wren and Axolotl in

05:20:57.720 --> 05:20:58.740
which they'd never existed.

05:20:58.799 --> 05:21:01.860
Now that she'd met them, she believed

05:21:01.860 --> 05:21:03.299
that some humans were worth saving.

05:21:03.360 --> 05:21:07.799
Just like, now that she knew cricket, she

05:21:07.799 --> 05:21:09.299
couldn't wish for the destruction of all

05:21:09.299 --> 05:21:09.959
hive wings.

05:21:10.020 --> 05:21:12.419
Maybe Sunday was right.

05:21:12.540 --> 05:21:15.119
That silk wings are too soft, too

05:21:15.119 --> 05:21:15.599
forgiving.

05:21:15.659 --> 05:21:18.479
But I don't forgive them.

05:21:18.540 --> 05:21:23.279
I just want the punishment to fit, and to

05:21:23.279 --> 05:21:24.540
go where it's deserved.

05:21:24.599 --> 05:21:27.419
I don't want to be one of these dragons

05:21:27.419 --> 05:21:30.060
burning everything, and hurting everyone

05:21:30.060 --> 05:21:30.720
for revenge.

05:21:30.779 --> 05:21:34.500
With an awful lurch, she wondered if

05:21:34.500 --> 05:21:36.479
anyone had saved the dragon eggs in the

05:21:36.479 --> 05:21:36.959
human cities.

05:21:37.020 --> 05:21:39.540
Perhaps the dragon sought their

05:21:39.540 --> 05:21:40.619
dragonettes were already dead.

05:21:40.680 --> 05:21:44.279
In their rage, they didn't realize, they

05:21:44.279 --> 05:21:46.080
were also destroying any hope of finding

05:21:46.080 --> 05:21:46.439
them again.

05:21:46.500 --> 05:21:48.720
Luna shivered.

05:21:48.779 --> 05:21:52.619
The burning city faded, and she was on

05:21:52.619 --> 05:21:53.340
another beach.

05:21:53.400 --> 05:21:56.459
But it was still nighttime, a different

05:21:56.459 --> 05:21:57.240
nighttime.

05:21:57.299 --> 05:21:59.520
The moons were in different phases now

05:21:59.520 --> 05:22:00.959
and it was raining.

05:22:01.020 --> 05:22:04.799
A wet, trembling group of bedraggled

05:22:04.799 --> 05:22:06.360
humans were gathered by the water

05:22:06.360 --> 05:22:08.580
climbing into things that looked like

05:22:08.580 --> 05:22:10.979
large wooden bowls, floating on the

05:22:10.979 --> 05:22:11.639
surface of the ocean.

05:22:11.700 --> 05:22:14.880
Luna had seen them in the cave paintings

05:22:14.880 --> 05:22:17.220
the crescents that carried the humans

05:22:17.220 --> 05:22:18.240
across the sea.

05:22:18.299 --> 05:22:21.060
Several of the humans had long sticks

05:22:21.060 --> 05:22:23.400
with flat ends that they used to push the

05:22:23.400 --> 05:22:25.979
bowls forward, out into the waves.

05:22:26.040 --> 05:22:29.159
Other humans were watching the sky, armed

05:22:29.159 --> 05:22:31.500
with swords and spears, that Luna thought

05:22:31.500 --> 05:22:33.360
would not be much help against the fiery

05:22:33.360 --> 05:22:35.220
vengeance of the dragons she'd seen.

05:22:35.279 --> 05:22:37.860
The humans were probably more protected

05:22:37.860 --> 05:22:40.080
by the rain than by those tiny, sharp

05:22:40.080 --> 05:22:40.319
things.

05:22:40.439 --> 05:22:44.939
One human in a long cloak, with the hood

05:22:44.939 --> 05:22:47.340
pulled up, stepped into the largest bowl

05:22:47.340 --> 05:22:49.979
and turned back, reaching as a box was

05:22:49.979 --> 05:22:50.520
passed to him.

05:22:50.580 --> 05:22:53.459
Luna caught a glimpse of thick black

05:22:53.459 --> 05:22:55.860
gloves, and she darted closer to see his

05:22:55.860 --> 05:22:56.400
face.

05:22:56.400 --> 05:22:58.860
Yes, it was cotton mouth.

05:22:58.979 --> 05:23:01.619
He must be the one leading them all

05:23:01.619 --> 05:23:03.240
across the ocean in those paintings.

05:23:03.299 --> 05:23:05.159
Him and this box.

05:23:05.279 --> 05:23:09.180
Luna was sure the box held a dragon egg.

05:23:09.240 --> 05:23:11.459
The largest one, she guessed.

05:23:11.580 --> 05:23:13.560
The one she'd seen him bring into his

05:23:13.560 --> 05:23:14.099
cage room.

05:23:14.159 --> 05:23:18.000
Even after all this, after all the burned

05:23:18.000 --> 05:23:20.459
cities and death and destruction, he

05:23:20.459 --> 05:23:21.659
hadn't given up on his plan.

05:23:21.720 --> 05:23:24.720
What is wrong with you?

05:23:24.840 --> 05:23:26.759
She thought furiously at him.

05:23:26.819 --> 05:23:29.459
If you're so clever, couldn't you imagine

05:23:29.459 --> 05:23:31.560
a better world instead of a worse one?

05:23:31.619 --> 05:23:34.080
Why did you work so hard on something

05:23:34.080 --> 05:23:35.700
that would cause so much misery?

05:23:35.700 --> 05:23:37.020
For power?

05:23:37.080 --> 05:23:39.360
Couldn't you have put all that energy

05:23:39.360 --> 05:23:41.279
into making peace with other humans?

05:23:41.279 --> 05:23:43.919
Instead, and left the dragons alone?

05:23:43.979 --> 05:23:47.459
Don't you realize you destroyed your own

05:23:47.459 --> 05:23:47.759
world?

05:23:47.819 --> 05:23:51.060
Cottonmouth looked up at the cliffs

05:23:51.060 --> 05:23:52.319
looming over the beach.

05:23:52.380 --> 05:23:55.259
Any sign of my brother?

05:23:55.259 --> 05:23:57.479
He asked one of the humans near him.

05:23:57.540 --> 05:23:59.759
The human shook her head.

05:23:59.880 --> 05:24:01.319
Sorry, sir.

05:24:01.380 --> 05:24:03.419
No word from coyotes since he rode to

05:24:03.419 --> 05:24:04.259
warn the southern villages.

05:24:04.319 --> 05:24:07.139
Cottonmouth pressed his lips together.

05:24:07.200 --> 05:24:09.840
Then we leave without him.

05:24:09.900 --> 05:24:12.419
He strode to the front of the floating

05:24:12.419 --> 05:24:14.939
crescent and sat down, tucking the box

05:24:14.939 --> 05:24:16.919
between his knees, and setting his hands

05:24:16.919 --> 05:24:17.880
flat on top of it.

05:24:17.939 --> 05:24:20.819
Other humans scurry to get in behind him

05:24:20.819 --> 05:24:22.560
and push off from the shore.

05:24:22.619 --> 05:24:26.220
Not quite the heroic story of the cave

05:24:26.220 --> 05:24:28.080
paintings, Luna noticed.

05:24:28.139 --> 05:24:31.919
He wasn't standing alone, nobly leading

05:24:31.919 --> 05:24:32.819
them across the ocean.

05:24:32.880 --> 05:24:36.900
He was crouched, filthy and wet, muttering

05:24:36.900 --> 05:24:38.939
to the box, as other people did all the

05:24:38.939 --> 05:24:40.380
work to get him out to sea.

05:24:40.439 --> 05:24:43.080
But he did have a lot of other humans

05:24:43.080 --> 05:24:43.500
with him.

05:24:43.560 --> 05:24:46.979
Luna stepped back to watch as they all

05:24:46.979 --> 05:24:48.720
paddled away into the surging waves.

05:24:48.779 --> 05:24:53.159
Maybe they'll drown on the way, Dusky

05:24:53.159 --> 05:24:53.639
said hopefully.

05:24:53.700 --> 05:24:56.520
Luna knew at least some of them would

05:24:56.520 --> 05:24:56.819
make it.

05:24:56.880 --> 05:24:59.580
If the cave paintings were right

05:24:59.580 --> 05:25:01.799
Cottonmouth would be one of them, still

05:25:01.799 --> 05:25:03.119
carrying that box.

05:25:03.180 --> 05:25:05.520
Is there more to this story?

05:25:05.639 --> 05:25:07.680
She asked this guy.

05:25:07.740 --> 05:25:09.299
Are we almost done?

05:25:09.360 --> 05:25:12.900
It was depressing, being trapped in

05:25:12.900 --> 05:25:15.540
cottonmouth's spiteful life at the end of

05:25:15.540 --> 05:25:16.020
a whole world.

05:25:16.080 --> 05:25:19.500
The shadow flickered over them again and

05:25:19.500 --> 05:25:22.619
lifted, leaving them in a sunlit jungle.

05:25:22.680 --> 05:25:25.500
They were standing beside a sheer rocky

05:25:25.500 --> 05:25:28.319
cliff face, pockmarked with caves, and

05:25:28.319 --> 05:25:30.599
all around them, the muggy air buzzed

05:25:30.599 --> 05:25:31.139
with insects.

05:25:31.200 --> 05:25:34.139
Lana turned slowly.

05:25:34.200 --> 05:25:36.299
There were so many trees here.

05:25:36.360 --> 05:25:39.060
Could this possibly be Pantala?

05:25:39.119 --> 05:25:41.520
Was this what it looked like before Queen

05:25:41.520 --> 05:25:43.080
Wasp and the tree wars?

05:25:43.139 --> 05:25:46.860
Through a gap in the vines, she glimpsed

05:25:46.860 --> 05:25:48.479
a huge, sparkling stretch of water.

05:25:48.540 --> 05:25:52.680
It was still and calm, not roiling with

05:25:52.680 --> 05:25:53.340
waves.

05:25:53.400 --> 05:25:56.700
So if it wasn't the ocean, Could it be

05:25:56.700 --> 05:25:57.599
Lake Scorpion?

05:25:57.659 --> 05:26:01.139
Voices approached, chatting quietly in

05:26:01.139 --> 05:26:01.319
human.

05:26:01.380 --> 05:26:05.279
As Luna turned toward them, suddenly a

05:26:05.279 --> 05:26:06.959
figure surged up from the ground very

05:26:06.959 --> 05:26:09.540
close to her talons, he'd been so hidden

05:26:09.540 --> 05:26:11.400
by the undergrowth, she'd nearly stepped

05:26:11.400 --> 05:26:13.319
on him, not that he would have noticed.

05:26:13.380 --> 05:26:15.360
Stop!

05:26:15.419 --> 05:26:17.520
The figure shouted, don't move.

05:26:17.580 --> 05:26:21.180
Luna found herself freezing, along with

05:26:21.180 --> 05:26:23.340
the 2 humans who'd just stepped into the

05:26:23.340 --> 05:26:24.060
glade.

05:26:24.119 --> 05:26:25.319
They glanced at each other.

05:26:25.380 --> 05:26:27.659
Then back of the man flapping his hands

05:26:27.659 --> 05:26:28.560
frantically at them.

05:26:28.619 --> 05:26:31.919
He was wrapped in leaves in an odd leaf

05:26:31.919 --> 05:26:34.619
hat, but Luna realized that under all of

05:26:34.619 --> 05:26:36.000
that, was cottonmouth.

05:26:36.119 --> 05:26:39.479
Sorry, sir, said one of the humans.

05:26:39.540 --> 05:26:41.819
We were going to check the caves for a

05:26:41.819 --> 05:26:42.299
place to hide.

05:26:42.360 --> 05:26:45.299
One of the night guards thought she saw a

05:26:45.299 --> 05:26:47.340
dragon fly overhead, said the other.

05:26:47.400 --> 05:26:50.220
She said maybe they followed us, and not

05:26:50.220 --> 05:26:52.080
even crossing an ocean will keep us safe

05:26:52.080 --> 05:26:52.500
from them.

05:26:52.560 --> 05:26:54.659
She's wrong.

05:26:54.779 --> 05:26:56.880
There are no dragons here, but it doesn't

05:26:56.880 --> 05:26:57.119
matter.

05:26:57.180 --> 05:27:00.000
Cottonmouth said, one of his hands

05:27:00.000 --> 05:27:01.680
shaking as he pointed at the others.

05:27:01.740 --> 05:27:03.540
I found the answer.

05:27:03.599 --> 05:27:05.099
I know what to do.

05:27:05.159 --> 05:27:07.860
I know how to get the dragons to bow down

05:27:07.860 --> 05:27:08.159
to us.

05:27:08.279 --> 05:27:11.040
He sounded insane to Luna.

05:27:11.099 --> 05:27:14.159
But the humans heroically managed not to

05:27:14.159 --> 05:27:15.000
look too skeptical.

05:27:15.060 --> 05:27:16.439
After a moment.

05:27:16.500 --> 05:27:19.919
One of them politely said, Oh?

05:27:20.040 --> 05:27:22.680
This plant.

05:27:22.799 --> 05:27:25.319
Cottonmouth crouched on the jungle floor

05:27:25.319 --> 05:27:27.119
and stared intently at something.

05:27:27.180 --> 05:27:30.180
Look, it takes over the minds of

05:27:30.180 --> 05:27:30.779
insects.

05:27:30.840 --> 05:27:32.159
It controls them.

05:27:32.220 --> 05:27:35.159
These ants will carry the seeds to a high

05:27:35.159 --> 05:27:36.840
place and then die.

05:27:36.900 --> 05:27:38.880
So the plant can grow out of their

05:27:38.880 --> 05:27:39.360
bodies.

05:27:39.419 --> 05:27:42.299
These caterpillars will go wherever it

05:27:42.299 --> 05:27:45.360
tells them to, swallow the seeds, and

05:27:45.360 --> 05:27:46.919
then feed the plant with their own body

05:27:46.919 --> 05:27:47.700
as it grows.

05:27:47.819 --> 05:27:50.159
Isn't that magnificent?

05:27:50.220 --> 05:27:53.819
The plant spreads and survives by ruling

05:27:53.819 --> 05:27:54.779
other creatures.

05:27:54.779 --> 05:27:57.659
By dominating them, it's perfect.

05:27:57.779 --> 05:28:00.779
Now the humans did look at each other

05:28:00.779 --> 05:28:01.020
again.

05:28:01.080 --> 05:28:02.819
One looked worried.

05:28:02.939 --> 05:28:04.259
The other disturbed.

05:28:04.319 --> 05:28:06.659
That's...

05:28:06.659 --> 05:28:09.180
One of them started trailing off.

05:28:09.299 --> 05:28:12.540
Unnerving. finished the other.

05:28:12.599 --> 05:28:15.419
Sounds like a pretty creepy plant.

05:28:15.479 --> 05:28:16.080
Sir.

05:28:16.200 --> 05:28:19.560
Cottonmouth made an impatient gesture.

05:28:19.619 --> 05:28:21.060
Don't be absurd.

05:28:21.119 --> 05:28:23.580
I can make it work on dragons.

05:28:23.639 --> 05:28:24.779
It's exactly what I need.

05:28:24.900 --> 05:28:28.319
He snatched up a metal implement and

05:28:28.319 --> 05:28:30.360
began digging up one of the plants, an

05:28:30.360 --> 05:28:31.500
eerie glint in his eyes.

05:28:31.619 --> 05:28:35.220
Luna felt dusky bury his head in her

05:28:35.220 --> 05:28:37.860
scales again, as the flicker came and

05:28:37.860 --> 05:28:41.099
went, and now they were in a cave, lit by

05:28:41.099 --> 05:28:41.880
oil lamps.

05:28:41.939 --> 05:28:44.580
The walls were rough, and the stone

05:28:44.580 --> 05:28:46.200
beneath her talons was damp.

05:28:46.259 --> 05:28:48.900
Out in the tunnels, she could hear

05:28:48.900 --> 05:28:51.540
clanging and muffled shouts, as though

05:28:51.540 --> 05:28:53.819
the humans were busy building or digging

05:28:53.819 --> 05:28:55.139
or whatever busy thing they were up to.

05:28:55.200 --> 05:28:57.959
The air smelled faintly of rotting

05:28:57.959 --> 05:28:59.819
greenery, and the place was a mess.

05:28:59.939 --> 05:29:02.759
But something about it still reminded her

05:29:02.759 --> 05:29:05.400
of the cold, smooth room, with all the

05:29:05.400 --> 05:29:05.819
cages.

05:29:05.880 --> 05:29:09.299
Perhaps that was partly cotton mouth

05:29:09.299 --> 05:29:11.400
stepping briskly between the piles of

05:29:11.400 --> 05:29:13.020
vines and pots of dirt.

05:29:13.080 --> 05:29:15.540
Or maybe it was the small creatures

05:29:15.540 --> 05:29:17.279
trapped in makeshift cages around the

05:29:17.279 --> 05:29:17.459
room.

05:29:17.520 --> 05:29:20.880
Most of them were lizards of various

05:29:20.880 --> 05:29:23.759
kinds, but there was a monkey too, and a

05:29:23.759 --> 05:29:25.259
long feathered blue green bird.

05:29:25.319 --> 05:29:28.139
And there was the dragon egg.

05:29:28.200 --> 05:29:29.819
Luna caught her breath.

05:29:29.880 --> 05:29:32.700
A small crack had appeared near the top

05:29:32.700 --> 05:29:33.119
of the egg.

05:29:33.180 --> 05:29:36.299
The shell was edging toward translucent

05:29:36.299 --> 05:29:38.279
and below the surface, she could see

05:29:38.279 --> 05:29:38.639
movement.

05:29:38.700 --> 05:29:40.979
It was almost ready to hatch.

05:29:41.099 --> 05:29:43.619
Running out of time.

05:29:43.680 --> 05:29:45.060
Cottonmouth muttered.

05:29:45.119 --> 05:29:46.860
Why didn't that one work?

05:29:46.919 --> 05:29:48.599
This one was interesting.

05:29:48.659 --> 05:29:52.259
He tapped a sheaf of papers, and bent

05:29:52.259 --> 05:29:54.360
over one of the chameleons, which was

05:29:54.360 --> 05:29:56.700
lying still and listless on a large red

05:29:56.700 --> 05:29:57.599
veined leaf.

05:29:57.659 --> 05:29:59.220
Hmm.

05:29:59.340 --> 05:30:02.159
He poked it with his riding implement, but

05:30:02.159 --> 05:30:03.479
the chameleon just blinked.

05:30:03.540 --> 05:30:04.979
Get up.

05:30:05.040 --> 05:30:06.659
Cottonmouth snapped.

05:30:06.779 --> 05:30:07.380
Move.

05:30:07.439 --> 05:30:09.360
The chameleon did not move.

05:30:09.419 --> 05:30:13.020
Cottonmouth muttered a few curses and

05:30:13.020 --> 05:30:15.419
squinted at the dragon egg, then hurried

05:30:15.419 --> 05:30:18.000
over to the largest pot, where several

05:30:18.000 --> 05:30:20.340
breath of evil vines rose from the dirt

05:30:20.340 --> 05:30:22.139
and twined together.

05:30:22.200 --> 05:30:25.319
The egg rocked slightly, and another

05:30:25.319 --> 05:30:26.580
crack appeared around the middle.

05:30:26.700 --> 05:30:29.819
Cottonmouth hissed and sprinted across

05:30:29.819 --> 05:30:30.060
the room.

05:30:30.119 --> 05:30:32.880
He returned with the same kind of metal

05:30:32.880 --> 05:30:35.459
choker stick that Luna had seen used on

05:30:35.459 --> 05:30:37.619
the other newly hatched dragonette.

05:30:37.680 --> 05:30:40.259
She watched him tug on those huge black

05:30:40.259 --> 05:30:43.619
gloves. lift the stick and prowl closer

05:30:43.619 --> 05:30:44.040
to the egg.

05:30:44.099 --> 05:30:48.060
I don't like this part, a voice said

05:30:48.060 --> 05:30:51.060
suddenly, high and clear, and all at once

05:30:51.060 --> 05:30:53.939
the makeshift lab swirled away, leaving

05:30:53.939 --> 05:30:55.979
Luna and Dusky in a featureless gray

05:30:55.979 --> 05:30:56.700
mist.

05:30:56.759 --> 05:31:00.240
Luna glanced at Dusky, who stared back at

05:31:00.240 --> 05:31:01.020
her with wide eyes.

05:31:01.080 --> 05:31:03.299
Who said that?

05:31:03.360 --> 05:31:05.040
She asked cautiously.

05:31:05.099 --> 05:31:06.900
There was no response.

05:31:06.959 --> 05:31:08.580
Hello?

05:31:08.639 --> 05:31:11.340
It was the little dragon.

05:31:11.400 --> 05:31:12.779
Dusky whispered.

05:31:12.840 --> 05:31:14.819
The little dragon?

05:31:14.880 --> 05:31:16.080
Luna echoed.

05:31:16.139 --> 05:31:17.520
The one in the egg?

05:31:17.580 --> 05:31:21.000
The mist lifted abruptly, and they were

05:31:21.000 --> 05:31:21.900
back in the throne room.

05:31:22.020 --> 05:31:24.659
Luna had a weird moment of vertigo.

05:31:24.720 --> 05:31:26.459
Was this real?

05:31:26.580 --> 05:31:28.439
Were they back in reality?

05:31:28.500 --> 05:31:30.119
Out of the hallucination?

05:31:30.180 --> 05:31:34.080
As she realized that it was the same, but

05:31:34.080 --> 05:31:34.500
different.

05:31:34.619 --> 05:31:37.740
No plants covered the floor or blocked

05:31:37.740 --> 05:31:38.400
the archway.

05:31:38.459 --> 05:31:40.860
The throne and the columns were there

05:31:40.860 --> 05:31:44.220
looking newly chiseled and smooth, but no

05:31:44.220 --> 05:31:46.799
one sat on the throne, and no plant grew

05:31:46.799 --> 05:31:47.580
from the base of it either.

05:31:47.639 --> 05:31:51.540
This room seemed brand new, untouched by

05:31:51.540 --> 05:31:53.639
the rustling terror Luna associated with

05:31:53.639 --> 05:31:54.000
it.

05:31:54.000 --> 05:31:56.759
Now that she could see the floor, she

05:31:56.759 --> 05:31:57.959
realized it was dirt.

05:31:58.020 --> 05:31:59.880
Not stone, as she might have expected.

05:31:59.939 --> 05:32:03.060
Her claws sank into it, and she was

05:32:03.060 --> 05:32:04.979
surprised by how soft and rich it was.

05:32:05.040 --> 05:32:07.619
This will do.

05:32:07.740 --> 05:32:10.979
Cottonmouth said, sweeping into the space

05:32:10.979 --> 05:32:12.959
and nearly walking straight through Luna

05:32:12.959 --> 05:32:14.279
before she jumped out of the way.

05:32:14.400 --> 05:32:17.340
Three humans crowded in behind him.

05:32:17.400 --> 05:32:20.459
They each carried something, a pot

05:32:20.459 --> 05:32:23.220
overflowing with vines, a bag that

05:32:23.220 --> 05:32:26.159
clanked ominously, and a large wooden box

05:32:26.159 --> 05:32:27.900
with holes in the top that was making

05:32:27.900 --> 05:32:29.400
some very worrying noises.

05:32:29.459 --> 05:32:32.279
Luna had an awful feeling about what was

05:32:32.279 --> 05:32:32.759
in there.

05:32:32.819 --> 05:32:36.599
All is as you ordered, my lord, said one

05:32:36.599 --> 05:32:38.759
of the humans, setting down the bag and

05:32:38.759 --> 05:32:39.599
gesturing at the room.

05:32:39.659 --> 05:32:42.840
Is this really going to work, sir?

05:32:42.900 --> 05:32:45.360
Another human said reverently.

05:32:45.419 --> 05:32:48.720
She was the one carrying the box, and she

05:32:48.720 --> 05:32:50.220
lowered it to the ground in the center of

05:32:50.220 --> 05:32:51.959
the room with gentle caution.

05:32:52.020 --> 05:32:53.759
Of course.

05:32:53.819 --> 05:32:56.220
Cottonmouth waved one hand.

05:32:56.279 --> 05:33:00.360
He was dressed regally again in head to

05:33:00.360 --> 05:33:03.000
toe robes embroidered with silver, plus

05:33:03.000 --> 05:33:04.919
the gold medallions and the feathers in

05:33:04.919 --> 05:33:05.220
his hair.

05:33:05.279 --> 05:33:07.979
But I must not be disturbed.

05:33:08.040 --> 05:33:11.099
You will stay at the top of the abyss, and

05:33:11.099 --> 05:33:12.599
ensure that no one comes down here while

05:33:12.599 --> 05:33:13.020
I work.

05:33:13.080 --> 05:33:16.619
If I need anything, I will speak through

05:33:16.619 --> 05:33:16.979
you.

05:33:17.040 --> 05:33:20.939
Yes, my Lord, said the 1st two.

05:33:21.000 --> 05:33:24.599
The 3rd human, who had not yet spoken, set

05:33:24.599 --> 05:33:26.459
down the pot of vines without a word.

05:33:26.520 --> 05:33:28.619
He looked slightly different from the

05:33:28.619 --> 05:33:31.500
others, more like the ones Luna had seen

05:33:31.500 --> 05:33:33.299
stealing the sea dragon eggs.

05:33:33.360 --> 05:33:36.000
His hair was a pale shade of lime green.

05:33:36.060 --> 05:33:39.119
Cottonmouth narrowed his eyes at the

05:33:39.119 --> 05:33:39.720
silent human.

05:33:39.840 --> 05:33:43.259
A moment later, that human jerked upright

05:33:43.259 --> 05:33:46.200
and turned to face cottonmouth, his eyes

05:33:46.200 --> 05:33:48.840
had an eerie white glaze over them, and

05:33:48.840 --> 05:33:51.779
his gaze was stiff, petrified, in a blank

05:33:51.779 --> 05:33:52.259
expression.

05:33:52.319 --> 05:33:55.979
He awkwardly fell to his knees, bowed his

05:33:55.979 --> 05:33:58.560
head and said, That's better.

05:33:58.680 --> 05:34:02.220
Cottonmouth smiled coldly.

05:34:02.279 --> 05:34:04.740
The human slumped, as if he'd been

05:34:04.740 --> 05:34:05.099
released.

05:34:05.159 --> 05:34:07.799
He staggered to his feet and backed out

05:34:07.799 --> 05:34:09.659
of the room, bowing as he went.

05:34:09.720 --> 05:34:12.659
The other 2 bowed as well and followed.

05:34:12.720 --> 05:34:14.700
Yes.

05:34:14.759 --> 05:34:17.939
Cotton Mouth mused, looking around.

05:34:18.000 --> 05:34:20.220
This will do.

05:34:20.279 --> 05:34:24.299
A perfect place to finally get what I've

05:34:24.299 --> 05:34:25.020
always wanted.

05:34:25.080 --> 05:34:29.159
He took the pot over to the throne and

05:34:29.159 --> 05:34:30.959
transplanted the vines into the dirt

05:34:30.959 --> 05:34:33.599
there, patting them down like a gardener

05:34:33.599 --> 05:34:35.759
who actually cared about his seedlings.

05:34:35.819 --> 05:34:39.779
At last, he stood up and stalked over to

05:34:39.779 --> 05:34:40.020
the box.

05:34:40.080 --> 05:34:43.380
He unlatched the top, and threw it

05:34:43.380 --> 05:34:43.560
aside.

05:34:43.680 --> 05:34:47.939
A small dragon head popped out and hissed

05:34:47.939 --> 05:34:48.360
at him.

05:34:48.419 --> 05:34:51.779
She didn't look like any of the 10 tribes

05:34:51.779 --> 05:34:55.080
Luna had met, or rather, she looked like

05:34:55.080 --> 05:34:56.340
a combination of a few of them.

05:34:56.400 --> 05:34:59.040
Her orange scales could have come from a

05:34:59.040 --> 05:35:00.779
hive wing or a sky wing.

05:35:00.900 --> 05:35:04.799
But her 2 green wings curved like leaves

05:35:04.799 --> 05:35:06.659
and something in the shape of her eyes

05:35:06.659 --> 05:35:08.819
reminded Luna of Queen Glory.

05:35:08.939 --> 05:35:12.180
Don't you hiss at me, lizard.

05:35:12.240 --> 05:35:14.099
Cottonmouth growled.

05:35:14.159 --> 05:35:16.380
He unhooked a chain from inside the box

05:35:16.380 --> 05:35:17.819
and tugged her out.

05:35:17.880 --> 05:35:19.740
The other end wound around her neck.

05:35:19.799 --> 05:35:24.599
He calls her lizard, Dusky said softly.

05:35:24.659 --> 05:35:26.400
But she doesn't like that.

05:35:26.459 --> 05:35:29.459
She wants a real name, one that comes

05:35:29.459 --> 05:35:31.319
from dragons, not humans.

05:35:31.380 --> 05:35:35.159
I can speak for myself, the dragonette

05:35:35.159 --> 05:35:37.860
said, and dragon, looking straight at

05:35:37.860 --> 05:35:38.520
Dusky.

05:35:38.580 --> 05:35:42.959
Chapter 17.

05:35:43.200 --> 05:35:47.639
For a brief, frozen moment, everything in

05:35:47.639 --> 05:35:48.900
the room stopped breathing.

05:35:48.959 --> 05:35:51.779
No, you can't.

05:35:51.840 --> 05:35:54.900
Cottonmouth growled at the dragon inhuman

05:35:54.900 --> 05:35:56.220
breaking the spell.

05:35:56.279 --> 05:35:58.200
Stop interrupting.

05:35:58.259 --> 05:36:02.159
Our guests asked for our origin story.

05:36:02.220 --> 05:36:04.740
And I haven't had a chance to show my

05:36:04.740 --> 05:36:08.040
genius to anyone, since the last guardian

05:36:08.040 --> 05:36:09.000
so you shut up.

05:36:09.060 --> 05:36:11.580
I won't.

05:36:11.700 --> 05:36:12.959
Lizard snapped at him.

05:36:13.020 --> 05:36:15.540
I have been stuck with this story in all

05:36:15.540 --> 05:36:17.939
these memories for 5000 years, and it's

05:36:17.939 --> 05:36:19.919
boring, and I hate it, and I hate you.

05:36:20.040 --> 05:36:22.080
Well.

05:36:22.259 --> 05:36:23.639
He snarled.

05:36:23.759 --> 05:36:27.000
As you well know, the feeling is mutual.

05:36:27.060 --> 05:36:31.020
It is not though, she said, because you

05:36:31.020 --> 05:36:31.680
did this to us.

05:36:31.740 --> 05:36:34.740
So I am entitled to hate you way more

05:36:34.740 --> 05:36:35.340
than you hate me.

05:36:35.400 --> 05:36:39.119
Movement beyond them caught Luna's eye

05:36:39.119 --> 05:36:41.639
and she realized that the vines were

05:36:41.639 --> 05:36:44.400
growing visibly, sprouting new tendrils

05:36:44.400 --> 05:36:46.200
and starting to climb the base of the

05:36:46.200 --> 05:36:46.500
throne.

05:36:46.560 --> 05:36:49.139
Is that supposed to happen?

05:36:49.200 --> 05:36:50.340
She wondered.

05:36:50.400 --> 05:36:53.400
I mean, did they really grow that fast?

05:36:53.459 --> 05:36:55.439
Yes?

05:36:55.560 --> 05:36:57.900
Lizard said venomously.

05:36:57.959 --> 05:36:59.040
Stupid weed.

05:36:59.099 --> 05:37:02.459
Oh, wow, Luna said.

05:37:02.520 --> 05:37:04.319
You really can hear us now?

05:37:04.380 --> 05:37:06.720
This part is actually happening like

05:37:06.720 --> 05:37:07.619
right now?

05:37:07.680 --> 05:37:11.220
Lizard rolled her eyes and stomped over

05:37:11.220 --> 05:37:13.439
to Dusky, dragging Cottonmouth behind

05:37:13.439 --> 05:37:13.680
her.

05:37:13.740 --> 05:37:15.720
We gave you hours.

05:37:15.779 --> 05:37:18.540
Now give me your memories, she ordered.

05:37:18.599 --> 05:37:21.299
She reached out and tapped Desky on the

05:37:21.299 --> 05:37:22.200
head with one of her claws.

05:37:22.259 --> 05:37:24.959
Um, he said.

05:37:25.020 --> 05:37:26.400
I...

05:37:26.400 --> 05:37:27.900
Don't want to?

05:37:28.020 --> 05:37:29.520
And I don't know how.

05:37:29.580 --> 05:37:33.779
You just say yes, she said impatiently.

05:37:33.840 --> 05:37:36.779
When I ask for them, you say yes, and

05:37:36.779 --> 05:37:37.560
then I can see them.

05:37:37.619 --> 05:37:38.520
Give me them.

05:37:38.639 --> 05:37:42.840
No, he said, a little more firmly.

05:37:42.900 --> 05:37:44.580
She scowled at him.

05:37:44.639 --> 05:37:45.720
You're doing it wrong.

05:37:45.779 --> 05:37:48.959
Why would he give you his memories?

05:37:49.020 --> 05:37:50.040
Luna asked.

05:37:50.099 --> 05:37:53.939
Because I want them, Lizard exploded.

05:37:54.000 --> 05:37:56.759
And I am the most miserable dragon who

05:37:56.759 --> 05:37:59.220
ever lived, and then died, and then had

05:37:59.220 --> 05:38:02.220
to half live, half be dead forever, all

05:38:02.220 --> 05:38:04.619
stuck together with a hateful human and a

05:38:04.619 --> 05:38:06.900
desperate weed, so I should get to have

05:38:06.900 --> 05:38:07.680
anything I want.

05:38:07.740 --> 05:38:08.759
Give them.

05:38:08.880 --> 05:38:11.939
Dusky widened his eyes at Luna.

05:38:12.000 --> 05:38:14.459
But how did that happen?

05:38:14.520 --> 05:38:15.599
Luna asked.

05:38:15.659 --> 05:38:17.700
She looked up at the throne.

05:38:17.759 --> 05:38:19.919
And the vines slowly curling around it.

05:38:19.979 --> 05:38:22.200
What's the end of the story?

05:38:22.259 --> 05:38:24.779
What happened?

05:38:24.779 --> 05:38:28.500
Is he was stupid and accidentally let the

05:38:28.500 --> 05:38:29.819
plant get us both.

05:38:29.939 --> 05:38:31.020
Lizard hissed.

05:38:31.080 --> 05:38:33.840
She pointed at the throne, and the scene

05:38:33.840 --> 05:38:34.619
around them shifted.

05:38:34.680 --> 05:38:39.000
For a gray, falling moment, Luna could

05:38:39.000 --> 05:38:40.319
see the plants again all around her.

05:38:40.380 --> 05:38:42.959
And the horrible tableau of the vines

05:38:42.959 --> 05:38:45.000
growing through the human and dragonette

05:38:45.000 --> 05:38:47.040
and then the newer room shivered back

05:38:47.040 --> 05:38:47.459
into place.

05:38:47.520 --> 05:38:50.880
The sensation of vines wrapped tightly

05:38:50.880 --> 05:38:53.099
around her wrists and neck lingered

05:38:53.099 --> 05:38:55.200
though, like the ghost of a strangling.

05:38:55.319 --> 05:38:59.759
No, said Cottonmouth, what happened?

05:38:59.880 --> 05:39:02.819
Is that lizard was insufferable and

05:39:02.819 --> 05:39:04.439
rebellious and ruined everything?

05:39:04.560 --> 05:39:08.459
He inhaled and exhaled slowly.

05:39:08.580 --> 05:39:10.259
But who cares?

05:39:10.319 --> 05:39:11.580
I made it work.

05:39:11.639 --> 05:39:14.459
So what if this meat shell couldn't move

05:39:14.459 --> 05:39:14.880
anymore?

05:39:14.939 --> 05:39:17.939
He waved dismissively at his body.

05:39:18.000 --> 05:39:21.419
I couldn't walk or climb the abyss or go

05:39:21.419 --> 05:39:24.779
outside, but I soon realized that with

05:39:24.779 --> 05:39:27.659
this plant, I could take anyone, be

05:39:27.659 --> 05:39:28.680
anywhere I wanted.

05:39:28.740 --> 05:39:31.619
I could be a 1000 different creatures at

05:39:31.619 --> 05:39:31.860
once.

05:39:31.919 --> 05:39:34.139
The whole continent was mine.

05:39:34.200 --> 05:39:38.459
I was emperor at last of even more than

05:39:38.459 --> 05:39:39.360
I'd expected.

05:39:39.419 --> 05:39:41.459
Ha!

05:39:41.520 --> 05:39:45.000
Emperor of bees and seagulls, Lizard

05:39:45.000 --> 05:39:45.479
snorted.

05:39:45.599 --> 05:39:47.580
There were no dragons here then.

05:39:47.639 --> 05:39:50.279
No one anywhere except your little band

05:39:50.279 --> 05:39:52.619
of shivering cave dwellers, and you kept

05:39:52.619 --> 05:39:54.419
them scared so they wouldn't go outside.

05:39:54.479 --> 05:39:57.540
Cottonmouth curled his fists.

05:39:57.599 --> 05:40:00.119
I kept them safe.

05:40:00.180 --> 05:40:03.659
Otherwise, when the dragons came again

05:40:03.659 --> 05:40:06.000
they would have died, just like everyone

05:40:06.000 --> 05:40:06.720
did last time.

05:40:06.779 --> 05:40:11.459
Dragons, he spat, burning my vines

05:40:11.459 --> 05:40:15.060
destroying my seeds, cutting me back, and

05:40:15.060 --> 05:40:17.939
taking my continent, ruining everything

05:40:17.939 --> 05:40:19.319
like they always do.

05:40:19.380 --> 05:40:24.659
This old wine, Lizard said, rolling her

05:40:24.659 --> 05:40:25.139
eyes.

05:40:25.200 --> 05:40:26.700
You poor human.

05:40:26.759 --> 05:40:29.580
Can't summon a cloud of possessed bats

05:40:29.580 --> 05:40:30.060
anymore?

05:40:30.119 --> 05:40:31.259
What a tragedy.

05:40:31.380 --> 05:40:34.200
I should have wiped out your whole

05:40:34.200 --> 05:40:35.639
species from the start.

05:40:35.700 --> 05:40:38.099
Cottonmouth said grimly.

05:40:38.159 --> 05:40:41.639
You should have left us alone, Luna

05:40:41.639 --> 05:40:42.000
cried.

05:40:42.060 --> 05:40:44.340
The scorching wouldn't have happened if

05:40:44.340 --> 05:40:45.659
you hadn't stolen all those eggs.

05:40:45.720 --> 05:40:48.599
That's where you're wrong.

05:40:48.720 --> 05:40:50.759
Cottonmouth said.

05:40:50.819 --> 05:40:53.099
Swinging around to glower at her.

05:40:53.159 --> 05:40:56.099
Dragons are dangerous by nature.

05:40:56.220 --> 05:40:58.439
They're too big and powerful.

05:40:58.500 --> 05:41:00.959
They would have crawled out of their

05:41:00.959 --> 05:41:03.840
caves and attacked us, and taken our land

05:41:03.840 --> 05:41:04.380
eventually.

05:41:04.439 --> 05:41:07.500
I knew we had to find a way to control

05:41:07.500 --> 05:41:09.900
them before they became too much of a

05:41:09.900 --> 05:41:10.200
threat.

05:41:10.259 --> 05:41:13.919
Well, great job, Luna said.

05:41:13.979 --> 05:41:16.080
Seems like that worked out really well

05:41:16.080 --> 05:41:16.439
for you.

05:41:16.560 --> 05:41:20.580
He glared at her, drawing himself up, and

05:41:20.580 --> 05:41:22.319
twitching the chain with lizard on the

05:41:22.319 --> 05:41:22.740
end of it.

05:41:22.799 --> 05:41:26.639
You seem to have forgotten that I am

05:41:26.639 --> 05:41:27.360
winning this war.

05:41:27.419 --> 05:41:31.200
I have 3 tribes of dragons in my grasp

05:41:31.200 --> 05:41:34.259
and soon, I will reach across the ocean

05:41:34.259 --> 05:41:36.659
and take all the ones on my home

05:41:36.659 --> 05:41:38.040
continent as well.

05:41:38.099 --> 05:41:40.500
Thanks to you and your friends.

05:41:40.560 --> 05:41:42.479
I'll figure out how to get there.

05:41:42.540 --> 05:41:46.560
I'll get sundew, and spread my plant

05:41:46.560 --> 05:41:47.819
across the whole world.

05:41:47.880 --> 05:41:51.959
I'll inject myself into every brain until

05:41:51.959 --> 05:41:55.380
every dragon. and every human belong to

05:41:55.380 --> 05:41:55.619
me.

05:41:55.680 --> 05:41:59.759
You will all be my fingers, my little

05:41:59.759 --> 05:42:00.659
playthings.

05:42:00.720 --> 05:42:01.799
Nothing more.

05:42:01.860 --> 05:42:04.259
Luna paused.

05:42:04.319 --> 05:42:06.479
I'll get sundo.

05:42:06.540 --> 05:42:09.599
He said, I'll get sundew.

05:42:09.659 --> 05:42:11.700
Which means he doesn't have her yet.

05:42:11.759 --> 05:42:14.819
She's still safe from him, wherever she

05:42:14.819 --> 05:42:15.000
is.

05:42:15.060 --> 05:42:18.180
Luna felt a wave of relief.

05:42:18.240 --> 05:42:21.000
As long as sundew was free, there was

05:42:21.000 --> 05:42:21.240
hope.

05:42:21.299 --> 05:42:23.700
There was still someone out there who

05:42:23.700 --> 05:42:25.380
could save blue and sore tail.

05:42:25.439 --> 05:42:28.860
For those all your memories we just saw?

05:42:28.919 --> 05:42:29.819
she asked.

05:42:29.880 --> 05:42:31.740
They couldn't be.

05:42:31.799 --> 05:42:32.639
You weren't in all of them.

05:42:32.700 --> 05:42:36.119
Some of them were lifted from humans.

05:42:36.180 --> 05:42:40.020
I absorbed long ago, he said. ones that

05:42:40.020 --> 05:42:42.360
escaped to this continent with me, and

05:42:42.360 --> 05:42:44.159
then offered themselves to my service.

05:42:44.220 --> 05:42:46.200
Yikes!

05:42:46.259 --> 05:42:47.159
Luna thought.

05:42:47.220 --> 05:42:49.740
Let's just breeze right past the word

05:42:49.740 --> 05:42:51.060
absorbed there.

05:42:51.119 --> 05:42:54.119
I thought the plant couldn't get into our

05:42:54.119 --> 05:42:55.919
minds, she said slowly.

05:42:56.040 --> 05:42:59.040
Cricket said wasp controls the hive

05:42:59.040 --> 05:43:01.139
wing's bodies, but can't hear their

05:43:01.139 --> 05:43:02.639
thoughts or see their memories.

05:43:02.700 --> 05:43:05.099
That is true.

05:43:05.159 --> 05:43:08.159
He said, with a satisfied smile.

05:43:08.279 --> 05:43:11.040
I never told her she could get those.

05:43:11.159 --> 05:43:15.599
She's a clever instrument, but it never

05:43:15.599 --> 05:43:18.299
even occurred to her to try burrowing

05:43:18.299 --> 05:43:19.619
into her puppet's brains.

05:43:19.680 --> 05:43:24.060
Okay, ew, Lizard interjected.

05:43:24.119 --> 05:43:26.459
She wrestled the chain off her neck and

05:43:26.459 --> 05:43:27.119
threw it on the floor.

05:43:27.180 --> 05:43:30.360
Why do you insist on phrasing everything

05:43:30.360 --> 05:43:32.340
in the grossest possible way?

05:43:32.400 --> 05:43:34.380
It doesn't even work like that.

05:43:34.439 --> 05:43:37.020
He can't just dig them out.

05:43:37.080 --> 05:43:38.400
It's like I told you.

05:43:38.459 --> 05:43:41.700
One of us has to ask, and the dragon, or

05:43:41.700 --> 05:43:44.400
human, or scorpion, or slug, or whatever

05:43:44.400 --> 05:43:45.720
has to agree to let us in.

05:43:45.779 --> 05:43:47.340
It's not easy.

05:43:47.400 --> 05:43:50.220
Mostly they say no, and there's nothing

05:43:50.220 --> 05:43:51.000
he can do about it.

05:43:51.060 --> 05:43:51.959
Ha ha.

05:43:52.020 --> 05:43:55.380
My human worshipers tend to be more

05:43:55.380 --> 05:43:57.419
amenable than my dragon toys.

05:43:57.479 --> 05:44:00.599
Cottonmouth said, tapping his fingers

05:44:00.599 --> 05:44:00.840
together.

05:44:00.900 --> 05:44:05.159
But I am about to have 100s of silk wings

05:44:05.159 --> 05:44:07.919
and they are a weak, fearful tribe.

05:44:07.979 --> 05:44:10.500
I'm sure most of them will say yes

05:44:10.500 --> 05:44:12.060
without a moment of resistance.

05:44:12.119 --> 05:44:15.119
Luna hoped that wasn't true.

05:44:15.180 --> 05:44:18.180
Her tribe was gentle, but that didn't

05:44:18.180 --> 05:44:19.259
mean they couldn't be strong.

05:44:19.319 --> 05:44:22.619
Blue was the gentlest, sweetest dragon

05:44:22.619 --> 05:44:24.779
she knew, but he would put up a fight

05:44:24.779 --> 05:44:25.500
when it mattered.

05:44:25.560 --> 05:44:26.939
She was sure of it.

05:44:27.000 --> 05:44:29.459
They were like strands of silk.

05:44:29.520 --> 05:44:32.880
Soft and insubstantial on their own, maybe

05:44:32.880 --> 05:44:35.040
but when you wove them together, they

05:44:35.040 --> 05:44:36.419
could support 100s of dragons.

05:44:36.540 --> 05:44:39.959
I don't understand how this works, she

05:44:39.959 --> 05:44:42.060
said, turning toward lizard.

05:44:42.119 --> 05:44:44.040
If you're all stuck together.

05:44:44.099 --> 05:44:46.259
Do you control anything?

05:44:46.319 --> 05:44:47.459
Does the plant?

05:44:47.520 --> 05:44:49.500
Or is that human the one doing

05:44:49.500 --> 05:44:49.979
everything?

05:44:50.040 --> 05:44:54.060
The plant just wants to spread as far as

05:44:54.060 --> 05:44:57.000
it can, Lizard said, wrinkling her nose.

05:44:57.119 --> 05:45:00.119
It doesn't have thoughts exactly, and it

05:45:00.119 --> 05:45:02.939
can't do anything on its own, but I feel

05:45:02.939 --> 05:45:04.439
it inside me all the time.

05:45:04.500 --> 05:45:07.799
Wriggling and starving and grasping for

05:45:07.799 --> 05:45:09.180
any hold it can get.

05:45:09.240 --> 05:45:11.759
Any scrap of dirt in the world where it

05:45:11.759 --> 05:45:13.080
can slither another root.

05:45:13.139 --> 05:45:15.240
It's more alive than we are.

05:45:15.299 --> 05:45:18.360
But it uses our brains to scheme and plan

05:45:18.360 --> 05:45:20.700
and spread, and to control anything

05:45:20.700 --> 05:45:22.740
smarter than it is, which is most

05:45:22.740 --> 05:45:23.040
everything.

05:45:23.159 --> 05:45:26.159
My brain.

05:45:26.279 --> 05:45:28.740
Cottonmouth corrected her smugly.

05:45:28.799 --> 05:45:30.720
You are pointless here.

05:45:30.779 --> 05:45:35.759
A flare of rage seized Lizard's face, and

05:45:35.759 --> 05:45:37.740
she darted toward him, lashing out with

05:45:37.740 --> 05:45:38.279
her claws.

05:45:38.340 --> 05:45:41.400
A long, sharp stick appeared in his hands

05:45:41.400 --> 05:45:43.979
he jabbed her with it, knocking her back

05:45:43.979 --> 05:45:46.200
toward Dusky, and she tumbled into a ball

05:45:46.200 --> 05:45:47.759
and lay there growling.

05:45:47.819 --> 05:45:51.060
I control some things.

05:45:51.119 --> 05:45:53.939
Lizard said, breathing in short gasps.

05:45:54.000 --> 05:45:56.400
I got myself a new toy.

05:45:56.459 --> 05:45:58.799
She flicked her tail at Dusky.

05:45:58.860 --> 05:46:01.139
That was an accident.

05:46:01.259 --> 05:46:04.680
Cottonmouth hung lizard's chain on a loop

05:46:04.680 --> 05:46:07.380
on the wall, folded his arms, and frowned

05:46:07.380 --> 05:46:08.040
at Dusky.

05:46:08.099 --> 05:46:10.380
And a distraction.

05:46:10.619 --> 05:46:12.360
We should probably kill it right now.

05:46:12.419 --> 05:46:16.380
No, Lizard shrieked.

05:46:16.439 --> 05:46:18.299
He's mine, mine, mine.

05:46:18.360 --> 05:46:20.040
You're a hateful bag of worms.

05:46:20.099 --> 05:46:22.259
If you hurt him, I'm going to let her

05:46:22.259 --> 05:46:22.500
go.

05:46:22.619 --> 05:46:24.900
She pointed at Luna.

05:46:24.959 --> 05:46:28.919
I don't need your tantrums right now.

05:46:28.979 --> 05:46:30.779
Cottonmouth hissed.

05:46:30.900 --> 05:46:34.860
We are this close to taking over the

05:46:34.860 --> 05:46:35.880
world, brat.

05:46:35.939 --> 05:46:38.580
I want them!

05:46:38.700 --> 05:46:41.520
Lizard yelled, stamping one of her feet.

05:46:41.580 --> 05:46:43.319
I want to play with them.

05:46:43.380 --> 05:46:45.779
You go stuff your nostrils with

05:46:45.779 --> 05:46:46.319
mushrooms.

05:46:46.439 --> 05:46:49.439
Cottonmouth rubbed his eyebrows

05:46:49.439 --> 05:46:50.159
grimacing.

05:46:50.220 --> 05:46:55.259
If you can shut up and stay out of my

05:46:55.259 --> 05:46:55.680
way.

05:46:55.799 --> 05:46:59.819
He growled, you can keep them, for now.

05:46:59.880 --> 05:47:03.180
But I have a lot of work to do, so they

05:47:03.180 --> 05:47:04.560
had better not be a problem.

05:47:04.680 --> 05:47:08.819
They won't be, Lizard said, suddenly calm

05:47:08.819 --> 05:47:09.000
again.

05:47:09.119 --> 05:47:12.119
Go away and do your boring things.

05:47:12.180 --> 05:47:16.080
Cottonmouth snorted, and strode across

05:47:16.080 --> 05:47:16.619
the throne room.

05:47:16.680 --> 05:47:19.439
He climbed a set of steps carved into the

05:47:19.439 --> 05:47:21.720
side of the base, settled himself on the

05:47:21.720 --> 05:47:24.599
throne, rested his hands on his knees, and

05:47:24.599 --> 05:47:25.319
closed his eyes.

05:47:25.380 --> 05:47:27.659
There was a pause.

05:47:27.720 --> 05:47:30.299
Lizard glared at the oblivious human.

05:47:30.360 --> 05:47:32.939
Switching her tail furiously back and

05:47:32.939 --> 05:47:33.840
forth across the floor.

05:47:33.900 --> 05:47:36.180
What's happening?

05:47:36.240 --> 05:47:37.259
Luna asked.

05:47:37.380 --> 05:47:40.259
He's checking on all his creatures.

05:47:40.380 --> 05:47:42.599
Lizard rolled her eyes.

05:47:42.659 --> 05:47:46.080
He thinks he's so great, controlling a

05:47:46.080 --> 05:47:48.779
1000 bodies at once, but it gets way

05:47:48.779 --> 05:47:51.119
harder the more there are, especially

05:47:51.119 --> 05:47:53.819
when they're smarter than like mice or

05:47:53.819 --> 05:47:54.779
centipedes.

05:47:54.840 --> 05:47:58.139
Usually he has Queen Wasp helping him, but

05:47:58.139 --> 05:48:00.060
she only manages the ones she injected.

05:48:00.119 --> 05:48:02.759
So he has to control all these new silk

05:48:02.759 --> 05:48:04.020
wings and leaf wings himself.

05:48:04.080 --> 05:48:06.959
If he doesn't, keep his boot pressing on

05:48:06.959 --> 05:48:08.939
them all the time, they try to escape.

05:48:09.000 --> 05:48:11.880
I mean, they can't, but they'll try.

05:48:11.939 --> 05:48:14.159
And then he'll have to focus on them and

05:48:14.159 --> 05:48:14.700
fly them back.

05:48:14.759 --> 05:48:17.819
It makes him tired and grouchy, and it's

05:48:17.819 --> 05:48:18.720
very funny to watch.

05:48:18.840 --> 05:48:22.259
How are you able to speak dragon?

05:48:22.319 --> 05:48:23.279
Luna asked.

05:48:23.340 --> 05:48:26.220
And why do we understand him and the

05:48:26.220 --> 05:48:27.840
people in the story, who were speaking

05:48:27.840 --> 05:48:28.860
human?

05:48:28.919 --> 05:48:31.500
I learned it from the dragons he's taken

05:48:31.500 --> 05:48:32.040
over the years.

05:48:32.159 --> 05:48:35.159
Lizard said, as if that were so very

05:48:35.159 --> 05:48:36.659
obviously obvious.

05:48:36.720 --> 05:48:40.200
And you're in our mind space now, so you

05:48:40.200 --> 05:48:42.180
see and hear and understand anything we

05:48:42.180 --> 05:48:42.659
want you to.

05:48:42.720 --> 05:48:45.180
Mind space?

05:48:45.240 --> 05:48:46.680
Dusky echoed.

05:48:46.799 --> 05:48:49.259
Lizard waved impatiently at the walls.

05:48:49.319 --> 05:48:51.599
The place we are stuck.

05:48:51.659 --> 05:48:54.240
Where our minds go so we can talk to each

05:48:54.240 --> 05:48:54.419
other.

05:48:54.479 --> 05:48:56.819
We can make it look however we like.

05:48:56.880 --> 05:49:00.540
Luna glanced to the cold, empty walls of

05:49:00.540 --> 05:49:01.139
the throne room.

05:49:01.200 --> 05:49:03.419
You both can?

05:49:03.479 --> 05:49:06.000
If you have a choice, why would you make

05:49:06.000 --> 05:49:07.439
it look like the place where you're

05:49:07.439 --> 05:49:08.040
actually stuck?

05:49:08.099 --> 05:49:11.520
I suppose we could do this instead.

05:49:11.580 --> 05:49:15.060
Lizard said, in a bored voice.

05:49:15.119 --> 05:49:17.159
And suddenly they were standing in a

05:49:17.159 --> 05:49:19.380
silkwing playground, outside a school

05:49:19.380 --> 05:49:22.200
that said, Weaver Hall on it, with a

05:49:22.200 --> 05:49:24.240
balcony open to the clear blue Savannah

05:49:24.240 --> 05:49:25.200
sky off to their right.

05:49:25.259 --> 05:49:28.500
The only incongruous part was Cottonmouth

05:49:28.500 --> 05:49:30.779
who was now sitting in the same position

05:49:30.779 --> 05:49:33.180
with the same expression, at the top of a

05:49:33.180 --> 05:49:34.139
slide.

05:49:34.200 --> 05:49:36.299
Dusky yelped with surprise.

05:49:36.360 --> 05:49:39.540
This is my school, my playground.

05:49:39.599 --> 05:49:43.020
Boring though, Lizard said.

05:49:43.080 --> 05:49:45.840
It's not real, and I can't really play

05:49:45.840 --> 05:49:47.400
here or have real friends.

05:49:47.459 --> 05:49:49.500
So what is even the point?

05:49:49.560 --> 05:49:52.799
Dusky gave Lizard a wide-eyed look?

05:49:52.860 --> 05:49:55.259
How do you know this place?

05:49:55.319 --> 05:49:57.360
Did you get my memories?

05:49:57.419 --> 05:49:59.400
Not yet.

05:49:59.459 --> 05:50:00.540
She snapped.

05:50:00.599 --> 05:50:03.900
You have to let me have them, you bozo.

05:50:03.959 --> 05:50:06.000
But I've seen this place through hive

05:50:06.000 --> 05:50:06.599
wing eyes.

05:50:06.659 --> 05:50:07.919
I saw you here.

05:50:07.979 --> 05:50:09.900
I used to watch you whenever I wanted

05:50:09.900 --> 05:50:10.200
to.

05:50:10.319 --> 05:50:15.360
That's heebie jeebie, Dusky said, frowning

05:50:15.360 --> 05:50:15.720
at her.

05:50:15.779 --> 05:50:18.959
That gives me the heebie jeebies.

05:50:19.020 --> 05:50:21.479
Luna corrected him, and he transferred

05:50:21.479 --> 05:50:23.939
his frown to her, with an extra dose of

05:50:23.939 --> 05:50:26.159
what on earth are you talking about on

05:50:26.159 --> 05:50:26.459
top?

05:50:26.520 --> 05:50:30.000
So, you can see through the eyes of

05:50:30.000 --> 05:50:31.919
anyone who's been infected by the plant?

05:50:31.979 --> 05:50:33.659
Luna asked Lizard.

05:50:33.720 --> 05:50:36.779
Like, right now, you could jump into

05:50:36.779 --> 05:50:38.159
someone and see what they see.

05:50:38.220 --> 05:50:43.680
Yes, she said, in that same bored tone.

05:50:43.740 --> 05:50:44.880
Fine.

05:50:44.939 --> 05:50:45.659
Who?

05:50:45.779 --> 05:50:49.619
His name is SoreTail, Luna said

05:50:49.619 --> 05:50:49.919
hopefully.

05:50:49.979 --> 05:50:51.720
He's a silkwing.

05:50:51.779 --> 05:50:52.979
In cicada hive right now?

05:50:53.040 --> 05:50:55.020
With my brother, Blue?

05:50:55.139 --> 05:50:58.380
Hmm, Lizard said.

05:50:58.439 --> 05:51:01.080
She shot Luna a sly sideways look.

05:51:01.139 --> 05:51:04.680
If you give me your memories, I'll know

05:51:04.680 --> 05:51:06.479
what he looks like, and it'll be easy to

05:51:06.479 --> 05:51:06.840
find him.

05:51:06.900 --> 05:51:09.419
I don't think I should do that.

05:51:09.479 --> 05:51:10.680
Luna said.

05:51:10.740 --> 05:51:13.080
Not if that means Cottonmouth can have

05:51:13.080 --> 05:51:13.439
them too.

05:51:13.500 --> 05:51:16.439
Besides, you definitely know blue and

05:51:16.439 --> 05:51:17.040
sword tail.

05:51:17.099 --> 05:51:18.360
They've been part of all the trouble

05:51:18.360 --> 05:51:18.779
lately.

05:51:18.840 --> 05:51:21.240
Yeah, I do.

05:51:21.299 --> 05:51:23.639
Lizard said, dropping the act.

05:51:23.700 --> 05:51:26.939
I've never seen Cottonmouth so angry.

05:51:27.000 --> 05:51:28.979
I hoped he would have some kind of

05:51:28.979 --> 05:51:30.479
apoplexy attack and die.

05:51:30.540 --> 05:51:33.479
She closed her eyes and put one claw to

05:51:33.479 --> 05:51:33.840
her temple.

05:51:33.900 --> 05:51:36.479
What would happen to you if he did?

05:51:36.540 --> 05:51:37.680
Luna asked.

05:51:37.740 --> 05:51:40.259
Knowing my luck, it would be too much

05:51:40.259 --> 05:51:42.360
happiness for me to handle, and I would

05:51:42.360 --> 05:51:43.919
probably immediately also die.

05:51:44.040 --> 05:51:46.380
Of joy, Lizard said.

05:51:46.439 --> 05:51:48.000
Here they are.

05:51:48.060 --> 05:51:51.000
Luna felt dizzy from the sudden

05:51:51.000 --> 05:51:52.560
transition to another new place.

05:51:52.619 --> 05:51:55.080
It took her a moment to recognize the

05:51:55.080 --> 05:51:56.400
market in cicada hive.

05:51:56.520 --> 05:51:58.799
She'd never seen it from up on one of the

05:51:58.799 --> 05:52:00.060
guard balconies before.

05:52:00.119 --> 05:52:02.819
The murals and posters of Queen Wasp

05:52:02.819 --> 05:52:05.459
still loomed overhead, and the flame silk

05:52:05.459 --> 05:52:08.099
lanterns glowed as they always had, but

05:52:08.099 --> 05:52:10.020
an eerie quiet filled the cavernous

05:52:10.020 --> 05:52:10.259
space.

05:52:10.380 --> 05:52:12.900
All the shops along the outer wall were

05:52:12.900 --> 05:52:14.099
closed and barricaded.

05:52:14.159 --> 05:52:16.799
From here, Luna could see the empty

05:52:16.799 --> 05:52:19.560
windows of The Sugar Dream, where she and

05:52:19.560 --> 05:52:21.180
Blue had gone to get honey drops on her

05:52:21.180 --> 05:52:22.200
metamorphosis day.

05:52:22.259 --> 05:52:25.500
The last normal day will maybe ever

05:52:25.500 --> 05:52:25.860
have.

05:52:25.979 --> 05:52:29.340
Instead of busy stalls and bustling

05:52:29.340 --> 05:52:29.880
shoppers.

05:52:29.939 --> 05:52:32.459
The center of the market held 100s of

05:52:32.459 --> 05:52:35.220
quiet, seated silk wings, their heads

05:52:35.220 --> 05:52:37.319
were bowed, and their wings were folded

05:52:37.319 --> 05:52:37.560
down.

05:52:37.560 --> 05:52:40.619
Several had tiny wingless dragonettes

05:52:40.619 --> 05:52:42.419
sitting between their front talons

05:52:42.419 --> 05:52:43.680
leaning against their legs.

05:52:43.740 --> 05:52:46.319
A few silk wings were walking between the

05:52:46.319 --> 05:52:49.380
dragons, handing out dried seaweed, and

05:52:49.380 --> 05:52:51.659
packets of nuts tied up in twists of

05:52:51.659 --> 05:52:51.959
silk.

05:52:52.020 --> 05:52:55.680
Beside Luna on the balcony, Lizard

05:52:55.680 --> 05:52:57.900
flicked her tail, staring down at the

05:52:57.900 --> 05:52:58.619
dragons below.

05:52:58.680 --> 05:53:01.979
Dusky stood on her other side, clutching

05:53:01.979 --> 05:53:02.880
the railing nervously.

05:53:02.939 --> 05:53:05.819
Across the hive, Luna could see

05:53:05.819 --> 05:53:08.040
Cottonmouth sitting on another balcony

05:53:08.040 --> 05:53:09.419
eyes still closed.

05:53:09.479 --> 05:53:13.500
Are you inside sore tail right now?

05:53:13.560 --> 05:53:14.700
Luna asked.

05:53:14.759 --> 05:53:17.759
Lizard scoffed.

05:53:17.819 --> 05:53:20.099
No, I'm in hive wing.

05:53:20.159 --> 05:53:22.020
It would be stupid to jump into him

05:53:22.020 --> 05:53:23.639
because then you'd only see me.

05:53:23.700 --> 05:53:26.880
No, your dopey dream boat is down there.

05:53:26.939 --> 05:53:30.240
She pointed to the exit across from them

05:53:30.240 --> 05:53:32.580
which led to the spiraling tunnels that

05:53:32.580 --> 05:53:33.659
connected the hive levels.

05:53:33.720 --> 05:53:37.500
Standing in the entryway, holding a spear

05:53:37.500 --> 05:53:40.619
looking burly and blank, was sore tail

05:53:40.619 --> 05:53:43.200
and right next to him, looking much less

05:53:43.200 --> 05:53:45.360
burly but equally blank, was blue.

05:53:45.419 --> 05:53:47.880
Luna gasped.

05:53:47.939 --> 05:53:49.799
It was bad enough to know they were

05:53:49.799 --> 05:53:52.439
possessed by the queen, or by cotton

05:53:52.439 --> 05:53:54.659
mouth and lizard, and the breath of evil

05:53:54.659 --> 05:53:56.880
however that worked, but it was

05:53:56.880 --> 05:53:57.720
heartbreaking to see it.

05:53:57.779 --> 05:54:02.459
Soretail, she breathed, leaning over the

05:54:02.459 --> 05:54:02.939
edge.

05:54:03.000 --> 05:54:06.540
He looked thinner, and so tired, but so

05:54:06.540 --> 05:54:07.319
perfectly himself.

05:54:07.380 --> 05:54:10.680
Even zombie sword tail looked like he

05:54:10.680 --> 05:54:12.419
might tell a funny story, or start

05:54:12.419 --> 05:54:13.319
laughing at any moment.

05:54:13.380 --> 05:54:16.860
It wasn't completely gone, the spark in

05:54:16.860 --> 05:54:19.020
his eyes, or the tiny smile at the corner

05:54:19.020 --> 05:54:19.500
of his mouth.

05:54:19.560 --> 05:54:22.680
Unless Luna was imagining things from a

05:54:22.680 --> 05:54:22.979
distance.

05:54:23.099 --> 05:54:26.279
But she kind of had to. so that she

05:54:26.279 --> 05:54:27.000
wouldn't fall apart.

05:54:27.060 --> 05:54:29.819
Don't bother flying over there.

05:54:29.880 --> 05:54:33.180
He can't hear you, Lizard said, guessing

05:54:33.180 --> 05:54:34.020
Luna's thoughts.

05:54:34.080 --> 05:54:36.540
Not unless I come along and make this

05:54:36.540 --> 05:54:38.400
hive wing say whatever you want to say

05:54:38.400 --> 05:54:40.500
which would freak him out and be so

05:54:40.500 --> 05:54:41.340
funny.

05:54:41.400 --> 05:54:43.740
Imagine, a hive wing guard suddenly

05:54:43.740 --> 05:54:48.240
proclaiming, oh, sore tail, I love you

05:54:48.240 --> 05:54:51.060
look at your dreamy snout.

05:54:51.119 --> 05:54:51.840
Ha.

05:54:51.900 --> 05:54:53.099
This is a great idea.

05:54:53.159 --> 05:54:53.700
Let's do it.

05:54:53.759 --> 05:54:55.860
Yeesh.

05:54:55.919 --> 05:54:57.479
Luna said with a shudder.

05:54:57.540 --> 05:54:59.340
Maybe as a last resort.

05:54:59.459 --> 05:55:01.560
Can't you bring him into this mind

05:55:01.560 --> 05:55:02.220
space?

05:55:02.279 --> 05:55:03.419
Like the 2 of us?

05:55:03.479 --> 05:55:05.580
She gestured to Dusky.

05:55:05.639 --> 05:55:09.060
Lizard sighed for an unnaturally long

05:55:09.060 --> 05:55:09.299
time.

05:55:09.419 --> 05:55:13.139
I could, she said finally.

05:55:13.200 --> 05:55:15.599
But it would be so exhausting.

05:55:15.659 --> 05:55:17.759
It's easier when you're already in the

05:55:17.759 --> 05:55:18.540
same room as me.

05:55:18.599 --> 05:55:21.720
He's like, all the way across the

05:55:21.720 --> 05:55:22.380
continent.

05:55:22.439 --> 05:55:24.240
Blech, not worth it.

05:55:24.299 --> 05:55:27.119
Please, Luna said.

05:55:27.240 --> 05:55:29.159
I just want to talk to him for a moment

05:55:29.159 --> 05:55:30.840
to let him know I'm all right.

05:55:30.900 --> 05:55:34.259
This earned her skeptical, assessing look

05:55:34.259 --> 05:55:35.220
from the small dragon.

05:55:35.340 --> 05:55:37.380
You're really not, though.

05:55:37.439 --> 05:55:39.060
Lizard pointed out.

05:55:39.119 --> 05:55:41.759
You're trapped in vines in an ancient

05:55:41.759 --> 05:55:43.500
throne room at the bottom of the abyss

05:55:43.500 --> 05:55:46.080
and you've been infected by the plant, and

05:55:46.080 --> 05:55:47.580
you're definitely going to die down here

05:55:47.580 --> 05:55:49.979
and then your bones will decompose and

05:55:49.979 --> 05:55:50.700
feed our roots.

05:55:50.819 --> 05:55:52.979
Won't you find that pretty depressing?

05:55:53.040 --> 05:55:56.220
Luna had no idea what to say to that.

05:55:56.279 --> 05:55:59.040
She hadn't quite accepted the idea that

05:55:59.040 --> 05:56:01.500
she was really trapped in vines, or even

05:56:01.500 --> 05:56:02.939
infected by the breath of evil.

05:56:03.000 --> 05:56:06.180
She felt like she was really here, not

05:56:06.180 --> 05:56:06.720
really there.

05:56:06.779 --> 05:56:10.500
She felt entirely herself, not possessed

05:56:10.500 --> 05:56:11.099
by anyone else.

05:56:11.159 --> 05:56:14.340
But she knew these weren't really her

05:56:14.340 --> 05:56:14.759
talons.

05:56:14.819 --> 05:56:18.840
She knew this was only her mind, floating

05:56:18.840 --> 05:56:20.880
in the weird vision space that Lizard and

05:56:20.880 --> 05:56:21.779
Cottonmouth had created.

05:56:21.840 --> 05:56:24.720
She had been fiercely avoiding the mental

05:56:24.720 --> 05:56:26.520
image of her body trapped in the vines.

05:56:26.580 --> 05:56:28.560
Asel?

05:56:28.619 --> 05:56:30.360
I'm not sure we could even reach your

05:56:30.360 --> 05:56:31.200
brother to get him here.

05:56:31.319 --> 05:56:34.919
Lizard went on, in such a, this is a

05:56:34.919 --> 05:56:37.259
totally normal conversation voice, that

05:56:37.259 --> 05:56:38.880
Luna almost wanted to throw her off the

05:56:38.880 --> 05:56:39.360
balcony.

05:56:39.419 --> 05:56:43.319
He's buried himself way down, even when

05:56:43.319 --> 05:56:45.659
we're not inside him, he barely reacts to

05:56:45.659 --> 05:56:45.900
anything.

05:56:45.959 --> 05:56:48.360
Sortell is making sure he eats.

05:56:48.419 --> 05:56:52.020
I thought Blue was boring before, but now

05:56:52.020 --> 05:56:53.099
he's like a piece of furniture.

05:56:53.220 --> 05:56:56.220
Pretty but super boring furniture.

05:56:56.279 --> 05:56:58.619
Lizard side.

05:56:58.680 --> 05:57:00.720
All these dragons are boring.

05:57:00.779 --> 05:57:03.720
Look at how sad and mopey and pathetic

05:57:03.720 --> 05:57:03.959
they are.

05:57:04.020 --> 05:57:06.180
I thought everything would be more fun

05:57:06.180 --> 05:57:08.880
once we had some shimmery silk wings to

05:57:08.880 --> 05:57:09.180
play with.

05:57:09.240 --> 05:57:12.000
But instead, it's going to be exactly the

05:57:12.000 --> 05:57:12.240
same.

05:57:12.299 --> 05:57:15.000
That's really mean.

05:57:15.060 --> 05:57:17.220
Dusky said out of nowhere.

05:57:17.279 --> 05:57:19.799
Lizard gave him a surprised look.

05:57:19.860 --> 05:57:23.400
Not in, oh no, I didn't realize I was

05:57:23.400 --> 05:57:25.139
being a jerk, kind of surprise.

05:57:25.200 --> 05:57:28.200
More like, oh, you talk and have

05:57:28.200 --> 05:57:28.919
opinions?

05:57:28.919 --> 05:57:30.540
That's disappointing.

05:57:30.599 --> 05:57:31.560
Kind of surprise.

05:57:31.619 --> 05:57:35.700
Yeah, I agree, Luna said.

05:57:35.759 --> 05:57:36.779
Really mean.

05:57:36.840 --> 05:57:38.880
Don't you feel bad for these dragons?

05:57:38.939 --> 05:57:40.799
Bad for them?

05:57:40.860 --> 05:57:42.959
Lizard suddenly yelled.

05:57:43.020 --> 05:57:44.759
Bad for them?

05:57:44.819 --> 05:57:46.080
Are you kidding me?

05:57:46.139 --> 05:57:49.799
Her rage shot them back into the throne

05:57:49.799 --> 05:57:49.979
room.

05:57:50.040 --> 05:57:53.159
Luna felt her real body slammed sideways

05:57:53.159 --> 05:57:55.680
into a wall, vines tightening around her

05:57:55.680 --> 05:57:55.979
throat.

05:57:56.040 --> 05:57:59.159
Her vision flickered from the mind space

05:57:59.159 --> 05:58:01.319
to the real room and its swarm of

05:58:01.319 --> 05:58:03.180
tendrils, then back to the empty room

05:58:03.180 --> 05:58:03.479
again.

05:58:03.540 --> 05:58:07.259
Don't hurt her, Dusky shouted.

05:58:07.319 --> 05:58:10.200
He tried to grab lizard, but she kicked

05:58:10.200 --> 05:58:12.240
him away from her and hissed, flaring her

05:58:12.240 --> 05:58:12.659
wings.

05:58:12.720 --> 05:58:16.380
Why would I ever feel bad for anyone

05:58:16.380 --> 05:58:16.560
else?

05:58:16.680 --> 05:58:18.119
Lizard shrieked.

05:58:18.180 --> 05:58:20.880
Those dragons can fly and have friends

05:58:20.880 --> 05:58:24.060
and breathe real air and eat actual food

05:58:24.060 --> 05:58:27.180
and have their own thoughts with nobody

05:58:27.180 --> 05:58:28.080
listening.

05:58:28.139 --> 05:58:31.080
They aren't trapped with a narcissistic

05:58:31.080 --> 05:58:33.599
monster human for all of eternity.

05:58:33.659 --> 05:58:36.959
My life is the most unfair and the most

05:58:36.959 --> 05:58:37.319
sad.

05:58:37.380 --> 05:58:39.540
They should feel bad for me.

05:58:39.659 --> 05:58:41.459
I do.

05:58:41.520 --> 05:58:44.939
Luna managed to choke out, as the real

05:58:44.939 --> 05:58:46.139
throne room appeared again.

05:58:46.200 --> 05:58:48.779
Looming around her like rustling gray

05:58:48.779 --> 05:58:49.139
death.

05:58:49.200 --> 05:58:52.020
The pressure on her neck lessened.

05:58:52.080 --> 05:58:55.139
She took in a gasping breath, and then

05:58:55.139 --> 05:58:56.939
she was back in the false mind space

05:58:56.939 --> 05:58:59.400
throne room, facing Lizard and Dusky.

05:58:59.459 --> 05:59:01.439
You agree?

05:59:01.500 --> 05:59:02.819
My life is the worst.

05:59:02.939 --> 05:59:05.159
Lizard asked her suspiciously.

05:59:05.220 --> 05:59:08.520
Luna nodded, trying to breathe her racing

05:59:08.520 --> 05:59:09.900
heartbeat back to normal.

05:59:09.959 --> 05:59:12.419
Can't we get you out?

05:59:12.479 --> 05:59:15.540
Desky asked the furious dragonette.

05:59:15.599 --> 05:59:18.299
Lizard lashed her tail and narrowed her

05:59:18.299 --> 05:59:18.720
eyes at him.

05:59:18.779 --> 05:59:21.959
Is there a way to set you free?

05:59:22.020 --> 05:59:25.200
A low chuckle came from the human on the

05:59:25.200 --> 05:59:27.479
throne, and lizard shot a glare at him

05:59:27.479 --> 05:59:27.659
too.

05:59:27.720 --> 05:59:30.360
We're only alive.

05:59:30.419 --> 05:59:31.979
If you can call it that.

05:59:32.099 --> 05:59:34.380
Because of the plant, she said.

05:59:34.500 --> 05:59:37.200
We'd all die if we were separated.

05:59:37.259 --> 05:59:40.020
Anyway, I don't need to be set free.

05:59:40.139 --> 05:59:42.959
Here, I get to make his life worse.

05:59:43.020 --> 05:59:46.439
She stuck out her tongue at Cottonmouth.

05:59:46.500 --> 05:59:51.119
You are insignificant to me, he said

05:59:51.119 --> 05:59:53.040
coldly, without opening his eyes.

05:59:53.099 --> 05:59:56.639
He can say whatever he wants, but I can

05:59:56.639 --> 05:59:59.040
feel what he's feeling, Lizard said.

05:59:59.099 --> 06:00:03.180
I torment him, just existing alongside

06:00:03.180 --> 06:00:06.180
his brain, having a dragon clawing around

06:00:06.180 --> 06:00:09.599
in his head, listening to me talk all day

06:00:09.599 --> 06:00:11.759
and he can't do anything about it.

06:00:11.819 --> 06:00:15.419
All this power, and all these creatures.

06:00:15.479 --> 06:00:18.119
But he can never get away from me, and

06:00:18.119 --> 06:00:19.380
how much I hate him.

06:00:19.439 --> 06:00:22.500
Perhaps you could not be a brat.

06:00:22.560 --> 06:00:25.919
For one solitary shining minute of your

06:00:25.919 --> 06:00:28.020
life, said Cottonmouth.

06:00:28.080 --> 06:00:30.360
He stood up and shook out his robes.

06:00:30.360 --> 06:00:33.360
I think Luna would enjoy a little show

06:00:33.360 --> 06:00:34.259
don't you?

06:00:34.319 --> 06:00:38.159
Ooh, ooh, Lizard said.

06:00:38.220 --> 06:00:40.139
Do we get to watch all your stupid

06:00:40.139 --> 06:00:40.979
memories again?

06:00:41.040 --> 06:00:42.840
Could we be so blessed?

06:00:42.900 --> 06:00:46.619
If only you had any interesting memories

06:00:46.619 --> 06:00:47.159
of your own?

06:00:47.220 --> 06:00:49.319
He said dispassionately.

06:00:49.380 --> 06:00:51.000
Oh, that's right.

06:00:51.060 --> 06:00:53.159
You died before making any.

06:00:53.220 --> 06:00:56.880
Lizard snapped her jaw shut, and clenched

06:00:56.880 --> 06:00:57.659
her talons.

06:00:57.720 --> 06:01:00.599
It's time for a lovely experiment.

06:01:00.659 --> 06:01:03.659
Cottonmouth said, coming down the steps

06:01:03.659 --> 06:01:05.459
from the throne, rubbing his hands

06:01:05.459 --> 06:01:05.819
together.

06:01:05.880 --> 06:01:09.000
I know we're all wondering whether the

06:01:09.000 --> 06:01:11.340
mind control will work on dragons from

06:01:11.340 --> 06:01:14.279
what is it you call my old home?

06:01:14.340 --> 06:01:16.200
The distant kingdoms?

06:01:16.319 --> 06:01:19.020
Let's find out, shall we?

06:01:19.080 --> 06:01:21.119
He snapped his fingers.

06:01:21.180 --> 06:01:24.840
The room folded away, and a new scene

06:01:24.840 --> 06:01:25.860
flickered up around them.

06:01:25.919 --> 06:01:27.959
They were inside a hive.

06:01:27.959 --> 06:01:30.119
Luna realized by the patterns on the

06:01:30.119 --> 06:01:30.419
walls.

06:01:30.479 --> 06:01:34.200
The view out the windows also told her

06:01:34.200 --> 06:01:36.119
they were on one of the highest levels of

06:01:36.119 --> 06:01:38.700
this hive and near a coastline.

06:01:38.759 --> 06:01:42.360
The savannah was gold and rust colored in

06:01:42.360 --> 06:01:43.259
the sunset light.

06:01:43.319 --> 06:01:46.020
A flight of swallows swept in arcs around

06:01:46.020 --> 06:01:48.540
the sky, like in a tapestry Luna had

06:01:48.540 --> 06:01:50.040
woven for art class long ago.

06:01:50.099 --> 06:01:53.819
Queen Wasp sat coiled on a polished

06:01:53.819 --> 06:01:54.840
obsidian throne.

06:01:54.900 --> 06:01:57.180
Lizards stood on one side of her

06:01:57.180 --> 06:02:01.139
cottonmouth on the other, and crouched in

06:02:01.139 --> 06:02:03.299
front of them, bound with the breath of

06:02:03.299 --> 06:02:07.080
evil vines, were tsunami, pineapple, and

06:02:07.080 --> 06:02:07.740
Kibli.

06:02:07.799 --> 06:02:11.939
Chapter 18.

06:02:12.119 --> 06:02:14.580
Oh, no.

06:02:14.700 --> 06:02:16.080
Luna breathed.

06:02:16.139 --> 06:02:18.959
She darted forward, but none of the 3

06:02:18.959 --> 06:02:21.119
Pyrean dragons reacted to her presence

06:02:21.119 --> 06:02:23.340
and when she reached for their talons

06:02:23.340 --> 06:02:25.860
hers drifted through them, like she was

06:02:25.860 --> 06:02:26.400
made of smoke.

06:02:26.459 --> 06:02:28.979
We're not really here.

06:02:29.040 --> 06:02:31.979
Lizard said, almost pityingly.

06:02:32.099 --> 06:02:33.659
Except him.

06:02:33.720 --> 06:02:35.580
He's inside one of WASP's attendants.

06:02:35.700 --> 06:02:39.060
She flicked her tail at Cottonmouth, who

06:02:39.060 --> 06:02:40.680
was holding his head in a weird, bird

06:02:40.680 --> 06:02:43.200
like way, tilting it back and forth and

06:02:43.200 --> 06:02:45.180
sideways to glare at the prisoners.

06:02:45.240 --> 06:02:46.979
Can you do something?

06:02:47.099 --> 06:02:49.860
Luna begged. crouching beside Lizard.

06:02:49.919 --> 06:02:52.319
Can't you take overcontrolled and set

06:02:52.319 --> 06:02:52.860
them free?

06:02:52.919 --> 06:02:56.340
No, Lizard said sulkily.

06:02:56.459 --> 06:02:58.860
And even if I could, why would I?

06:02:58.919 --> 06:03:00.900
I don't care about those dragons.

06:03:00.959 --> 06:03:02.159
They have nothing to do with me.

06:03:02.220 --> 06:03:05.220
They're my friends, Luna said.

06:03:05.279 --> 06:03:07.080
So?

06:03:07.319 --> 06:03:10.380
Lizard yawned, showing off bright white

06:03:10.380 --> 06:03:10.979
little teeth.

06:03:11.040 --> 06:03:13.259
I don't have any friends, remember?

06:03:13.319 --> 06:03:16.139
Besides, maybe they'll give me their

06:03:16.139 --> 06:03:16.619
memories.

06:03:16.680 --> 06:03:20.580
Luna turned back to her friends, feeling

06:03:20.580 --> 06:03:22.979
a wave of despair crash down around her.

06:03:23.040 --> 06:03:25.139
She couldn't just watch this happen.

06:03:25.200 --> 06:03:27.419
There had to be something she could do.

06:03:27.479 --> 06:03:30.479
At last.

06:03:30.599 --> 06:03:35.759
Queen Wasp hissed, taking her long claws

06:03:35.759 --> 06:03:37.259
against the bowl she was holding.

06:03:37.319 --> 06:03:40.139
It was made of white porcelain, and when

06:03:40.139 --> 06:03:41.279
Luna edged closer.

06:03:41.340 --> 06:03:43.919
She could see a layer of green residue at

06:03:43.919 --> 06:03:44.220
the bottom.

06:03:44.279 --> 06:03:47.400
I have my power again.

06:03:47.459 --> 06:03:51.779
Time to add to my army, starting with

06:03:51.779 --> 06:03:54.479
these unusual hideous worms.

06:03:54.540 --> 06:03:57.720
She set down the bowl, and a vicious

06:03:57.720 --> 06:03:59.639
looking stinger slid out of the end of

06:03:59.639 --> 06:04:00.000
her tail.

06:04:00.060 --> 06:04:04.020
Wait, Cottonmouth said.

06:04:04.080 --> 06:04:07.439
Wasp whipped her head around to glare at

06:04:07.439 --> 06:04:07.680
him.

06:04:07.740 --> 06:04:10.680
No one gave you permission to speak

06:04:10.680 --> 06:04:11.459
malachite.

06:04:11.520 --> 06:04:14.279
It's not malachite.

06:04:14.400 --> 06:04:16.200
Cottonmouth said harshly.

06:04:16.259 --> 06:04:17.040
It's me.

06:04:17.099 --> 06:04:19.979
I'm here to speak to these dragons.

06:04:20.040 --> 06:04:23.040
Stand down, or I will make you cut your

06:04:23.040 --> 06:04:23.639
own throat.

06:04:23.700 --> 06:04:27.540
Luna realized that the queen and everyone

06:04:27.540 --> 06:04:29.639
else in the real world still saw

06:04:29.639 --> 06:04:31.080
Malachite, the dragon.

06:04:31.139 --> 06:04:34.080
Only she, Dusky, and Lizard, saw

06:04:34.080 --> 06:04:35.340
Cottonmouth in his place.

06:04:35.459 --> 06:04:39.419
The queen's wings buzzed, an almost

06:04:39.419 --> 06:04:41.459
inaudible vibration in the air as they

06:04:41.459 --> 06:04:42.060
rubbed together.

06:04:42.119 --> 06:04:47.459
After a long moment, she said, You can't

06:04:47.459 --> 06:04:48.119
do that.

06:04:48.180 --> 06:04:52.080
I can, he said.

06:04:52.139 --> 06:04:54.360
I don't need you anymore.

06:04:54.419 --> 06:04:58.259
Shall we find out what I can make you

06:04:58.259 --> 06:04:58.740
do?

06:04:58.799 --> 06:05:03.060
Queen Wasp bared her teeth, inflict one

06:05:03.060 --> 06:05:04.200
talent toward the prisoners.

06:05:04.319 --> 06:05:06.180
Very well.

06:05:06.240 --> 06:05:08.340
Speak to them if you must.

06:05:08.400 --> 06:05:11.459
Unbind their mouths.

06:05:11.580 --> 06:05:13.799
Cottonmouth ordered one of the guards.

06:05:13.860 --> 06:05:17.639
Wasp twitched slightly, her claws

06:05:17.639 --> 06:05:18.240
flexing.

06:05:18.360 --> 06:05:20.459
That seems unwise.

06:05:20.580 --> 06:05:24.419
I need answers from them, Cottonmouth

06:05:24.419 --> 06:05:24.840
said.

06:05:24.900 --> 06:05:26.580
They won't do anything stupid.

06:05:26.639 --> 06:05:29.099
They know how outnumbered they are.

06:05:29.159 --> 06:05:33.299
The guard looked from wasp to cottonmouth

06:05:33.299 --> 06:05:35.279
and then the white film slid over his

06:05:35.279 --> 06:05:37.680
eyes, and he hurried to the prisoners to

06:05:37.680 --> 06:05:39.240
pull the bindings off their snouts.

06:05:39.360 --> 06:05:42.779
Cottonmouth stepped forward, and the

06:05:42.779 --> 06:05:44.459
Pyrean dragons looked up at him.

06:05:44.520 --> 06:05:46.259
Tsunami defiant.

06:05:46.319 --> 06:05:48.720
Pineapple, pale greenish blue with

06:05:48.720 --> 06:05:51.720
anxiety, Kibley managing a mask that was

06:05:51.720 --> 06:05:54.240
cheerful, curious, and faintly bored at

06:05:54.240 --> 06:05:54.659
the same time.

06:05:54.720 --> 06:05:59.819
Tell me where sundew is, Cottonmouth

06:05:59.819 --> 06:06:00.360
commanded.

06:06:00.419 --> 06:06:03.840
We'll never help you catch her, tsunami

06:06:03.840 --> 06:06:06.119
snarled, at the same moment as Kibley

06:06:06.119 --> 06:06:07.139
said, who?

06:06:07.200 --> 06:06:10.439
There was a brief pause, and then tsunami

06:06:10.439 --> 06:06:12.659
said, I mean, who?

06:06:12.720 --> 06:06:13.500
Right.

06:06:13.619 --> 06:06:14.220
Who?

06:06:14.279 --> 06:06:15.779
No idea who you're talking about.

06:06:15.840 --> 06:06:17.759
Never heard of a son, what's it?

06:06:17.880 --> 06:06:20.040
Good save.

06:06:20.159 --> 06:06:21.419
Kibley said to her.

06:06:21.479 --> 06:06:24.900
Did she go all the way to the distant

06:06:24.900 --> 06:06:26.040
kingdoms to get you?

06:06:26.099 --> 06:06:29.459
Cottonmouth asked, his eyes glittering.

06:06:29.580 --> 06:06:31.919
Are there more of you?

06:06:31.979 --> 06:06:36.240
I'm told one is quite enough of me, Kibley

06:06:36.240 --> 06:06:36.479
said.

06:06:36.540 --> 06:06:38.159
It's a vicious lie, though.

06:06:38.220 --> 06:06:40.319
I think 500 of me would be adorable

06:06:40.319 --> 06:06:40.680
actually.

06:06:40.740 --> 06:06:44.520
Three moons, tsunami said.

06:06:44.580 --> 06:06:46.259
I cannot imagine anything more

06:06:46.259 --> 06:06:47.099
exhausting.

06:06:47.159 --> 06:06:50.279
Pineapple agrees with me, Kibley said.

06:06:50.340 --> 06:06:52.380
Nudging the rain wing's tail with his

06:06:52.380 --> 06:06:52.560
own.

06:06:52.680 --> 06:06:55.560
He's survived a lot already.

06:06:55.619 --> 06:06:58.680
He's never even used all his skills

06:06:58.680 --> 06:06:59.939
against another dragon before.

06:07:00.000 --> 06:07:03.360
He can handle however many Kibley's life

06:07:03.360 --> 06:07:04.020
throws at him.

06:07:04.139 --> 06:07:07.259
I am thinking about throwing you at

06:07:07.259 --> 06:07:09.299
something, tsunami muttered.

06:07:09.360 --> 06:07:12.720
Pineapple blinked, and gave Kibble a

06:07:12.720 --> 06:07:15.240
small sideways smile, and some of the

06:07:15.240 --> 06:07:16.740
green faded out of his scales.

06:07:16.799 --> 06:07:19.799
He took a deep breath, and shimmers of

06:07:19.799 --> 06:07:21.419
purple appeared around his ears.

06:07:21.659 --> 06:07:24.659
Queen Wasp stirred slightly behind cotton

06:07:24.659 --> 06:07:25.500
mouth.

06:07:25.560 --> 06:07:27.240
There are more of them.

06:07:27.299 --> 06:07:29.700
Someone stole the invisible one.

06:07:29.759 --> 06:07:32.580
Moon, Luna thought.

06:07:32.639 --> 06:07:35.159
Sundew and Lynx must have rescued her.

06:07:35.220 --> 06:07:38.459
She wondered if there was any chance the

06:07:38.459 --> 06:07:40.319
other 3 were here in this throne room

06:07:40.319 --> 06:07:41.880
right now, invisible.

06:07:41.939 --> 06:07:44.520
Maybe they would swoop in and rescue

06:07:44.520 --> 06:07:44.880
everyone.

06:07:44.939 --> 06:07:47.819
There were a lot of hive wings lurking

06:07:47.819 --> 06:07:49.259
around along the edges of the walls.

06:07:49.319 --> 06:07:50.580
That would be a problem.

06:07:50.639 --> 06:07:53.099
But maybe sundew could smash some

06:07:53.099 --> 06:07:55.020
poisonous flowers into their noses and

06:07:55.020 --> 06:07:55.560
knock them out.

06:07:55.619 --> 06:07:57.360
That would be very awesome.

06:07:57.419 --> 06:08:01.200
Was that Sundu?

06:08:01.259 --> 06:08:03.180
Cottonmouth asked the prisoners.

06:08:03.299 --> 06:08:06.959
Was she here in this very hive?

06:08:06.959 --> 06:08:09.479
And did the incompetent dragon behind me

06:08:09.479 --> 06:08:10.560
let her get away?

06:08:10.680 --> 06:08:13.979
Kibli and Tsunami exchanged glances.

06:08:14.099 --> 06:08:18.299
I feel like You're not actually talking

06:08:18.299 --> 06:08:19.740
to us anymore?

06:08:19.799 --> 06:08:20.939
Kibley offered.

06:08:21.060 --> 06:08:25.319
You took that silk wing guard off to do

06:08:25.319 --> 06:08:25.979
something else.

06:08:26.040 --> 06:08:28.979
Wasp spat at Cottonmouth.

06:08:29.040 --> 06:08:31.500
My hive wings aren't equipped to watch

06:08:31.500 --> 06:08:32.939
for invisible dragons.

06:08:33.060 --> 06:08:34.740
It's your fault.

06:08:34.860 --> 06:08:38.040
Cottonmouth suddenly vanished from his

06:08:38.040 --> 06:08:40.560
spot in front of the prisoners, leaving a

06:08:40.560 --> 06:08:42.840
bewildered looking orange hive wing with

06:08:42.840 --> 06:08:43.799
red wings in his wake.

06:08:43.860 --> 06:08:46.860
The hive wing blinked, reaching for the

06:08:46.860 --> 06:08:49.259
spectacles on his snout, as the human

06:08:49.259 --> 06:08:51.299
reappeared where Wasp had been sitting.

06:08:51.360 --> 06:08:54.779
Cottonmouth reached up and clamped one

06:08:54.779 --> 06:08:55.979
hand around his own throat.

06:08:56.040 --> 06:08:59.759
A brief, silent struggle played out on

06:08:59.759 --> 06:09:00.180
the throne.

06:09:00.240 --> 06:09:04.020
This is always weird, Lizard said

06:09:04.020 --> 06:09:06.060
conversationally to Luna and Dusky.

06:09:06.119 --> 06:09:08.939
When he's punishing someone, he has to

06:09:08.939 --> 06:09:09.959
jump into them to do it.

06:09:10.020 --> 06:09:13.020
So inside the mind space.

06:09:13.080 --> 06:09:14.220
It looks like he's doing it to himself.

06:09:14.279 --> 06:09:17.159
He'll stop when it starts to really hurt

06:09:17.159 --> 06:09:17.459
though.

06:09:17.520 --> 06:09:19.979
He's a total coward about feeling any

06:09:19.979 --> 06:09:20.700
pain.

06:09:20.759 --> 06:09:23.520
The hive wing that Cottonmouth had been

06:09:23.520 --> 06:09:24.540
in a moment before.

06:09:24.599 --> 06:09:28.080
Malachite, Luna remembered. looked down

06:09:28.080 --> 06:09:29.819
at the prisoners, then back at the

06:09:29.819 --> 06:09:30.180
throne.

06:09:30.240 --> 06:09:33.060
A moment later, he was crouching beside

06:09:33.060 --> 06:09:35.340
tsunami, trying to slice through the

06:09:35.340 --> 06:09:36.360
vines with his claws.

06:09:36.419 --> 06:09:38.220
What's happening?

06:09:38.279 --> 06:09:39.599
he whispered to her.

06:09:39.659 --> 06:09:41.159
Do you know Katie did?

06:09:41.220 --> 06:09:42.360
How long have I?

06:09:42.720 --> 06:09:43.919
How long has it been since?

06:09:43.919 --> 06:09:45.419
Cat and mouth?

06:09:45.540 --> 06:09:47.939
Lizard said in a bored voice.

06:09:48.000 --> 06:09:49.919
You're getting distracted again?

06:09:49.979 --> 06:09:54.419
The human glanced over at Malachite, spat

06:09:54.419 --> 06:09:56.220
out a curse and let the queen go.

06:09:56.279 --> 06:09:59.400
She reappeared on the throne as he jumped

06:09:59.400 --> 06:10:00.479
back into Malachite.

06:10:00.540 --> 06:10:03.119
The hive wing barely had time to whisper

06:10:03.119 --> 06:10:06.180
no, under his breath, and then he

06:10:06.180 --> 06:10:08.700
vanished, and all Luna could see was

06:10:08.700 --> 06:10:11.400
Cottonmouth again, standing over tsunami

06:10:11.400 --> 06:10:12.599
with a disgusted expression.

06:10:12.659 --> 06:10:16.380
See, lizard said to Luna.

06:10:16.439 --> 06:10:18.299
Like how mad he is.

06:10:18.360 --> 06:10:18.840
So funny.

06:10:18.900 --> 06:10:22.619
Tsunami strained at the vines, but

06:10:22.619 --> 06:10:24.419
Malachi hadn't managed to saw through

06:10:24.419 --> 06:10:26.040
enough of them for her to break free.

06:10:26.099 --> 06:10:29.159
Let's get this over with.

06:10:29.220 --> 06:10:32.759
Cottonmouth said, before you let any more

06:10:32.759 --> 06:10:33.659
of them escape.

06:10:33.720 --> 06:10:35.459
From the throne.

06:10:35.520 --> 06:10:39.119
WASP glared at him with deep, glittering

06:10:39.119 --> 06:10:39.360
eyes.

06:10:39.419 --> 06:10:43.200
Thin trails of dark, greenish blood oozed

06:10:43.200 --> 06:10:45.479
down her neck, from where her own claws

06:10:45.479 --> 06:10:46.500
had dug into her scales.

06:10:46.560 --> 06:10:50.639
I have your permission to go ahead now, do

06:10:50.639 --> 06:10:50.939
I?

06:10:51.060 --> 06:10:52.500
She snarled.

06:10:52.560 --> 06:10:56.220
Yes, Cottonmouth said brusquely.

06:10:56.220 --> 06:10:57.840
Start with the annoying one.

06:10:57.900 --> 06:11:03.060
Start with me, tsunami growled, if you

06:11:03.060 --> 06:11:03.479
dare.

06:11:03.599 --> 06:11:07.259
Hey, hang on, Kibley said.

06:11:07.380 --> 06:11:09.119
Who else do you think he meant?

06:11:09.240 --> 06:11:10.680
Hey granddadder.

06:11:10.740 --> 06:11:14.159
Queen Wasp slithered off her throne and

06:11:14.159 --> 06:11:16.380
stepped toward them, raising her tail

06:11:16.380 --> 06:11:17.099
stinger high.

06:11:17.159 --> 06:11:19.380
No, no, no.

06:11:19.439 --> 06:11:20.400
Luna thought.

06:11:20.459 --> 06:11:22.080
Sundu, where are you?

06:11:22.139 --> 06:11:24.540
Lizard, she pleaded.

06:11:24.599 --> 06:11:26.279
Please, do something.

06:11:26.340 --> 06:11:27.479
Please help.

06:11:27.540 --> 06:11:29.459
Stop bothering me.

06:11:29.580 --> 06:11:31.560
Lizard snapped at her.

06:11:31.619 --> 06:11:34.319
I'll give you my memories if you help set

06:11:34.319 --> 06:11:34.979
them free.

06:11:35.159 --> 06:11:36.240
Luna blurted.

06:11:36.299 --> 06:11:38.400
Lizard eyes narrowed.

06:11:38.459 --> 06:11:39.299
Calculating.

06:11:39.360 --> 06:11:43.680
Suddenly, Kibley shouted, Pineapple, now

06:11:43.680 --> 06:11:44.400
the queen.

06:11:44.520 --> 06:11:47.700
Opened his mouth, and roared fire in

06:11:47.700 --> 06:11:48.779
cotton mouthed face.

06:11:48.840 --> 06:11:51.900
Cottonmouth shrieked and vanished, leaving

06:11:51.900 --> 06:11:54.180
Malachide writhing on the ground, trying

06:11:54.180 --> 06:11:55.200
to beat out the flames.

06:11:55.259 --> 06:11:58.560
Beside Kibley, pineapples jaws hinged

06:11:58.560 --> 06:12:00.659
open farther than anything Luna had ever

06:12:00.659 --> 06:12:03.240
seen a dragon do, and a black spray of

06:12:03.240 --> 06:12:04.919
liquid shot from his top fangs.

06:12:04.979 --> 06:12:07.799
It splattered all over wasp's face

06:12:07.799 --> 06:12:10.139
hissing like acid against her scales.

06:12:10.200 --> 06:12:15.659
Chaos erupted, wasp screaming, hive wings

06:12:15.659 --> 06:12:17.520
shouting and crashing into one another

06:12:17.520 --> 06:12:20.159
the fire spreading from malachite, to the

06:12:20.159 --> 06:12:22.080
woven carpets on the floor, to the

06:12:22.080 --> 06:12:24.959
tapestries and tree stuff of the walls

06:12:24.959 --> 06:12:27.479
Dusky bolted over to Luna and climbed

06:12:27.479 --> 06:12:29.580
onto her back, burying his face and her

06:12:29.580 --> 06:12:29.819
neck.

06:12:29.939 --> 06:12:33.119
Through the rising smoke, Luna saw

06:12:33.119 --> 06:12:35.159
Cottonmouth flicker into one hive wing

06:12:35.159 --> 06:12:36.540
guard, then another.

06:12:36.599 --> 06:12:38.880
One moment, they would all snap into

06:12:38.880 --> 06:12:41.159
synchronized motion, eyes white.

06:12:41.220 --> 06:12:43.860
And then, a moment later, they'd fall out

06:12:43.860 --> 06:12:45.599
again, stumbling and blinking.

06:12:45.659 --> 06:12:50.400
Oh, this is perfect, Lizard cried

06:12:50.400 --> 06:12:51.000
gleefully.

06:12:51.060 --> 06:12:53.819
He controls those hive wings through WASP

06:12:53.819 --> 06:12:55.560
but when he tries to reach them through

06:12:55.560 --> 06:12:58.259
her, he has to feel her face melting off

06:12:58.259 --> 06:13:00.119
ha, ha. amazing.

06:13:00.240 --> 06:13:03.900
Luna saw Kibbly roll under Wasp's

06:13:03.900 --> 06:13:04.680
flailing wings.

06:13:04.860 --> 06:13:07.259
A heartbeat away from the stingers she

06:13:07.259 --> 06:13:08.279
was whipping in all directions.

06:13:08.340 --> 06:13:11.819
He came up on the other side. stabbed his

06:13:11.819 --> 06:13:14.459
own tail barb into the nearest guard, and

06:13:14.459 --> 06:13:16.500
wrestled the spear out of her talons as

06:13:16.500 --> 06:13:17.220
she collapsed.

06:13:17.279 --> 06:13:20.639
Still wrapped in vines, he ducked and

06:13:20.639 --> 06:13:22.979
rolled back to pineapple, who was staring

06:13:22.979 --> 06:13:24.900
at WASP with an expression of blank

06:13:24.900 --> 06:13:25.380
shock.

06:13:25.439 --> 06:13:28.860
Luna knew exactly how he felt, and she

06:13:28.860 --> 06:13:31.020
wished she could shake him, and hug him

06:13:31.020 --> 06:13:33.299
and shout, pineapple, you had to.

06:13:33.360 --> 06:13:34.560
She deserved it.

06:13:34.619 --> 06:13:37.139
Stop feeling bad about it, and escape

06:13:37.139 --> 06:13:37.799
right now.

06:13:37.860 --> 06:13:40.740
She wished she could grab the spear from

06:13:40.740 --> 06:13:42.840
Kibley and cut the vines for them.

06:13:42.900 --> 06:13:45.779
She wished she could do anything helpful

06:13:45.779 --> 06:13:46.080
at all.

06:13:46.139 --> 06:13:48.599
On the other side of the room.

06:13:48.659 --> 06:13:51.840
Tsunami was roaring and swinging her tail

06:13:51.840 --> 06:13:54.180
around, smacking away guards as they

06:13:54.180 --> 06:13:54.959
tried to approach her.

06:13:55.020 --> 06:13:57.900
The flames were licking toward her talons

06:13:57.900 --> 06:14:00.119
but when she tried to get to Kibley and

06:14:00.119 --> 06:14:02.459
Pineapple, she nearly ran her face into

06:14:02.459 --> 06:14:05.040
Wasp's tail stinger and had to jump back

06:14:05.040 --> 06:14:05.459
in a hurry.

06:14:05.520 --> 06:14:08.939
Kibble's sawed awkwardly at the vines

06:14:08.939 --> 06:14:10.259
around pineapple with the tip of the

06:14:10.259 --> 06:14:10.500
spear.

06:14:10.560 --> 06:14:13.319
Luna saw him glance at the trail of fire

06:14:13.319 --> 06:14:14.759
spreading across the carpet.

06:14:14.819 --> 06:14:18.240
With a shiver of horror, she thought, Now

06:14:18.240 --> 06:14:20.340
Kibley, don't burn the vines.

06:14:20.400 --> 06:14:22.200
But he turned away from them.

06:14:22.259 --> 06:14:24.419
So either he remembered about the smoke

06:14:24.419 --> 06:14:26.520
on his own, or he didn't want to risk

06:14:26.520 --> 06:14:27.900
burning pineapple.

06:14:27.959 --> 06:14:30.840
Wasp staggered back to her throne

06:14:30.840 --> 06:14:31.919
clutching her face.

06:14:31.979 --> 06:14:33.479
She flickered.

06:14:33.540 --> 06:14:37.680
Cottonmouth, wasp, Cottonmouth, wasp, and

06:14:37.680 --> 06:14:40.439
then, for a moment, Cottonmouth was there

06:14:40.439 --> 06:14:43.259
his human face contorted in agony.

06:14:43.319 --> 06:14:46.799
The hive wing guards all froze, and their

06:14:46.799 --> 06:14:48.900
eyes went white, marble, white.

06:14:48.959 --> 06:14:50.939
Oh, no.

06:14:51.000 --> 06:14:52.979
Luna wrung her talons together.

06:14:53.040 --> 06:14:54.959
He's going to fight through the pain.

06:14:55.020 --> 06:14:56.340
He can't let them escape.

06:14:56.400 --> 06:15:00.240
Lizard appeared at her side and looked up

06:15:00.240 --> 06:15:01.139
at her speculatively.

06:15:01.200 --> 06:15:03.000
Did you mean it?

06:15:03.060 --> 06:15:03.959
She asked.

06:15:04.020 --> 06:15:06.000
You'll give me your memories?

06:15:06.060 --> 06:15:08.819
Yes, Luna said.

06:15:08.880 --> 06:15:11.700
If you help them get free, I'll give you

06:15:11.700 --> 06:15:13.080
all of them, whatever you want.

06:15:13.200 --> 06:15:14.819
Me too.

06:15:14.939 --> 06:15:16.560
Dusky whispered.

06:15:16.619 --> 06:15:19.380
Lizard grinned fiercely.

06:15:19.439 --> 06:15:22.020
She blinked out of sight. and then

06:15:22.020 --> 06:15:24.180
suddenly reappeared across the room, where

06:15:24.180 --> 06:15:25.500
Amalachite had been lying.

06:15:25.560 --> 06:15:28.560
She lunged to her feet, grabbed a

06:15:28.560 --> 06:15:31.319
discarded sword, bolted over to tsunami

06:15:31.319 --> 06:15:33.240
and sliced through the vines around her.

06:15:33.299 --> 06:15:35.340
It was not carefully done.

06:15:35.459 --> 06:15:38.159
Luna could see blue blood welling up

06:15:38.159 --> 06:15:40.979
along tsunami scales from the cut lizard

06:15:40.979 --> 06:15:42.779
made, but tsunami was free.

06:15:42.900 --> 06:15:44.819
And now she could find her way through

06:15:44.819 --> 06:15:46.080
the hive wings with her claws.

06:15:46.200 --> 06:15:49.979
A moment later, Tsunami and Lizard were

06:15:49.979 --> 06:15:52.259
at Kibli's side, cutting away the vines

06:15:52.259 --> 06:15:52.680
around him.

06:15:52.740 --> 06:15:55.860
As the vines fell away from pineapple

06:15:55.860 --> 06:15:58.619
next, the rain wings scales shimmered

06:15:58.619 --> 06:16:01.020
into camouflage, and Luna could only see

06:16:01.020 --> 06:16:03.060
him in flickers of movement and changing

06:16:03.060 --> 06:16:03.479
color.

06:16:03.479 --> 06:16:07.080
The 3 Pyrean dragons ran for the window.

06:16:07.139 --> 06:16:10.139
White eyed hive wings blocked their way

06:16:10.139 --> 06:16:13.619
and they fought, outnumbered 10 to 3, as

06:16:13.619 --> 06:16:15.360
thick smoke filled the room.

06:16:15.419 --> 06:16:18.779
To her horror, Luna saw the fire reach

06:16:18.779 --> 06:16:21.299
the discarded vines, and a greenish smoke

06:16:21.299 --> 06:16:23.099
start to rise from them.

06:16:23.159 --> 06:16:25.200
Get out quick, she prayed.

06:16:25.259 --> 06:16:28.259
I think that was pretty helpful of me

06:16:28.259 --> 06:16:31.500
Lizard said, appearing next to Luna again

06:16:31.500 --> 06:16:34.619
with a self satisfied smile on her face.

06:16:34.680 --> 06:16:35.159
You're welcome.

06:16:35.220 --> 06:16:38.880
Across the room, Malachite staggered

06:16:38.880 --> 06:16:39.599
shaking his head.

06:16:39.659 --> 06:16:42.119
He looked around at the burning throne

06:16:42.119 --> 06:16:44.819
room with a bewildered expression, then

06:16:44.819 --> 06:16:46.680
turned and ran out through the archway to

06:16:46.680 --> 06:16:47.340
the rest of the hive.

06:16:47.459 --> 06:16:50.159
But they're not.

06:16:50.580 --> 06:16:51.419
Luna started.

06:16:51.479 --> 06:16:54.000
And then Kibley sent out another blast of

06:16:54.000 --> 06:16:56.700
flames, and another spray of black venom

06:16:56.700 --> 06:16:58.439
splattered over the hive wing guards.

06:16:58.500 --> 06:17:01.799
Everywhere a droplet fell, a hive wing

06:17:01.799 --> 06:17:03.060
screamed and jumped aside.

06:17:03.119 --> 06:17:05.700
His or her eyes flicking back to normal.

06:17:05.819 --> 06:17:09.180
A path opened to the crowd of guards.

06:17:09.240 --> 06:17:12.119
Tsunami charged into it, battering hive

06:17:12.119 --> 06:17:14.040
wings aside with her tail and wings and

06:17:14.040 --> 06:17:16.139
talons, and then she whipped around.

06:17:16.200 --> 06:17:19.080
Grabbed Kibley's arms and threw him into

06:17:19.080 --> 06:17:19.439
the sky.

06:17:19.500 --> 06:17:23.520
A rush of camouflaged wings shot over her

06:17:23.520 --> 06:17:25.979
head, and tsunami turned and leaped out

06:17:25.979 --> 06:17:26.639
into the air too.

06:17:26.700 --> 06:17:29.819
They shot away over the savannah, into

06:17:29.819 --> 06:17:30.540
the falling night.

06:17:30.659 --> 06:17:33.119
After them.

06:17:33.180 --> 06:17:36.659
Cottonmouth screamed from the throne, and

06:17:36.659 --> 06:17:39.360
then he vanished, leaving only Wasp, who

06:17:39.360 --> 06:17:41.700
dug her claws into her face, and roared

06:17:41.700 --> 06:17:42.840
with fury and pain.

06:17:42.900 --> 06:17:45.779
Half the hive wing guards launched

06:17:45.779 --> 06:17:47.759
themselves after the escaping prisoners

06:17:47.759 --> 06:17:50.220
but 5 of them lay howling on the floor

06:17:50.220 --> 06:17:53.400
clutching burns or venom wounds, and 3

06:17:53.400 --> 06:17:55.259
others had fallen elsewhere in the room.

06:17:55.319 --> 06:17:57.779
Someone should get them out of here.

06:17:57.840 --> 06:18:00.900
Luna said to Lizard, they'll die of the

06:18:00.900 --> 06:18:01.979
smoke or the fire.

06:18:02.040 --> 06:18:03.959
The whole hive could burn if someone

06:18:03.959 --> 06:18:04.919
doesn't do something about it.

06:18:04.979 --> 06:18:07.680
Lizard wrinkled her snout.

06:18:07.740 --> 06:18:09.840
What do you care?

06:18:09.840 --> 06:18:10.799
she asked.

06:18:10.860 --> 06:18:13.740
This is Wasp Hive, not Cicada Hive.

06:18:13.799 --> 06:18:15.540
There aren't even any silk wings here

06:18:15.540 --> 06:18:15.840
right now.

06:18:15.900 --> 06:18:18.659
She cocked her head as if listening.

06:18:18.720 --> 06:18:22.200
Oh, lots of leaf wings are coming now.

06:18:22.259 --> 06:18:24.599
Cottonmouth went to get the dragons he

06:18:24.599 --> 06:18:26.279
can control without going through WASP.

06:18:26.340 --> 06:18:28.740
What if Wasp dies?

06:18:28.740 --> 06:18:29.880
Luna asked.

06:18:29.939 --> 06:18:31.919
Would he lose all the hive wings?

06:18:31.979 --> 06:18:35.759
No, Lizard said contemplatively.

06:18:35.819 --> 06:18:38.400
I think then he'd control them directly.

06:18:38.459 --> 06:18:41.159
He's already got the ones who breathed

06:18:41.159 --> 06:18:42.659
the smoke at the poison jungle.

06:18:42.720 --> 06:18:44.400
It wouldn't be hard to make extra sure

06:18:44.400 --> 06:18:46.619
yet, everyone, especially if you could

06:18:46.619 --> 06:18:48.360
find stupid sundo and grow more of the

06:18:48.360 --> 06:18:48.900
plant.

06:18:49.020 --> 06:18:51.180
Luna crossed to the window.

06:18:51.240 --> 06:18:53.580
Walking straight through some of the hive

06:18:53.580 --> 06:18:54.180
wings on the floor.

06:18:54.240 --> 06:18:57.659
Tsunami, Kibble, and Pineapple were

06:18:57.659 --> 06:19:00.119
almost out of sight, but dragons were

06:19:00.119 --> 06:19:01.619
streaming toward them from every corner

06:19:01.619 --> 06:19:02.279
of the sky.

06:19:02.340 --> 06:19:05.279
How will I know if they're all right?

06:19:05.279 --> 06:19:08.340
she said, twisting her front talons

06:19:08.340 --> 06:19:08.580
together.

06:19:08.639 --> 06:19:10.860
They're not.

06:19:10.919 --> 06:19:13.740
Said Cottonmouth's voice in her mind.

06:19:13.799 --> 06:19:16.560
I absorbed one of them before they

06:19:16.560 --> 06:19:17.099
escaped.

06:19:17.159 --> 06:19:19.979
He chuckled mercilessly.

06:19:20.040 --> 06:19:23.040
They'll all be here soon enough.

06:19:23.099 --> 06:19:31.259
Part 3 Talons United.

06:19:31.319 --> 06:19:34.080
Chapter 19.

06:19:34.319 --> 06:19:38.819
You're lying, Luna said fiercely, turning

06:19:38.819 --> 06:19:39.360
in a circle.

06:19:39.419 --> 06:19:40.500
They got away.

06:19:40.560 --> 06:19:41.340
They got away.

06:19:41.400 --> 06:19:43.979
There wasn't enough smoke to infect them

06:19:43.979 --> 06:19:44.700
before they escaped.

06:19:44.819 --> 06:19:48.479
Perhaps, said Cottonmouth.

06:19:48.540 --> 06:19:51.180
But one of them also accepted a drink

06:19:51.180 --> 06:19:54.299
from the guards while in prison, a

06:19:54.299 --> 06:19:56.340
special, slightly greenish, bitter

06:19:56.340 --> 06:19:58.740
tasting drink, not very clever.

06:19:58.799 --> 06:20:00.540
I mean, of your friend.

06:20:00.599 --> 06:20:03.180
It was extremely clever of me.

06:20:03.240 --> 06:20:07.259
This guy in front of Luna shifted, and

06:20:07.259 --> 06:20:09.779
slowly melted away, until she was back in

06:20:09.779 --> 06:20:10.439
the throne room again.

06:20:10.500 --> 06:20:14.040
This was the real one, in the present, she

06:20:14.040 --> 06:20:16.619
realized, as she saw the vines covering

06:20:16.619 --> 06:20:17.819
the walls and blocking the door.

06:20:17.880 --> 06:20:21.419
The husks of Cottonmouth and Lizard, sat

06:20:21.419 --> 06:20:23.400
in their eternally petrified spots on the

06:20:23.400 --> 06:20:23.700
throne.

06:20:23.819 --> 06:20:27.000
Thick, thorny vines pressed into her

06:20:27.000 --> 06:20:29.639
scales, pinning down her wings and arms

06:20:29.639 --> 06:20:30.659
and tail and neck.

06:20:30.720 --> 06:20:33.779
She felt like a stone knotted into a

06:20:33.779 --> 06:20:36.360
tapestry, or an insect, wrapped up for

06:20:36.360 --> 06:20:37.619
later in a spider's web.

06:20:37.680 --> 06:20:41.939
When she rolled her eyes sideways, she

06:20:41.939 --> 06:20:44.340
could see Dusky, tangled up beside her.

06:20:44.400 --> 06:20:47.400
He had his eyes closed, and he looked

06:20:47.400 --> 06:20:50.099
fragile and breakable, as though the

06:20:50.099 --> 06:20:52.139
vines only needed to tighten a hair's

06:20:52.139 --> 06:20:53.099
breadth to crush him.

06:20:53.159 --> 06:20:55.139
Luna.

06:20:55.200 --> 06:20:56.279
Luna, where are you?

06:20:56.400 --> 06:20:57.840
Cricket.

06:20:57.900 --> 06:21:00.119
Luna tried to wriggle around.

06:21:00.180 --> 06:21:02.759
She was able to move the smallest amount

06:21:02.759 --> 06:21:04.740
but only enough to see the doorway more

06:21:04.740 --> 06:21:05.099
clearly.

06:21:05.159 --> 06:21:07.500
Cricket's voice was coming from the other

06:21:07.500 --> 06:21:08.520
side of the vines.

06:21:08.580 --> 06:21:11.099
Don't touch those.

06:21:11.159 --> 06:21:12.840
That was Bryony.

06:21:12.900 --> 06:21:14.279
See the thorns?

06:21:14.340 --> 06:21:16.020
Touching them is exactly what it wants

06:21:16.020 --> 06:21:16.439
you to do.

06:21:16.500 --> 06:21:19.500
But I think Luna is in there, Cricket

06:21:19.500 --> 06:21:19.799
said.

06:21:19.919 --> 06:21:21.180
She could be trapped.

06:21:21.240 --> 06:21:22.080
Luna?

06:21:22.139 --> 06:21:23.279
Luna, can you hear me?

06:21:23.340 --> 06:21:26.459
Luna strained to lift her head.

06:21:26.520 --> 06:21:29.580
And then, suddenly, the vines slipped

06:21:29.580 --> 06:21:30.479
away from her snout.

06:21:30.540 --> 06:21:33.000
Cricket, she yelled.

06:21:33.060 --> 06:21:34.560
Cricket, be careful.

06:21:34.619 --> 06:21:35.580
The vines.

06:21:35.880 --> 06:21:37.979
Something seized hold of her throat.

06:21:38.040 --> 06:21:40.619
She tried to look down before she

06:21:40.619 --> 06:21:43.319
realized, it was her own muscles locking

06:21:43.319 --> 06:21:45.180
around her voice, and she couldn't move

06:21:45.180 --> 06:21:45.900
her head anymore.

06:21:45.959 --> 06:21:47.580
Luna!

06:21:47.639 --> 06:21:48.720
Cricket was shouting.

06:21:48.779 --> 06:21:50.400
Luna, are you all right?

06:21:50.459 --> 06:21:55.500
She heard her own voice say, Cricket, you

06:21:55.500 --> 06:21:56.759
have to get sundew.

06:21:56.880 --> 06:21:59.220
Sundew is the only one who can get in

06:21:59.220 --> 06:21:59.459
here.

06:21:59.580 --> 06:22:03.779
But we don't know where she is, Cricket

06:22:03.779 --> 06:22:04.380
called back.

06:22:04.439 --> 06:22:06.419
Can't Briny and I help?

06:22:06.479 --> 06:22:08.400
Luna, what happened?

06:22:08.459 --> 06:22:09.900
Is Dusky in there too?

06:22:09.959 --> 06:22:11.099
Is he all right?

06:22:11.159 --> 06:22:12.959
There has to be something we can do.

06:22:13.080 --> 06:22:16.380
Please, Cricket.

06:22:16.500 --> 06:22:19.139
Luna's voice, but not Luna said.

06:22:19.200 --> 06:22:21.599
It has to be sundew.

06:22:21.659 --> 06:22:24.240
Go find her, and tell her to hurry.

06:22:24.299 --> 06:22:26.040
I can't hold out much longer.

06:22:26.099 --> 06:22:29.340
The plant will have me soon if sundew

06:22:29.340 --> 06:22:29.819
doesn't come.

06:22:29.939 --> 06:22:33.360
Oh, no, Bryney said softly.

06:22:33.419 --> 06:22:34.919
Hang in there, Luna.

06:22:34.979 --> 06:22:38.099
We'll try, Cricket called.

06:22:38.159 --> 06:22:40.560
And then there was a flurry of wing beats

06:22:40.560 --> 06:22:41.459
and silence.

06:22:41.520 --> 06:22:45.240
The pressure eased on Luna's throat, and

06:22:45.240 --> 06:22:47.159
she gasped for air as she flickered back

06:22:47.159 --> 06:22:48.779
into the mind space version of the throne

06:22:48.779 --> 06:22:49.020
room.

06:22:49.080 --> 06:22:52.139
Cottonmouth stood at the base of the

06:22:52.139 --> 06:22:54.119
throne, with a chain wrapped around

06:22:54.119 --> 06:22:56.400
lizard's throat and his boot on her neck

06:22:56.400 --> 06:22:58.439
pinning her to the dirt floor.

06:22:58.619 --> 06:23:01.619
Dusky hovered beside them, wringing his

06:23:01.619 --> 06:23:02.340
talons.

06:23:02.459 --> 06:23:05.700
Luna dropped into a crouch, and buried

06:23:05.700 --> 06:23:06.659
her head in her claws.

06:23:06.779 --> 06:23:10.259
She felt like a tapestry, with a 1000

06:23:10.259 --> 06:23:11.340
holes stabbed in it.

06:23:11.400 --> 06:23:14.159
Was any part of hers still real?

06:23:14.220 --> 06:23:16.020
Did she have any control?

06:23:16.080 --> 06:23:18.119
Was anything still connected?

06:23:18.180 --> 06:23:21.180
Could her mind reach her talons or her

06:23:21.180 --> 06:23:21.720
wings?

06:23:21.779 --> 06:23:24.000
Or would it be drifting in a nowhere

06:23:24.000 --> 06:23:24.720
space forever?

06:23:24.779 --> 06:23:28.200
I can't believe he used me to trick

06:23:28.200 --> 06:23:28.740
cricket.

06:23:28.799 --> 06:23:31.919
My voice, sending her to bring sundew

06:23:31.919 --> 06:23:33.180
into this trap.

06:23:33.240 --> 06:23:35.159
She stood up abruptly.

06:23:35.220 --> 06:23:37.979
That was horrible, she said to

06:23:37.979 --> 06:23:38.639
Cottonmouth.

06:23:38.700 --> 06:23:40.319
You're a horrible creature.

06:23:40.380 --> 06:23:42.299
What is wrong with you that you would do

06:23:42.299 --> 06:23:42.840
that to someone?

06:23:42.959 --> 06:23:47.099
You say that, but you wish you had this

06:23:47.099 --> 06:23:47.459
power.

06:23:47.580 --> 06:23:48.959
He said.

06:23:49.020 --> 06:23:51.779
Anyone who had the chance to be me would

06:23:51.779 --> 06:23:52.860
take it in a heartbeat.

06:23:52.919 --> 06:23:55.919
That's not true, Luna said.

06:23:55.979 --> 06:23:58.080
I don't know anyone who would want to

06:23:58.080 --> 06:23:59.520
control other dragons like this.

06:23:59.580 --> 06:24:01.979
Ha, he spat.

06:24:02.040 --> 06:24:04.259
Just look at Queen Wasp.

06:24:04.319 --> 06:24:06.659
She was thrilled about this partnership.

06:24:06.720 --> 06:24:09.360
And don't forget Hawthorne and Queen

06:24:09.360 --> 06:24:11.639
Sequoia, who tried to do it to her.

06:24:11.700 --> 06:24:14.099
They wanted it to work.

06:24:14.159 --> 06:24:15.479
Oh, yes, they did.

06:24:15.540 --> 06:24:18.119
Not to mention this little snake here.

06:24:18.180 --> 06:24:21.479
He jabbed his foot harder into lizard's

06:24:21.479 --> 06:24:21.720
neck.

06:24:21.840 --> 06:24:24.659
She's a precocious little puppeteer

06:24:24.659 --> 06:24:25.080
aren't you?

06:24:25.139 --> 06:24:27.060
You'd love it.

06:24:27.180 --> 06:24:30.000
If I took a long nap, and everyone was

06:24:30.000 --> 06:24:31.020
yours to play with.

06:24:31.080 --> 06:24:34.259
Please, please stop hurting her.

06:24:34.319 --> 06:24:35.639
Dusky said.

06:24:35.700 --> 06:24:37.860
He's not hurting me.

06:24:37.919 --> 06:24:39.540
Lizard said.

06:24:39.599 --> 06:24:40.560
She yawned.

06:24:40.619 --> 06:24:42.540
This is all theater.

06:24:42.599 --> 06:24:44.340
He can't actually do anything to me.

06:24:44.400 --> 06:24:47.220
So he's acting out his frustrations by

06:24:47.220 --> 06:24:48.779
pretending he's so menacing.

06:24:48.840 --> 06:24:51.240
But I can't feel anything.

06:24:51.299 --> 06:24:53.099
So it's totally pointless.

06:24:53.159 --> 06:24:54.959
Wake me when he's done.

06:24:55.020 --> 06:24:58.080
She closed her eyes and let out a snore.

06:24:58.200 --> 06:25:01.680
Cottonmouth stepped off her, and threw

06:25:01.680 --> 06:25:03.000
the chain violently across the room.

06:25:03.060 --> 06:25:06.119
He stormed up the steps to the throne and

06:25:06.119 --> 06:25:08.400
sat down, closing his eyes as well.

06:25:08.459 --> 06:25:11.700
Lizard lay where she was for a moment

06:25:11.700 --> 06:25:12.060
longer.

06:25:12.119 --> 06:25:14.880
Stretching and snuggling into the stone.

06:25:14.939 --> 06:25:18.180
Then she opened one eye, confirmed that

06:25:18.180 --> 06:25:20.759
Cottonmouth was gone, jumped to her feet

06:25:20.759 --> 06:25:21.720
and shook out her wings.

06:25:21.779 --> 06:25:24.959
I guess we're done with cottonmouth plays

06:25:24.959 --> 06:25:25.919
emperor for today.

06:25:26.040 --> 06:25:28.619
She said, with a toss of her head.

06:25:28.680 --> 06:25:31.380
Now he's going to be busy chasing those

06:25:31.380 --> 06:25:33.119
funny looking dragons around for a

06:25:33.119 --> 06:25:33.299
while.

06:25:33.419 --> 06:25:37.080
She reached out her front talons, curling

06:25:37.080 --> 06:25:37.680
her claws in.

06:25:37.799 --> 06:25:40.439
Time to give your memories to me.

06:25:40.500 --> 06:25:42.599
Give, give, give.

06:25:42.659 --> 06:25:46.080
Wait, I need to ask some questions first

06:25:46.080 --> 06:25:47.159
Luna said.

06:25:47.279 --> 06:25:49.560
No, Lizard shouted.

06:25:49.619 --> 06:25:51.000
You promised.

06:25:51.060 --> 06:25:53.400
I did, Luna said.

06:25:53.459 --> 06:25:55.259
I will give them to you.

06:25:55.319 --> 06:25:57.060
I just want to understand some things.

06:25:57.119 --> 06:25:59.400
Gah!

06:25:59.459 --> 06:26:00.119
Fine.

06:26:00.180 --> 06:26:01.080
Hurry up.

06:26:01.139 --> 06:26:04.680
Lizard stomped impatiently around Dusky

06:26:04.680 --> 06:26:05.700
flapping her wings.

06:26:05.759 --> 06:26:09.240
If we give them to you, will we lose

06:26:09.240 --> 06:26:09.540
them?

06:26:09.659 --> 06:26:10.740
Luna asked.

06:26:10.799 --> 06:26:12.959
I mean, do we disappear?

06:26:13.020 --> 06:26:14.819
Or forget everything?

06:26:14.880 --> 06:26:18.720
No, Lizard said, stupid question.

06:26:18.779 --> 06:26:21.180
It only means I can watch your memories

06:26:21.180 --> 06:26:23.099
the way you watched stupid cotton

06:26:23.099 --> 06:26:23.459
mouths.

06:26:23.580 --> 06:26:26.040
You will barely even notice.

06:26:26.099 --> 06:26:27.180
What is the problem?

06:26:27.240 --> 06:26:31.319
But then, he'll be able to see all our

06:26:31.319 --> 06:26:33.659
memories too, Luna asked.

06:26:33.720 --> 06:26:36.540
Can he wander through them and see any

06:26:36.540 --> 06:26:37.680
memory he wants to see?

06:26:37.740 --> 06:26:40.560
Yeah, but why would he?

06:26:40.619 --> 06:26:41.819
Lizard asked.

06:26:41.880 --> 06:26:43.979
He's the kind of person who's only

06:26:43.979 --> 06:26:45.900
interested in pictures if he's in them.

06:26:45.959 --> 06:26:49.200
He might shuffle through your memories to

06:26:49.200 --> 06:26:51.360
see if there is anything about him, but

06:26:51.360 --> 06:26:52.979
he will not care about your friends or

06:26:52.979 --> 06:26:55.500
family or crushes or anything you care

06:26:55.500 --> 06:26:55.799
about.

06:26:55.860 --> 06:26:59.759
I'm not sure that's quite true, Luna

06:26:59.759 --> 06:27:00.060
thought.

06:27:00.119 --> 06:27:02.819
I care about a few things he probably

06:27:02.819 --> 06:27:04.500
would be very interested in.

06:27:04.619 --> 06:27:08.220
What about the chrysalis, she asked.

06:27:08.279 --> 06:27:10.799
What if he uses my memories to catch

06:27:10.799 --> 06:27:12.599
everyone who was in the chrysalis in

06:27:12.599 --> 06:27:13.319
cicada hive?

06:27:13.380 --> 06:27:17.159
Lizard rolled her eyes, and gave Luna a

06:27:17.159 --> 06:27:19.740
look that was somehow extremely pitying

06:27:19.740 --> 06:27:21.599
yet not at all sympathetic at the same

06:27:21.599 --> 06:27:21.779
time.

06:27:21.840 --> 06:27:25.860
There is no more chrysalis, she said.

06:27:25.979 --> 06:27:28.860
Soon, all those silk wings will be

06:27:28.860 --> 06:27:31.139
exactly like the hive wings, and we'll

06:27:31.139 --> 06:27:31.740
control all of them.

06:27:31.799 --> 06:27:34.319
Who cares about your little rebel group

06:27:34.319 --> 06:27:36.360
when we've already crushed them into

06:27:36.360 --> 06:27:36.720
dust.

06:27:36.840 --> 06:27:40.380
Besides, only Queen Wasp would be

06:27:40.380 --> 06:27:42.240
interested in that, and she won't get

06:27:42.240 --> 06:27:42.900
your memories.

06:27:42.959 --> 06:27:44.340
She won't?

06:27:44.459 --> 06:27:46.139
You are so dense.

06:27:46.200 --> 06:27:47.580
Lizard barked.

06:27:47.639 --> 06:27:50.220
She is not in here with me and

06:27:50.220 --> 06:27:52.259
Cottonmouth and the ravenous plant.

06:27:52.319 --> 06:27:55.439
She's only a puppet, who can control some

06:27:55.439 --> 06:27:57.840
of the other puppets because she eats the

06:27:57.840 --> 06:28:00.240
plant, and it combines with her venom in

06:28:00.240 --> 06:28:00.779
a useful way.

06:28:00.840 --> 06:28:04.740
She paused, thinking, Hmm.

06:28:04.860 --> 06:28:07.500
Your chatty friend has tail venom like

06:28:07.500 --> 06:28:07.680
that.

06:28:07.740 --> 06:28:10.020
I wonder if we could use him the same

06:28:10.020 --> 06:28:10.259
way.

06:28:10.319 --> 06:28:12.720
Luna shivered.

06:28:12.779 --> 06:28:15.299
She could not, in any universe.

06:28:15.360 --> 06:28:17.580
Imagine Kibley becoming another queen

06:28:17.580 --> 06:28:18.119
wasp.

06:28:18.180 --> 06:28:20.340
Lizard shrugged.

06:28:20.400 --> 06:28:23.700
Anyway, she's only in charge of the hive

06:28:23.700 --> 06:28:25.139
wings when he lets her be.

06:28:25.200 --> 06:28:28.200
She thinks she's his equal, but she is

06:28:28.200 --> 06:28:29.580
basically one of his big toes.

06:28:29.700 --> 06:28:32.400
Luna thought it was fascinating.

06:28:32.459 --> 06:28:35.459
How sometimes lizard said he, and

06:28:35.459 --> 06:28:36.779
sometimes she said we.

06:28:36.900 --> 06:28:41.220
Do you have, um, big toes of your own?

06:28:41.220 --> 06:28:42.060
she asked.

06:28:42.119 --> 06:28:45.000
I mean, do you each have separate dragons

06:28:45.000 --> 06:28:45.479
you control?

06:28:45.599 --> 06:28:48.180
No.

06:28:48.240 --> 06:28:50.459
Lizard lay down on the floor.

06:28:50.520 --> 06:28:54.659
They all belong to all 3 of us, me, him

06:28:54.659 --> 06:28:55.500
and the plant.

06:28:55.560 --> 06:28:57.659
But he does most of the active

06:28:57.659 --> 06:29:00.119
controlling because he is an enormous

06:29:00.119 --> 06:29:02.279
jerk when I do anything, and it's not

06:29:02.279 --> 06:29:02.639
worth it.

06:29:02.700 --> 06:29:05.040
And the plant is too stupid to do

06:29:05.040 --> 06:29:07.259
anything on its own, except to make more

06:29:07.259 --> 06:29:07.619
of itself.

06:29:07.680 --> 06:29:09.240
Dusky.

06:29:09.299 --> 06:29:11.580
I hate this conversation.

06:29:11.639 --> 06:29:13.380
It's so boring.

06:29:13.439 --> 06:29:15.119
Make her stop.

06:29:15.240 --> 06:29:18.599
Almost done, Luna said.

06:29:18.659 --> 06:29:21.000
Although really she suspected she could

06:29:21.000 --> 06:29:22.680
have asked questions for years.

06:29:22.740 --> 06:29:24.900
She felt like cricket must feel all the

06:29:24.900 --> 06:29:27.119
time, overwhelmed by everything she

06:29:27.119 --> 06:29:27.659
wanted to know.

06:29:27.720 --> 06:29:30.599
This is important, Lizard.

06:29:30.659 --> 06:29:32.520
If I saw something in one of my

06:29:32.520 --> 06:29:32.939
memories.

06:29:33.000 --> 06:29:35.400
Would Cottonmouth be able to go into that

06:29:35.400 --> 06:29:36.419
memory and study it?

06:29:36.540 --> 06:29:40.080
That is, like a book I opened or

06:29:40.080 --> 06:29:40.319
something?

06:29:40.380 --> 06:29:42.720
Could he go in and read the pages?

06:29:42.779 --> 06:29:44.880
Even if I didn't read them or don't

06:29:44.880 --> 06:29:46.080
remember them word for word?

06:29:46.139 --> 06:29:49.500
She hoped that was vague enough, but

06:29:49.500 --> 06:29:50.340
would give her a clear answer.

06:29:50.400 --> 06:29:53.220
She needed to be sure that Cottonmouth

06:29:53.220 --> 06:29:55.500
couldn't use her memories to copy the map

06:29:55.500 --> 06:29:57.479
from Pentala to Pyrea.

06:29:57.540 --> 06:30:00.119
She'd only seen it briefly a few times.

06:30:00.180 --> 06:30:02.220
And she definitely wouldn't have been

06:30:02.220 --> 06:30:03.180
able to draw it herself.

06:30:03.240 --> 06:30:05.700
But what if Cottonmouth could freeze one

06:30:05.700 --> 06:30:07.919
of those moments in her mind and memorize

06:30:07.919 --> 06:30:08.099
it?

06:30:08.159 --> 06:30:11.520
Lizard thought for a while, flicking her

06:30:11.520 --> 06:30:11.759
tail.

06:30:11.880 --> 06:30:14.880
Luna was glad she didn't give a flippant

06:30:14.880 --> 06:30:15.540
angry answer.

06:30:15.599 --> 06:30:18.000
The little dragon could probably guess

06:30:18.000 --> 06:30:21.240
that Luna needed the answer to be no, and

06:30:21.240 --> 06:30:22.740
the fact that she didn't just say that

06:30:22.740 --> 06:30:25.380
right away meant that hopefully she would

06:30:25.380 --> 06:30:25.919
be truthful.

06:30:25.979 --> 06:30:29.279
Luna wasn't sure what she would do if the

06:30:29.279 --> 06:30:30.000
answer was yes.

06:30:30.060 --> 06:30:33.479
She'd promised Lizard her memories, but

06:30:33.479 --> 06:30:35.939
she also could never, never, let

06:30:35.939 --> 06:30:37.619
Cottonmouth get his tendrils on that

06:30:37.619 --> 06:30:37.860
map.

06:30:37.919 --> 06:30:41.759
I don't think he could, Lizard said.

06:30:41.880 --> 06:30:44.400
I haven't seen him do anything like that

06:30:44.400 --> 06:30:45.959
with the memories the humans have given

06:30:45.959 --> 06:30:46.259
him.

06:30:46.319 --> 06:30:48.060
Could you try it?

06:30:48.119 --> 06:30:50.159
With some of the memories you already

06:30:50.159 --> 06:30:50.520
have?

06:30:50.580 --> 06:30:51.840
Luna asked.

06:30:51.900 --> 06:30:54.779
Choose a dragon holding a book or a

06:30:54.779 --> 06:30:56.279
scroll, and see if you can read it?

06:30:56.340 --> 06:30:59.580
Lizard scowled and scuffed her talent

06:30:59.580 --> 06:31:00.119
through the dirt.

06:31:00.180 --> 06:31:04.200
I can't do that, she muttered finally.

06:31:04.259 --> 06:31:05.639
Why not?

06:31:05.700 --> 06:31:08.880
I don't have any dragon memories, all

06:31:08.880 --> 06:31:09.119
right?

06:31:09.180 --> 06:31:10.799
Lizard snapped.

06:31:10.860 --> 06:31:13.380
No dragon has ever said yes before.

06:31:13.439 --> 06:31:16.680
They just won't give them to us, and I

06:31:16.680 --> 06:31:19.080
don't know why, and it's so aggravating.

06:31:19.139 --> 06:31:21.659
Luna blinked at her.

06:31:21.720 --> 06:31:26.340
But you said, The humans give them up all

06:31:26.340 --> 06:31:28.619
the time, Lizard growled.

06:31:28.680 --> 06:31:31.380
They think he's some kind of god, and

06:31:31.380 --> 06:31:32.220
will give him anything.

06:31:32.279 --> 06:31:35.459
We've only had 4 guardians say no in all

06:31:35.459 --> 06:31:37.860
these centuries, including the useless

06:31:37.860 --> 06:31:38.459
one we have now.

06:31:38.520 --> 06:31:41.279
But we haven't absorbed that many dragons

06:31:41.279 --> 06:31:41.639
actually.

06:31:41.700 --> 06:31:44.939
There weren't any here for the 1st 3000

06:31:44.939 --> 06:31:47.459
years, and then the ones that arrived

06:31:47.459 --> 06:31:49.860
figured out the hive mind, and cleared

06:31:49.860 --> 06:31:50.759
the plant from the land.

06:31:50.819 --> 06:31:52.979
They nearly got rid of us entirely.

06:31:53.040 --> 06:31:56.700
The few dragons we had before WASP came

06:31:56.700 --> 06:31:58.560
along always thought Cottonmouth was

06:31:58.560 --> 06:32:01.560
creepy, which he is, and that I'm just a

06:32:01.560 --> 06:32:05.400
baby, or worse, his pet, like some kind

06:32:05.400 --> 06:32:07.080
of traitor to my species.

06:32:07.139 --> 06:32:09.959
So they never, never say yes.

06:32:10.020 --> 06:32:12.720
And I've wanted dragon memories of my own

06:32:12.720 --> 06:32:13.439
for so long.

06:32:13.619 --> 06:32:17.040
She rubbed her snout, ducking her head

06:32:17.040 --> 06:32:17.520
away from them.

06:32:17.580 --> 06:32:19.619
You promised.

06:32:19.680 --> 06:32:22.200
Luna didn't know what to think.

06:32:22.259 --> 06:32:24.659
She wanted to be sure the map would be

06:32:24.659 --> 06:32:27.659
safe, but she also felt so sorry for this

06:32:27.659 --> 06:32:28.680
awful little dragon.

06:32:28.740 --> 06:32:31.799
She's never known what it's really like

06:32:31.799 --> 06:32:33.119
to live a dragon life.

06:32:33.180 --> 06:32:36.659
She's never been part of the tapestry.

06:32:36.720 --> 06:32:39.599
She's like a thread of silk that didn't

06:32:39.599 --> 06:32:40.560
get woven in anywhere.

06:32:40.680 --> 06:32:45.000
Take mine 1st then, Dusky said.

06:32:45.119 --> 06:32:47.340
See if you can read any of my books.

06:32:47.459 --> 06:32:51.299
Lizard turned to him eagerly, her eyes

06:32:51.299 --> 06:32:51.959
sparking.

06:32:52.020 --> 06:32:53.819
That's a yes?

06:32:53.880 --> 06:32:54.419
I can have them.

06:32:54.540 --> 06:32:57.900
He nodded, and she grabbed his front

06:32:57.900 --> 06:33:00.360
talons, lacing their claws together.

06:33:00.419 --> 06:33:04.619
A long, hushed silence followed, and then

06:33:04.619 --> 06:33:07.200
lizard exhaled, let go of him, and

06:33:07.200 --> 06:33:09.000
pressed her talons to her temples.

06:33:09.240 --> 06:33:11.520
Wow, she whispered.

06:33:11.580 --> 06:33:14.639
Luna was about to ask what it felt like

06:33:14.639 --> 06:33:16.979
when suddenly she was surrounded by

06:33:16.979 --> 06:33:17.939
brilliant sunlight.

06:33:18.060 --> 06:33:21.060
Lizard stood beside her, blinking

06:33:21.060 --> 06:33:21.540
rapidly.

06:33:21.599 --> 06:33:24.779
They were high up in the web canopy, with

06:33:24.779 --> 06:33:26.639
silk wings peacefully climbing or

06:33:26.639 --> 06:33:29.400
sleeping or weaving in cells and hammocks

06:33:29.400 --> 06:33:29.880
all around them.

06:33:29.939 --> 06:33:32.459
My tribe.

06:33:32.520 --> 06:33:34.799
Luna's heart skipped a beat.

06:33:34.860 --> 06:33:37.500
She'd almost forgotten what normal life

06:33:37.500 --> 06:33:39.959
had been like in the webs, away from the

06:33:39.959 --> 06:33:42.720
hive wings, the shimmering scale colors

06:33:42.720 --> 06:33:46.020
the soft silk under her talons, the quiet

06:33:46.020 --> 06:33:48.000
murmurs of dragon families all around

06:33:48.000 --> 06:33:50.040
them, the sunlight.

06:33:50.159 --> 06:33:52.259
She'd missed this.

06:33:52.319 --> 06:33:55.979
It was only hours and snatches, though

06:33:55.979 --> 06:33:57.720
she reminded herself.

06:33:57.779 --> 06:34:01.139
These dragons didn't get to choose their

06:34:01.139 --> 06:34:03.720
homes or families or work assignments.

06:34:03.779 --> 06:34:06.299
They're finding happiness where they can

06:34:06.299 --> 06:34:09.180
but they should have freedom too, and a

06:34:09.180 --> 06:34:10.619
chance to be truly happy.

06:34:10.680 --> 06:34:13.500
She didn't recognize the nearby hive.

06:34:13.619 --> 06:34:16.319
But if this was Dusky's memory, she

06:34:16.319 --> 06:34:17.819
guessed it was bloodworm hive.

06:34:17.880 --> 06:34:20.880
She turned, balancing lightly on the

06:34:20.880 --> 06:34:23.819
canopy, and spotted a version of Dusky so

06:34:23.819 --> 06:34:26.159
tiny, she almost couldn't believe he was

06:34:26.159 --> 06:34:26.340
real.

06:34:26.400 --> 06:34:29.580
He lay curled between the front talons of

06:34:29.580 --> 06:34:32.459
a lavender and silver silk wing, tangling

06:34:32.459 --> 06:34:34.080
a ball of silk thread with his claws.

06:34:34.139 --> 06:34:36.840
The silk wing smiled down at him.

06:34:36.959 --> 06:34:39.180
Try again, Dusky.

06:34:39.240 --> 06:34:42.240
Dada. said Baby Dusky.

06:34:42.299 --> 06:34:44.759
No, no, I'm Dada.

06:34:44.880 --> 06:34:46.319
You're Dusky.

06:34:46.380 --> 06:34:48.240
Dada.

06:34:48.299 --> 06:34:49.200
He ha.

06:34:49.259 --> 06:34:51.540
Dusky batted the ball into his dad's

06:34:51.540 --> 06:34:51.840
nose.

06:34:51.959 --> 06:34:54.599
And his dad snorted and shook his head

06:34:54.599 --> 06:34:55.080
with a laugh.

06:34:55.200 --> 06:34:58.020
The baby beamed with delight at the funny

06:34:58.020 --> 06:34:58.380
noise.

06:34:58.439 --> 06:35:01.979
I, dada, he said confidently.

06:35:02.040 --> 06:35:05.939
You can be Data, his father explained

06:35:05.939 --> 06:35:08.580
wrapping the thread around one of Dusky's

06:35:08.580 --> 06:35:09.060
little talons.

06:35:09.180 --> 06:35:11.340
Data is the boss.

06:35:11.400 --> 06:35:12.180
That's me.

06:35:12.240 --> 06:35:15.000
Data makes all the tough decisions, like

06:35:15.000 --> 06:35:16.020
what we're having for dinner.

06:35:16.080 --> 06:35:18.240
Bye, bye, boss.

06:35:18.360 --> 06:35:19.500
Deske shouted.

06:35:19.560 --> 06:35:22.500
I don't have any bananas.

06:35:22.560 --> 06:35:24.060
You little barbarian.

06:35:24.119 --> 06:35:27.180
It's yams or garbanzo beans again.

06:35:27.240 --> 06:35:27.840
I'm afraid.

06:35:27.900 --> 06:35:31.979
Dusky wiggled out of his dad's talons and

06:35:31.979 --> 06:35:34.500
bounced across the silk web to a pile of

06:35:34.500 --> 06:35:35.700
leaves in the corner of the cell.

06:35:35.759 --> 06:35:38.639
He threw himself into the leaves, and dug

06:35:38.639 --> 06:35:39.599
furiously for a moment.

06:35:39.659 --> 06:35:42.299
Finally, he emerged in triumph.

06:35:42.419 --> 06:35:45.419
Brandishing a very brown, rather squashed

06:35:45.419 --> 06:35:45.900
banana.

06:35:45.959 --> 06:35:50.580
Oh dear, his dad said, laughing again.

06:35:50.639 --> 06:35:54.659
I guess we do have one dead banana.

06:35:54.720 --> 06:35:55.860
Did you hide that?

06:35:55.919 --> 06:35:57.959
And how long ago troublemaker?

06:35:58.020 --> 06:36:01.259
Bye, bye, bye, Dusky said happily.

06:36:01.319 --> 06:36:02.880
He pointed to himself.

06:36:02.939 --> 06:36:04.380
Ah, da da.

06:36:04.500 --> 06:36:05.939
Hmm.

06:36:06.000 --> 06:36:07.080
All right.

06:36:07.200 --> 06:36:09.419
I bow to your impeccable logic.

06:36:09.479 --> 06:36:12.599
His dad said, nodding thoughtfully.

06:36:12.659 --> 06:36:15.720
Dusky trotted over and sat between his

06:36:15.720 --> 06:36:18.419
dad's talons again, cradling his mushy

06:36:18.419 --> 06:36:18.840
banana.

06:36:18.900 --> 06:36:21.599
His dad leaned down and nudged him with

06:36:21.599 --> 06:36:22.020
his snout.

06:36:22.080 --> 06:36:24.479
I love you, Dusky.

06:36:24.540 --> 06:36:27.599
The scene vanished as quickly as it had

06:36:27.599 --> 06:36:28.020
begun.

06:36:28.080 --> 06:36:30.540
Flinging Luna back into the throne room

06:36:30.540 --> 06:36:31.319
mind space.

06:36:31.439 --> 06:36:33.119
Yuck!

06:36:33.180 --> 06:36:34.200
Lizard declared.

06:36:34.259 --> 06:36:35.220
Arrr!

06:36:35.279 --> 06:36:36.540
Why?

06:36:36.599 --> 06:36:37.439
So boring.

06:36:37.500 --> 06:36:39.659
Boo, hiss.

06:36:39.720 --> 06:36:42.180
She threw herself down on the floor and

06:36:42.180 --> 06:36:43.380
covered her face with her wings.

06:36:43.500 --> 06:36:46.680
Dusky stood staring at his face.

06:36:46.740 --> 06:36:48.720
His claws trembling slightly.

06:36:48.779 --> 06:36:52.500
Luna crouched beside him and tucked 2 of

06:36:52.500 --> 06:36:53.340
her wings over his back.

06:36:53.400 --> 06:36:55.860
Did you see that too?

06:36:55.919 --> 06:36:56.939
She whispered.

06:36:57.000 --> 06:37:00.299
He nodded, and a tear slipped down his

06:37:00.299 --> 06:37:00.540
nose.

06:37:00.659 --> 06:37:02.819
Oh, dusky.

06:37:02.880 --> 06:37:04.560
She hugged him close.

06:37:04.619 --> 06:37:06.599
Your dad was wonderful.

06:37:06.659 --> 06:37:10.139
He nodded again, and leaned into her.

06:37:10.200 --> 06:37:11.639
Crying silently.

06:37:11.700 --> 06:37:16.080
Maybe, after all of this is over, we can

06:37:16.080 --> 06:37:18.060
find his mom, Luna thought.

06:37:18.119 --> 06:37:21.000
White Speck said she was shipped off to

06:37:21.000 --> 06:37:22.080
Vinegaroon Hive.

06:37:22.139 --> 06:37:24.240
Maybe we can look for her there.

06:37:24.299 --> 06:37:28.380
She realized with a jolt that she was

06:37:28.380 --> 06:37:31.080
still thinking about an after, as though

06:37:31.080 --> 06:37:31.740
they had a future.

06:37:31.799 --> 06:37:35.400
The image of her and Dusky, snarled in

06:37:35.400 --> 06:37:37.979
vines, shoved its way into her head.

06:37:38.040 --> 06:37:40.259
Lizard said we would die here.

06:37:40.319 --> 06:37:43.380
But Cricket wouldn't let that happen.

06:37:43.439 --> 06:37:46.500
She would find Sundew, and they would get

06:37:46.500 --> 06:37:47.580
Luna and Dusky out.

06:37:47.639 --> 06:37:49.500
Somehow.

06:37:49.560 --> 06:37:52.500
It was so strange to realize that she

06:37:52.500 --> 06:37:53.459
believed in cricket.

06:37:53.580 --> 06:37:56.759
She knew for certain that, hive wing or

06:37:56.759 --> 06:37:58.919
not, cricket wouldn't abandon her there.

06:37:58.979 --> 06:38:02.400
But we'll still have the other mind in

06:38:02.400 --> 06:38:02.880
our heads.

06:38:02.939 --> 06:38:05.340
Even if we do escape the throne room.

06:38:05.400 --> 06:38:09.599
I know so much about it, them, now.

06:38:09.659 --> 06:38:12.000
But I still have no idea how to free the

06:38:12.000 --> 06:38:13.200
dragons they've absorbed.

06:38:13.259 --> 06:38:15.479
I wish I could talk to SoreTail.

06:38:15.599 --> 06:38:19.080
She glanced at Lizard, but the small

06:38:19.080 --> 06:38:21.659
dragon was clearly having some feelings.

06:38:21.779 --> 06:38:24.180
And Luna guessed this would be the wrong

06:38:24.180 --> 06:38:25.619
time to ask for another favor.

06:38:25.740 --> 06:38:28.560
I wonder what's happening with the

06:38:28.560 --> 06:38:28.799
others.

06:38:28.860 --> 06:38:31.200
Will cricket find sundoo?

06:38:31.319 --> 06:38:34.139
Are Kibli and Pineapple and Tsunami all

06:38:34.139 --> 06:38:34.319
right?

06:38:34.380 --> 06:38:36.959
Where are sundoom links and moon?

06:38:37.080 --> 06:38:40.799
It seemed like a long time past before

06:38:40.799 --> 06:38:42.959
Lizard finally lifted her wings and sat

06:38:42.959 --> 06:38:43.439
up again.

06:38:43.500 --> 06:38:46.500
She rubbed her face violently and turned

06:38:46.500 --> 06:38:47.880
toward Luna and Dusky.

06:38:47.939 --> 06:38:51.240
Must be weird having a parent who cares

06:38:51.240 --> 06:38:53.159
about you, she said dismissively.

06:38:53.279 --> 06:38:55.200
Not very dragon like.

06:38:55.259 --> 06:38:57.659
Luna tilted her head.

06:38:57.720 --> 06:39:00.180
Is that really what you think?

06:39:00.299 --> 06:39:01.200
She asked.

06:39:01.259 --> 06:39:03.299
The dragons don't care about their

06:39:03.299 --> 06:39:04.020
dragonettes?

06:39:04.139 --> 06:39:06.299
Lizard Meda.

06:39:06.360 --> 06:39:07.979
Yeah, obviously, face.

06:39:08.099 --> 06:39:13.139
We are reptiles, she said, with startling

06:39:13.139 --> 06:39:13.799
vehemence.

06:39:13.860 --> 06:39:16.080
Lizards don't care about their eggs.

06:39:16.139 --> 06:39:17.939
Reptiles don't love anything.

06:39:18.000 --> 06:39:21.000
That sounds like something Cottonmouth

06:39:21.000 --> 06:39:22.919
has told you, Luna pointed out.

06:39:22.979 --> 06:39:26.099
Maybe even something all the humans have

06:39:26.099 --> 06:39:26.700
always believed.

06:39:26.759 --> 06:39:29.340
But you've been watching dragons like

06:39:29.340 --> 06:39:30.720
Dusky through hive wing eyes.

06:39:30.779 --> 06:39:33.240
You must have seen that dragons can love

06:39:33.240 --> 06:39:33.479
each other.

06:39:33.540 --> 06:39:35.939
Lizard snorted.

06:39:36.000 --> 06:39:39.299
Maybe fluffy little stilt wings can.

06:39:39.360 --> 06:39:42.900
Most dragons don't, not dragons like me.

06:39:42.959 --> 06:39:45.180
Lizard!

06:39:45.299 --> 06:39:48.599
Luna cried, then lowered her voice, as

06:39:48.599 --> 06:39:49.979
she saw a cottonmouth twitch on his

06:39:49.979 --> 06:39:50.279
throne.

06:39:50.400 --> 06:39:52.919
Lizard, think about this.

06:39:52.979 --> 06:39:55.319
We saw your mother in his memory.

06:39:55.380 --> 06:39:58.799
She burned an entire civilization down

06:39:58.799 --> 06:40:00.779
because she loved you so much.

06:40:00.840 --> 06:40:04.500
Lizard opened her mouth, and then closed

06:40:04.500 --> 06:40:07.139
it again, emotions warring across her

06:40:07.139 --> 06:40:07.740
face.

06:40:07.799 --> 06:40:10.919
She was just mad they stole something

06:40:10.919 --> 06:40:11.400
from her.

06:40:11.459 --> 06:40:12.900
She said finally.

06:40:13.020 --> 06:40:16.080
Like Cottonmouth said, dragons are

06:40:16.080 --> 06:40:16.799
violent by nature.

06:40:16.860 --> 06:40:20.400
It was probably like instinctive for her

06:40:20.400 --> 06:40:21.240
to start burning stuff.

06:40:21.299 --> 06:40:24.900
She fluffed her wings back, and her

06:40:24.900 --> 06:40:26.819
expression settled on indignant.

06:40:26.880 --> 06:40:28.560
She could have looked for me.

06:40:28.619 --> 06:40:31.200
She didn't even try to find me before she

06:40:31.200 --> 06:40:32.099
started burning everything.

06:40:32.159 --> 06:40:35.520
We don't know that, Luna said.

06:40:35.580 --> 06:40:37.680
We only know what he knows.

06:40:37.740 --> 06:40:40.500
She flicked her tail at the human on the

06:40:40.500 --> 06:40:40.799
throne.

06:40:40.919 --> 06:40:44.459
Are your memories all as sappy as his?

06:40:44.520 --> 06:40:47.040
Lizard demanded. jerking her chin at

06:40:47.040 --> 06:40:47.459
dusky.

06:40:47.520 --> 06:40:50.340
Some of them, Luna said.

06:40:50.400 --> 06:40:51.299
Probably.

06:40:51.360 --> 06:40:54.720
Lizard blew out a gust of air, then held

06:40:54.720 --> 06:40:55.560
out her talons.

06:40:55.619 --> 06:40:57.119
Give them anyway.

06:40:57.180 --> 06:40:58.799
Did you check?

06:40:58.919 --> 06:41:00.419
I mean, are you sure?

06:41:00.479 --> 06:41:01.860
Luna started.

06:41:01.919 --> 06:41:05.580
Yes, yes, Lizard said impatiently.

06:41:05.639 --> 06:41:08.040
I looked at the books in one of Dusky's

06:41:08.040 --> 06:41:08.819
library memories.

06:41:08.880 --> 06:41:10.860
It felt like I was reading them over his

06:41:10.860 --> 06:41:13.319
shoulder, but then the words slid right

06:41:13.319 --> 06:41:14.759
off my brain when I left the memory.

06:41:14.819 --> 06:41:17.099
Whenever you're trying to protect should

06:41:17.099 --> 06:41:17.400
be fine.

06:41:17.459 --> 06:41:20.580
Luna still wasn't sure this was a good

06:41:20.580 --> 06:41:23.759
idea, but she had promised, and Lizard

06:41:23.759 --> 06:41:25.439
had kept her side of the deal by helping

06:41:25.439 --> 06:41:26.099
her friends escape.

06:41:26.159 --> 06:41:30.119
And maybe, this is the only good thing

06:41:30.119 --> 06:41:31.080
left that I can do.

06:41:31.139 --> 06:41:33.840
I can't help anyone else right now.

06:41:33.900 --> 06:41:36.659
But I can give lizard a chance to feel

06:41:36.659 --> 06:41:38.279
what it's like to be part of our world.

06:41:38.340 --> 06:41:43.139
She sat back, and let Lizard seize her

06:41:43.139 --> 06:41:43.979
front talons.

06:41:44.099 --> 06:41:47.819
She had only about a moment to wonder

06:41:47.819 --> 06:41:50.459
which memory they'd fall into 1st, and

06:41:50.459 --> 06:41:52.560
then they were there, in the art room at

06:41:52.560 --> 06:41:56.040
Silkworm Hall, her and Blue, Sortell and

06:41:56.040 --> 06:41:56.459
Io.

06:41:56.520 --> 06:41:59.340
She was vaguely aware that Lizard and

06:41:59.340 --> 06:42:00.240
Dusky were there too.

06:42:00.360 --> 06:42:03.360
Perched atop the tall cabinets, but they

06:42:03.360 --> 06:42:05.340
faded into the background next to Luna's

06:42:05.340 --> 06:42:06.540
3 best friends in the world.

06:42:06.599 --> 06:42:09.119
Are we allowed to be in here after

06:42:09.119 --> 06:42:09.419
school?

06:42:09.479 --> 06:42:10.979
Blue whispered.

06:42:11.040 --> 06:42:14.459
I need Luna's help with my metamorphosis

06:42:14.459 --> 06:42:14.939
weaving idea.

06:42:15.000 --> 06:42:16.979
Io said cheerfully.

06:42:17.040 --> 06:42:19.500
Are they really going to be mad at us for

06:42:19.500 --> 06:42:20.400
doing extra work?

06:42:20.459 --> 06:42:21.419
I don't think so.

06:42:21.479 --> 06:42:23.459
But the rules.

06:42:23.700 --> 06:42:27.360
Are vague on this point, Swartell said

06:42:27.360 --> 06:42:29.220
bumping blues side with his hip.

06:42:29.279 --> 06:42:30.360
Come on, Blue.

06:42:30.479 --> 06:42:32.279
They totally won't care as long as we

06:42:32.279 --> 06:42:32.880
don't break anything.

06:42:32.939 --> 06:42:35.340
Stop worrying so much, my little

06:42:35.340 --> 06:42:36.000
caterpillar.

06:42:36.060 --> 06:42:39.240
Blue looked around at the mess of silk

06:42:39.240 --> 06:42:41.880
and fluff, and scribbled notes, and ends

06:42:41.880 --> 06:42:43.560
of threads, and spilled dies.

06:42:43.619 --> 06:42:45.720
Ooh, he said.

06:42:45.779 --> 06:42:48.360
Maybe if I tidy up, that'll make them

06:42:48.360 --> 06:42:49.080
less mad.

06:42:49.139 --> 06:42:51.900
Luna laughed from the top of the table

06:42:51.900 --> 06:42:52.919
where she was sitting.

06:42:52.979 --> 06:42:54.840
That would be too funny.

06:42:54.900 --> 06:42:57.900
Silkworm Hall's model student banished to

06:42:57.900 --> 06:42:59.700
misbehavior's way for stealth cleaning

06:42:59.700 --> 06:43:00.599
without permission.

06:43:00.659 --> 06:43:04.080
Blue hesitated, biting one of his claws.

06:43:04.139 --> 06:43:06.180
Do you think I need permission?

06:43:06.299 --> 06:43:07.860
No.

06:43:07.919 --> 06:43:10.319
Luna threw a silk pillow at his head.

06:43:10.439 --> 06:43:12.360
You walking lump of sugar?

06:43:12.419 --> 06:43:13.860
Go ahead and tidy if you want to.

06:43:13.919 --> 06:43:16.919
Her brother happily bustled off to get a

06:43:16.919 --> 06:43:17.220
broom.

06:43:17.279 --> 06:43:20.639
I'll follow him, Swartell suggested.

06:43:20.700 --> 06:43:22.860
Just to make sure he doesn't walk himself

06:43:22.860 --> 06:43:24.240
straight into a high wing guard.

06:43:24.299 --> 06:43:28.080
Thanks, Hordail, Luna said, returning his

06:43:28.080 --> 06:43:28.319
smile.

06:43:28.380 --> 06:43:32.040
As soon as they were gone, Luna and Io

06:43:32.040 --> 06:43:33.240
leaned over the drawing on the table.

06:43:33.299 --> 06:43:36.599
I thought I would use purple for my color

06:43:36.599 --> 06:43:37.680
Io said.

06:43:37.740 --> 06:43:40.139
I love that, Luna said.

06:43:40.200 --> 06:43:42.779
Silver waterfall, Purple Mountains?

06:43:42.840 --> 06:43:46.139
Yes, and some purple butterflies in the

06:43:46.139 --> 06:43:46.799
spray, I think.

06:43:46.860 --> 06:43:50.279
IO glanced around, making sure Blue was

06:43:50.279 --> 06:43:50.759
out of the room.

06:43:50.880 --> 06:43:52.979
She lowered her voice to a whisper.

06:43:53.040 --> 06:43:56.040
But I can't figure out where to hide my

06:43:56.040 --> 06:43:57.060
chrysalis symbol.

06:43:57.119 --> 06:43:58.680
Hmm.

06:43:58.799 --> 06:44:02.040
Luna studied the design again, tilting

06:44:02.040 --> 06:44:02.340
her head.

06:44:02.400 --> 06:44:05.279
This was not long after she'd learned of

06:44:05.279 --> 06:44:06.119
the chrysalis.

06:44:06.180 --> 06:44:08.099
The secret group of silk wings that

06:44:08.099 --> 06:44:09.360
wanted to change things.

06:44:09.360 --> 06:44:11.700
Io was the one who had told her about how

06:44:11.700 --> 06:44:14.159
chrysalis members. wove a little red

06:44:14.159 --> 06:44:16.619
shape into their weavings, a shape that

06:44:16.619 --> 06:44:19.020
could be a leaf or a teardrop, depending

06:44:19.020 --> 06:44:19.860
on how you looked at it.

06:44:19.919 --> 06:44:23.279
It was a small wave to other chrysalis

06:44:23.279 --> 06:44:23.700
members.

06:44:23.759 --> 06:44:25.020
We're out here.

06:44:25.080 --> 06:44:26.520
We'll keep fighting.

06:44:26.580 --> 06:44:28.020
We have one another.

06:44:28.080 --> 06:44:29.639
You're not alone.

06:44:29.700 --> 06:44:33.000
But if you added a fish to the pond below

06:44:33.000 --> 06:44:34.919
the waterfall, Luna suggested.

06:44:34.979 --> 06:44:38.279
It could be purple, but with silver silk

06:44:38.279 --> 06:44:40.619
woven over top of it, so it's partly

06:44:40.619 --> 06:44:42.419
underwater, and you could hide the

06:44:42.419 --> 06:44:44.040
chrysalis leaf in its scales.

06:44:44.279 --> 06:44:48.779
Ooh, IO said, as Blue came back into the

06:44:48.779 --> 06:44:50.220
room, dragging a broom.

06:44:50.279 --> 06:44:52.200
She picked up a pencil and started

06:44:52.200 --> 06:44:52.740
sketching.

06:44:52.799 --> 06:44:56.279
I wish I could do a forest for my weaving

06:44:56.279 --> 06:44:57.779
Luna said dreamily.

06:44:57.840 --> 06:45:00.659
Or for a truly giant tapestry.

06:45:00.720 --> 06:45:03.959
Trees as far as the eye can see, with

06:45:03.959 --> 06:45:06.240
silk wing palaces and playgrounds

06:45:06.240 --> 06:45:08.520
everywhere connecting them, and all the

06:45:08.520 --> 06:45:11.099
dragons are happy and kind, and take care

06:45:11.099 --> 06:45:11.459
of each other.

06:45:11.520 --> 06:45:13.560
Luna.

06:45:13.619 --> 06:45:16.319
Blue paused his weeping, and shot an

06:45:16.319 --> 06:45:17.340
anxious look at the door.

06:45:17.400 --> 06:45:19.860
No trees is definitely a rule.

06:45:19.919 --> 06:45:23.040
Doesn't it seem like a silly rule

06:45:23.040 --> 06:45:23.220
though?

06:45:23.279 --> 06:45:24.360
Luna asked.

06:45:24.419 --> 06:45:26.580
He wrung his talons together.

06:45:26.639 --> 06:45:28.680
I don't want you to get in trouble.

06:45:28.740 --> 06:45:30.959
I don't want anything bad to happen to

06:45:30.959 --> 06:45:31.380
you ever.

06:45:31.439 --> 06:45:35.099
The Luno watching sighed inwardly from

06:45:35.099 --> 06:45:35.459
the future.

06:45:35.520 --> 06:45:37.319
Poor Blue.

06:45:37.380 --> 06:45:39.540
Would never have imagined the trouble she

06:45:39.540 --> 06:45:40.020
was in now.

06:45:40.080 --> 06:45:44.159
I know, sweetness, Luna said, flicking

06:45:44.159 --> 06:45:44.759
her tail at him.

06:45:44.819 --> 06:45:48.540
Don't worry, I'll probably end up doing a

06:45:48.540 --> 06:45:50.400
night sky or something, like everyone

06:45:50.400 --> 06:45:50.639
else.

06:45:50.759 --> 06:45:54.419
Blue exhaled with relief and went back to

06:45:54.419 --> 06:45:54.779
sweeping.

06:45:54.840 --> 06:45:58.020
Io was just leaning forward to show her

06:45:58.020 --> 06:46:00.479
new sketch to Luna when Sortell came

06:46:00.479 --> 06:46:01.200
flying into the room.

06:46:01.319 --> 06:46:05.099
Look out, look out, he said in a rush.

06:46:05.159 --> 06:46:06.360
Headmaster coming.

06:46:06.419 --> 06:46:07.200
Everybody hide.

06:46:07.259 --> 06:46:09.240
He bolted out the door again.

06:46:09.299 --> 06:46:12.840
Io dove into one of the cabinets and

06:46:12.840 --> 06:46:14.159
pulled the door shut behind her.

06:46:14.220 --> 06:46:17.400
Luna shot across the room to Blue, grabbed

06:46:17.400 --> 06:46:19.200
him, and threw him into the pile of

06:46:19.200 --> 06:46:21.479
discarded, half finished weavings that

06:46:21.479 --> 06:46:23.580
Miss Clorin kept in the corner for scraps

06:46:23.580 --> 06:46:24.240
and practice.

06:46:24.299 --> 06:46:27.659
Stay really still, she whispered.

06:46:27.720 --> 06:46:29.639
And then she covered him over with

06:46:29.639 --> 06:46:31.740
weaving scraps, until he was completely

06:46:31.740 --> 06:46:32.099
buried.

06:46:32.159 --> 06:46:34.680
Shouldn't we turn ourselves in?

06:46:34.740 --> 06:46:36.119
He whispered back.

06:46:36.180 --> 06:46:37.680
We weren't doing anything wrong.

06:46:37.740 --> 06:46:40.439
Sh, she said.

06:46:40.500 --> 06:46:42.240
Do not move blue.

06:46:42.299 --> 06:46:45.599
She ducked behind a loom in the farthest

06:46:45.599 --> 06:46:46.380
corner from the door.

06:46:46.439 --> 06:46:48.000
A heartbeat later.

06:46:48.060 --> 06:46:49.799
The headmaster poked his head into the

06:46:49.799 --> 06:46:49.979
room.

06:46:50.040 --> 06:46:53.220
He swiveled his snout in a slow

06:46:53.220 --> 06:46:54.119
appraising arc.

06:46:54.180 --> 06:46:57.720
His gaze lingering on the broom, and Io's

06:46:57.720 --> 06:46:59.819
sketch on the table, and then coming to a

06:46:59.819 --> 06:47:02.459
stop on the weaving discard pile.

06:47:02.520 --> 06:47:04.259
To Luna's horror.

06:47:04.319 --> 06:47:07.200
He stepped stealthily into the room, as

06:47:07.200 --> 06:47:09.479
if the weavings were his prey, and he was

06:47:09.479 --> 06:47:10.259
sneaking up on them.

06:47:10.319 --> 06:47:11.939
I'm over here.

06:47:12.060 --> 06:47:13.380
Luna shouted.

06:47:13.439 --> 06:47:16.080
Bursting out of her hiding spot at the

06:47:16.080 --> 06:47:18.240
same exact moment as Swordtail came

06:47:18.240 --> 06:47:21.240
pelting into the room, yelling, I'm sorry

06:47:21.240 --> 06:47:21.959
I did it.

06:47:22.080 --> 06:47:23.279
Whatever it is, it was me.

06:47:23.400 --> 06:47:26.580
The headmaster jumped nearly a foot in

06:47:26.580 --> 06:47:26.939
the air.

06:47:27.000 --> 06:47:29.520
He swung around and glared at the 2 of

06:47:29.520 --> 06:47:29.700
them.

06:47:29.759 --> 06:47:32.159
What are you doing here after school?

06:47:32.220 --> 06:47:33.540
He demanded.

06:47:33.599 --> 06:47:35.099
Thieving little worms.

06:47:35.159 --> 06:47:36.419
My office, now.

06:47:36.479 --> 06:47:37.979
Thieving?

06:47:38.040 --> 06:47:40.020
Literally, what would we steal?

06:47:40.080 --> 06:47:43.020
Swordell asked as the headmaster pushed

06:47:43.020 --> 06:47:43.500
him out the door.

06:47:43.560 --> 06:47:46.500
Luna started after them, resisting the

06:47:46.500 --> 06:47:48.299
urge to glance back and make sure Blue

06:47:48.299 --> 06:47:49.020
was still hidden.

06:47:49.080 --> 06:47:51.000
Io would get him out safely.

06:47:51.060 --> 06:47:53.400
Why did you do that?

06:47:53.520 --> 06:47:55.680
Lizard called from her perch.

06:47:55.740 --> 06:47:57.900
The memory froze around them.

06:47:57.959 --> 06:48:00.959
Luna shook herself, and turned toward the

06:48:00.959 --> 06:48:01.500
small dragon.

06:48:01.560 --> 06:48:03.119
Do what?

06:48:03.180 --> 06:48:06.419
You enter nitwit, Lizard said.

06:48:06.479 --> 06:48:09.180
You both got caught on purpose, like you

06:48:09.180 --> 06:48:10.680
were volunteering to get in trouble.

06:48:10.799 --> 06:48:12.900
Were your brains not working that day?

06:48:12.959 --> 06:48:15.900
Do silkwing brains work at all?

06:48:15.959 --> 06:48:18.479
Don't be mean.

06:48:18.540 --> 06:48:20.040
Dusky piped up.

06:48:20.099 --> 06:48:21.419
They were helping.

06:48:21.479 --> 06:48:23.580
Helping?

06:48:23.700 --> 06:48:26.939
Lizard echoed, as though he'd said hippo

06:48:26.939 --> 06:48:27.479
carcass.

06:48:27.540 --> 06:48:28.560
Why?

06:48:28.619 --> 06:48:32.400
Blue was about to get caught, Luna said

06:48:32.400 --> 06:48:34.139
pointing toward the corner where her

06:48:34.139 --> 06:48:35.040
brother was tucked away.

06:48:35.099 --> 06:48:38.099
We were distracting the headmaster, so

06:48:38.099 --> 06:48:39.360
Blue and Io could get away.

06:48:39.479 --> 06:48:40.860
It's really not that weird.

06:48:40.919 --> 06:48:44.099
I think it is, Lizard said.

06:48:44.159 --> 06:48:46.979
He could have caught Blue, and you could

06:48:46.979 --> 06:48:47.520
have gotten away.

06:48:47.580 --> 06:48:50.939
But blue would have been so sad if he got

06:48:50.939 --> 06:48:52.439
in trouble, Luna said.

06:48:52.560 --> 06:48:55.020
It didn't bother me or soordail nearly as

06:48:55.020 --> 06:48:55.200
much.

06:48:55.259 --> 06:48:58.919
She hadn't loved the week of punishment

06:48:58.919 --> 06:49:01.380
spent sorting and dying the new bales of

06:49:01.380 --> 06:49:04.500
silk, but SwordTail had been with her, and

06:49:04.500 --> 06:49:06.540
side by side, it hadn't been too bad.

06:49:06.599 --> 06:49:09.840
Besides, we're the ones who talked him

06:49:09.840 --> 06:49:10.799
into staying after school.

06:49:10.860 --> 06:49:13.380
So it would have been really unfair if

06:49:13.380 --> 06:49:14.939
you wound up being the only one punished

06:49:14.939 --> 06:49:15.240
for it.

06:49:15.299 --> 06:49:18.479
Lizard shook her head and made a face.

06:49:18.540 --> 06:49:20.040
So weird.

06:49:20.099 --> 06:49:23.220
He's just... another dragon.

06:49:23.279 --> 06:49:26.279
Who cares if he's sad or it's unfair?

06:49:26.340 --> 06:49:30.479
I mean, we do, Luna said.

06:49:30.540 --> 06:49:31.979
Because we love him.

06:49:32.099 --> 06:49:34.979
Gross, Lizard shouted.

06:49:35.040 --> 06:49:36.299
Stop saying that word.

06:49:36.360 --> 06:49:39.360
She sat up suddenly and grabbed her

06:49:39.360 --> 06:49:39.900
head.

06:49:39.959 --> 06:49:42.360
They jerked abruptly back to the fake

06:49:42.360 --> 06:49:45.119
throne room, and in the mind space, Luna

06:49:45.119 --> 06:49:47.220
could feel a weird thrum in the air.

06:49:47.279 --> 06:49:52.139
Oh, ooh, incoming, Lizard said.

06:49:52.259 --> 06:49:54.000
This one's worth bringing here.

06:49:54.060 --> 06:49:57.959
The thrum intensified for a moment, and

06:49:57.959 --> 06:49:59.340
then there was a sound on the edge of

06:49:59.340 --> 06:50:01.799
hearing that might have been a boom or a

06:50:01.799 --> 06:50:02.099
click.

06:50:02.159 --> 06:50:04.860
And suddenly, Pineapple was sitting

06:50:04.860 --> 06:50:05.700
beside Luna.

06:50:05.759 --> 06:50:08.220
Bright green, and looking petrified.

06:50:08.340 --> 06:50:12.540
Chapter 20.

06:50:12.840 --> 06:50:15.240
Surprise!

06:50:15.299 --> 06:50:16.860
Lizard crowed.

06:50:16.919 --> 06:50:18.360
Pineapple?

06:50:18.419 --> 06:50:19.439
Luna cried.

06:50:19.500 --> 06:50:21.479
She jumped forward to catch him as he

06:50:21.479 --> 06:50:23.520
staggered, but he was bigger and heavier

06:50:23.520 --> 06:50:25.740
than her, and they both collapsed to the

06:50:25.740 --> 06:50:26.040
floor.

06:50:26.099 --> 06:50:30.000
She sat up and patted his face gently.

06:50:30.060 --> 06:50:32.279
Pineapple, are you all right?

06:50:32.340 --> 06:50:33.659
What are you doing here?

06:50:33.720 --> 06:50:35.759
Are you in the abyss in real life too?

06:50:35.819 --> 06:50:39.360
Not yet, Lizard answered for him.

06:50:39.419 --> 06:50:41.759
But he's coming this way with the other

06:50:41.759 --> 06:50:45.360
two, flying fast, with a lot of dragons

06:50:45.360 --> 06:50:45.840
chasing him.

06:50:45.900 --> 06:50:48.659
I mean, he's not the one flying himself

06:50:48.659 --> 06:50:49.319
anymore though.

06:50:49.380 --> 06:50:51.959
She tipped her head toward Cottonmouth.

06:50:52.080 --> 06:50:53.340
He is.

06:50:54.360 --> 06:50:57.479
Oh no, Luna said, her heart's sinking.

06:50:57.540 --> 06:50:59.400
Pineapple, can you hear me?

06:50:59.459 --> 06:51:00.959
What?

06:51:01.080 --> 06:51:02.639
Luna?

06:51:02.700 --> 06:51:05.939
Pineapple held out his talons and turned

06:51:05.939 --> 06:51:07.860
them in front of his face, like he didn't

06:51:07.860 --> 06:51:08.459
recognize them.

06:51:08.520 --> 06:51:11.220
Why did my wings do that?

06:51:11.279 --> 06:51:13.139
Why can't I?

06:51:13.319 --> 06:51:15.000
He trailed off.

06:51:15.060 --> 06:51:16.500
They met Luna's eyes.

06:51:16.560 --> 06:51:18.240
Am I dead?

06:51:18.299 --> 06:51:19.919
No.

06:51:19.979 --> 06:51:21.659
Luna spread her wings.

06:51:21.720 --> 06:51:23.759
You're still alive, pineapple.

06:51:23.819 --> 06:51:25.740
The plant got you, but you're not dead.

06:51:25.799 --> 06:51:28.799
Oh, he said.

06:51:28.860 --> 06:51:31.979
I guess it works on Pyrean Dragons too

06:51:31.979 --> 06:51:32.159
then.

06:51:32.220 --> 06:51:34.139
That answers that question.

06:51:34.200 --> 06:51:36.959
He opened and closed his talons again.

06:51:37.020 --> 06:51:41.040
So this isn't real, and it's controlling

06:51:41.040 --> 06:51:41.880
my body right now?

06:51:41.939 --> 06:51:44.520
Yes, Luna said.

06:51:44.580 --> 06:51:46.619
Technically, he is.

06:51:46.740 --> 06:51:50.220
She pointed to cottonmouth, and pineapple

06:51:50.220 --> 06:51:51.720
squinted at the human in puzzlement.

06:51:51.779 --> 06:51:55.139
But the plant is part of him, or he's

06:51:55.139 --> 06:51:55.500
part of it.

06:51:55.560 --> 06:51:56.939
And so is she.

06:51:57.000 --> 06:52:00.180
Pineapple transferred his confused look

06:52:00.180 --> 06:52:00.900
to Lizard.

06:52:00.959 --> 06:52:03.540
Pineapple, what's happened to the

06:52:03.540 --> 06:52:03.779
others?

06:52:03.840 --> 06:52:06.540
I saw you escape Queen Wasp, but then

06:52:06.540 --> 06:52:06.779
what?

06:52:06.840 --> 06:52:08.759
Did you find moon and everyone else?

06:52:08.819 --> 06:52:11.400
It'll be faster if we go see for

06:52:11.400 --> 06:52:13.619
ourselves, Lizard said briskly.

06:52:13.680 --> 06:52:17.099
The ground fell away from Luna's feet, and

06:52:17.099 --> 06:52:19.380
she yelped in surprise as the sky

06:52:19.380 --> 06:52:20.400
appeared all around her.

06:52:20.459 --> 06:52:24.240
For a startled moment, she plummeted, and

06:52:24.240 --> 06:52:26.159
then she managed to ride herself and

06:52:26.159 --> 06:52:27.720
swing back into an air current.

06:52:27.779 --> 06:52:31.139
The Pentalin coastline was flashing by

06:52:31.139 --> 06:52:34.139
below her, the ocean to her left, an

06:52:34.139 --> 06:52:36.900
inlet to her right, a peninsula jutting

06:52:36.900 --> 06:52:37.319
out up ahead.

06:52:37.380 --> 06:52:40.200
She chanced to look behind her and saw

06:52:40.200 --> 06:52:42.240
clouds of green dragons filling the

06:52:42.240 --> 06:52:42.900
evening sky.

06:52:42.959 --> 06:52:45.299
The leaf wings that had fallen to the

06:52:45.299 --> 06:52:47.880
plant on the snarling river battlefield.

06:52:48.060 --> 06:52:51.000
Right above her was tsunami, her face

06:52:51.000 --> 06:52:51.659
grim.

06:52:51.720 --> 06:52:53.340
Her wings beating furiously.

06:52:53.400 --> 06:52:56.340
Kibble's sword a few wing beats behind.

06:52:56.400 --> 06:52:59.099
His eyes kept darting to the patch of sky

06:52:59.099 --> 06:53:01.560
beside him, where Luna knew he was seeing

06:53:01.560 --> 06:53:02.279
pineapple.

06:53:02.340 --> 06:53:04.979
But she could see cottonmouth floating

06:53:04.979 --> 06:53:06.119
eerily in midair.

06:53:06.180 --> 06:53:08.159
Doing okay?

06:53:08.220 --> 06:53:09.540
Kibley called.

06:53:09.599 --> 06:53:12.779
Cottonmouth tilted his head in that odd

06:53:12.779 --> 06:53:14.520
way he did whenever he was inside a

06:53:14.520 --> 06:53:15.060
dragon.

06:53:15.119 --> 06:53:17.340
Yes, he answered.

06:53:17.459 --> 06:53:20.520
A little furrow appeared in Kibley's

06:53:20.520 --> 06:53:20.819
forehead.

06:53:20.880 --> 06:53:23.520
Don't feel bad about what you did to

06:53:23.520 --> 06:53:24.959
Queen Wasp, he said.

06:53:25.020 --> 06:53:27.180
She would have done much worse to us.

06:53:27.240 --> 06:53:29.400
You're the whole reason we escaped

06:53:29.400 --> 06:53:30.060
pineapple.

06:53:30.119 --> 06:53:33.540
Yes, Cottonmouth said again.

06:53:33.599 --> 06:53:35.759
Kibley looked even more worried.

06:53:35.819 --> 06:53:37.979
Where are we going?

06:53:38.040 --> 06:53:39.599
Tsunami called back to them.

06:53:39.659 --> 06:53:41.099
If we can lose them.

06:53:41.159 --> 06:53:44.880
If we keep flying south, we'll reach a

06:53:44.880 --> 06:53:46.799
big lake, Cotton Mouth said.

06:53:46.860 --> 06:53:49.080
There are a 1000000 caves there where we

06:53:49.080 --> 06:53:49.560
can hide.

06:53:49.619 --> 06:53:51.360
Hello, what?

06:53:51.419 --> 06:53:52.500
Kibley said.

06:53:52.619 --> 06:53:53.880
How do you know that?

06:53:53.939 --> 06:53:56.819
Cottonmouth blinked slowly and looked

06:53:56.819 --> 06:54:00.119
around, his gaze snagging on Luna, Lizard

06:54:00.119 --> 06:54:01.560
and Dusky flying alongside them.

06:54:01.619 --> 06:54:03.840
Luna told me.

06:54:03.900 --> 06:54:05.220
He said at length.

06:54:05.279 --> 06:54:07.020
Oh, right.

06:54:07.080 --> 06:54:09.419
Just your normal, everyday conversation

06:54:09.419 --> 06:54:11.520
about the geography of Penthala?

06:54:11.580 --> 06:54:12.720
Kibli asked.

06:54:12.779 --> 06:54:15.840
That's right, Cottonmouth answered.

06:54:15.900 --> 06:54:18.959
I find it hard to believe those green

06:54:18.959 --> 06:54:20.700
dragons haven't caught us with you 2

06:54:20.700 --> 06:54:21.479
moving this slowly.

06:54:21.540 --> 06:54:24.180
Tsunami observed over her shoulder.

06:54:24.240 --> 06:54:27.180
Stop talking so much, and fly faster.

06:54:27.299 --> 06:54:30.119
Kibley closed his mouth on whatever he

06:54:30.119 --> 06:54:32.520
was about to say, but he cast a worried

06:54:32.520 --> 06:54:34.259
glance sideways at pineapple.

06:54:34.319 --> 06:54:37.259
Hmm, Lizard said.

06:54:37.319 --> 06:54:38.459
Boring.

06:54:38.520 --> 06:54:39.900
Flat, flap, flap.

06:54:39.959 --> 06:54:40.860
We don't need to watch this.

06:54:40.919 --> 06:54:43.799
What if sundew shows up?

06:54:43.860 --> 06:54:44.580
Luna said.

06:54:44.639 --> 06:54:45.840
Don't you want to see that?

06:54:45.900 --> 06:54:48.840
Lizard frowned at Cottonmouth.

06:54:48.959 --> 06:54:51.240
I suppose, she said.

06:54:51.360 --> 06:54:53.759
I guess it would be better to know before

06:54:53.759 --> 06:54:56.099
he starts gloating like a big old gloat

06:54:56.099 --> 06:54:56.459
snake.

06:54:56.520 --> 06:54:59.639
The 3 Pyrean dragons flew without

06:54:59.639 --> 06:55:01.860
speaking for a while, beating their wings

06:55:01.860 --> 06:55:02.639
steadily.

06:55:02.700 --> 06:55:05.279
Luna realized she wasn't getting tired.

06:55:05.340 --> 06:55:08.099
Despite carrying dusky on her back, and

06:55:08.099 --> 06:55:09.360
no matter how long they flew.

06:55:09.419 --> 06:55:12.599
As far as she could see, Lizard was also

06:55:12.599 --> 06:55:14.340
keeping up easily despite her small

06:55:14.340 --> 06:55:14.639
size.

06:55:14.759 --> 06:55:17.099
I guess that makes sense.

06:55:17.159 --> 06:55:20.340
Since we're not really here, or using our

06:55:20.340 --> 06:55:23.880
real wings, Could you jump into pineapple

06:55:23.880 --> 06:55:24.360
and talk to them?

06:55:24.419 --> 06:55:26.279
Luna asked lizard.

06:55:26.340 --> 06:55:28.979
Not allow cotton mouths in there.

06:55:29.040 --> 06:55:30.599
Lizard said with a shrug.

06:55:30.659 --> 06:55:32.040
Oh.

06:55:32.159 --> 06:55:34.439
One of the leaf wings then, maybe?

06:55:34.500 --> 06:55:37.740
They're not going to catch up, Lizard

06:55:37.740 --> 06:55:39.299
pointed out, as though this was

06:55:39.299 --> 06:55:40.259
blindingly obvious.

06:55:40.319 --> 06:55:43.259
Cottonmouth is holding them back, but

06:55:43.259 --> 06:55:44.700
keeping them in sight to drive these

06:55:44.700 --> 06:55:45.419
dragons south.

06:55:45.479 --> 06:55:48.180
Luna did not like the sound of that.

06:55:48.240 --> 06:55:49.740
Why?

06:55:49.799 --> 06:55:52.919
He's bringing them to us in the hopes

06:55:52.919 --> 06:55:54.000
that sundew will follow.

06:55:54.060 --> 06:55:56.639
Lizard rolled her eyes again.

06:55:56.700 --> 06:55:59.580
Is her leaf speak really that

06:55:59.580 --> 06:56:00.240
impressive?

06:56:00.299 --> 06:56:01.200
Luna asked.

06:56:01.259 --> 06:56:03.180
He seems so obsessed with her?

06:56:03.240 --> 06:56:05.939
I guess it's impressive.

06:56:06.000 --> 06:56:08.159
Lizard said with a snort.

06:56:08.220 --> 06:56:10.200
She flexed her own talons.

06:56:10.259 --> 06:56:12.840
It's stronger than mine, that's for

06:56:12.840 --> 06:56:13.080
sure.

06:56:13.200 --> 06:56:16.259
I can maybe double a plant's normal

06:56:16.259 --> 06:56:18.419
growth speed, but I have to stay focused

06:56:18.419 --> 06:56:21.060
on it, and I can make plans move a bit if

06:56:21.060 --> 06:56:21.659
I'm near them.

06:56:21.779 --> 06:56:25.319
But sundew can make them grow so fast.

06:56:25.380 --> 06:56:28.619
If he absorbs her, he could make her

06:56:28.619 --> 06:56:30.479
cover this whole continent in breath of

06:56:30.479 --> 06:56:31.680
evil within a month, I bet.

06:56:31.740 --> 06:56:34.680
Yikes, Luna said.

06:56:34.740 --> 06:56:37.380
She really didn't like the tapestry that

06:56:37.380 --> 06:56:39.900
conjured up in her head, a nightmare of

06:56:39.900 --> 06:56:42.360
vines choking the entire landscape, and

06:56:42.360 --> 06:56:44.459
every dragon wide eyed and hopeless.

06:56:44.580 --> 06:56:48.419
They flew onward, as the sky darkened

06:56:48.419 --> 06:56:50.279
into night, and the moons rose.

06:56:50.340 --> 06:56:52.979
Two of them shimmered over the ocean

06:56:52.979 --> 06:56:55.560
casting silvery tails that seemed to

06:56:55.560 --> 06:56:57.659
belong to giant distant dragons.

06:56:57.720 --> 06:57:00.299
Maybe sundew shouldn't have come with

06:57:00.299 --> 06:57:00.419
us.

06:57:00.540 --> 06:57:03.720
Maybe she should have stayed in Pyria, so

06:57:03.720 --> 06:57:05.340
Cottonmouth couldn't get her and her

06:57:05.340 --> 06:57:05.580
power.

06:57:05.639 --> 06:57:09.180
But maybe, she's the only one who can

06:57:09.180 --> 06:57:09.479
stop him.

06:57:09.599 --> 06:57:12.119
If her leaf speak is that strong.

06:57:12.240 --> 06:57:15.240
Maybe bringing her into the abyss will

06:57:15.240 --> 06:57:17.040
mean she can control the plant and

06:57:17.040 --> 06:57:17.520
destroy it.

06:57:17.580 --> 06:57:21.060
It was interesting that Lizard had leaf

06:57:21.060 --> 06:57:21.540
speak too.

06:57:21.659 --> 06:57:24.180
Maybe leaf wings were descended from

06:57:24.180 --> 06:57:26.220
lizard's mother way, way back.

06:57:26.340 --> 06:57:28.560
Maybe other tribes were too.

06:57:28.619 --> 06:57:32.880
Wait, lizard, Luna said. suddenly

06:57:32.880 --> 06:57:33.540
realizing something.

06:57:33.599 --> 06:57:36.720
Are you controlling the vines moving in

06:57:36.720 --> 06:57:37.259
the abyss?

06:57:37.319 --> 06:57:40.560
Like, that's your power, not his?

06:57:40.619 --> 06:57:45.299
All me, Lizard said, banning out her

06:57:45.299 --> 06:57:47.279
wings and soaring to a higher current.

06:57:47.279 --> 06:57:50.099
Otherwise, the plant can only move as

06:57:50.099 --> 06:57:51.299
much as a normal plant.

06:57:51.419 --> 06:57:52.439
Ha ha!

06:57:52.500 --> 06:57:54.360
That's right, you old man.

06:57:54.419 --> 06:57:56.759
She shouted at Cottonmouth suddenly.

06:57:56.819 --> 06:57:59.220
I am important and useful.

06:57:59.279 --> 06:58:02.520
He didn't even turn to look at her, and

06:58:02.520 --> 06:58:03.900
the wind whipped her words away.

06:58:03.959 --> 06:58:08.099
But that means, You're the one who

06:58:08.099 --> 06:58:10.619
blocked the doorway, Luna said.

06:58:10.680 --> 06:58:12.419
And you're the one who's got the vines

06:58:12.419 --> 06:58:14.459
wrapped around me and Dusky in the real

06:58:14.459 --> 06:58:14.819
world.

06:58:14.880 --> 06:58:16.439
You trapped us.

06:58:16.500 --> 06:58:20.040
That's right, Lizard said smugly.

06:58:20.099 --> 06:58:23.279
He couldn't have done that without me, but

06:58:23.279 --> 06:58:24.180
do I get a thank you?

06:58:24.240 --> 06:58:27.720
Does he spend one minute thinking about

06:58:27.720 --> 06:58:28.500
how great I am?

06:58:28.560 --> 06:58:30.779
No, and that's fine.

06:58:30.840 --> 06:58:32.580
I don't think about you either.

06:58:32.700 --> 06:58:37.259
Lizard, Luna said, trying to keep the

06:58:37.259 --> 06:58:38.520
little dragon focused on her.

06:58:38.580 --> 06:58:41.340
That means you could let us go.

06:58:41.400 --> 06:58:44.340
Lizard looked at her as though Luna were

06:58:44.340 --> 06:58:44.700
insane.

06:58:44.759 --> 06:58:46.860
Why would I do that?

06:58:46.919 --> 06:58:49.979
I went to a lot of trouble to get Desky.

06:58:50.040 --> 06:58:53.459
But you have him now, Luna argued.

06:58:53.520 --> 06:58:55.979
He's in your mind space forever, right?

06:58:56.040 --> 06:58:58.319
So you could let his body go free?

06:58:58.380 --> 06:58:59.759
And mine.

06:58:59.819 --> 06:59:02.400
I like him better right here with me

06:59:02.400 --> 06:59:04.619
Lizard said sulkily.

06:59:04.680 --> 06:59:07.080
If I can't go anywhere, why should he?

06:59:07.139 --> 06:59:10.500
But won't he die if you leave him like

06:59:10.500 --> 06:59:10.740
this?

06:59:10.799 --> 06:59:12.180
Luna asked.

06:59:12.240 --> 06:59:15.479
And then he'll be gone really soon, just

06:59:15.479 --> 06:59:15.959
like that.

06:59:16.020 --> 06:59:19.439
Whereas if you let him go, he could live

06:59:19.439 --> 06:59:22.020
so long and be in your mind space giving

06:59:22.020 --> 06:59:23.580
you memories his whole life.

06:59:23.639 --> 06:59:26.819
You are such a pain, Lizard shouted.

06:59:26.880 --> 06:59:28.560
Stop messing with my head.

06:59:28.680 --> 06:59:32.459
She stuck out her tongue at Luna, and

06:59:32.459 --> 06:59:34.500
whisked away to fly next to tsunami

06:59:34.500 --> 06:59:35.099
instead.

06:59:35.159 --> 06:59:38.520
There's something here, Luna thought.

06:59:38.580 --> 06:59:41.819
A way to change things, a way to change

06:59:41.819 --> 06:59:43.500
how lizard sees the world may be.

06:59:43.619 --> 06:59:46.139
Something about her reaction to our

06:59:46.139 --> 06:59:46.740
memories.

06:59:46.860 --> 06:59:49.979
She had the 1st glimmer of an idea.

06:59:50.040 --> 06:59:52.799
She turned it over carefully in her head

06:59:52.799 --> 06:59:55.380
as they flew. thinking about lizard's

06:59:55.380 --> 06:59:58.439
short, awful life, and very long, lonely

06:59:58.439 --> 06:59:58.799
existence.

06:59:58.860 --> 07:00:01.319
Tsunami.

07:00:01.380 --> 07:00:03.119
Look, Kibley called.

07:00:03.240 --> 07:00:06.240
The sea wing swooped around, and Kibli

07:00:06.240 --> 07:00:07.860
pointed down at a speck of light on a

07:00:07.860 --> 07:00:08.700
beach up ahead of them.

07:00:08.759 --> 07:00:10.680
What are you thinking?

07:00:10.740 --> 07:00:11.819
Tsunami asked.

07:00:11.880 --> 07:00:15.119
I think that looks like fire, Kibley

07:00:15.119 --> 07:00:15.360
said.

07:00:15.419 --> 07:00:18.180
And there aren't any free dragons on this

07:00:18.180 --> 07:00:21.419
continent who can make fire, except moon

07:00:21.419 --> 07:00:22.860
moon, or bullfrog, right?

07:00:22.919 --> 07:00:26.400
If one of them has made a fire, so that

07:00:26.400 --> 07:00:29.159
every dragon in Pentala can find them, I'm

07:00:29.159 --> 07:00:30.900
going to shove them into the ocean and

07:00:30.900 --> 07:00:33.000
cover their eyeballs with starfish.

07:00:33.119 --> 07:00:34.560
Tsunami growled.

07:00:34.619 --> 07:00:37.979
But it could be a signal for us, Kibley

07:00:37.979 --> 07:00:38.279
said.

07:00:38.340 --> 07:00:41.279
If I were them, I'd make a fire, then

07:00:41.279 --> 07:00:43.439
turn invisible, and hide nearby to see

07:00:43.439 --> 07:00:44.159
who shows up.

07:00:44.220 --> 07:00:45.479
It's not that stupid.

07:00:45.540 --> 07:00:48.659
Tsunami sighed heavily.

07:00:48.720 --> 07:00:50.759
All right, fine.

07:00:50.819 --> 07:00:51.900
We can check.

07:00:51.959 --> 07:00:54.240
Maybe the dragons chasing us will fly

07:00:54.240 --> 07:00:55.740
right over us in the dark.

07:00:55.799 --> 07:00:58.139
It would be nice if you were a night wing

07:00:58.139 --> 07:00:58.439
right now.

07:00:58.500 --> 07:01:01.680
Wow, there's a sentence I never thought

07:01:01.680 --> 07:01:02.159
I'd say.

07:01:02.220 --> 07:01:05.220
Pineapple, camouflage, she called.

07:01:05.279 --> 07:01:08.580
Cottonmouth tilted his head, then

07:01:08.580 --> 07:01:10.740
squinted as though something very strange

07:01:10.740 --> 07:01:11.939
was coming out of his ears.

07:01:12.000 --> 07:01:15.720
He, he, he, lizard chortled.

07:01:15.779 --> 07:01:17.040
He doesn't know how to do that.

07:01:17.099 --> 07:01:19.380
He's turning all sorts of silly colors.

07:01:19.439 --> 07:01:21.479
Pineapple?

07:01:21.540 --> 07:01:22.439
Kibley said.

07:01:22.500 --> 07:01:24.659
I don't feel well.

07:01:24.720 --> 07:01:26.880
Cottonmouth said hurriedly.

07:01:26.939 --> 07:01:29.400
He veered suddenly down toward the beach

07:01:29.400 --> 07:01:31.139
and the others swung around to follow

07:01:31.139 --> 07:01:31.380
him.

07:01:31.439 --> 07:01:34.259
It was a fire.

07:01:34.319 --> 07:01:36.779
A small one, just a few branches.

07:01:36.840 --> 07:01:39.479
Crackling quietly on an empty stretch of

07:01:39.479 --> 07:01:41.819
sand nearby.

07:01:41.880 --> 07:01:44.040
Moon speckled waves crept ashore and

07:01:44.040 --> 07:01:45.060
rippled out again.

07:01:45.119 --> 07:01:47.880
There were boulders scattered everywhere

07:01:47.880 --> 07:01:51.299
3 times as tall as a dragon, and notches

07:01:51.299 --> 07:01:53.700
in the cliff face behind them, signaled

07:01:53.700 --> 07:01:55.020
caves where dragons could hide.

07:01:55.080 --> 07:01:56.819
Hello?

07:01:56.880 --> 07:01:58.200
Tsunami called.

07:01:58.259 --> 07:01:59.340
Moon?

07:01:59.400 --> 07:02:00.479
Sundew.

07:02:00.540 --> 07:02:01.319
It's us.

07:02:01.439 --> 07:02:05.279
But we are being chased, so Kibley

07:02:05.279 --> 07:02:05.580
started.

07:02:05.639 --> 07:02:07.979
But before he could finish, something

07:02:07.979 --> 07:02:09.659
invisible taggled him to the ground.

07:02:09.720 --> 07:02:11.700
Eep, he yelled.

07:02:11.759 --> 07:02:14.220
Is this an attack or a hug?

07:02:14.279 --> 07:02:17.220
Three dragons appeared out of thin air.

07:02:17.279 --> 07:02:19.740
Sundew was sitting up next to the fire.

07:02:19.799 --> 07:02:22.319
Pressing the ice wing wristbands together

07:02:22.319 --> 07:02:25.139
with lynx standing nearby, smiling.

07:02:25.259 --> 07:02:28.020
Moon had her arms and wings wrapped

07:02:28.020 --> 07:02:30.000
around Kibley, and her face buried in his

07:02:30.000 --> 07:02:30.299
neck.

07:02:30.419 --> 07:02:33.479
And she was radiating happiness so bright

07:02:33.479 --> 07:02:35.939
the fire and the moonlight seemed

07:02:35.939 --> 07:02:36.540
unnecessary.

07:02:36.599 --> 07:02:39.840
Luna had to close her eyes for a moment.

07:02:39.900 --> 07:02:41.759
Sore tail.

07:02:41.819 --> 07:02:43.500
I miss you so much.

07:02:43.560 --> 07:02:48.299
Aw, Kibley said, hugging Moon close.

07:02:48.360 --> 07:02:51.299
Best invisible attack ever.

07:02:51.360 --> 07:02:54.000
You got away.

07:02:54.060 --> 07:02:55.319
Sandu cried.

07:02:55.380 --> 07:02:56.159
Are you all right?

07:02:56.220 --> 07:02:58.139
Are you yourselves?

07:02:58.200 --> 07:03:01.439
Absolutely, tsunami said.

07:03:01.500 --> 07:03:05.819
And, Yes, said Cottonmouth, a little too

07:03:05.819 --> 07:03:07.799
fast, but no one else seemed to notice.

07:03:07.919 --> 07:03:11.639
We wanted to rescue you too, Sundu went

07:03:11.639 --> 07:03:14.340
on, but we'd left Cricket and Luna and

07:03:14.340 --> 07:03:15.299
ran alone for so long.

07:03:15.419 --> 07:03:18.000
We were worried about them.

07:03:18.060 --> 07:03:19.319
Links finished.

07:03:19.380 --> 07:03:22.560
We were hoping if we got to the abyss, we

07:03:22.560 --> 07:03:24.599
could defeat Queen Wasp that way and then

07:03:24.599 --> 07:03:25.500
come back for you.

07:03:25.560 --> 07:03:27.299
Make sense?

07:03:27.360 --> 07:03:28.439
Tsunami said.

07:03:28.500 --> 07:03:30.959
I myself am pretty good at doing the

07:03:30.959 --> 07:03:32.939
smart thing, instead of the impulsive

07:03:32.939 --> 07:03:33.599
thing these days.

07:03:33.659 --> 07:03:35.040
Sometimes.

07:03:35.159 --> 07:03:38.279
Once in a while, I'm working on it.

07:03:38.340 --> 07:03:42.419
I wanted to stay and free you, Moon said

07:03:42.419 --> 07:03:44.099
in a quiet voice to Kibli.

07:03:44.159 --> 07:03:46.919
They were sitting up now, with one of his

07:03:46.919 --> 07:03:48.900
wings around her, and their tails

07:03:48.900 --> 07:03:50.819
intertwined carefully around his venom

07:03:50.819 --> 07:03:51.240
barb.

07:03:51.299 --> 07:03:54.479
But then you remembered that I'm very

07:03:54.479 --> 07:03:56.819
clever, and would totally figure out how

07:03:56.819 --> 07:03:57.779
to escape on my own.

07:03:57.840 --> 07:04:00.360
Kibli joked, right?

07:04:00.419 --> 07:04:01.860
Guess what I did.

07:04:01.919 --> 07:04:03.540
Guess what I did.

07:04:03.599 --> 07:04:06.720
I stood there, like an absolute hero.

07:04:06.779 --> 07:04:08.819
While pineapple saved all of us.

07:04:08.880 --> 07:04:10.380
Didn't I, tsunami?

07:04:10.439 --> 07:04:13.619
Heroes and books talk way less than you

07:04:13.619 --> 07:04:15.299
do, Tsunami said.

07:04:15.360 --> 07:04:17.759
When we get back to school, I'm going to

07:04:17.759 --> 07:04:20.279
start a class called Not Taunting the Bad

07:04:20.279 --> 07:04:22.259
Guys while they're Holding You Hostage

07:04:22.259 --> 07:04:24.479
and you're getting an automatic fail

07:04:24.479 --> 07:04:25.380
before it even starts.

07:04:25.439 --> 07:04:28.439
Rude, Kibley said.

07:04:28.500 --> 07:04:31.020
Bad guys love my taunting.

07:04:31.080 --> 07:04:33.419
Tsunami glance to the sky.

07:04:33.479 --> 07:04:36.659
We should hide, and destroyed this.

07:04:36.720 --> 07:04:40.020
She stepped over and swept sand into the

07:04:40.020 --> 07:04:42.540
fire with her tail and talons until the

07:04:42.540 --> 07:04:44.220
flames were out and the embers were

07:04:44.220 --> 07:04:44.580
covered.

07:04:44.639 --> 07:04:48.540
Back to being invisible, Sandu agreed.

07:04:48.599 --> 07:04:51.419
She held up her talons and glanced around

07:04:51.419 --> 07:04:52.439
at the other dragons.

07:04:52.500 --> 07:04:53.819
Are you ready?

07:04:53.880 --> 07:04:57.240
Meet at the tallest tree by Lake Scorpion

07:04:57.240 --> 07:04:59.639
if we get separated, Link said.

07:04:59.700 --> 07:05:02.220
That's the biggest leg on the southern

07:05:02.220 --> 07:05:03.779
peninsula, apparently.

07:05:03.840 --> 07:05:07.200
Sundoo touched the wristband diamonds

07:05:07.200 --> 07:05:11.459
together and murmured, Hidden B. And all

07:05:11.459 --> 07:05:13.080
6 of them flickered out of sight

07:05:13.080 --> 07:05:14.700
including Cottonmouth.

07:05:14.759 --> 07:05:17.759
Luna was left standing with Lizard and

07:05:17.759 --> 07:05:19.979
Dusky on what seemed to be a deserted

07:05:19.979 --> 07:05:20.520
beach.

07:05:20.700 --> 07:05:22.740
It felt like a giant blanket of

07:05:22.740 --> 07:05:24.720
loneliness suddenly crashing down and

07:05:24.720 --> 07:05:25.380
smothering her.

07:05:25.439 --> 07:05:28.799
She had forgotten for a moment, that she

07:05:28.799 --> 07:05:29.520
wasn't really with them.

07:05:29.639 --> 07:05:32.400
She'd forgotten that she was half a

07:05:32.400 --> 07:05:35.279
continent away, pinned under vines in a

07:05:35.279 --> 07:05:37.680
dark abyss, absorbed by the other mind.

07:05:37.740 --> 07:05:42.000
And that I might die here, and never see

07:05:42.000 --> 07:05:42.720
any of them again.

07:05:42.779 --> 07:05:46.380
That must be the same like you mentioned

07:05:46.380 --> 07:05:46.919
pineapple.

07:05:47.040 --> 07:05:49.259
Kibley's voice said out of the dark.

07:05:49.319 --> 07:05:52.020
Oh, I can still hear them.

07:05:52.080 --> 07:05:55.500
Because we're getting this through cotton

07:05:55.500 --> 07:05:57.959
mouth pineapple, and he's invisible with

07:05:57.959 --> 07:05:58.200
them.

07:05:58.259 --> 07:05:59.639
She realized.

07:05:59.700 --> 07:06:02.639
That's kind of a weird coincidence that

07:06:02.639 --> 07:06:03.419
you're going there too.

07:06:03.540 --> 07:06:05.040
Kibley went on.

07:06:05.099 --> 07:06:08.700
Cricket and Luna left us a message, said

07:06:08.700 --> 07:06:09.659
Sundew's voice.

07:06:09.720 --> 07:06:10.979
That's where they're going.

07:06:11.099 --> 07:06:13.860
Supposedly the abyss is near there, or at

07:06:13.860 --> 07:06:14.759
least they think so.

07:06:14.819 --> 07:06:18.599
Hmm, Kibley said thoughtfully.

07:06:18.659 --> 07:06:21.299
If everyone is able to fly.

07:06:21.419 --> 07:06:23.340
Tsunami's voice interjected.

07:06:23.400 --> 07:06:25.560
I think we should get as far as we can

07:06:25.560 --> 07:06:26.099
tonight.

07:06:26.159 --> 07:06:29.040
Agreed, said Sundo.

07:06:29.099 --> 07:06:31.139
I'm worried about Ren and the others.

07:06:31.200 --> 07:06:33.900
If they go into the abyss without us, and

07:06:33.900 --> 07:06:34.860
anything happens to them?

07:06:34.979 --> 07:06:38.880
I'm ready to fly, Link said.

07:06:38.939 --> 07:06:41.520
Her voice closer to Luna than Luna had

07:06:41.520 --> 07:06:41.759
expected.

07:06:41.819 --> 07:06:45.419
She wished she could turn and grab Lynx's

07:06:45.419 --> 07:06:47.279
talons, and they could both know the

07:06:47.279 --> 07:06:47.759
other was there.

07:06:47.819 --> 07:06:50.580
Like they had in the sky over the ocean

07:06:50.580 --> 07:06:52.860
the 1st time they turned invisible.

07:06:52.919 --> 07:06:54.599
Me too.

07:06:54.659 --> 07:06:56.939
Moon and Kibley said at the same time

07:06:57.119 --> 07:06:59.099
Ready.

07:06:59.159 --> 07:07:01.740
Cottonmouth agreed, a half beat later.

07:07:01.799 --> 07:07:05.880
Ooh, exciting, Lizard said.

07:07:05.939 --> 07:07:09.060
The beach and the dark starry sky faded

07:07:09.060 --> 07:07:11.520
to gray, and the mind space throne room

07:07:11.520 --> 07:07:12.540
closed in around them.

07:07:12.599 --> 07:07:15.240
Pineapple was still beside Luna.

07:07:15.299 --> 07:07:18.119
He was watching Cottonmouth with a

07:07:18.119 --> 07:07:20.279
faraway expression, as though he were

07:07:20.279 --> 07:07:23.580
trying to unravel a tapestry, not by not

07:07:23.580 --> 07:07:24.000
with his mind.

07:07:24.060 --> 07:07:28.619
More dragons coming to the abyss, Lizard

07:07:28.619 --> 07:07:30.479
said, rubbing her claws together.

07:07:30.540 --> 07:07:32.459
Weird dragons.

07:07:32.520 --> 07:07:35.220
Dragons who probably have more normal

07:07:35.220 --> 07:07:37.919
prickly memories than you 2 cuddly

07:07:37.919 --> 07:07:39.419
butterfly hug monsters.

07:07:39.479 --> 07:07:41.819
It's going to be crowded in our throne

07:07:41.819 --> 07:07:43.200
room for the 1st time ever.

07:07:43.259 --> 07:07:46.200
So many dragons to absorb.

07:07:46.319 --> 07:07:48.779
She grinned to the lea.

07:07:48.900 --> 07:07:52.380
Sundu is going to tear this place apart

07:07:52.380 --> 07:07:55.500
Luna said, with as much ferocity as she

07:07:55.500 --> 07:07:55.979
could muster.

07:07:56.040 --> 07:07:58.919
Uh-huh, Lizard said.

07:07:58.979 --> 07:08:00.000
We'll see.

07:08:00.060 --> 07:08:03.959
There is one thing I can try, Luna

07:08:03.959 --> 07:08:04.619
thought to herself.

07:08:04.680 --> 07:08:08.099
I shouldn't sit here and wait for Sundu

07:08:08.099 --> 07:08:10.319
to save us, especially if this whole

07:08:10.319 --> 07:08:11.400
thing is a trap for her.

07:08:11.459 --> 07:08:14.520
I have to do something, no matter how

07:08:14.520 --> 07:08:15.240
small it seems.

07:08:15.299 --> 07:08:20.759
Lizard, I have a new proposal, Luna

07:08:20.759 --> 07:08:21.119
said.

07:08:21.180 --> 07:08:24.299
Lizard quirked an eyebrow at her, and

07:08:24.299 --> 07:08:25.740
Luna pointed to pineapple.

07:08:25.860 --> 07:08:28.979
If I can convince him to give you his

07:08:28.979 --> 07:08:29.880
memories too.

07:08:30.180 --> 07:08:33.599
I want you to set me and Dusky free.

07:08:33.659 --> 07:08:38.279
Chapter 21.

07:08:38.520 --> 07:08:41.880
No, Lizard said.

07:08:41.939 --> 07:08:44.459
She added a yawn for good measure.

07:08:44.520 --> 07:08:46.919
Obviously not.

07:08:47.040 --> 07:08:50.880
Hear me out, Luna said.

07:08:50.939 --> 07:08:53.220
She sat down and spread her wings.

07:08:53.279 --> 07:08:56.099
You think silk wings must be different

07:08:56.099 --> 07:08:57.299
from other dragons, right?

07:08:57.360 --> 07:08:59.880
That all other dragons will be tougher

07:08:59.880 --> 07:09:02.400
and meaner and stronger than us, or

07:09:02.400 --> 07:09:03.299
something like that?

07:09:03.419 --> 07:09:05.700
Yeah, Lizard said.

07:09:05.759 --> 07:09:06.779
I'm sure of it.

07:09:06.900 --> 07:09:09.900
Other dragons don't do hugging and saving

07:09:09.900 --> 07:09:11.639
each other and sappy nonsense.

07:09:11.700 --> 07:09:14.400
I've seen the ones in cotton mouths

07:09:14.400 --> 07:09:14.939
memories.

07:09:15.000 --> 07:09:16.080
They're terrifying.

07:09:16.139 --> 07:09:18.720
Big and scary.

07:09:18.720 --> 07:09:19.979
To the end hungry.

07:09:20.040 --> 07:09:23.520
I want to feel what it's like to be the

07:09:23.520 --> 07:09:24.659
dragon eating the human.

07:09:24.720 --> 07:09:27.360
I want some memories that match the

07:09:27.360 --> 07:09:29.040
enormous monster I could have been.

07:09:29.099 --> 07:09:32.759
That's why I'm offering you pineapples

07:09:32.759 --> 07:09:33.840
Luna said.

07:09:33.900 --> 07:09:38.220
Oh, pineapple said beside her, and she

07:09:38.220 --> 07:09:39.599
trod on his foot to shut him up.

07:09:39.659 --> 07:09:43.020
That's not enough, Lizard said.

07:09:43.080 --> 07:09:45.840
For me to let you fly out of here?

07:09:45.900 --> 07:09:47.880
One dragon's memories?

07:09:47.939 --> 07:09:48.959
Pfft!

07:09:49.020 --> 07:09:49.919
Never going to happen.

07:09:49.979 --> 07:09:52.319
But you could always bring us back

07:09:52.319 --> 07:09:52.860
couldn't you?

07:09:52.919 --> 07:09:54.779
Luna said desperately.

07:09:54.840 --> 07:09:57.599
You would only be letting our bodies out

07:09:57.599 --> 07:09:58.080
into the world.

07:09:58.200 --> 07:10:00.779
Knowing you could still control them and

07:10:00.779 --> 07:10:01.919
bring us here whenever you wanted.

07:10:01.979 --> 07:10:05.279
She waved her talons at the mind space.

07:10:05.340 --> 07:10:07.799
I feel like we're the ones who aren't

07:10:07.799 --> 07:10:08.880
getting enough out of this deal.

07:10:08.939 --> 07:10:12.240
The small dragon lashed her tail and

07:10:12.240 --> 07:10:13.680
narrowed her eyes at pineapple.

07:10:13.740 --> 07:10:17.939
I can't unblock the door, she said at

07:10:17.939 --> 07:10:18.180
last.

07:10:18.240 --> 07:10:21.540
That's part of his whole elaborate sundew

07:10:21.540 --> 07:10:21.959
trap.

07:10:22.020 --> 07:10:24.959
He'll never let you wander off, even for

07:10:24.959 --> 07:10:27.000
a minute, because you're the bait.

07:10:27.060 --> 07:10:27.959
Remember?

07:10:28.020 --> 07:10:30.479
Luna's wings drooped.

07:10:30.540 --> 07:10:33.540
She had been hoping that wasn't quite all

07:10:33.540 --> 07:10:34.020
she was.

07:10:34.139 --> 07:10:38.819
But I can let you out of the vines, Lizard

07:10:38.819 --> 07:10:39.720
said reluctantly.

07:10:39.779 --> 07:10:40.919
She tossed her head.

07:10:41.040 --> 07:10:43.740
It's a little tiring keeping them wrapped

07:10:43.740 --> 07:10:44.279
around you anyway.

07:10:44.340 --> 07:10:48.119
Luna felt a tightness in her chest start

07:10:48.119 --> 07:10:48.599
to ease.

07:10:48.659 --> 07:10:51.479
She hadn't even realized how hard it had

07:10:51.479 --> 07:10:52.080
been to breathe.

07:10:52.139 --> 07:10:55.560
She closed her eyes and tried to focus on

07:10:55.560 --> 07:10:57.779
feeling her body, her real body.

07:10:57.840 --> 07:11:00.840
She didn't think either lizard or cotton

07:11:00.840 --> 07:11:02.220
mouth were inside it right then.

07:11:02.279 --> 07:11:04.200
It wasn't like they could use her for

07:11:04.200 --> 07:11:05.939
anything, as long as she was still

07:11:05.939 --> 07:11:06.959
trapped in the throne room.

07:11:07.020 --> 07:11:11.220
So much for my great superpower, Luna

07:11:11.220 --> 07:11:11.520
thought.

07:11:11.639 --> 07:11:15.299
The wondrous and rare flame silk, chosen

07:11:15.299 --> 07:11:16.979
by destiny to have fire under her

07:11:16.979 --> 07:11:17.819
scales.

07:11:17.880 --> 07:11:20.279
Ends up in the one situation where she

07:11:20.279 --> 07:11:21.000
can't use it.

07:11:21.060 --> 07:11:24.419
She remembered what she'd down with

07:11:24.419 --> 07:11:25.680
cricket when they were invisible

07:11:25.680 --> 07:11:28.020
grounding herself in her senses other

07:11:28.020 --> 07:11:28.619
than sight.

07:11:28.740 --> 07:11:33.060
She breathed into her scales, sensing the

07:11:33.060 --> 07:11:34.799
places where they touched the damp

07:11:34.799 --> 07:11:35.700
slippery vines.

07:11:35.759 --> 07:11:38.400
Until she could feel her real talons

07:11:38.400 --> 07:11:39.479
stretch and flex.

07:11:39.599 --> 07:11:43.560
Finally, her wings fluttered loose, and

07:11:43.560 --> 07:11:45.360
she stretched them as wide as she could.

07:11:45.419 --> 07:11:49.200
With her eyes closed, she felt her way

07:11:49.200 --> 07:11:51.659
along the vines until she reached Dusky's

07:11:51.659 --> 07:11:53.700
cold scales, and then she carefully

07:11:53.700 --> 07:11:56.220
untangled him too, and hugged him close

07:11:56.220 --> 07:11:56.639
to her chest.

07:11:56.700 --> 07:11:59.279
All right, all right.

07:11:59.340 --> 07:12:02.819
Lizard said impatiently, bringing Luna's

07:12:02.819 --> 07:12:04.200
attention back to the mind space.

07:12:04.259 --> 07:12:06.240
Luna opened her eyes.

07:12:06.299 --> 07:12:09.360
Disconcerted by the feeling of dusky in

07:12:09.360 --> 07:12:11.700
her arms, while her eyes told her he was

07:12:11.700 --> 07:12:14.099
standing a few steps away beside Lizard.

07:12:14.159 --> 07:12:17.040
Big, fierce memories now.

07:12:17.159 --> 07:12:18.360
Lizard demanded.

07:12:18.419 --> 07:12:21.299
Ooh, you're the one with the death spit.

07:12:21.419 --> 07:12:24.779
She eyed pineapple and rubbed her talons

07:12:24.779 --> 07:12:25.740
together with glee.

07:12:25.799 --> 07:12:28.860
Show me all the times you've melted

07:12:28.860 --> 07:12:31.439
dragons' faces with your death spit.

07:12:31.500 --> 07:12:33.599
Um.

07:12:33.720 --> 07:12:37.080
Pineapple gave Luna an, are you sure

07:12:37.080 --> 07:12:37.560
about this?

07:12:37.619 --> 07:12:38.459
Look.

07:12:38.520 --> 07:12:40.919
Trust me, Luna said.

07:12:40.979 --> 07:12:43.439
Tell her yes, she can see your memories.

07:12:43.500 --> 07:12:48.000
All right, Pineapple said, shrugging

07:12:48.000 --> 07:12:48.540
agreeably.

07:12:48.599 --> 07:12:51.299
Lizard grabbed his talons, and a

07:12:51.299 --> 07:12:52.080
heartbeat later.

07:12:52.139 --> 07:12:54.180
They were all standing on a platform in

07:12:54.180 --> 07:12:56.639
the greenest, leafiest place Luna had

07:12:56.639 --> 07:12:57.299
ever seen.

07:12:57.659 --> 07:12:59.580
Luna gasped with awe.

07:12:59.639 --> 07:13:01.799
It was beautiful.

07:13:01.860 --> 07:13:05.159
There were trees all around them.

07:13:05.220 --> 07:13:09.299
Huge trees, 50 times the size of dragons

07:13:09.299 --> 07:13:12.299
and there were flowers everywhere, tiny

07:13:12.299 --> 07:13:15.479
lavender ones that looked like claws, and

07:13:15.479 --> 07:13:18.180
giant bright orange and gold ones, like

07:13:18.180 --> 07:13:21.299
rioting flame silk, and there were birds

07:13:21.299 --> 07:13:23.340
100s of birds in every color.

07:13:23.400 --> 07:13:25.860
Some of them in 8 different colors at

07:13:25.860 --> 07:13:26.220
once.

07:13:26.279 --> 07:13:29.099
And there were glass winged butterflies

07:13:29.099 --> 07:13:32.220
as big as Luna's talons, and everything

07:13:32.220 --> 07:13:34.740
around them smelled like green, and

07:13:34.740 --> 07:13:37.740
mangoes, and bananas, and mammals and

07:13:37.740 --> 07:13:40.020
birds, mammals?

07:13:40.080 --> 07:13:41.220
Oh, yes.

07:13:41.279 --> 07:13:44.520
Now she could see furry little silver

07:13:44.520 --> 07:13:46.740
gray creatures snoozing on the nearest

07:13:46.740 --> 07:13:49.439
branches, and the air was warm and

07:13:49.439 --> 07:13:52.259
buzzing, and sunlight through leaves was

07:13:52.259 --> 07:13:54.479
somehow so much gentler and more peaceful

07:13:54.479 --> 07:13:56.759
than the same sun beating down on the

07:13:56.759 --> 07:13:59.400
hives, and, Luna.

07:13:59.520 --> 07:14:00.659
Dusky breathed.

07:14:00.720 --> 07:14:03.060
I love this place.

07:14:03.119 --> 07:14:05.580
Where are we?

07:14:05.639 --> 07:14:07.380
Lizard demanded.

07:14:07.439 --> 07:14:11.220
The rainforest in the distant kingdoms

07:14:11.220 --> 07:14:12.479
Luna guessed.

07:14:12.599 --> 07:14:15.419
She knew that's where Pineapple's tribe

07:14:15.419 --> 07:14:18.299
lived, but she'd never imagined how close

07:14:18.299 --> 07:14:20.639
it would look to her dream of a silkwing

07:14:20.639 --> 07:14:20.880
future.

07:14:20.939 --> 07:14:23.580
She wasn't sure she could possibly

07:14:23.580 --> 07:14:26.220
capture all this in a weaving, but she

07:14:26.220 --> 07:14:27.540
would be happy to spend her whole life

07:14:27.540 --> 07:14:28.080
trying to.

07:14:28.139 --> 07:14:32.220
Lizard turned in a circle and stomped her

07:14:32.220 --> 07:14:34.139
foot on the polished wooden platform.

07:14:34.200 --> 07:14:36.659
Is there about to be a battle?

07:14:36.720 --> 07:14:38.220
Is someone going to attack?

07:14:38.279 --> 07:14:39.659
Where is he?

07:14:39.720 --> 07:14:43.919
Up there, Dusky said, pointing.

07:14:43.979 --> 07:14:47.279
They looked up and saw a huge leaf

07:14:47.279 --> 07:14:49.500
hammock hanging just beyond the platform

07:14:49.500 --> 07:14:52.860
cuddled inside of it, drenched in

07:14:52.860 --> 07:14:55.860
sunlight, were 2 sleeping dragons, one

07:14:55.860 --> 07:14:58.680
bright yellow with splashes of pink, one

07:14:58.680 --> 07:15:00.779
bright pink, with hints of yellow around

07:15:00.779 --> 07:15:01.139
his ears.

07:15:01.200 --> 07:15:03.119
What?

07:15:03.240 --> 07:15:04.619
Lizard barked.

07:15:04.680 --> 07:15:07.740
The yellow rain wing yawned and looked up

07:15:07.740 --> 07:15:09.000
at the leaf canopy overhead.

07:15:09.060 --> 07:15:12.419
We should probably be done with suntime

07:15:12.419 --> 07:15:12.720
now.

07:15:12.840 --> 07:15:14.520
From his voice.

07:15:14.639 --> 07:15:16.919
Luna realized that was pineapple.

07:15:16.979 --> 07:15:19.139
He looked so rested and happy.

07:15:19.200 --> 07:15:22.799
The pink rain wing shook his head, and

07:15:22.799 --> 07:15:24.419
snuggled farther into the hammock.

07:15:24.479 --> 07:15:26.400
Nuh uh.

07:15:26.459 --> 07:15:28.860
I need more pineapple time.

07:15:28.979 --> 07:15:31.139
Pineapple laughed.

07:15:31.200 --> 07:15:34.200
Your entire life is pineapple time.

07:15:34.259 --> 07:15:35.580
I'm always here for you.

07:15:35.639 --> 07:15:39.659
Because I'm very cute, said the pink

07:15:39.659 --> 07:15:41.279
dragon, with his eyes still closed.

07:15:41.400 --> 07:15:45.299
And excellent at tree gliding and related

07:15:45.299 --> 07:15:46.020
to royalty.

07:15:46.080 --> 07:15:48.840
Hmm, said pineapple.

07:15:48.900 --> 07:15:51.540
If those are my reasons, I must be a

07:15:51.540 --> 07:15:52.740
pretty shallow dragon.

07:15:52.860 --> 07:15:56.040
No, no, said the Pink Dragon.

07:15:56.099 --> 07:15:59.639
You are so deep, the most deep.

07:15:59.700 --> 07:16:01.319
Very deep.

07:16:01.380 --> 07:16:06.599
So, so, DB.

07:16:06.659 --> 07:16:10.560
He trailed off, making snoozy, snoring

07:16:10.560 --> 07:16:10.919
noises.

07:16:10.979 --> 07:16:13.799
Pineapple chuckled softly.

07:16:13.860 --> 07:16:15.299
All right.

07:16:15.360 --> 07:16:18.540
I'll prove what a deep boyfriend I am by

07:16:18.540 --> 07:16:19.560
letting you drool on me.

07:16:19.619 --> 07:16:21.299
Just this once.

07:16:21.419 --> 07:16:24.659
Very cute drool.

07:16:24.720 --> 07:16:26.459
The pink dragon mumbled.

07:16:26.520 --> 07:16:28.319
Jambu.

07:16:28.380 --> 07:16:30.779
A voice called from somewhere out in the

07:16:30.779 --> 07:16:31.080
trees.

07:16:31.139 --> 07:16:34.259
Jumboo.

07:16:34.319 --> 07:16:38.400
Not here. the pink dragon called, waking

07:16:38.400 --> 07:16:38.759
up again.

07:16:38.819 --> 07:16:42.000
No jamboos, no pineapples, just as

07:16:42.000 --> 07:16:42.540
frogs.

07:16:42.599 --> 07:16:44.220
Rubit, go away.

07:16:44.279 --> 07:16:47.400
Luna recognized the dragon who came

07:16:47.400 --> 07:16:48.900
sailing down onto the platform.

07:16:48.959 --> 07:16:51.959
This was Queen Glory, the one who

07:16:51.959 --> 07:16:54.000
currently ruled both the rain wings and

07:16:54.000 --> 07:16:54.840
night wings.

07:16:54.900 --> 07:16:59.580
Jamboo, you goof, Glory said, throwing a

07:16:59.580 --> 07:17:01.200
nut that bounced off the pink dragon's

07:17:01.200 --> 07:17:01.380
head.

07:17:01.439 --> 07:17:03.540
Suntime ended ages ago.

07:17:03.599 --> 07:17:07.979
Told you, Pineapple said, nudging Jambu

07:17:07.979 --> 07:17:08.400
with a grin.

07:17:08.459 --> 07:17:11.939
Jambu flopped one arm and one wing over

07:17:11.939 --> 07:17:13.740
the edge of the hammock, and gave

07:17:13.740 --> 07:17:15.240
glorious soulful look.

07:17:15.360 --> 07:17:19.560
But I'm tired. he said.

07:17:19.619 --> 07:17:23.159
I watched Peacemaker and his little

07:17:23.159 --> 07:17:26.099
friends all morning, and that dragonette

07:17:26.099 --> 07:17:28.380
has so much energy, and it was

07:17:28.380 --> 07:17:29.340
exhausting.

07:17:29.400 --> 07:17:33.000
Yes, well, he could be worse, Glory

07:17:33.000 --> 07:17:33.240
said.

07:17:33.299 --> 07:17:35.639
Zambu, listen, I have to go to

07:17:35.639 --> 07:17:36.180
sanctuary.

07:17:36.240 --> 07:17:37.979
I was hoping you'd come with me.

07:17:38.040 --> 07:17:41.459
Pineapple rested his head on Jambu's

07:17:41.459 --> 07:17:41.819
shoulder.

07:17:41.880 --> 07:17:43.500
Right now?

07:17:43.560 --> 07:17:44.400
Why?

07:17:44.459 --> 07:17:45.779
What's happened?

07:17:45.840 --> 07:17:48.540
Dragons have arrived from the lost

07:17:48.540 --> 07:17:50.700
continent, apparently, Glory said.

07:17:50.759 --> 07:17:52.380
They've come asking for help.

07:17:52.439 --> 07:17:54.599
So we're having a queens gathering.

07:17:54.659 --> 07:17:56.639
I won't know the details until I get

07:17:56.639 --> 07:17:56.880
there.

07:17:56.939 --> 07:17:58.979
But I want to bring a few dragons I can

07:17:58.979 --> 07:17:59.340
count on.

07:17:59.400 --> 07:18:06.479
John Boo said, burying his face in the

07:18:06.479 --> 07:18:07.200
leaf hammock.

07:18:07.259 --> 07:18:11.520
Hours and hours of boring politics talk.

07:18:11.580 --> 07:18:13.680
I mean, yay.

07:18:13.740 --> 07:18:16.560
I could go in his place.

07:18:16.619 --> 07:18:17.939
Pineapple offered.

07:18:18.000 --> 07:18:20.700
Jambu looked up and batted his

07:18:20.700 --> 07:18:21.299
eyelashes.

07:18:21.360 --> 07:18:24.180
Ooh, and I could go back to sleep.

07:18:24.240 --> 07:18:26.939
Glory shrugged elegantly.

07:18:27.000 --> 07:18:29.459
I suppose that's all right with me.

07:18:29.520 --> 07:18:31.740
If you really don't mind coming along.

07:18:31.799 --> 07:18:34.860
I wouldn't mind, Pineapple said.

07:18:34.919 --> 07:18:36.479
I'd like to be helpful.

07:18:36.540 --> 07:18:41.279
Well, I, Jambu said, would like to be

07:18:41.279 --> 07:18:43.439
sleeping instead of helpful.

07:18:43.500 --> 07:18:46.080
Pineapple bummed him with his snout.

07:18:46.139 --> 07:18:49.259
You've done lots of helpful things, he

07:18:49.259 --> 07:18:49.619
said.

07:18:49.680 --> 07:18:51.659
You helped our amazing queen become

07:18:51.659 --> 07:18:52.139
queen.

07:18:52.200 --> 07:18:53.700
Let me take a turn.

07:18:53.759 --> 07:18:56.159
All right, yes.

07:18:56.220 --> 07:18:57.060
Love you.

07:18:57.119 --> 07:18:57.840
Bye.

07:18:57.900 --> 07:19:00.659
Jambu said, wriggling all the way back

07:19:00.659 --> 07:19:01.500
into the hammock.

07:19:01.560 --> 07:19:04.259
Pineapple laughed as he extricated

07:19:04.259 --> 07:19:04.560
himself.

07:19:04.619 --> 07:19:07.680
Once he was hovering in the air beside

07:19:07.680 --> 07:19:10.020
the hammock, he reached in and squeezed

07:19:10.020 --> 07:19:11.279
one of Jambu's talons.

07:19:11.340 --> 07:19:13.259
I'll miss you too.

07:19:13.319 --> 07:19:16.799
Deep and noble.

07:19:16.919 --> 07:19:19.439
John Boo mumbled sleepily.

07:19:19.500 --> 07:19:21.240
Thanks, pineapple.

07:19:21.299 --> 07:19:23.819
Glory said, moving a small blue

07:19:23.819 --> 07:19:25.139
salamander off her tail.

07:19:25.139 --> 07:19:28.500
Hopefully, you'll be home and sleeping in

07:19:28.500 --> 07:19:29.639
the sun again in no time.

07:19:29.700 --> 07:19:33.240
The memory drifted away like morning mist

07:19:33.240 --> 07:19:36.060
slower than the others, leaving the ghost

07:19:36.060 --> 07:19:37.740
of the scent of jasmine in the mind

07:19:37.740 --> 07:19:38.159
space.

07:19:38.220 --> 07:19:41.040
Talons and tentacles!

07:19:41.159 --> 07:19:43.259
Lizard yelled, making them all jump.

07:19:43.319 --> 07:19:45.720
That was even worse than yours.

07:19:45.779 --> 07:19:49.319
She clamped her talons to her temples and

07:19:49.319 --> 07:19:50.459
scrunched her eyes shut.

07:19:50.520 --> 07:19:54.240
Luna glanced over at pineapple, but he'd

07:19:54.240 --> 07:19:56.819
gone back to his far away, undoing knots

07:19:56.819 --> 07:19:57.779
in his brain expression.

07:19:57.840 --> 07:20:01.439
They'd flown together for 3 days, and he

07:20:01.439 --> 07:20:02.880
hadn't let on that he was missing someone

07:20:02.880 --> 07:20:03.779
back at home.

07:20:03.900 --> 07:20:06.240
He'd always acted so cheerful and even

07:20:06.240 --> 07:20:06.779
keeled.

07:20:06.840 --> 07:20:09.959
He might have been really sad all that

07:20:09.959 --> 07:20:11.880
time, and I had no idea.

07:20:11.939 --> 07:20:14.159
I wish he'd told me.

07:20:14.220 --> 07:20:17.040
We could have talked about Jambu and Sore

07:20:17.040 --> 07:20:17.400
Tail.

07:20:17.459 --> 07:20:20.220
At the very least, I could have given him

07:20:20.220 --> 07:20:22.259
a hug or told him I understood.

07:20:22.319 --> 07:20:25.860
Or said thank you, for coming all this

07:20:25.860 --> 07:20:28.560
way and risking so much, to help save

07:20:28.560 --> 07:20:31.020
someone I love the way he loves Jambu.

07:20:31.080 --> 07:20:33.599
We're going to get you home, pineapple

07:20:33.599 --> 07:20:34.380
she said.

07:20:34.439 --> 07:20:37.619
I don't know how, but I promise you'll

07:20:37.619 --> 07:20:37.979
see him again.

07:20:38.099 --> 07:20:41.759
He blinked, as if he were coming out of a

07:20:41.759 --> 07:20:42.360
fog.

07:20:42.419 --> 07:20:44.220
And then he looked down at her and

07:20:44.220 --> 07:20:44.520
smiled.

07:20:44.580 --> 07:20:47.520
Little rays of yellow bloomed all around

07:20:47.520 --> 07:20:48.119
his scales.

07:20:48.240 --> 07:20:51.000
I know, he said.

07:20:51.060 --> 07:20:52.139
I will.

07:20:52.259 --> 07:20:54.299
None!

07:20:54.360 --> 07:20:55.919
Lizard exploded.

07:20:55.979 --> 07:20:58.680
She stormed over to pineapple, and

07:20:58.680 --> 07:21:00.479
deliberately stommed on one of his feet.

07:21:00.540 --> 07:21:03.299
He took a polite step back as she kept

07:21:03.299 --> 07:21:07.439
shouting, not one single face melting.

07:21:07.560 --> 07:21:09.180
What is wrong with you?

07:21:09.299 --> 07:21:11.520
You have death spit?

07:21:11.580 --> 07:21:13.560
And instead of using it for something

07:21:13.560 --> 07:21:16.919
cool, like melting the faces of your

07:21:16.919 --> 07:21:17.400
enemies.

07:21:17.520 --> 07:21:21.119
You spend all of your time, cuddling, and

07:21:21.119 --> 07:21:22.979
eating chocolate, and making up songs

07:21:22.979 --> 07:21:25.200
about pandas with your boyfriend.

07:21:25.319 --> 07:21:27.599
Oh, wow.

07:21:27.659 --> 07:21:30.479
Luna said, thinking about the rainforest

07:21:30.479 --> 07:21:30.720
again.

07:21:30.779 --> 07:21:34.680
She'd only had chocolate twice before, and

07:21:34.680 --> 07:21:36.240
it was almost as wonderful as honey

07:21:36.240 --> 07:21:36.659
drops.

07:21:36.720 --> 07:21:39.479
That sounds like the perfect life.

07:21:39.540 --> 07:21:42.180
I don't have any enemies.

07:21:42.240 --> 07:21:44.759
Pineapple told lizard mildly.

07:21:44.819 --> 07:21:48.479
At least, until Queen Wasp, and that was

07:21:48.479 --> 07:21:49.319
quite stressful, actually.

07:21:49.380 --> 07:21:52.080
I think you might be overestimating the

07:21:52.080 --> 07:21:53.400
awesomeness of face melting.

07:21:53.459 --> 07:21:56.700
You literally make no sense.

07:21:56.759 --> 07:22:00.479
Lizard huffed away, across the throne

07:22:00.479 --> 07:22:02.759
room, and threw herself into a petulant

07:22:02.759 --> 07:22:03.479
sulk in the corner.

07:22:03.599 --> 07:22:07.200
Luna tried sensing her real body again.

07:22:07.259 --> 07:22:10.919
She opened and closed her wings, and felt

07:22:10.919 --> 07:22:13.439
the weight of Dusky in her arms, still

07:22:13.439 --> 07:22:13.799
free.

07:22:13.860 --> 07:22:16.619
So at least a lizard hadn't taken out her

07:22:16.619 --> 07:22:18.959
anger on them by snaring them in the

07:22:18.959 --> 07:22:19.380
vines again.

07:22:19.439 --> 07:22:23.279
When she opened her eyes, Pineapple was

07:22:23.279 --> 07:22:24.060
watching her curiously.

07:22:24.119 --> 07:22:27.360
Why did you let that dragonette think

07:22:27.360 --> 07:22:29.880
she'd find scary memories in my head?

07:22:29.939 --> 07:22:31.680
He asked quietly.

07:22:31.799 --> 07:22:34.919
Because that's what she expects to find

07:22:34.919 --> 07:22:36.000
Luna said.

07:22:36.060 --> 07:22:38.639
But I want her to see that dragons are

07:22:38.639 --> 07:22:39.299
not what she thinks.

07:22:39.419 --> 07:22:42.840
I want her to know what it really feels

07:22:42.840 --> 07:22:46.080
like to live a dragon life, which is

07:22:46.080 --> 07:22:47.279
something she never got to do.

07:22:47.340 --> 07:22:51.900
I want to weave her into our tapestry, she

07:22:51.900 --> 07:22:52.139
thought.

07:22:52.200 --> 07:22:54.779
But she wasn't sure if that would sound

07:22:54.779 --> 07:22:57.119
too mystical and fluffy to pineapple.

07:22:57.180 --> 07:23:02.340
Aw, pineapple said, poor little dragon.

07:23:02.400 --> 07:23:06.000
And I'm hoping she sees that dragons

07:23:06.000 --> 07:23:07.439
mostly want to take care of each other

07:23:07.439 --> 07:23:10.919
and love, and be loved, and not fight all

07:23:10.919 --> 07:23:12.299
the time, or hurt anyone.

07:23:12.360 --> 07:23:15.599
Luna hesitated and took a breath.

07:23:15.659 --> 07:23:19.139
At least, I hope that's what most dragons

07:23:19.139 --> 07:23:19.740
are like.

07:23:19.799 --> 07:23:21.479
Sometimes I'm not sure.

07:23:21.540 --> 07:23:25.500
I mean, I'm not sure about hive wings, I

07:23:25.500 --> 07:23:25.680
guess.

07:23:25.740 --> 07:23:28.139
Pineapple nodded.

07:23:28.259 --> 07:23:30.599
I know exactly what you mean.

07:23:30.659 --> 07:23:33.720
That's how I felt about Nightwings when

07:23:33.720 --> 07:23:35.279
they 1st came to the rainforest.

07:23:35.340 --> 07:23:38.939
They'd done all these terrible things, and

07:23:38.939 --> 07:23:40.500
they thought they were the only dragons

07:23:40.500 --> 07:23:42.840
worth caring about, and that everything

07:23:42.840 --> 07:23:45.119
should belong to them, and they should

07:23:45.119 --> 07:23:47.880
get to decide how all other dragons lived

07:23:47.880 --> 07:23:48.360
their lives.

07:23:48.419 --> 07:23:51.479
I thought they were too different from us

07:23:51.479 --> 07:23:53.279
and they'd only cause trouble.

07:23:53.340 --> 07:23:56.400
He looked down at his talons.

07:23:56.459 --> 07:23:59.279
I didn't see how we could even start

07:23:59.279 --> 07:24:00.000
forgiving them.

07:24:00.060 --> 07:24:02.459
Did you?

07:24:02.520 --> 07:24:03.540
Luna asked.

07:24:03.599 --> 07:24:08.040
It's a work in progress, he said, with a

07:24:08.040 --> 07:24:08.700
rueful smile.

07:24:08.819 --> 07:24:11.040
But they're more like us than I

07:24:11.040 --> 07:24:11.459
expected.

07:24:11.520 --> 07:24:14.459
They wanted to live somewhere safe and

07:24:14.459 --> 07:24:15.479
take care of their families.

07:24:15.599 --> 07:24:18.419
We just had to make it really clear to

07:24:18.419 --> 07:24:20.459
them that they should treat dragons

07:24:20.459 --> 07:24:22.560
equally, even if they're from different

07:24:22.560 --> 07:24:25.500
tribes, and that glory was their queen

07:24:25.500 --> 07:24:28.259
now, and that they had to work to atone

07:24:28.259 --> 07:24:29.220
for everything they did.

07:24:29.279 --> 07:24:32.400
There are some night wings.

07:24:32.759 --> 07:24:35.279
I don't know if I'd call them friends

07:24:35.279 --> 07:24:35.700
yet.

07:24:35.819 --> 07:24:38.220
But I can see that they're trying to be

07:24:38.220 --> 07:24:38.459
better.

07:24:38.580 --> 07:24:40.680
Hmm.

07:24:40.799 --> 07:24:43.500
Luna found it almost impossible to

07:24:43.500 --> 07:24:45.419
imagine trusting any hive wings who

07:24:45.419 --> 07:24:46.080
weren't cricket.

07:24:46.139 --> 07:24:49.139
Pineapple lifted his head and twitched

07:24:49.139 --> 07:24:49.500
his ears.

07:24:49.560 --> 07:24:52.439
Do you hear that?

07:24:52.500 --> 07:24:55.740
Is it cricket coming back?

07:24:55.799 --> 07:24:56.279
Luna asked.

07:24:56.340 --> 07:24:57.659
Oh, wait.

07:24:57.720 --> 07:24:58.319
No.

07:24:58.380 --> 07:25:00.659
You're not where I am in the real world.

07:25:00.720 --> 07:25:01.860
What is it?

07:25:01.919 --> 07:25:06.240
I thought I heard someone say my name, he

07:25:06.240 --> 07:25:06.599
said.

07:25:06.659 --> 07:25:08.279
Turning slowly in a circle.

07:25:08.340 --> 07:25:09.659
Hello?

07:25:09.720 --> 07:25:11.759
Pineapple?

07:25:11.880 --> 07:25:14.819
I heard at that time, Luna said

07:25:14.880 --> 07:25:15.479
startled.

07:25:15.540 --> 07:25:18.720
I'm here, Pineapple said.

07:25:18.779 --> 07:25:19.500
I'm in here.

07:25:19.619 --> 07:25:20.700
Down here.

07:25:20.759 --> 07:25:21.959
Hmm.

07:25:22.080 --> 07:25:24.119
I'm right here.

07:25:24.180 --> 07:25:26.880
Oh, there.

07:25:26.939 --> 07:25:30.540
Found you, Moon said, appearing next to

07:25:30.540 --> 07:25:30.720
him.

07:25:30.779 --> 07:25:32.639
That was very confusing.

07:25:32.700 --> 07:25:36.119
She blinked at the throne room, the small

07:25:36.119 --> 07:25:38.639
dragons staring at her, the silent human

07:25:38.639 --> 07:25:41.819
on the throne, and finally, at Luna.

07:25:41.880 --> 07:25:44.279
Um, where are we?

07:25:44.400 --> 07:25:49.020
Chapter 22.

07:25:49.200 --> 07:25:51.360
Oh, no.

07:25:51.419 --> 07:25:52.860
Luna cried.

07:25:52.919 --> 07:25:54.479
Moon, what happened?

07:25:54.540 --> 07:25:55.979
How did the plant get you?

07:25:56.040 --> 07:25:58.619
The planned?

07:25:58.740 --> 07:26:01.200
Moon said, her eyes going slightly

07:26:01.200 --> 07:26:01.680
unfocused.

07:26:01.740 --> 07:26:02.759
I don't.

07:26:02.819 --> 07:26:05.759
We don't have her, Lizard said.

07:26:05.880 --> 07:26:08.340
She stood up and came over to peer at

07:26:08.340 --> 07:26:08.819
Moon.

07:26:08.880 --> 07:26:10.919
We haven't absorbed this one.

07:26:11.040 --> 07:26:12.840
What in the moons?

07:26:12.900 --> 07:26:14.520
How are you here?

07:26:14.580 --> 07:26:17.520
Kibli, shh.

07:26:17.580 --> 07:26:19.799
Moon said to the air, then shook her

07:26:19.799 --> 07:26:20.220
head.

07:26:20.279 --> 07:26:21.840
Pineapple.

07:26:21.900 --> 07:26:23.819
There's something else in your head, isn't

07:26:23.819 --> 07:26:24.060
there?

07:26:24.119 --> 07:26:27.479
I had to kind of um, slide around it to

07:26:27.479 --> 07:26:27.959
find you.

07:26:28.020 --> 07:26:31.080
He nodded, and she touched one of his

07:26:31.080 --> 07:26:31.740
talons.

07:26:31.799 --> 07:26:33.900
The other mind got you.

07:26:33.959 --> 07:26:35.040
But how?

07:26:35.099 --> 07:26:37.680
I think it was a drink.

07:26:37.799 --> 07:26:39.959
They gave me while we were in the Wasp

07:26:39.959 --> 07:26:41.700
Hive Prison, he said.

07:26:41.759 --> 07:26:44.520
Sorry, I should have been more

07:26:44.520 --> 07:26:45.119
suspicious.

07:26:45.180 --> 07:26:48.180
I bet Kibli and Tsunami didn't drink it.

07:26:48.240 --> 07:26:50.040
Moon.

07:26:50.159 --> 07:26:51.720
Luna said insistently.

07:26:51.779 --> 07:26:52.740
Talk to me.

07:26:52.799 --> 07:26:53.939
How are you doing this?

07:26:54.000 --> 07:26:56.880
The Night Wing scratched her head and

07:26:56.880 --> 07:26:57.720
peered at Luna.

07:26:57.840 --> 07:26:59.759
Are you really here?

07:26:59.819 --> 07:27:01.740
Actually, Luna?

07:27:01.799 --> 07:27:05.040
Yes, Pineapple answered.

07:27:05.099 --> 07:27:07.919
Well, the other mind controls my body.

07:27:07.979 --> 07:27:10.139
My own mind was brought here.

07:27:10.200 --> 07:27:12.360
I think it's a mental construct.

07:27:12.419 --> 07:27:15.900
Like, an imaginary space where several

07:27:15.900 --> 07:27:18.119
minds can meet, as though it's a real

07:27:18.119 --> 07:27:18.360
place.

07:27:18.419 --> 07:27:22.139
The other mind seems to be 3 minds woven

07:27:22.139 --> 07:27:22.439
together.

07:27:22.500 --> 07:27:26.400
The plants, humans, and a young dragons.

07:27:26.520 --> 07:27:28.740
He nodded at Lizard.

07:27:28.799 --> 07:27:31.380
Ha, Lizard said.

07:27:31.439 --> 07:27:35.220
Unlike 5000 years old, you snoozy

07:27:35.220 --> 07:27:35.759
gorilla.

07:27:35.880 --> 07:27:39.540
And Luna is here too, Pineapple said.

07:27:39.659 --> 07:27:42.540
So she must have been caught and taken

07:27:42.540 --> 07:27:43.979
over by the other mind as well.

07:27:44.040 --> 07:27:46.860
Watch out, if you run into her in the

07:27:46.860 --> 07:27:47.279
real world.

07:27:47.340 --> 07:27:50.400
You won't, Luna said.

07:27:50.459 --> 07:27:52.380
I'm in the abyss.

07:27:52.439 --> 07:27:54.240
Moon, how are you here?

07:27:54.299 --> 07:27:58.319
The Night Wing hesitated again for a

07:27:58.319 --> 07:28:01.020
painfully long time, and then she said

07:28:01.020 --> 07:28:02.040
all in a rush.

07:28:02.099 --> 07:28:04.680
Don't be mad, I can read minds.

07:28:04.740 --> 07:28:06.419
What?

07:28:06.479 --> 07:28:07.919
What?

07:28:07.979 --> 07:28:09.900
You...

07:28:10.139 --> 07:28:12.779
I thought you could see the future, Luna

07:28:12.779 --> 07:28:13.200
blurted.

07:28:13.259 --> 07:28:15.479
I can do that too.

07:28:15.540 --> 07:28:17.939
Moon squirmed uncomfortably.

07:28:18.000 --> 07:28:19.979
I didn't know how to tell you.

07:28:20.040 --> 07:28:22.619
It's hard to bring up, and then the

07:28:22.619 --> 07:28:25.020
longer I don't tell someone, the weirder

07:28:25.020 --> 07:28:25.439
it gets.

07:28:25.500 --> 07:28:27.900
I'm still bad at dealing with it.

07:28:27.959 --> 07:28:30.240
It's one of the many things wrong with

07:28:30.240 --> 07:28:30.599
me.

07:28:30.659 --> 07:28:32.220
I'm sorry, Luna.

07:28:32.279 --> 07:28:35.939
If it makes you feel any better, Pineapple

07:28:35.939 --> 07:28:37.799
offered, I just found out too.

07:28:37.860 --> 07:28:41.819
Bullfrog and Sky and Lynx don't know

07:28:41.819 --> 07:28:42.299
either.

07:28:42.360 --> 07:28:44.159
Moon said with a wince.

07:28:44.279 --> 07:28:46.860
Queen Glory thinks we should keep it

07:28:46.860 --> 07:28:48.779
pretty quiet as long as we can.

07:28:48.900 --> 07:28:53.400
The whole time, on the beach, and in

07:28:53.400 --> 07:28:55.680
sanctuary, and when we were flying back

07:28:55.680 --> 07:28:58.200
here, you could hear all my thoughts?

07:28:58.259 --> 07:29:01.500
Everything I was thinking?

07:29:01.560 --> 07:29:03.360
Luna's head was spinning.

07:29:03.419 --> 07:29:06.659
I try not to, Moon said.

07:29:06.720 --> 07:29:09.240
I've gotten better at filtering out most

07:29:09.240 --> 07:29:09.779
dragons.

07:29:09.840 --> 07:29:13.319
I mean, it feels like 100 conversations

07:29:13.319 --> 07:29:15.060
going on all around me at once.

07:29:15.119 --> 07:29:17.580
So I've had to learn how to make it

07:29:17.580 --> 07:29:18.419
quieter.

07:29:18.479 --> 07:29:22.680
Unless you're directly thinking at me, I

07:29:22.680 --> 07:29:24.540
usually can avoid hearing it.

07:29:24.599 --> 07:29:26.220
Three moons.

07:29:26.279 --> 07:29:30.000
Luna had thought all kinds of things at

07:29:30.000 --> 07:29:30.479
Moon.

07:29:30.540 --> 07:29:32.819
She didn't know whether she felt more

07:29:32.819 --> 07:29:35.580
angry at Moon for keeping this secret or

07:29:35.580 --> 07:29:38.040
guilty about all the mean things she'd

07:29:38.040 --> 07:29:38.939
ever thought around her.

07:29:39.000 --> 07:29:41.759
While she was struggling to figure out

07:29:41.759 --> 07:29:42.240
what to say.

07:29:42.299 --> 07:29:45.119
Pineapple brushed Moon's wing with his.

07:29:45.180 --> 07:29:50.759
So right now you're, he prompted, we

07:29:50.759 --> 07:29:52.919
stopped to get some sleep, she said.

07:29:52.979 --> 07:29:55.619
And Kibble asked me to check your mind

07:29:55.619 --> 07:29:57.540
because he said you've been acting

07:29:57.540 --> 07:29:57.779
weird.

07:29:57.840 --> 07:30:00.779
Oh, pineapple, what do we do now?

07:30:00.840 --> 07:30:05.400
Time me up and leave me behind, Pineapple

07:30:05.400 --> 07:30:05.580
said.

07:30:05.700 --> 07:30:08.939
I'm dangerous, as long as he's...

07:30:08.939 --> 07:30:12.119
A strangled roar of fury came from the

07:30:12.119 --> 07:30:12.540
throne.

07:30:12.659 --> 07:30:15.779
Cottonmouth's consciousness was back, and

07:30:15.779 --> 07:30:17.159
he'd finally spotted Moon.

07:30:17.220 --> 07:30:19.680
He shot to his feet and pointed at her.

07:30:19.740 --> 07:30:21.360
How?

07:30:21.360 --> 07:30:22.380
he bellowed.

07:30:22.439 --> 07:30:24.119
What sorcery is this?

07:30:24.240 --> 07:30:28.259
Uh-oh, Moon said, and vanished.

07:30:28.319 --> 07:30:32.459
Cottonmouth roared again and slammed one

07:30:32.459 --> 07:30:34.200
of his fists into the stone behind him

07:30:34.200 --> 07:30:37.380
cracks like lightning zigzagged out from

07:30:37.380 --> 07:30:37.799
the impact.

07:30:37.860 --> 07:30:39.479
Not real.

07:30:39.599 --> 07:30:41.759
Lizard whispered to Dusky.

07:30:41.819 --> 07:30:43.619
So melodramatic.

07:30:43.680 --> 07:30:45.840
What is he doing?

07:30:45.959 --> 07:30:49.380
Luna asked anxiously, as Cottonmouth's

07:30:49.380 --> 07:30:49.979
eyes closed.

07:30:50.040 --> 07:30:53.459
Lizard, is he hurting pineapple or moon

07:30:53.459 --> 07:30:54.119
in the real world?

07:30:54.180 --> 07:30:55.979
Can we see what's happening?

07:30:56.040 --> 07:30:59.819
Lizard shrugged, and flung their minds

07:30:59.819 --> 07:31:00.900
down on a dark beach.

07:31:00.959 --> 07:31:03.959
Rain was pouring from the sky and

07:31:03.959 --> 07:31:05.279
thunders seem to be coming from

07:31:05.279 --> 07:31:06.060
everywhere at once.

07:31:06.119 --> 07:31:09.900
Wet talon prints were scuffling outside a

07:31:09.900 --> 07:31:12.840
nearby cave, and Luna remembered that all

07:31:12.840 --> 07:31:14.580
these dragons were currently invisible.

07:31:14.639 --> 07:31:16.979
She ran toward the sound of shouting.

07:31:17.099 --> 07:31:19.680
Everyone wake up!

07:31:19.799 --> 07:31:20.880
Kibley was yelling.

07:31:20.939 --> 07:31:23.159
Pineapple has the other mind in his

07:31:23.159 --> 07:31:23.580
head.

07:31:23.639 --> 07:31:25.380
That's not true.

07:31:25.439 --> 07:31:27.840
Cottonmouth shouted back.

07:31:27.959 --> 07:31:29.279
Moon does.

07:31:29.340 --> 07:31:31.860
She's the one who's been infected.

07:31:31.919 --> 07:31:33.360
She's lying to you.

07:31:33.419 --> 07:31:36.659
There was a sound of claws connecting

07:31:36.659 --> 07:31:38.939
with scales and a gasp of pain.

07:31:39.000 --> 07:31:40.319
Moon?

07:31:40.380 --> 07:31:42.000
Kibley cried frantically.

07:31:42.060 --> 07:31:43.560
Where is he?

07:31:43.619 --> 07:31:44.819
Tsunami roared.

07:31:44.880 --> 07:31:46.860
Kibli, where's pineapple?

07:31:46.979 --> 07:31:48.479
I think he's.

07:31:49.200 --> 07:31:50.939
Kibley's voice cut out with a yelp.

07:31:51.000 --> 07:31:52.919
Sundo.

07:31:53.040 --> 07:31:54.240
We need to see him.

07:31:54.299 --> 07:31:56.279
Lynx's voice said urgently.

07:31:56.340 --> 07:31:59.040
Use the bracelets, and then make everyone

07:31:59.040 --> 07:32:00.599
but pineapple invisible again.

07:32:00.659 --> 07:32:03.900
A flash of lightning illuminated the

07:32:03.900 --> 07:32:06.060
beach as 6 dragons appeared.

07:32:06.119 --> 07:32:08.459
Sundew in the opening of the cave

07:32:08.459 --> 07:32:11.459
pressing the wristbands together, links

07:32:11.459 --> 07:32:14.580
right behind her, wings touching, Kibley

07:32:14.580 --> 07:32:17.400
on the sand outside, a long, bloody slash

07:32:17.400 --> 07:32:20.159
along his neck, tsunami, a few steps

07:32:20.159 --> 07:32:20.580
away.

07:32:20.639 --> 07:32:22.439
Crouched and ready to pounce.

07:32:22.500 --> 07:32:26.159
Moon in motion, darting away from the

07:32:26.159 --> 07:32:28.740
cave into the boulders, and cottonmouth

07:32:28.740 --> 07:32:31.380
inside pineapple, reared up tall and

07:32:31.380 --> 07:32:33.299
hissing, slashing the air in front of

07:32:33.299 --> 07:32:33.479
him.

07:32:33.540 --> 07:32:35.340
Don't attack him.

07:32:35.400 --> 07:32:37.200
Kibli yelled to tsunami.

07:32:37.259 --> 07:32:38.459
He'll use his venom.

07:32:38.520 --> 07:32:41.459
Sundu, quick, now.

07:32:41.520 --> 07:32:42.900
Leng shrieked.

07:32:42.959 --> 07:32:46.080
Cottonmouth whipped around, fast as a

07:32:46.080 --> 07:32:48.479
cobra, and launched himself at sundew.

07:32:48.540 --> 07:32:51.119
Lynx darted forward at the same moment

07:32:51.119 --> 07:32:53.580
and shot a blast of freezing air at his

07:32:53.580 --> 07:32:53.759
face.

07:32:53.819 --> 07:32:57.060
He rolled out of the way just barely in

07:32:57.060 --> 07:33:00.360
time, so it hit his shoulder instead, and

07:33:00.360 --> 07:33:02.340
he roared with rage and spun to attack

07:33:02.340 --> 07:33:05.040
her, and then 5 of the dragons vanished

07:33:05.040 --> 07:33:05.220
again.

07:33:05.340 --> 07:33:09.299
No, Cottonmouth howled.

07:33:09.360 --> 07:33:12.000
He leaped for the spot where sundew had

07:33:12.000 --> 07:33:14.340
been, and his talons closed on empty

07:33:14.340 --> 07:33:14.939
air.

07:33:15.000 --> 07:33:16.619
You need me.

07:33:16.680 --> 07:33:19.619
He whirled and put his back against the

07:33:19.619 --> 07:33:21.180
rock wall, seething.

07:33:21.299 --> 07:33:23.580
I have your flame silk.

07:33:23.700 --> 07:33:26.099
I'll kill her right now if you fly away.

07:33:26.159 --> 07:33:29.340
Uh-oh, Lizard said.

07:33:29.400 --> 07:33:31.080
Conversationally to Luna.

07:33:31.139 --> 07:33:33.479
I might have to strangle you after all.

07:33:33.540 --> 07:33:36.900
Couldn't you not do what he wants?

07:33:36.959 --> 07:33:38.400
Luna burst out.

07:33:38.459 --> 07:33:41.279
Don't you hate him enough to always do

07:33:41.279 --> 07:33:42.540
the opposite of what he says?

07:33:42.599 --> 07:33:44.700
Don't you want to fight him?

07:33:44.759 --> 07:33:47.459
Lizard scowled.

07:33:47.520 --> 07:33:48.900
Shut up.

07:33:48.959 --> 07:33:50.580
She said with a snarl.

07:33:50.639 --> 07:33:53.580
I do what I want when I know what I

07:33:53.580 --> 07:33:53.819
want.

07:33:53.880 --> 07:33:56.099
But what he does works too.

07:33:56.159 --> 07:33:59.279
I wanted dragon memories, and now I have

07:33:59.279 --> 07:34:01.319
them, even though they're stupid.

07:34:01.380 --> 07:34:03.779
And the whole reason I have them is

07:34:03.779 --> 07:34:05.400
because of his sneaky plans.

07:34:05.459 --> 07:34:07.020
Why should I fight?

07:34:07.080 --> 07:34:08.939
There's nothing to fight for.

07:34:09.000 --> 07:34:12.540
Luna's friends reappeared on the beach.

07:34:12.599 --> 07:34:15.180
In a semicircle around pineapple, but

07:34:15.180 --> 07:34:16.380
several paces away.

07:34:16.439 --> 07:34:18.180
Kibley was the closest.

07:34:18.299 --> 07:34:21.479
In his talons, he held a sharp wooden

07:34:21.479 --> 07:34:24.119
stick, which he lit on fire and pointed

07:34:24.119 --> 07:34:24.720
at pineapple.

07:34:24.779 --> 07:34:28.380
Opposite him in the half circle, Lynx had

07:34:28.380 --> 07:34:30.900
her jaws hinged open, ready to shoot ice

07:34:30.900 --> 07:34:31.740
again.

07:34:31.799 --> 07:34:34.560
But Cotton Mouth's gaze went straight to

07:34:34.560 --> 07:34:36.779
sundew. standing directly across from

07:34:36.779 --> 07:34:37.020
him.

07:34:37.080 --> 07:34:39.540
Are you lying?

07:34:39.659 --> 07:34:40.619
Sundu asked.

07:34:40.680 --> 07:34:42.060
No.

07:34:42.119 --> 07:34:44.580
I have Luna, he said.

07:34:44.639 --> 07:34:46.799
Ask your devil creature.

07:34:46.860 --> 07:34:48.659
He nodded at Moon.

07:34:48.779 --> 07:34:50.580
It's true.

07:34:50.819 --> 07:34:51.720
Moon said.

07:34:51.840 --> 07:34:55.740
Luna was there, in the mind space, with

07:34:55.740 --> 07:34:56.639
real pineapple.

07:34:56.759 --> 07:34:59.819
Does it have cricket and sky too?

07:34:59.939 --> 07:35:01.259
Sundu asked.

07:35:01.319 --> 07:35:02.939
Moon shook her head.

07:35:03.000 --> 07:35:05.400
How did you catch Luna?

07:35:05.459 --> 07:35:07.380
She asked Cottonmouth.

07:35:07.439 --> 07:35:11.639
She flew into the abyss and threw herself

07:35:11.639 --> 07:35:12.540
into my vines.

07:35:12.659 --> 07:35:15.000
Cottonmouth said nastily.

07:35:15.060 --> 07:35:18.180
Perhaps she was trying to prove what they

07:35:18.180 --> 07:35:20.939
say about the tiny, tiny brains of silk

07:35:20.939 --> 07:35:21.419
wings.

07:35:21.419 --> 07:35:23.099
She's still alive.

07:35:23.220 --> 07:35:25.680
But if you want her to stay that way

07:35:25.680 --> 07:35:27.479
you'll come down here and join her.

07:35:27.599 --> 07:35:30.360
Luna lashed her tail.

07:35:30.419 --> 07:35:34.080
Don't listen to him, she said, even

07:35:34.080 --> 07:35:35.400
though she knew they couldn't hear her.

07:35:35.520 --> 07:35:39.419
Sundew and Kibley exchanged glances.

07:35:39.540 --> 07:35:44.220
You want us to come to the abyss, Kibble

07:35:44.220 --> 07:35:44.819
clarified.

07:35:44.880 --> 07:35:46.979
Will you let Luna go?

07:35:47.040 --> 07:35:49.020
If we do, Sundu asked.

07:35:49.080 --> 07:35:50.939
Certainly.

07:35:51.000 --> 07:35:53.880
Cottonmouth said, with a magnanimous

07:35:53.880 --> 07:35:54.779
sweep of his arms.

07:35:54.840 --> 07:35:57.840
I will allow her to fly right back out

07:35:57.840 --> 07:35:59.220
into the open sky.

07:35:59.279 --> 07:36:01.200
In exchange for one of you.

07:36:01.319 --> 07:36:04.139
I think you know who I mean.

07:36:04.200 --> 07:36:06.840
Not going to happen.

07:36:06.900 --> 07:36:08.759
Tsunami growled.

07:36:08.819 --> 07:36:12.299
Sandu made a little wait, gesture at

07:36:12.299 --> 07:36:12.479
her.

07:36:12.540 --> 07:36:15.900
We had been planning a trip to the Abyss

07:36:15.900 --> 07:36:17.040
anyway, she said.

07:36:17.159 --> 07:36:18.360
How about this?

07:36:18.419 --> 07:36:20.880
You lead us there, and we'll see what

07:36:20.880 --> 07:36:21.180
happens.

07:36:21.240 --> 07:36:25.560
Sundo, Link said worriedly.

07:36:25.619 --> 07:36:28.080
Sounds interesting.

07:36:28.139 --> 07:36:31.020
Cottonmouth said, his eyes glittering.

07:36:31.080 --> 07:36:33.060
Sundew pointed at him.

07:36:33.119 --> 07:36:35.040
You fly ahead of us.

07:36:35.099 --> 07:36:37.860
The rest of us will be invisible, so none

07:36:37.860 --> 07:36:39.779
of your zombies can show up and grab us.

07:36:39.840 --> 07:36:42.540
When we get to the abyss, I'll go down

07:36:42.540 --> 07:36:42.779
with you.

07:36:42.840 --> 07:36:44.159
Nobody else.

07:36:44.220 --> 07:36:49.919
R, no, Kibley started, and Links said

07:36:49.919 --> 07:36:53.939
sundo, again, and tsunami growled, but

07:36:53.939 --> 07:36:56.159
Cottonmouth said, agreed.

07:36:56.220 --> 07:36:58.080
He looked up at the sky.

07:36:58.139 --> 07:37:00.060
The rain is slowing.

07:37:00.119 --> 07:37:01.680
Shall we go now?

07:37:01.740 --> 07:37:04.259
Sundew looked at Moon.

07:37:04.380 --> 07:37:06.900
Is pineapple all right in there?

07:37:06.959 --> 07:37:09.840
Will he be okay if we keep flying now?

07:37:09.959 --> 07:37:13.740
Moon's gaze drifted vaguely over Sundew's

07:37:13.740 --> 07:37:13.979
shoulder.

07:37:14.099 --> 07:37:17.099
And Luna realized, she'd seen that look

07:37:17.099 --> 07:37:18.540
on Moon's face a 1000000 times.

07:37:18.599 --> 07:37:21.000
That's her.

07:37:21.119 --> 07:37:23.400
Listening to thoughts expression.

07:37:23.459 --> 07:37:27.299
Or distracted by other dragon's thoughts

07:37:27.299 --> 07:37:27.840
I guess.

07:37:27.900 --> 07:37:30.840
She must be talking to pineapple in the

07:37:30.840 --> 07:37:31.439
mind space.

07:37:31.560 --> 07:37:33.779
He says yes.

07:37:33.840 --> 07:37:35.099
Moon reported.

07:37:35.159 --> 07:37:36.599
Her eyes focusing again.

07:37:36.659 --> 07:37:39.119
He says go save Luna.

07:37:39.240 --> 07:37:41.220
It's not about me.

07:37:41.279 --> 07:37:43.860
Luna couldn't stop herself from

07:37:43.860 --> 07:37:44.340
protesting.

07:37:44.400 --> 07:37:47.580
You have to come destroy the plant.

07:37:47.639 --> 07:37:49.919
She reached for the leaf wing

07:37:49.919 --> 07:37:50.459
hopelessly.

07:37:50.520 --> 07:37:53.520
Sundo, please don't let him catch you.

07:37:53.580 --> 07:37:55.979
You're the only one who can stop him.

07:37:56.040 --> 07:37:59.099
But Sundu couldn't hear her.

07:37:59.159 --> 07:38:01.319
And Luna's claws drifted through her

07:38:01.319 --> 07:38:03.840
friend, as ineffective as smoke.

07:38:03.900 --> 07:38:08.459
Chapter 23.

07:38:08.700 --> 07:38:11.040
See?

07:38:11.099 --> 07:38:14.099
That's the thing, Lizard said, shifting

07:38:14.099 --> 07:38:15.419
them back into the mind space.

07:38:15.479 --> 07:38:17.340
She tossed her head at Luna.

07:38:17.400 --> 07:38:20.639
You tell me to fight cottonmouth, but all

07:38:20.639 --> 07:38:22.500
you really want is to kill the plant

07:38:22.500 --> 07:38:24.180
which means killing me too.

07:38:24.240 --> 07:38:26.700
Of course I'm going to stick with a

07:38:26.700 --> 07:38:28.560
monster who's at least got a reason to

07:38:28.560 --> 07:38:29.819
keep me alive.

07:38:29.880 --> 07:38:31.680
Luna sighed.

07:38:31.740 --> 07:38:33.299
Lizard was right.

07:38:33.360 --> 07:38:36.360
If Sundew managed to crush the plant with

07:38:36.360 --> 07:38:38.819
her leaf speak, then lizard's

07:38:38.819 --> 07:38:40.740
consciousness would die, along with a

07:38:40.740 --> 07:38:42.299
plant and cotton mouth.

07:38:42.419 --> 07:38:45.240
Luna crouched on the floor of the mind

07:38:45.240 --> 07:38:47.700
space temple, and traced a tree in the

07:38:47.700 --> 07:38:49.020
dirt with her claws.

07:38:49.080 --> 07:38:51.720
Her idea about giving lizard real dragon

07:38:51.720 --> 07:38:54.000
memories, hadn't quite worked the way

07:38:54.000 --> 07:38:54.599
she'd hoped.

07:38:54.720 --> 07:38:57.540
She'd wanted to give Lizard a feeling of

07:38:57.540 --> 07:39:00.000
connection, and some understanding of

07:39:00.000 --> 07:39:01.680
dragons from a dragon point of view.

07:39:01.799 --> 07:39:04.259
Instead of cotton mouths, twisted

07:39:04.259 --> 07:39:04.740
perspective.

07:39:04.799 --> 07:39:07.319
It had worked for Luna.

07:39:07.380 --> 07:39:10.439
She felt closer to Dusky and Pineapple

07:39:10.439 --> 07:39:12.779
even with only those two short memories.

07:39:12.840 --> 07:39:16.439
And seeing the rainforest, made Luna feel

07:39:16.439 --> 07:39:17.040
so hopeful.

07:39:17.099 --> 07:39:19.979
She loved knowing that somewhere like

07:39:19.979 --> 07:39:22.919
that existed, and that it was possible to

07:39:22.919 --> 07:39:24.240
live peacefully and kindly.

07:39:24.299 --> 07:39:27.599
If they survived Queen Wasp and the other

07:39:27.599 --> 07:39:27.840
mind.

07:39:27.900 --> 07:39:30.240
The Silk Wings could try to build a home

07:39:30.240 --> 07:39:30.720
like that.

07:39:30.779 --> 07:39:34.799
But perhaps, it only made Lizard feel

07:39:34.799 --> 07:39:35.279
worse.

07:39:35.340 --> 07:39:38.939
Or even less connected, knowing she'd

07:39:38.939 --> 07:39:40.680
never get to go there, or have that kind

07:39:40.680 --> 07:39:41.040
of life.

07:39:41.099 --> 07:39:45.180
I'm sorry about our memories, lizard, she

07:39:45.180 --> 07:39:45.419
said.

07:39:45.479 --> 07:39:50.099
You should be, Lizard said, dragging

07:39:50.099 --> 07:39:51.959
Dusky over and plunking them both down

07:39:51.959 --> 07:39:52.860
beside Luna.

07:39:52.979 --> 07:39:55.680
The angry little dragon drew a circle in

07:39:55.680 --> 07:39:58.139
the dirt, and Dusky leaned over to add

07:39:58.139 --> 07:39:59.040
sun rays around it.

07:39:59.099 --> 07:40:02.220
You all seem to spend your time doing

07:40:02.220 --> 07:40:04.740
things for other dragons, or hugging.

07:40:04.799 --> 07:40:06.900
So much hugging.

07:40:06.959 --> 07:40:08.099
Yeesh.

07:40:08.159 --> 07:40:10.139
She gave a little shudder.

07:40:10.200 --> 07:40:13.500
Dusky drew a snaking line in front of her

07:40:13.500 --> 07:40:14.759
and Lizard added wings to it.

07:40:14.819 --> 07:40:18.900
It's just my luck that the 3 most boring

07:40:18.900 --> 07:40:21.360
dragons ever are the ones who agree to

07:40:21.360 --> 07:40:22.200
give me their memories.

07:40:22.259 --> 07:40:26.159
Actually, I meant I'm sorry if our

07:40:26.159 --> 07:40:27.299
memories made you sad.

07:40:27.360 --> 07:40:29.040
Luna offered.

07:40:29.099 --> 07:40:32.520
Lizard gave her the most outraged look

07:40:32.520 --> 07:40:33.479
Luna had ever seen.

07:40:33.540 --> 07:40:36.540
I'm not sad.

07:40:36.599 --> 07:40:37.560
They didn't make me sad.

07:40:37.619 --> 07:40:39.299
What a weird thing to say.

07:40:39.419 --> 07:40:41.220
Why would I be sad?

07:40:41.279 --> 07:40:44.819
Because no one's ever hugged you?

07:40:44.880 --> 07:40:46.500
Dusky guessed.

07:40:46.560 --> 07:40:48.659
I don't care about that.

07:40:48.720 --> 07:40:52.380
Lizard shoved him over, so he toppled on

07:40:52.380 --> 07:40:52.619
his side.

07:40:52.680 --> 07:40:56.040
I never got to set anyone on fire.

07:40:56.099 --> 07:40:59.400
I never got to fly into battle, or eat a

07:40:59.400 --> 07:41:01.439
human, or stab anyone even once.

07:41:01.500 --> 07:41:03.779
That's what I'm sad about.

07:41:03.840 --> 07:41:05.400
Real dragon stuff.

07:41:05.520 --> 07:41:07.740
Except, I'm not sad.

07:41:07.799 --> 07:41:08.400
Shut up.

07:41:08.459 --> 07:41:12.959
Hugs are better than all of that, Dusky

07:41:12.959 --> 07:41:14.939
said, sitting himself up again.

07:41:15.000 --> 07:41:17.520
I barf at you.

07:41:17.580 --> 07:41:19.139
Lizard snapped.

07:41:19.200 --> 07:41:21.119
Do you want one?

07:41:21.240 --> 07:41:22.560
Dusky asked.

07:41:22.619 --> 07:41:25.979
Maybe you'll like them better if you get

07:41:25.979 --> 07:41:26.700
a real hug.

07:41:26.759 --> 07:41:29.279
It won't be real.

07:41:29.340 --> 07:41:30.900
Lizard barked.

07:41:30.959 --> 07:41:32.459
Nothing about this is real.

07:41:32.580 --> 07:41:37.439
But It would be close, right?

07:41:37.500 --> 07:41:38.340
He said.

07:41:38.459 --> 07:41:40.200
Can I hug you?

07:41:40.259 --> 07:41:43.799
She scowled ferociously.

07:41:43.860 --> 07:41:47.220
Then wrapped her wings around herself and

07:41:47.220 --> 07:41:48.180
hunched her shoulders.

07:41:48.240 --> 07:41:49.860
Fine.

07:41:49.919 --> 07:41:52.619
But only if you promise to shut up about

07:41:52.619 --> 07:41:54.779
hugs and sad feelings from now on.

07:41:54.840 --> 07:41:58.380
Dusky didn't have wings to hug with yet

07:41:58.380 --> 07:42:01.680
but even as tiny as he was, he was still

07:42:01.680 --> 07:42:02.520
bigger than lizard.

07:42:02.639 --> 07:42:06.119
His arms fit around her folded wings, and

07:42:06.119 --> 07:42:07.500
he rested his chin on the top of her

07:42:07.500 --> 07:42:07.740
head.

07:42:07.799 --> 07:42:09.900
Humph.

07:42:09.959 --> 07:42:11.819
Lizard muttered after a moment.

07:42:11.880 --> 07:42:13.619
Stupid.

07:42:13.680 --> 07:42:15.959
But she didn't push him away.

07:42:16.020 --> 07:42:18.599
Luna watched them for a moment.

07:42:18.659 --> 07:42:21.540
Wondering how it felt to be hugged for

07:42:21.540 --> 07:42:24.599
the 1st time, in a 5000 year half life

07:42:24.599 --> 07:42:27.000
and whether lizards saw the world any

07:42:27.000 --> 07:42:29.400
differently, with all of pineapples and

07:42:29.400 --> 07:42:31.740
duskies and Luna's memories in her head.

07:42:31.799 --> 07:42:35.099
Luna crossed the room and crouched beside

07:42:35.099 --> 07:42:35.819
pineapple.

07:42:35.939 --> 07:42:38.520
I think we need more memories.

07:42:38.580 --> 07:42:41.040
She said to him in a low voice.

07:42:41.099 --> 07:42:43.560
He blinked out her sleepily.

07:42:43.619 --> 07:42:45.599
For lizard.

07:42:45.659 --> 07:42:47.819
Didn't we give her all of ours?

07:42:47.880 --> 07:42:51.299
Yes, but I think it wasn't enough.

07:42:51.360 --> 07:42:54.060
She can convince herself that we're

07:42:54.060 --> 07:42:56.040
different from other dragons, because of

07:42:56.040 --> 07:42:58.979
our tribes, but that most dragons are the

07:42:58.979 --> 07:42:59.819
way she thinks they are.

07:42:59.880 --> 07:43:02.880
We need to show her memories from more

07:43:02.880 --> 07:43:03.779
different tribes.

07:43:03.840 --> 07:43:07.080
Luna dug her talons into the dirt.

07:43:07.139 --> 07:43:10.200
I don't know how to get them, though.

07:43:10.319 --> 07:43:13.500
I mean, I'm not volunteering anyone to

07:43:13.500 --> 07:43:14.580
get absorbed by the plant.

07:43:14.639 --> 07:43:18.240
They already have lots of hive wings

07:43:18.240 --> 07:43:18.599
don't they?

07:43:18.659 --> 07:43:19.439
he asked.

07:43:19.500 --> 07:43:21.959
Maybe one of them would let her have his

07:43:21.959 --> 07:43:22.319
memories.

07:43:22.380 --> 07:43:25.799
But what if their memories are as bad as

07:43:25.799 --> 07:43:27.060
she expects the dragons to be?

07:43:27.180 --> 07:43:28.500
Luna worried.

07:43:28.619 --> 07:43:30.840
That would reverse everything I'm trying

07:43:30.840 --> 07:43:31.259
to do.

07:43:31.319 --> 07:43:34.740
She thought for a moment, then said

07:43:34.740 --> 07:43:38.700
slowly, What if could Moon help?

07:43:38.759 --> 07:43:41.400
I don't know how mind reading works, but

07:43:41.400 --> 07:43:42.540
maybe?

07:43:42.599 --> 07:43:46.319
She's been checking in with me, he said.

07:43:46.380 --> 07:43:48.599
I'll ask when she comes back.

07:43:48.659 --> 07:43:51.000
Thanks, pineapple.

07:43:51.060 --> 07:43:54.240
He smiled, and brushed one of her wings

07:43:54.240 --> 07:43:54.720
with his.

07:43:54.779 --> 07:43:59.040
Luna closed her eyes, reached through her

07:43:59.040 --> 07:44:01.619
scales until she sensed her real body, and

07:44:01.619 --> 07:44:04.380
hugged Desky closer, hoping he could feel

07:44:04.380 --> 07:44:04.860
it somehow.

07:44:04.979 --> 07:44:06.959
In her real body.

07:44:07.020 --> 07:44:09.419
She felt the slippery twists and tangles

07:44:09.419 --> 07:44:10.500
of vines underneath her.

07:44:10.560 --> 07:44:13.080
What else can I do?

07:44:13.139 --> 07:44:16.740
Her wrists felt warm, and she was sure

07:44:16.740 --> 07:44:18.360
they were glowing brightly in the dim

07:44:18.360 --> 07:44:19.500
gray green tomb.

07:44:19.560 --> 07:44:22.560
Why would the prophecy send me down

07:44:22.560 --> 07:44:22.979
here?

07:44:23.040 --> 07:44:26.099
Why would the universe give me flame silk

07:44:26.099 --> 07:44:29.040
and put me in front of a monster, if I'm

07:44:29.040 --> 07:44:29.759
not supposed to use it?

07:44:29.819 --> 07:44:33.180
Maybe because I'm not the one who's

07:44:33.180 --> 07:44:34.740
supposed to change the world after all.

07:44:34.799 --> 07:44:36.540
Maybe.

07:44:36.599 --> 07:44:39.240
I'm supposed to sit here. and wait to be

07:44:39.240 --> 07:44:40.680
rescued, again.

07:44:40.740 --> 07:44:44.459
She sank her real claws into the vines

07:44:44.459 --> 07:44:47.279
and felt sap ooze around the holes she

07:44:47.279 --> 07:44:47.520
left.

07:44:47.639 --> 07:44:52.139
If I set these vines on fire, would the

07:44:52.139 --> 07:44:54.479
smoke really rise all the way to Bryony's

07:44:54.479 --> 07:44:55.200
group of dragons?

07:44:55.319 --> 07:44:58.139
Would everyone in the caves be infected

07:44:58.139 --> 07:44:58.740
and absorbed?

07:44:58.799 --> 07:45:02.159
But if the fire destroyed all of the

07:45:02.159 --> 07:45:04.619
plant down here, there'd be nothing left

07:45:04.619 --> 07:45:06.479
to control anyone, would there?

07:45:06.540 --> 07:45:09.840
She wasn't sure, it was safe to take that

07:45:09.840 --> 07:45:10.080
chance.

07:45:10.139 --> 07:45:13.680
What if the other mind could live on and

07:45:13.680 --> 07:45:16.500
use its power, as long as any plant roots

07:45:16.500 --> 07:45:17.340
survived anywhere?

07:45:17.400 --> 07:45:19.680
Lizard.

07:45:19.740 --> 07:45:20.939
Pineapple said.

07:45:21.000 --> 07:45:23.880
We can get you more memories, if you want

07:45:23.880 --> 07:45:24.180
them.

07:45:24.240 --> 07:45:27.779
Luna opened her eyes, and saw him crouch

07:45:27.779 --> 07:45:30.119
beside Lizard, who had wiggled out of

07:45:30.119 --> 07:45:32.279
Desky's hug, but was still sitting near

07:45:32.279 --> 07:45:34.259
him, tails lightly touching.

07:45:34.319 --> 07:45:36.180
Moon was there too.

07:45:36.299 --> 07:45:39.299
Hovering at pineapple side, with her gaze

07:45:39.299 --> 07:45:41.040
fixed nervously on cotton mouth.

07:45:41.099 --> 07:45:42.779
You can?

07:45:42.900 --> 07:45:44.400
Lizard sat up.

07:45:44.459 --> 07:45:45.299
How?

07:45:45.360 --> 07:45:46.799
Did you infect the others?

07:45:46.860 --> 07:45:51.479
No, Pineapple said, giving her a serious

07:45:51.479 --> 07:45:51.779
look.

07:45:51.840 --> 07:45:54.180
That's not going to happen.

07:45:54.299 --> 07:45:57.240
But we think moon can be a conduit.

07:45:57.299 --> 07:45:59.700
It wouldn't give you all of someone's

07:45:59.700 --> 07:46:01.979
memories, but she can connect to the

07:46:01.979 --> 07:46:04.200
others flying with her, and they could

07:46:04.200 --> 07:46:05.819
each choose a memory to share with you.

07:46:05.880 --> 07:46:08.880
He glanced at the silent human on the

07:46:08.880 --> 07:46:09.180
throne.

07:46:09.299 --> 07:46:11.880
Just you, possibly.

07:46:12.000 --> 07:46:14.639
Not totally sure how this will work.

07:46:14.700 --> 07:46:19.680
Yes, yes, Lizard said immediately, holding

07:46:19.680 --> 07:46:20.340
out her talons.

07:46:20.400 --> 07:46:22.500
Give, give.

07:46:22.799 --> 07:46:23.939
Wait.

07:46:24.060 --> 07:46:27.240
She pulled back and eyed him with

07:46:27.240 --> 07:46:27.720
suspicion.

07:46:27.779 --> 07:46:29.759
What do you want for them?

07:46:29.819 --> 07:46:31.500
I can't let Luna go.

07:46:31.560 --> 07:46:33.720
He shrugged.

07:46:33.779 --> 07:46:35.520
No trade.

07:46:35.580 --> 07:46:38.700
We're flying right now, so it should be

07:46:38.700 --> 07:46:39.180
easy to do.

07:46:39.240 --> 07:46:41.700
And Luna said they might make you happy

07:46:41.700 --> 07:46:43.560
so... why not?

07:46:43.619 --> 07:46:47.159
That sentence seemed to puzzle lizard

07:46:47.159 --> 07:46:47.700
into silence.

07:46:47.759 --> 07:46:51.180
She looked down at the dirt, where she

07:46:51.180 --> 07:46:52.919
had drawn an awkward looking butterfly.

07:46:52.979 --> 07:46:55.860
Beside it, Dusky had drawn another.

07:46:55.919 --> 07:46:57.840
With their wings touching.

07:46:57.900 --> 07:47:00.840
Fine, Lizard said.

07:47:00.900 --> 07:47:02.459
Whatever, sure.

07:47:02.520 --> 07:47:03.360
I'll take it.

07:47:03.419 --> 07:47:05.639
She held out her talons.

07:47:05.700 --> 07:47:08.819
Pineapple took one, and Dusky took the

07:47:08.819 --> 07:47:09.000
other.

07:47:09.060 --> 07:47:12.360
Moon slid pineapple's other talon between

07:47:12.360 --> 07:47:15.419
hers, and Luna took Dusky's free talon

07:47:15.419 --> 07:47:16.319
forming a chain.

07:47:16.380 --> 07:47:20.580
Wait, Lizard said, as Moon closed her

07:47:20.580 --> 07:47:20.880
eyes.

07:47:20.939 --> 07:47:23.700
I only want something fierce, no

07:47:23.700 --> 07:47:24.119
hugging.

07:47:24.180 --> 07:47:26.580
Suddenly they were back in the

07:47:26.580 --> 07:47:27.419
rainforest.

07:47:27.479 --> 07:47:30.180
But now it was nighttime, with the 3

07:47:30.180 --> 07:47:31.740
moons spread out across the sky.

07:47:31.799 --> 07:47:35.279
This was blurrier than the other memories

07:47:35.279 --> 07:47:38.340
like paint on glass, or like a sketch

07:47:38.340 --> 07:47:39.419
left out in the rain.

07:47:39.479 --> 07:47:42.360
The frogs and insects and trees.

07:47:42.479 --> 07:47:44.400
All seem to be holding competing

07:47:44.400 --> 07:47:46.680
orchestras, filling the forest with

07:47:46.680 --> 07:47:46.919
noise.

07:47:46.979 --> 07:47:50.819
A tiny black dragon, no bigger than

07:47:50.819 --> 07:47:52.740
lizard, was sitting in a pool of

07:47:52.740 --> 07:47:54.900
moonlight, gazing up at the stars.

07:47:54.959 --> 07:47:57.240
Imperial.

07:47:57.299 --> 07:47:59.819
She whispered, pointing to the biggest

07:47:59.819 --> 07:48:00.240
moon.

07:48:00.299 --> 07:48:03.360
Her claw traced across the sky to the

07:48:03.360 --> 07:48:03.720
next one.

07:48:03.779 --> 07:48:07.020
Oracle and perception.

07:48:07.080 --> 07:48:10.500
She brought her talons down and wrapped

07:48:10.500 --> 07:48:11.340
her wings around herself.

07:48:11.400 --> 07:48:13.799
I remembered.

07:48:13.919 --> 07:48:16.919
She looked up at Oracle and whispered

07:48:16.919 --> 07:48:19.020
Mother will be here soon.

07:48:19.080 --> 07:48:23.159
A moment passed, and then she looked away

07:48:23.159 --> 07:48:23.639
from the moon.

07:48:23.759 --> 07:48:27.900
Well, she said she'd try.

07:48:27.959 --> 07:48:30.720
The small black wings fluttered.

07:48:30.779 --> 07:48:34.139
If she doesn't come tonight, she'll come

07:48:34.139 --> 07:48:34.560
tomorrow.

07:48:34.619 --> 07:48:36.540
Or the next day.

07:48:36.599 --> 07:48:38.400
Another pause.

07:48:38.459 --> 07:48:41.040
She'll always come back.

07:48:41.099 --> 07:48:43.799
Luna didn't know.

07:48:43.860 --> 07:48:45.959
If she was somehow feeling Moon's

07:48:45.959 --> 07:48:46.680
emotions too.

07:48:46.799 --> 07:48:48.900
But the loneliness was almost

07:48:48.900 --> 07:48:49.680
overwhelming.

07:48:49.740 --> 07:48:54.180
This dragon was so small to be alone in

07:48:54.180 --> 07:48:55.799
this wild, noisy place.

07:48:55.860 --> 07:49:00.060
Another moment, and then little moon said

07:49:00.060 --> 07:49:01.259
even more quietly.

07:49:01.380 --> 07:49:03.959
I'll be all right.

07:49:04.020 --> 07:49:08.159
A cold wind whisked around Luna's talons

07:49:08.159 --> 07:49:11.099
and the warm rainforest folded aside

07:49:11.099 --> 07:49:13.380
replaced by rolling hills of endless

07:49:13.380 --> 07:49:13.619
snow.

07:49:13.680 --> 07:49:17.279
Someone had built a small snow fort.

07:49:17.400 --> 07:49:20.099
Probably one of the 5 white and blue

07:49:20.099 --> 07:49:22.619
dragonettes running around it. and

07:49:22.619 --> 07:49:24.720
fortified it with frost breath to make it

07:49:24.720 --> 07:49:26.459
shine in the winter sunlight.

07:49:26.520 --> 07:49:30.479
This is our fort, shouted one of the

07:49:30.479 --> 07:49:32.580
dragonettes, scaling the wall and sitting

07:49:32.580 --> 07:49:34.380
on top of it, glaring down.

07:49:34.439 --> 07:49:37.680
She wore a lopsided tiara talon made out

07:49:37.680 --> 07:49:38.459
of icicles.

07:49:38.520 --> 07:49:39.720
Go make your own.

07:49:39.779 --> 07:49:44.040
No, I think we'll take this one, said the

07:49:44.040 --> 07:49:44.939
biggest dragonette.

07:49:45.060 --> 07:49:47.880
He nudged the dragon next to him, and she

07:49:47.880 --> 07:49:49.799
pounced on the smallest dragonette.

07:49:49.860 --> 07:49:50.819
Ha, ha.

07:49:50.939 --> 07:49:52.080
And now we have a hostage.

07:49:52.139 --> 07:49:55.020
The captured dragonette squeaked and

07:49:55.020 --> 07:49:55.500
wriggled.

07:49:55.560 --> 07:49:57.900
Luna recognized the pattern of blue

07:49:57.900 --> 07:49:59.580
scales freckled across her snout.

07:49:59.700 --> 07:50:01.439
This one was lynx.

07:50:01.500 --> 07:50:05.220
Surrender the fort, snowfall, or we'll

07:50:05.220 --> 07:50:05.939
toss her in the ocean.

07:50:06.060 --> 07:50:09.180
And maybe the walruses will eat her

07:50:09.180 --> 07:50:11.819
cackled the one who had lynx pinned

07:50:11.819 --> 07:50:12.119
down.

07:50:12.180 --> 07:50:15.599
Do your worst, Snowfall shouted.

07:50:15.659 --> 07:50:17.639
You took the wrong hostage.

07:50:17.700 --> 07:50:20.220
Lynx can swim better than either of you

07:50:20.220 --> 07:50:22.139
and she's not afraid of walruses.

07:50:22.200 --> 07:50:23.220
Write links.

07:50:23.340 --> 07:50:27.060
Lynx managed to rest her snout free long

07:50:27.060 --> 07:50:27.900
enough to yell.

07:50:27.959 --> 07:50:30.180
Walruses are adorable, boss.

07:50:30.240 --> 07:50:32.759
Before her captor stuffed her head back

07:50:32.759 --> 07:50:33.299
into the snow.

07:50:33.360 --> 07:50:36.779
The 5th dragonette suddenly surged over

07:50:36.779 --> 07:50:39.000
the wall of the fort, pelting the 2

07:50:39.000 --> 07:50:40.680
hostage takers with snowballs.

07:50:40.740 --> 07:50:44.159
Let her go, he shouted, we never leave a

07:50:44.159 --> 07:50:44.759
dragon behind.

07:50:44.819 --> 07:50:50.099
Winter, Snowfall said, with an aggravated

07:50:50.099 --> 07:50:52.740
sigh as the biggest dragonette easily

07:50:52.740 --> 07:50:53.340
knocked him over.

07:50:53.400 --> 07:50:55.860
Lingx doesn't need rescuing.

07:50:55.979 --> 07:50:58.680
This is why I don't play with you, because

07:50:58.680 --> 07:50:59.340
you play all wrong.

07:50:59.459 --> 07:51:02.520
I'm going to switch to Hellstorm side, if

07:51:02.520 --> 07:51:04.080
you keep doing stupid heroic things.

07:51:04.139 --> 07:51:05.700
Look, see?

07:51:05.759 --> 07:51:07.500
Now I'll have to rescue you.

07:51:07.560 --> 07:51:11.400
A gust of wind blew snow in Luna's face

07:51:11.400 --> 07:51:14.340
and as it melted away, so did the fort

07:51:14.340 --> 07:51:16.500
and the ice wings, and the frozen

07:51:16.500 --> 07:51:18.959
landscape, leaving them in the streets of

07:51:18.959 --> 07:51:21.659
a busy dragon town, baking in heat.

07:51:21.720 --> 07:51:24.540
When I try to remember being lizards

07:51:24.540 --> 07:51:24.959
age.

07:51:25.020 --> 07:51:27.299
Well, lizards size.

07:51:27.360 --> 07:51:29.880
My memories are short and blurry too.

07:51:30.000 --> 07:51:33.180
Luna thought, turning to try to guess

07:51:33.180 --> 07:51:34.979
where they were, and whose memory this

07:51:34.979 --> 07:51:35.220
was.

07:51:35.340 --> 07:51:38.819
Then a crowd of sand wings ran by

07:51:38.819 --> 07:51:40.979
shouting, Fight, fight, fight!

07:51:41.099 --> 07:51:43.919
And she realized, this must be Kibley's.

07:51:43.979 --> 07:51:46.860
Maybe this will be fierce enough for

07:51:46.860 --> 07:51:49.080
Lizard, she thought. hurrying after

07:51:49.080 --> 07:51:49.259
them.

07:51:49.380 --> 07:51:52.919
You took it from him, a voice yelled.

07:51:52.979 --> 07:51:54.360
So what?

07:51:54.419 --> 07:51:56.400
Another voice shouted back.

07:51:56.459 --> 07:51:58.560
I'm big and he's small.

07:51:58.619 --> 07:52:00.060
That's how it works.

07:52:00.180 --> 07:52:03.119
The dragons were gathering outside a

07:52:03.119 --> 07:52:06.180
cluster of market stalls, a tea shop, one

07:52:06.180 --> 07:52:08.580
selling candles, another hung with dried

07:52:08.580 --> 07:52:09.479
herbs and flowers.

07:52:09.599 --> 07:52:12.240
A fourth, glittering with bejeweled metal

07:52:12.240 --> 07:52:12.840
figurines.

07:52:12.900 --> 07:52:16.020
Two sand wings were facing off, hissing

07:52:16.020 --> 07:52:16.319
at each other.

07:52:16.439 --> 07:52:18.540
But neither looked like Kibley.

07:52:18.599 --> 07:52:21.540
The one she'd heard 1st was a tawny

07:52:21.540 --> 07:52:23.880
female sandwing, and the dragon facing

07:52:23.880 --> 07:52:27.180
her was twice her size, grinning smugly

07:52:27.180 --> 07:52:28.979
with a mouthful of broken teeth.

07:52:29.040 --> 07:52:33.659
But I made it, shouted a tiny dragonette

07:52:33.659 --> 07:52:35.400
charging between the feet of the female

07:52:35.400 --> 07:52:36.060
dragon.

07:52:36.119 --> 07:52:37.439
Aha.

07:52:37.500 --> 07:52:38.880
There was Kibley.

07:52:38.939 --> 07:52:41.700
I had to figure out how and get all this

07:52:41.700 --> 07:52:43.740
stuff, and it was really hard and you

07:52:43.740 --> 07:52:44.220
give it back.

07:52:44.279 --> 07:52:46.979
You don't care about this little

07:52:46.979 --> 07:52:49.500
pipsqueak, said the big dragon.

07:52:49.560 --> 07:52:52.439
Let me buy you a lemonade, and we'll

07:52:52.439 --> 07:52:53.340
forget all of this.

07:52:53.400 --> 07:52:58.319
Give him back his drum toy. hissed

07:52:58.319 --> 07:53:00.840
Kibley's defender, or fight me.

07:53:00.900 --> 07:53:04.259
Kibley looked up at her, his eyes around

07:53:04.259 --> 07:53:04.979
with awe.

07:53:05.040 --> 07:53:07.919
You would fight for me?

07:53:07.979 --> 07:53:09.540
He breathed.

07:53:09.599 --> 07:53:12.900
Instead of taking lemonade?

07:53:13.020 --> 07:53:16.380
It's not just for you, kid, she said.

07:53:16.439 --> 07:53:18.060
I'm fighting for justice.

07:53:18.119 --> 07:53:20.819
Yes.

07:53:20.880 --> 07:53:22.799
Kibble whispered to himself.

07:53:22.860 --> 07:53:25.500
I'm gonna do that too when I'm big.

07:53:25.619 --> 07:53:27.419
He puffed up his chest.

07:53:27.479 --> 07:53:30.180
No, I'm gonna do that right now.

07:53:30.299 --> 07:53:33.779
With a great hollering yell, he threw

07:53:33.779 --> 07:53:35.819
himself with a big dragon and sank his

07:53:35.819 --> 07:53:37.259
teeth into the thief's ankle.

07:53:37.319 --> 07:53:40.680
The memory broke apart in chaos and

07:53:40.680 --> 07:53:42.840
shouting, and dragons throwing punches.

07:53:42.900 --> 07:53:45.599
Dropping them into sundew's mind.

07:53:45.659 --> 07:53:48.299
The scene was the poison jungle.

07:53:48.360 --> 07:53:51.119
It started with chasing a frog through

07:53:51.119 --> 07:53:53.520
dark leaves, and ended with meeting a

07:53:53.520 --> 07:53:55.139
green dragon named Willow.

07:53:55.259 --> 07:53:58.080
Lizard's not going to like that one.

07:53:58.139 --> 07:53:59.279
Luna thought.

07:53:59.340 --> 07:54:02.159
She probably thought sundew of all

07:54:02.159 --> 07:54:04.200
dragons. could give her a battle memory.

07:54:04.259 --> 07:54:08.220
But even fierce, scary sundew, keeps

07:54:08.220 --> 07:54:09.720
thinking about the dragon she loves.

07:54:09.840 --> 07:54:14.040
The last memory took them to a cave that

07:54:14.040 --> 07:54:15.060
flickered with torches.

07:54:15.119 --> 07:54:18.479
Five little dragonettes sat in a circle

07:54:18.479 --> 07:54:21.419
by an underground river, studying a faded

07:54:21.419 --> 07:54:21.900
map.

07:54:22.139 --> 07:54:24.000
One was muskly and brown.

07:54:24.060 --> 07:54:26.400
One was tiny and golden yellow.

07:54:26.520 --> 07:54:28.799
One was a fidgety nightwing.

07:54:28.860 --> 07:54:31.979
The other 2 Luna recognized as a much

07:54:31.979 --> 07:54:34.439
younger tsunami and glory, who were

07:54:34.439 --> 07:54:35.159
arguing with each other.

07:54:35.220 --> 07:54:38.700
Look, the kingdom of sand is clearly

07:54:38.700 --> 07:54:41.759
biggest, tsunami shouted. stabbing one

07:54:41.759 --> 07:54:42.479
claw at the map.

07:54:42.540 --> 07:54:45.299
You don't know where the borders are

07:54:45.299 --> 07:54:46.680
Glory argued back.

07:54:46.740 --> 07:54:49.200
Maybe the Sky Kingdom includes all of

07:54:49.200 --> 07:54:49.380
this.

07:54:49.500 --> 07:54:52.680
She yanked the map toward her and pointed

07:54:52.680 --> 07:54:54.180
at a swath of northern mountains.

07:54:54.240 --> 07:54:57.840
Oh, please be careful, said the night

07:54:57.840 --> 07:54:59.340
wing, tisking nervously.

07:54:59.400 --> 07:55:02.580
If we tear this map, Kestrel will be

07:55:02.580 --> 07:55:03.000
furious.

07:55:03.060 --> 07:55:04.979
She'll do something awful to both of

07:55:04.979 --> 07:55:05.159
you.

07:55:05.220 --> 07:55:06.000
I know it.

07:55:06.119 --> 07:55:09.540
No, it'll be worse, said the little

07:55:09.540 --> 07:55:10.080
yellow one.

07:55:10.139 --> 07:55:12.360
Because Clay will tell her it was his

07:55:12.360 --> 07:55:13.860
fault, and she'll punish him instead.

07:55:13.979 --> 07:55:17.759
They all turned toward the brown dragon

07:55:17.759 --> 07:55:19.860
who was blissfully chewing on something

07:55:19.860 --> 07:55:22.139
and looked very startled to suddenly have

07:55:22.139 --> 07:55:22.560
their attention.

07:55:22.680 --> 07:55:25.319
Moof, he said.

07:55:25.380 --> 07:55:26.459
Wha?

07:55:26.520 --> 07:55:29.099
Yeah, he would do that.

07:55:29.220 --> 07:55:30.599
Tsunami agreed.

07:55:30.659 --> 07:55:34.020
All right, I'll keep my claws off it.

07:55:34.080 --> 07:55:37.020
Glory said, lifting her talons in the

07:55:37.020 --> 07:55:37.259
air.

07:55:37.319 --> 07:55:40.139
But I still say the Sky Kingdom is bigger

07:55:40.139 --> 07:55:40.619
than we think.

07:55:40.680 --> 07:55:43.919
Everyone is fighting over the kingdom of

07:55:43.919 --> 07:55:45.779
sand, tsunami cried.

07:55:45.840 --> 07:55:47.040
It has to be the biggest.

07:55:47.159 --> 07:55:50.340
Clay poked tsunami in the nose.

07:55:50.400 --> 07:55:53.400
Doesn't matter which one is the biggest

07:55:53.400 --> 07:55:54.479
he said.

07:55:54.540 --> 07:55:55.860
Oh, really?

07:55:55.919 --> 07:55:58.259
Tsunami batted his claw away.

07:55:58.319 --> 07:56:00.720
Nope, he said.

07:56:00.779 --> 07:56:03.180
Only matters which one has the best

07:56:03.180 --> 07:56:03.659
food.

07:56:03.720 --> 07:56:06.840
That's where we're going to live all

07:56:06.840 --> 07:56:07.319
together.

07:56:07.380 --> 07:56:10.380
One day, when we're old and creaky.

07:56:10.500 --> 07:56:13.799
The little one dissolved in laughter, and

07:56:13.799 --> 07:56:17.099
Gloria said, I have no intention of ever

07:56:17.099 --> 07:56:19.020
being creaky.

07:56:19.080 --> 07:56:22.259
Tsunami slung one wing around her and

07:56:22.259 --> 07:56:25.200
said, oh, you'll get there as long as

07:56:25.200 --> 07:56:26.639
Clay keeps stopping me from murdering

07:56:26.639 --> 07:56:26.819
you.

07:56:26.880 --> 07:56:29.459
And then they were back in the mind

07:56:29.459 --> 07:56:30.000
space.

07:56:30.060 --> 07:56:34.139
Moon exhaled, let go of pineapple, and

07:56:34.139 --> 07:56:35.520
rubbed her forehead with a wince.

07:56:35.639 --> 07:56:39.000
I'll be back, she whispered and

07:56:39.000 --> 07:56:39.599
disappeared.

07:56:39.659 --> 07:56:43.919
Luna looked from dusky to pineapple to

07:56:43.919 --> 07:56:44.400
lizard.

07:56:44.459 --> 07:56:46.979
They all looked a little wind blown from

07:56:46.979 --> 07:56:48.599
being whisked through all those memories

07:56:48.599 --> 07:56:49.740
one after the other.

07:56:49.799 --> 07:56:53.279
Well, Lizard said finally.

07:56:53.400 --> 07:56:55.740
I hated all of that.

07:56:55.799 --> 07:56:57.360
You did?

07:56:57.419 --> 07:56:58.560
Luna said.

07:56:58.619 --> 07:57:01.139
But that was so many different dragons.

07:57:01.200 --> 07:57:03.599
All those different kinds of lives.

07:57:03.659 --> 07:57:05.700
Isn't that what you wanted to see?

07:57:05.819 --> 07:57:08.939
Lizard growled to herself for a minute

07:57:08.939 --> 07:57:10.439
and then she burst out.

07:57:10.500 --> 07:57:12.659
I thought there would be someone like

07:57:12.659 --> 07:57:12.900
me.

07:57:12.959 --> 07:57:15.479
I wanted to know what I could have been

07:57:15.479 --> 07:57:17.819
like, but none of those dragons are

07:57:17.819 --> 07:57:18.779
anything like me.

07:57:18.840 --> 07:57:22.020
I think they are, Luna said.

07:57:22.080 --> 07:57:26.099
I mean, everyone is different, but we all

07:57:26.099 --> 07:57:27.000
still fit together.

07:57:27.060 --> 07:57:30.240
Like the threads of a tapestry.

07:57:30.299 --> 07:57:32.400
We can weave lizard in.

07:57:32.459 --> 07:57:34.680
She can still be part of something.

07:57:34.799 --> 07:57:37.680
Think about what you saw.

07:57:37.740 --> 07:57:41.220
Moon as a dragonette was so lonely, but

07:57:41.220 --> 07:57:42.419
she kept surviving anyway.

07:57:42.479 --> 07:57:44.639
That's just like you.

07:57:44.700 --> 07:57:48.240
Kibli stood up for himself, even when his

07:57:48.240 --> 07:57:49.799
enemy was much stronger than him.

07:57:49.860 --> 07:57:51.419
You do that too.

07:57:51.479 --> 07:57:54.060
Every time you yell at Cottonmouth

07:57:54.060 --> 07:57:57.180
Tsunami got mad so quickly as a

07:57:57.180 --> 07:57:59.459
dragonette, I think she still does that.

07:57:59.520 --> 07:58:01.139
And you do too.

07:58:01.200 --> 07:58:03.540
But you've had to learn to calm yourself

07:58:03.540 --> 07:58:05.819
down, with no one else here to help.

07:58:05.880 --> 07:58:08.759
Lizard rubbed her face.

07:58:08.819 --> 07:58:10.619
What about the other two?

07:58:10.740 --> 07:58:13.139
Luna thought for a moment.

07:58:13.259 --> 07:58:16.380
Sundew goes after what she wants, without

07:58:16.380 --> 07:58:17.459
letting anything stop her.

07:58:17.520 --> 07:58:20.159
I think you're determined like that.

07:58:20.279 --> 07:58:22.139
And you heard that ice wing.

07:58:22.259 --> 07:58:24.299
Lynx didn't need rescuing.

07:58:24.360 --> 07:58:26.279
She wasn't afraid of being fed to

07:58:26.279 --> 07:58:28.380
walruses, and neither are you.

07:58:28.500 --> 07:58:30.959
Lizard snorted.

07:58:31.080 --> 07:58:32.580
That's true.

07:58:32.700 --> 07:58:36.119
I have no idea what a walrus is, but I

07:58:36.119 --> 07:58:37.319
know I could take one in a fight.

07:58:37.380 --> 07:58:40.860
She paused and took a deep breath.

07:58:40.919 --> 07:58:44.400
If I'd had a chance to grow up and meet

07:58:44.400 --> 07:58:44.939
one anyway.

07:58:45.119 --> 07:58:48.119
I think I'm more like that other white

07:58:48.119 --> 07:58:49.319
dragon on the wall though.

07:58:49.380 --> 07:58:50.939
Snowfall?

07:58:51.000 --> 07:58:52.200
She was my favorite.

07:58:52.259 --> 07:58:54.419
Lizard?

07:58:54.779 --> 07:58:57.659
It's not fair what happened to you, Luna

07:58:57.659 --> 07:58:58.020
said.

07:58:58.080 --> 07:59:00.419
What's really not fair?

07:59:00.479 --> 07:59:03.119
Is the biggest difference between me and

07:59:03.119 --> 07:59:03.900
those dragons?

07:59:04.020 --> 07:59:06.299
Lizard said passionately.

07:59:06.360 --> 07:59:08.580
They all had someone who loved them.

07:59:08.639 --> 07:59:10.560
No one ever loved me.

07:59:10.680 --> 07:59:12.419
Not that I care.

07:59:12.479 --> 07:59:13.380
I don't care.

07:59:13.439 --> 07:59:14.459
I don't care.

07:59:14.520 --> 07:59:17.040
But that's the unfair part.

07:59:17.099 --> 07:59:18.419
Actually.

07:59:18.479 --> 07:59:20.279
You're right.

07:59:20.340 --> 07:59:22.439
Luna hesitated.

07:59:22.500 --> 07:59:26.759
I think maybe also, though, it's unfair

07:59:26.759 --> 07:59:28.860
that you never got to love someone.

07:59:29.040 --> 07:59:30.720
That's important too.

07:59:30.840 --> 07:59:33.299
And I'm sorry you never had that.

07:59:33.360 --> 07:59:37.200
Lizard sniffed, and wiped her face again

07:59:37.200 --> 07:59:38.520
with an impatient gesture.

07:59:38.580 --> 07:59:41.220
She glanced sideways at Dusky.

07:59:41.279 --> 07:59:44.520
Seems like loving someone makes you do

07:59:44.520 --> 07:59:46.560
really stupid things, she said.

07:59:46.619 --> 07:59:51.959
Yeah, true, Luna said, thinking of the

07:59:51.959 --> 07:59:54.000
many times Swordell had thrown himself

07:59:54.000 --> 07:59:57.540
into trouble to spare her, or Blue, of

07:59:57.540 --> 07:59:59.459
Blue breaking all the rules he cared

07:59:59.459 --> 08:00:02.340
about so much, to find Luna, when she was

08:00:02.340 --> 08:00:04.919
taken to the Flame Silk Cavern, and

08:00:04.919 --> 08:00:07.919
Cricket, leaving behind her entire tribe

08:00:07.919 --> 08:00:10.740
and risking her biggest secret, to help a

08:00:10.740 --> 08:00:11.939
silk wing she barely knew.

08:00:12.000 --> 08:00:14.819
Lizard looked at the throne.

08:00:14.939 --> 08:00:17.759
Had the tortured grimace on Cottonmouth's

08:00:17.759 --> 08:00:20.520
face as he puppeteered 100s of dragons at

08:00:20.520 --> 08:00:22.200
once, somewhere far away.

08:00:22.319 --> 08:00:26.159
She looked back at Luna, and the flame

08:00:26.159 --> 08:00:28.139
silk on Luna's horns reflected in the

08:00:28.139 --> 08:00:30.060
fathomless pools of lizard's eyes.

08:00:30.180 --> 08:00:32.880
All right, Lizard said.

08:00:32.939 --> 08:00:36.240
Listen, because I'm only going to say

08:00:36.240 --> 08:00:36.659
this once.

08:00:36.779 --> 08:00:39.659
She took a deep breath.

08:00:39.720 --> 08:00:43.020
If you cut the vine that's growing

08:00:43.020 --> 08:00:46.139
through our heads, she said, her voice

08:00:46.139 --> 08:00:46.979
low and shaking.

08:00:47.040 --> 08:00:50.159
The plant will be a normal plant again.

08:00:50.279 --> 08:00:52.020
And we'll be gone.

08:00:52.080 --> 08:00:56.700
Chapter 24.

08:00:56.939 --> 08:01:00.000
Luna stopped breathing.

08:01:00.060 --> 08:01:01.680
What?

08:01:01.740 --> 08:01:03.240
She finally whispered.

08:01:03.299 --> 08:01:06.840
You heard me, Lizard said.

08:01:06.900 --> 08:01:08.580
Don't make me say it again.

08:01:08.639 --> 08:01:10.439
Don't make me think about it.

08:01:10.500 --> 08:01:12.659
I don't want to talk about it.

08:01:12.720 --> 08:01:14.159
And you better not say thank you.

08:01:14.220 --> 08:01:16.500
And whatever you're going to do, I don't

08:01:16.500 --> 08:01:16.919
want to know.

08:01:16.979 --> 08:01:18.119
I shouldn't know.

08:01:18.180 --> 08:01:19.200
Distract me.

08:01:19.259 --> 08:01:21.060
Dusky, be interesting.

08:01:21.119 --> 08:01:22.860
Um.

08:01:23.099 --> 08:01:25.799
Dusky sat up. looking very alarmed.

08:01:25.860 --> 08:01:27.479
Like, how?

08:01:27.540 --> 08:01:29.639
Sing, dance.

08:01:29.759 --> 08:01:30.900
Grow an extra head.

08:01:30.959 --> 08:01:31.500
I don't know.

08:01:31.619 --> 08:01:34.619
Lizard shoved him again, and this time

08:01:34.619 --> 08:01:36.060
Desky pounced on her.

08:01:36.119 --> 08:01:38.459
Lizard yelped, and they rolled across the

08:01:38.459 --> 08:01:40.080
dirt, play wrestling.

08:01:40.139 --> 08:01:42.060
Quiet over there.

08:01:42.119 --> 08:01:45.240
Cottonmouth shouted, and then went back

08:01:45.240 --> 08:01:49.080
into his trance, muttering, Cut the

08:01:49.080 --> 08:01:49.500
vine.

08:01:49.560 --> 08:01:52.680
Luna pictured the throne room she'd flown

08:01:52.680 --> 08:01:52.979
into.

08:01:53.040 --> 08:01:55.500
The vine growing from the floor through

08:01:55.500 --> 08:01:57.299
lizard's head and then cotton mouths.

08:01:57.360 --> 08:01:59.400
Can I really do it?

08:01:59.459 --> 08:02:00.720
Me?

08:02:00.779 --> 08:02:01.799
Of all dragons?

08:02:01.860 --> 08:02:04.439
I should probably wait for sundew.

08:02:04.560 --> 08:02:06.779
She could do it easily, I bet.

08:02:06.840 --> 08:02:08.279
But.

08:02:08.700 --> 08:02:10.680
I should try, at least.

08:02:10.740 --> 08:02:12.599
I'm the one who knows about this.

08:02:12.659 --> 08:02:16.259
I'm the one who's here, in this throne

08:02:16.259 --> 08:02:17.340
room, right now.

08:02:17.400 --> 08:02:20.279
Even if I only get so far.

08:02:20.340 --> 08:02:23.939
Even if I only help a little bit, that

08:02:23.939 --> 08:02:25.439
would still be a little bit closer to

08:02:25.439 --> 08:02:27.599
defeating the other mind and freeing the

08:02:27.599 --> 08:02:27.840
others.

08:02:27.900 --> 08:02:31.380
I have to be like the dragons whose

08:02:31.380 --> 08:02:32.340
memories I just saw.

08:02:32.459 --> 08:02:34.740
Dragons who don't give up.

08:02:34.799 --> 08:02:37.680
Dragon to jump in to save the ones they

08:02:37.680 --> 08:02:37.919
love.

08:02:37.979 --> 08:02:41.580
Dragons who fight, even when the enemy

08:02:41.580 --> 08:02:42.659
seems much too big.

08:02:42.720 --> 08:02:45.959
Dragons who don't need rescuing.

08:02:46.020 --> 08:02:49.560
I don't want to be the dragon who always

08:02:49.560 --> 08:02:50.459
needs to be rescued.

08:02:50.520 --> 08:02:52.680
All right.

08:02:52.799 --> 08:02:54.599
So how do I do this?

08:02:54.720 --> 08:02:57.419
Can I get over there without him

08:02:57.419 --> 08:02:57.900
noticing?

08:02:57.959 --> 08:02:59.580
And then what?

08:02:59.639 --> 08:03:02.279
Saw through the vines with my claws?

08:03:02.400 --> 08:03:05.400
He can take over my body and stop me

08:03:05.400 --> 08:03:05.819
anytime.

08:03:05.939 --> 08:03:10.680
My only chance is to get there stealthily

08:03:10.680 --> 08:03:12.060
and then do it quickly.

08:03:12.119 --> 08:03:14.639
Ideally when he's distracted.

08:03:14.700 --> 08:03:18.959
She closed her eyes and reached her way

08:03:18.959 --> 08:03:20.099
back into her real body.

08:03:20.159 --> 08:03:24.000
It was heavy and cold, clammy from the

08:03:24.000 --> 08:03:25.439
damp vines under her talons.

08:03:25.500 --> 08:03:27.840
Her claws were still curled around

08:03:27.840 --> 08:03:29.819
Dusky's small, listless form.

08:03:29.880 --> 08:03:32.279
What do I do with him?

08:03:32.340 --> 08:03:35.340
If I leave him here on the vines.

08:03:35.400 --> 08:03:37.380
Cottonmouth could use him against me.

08:03:37.439 --> 08:03:41.400
The moment he realizes what I'm doing, he

08:03:41.400 --> 08:03:43.080
could hurt Dusky and make me stop.

08:03:43.139 --> 08:03:46.439
But I guess that's true no matter where

08:03:46.439 --> 08:03:47.220
Dusky is.

08:03:47.279 --> 08:03:49.380
And I'd rather have him with me.

08:03:49.500 --> 08:03:53.580
Blindly, she pushed and tugged the small

08:03:53.580 --> 08:03:56.040
dragonette over her shoulder until he was

08:03:56.040 --> 08:03:57.119
draped between her wings.

08:03:57.180 --> 08:04:00.720
She felt his tiny talons twitch against

08:04:00.720 --> 08:04:01.200
her neck.

08:04:01.259 --> 08:04:04.560
She forced her limbs to take a cautious

08:04:04.560 --> 08:04:07.500
step forward. and felt the vines flex and

08:04:07.500 --> 08:04:09.419
bow and ripple under her feet.

08:04:09.659 --> 08:04:12.240
It was worse than walking on the sand on

08:04:12.240 --> 08:04:13.259
Jerboa's beach.

08:04:13.319 --> 08:04:16.259
There were a lot of vines, and they were

08:04:16.259 --> 08:04:16.740
very thick.

08:04:16.799 --> 08:04:19.259
But her talons kept slipping through the

08:04:19.259 --> 08:04:20.939
gaps and tripping her up.

08:04:20.939 --> 08:04:22.919
It didn't help that she couldn't see

08:04:22.919 --> 08:04:25.319
where she was stepping, or be sure which

08:04:25.319 --> 08:04:25.979
way she was going.

08:04:26.040 --> 08:04:29.220
I hope I'm pointed at the throne.

08:04:29.340 --> 08:04:32.220
She slid forward another inch.

08:04:32.279 --> 08:04:33.599
And then another.

08:04:33.659 --> 08:04:35.159
Hurry.

08:04:35.220 --> 08:04:38.159
Her muscles screamed, but her mind

08:04:38.159 --> 08:04:39.000
screamed back.

08:04:39.060 --> 08:04:40.380
Careful.

08:04:40.439 --> 08:04:42.540
And what if he sees you?

08:04:42.599 --> 08:04:45.000
And too fast.

08:04:45.119 --> 08:04:48.240
And it was a whole stressful mess of

08:04:48.240 --> 08:04:50.099
conflicting instructions riding around

08:04:50.099 --> 08:04:50.700
inside of her.

08:04:50.819 --> 08:04:54.060
She wasn't sure how much time had passed

08:04:54.060 --> 08:04:56.400
or whether she felt time the same way

08:04:56.400 --> 08:04:57.840
inside the mind space.

08:04:57.900 --> 08:05:00.479
Her internal clock felt like it was all

08:05:00.479 --> 08:05:01.020
out of order.

08:05:01.080 --> 08:05:03.659
When she heard cotton mouth let out a

08:05:03.659 --> 08:05:04.020
hiss.

08:05:04.080 --> 08:05:07.439
Instantly, she froze her real body in

08:05:07.439 --> 08:05:07.680
place.

08:05:07.740 --> 08:05:11.939
Nothing to see here, nothing to see, she

08:05:11.939 --> 08:05:12.599
thought frantically.

08:05:12.659 --> 08:05:15.840
She opened her eyes in the mind space.

08:05:15.900 --> 08:05:18.599
Dusky and Lizard were still romping

08:05:18.599 --> 08:05:20.700
around the room, tackling and pinning

08:05:20.700 --> 08:05:22.619
each other, and wriggling free and

08:05:22.619 --> 08:05:22.979
running off.

08:05:23.040 --> 08:05:25.740
They looked so much like ordinary

08:05:25.740 --> 08:05:28.740
dragonettes playing for a moment, that

08:05:28.740 --> 08:05:29.759
Luna's heart hurt.

08:05:29.819 --> 08:05:32.520
I wish there was a way to save her.

08:05:32.580 --> 08:05:35.400
To keep lizard alive and give her a real

08:05:35.400 --> 08:05:35.700
life.

08:05:35.759 --> 08:05:39.599
We are approaching Lake Scorpion

08:05:39.599 --> 08:05:41.819
Cottonmouth said imperiously.

08:05:41.880 --> 08:05:45.659
Lizard, stop being infantile and focus.

08:05:45.720 --> 08:05:48.840
He stood up and glared around the mind

08:05:48.840 --> 08:05:51.479
space as Lizard stumbled to a stop.

08:05:51.540 --> 08:05:55.259
Make sure the mind walker does not get in

08:05:55.259 --> 08:05:55.500
here.

08:05:55.560 --> 08:05:58.680
Do not let her speak to these 2 again.

08:05:58.799 --> 08:06:01.979
He nodded at Luna and Pineapple.

08:06:02.040 --> 08:06:04.860
Why do I have to do anything?

08:06:04.919 --> 08:06:06.540
Lizard asked mutinously.

08:06:06.599 --> 08:06:09.840
I thought you were so brilliant, and I

08:06:09.840 --> 08:06:12.360
was so useless, that I might as well not

08:06:12.360 --> 08:06:12.840
even be here.

08:06:12.900 --> 08:06:15.479
But you are here.

08:06:15.540 --> 08:06:18.720
So do as you're told, he said.

08:06:18.779 --> 08:06:20.459
I'm busy enough.

08:06:20.520 --> 08:06:22.979
There are dragons causing trouble at

08:06:22.979 --> 08:06:24.000
Cicada Hive.

08:06:24.060 --> 08:06:27.720
Queen Wasp won't stop moaning and wailing

08:06:27.720 --> 08:06:30.360
about the pain in her face, so she's no

08:06:30.360 --> 08:06:30.900
help at all.

08:06:31.020 --> 08:06:34.740
And this rainbow dragon I'm in is about

08:06:34.740 --> 08:06:37.020
to run into my rogue hive wing and her

08:06:37.020 --> 08:06:38.400
merry band of human pets.

08:06:38.459 --> 08:06:40.619
He thought for a moment.

08:06:40.680 --> 08:06:42.000
I know.

08:06:42.060 --> 08:06:45.720
Jump into a hive wing and cicada hive and

08:06:45.720 --> 08:06:47.580
kill a couple of silk wings to make them

08:06:47.580 --> 08:06:48.180
all shut up.

08:06:48.240 --> 08:06:51.779
He didn't notice the expression on Luna's

08:06:51.779 --> 08:06:53.159
face, but Lizard did.

08:06:53.220 --> 08:06:55.979
Boring, she said.

08:06:56.040 --> 08:06:57.180
Don't feel like it.

08:06:57.240 --> 08:07:00.479
Ooh, I could make the guardian climb up

08:07:00.479 --> 08:07:02.040
and steal another dragonette, though.

08:07:02.099 --> 08:07:04.439
He gave her a withering look.

08:07:04.560 --> 08:07:07.439
How would that help me at all?

08:07:07.500 --> 08:07:10.200
No, I forbid it.

08:07:10.259 --> 08:07:12.060
You've already cluttered up the place

08:07:12.060 --> 08:07:13.020
with these toys.

08:07:13.080 --> 08:07:14.700
That is quite enough for now.

08:07:14.759 --> 08:07:19.380
Bleh, Lizard said, flopping down on the

08:07:19.380 --> 08:07:21.000
floor and resting her chin on her

08:07:21.000 --> 08:07:21.659
talons.

08:07:21.720 --> 08:07:25.680
Well, you can sulk, or you can come fight

08:07:25.680 --> 08:07:26.520
some dragons.

08:07:26.580 --> 08:07:27.959
I don't care which.

08:07:28.080 --> 08:07:30.779
Cottonmouth said, closing his eyes

08:07:30.779 --> 08:07:31.139
again.

08:07:31.200 --> 08:07:34.319
Just tell me if the mind walker comes

08:07:34.319 --> 08:07:34.619
back.

08:07:34.680 --> 08:07:37.740
I assume you can be trusted with a task

08:07:37.740 --> 08:07:38.880
that simple.

08:07:38.939 --> 08:07:42.419
Lizard stuck her tongue out at his blank

08:07:42.419 --> 08:07:42.720
face.

08:07:42.779 --> 08:07:46.200
Should we check on Cicada Hive?

08:07:46.259 --> 08:07:47.939
Luna asked nervously.

08:07:48.000 --> 08:07:49.799
What does he mean?

08:07:49.860 --> 08:07:51.479
Dragons are causing trouble.

08:07:51.540 --> 08:07:53.400
Are sore tail and blue all right?

08:07:53.459 --> 08:07:57.720
Probably, Lizard said, exhaling.

08:07:57.779 --> 08:08:01.439
She toppled dusky over. sat on him, and

08:08:01.439 --> 08:08:03.779
waved one talon in the air like a

08:08:03.779 --> 08:08:05.400
conjurer whisking away a curtain.

08:08:05.459 --> 08:08:09.060
The mind space floated aside, and the

08:08:09.060 --> 08:08:10.919
cicada hive market settled in around

08:08:10.919 --> 08:08:11.459
them.

08:08:11.580 --> 08:08:13.439
It was much noisier than before.

08:08:13.500 --> 08:08:16.500
Many of the silk wings were standing now

08:08:16.500 --> 08:08:18.779
shouting at the guards, asking for

08:08:18.779 --> 08:08:19.380
answers.

08:08:19.439 --> 08:08:22.500
The dragons guarding the exits were white

08:08:22.500 --> 08:08:25.020
eyed and perfectly still, blocking the

08:08:25.020 --> 08:08:27.119
way with their bodies, but not fighting

08:08:27.119 --> 08:08:28.080
back, or responding.

08:08:28.200 --> 08:08:31.439
Luna thought she saw a flicker of dark

08:08:31.439 --> 08:08:32.639
purple wings in the crowd.

08:08:32.700 --> 08:08:34.380
Aisle?

08:08:34.439 --> 08:08:37.020
But when she turned, she couldn't see her

08:08:37.020 --> 08:08:37.740
friend anywhere.

08:08:37.799 --> 08:08:40.740
She spotted Swordtail on the far side of

08:08:40.740 --> 08:08:42.959
the hive and spread her wings to fly over

08:08:42.959 --> 08:08:43.259
to him.

08:08:43.319 --> 08:08:47.880
Ooh, hang on, Lizard said, bumping her

08:08:47.880 --> 08:08:48.119
side.

08:08:48.180 --> 08:08:50.639
Exciting things happening over by Lake

08:08:50.639 --> 08:08:51.299
Scorpion.

08:08:51.360 --> 08:08:51.779
Come on.

08:08:51.900 --> 08:08:54.419
Luna had no choice.

08:08:54.540 --> 08:08:57.000
A moment later, they were hovering in the

08:08:57.000 --> 08:08:59.580
air above a huge lake, glittering in the

08:08:59.580 --> 08:09:00.479
midday sunshine.

08:09:00.540 --> 08:09:03.299
Luna blinked, disoriented by the light.

08:09:03.360 --> 08:09:05.880
She hadn't realized how much time had

08:09:05.880 --> 08:09:06.900
passed in the real world.

08:09:06.959 --> 08:09:10.500
Bringing sundew closer and closer to

08:09:10.500 --> 08:09:11.580
cottonmouths trap.

08:09:11.700 --> 08:09:13.799
Speaking of whom?

08:09:13.919 --> 08:09:16.979
There was the human, descending through

08:09:16.979 --> 08:09:18.659
the sky toward a cave opening on the

08:09:18.659 --> 08:09:19.799
north shore of the lake.

08:09:19.799 --> 08:09:22.319
It looked like the cave in the drawings

08:09:22.319 --> 08:09:24.479
Luna had seen, the one with all the

08:09:24.479 --> 08:09:25.439
humans walking into it.

08:09:25.560 --> 08:09:28.740
A leaf wing was waiting on the pebbly

08:09:28.740 --> 08:09:29.340
beach by the lake.

08:09:29.400 --> 08:09:32.400
Water rippled over the dragon's green

08:09:32.400 --> 08:09:34.860
talons, and it seemed to be staring up

08:09:34.860 --> 08:09:38.759
into the trees, real actual trees, on

08:09:38.759 --> 08:09:39.479
Pantala.

08:09:39.540 --> 08:09:43.020
Luna had never been to this peninsula, and

08:09:43.020 --> 08:09:44.220
she didn't know anyone else who had

08:09:44.220 --> 08:09:44.459
either.

08:09:44.520 --> 08:09:47.580
It wasn't quite the wild jungle of

08:09:47.580 --> 08:09:50.279
pineapple's memories, or the forest Luna

08:09:50.279 --> 08:09:52.860
had visited around sanctuary, but there

08:09:52.860 --> 08:09:53.700
were trees here.

08:09:53.759 --> 08:09:56.099
Growing along the hills that covered the

08:09:56.099 --> 08:09:56.700
cave system.

08:09:56.759 --> 08:10:00.779
I bet that leaf wing is as amazed as I am

08:10:00.779 --> 08:10:01.860
Luna thought.

08:10:01.919 --> 08:10:04.560
I wonder if they're thinking the leaf

08:10:04.560 --> 08:10:06.779
wings should have hidden here, instead of

08:10:06.779 --> 08:10:07.500
the poison jungle.

08:10:07.560 --> 08:10:10.380
But then again, it would have been much

08:10:10.380 --> 08:10:12.540
easier for wasp to find and attack them

08:10:12.540 --> 08:10:12.779
here.

08:10:12.840 --> 08:10:14.580
Wait.

08:10:14.639 --> 08:10:15.659
Who is that?

08:10:15.779 --> 08:10:17.819
Briony?

08:10:17.880 --> 08:10:19.200
Hemlock or pokeweed?

08:10:19.259 --> 08:10:20.520
Who else could it be?

08:10:20.639 --> 08:10:24.779
Cottonmouth in pineapple landed and

08:10:24.779 --> 08:10:27.419
approached the leaf wing, Luna nearly

08:10:27.419 --> 08:10:29.819
called out to warn the green dragon, not

08:10:29.819 --> 08:10:30.419
that it would have helped.

08:10:30.479 --> 08:10:33.299
But then the dragon turned, and she saw

08:10:33.299 --> 08:10:34.919
his boiled egg white eyes.

08:10:34.979 --> 08:10:36.840
Oh, no.

08:10:36.900 --> 08:10:39.060
One of Cottonmouth's creatures.

08:10:39.119 --> 08:10:41.040
They didn't speak.

08:10:41.099 --> 08:10:43.560
But the other dragon turned toward the

08:10:43.560 --> 08:10:46.200
copse of trees behind him, and 6 other

08:10:46.200 --> 08:10:47.880
white eyed dragons came forward.

08:10:47.939 --> 08:10:51.900
Three hive wings, 3 leaf wings, dragging

08:10:51.900 --> 08:10:53.580
cricket and bullfrog between them.

08:10:53.639 --> 08:10:55.380
Cricket!

08:10:55.439 --> 08:10:56.459
Luna yelped.

08:10:56.520 --> 08:10:59.759
The bespectacled hive wing had 2 leaf

08:10:59.759 --> 08:11:02.220
wings flanking her, brandishing spears at

08:11:02.220 --> 08:11:02.580
her side.

08:11:02.639 --> 08:11:05.340
She blinked in confusion at Cottonmouth.

08:11:05.400 --> 08:11:07.020
Pineapple?

08:11:07.020 --> 08:11:07.560
she said.

08:11:07.619 --> 08:11:08.819
What are you doing here?

08:11:08.939 --> 08:11:11.700
Pineapple is out to lunch.

08:11:11.759 --> 08:11:15.299
I'm afraid, Cottonmouth said, smirking

08:11:15.299 --> 08:11:15.900
cruelly.

08:11:15.959 --> 08:11:18.299
Cricket's face crumbled.

08:11:18.360 --> 08:11:20.459
Oh, no, pineapple.

08:11:20.520 --> 08:11:21.659
I'm so, so sorry.

08:11:21.720 --> 08:11:24.779
There was a kind of crackling in the air

08:11:24.779 --> 08:11:27.479
and suddenly, the rest of Luna's friends

08:11:27.479 --> 08:11:29.220
were standing behind pineapple.

08:11:29.279 --> 08:11:31.799
Sundew's scowl was so fierce.

08:11:31.860 --> 08:11:34.319
Luna was surprised Cottonmouth didn't go

08:11:34.319 --> 08:11:35.159
up in flames.

08:11:35.220 --> 08:11:37.139
Cricket burst into tears.

08:11:37.200 --> 08:11:38.400
All of you?

08:11:38.459 --> 08:11:41.400
No, Kibley said quickly.

08:11:41.459 --> 08:11:43.139
Cricket, we're all right.

08:11:43.200 --> 08:11:44.700
It only got pineapple.

08:11:44.759 --> 08:11:46.439
And Luna.

08:11:46.500 --> 08:11:48.779
Bullfrog looked startled.

08:11:48.840 --> 08:11:51.419
Cricket glanced toward the cave opening

08:11:51.419 --> 08:11:53.279
and pressed her talons together.

08:11:53.340 --> 08:11:56.099
But she's in the abyss.

08:11:56.159 --> 08:11:58.979
She said if I brought you, sundew, that

08:11:58.979 --> 08:11:59.700
she'd be okay.

08:11:59.819 --> 08:12:04.740
She will be, Sundoo snarled, her eyes

08:12:04.740 --> 08:12:06.000
locked on Cottonmouth.

08:12:06.060 --> 08:12:08.159
Tangles and threads.

08:12:08.220 --> 08:12:09.959
Luna suddenly realized.

08:12:10.020 --> 08:12:12.180
I should be trying to cut the vine.

08:12:12.240 --> 08:12:15.419
I got distracted by watching, but this is

08:12:15.419 --> 08:12:17.340
my best and last chance.

08:12:17.400 --> 08:12:19.560
Quick, before anything else terrible

08:12:19.560 --> 08:12:20.040
happens here.

08:12:20.159 --> 08:12:24.360
She closed her eyes and reached, reached

08:12:24.360 --> 08:12:25.259
for her real body.

08:12:25.319 --> 08:12:28.560
It was harder from here, where she could

08:12:28.560 --> 08:12:30.540
sense the warmth of the sun on her scales

08:12:30.540 --> 08:12:32.880
and hear the trees rustling in the wind.

08:12:32.939 --> 08:12:36.599
This felt so much more real, than the

08:12:36.599 --> 08:12:39.900
cold, damp, uneven, green, rot smelling

08:12:39.900 --> 08:12:40.919
place where she really was.

08:12:41.040 --> 08:12:44.520
Breathe, like cricket said.

08:12:44.580 --> 08:12:48.479
Finally, her real claws began to tingle.

08:12:48.540 --> 08:12:50.939
And when she ordered her muscles to move

08:12:50.939 --> 08:12:53.340
forward, it was her real body that moved

08:12:53.340 --> 08:12:55.380
not the one in the mind space.

08:12:55.439 --> 08:12:58.259
The weight of Dusky still rested between

08:12:58.259 --> 08:13:00.599
her shoulder blades, breathing deeply.

08:13:00.659 --> 08:13:04.200
Let cricket and bullfrog go.

08:13:04.259 --> 08:13:07.680
She heard Sundu say, with menace in her

08:13:07.680 --> 08:13:07.860
voice.

08:13:07.919 --> 08:13:10.020
One step.

08:13:10.080 --> 08:13:11.520
Another step.

08:13:11.639 --> 08:13:15.900
Slippery vines around my ankle, carefully

08:13:15.900 --> 08:13:16.799
disentangle them.

08:13:16.860 --> 08:13:18.840
Another step.

08:13:18.900 --> 08:13:21.959
Why in the world would I do that?

08:13:22.020 --> 08:13:23.880
Cottonmouth answered.

08:13:23.939 --> 08:13:27.360
It would be much more fair if I absorbed

08:13:27.360 --> 08:13:29.340
one of them, or both of them.

08:13:29.400 --> 08:13:32.400
Then you'd have 4 of your dragons, and

08:13:32.400 --> 08:13:34.919
I'd have 4 of your dragons, and you'd be

08:13:34.919 --> 08:13:36.599
much less tempted to try any clever

08:13:36.599 --> 08:13:36.959
tricks.

08:13:37.080 --> 08:13:40.439
Luna's real nose bumped into something

08:13:40.439 --> 08:13:40.919
solid.

08:13:40.979 --> 08:13:42.419
A wall?

08:13:42.479 --> 08:13:43.560
A column?

08:13:43.680 --> 08:13:46.919
She felt it with her talons, flat

08:13:46.919 --> 08:13:49.860
straight, a few vines zigzagging up it.

08:13:49.919 --> 08:13:51.060
The wall then.

08:13:51.119 --> 08:13:53.340
Pick a direction.

08:13:53.400 --> 08:13:53.819
Keep going.

08:13:53.880 --> 08:13:57.360
She turned right, and kept one left wing

08:13:57.360 --> 08:13:59.220
touching the wall, as she felt her way

08:13:59.220 --> 08:13:59.759
forward again.

08:13:59.819 --> 08:14:04.200
The clever tricks are non-negotiable.

08:14:04.259 --> 08:14:05.340
Kibley said.

08:14:05.400 --> 08:14:07.799
Sundew is not going to deliver herself

08:14:07.799 --> 08:14:11.939
into your, um, pedals, sundew.

08:14:12.060 --> 08:14:14.400
What do you call the part of plants that

08:14:14.400 --> 08:14:15.419
eats dragons?

08:14:15.479 --> 08:14:19.319
Jaws, Sundu said grimly.

08:14:19.380 --> 08:14:21.479
Yeep, Kibley said.

08:14:21.540 --> 08:14:23.159
I think I'll stick with pedals.

08:14:23.220 --> 08:14:26.580
Luna's wing on her right side brushed

08:14:26.580 --> 08:14:27.779
cold stone.

08:14:27.900 --> 08:14:30.659
She reached out and felt it, smooth and

08:14:30.659 --> 08:14:32.459
curved, one of the columns.

08:14:32.580 --> 08:14:34.799
Hope I'm going the right way.

08:14:34.860 --> 08:14:37.020
She took another step.

08:14:37.080 --> 08:14:39.659
Vines squishing and flexing under her

08:14:39.659 --> 08:14:40.020
talons.

08:14:40.139 --> 08:14:43.439
You don't exactly have a choice

08:14:43.439 --> 08:14:44.819
Cottonmouth said.

08:14:44.880 --> 08:14:48.119
I have infinitely more dragons than you

08:14:48.119 --> 08:14:49.139
do, and...

08:14:49.139 --> 08:14:51.959
Hang on, Kibley interrupted.

08:14:52.020 --> 08:14:54.840
Not literally infinitely.

08:14:54.900 --> 08:14:56.700
That's mathematically impossible.

08:14:56.759 --> 08:14:59.700
Another column on Luna's right.

08:14:59.819 --> 08:15:01.200
That seemed promising.

08:15:01.259 --> 08:15:03.720
She'd been close to the door, hadn't

08:15:03.720 --> 08:15:03.840
she?

08:15:03.900 --> 08:15:07.200
So if she was going the correct way, she

08:15:07.200 --> 08:15:09.479
would have to pass 2 columns before

08:15:09.479 --> 08:15:11.279
reaching the far wall with the throne.

08:15:11.340 --> 08:15:14.099
She thought, she hoped.

08:15:14.159 --> 08:15:16.740
It was hard to focus while listening to

08:15:16.740 --> 08:15:17.880
her friends in danger.

08:15:17.939 --> 08:15:21.479
She pictured the throne room again, using

08:15:21.479 --> 08:15:23.639
the mental tapestry she'd imagined when

08:15:23.639 --> 08:15:24.360
she 1st saw it.

08:15:24.419 --> 08:15:27.900
What if she anchored herself to make sure

08:15:27.900 --> 08:15:29.580
she could find her way back, if anything

08:15:29.580 --> 08:15:29.939
happened.

08:15:30.000 --> 08:15:31.799
Carefully.

08:15:31.860 --> 08:15:34.439
She rested both front talons on the

08:15:34.439 --> 08:15:37.560
column, then spun out a long thread of

08:15:37.560 --> 08:15:38.759
ordinary golden silk.

08:15:38.880 --> 08:15:41.639
She passed it around the column and tied

08:15:41.639 --> 08:15:44.099
it off, leaving the other end still

08:15:44.099 --> 08:15:46.439
unspooling from her wrist as she started

08:15:46.439 --> 08:15:46.979
forward again.

08:15:47.040 --> 08:15:50.639
Do not bother being aggravating.

08:15:50.759 --> 08:15:53.520
Cottonmouth said, in a bored voice.

08:15:53.580 --> 08:15:55.619
Sun do.

08:15:55.680 --> 08:15:58.020
This hive wing is Caribid.

08:15:58.139 --> 08:16:01.080
I chose him specially to be the one to

08:16:01.080 --> 08:16:01.619
inject you.

08:16:01.680 --> 08:16:04.919
He has marvelous stingers in his claws

08:16:04.919 --> 08:16:05.400
and tail.

08:16:05.459 --> 08:16:08.700
And the ability to inject much more toxin

08:16:08.700 --> 08:16:09.900
than boring wasp.

08:16:10.020 --> 08:16:12.659
He's been consuming all the breath of

08:16:12.659 --> 08:16:15.419
evil I could get him from the moment I

08:16:15.419 --> 08:16:15.659
met you.

08:16:15.720 --> 08:16:19.979
I think we might be able to absorb you on

08:16:19.979 --> 08:16:20.939
the 1st stab.

08:16:21.060 --> 08:16:24.900
Although, if we need to do more stabbing

08:16:24.900 --> 08:16:26.939
there's time for that too.

08:16:27.000 --> 08:16:31.080
Back up, tsunami yelled, making Luna

08:16:31.080 --> 08:16:31.619
stumble.

08:16:31.680 --> 08:16:33.240
Don't you get any closer?

08:16:33.360 --> 08:16:37.860
If you turn invisible again, or shoot any

08:16:37.860 --> 08:16:40.860
more unpleasant ice in me, I will have

08:16:40.860 --> 08:16:43.020
Caribid stab cricket first.

08:16:43.080 --> 08:16:45.360
Cottonmouth hiss.

08:16:45.419 --> 08:16:48.360
Luna walked straight into a wall.

08:16:48.419 --> 08:16:51.419
She was shaking a particularly clingy

08:16:51.419 --> 08:16:53.939
vine off one of her back feet, and forgot

08:16:53.939 --> 08:16:55.020
to reach forward for a moment.

08:16:55.080 --> 08:16:58.319
Her head thudded painfully against stone

08:16:58.319 --> 08:17:00.119
and she let out a gasp of pain.

08:17:00.180 --> 08:17:01.860
Luna?

08:17:01.919 --> 08:17:03.299
She heard lizards say.

08:17:03.419 --> 08:17:04.740
Nothing.

08:17:04.799 --> 08:17:06.779
She whispered, dizzy.

08:17:06.840 --> 08:17:09.900
She took a deep breath, waiting for the

08:17:09.900 --> 08:17:11.220
shock of the pain to subside.

08:17:11.279 --> 08:17:13.080
Ignore me.

08:17:13.139 --> 08:17:15.599
She'd reached the corner.

08:17:15.659 --> 08:17:19.439
With luck, if she turned right here, she'd

08:17:19.439 --> 08:17:20.099
find the throne.

08:17:20.159 --> 08:17:24.060
Or, if she'd come the wrong way, she'd be

08:17:24.060 --> 08:17:25.439
back at the blocked entrance to the

08:17:25.439 --> 08:17:25.560
room.

08:17:25.680 --> 08:17:29.819
She turned, kept one wing on the wall, and

08:17:29.819 --> 08:17:30.779
felt her way forward.

08:17:30.840 --> 08:17:35.220
Suddenly, chaos erupted in the mind space

08:17:35.220 --> 08:17:38.580
Dragon screams filled Luna's ears, and

08:17:38.580 --> 08:17:40.979
she instinctively froze, paralyzed with

08:17:40.979 --> 08:17:41.279
terror.

08:17:41.340 --> 08:17:43.740
What's happening?

08:17:43.799 --> 08:17:44.459
she cried.

08:17:44.520 --> 08:17:46.439
Should I open my eyes?

08:17:46.500 --> 08:17:48.959
But I can't help them in the outside

08:17:48.959 --> 08:17:49.439
world.

08:17:49.500 --> 08:17:52.139
I can only help them if I stay focused

08:17:52.139 --> 08:17:53.520
and keep going in here.

08:17:53.580 --> 08:17:56.580
A whole bunch of leaf wings just

08:17:56.580 --> 08:17:57.180
attacked!

08:17:57.240 --> 08:18:00.240
Lizard yelped, including Sandu's mother.

08:18:00.299 --> 08:18:01.500
This is so exciting.

08:18:01.560 --> 08:18:04.319
Didn't you know they were coming?

08:18:04.380 --> 08:18:05.520
Luna cried.

08:18:05.580 --> 08:18:07.139
Couldn't you have warned us?

08:18:07.200 --> 08:18:09.720
How and why exactly?

08:18:09.779 --> 08:18:11.099
Lizard asked.

08:18:11.159 --> 08:18:13.319
You can't expect me to do everything

08:18:13.319 --> 08:18:14.040
around here?

08:18:14.099 --> 08:18:17.279
That's true, Luna thought.

08:18:17.340 --> 08:18:18.779
Stay on task.

08:18:18.840 --> 08:18:21.840
She pressed forward again in her real

08:18:21.840 --> 08:18:22.319
body.

08:18:22.380 --> 08:18:25.380
The vines were so thick here, both

08:18:25.380 --> 08:18:27.299
underfoot and swarming up the wall.

08:18:27.419 --> 08:18:30.659
It was hard to feel the wall at all most

08:18:30.659 --> 08:18:31.080
of the time.

08:18:31.139 --> 08:18:33.540
She felt like she was floundering through

08:18:33.540 --> 08:18:36.119
a twisting pit of snakes, while at least

08:18:36.119 --> 08:18:38.279
20 dragons roared and battled in her

08:18:38.279 --> 08:18:38.520
ears.

08:18:38.639 --> 08:18:42.119
Plants are just bursting out of the

08:18:42.119 --> 08:18:44.459
ground, Lizard reported gleefully.

08:18:44.520 --> 08:18:47.459
Sendu's got carabit pinned in a bramble

08:18:47.459 --> 08:18:47.880
bush.

08:18:47.939 --> 08:18:51.240
Ooh, Cottonmouth nearly got tsunami with

08:18:51.240 --> 08:18:52.020
his death spit.

08:18:52.080 --> 08:18:53.400
Eee!

08:18:53.459 --> 08:18:55.740
Belladonna just tried to stab Moon and

08:18:55.740 --> 08:18:56.939
Kibley jumped in the way.

08:18:57.000 --> 08:19:00.720
That ice dragon has frozen 2 of the leaf

08:19:00.720 --> 08:19:01.080
wings.

08:19:01.139 --> 08:19:02.700
Ach!

08:19:02.759 --> 08:19:06.240
Like 9 of our dragons, just grabbed

08:19:06.240 --> 08:19:08.759
cricket, and threw her at Carabid.

08:19:08.819 --> 08:19:12.299
Oh, snap peas, we're finally getting

08:19:12.299 --> 08:19:12.900
cricket now.

08:19:12.959 --> 08:19:17.520
Cricket, Luna squeezed her eyes shut and

08:19:17.520 --> 08:19:19.439
covered them with her talons to stop

08:19:19.439 --> 08:19:20.459
herself from opening them.

08:19:20.520 --> 08:19:22.139
Can she hear me?

08:19:22.200 --> 08:19:25.860
Cricket, She felt the thread connected to

08:19:25.860 --> 08:19:27.599
the column flick against her wings

08:19:27.599 --> 08:19:28.740
humming softly.

08:19:28.799 --> 08:19:33.779
I'll take care of her, said Pineapple's

08:19:33.779 --> 08:19:35.700
voice, distant and drifting.

08:19:35.759 --> 08:19:37.259
You keep going.

08:19:37.319 --> 08:19:39.419
Forward.

08:19:39.479 --> 08:19:40.740
Another step.

08:19:40.799 --> 08:19:42.779
Fight the vines.

08:19:42.840 --> 08:19:43.860
Another step.

08:19:43.919 --> 08:19:48.360
And then, her reaching talons found a

08:19:48.360 --> 08:19:50.759
mass of vines, and her heart sank.

08:19:50.819 --> 08:19:53.400
Am I on the wrong end of the room?

08:19:53.459 --> 08:19:57.180
She plunged her talent through the vines

08:19:57.180 --> 08:19:58.680
feeling around frantically.

08:19:58.740 --> 08:20:00.360
There.

08:20:00.419 --> 08:20:03.360
There was a heavy stone shape under the

08:20:03.360 --> 08:20:05.819
vines, solid and unyielding.

08:20:05.880 --> 08:20:07.080
The throne.

08:20:07.139 --> 08:20:08.040
It has to be.

08:20:08.159 --> 08:20:10.020
I'm almost there.

08:20:10.139 --> 08:20:15.360
Sandew is mad, Lizard announced.

08:20:15.419 --> 08:20:17.880
Moon keeps yelling, don't hurt

08:20:17.880 --> 08:20:18.659
pineapple.

08:20:18.720 --> 08:20:19.439
Don't kill him.

08:20:19.500 --> 08:20:20.580
Sundo.

08:20:20.639 --> 08:20:21.720
Remember, it's not him.

08:20:21.779 --> 08:20:24.479
But with all these branches flying

08:20:24.479 --> 08:20:24.779
everywhere?

08:20:24.840 --> 08:20:27.000
I'm pretty sure someone's going to die.

08:20:27.060 --> 08:20:30.659
Luna could hear a moon's cries herself.

08:20:30.720 --> 08:20:34.020
She also heard links shouting, the

08:20:34.020 --> 08:20:36.840
wristbands, and Kibli shouting about 8

08:20:36.840 --> 08:20:39.299
different instructions, and Bullfrog and

08:20:39.299 --> 08:20:41.880
tsunami roaring furiously, and it was so

08:20:41.880 --> 08:20:42.419
hard to think.

08:20:42.540 --> 08:20:46.200
So hard to stay here, in the slow, tangled

08:20:46.200 --> 08:20:48.840
space, instead of opening her eyes to

08:20:48.840 --> 08:20:50.040
make sure her friends were safe.

08:20:50.099 --> 08:20:52.919
Do the thing I can do.

08:20:52.979 --> 08:20:54.720
Pray that it helps.

08:20:54.779 --> 08:20:57.720
I hope that Lizard is right about this.

08:20:57.840 --> 08:21:02.220
She found a vine so thick, her talons

08:21:02.220 --> 08:21:03.540
couldn't reach all the way around it.

08:21:03.659 --> 08:21:06.959
When she gingerly traced its path upward

08:21:06.959 --> 08:21:10.259
her claws brushed a tiny foot and brittle

08:21:10.259 --> 08:21:10.799
scales.

08:21:10.799 --> 08:21:13.200
Lizard's body.

08:21:13.259 --> 08:21:15.180
She thought with a shudder.

08:21:15.299 --> 08:21:17.759
This is the vine I have to cut.

08:21:17.819 --> 08:21:21.599
Do I cut it below Lizard's body before it

08:21:21.599 --> 08:21:22.020
reaches them?

08:21:22.139 --> 08:21:23.700
Or...

08:21:23.700 --> 08:21:26.159
If I cut the vine that's growing between

08:21:26.159 --> 08:21:28.799
lizard and cottonmouth, would that cut

08:21:28.799 --> 08:21:31.080
cottonmouth out of the other mind, but

08:21:31.080 --> 08:21:32.220
leave lizard alive?

08:21:32.279 --> 08:21:35.639
Lizard hadn't said exactly where to cut

08:21:35.639 --> 08:21:38.459
it, and Luna didn't want to ask, in case

08:21:38.459 --> 08:21:39.479
Cottonmouth heard her.

08:21:39.540 --> 08:21:43.080
All right, I'll try cutting it between

08:21:43.080 --> 08:21:44.639
them, and hope that works.

08:21:44.700 --> 08:21:49.979
Oh, wow, Lizard said, through the din of

08:21:49.979 --> 08:21:50.880
the roaring dragons.

08:21:50.939 --> 08:21:53.939
Someone injected that big brown one too.

08:21:54.000 --> 08:21:57.299
I wonder what his memories will be like.

08:21:57.599 --> 08:21:59.580
Bullfrog.

08:21:59.700 --> 08:22:01.259
Don't think about that.

08:22:01.319 --> 08:22:02.759
Focus on this.

08:22:02.880 --> 08:22:06.779
Luna was hovering in the air now, her

08:22:06.779 --> 08:22:08.819
wings keeping her aloft in front of the

08:22:08.819 --> 08:22:09.299
tall throne.

08:22:09.360 --> 08:22:12.000
She beat them once to rise a little

08:22:12.000 --> 08:22:15.000
higher, tracing the curve of the vine up

08:22:15.000 --> 08:22:17.819
and through lizard's skull, keeping one

08:22:17.819 --> 08:22:18.720
talent on the vine.

08:22:18.779 --> 08:22:21.840
She reached up to be sure Cottonmouth's

08:22:21.840 --> 08:22:24.119
head was above her, connected along the

08:22:24.119 --> 08:22:25.139
same winding trail.

08:22:25.200 --> 08:22:27.000
Here.

08:22:27.060 --> 08:22:29.159
But now what?

08:22:29.279 --> 08:22:31.319
She couldn't use her claws.

08:22:31.380 --> 08:22:34.020
The vine was so dense, and the moment she

08:22:34.020 --> 08:22:35.819
started to hack or slice at it

08:22:35.819 --> 08:22:38.159
Cottonmouth would surely sense the attack

08:22:38.159 --> 08:22:40.139
jump into her and stop her.

08:22:40.200 --> 08:22:43.560
She carefully rested her feet on the edge

08:22:43.560 --> 08:22:44.099
of the throne.

08:22:44.220 --> 08:22:47.279
The silk connecting her to the column

08:22:47.279 --> 08:22:48.540
rubbed against her wing again.

08:22:48.659 --> 08:22:51.299
What if?

08:22:51.659 --> 08:22:55.020
Luna spun out several more coils of silk

08:22:55.020 --> 08:22:56.520
and cut it loose from her wrist.

08:22:56.580 --> 08:22:59.279
She looped the silk lightly around the

08:22:59.279 --> 08:22:59.639
vine.

08:22:59.700 --> 08:23:05.400
Gentle, gentle, harmless, only leaves

08:23:05.400 --> 08:23:06.360
brushing each other.

08:23:06.419 --> 08:23:09.659
Crossed over the thread coming from the

08:23:09.659 --> 08:23:12.000
column, and tied the loose end to her

08:23:12.000 --> 08:23:12.240
arm.

08:23:12.299 --> 08:23:15.240
I hope the silk is strong enough.

08:23:15.299 --> 08:23:17.880
I hope my weight is enough to pull it

08:23:17.880 --> 08:23:19.619
straight through the vine in one quick

08:23:19.619 --> 08:23:20.220
slice.

08:23:20.279 --> 08:23:24.419
Luna took a deep breath, braced herself

08:23:24.419 --> 08:23:26.939
to shove off, and launched herself away

08:23:26.939 --> 08:23:28.979
from the throne at full speed.

08:23:29.340 --> 08:23:33.360
Chapter 25.

08:23:33.659 --> 08:23:36.299
The shriek.

08:23:36.360 --> 08:23:39.240
That filled Luna's head, drowned out all

08:23:39.240 --> 08:23:41.700
the other dragons, and then they all cut

08:23:41.700 --> 08:23:45.299
off mid roar, mid shout, mid scream.

08:23:45.419 --> 08:23:48.659
And Luna was flung violently out of the

08:23:48.659 --> 08:23:49.139
mind space.

08:23:49.200 --> 08:23:53.099
She opened her eyes just in time to see

08:23:53.099 --> 08:23:55.380
the wall of the real world throne room as

08:23:55.380 --> 08:23:56.520
she smashed into it.

08:23:56.580 --> 08:23:58.319
Oh.

08:23:58.500 --> 08:24:03.959
Oh, she moaned, sliding down and landing

08:24:03.959 --> 08:24:04.860
in the carpet of vines.

08:24:04.979 --> 08:24:08.040
Silence, enveloped her.

08:24:08.099 --> 08:24:12.000
She sat up, her head reeling, and reached

08:24:12.000 --> 08:24:12.599
over her shoulder.

08:24:12.659 --> 08:24:16.020
A little talon clutched hers, and her

08:24:16.020 --> 08:24:16.619
heart leaped.

08:24:16.680 --> 08:24:18.240
Tusky.

08:24:18.299 --> 08:24:19.080
Are you all right?

08:24:19.139 --> 08:24:21.779
The dragonette scrabbled up her back?

08:24:21.900 --> 08:24:24.299
Wrapped his talons around her neck and

08:24:24.299 --> 08:24:27.180
leaned into her, breathing deep, shaky

08:24:27.180 --> 08:24:27.479
breaths.

08:24:27.540 --> 08:24:30.000
I think so.

08:24:30.060 --> 08:24:31.680
He said after a moment.

08:24:31.740 --> 08:24:33.299
What happened?

08:24:33.419 --> 08:24:35.040
Where's Lizard?

08:24:35.159 --> 08:24:37.919
Luna turned to look at the throne.

08:24:37.979 --> 08:24:38.819
Finally.

08:24:38.880 --> 08:24:41.759
Her trick with the silk had worked.

08:24:41.819 --> 08:24:45.360
With her momentum pulling on one end, and

08:24:45.360 --> 08:24:47.459
the other anchored at the column, the

08:24:47.459 --> 08:24:49.139
silk had sliced right through the vine

08:24:49.139 --> 08:24:51.060
severing its connection with cotton

08:24:51.060 --> 08:24:51.360
mouth.

08:24:51.419 --> 08:24:53.340
How strange.

08:24:53.400 --> 08:24:56.220
I thought my flame silk was what made me

08:24:56.220 --> 08:24:56.459
special.

08:24:56.520 --> 08:24:59.520
And that it was the one magic thing I

08:24:59.520 --> 08:25:00.659
could use to save the day.

08:25:00.720 --> 08:25:05.159
But instead, it was my ordinary silk, and

08:25:05.159 --> 08:25:06.900
it could have come from any silk wing at

08:25:06.900 --> 08:25:07.080
all.

08:25:07.139 --> 08:25:11.159
And now, something was happening.

08:25:11.220 --> 08:25:14.700
All the vines that branched out of the

08:25:14.700 --> 08:25:17.340
top of cottonmouth's skull were withering

08:25:17.340 --> 08:25:20.159
shriveling into brown and curling shreds

08:25:20.159 --> 08:25:20.819
before her eyes.

08:25:20.880 --> 08:25:24.060
The decay spread rapidly out along the

08:25:24.060 --> 08:25:26.639
long tendrils of the plant, all the way

08:25:26.639 --> 08:25:28.619
up to the ceiling and racing along the

08:25:28.619 --> 08:25:28.860
walls.

08:25:28.919 --> 08:25:32.819
Luna scooped dusky up, and beat her wings

08:25:32.819 --> 08:25:34.860
to hover in the air just in case.

08:25:34.919 --> 08:25:38.099
She thought the plant was dying, but she

08:25:38.099 --> 08:25:40.080
didn't want to be standing on it, if it

08:25:40.080 --> 08:25:41.700
happened to have any last creepy death

08:25:41.700 --> 08:25:42.240
throws.

08:25:42.299 --> 08:25:45.360
Lizard, she said out loud.

08:25:45.419 --> 08:25:48.360
The petrified body of the dragonette on

08:25:48.360 --> 08:25:50.040
the throne looked exactly the same.

08:25:50.099 --> 08:25:53.340
While cotton mouths husk already looked

08:25:53.340 --> 08:25:54.779
like it was starting to crumble around

08:25:54.779 --> 08:25:55.380
the edges.

08:25:55.439 --> 08:25:57.240
Are you still there?

08:25:57.299 --> 08:25:58.500
Can you hear me?

08:25:58.560 --> 08:26:02.580
You did it wrong, said Lizard's voice.

08:26:02.639 --> 08:26:05.580
Echoing inside their skulls, instead of

08:26:05.580 --> 08:26:06.659
coming through their ears.

08:26:06.840 --> 08:26:08.400
Why would you do it wrong?

08:26:08.459 --> 08:26:10.439
I did?

08:26:10.500 --> 08:26:11.520
Luna said.

08:26:11.580 --> 08:26:13.080
But it looks like it's working.

08:26:13.139 --> 08:26:15.540
Do you mean I cut it in the wrong place?

08:26:15.659 --> 08:26:18.000
I was trying to get rid of cotton mouth

08:26:18.000 --> 08:26:18.599
and keep you.

08:26:18.720 --> 08:26:21.479
Keep me?

08:26:21.540 --> 08:26:24.540
There was a sort of floundering silence

08:26:24.540 --> 08:26:25.020
for a moment.

08:26:25.080 --> 08:26:27.900
You can't, you idiot.

08:26:27.959 --> 08:26:30.540
As long as the plant has an intelligent

08:26:30.540 --> 08:26:32.520
brain to work with, it won't give up.

08:26:32.580 --> 08:26:35.639
It wants to survive more than anything in

08:26:35.639 --> 08:26:36.000
the world.

08:26:36.060 --> 08:26:39.540
And with only 2 of us in here, now it's

08:26:39.540 --> 08:26:40.919
as strong as I am.

08:26:42.060 --> 08:26:42.900
Hang on.

08:26:43.020 --> 08:26:46.020
But you don't have to be evil, right?

08:26:46.080 --> 08:26:48.000
Now that Cottonmouth is gone?

08:26:48.119 --> 08:26:49.380
Luna tried.

08:26:49.439 --> 08:26:52.259
Maybe you and the plant can coexist.

08:26:52.319 --> 08:26:54.540
Maybe you'll like being a not evil

08:26:54.540 --> 08:26:54.959
plant.

08:26:55.020 --> 08:26:57.779
And we can come visit you down here

08:26:57.779 --> 08:26:58.560
right?

08:26:58.680 --> 08:27:00.720
And talk to you, like this?

08:27:00.779 --> 08:27:02.700
No!

08:27:02.819 --> 08:27:04.259
Lizard shouted.

08:27:04.319 --> 08:27:06.000
You are so stupid.

08:27:06.119 --> 08:27:09.479
The plant is already trying to use my

08:27:09.479 --> 08:27:12.060
leaf speak to grow back into cottonmouth

08:27:12.060 --> 08:27:14.580
or it'll replace him with a guardian, or

08:27:14.580 --> 08:27:16.500
if that doesn't work, it'll find some

08:27:16.500 --> 08:27:17.220
other awful human.

08:27:17.340 --> 08:27:21.540
Luna had forgotten about the Guardian, but

08:27:21.540 --> 08:27:22.020
there he was.

08:27:22.080 --> 08:27:24.479
Curled up at the foot of the throne

08:27:24.479 --> 08:27:26.939
rocking back and forth with a dazed

08:27:26.939 --> 08:27:27.540
expression.

08:27:27.599 --> 08:27:31.380
Luna, yelled Lizard's voice in her head.

08:27:31.439 --> 08:27:34.740
I don't want to just exist in this

08:27:34.740 --> 08:27:37.439
nothingness, trying to fight a desperate

08:27:37.439 --> 08:27:39.360
weed for the rest of eternity.

08:27:39.419 --> 08:27:41.159
I hate that plan.

08:27:41.220 --> 08:27:43.979
I'm sorry, lizard.

08:27:44.040 --> 08:27:47.279
Luna was crying now, and so was Dusky.

08:27:47.340 --> 08:27:48.659
I'm so sorry.

08:27:48.720 --> 08:27:50.459
I didn't want to lose you.

08:27:50.520 --> 08:27:52.560
You saved us, and it's not fair.

08:27:52.619 --> 08:27:56.400
And you're funny, Dusky chimed in.

08:27:56.459 --> 08:27:59.880
And fun to play with, and very loud, and

08:27:59.880 --> 08:28:02.700
scary sometimes, and bossy all the time

08:28:02.700 --> 08:28:06.240
and brave, and really interesting, and I

08:28:06.240 --> 08:28:07.319
don't want you to go away either.

08:28:07.380 --> 08:28:11.099
Lizard didn't reply for a moment, and

08:28:11.099 --> 08:28:13.439
when she did, her voice was muffled.

08:28:13.500 --> 08:28:17.340
Well, I have to, she said.

08:28:17.400 --> 08:28:19.560
So you should say goodbye.

08:28:19.619 --> 08:28:22.619
And then you should get over here and cut

08:28:22.619 --> 08:28:23.939
the vine below my head.

08:28:24.000 --> 08:28:26.759
So the plant will stop using my brain to

08:28:26.759 --> 08:28:28.080
connive and flail around.

08:28:28.139 --> 08:28:30.479
Do it quick, before it gets to

08:28:30.479 --> 08:28:31.200
Cottonmouth again.

08:28:31.259 --> 08:28:35.279
Luna realized with alarm that Lizard was

08:28:35.279 --> 08:28:35.459
right.

08:28:35.520 --> 08:28:38.400
A new spray of green was growing out of

08:28:38.400 --> 08:28:40.979
the vine, where Luna's silk had sliced it

08:28:40.979 --> 08:28:44.279
crawling tentatively up, as though

08:28:44.279 --> 08:28:45.659
Cottonmouth's head was the sun.

08:28:45.720 --> 08:28:49.740
She started forward, but Dusky tightened

08:28:49.740 --> 08:28:50.279
his arms around her.

08:28:50.340 --> 08:28:53.459
Wait, he said.

08:28:53.520 --> 08:28:56.759
Can we give lizard a new name first?

08:28:56.819 --> 08:28:58.380
A real name?

08:28:58.439 --> 08:28:59.759
Over own?

08:28:59.819 --> 08:29:01.740
So she doesn't have to die?

08:29:01.799 --> 08:29:03.959
Still stuck with his name for her?

08:29:04.020 --> 08:29:06.959
That seems pointless?

08:29:07.020 --> 08:29:08.159
Lizard said.

08:29:08.220 --> 08:29:10.740
But Luna thought she could hear a wary

08:29:10.740 --> 08:29:11.819
curiosity in her voice.

08:29:11.880 --> 08:29:15.299
A new name for 30 seconds?

08:29:15.419 --> 08:29:19.020
A new name, forever, Luna said.

08:29:19.080 --> 08:29:21.840
One we can remember you by and write

08:29:21.840 --> 08:29:24.299
songs about, and weave into tapestries.

08:29:24.360 --> 08:29:26.520
Hmm.

08:29:26.700 --> 08:29:29.759
Said the 5000 year old dragonette.

08:29:29.819 --> 08:29:32.639
You better not put my shriveled corpse

08:29:32.639 --> 08:29:33.959
with a hole in its skull in any

08:29:33.959 --> 08:29:34.560
tapestry.

08:29:34.680 --> 08:29:36.720
Yuck.

08:29:36.779 --> 08:29:38.220
Dusky objected.

08:29:38.279 --> 08:29:42.240
I won't, Luna promised. laughing through

08:29:42.240 --> 08:29:42.599
her tears.

08:29:42.659 --> 08:29:44.759
I'll weave you flying.

08:29:44.819 --> 08:29:47.099
You'll be with all the dragons who gave

08:29:47.099 --> 08:29:47.759
you their memories.

08:29:47.880 --> 08:29:51.540
Your friends, Dusky put in.

08:29:51.599 --> 08:29:53.279
Especially me.

08:29:53.340 --> 08:29:55.139
Can I be in the tapestry?

08:29:55.200 --> 08:29:56.939
He asked Luna.

08:29:57.000 --> 08:29:59.400
Of course, Luna said.

08:29:59.459 --> 08:30:00.540
You'll be together.

08:30:00.599 --> 08:30:01.979
And you'll be free.

08:30:02.040 --> 08:30:05.880
The tiny dragon sighed inside their heads

08:30:05.880 --> 08:30:07.799
long and wistful.

08:30:07.919 --> 08:30:10.860
What do you want to be called?

08:30:10.919 --> 08:30:12.540
Dusky asked.

08:30:12.599 --> 08:30:15.540
I don't know what tribe I was, she

08:30:15.540 --> 08:30:15.900
answered.

08:30:15.959 --> 08:30:18.599
I don't know what kinds of names we had.

08:30:18.659 --> 08:30:20.880
Or what my mother might have called me.

08:30:21.000 --> 08:30:23.700
She paused for a moment.

08:30:23.700 --> 08:30:25.500
Do you think?

08:30:25.919 --> 08:30:28.500
Would freedom be a weird name for a

08:30:28.500 --> 08:30:28.799
dragon?

08:30:28.860 --> 08:30:31.020
Not at all.

08:30:31.080 --> 08:30:32.340
Luna said.

08:30:32.400 --> 08:30:34.979
I like it, Dusky agreed.

08:30:35.040 --> 08:30:36.659
It's what you'll have.

08:30:36.720 --> 08:30:39.479
And also, what you're giving everyone.

08:30:39.540 --> 08:30:42.779
We'll call you freedom from now on.

08:30:42.840 --> 08:30:43.979
Luna said.

08:30:44.040 --> 08:30:45.720
Cool.

08:30:45.779 --> 08:30:47.939
Freedom said quietly.

08:30:48.060 --> 08:30:51.599
Luna reached up and squeezed one of

08:30:51.599 --> 08:30:52.560
Dusky's talons.

08:30:52.619 --> 08:30:55.380
They flew over to the throne, now

08:30:55.380 --> 08:30:57.540
surrounded by crackling dying vines.

08:30:57.599 --> 08:31:00.900
Only the original stem rising from the

08:31:00.900 --> 08:31:02.880
floor was still green and vibrant.

08:31:02.939 --> 08:31:06.060
That, and the new tendril that was trying

08:31:06.060 --> 08:31:07.799
to claw its way back from the severed

08:31:07.799 --> 08:31:08.099
vine.

08:31:08.159 --> 08:31:11.580
Luna set Dusky down on one corner of the

08:31:11.580 --> 08:31:11.939
throne.

08:31:12.000 --> 08:31:14.099
Can I help?

08:31:14.159 --> 08:31:14.819
he asked.

08:31:14.880 --> 08:31:17.880
She touched the top of his tiny head.

08:31:17.939 --> 08:31:19.740
He'd already been through so much.

08:31:19.799 --> 08:31:22.080
Are you sure?

08:31:22.139 --> 08:31:22.860
asked.

08:31:22.979 --> 08:31:24.840
Won't it make you sad?

08:31:24.900 --> 08:31:28.619
I'm already sad, he pointed out.

08:31:28.680 --> 08:31:30.299
This way.

08:31:30.360 --> 08:31:32.040
I'd be helping say goodbye.

08:31:32.099 --> 08:31:36.119
But, She's already dead.

08:31:36.240 --> 08:31:38.759
He said, matter of factly.

08:31:38.819 --> 08:31:42.000
What we're doing is setting her free from

08:31:42.000 --> 08:31:42.479
the plant.

08:31:42.540 --> 08:31:46.439
I suppose that's right, she realized.

08:31:46.500 --> 08:31:48.779
That's the right way to look at it.

08:31:48.840 --> 08:31:53.099
Luna produced more silk, and tied one end

08:31:53.099 --> 08:31:53.819
around his wrist.

08:31:53.939 --> 08:31:56.759
Then she wound the silk around the vine

08:31:56.759 --> 08:31:59.159
and tugged gently on the other side to

08:31:59.159 --> 08:32:00.060
tighten it.

08:32:00.119 --> 08:32:01.380
Thanks for this.

08:32:01.500 --> 08:32:03.599
Freedom said awkwardly.

08:32:03.659 --> 08:32:06.720
And most of all, for the look on

08:32:06.720 --> 08:32:08.520
Cottonmouth's face as he poofed into

08:32:08.520 --> 08:32:08.819
dust.

08:32:08.939 --> 08:32:11.580
It was even better than face melting.

08:32:11.639 --> 08:32:13.139
You're welcome.

08:32:13.200 --> 08:32:14.939
Luna said with a smile.

08:32:15.000 --> 08:32:18.779
And thank you for all your squishy

08:32:18.779 --> 08:32:21.000
ridiculous, cuddle monster memories.

08:32:21.060 --> 08:32:23.220
Freedom said in a rush.

08:32:23.279 --> 08:32:25.439
I guess maybe they weren't so bad.

08:32:25.500 --> 08:32:29.340
If I'd had a real life, it would be maybe

08:32:29.340 --> 08:32:29.819
okay.

08:32:29.880 --> 08:32:31.319
If you 2 were in it.

08:32:31.380 --> 08:32:36.060
Hey, we were in it, Dusky said.

08:32:36.119 --> 08:32:37.740
In your life, I mean.

08:32:37.799 --> 08:32:39.840
Huh.

08:32:39.900 --> 08:32:41.040
Freedom said.

08:32:41.159 --> 08:32:43.259
All right, fine.

08:32:43.319 --> 08:32:44.340
You can be right.

08:32:44.400 --> 08:32:46.139
Just this once.

08:32:46.200 --> 08:32:48.360
Are you ready?

08:32:48.419 --> 08:32:49.560
Luna asked.

08:32:49.619 --> 08:32:53.159
I am, Dusky said, nodding.

08:32:53.279 --> 08:32:55.799
Me too, said freedom.

08:32:55.860 --> 08:32:57.240
Goodbye.

08:32:57.299 --> 08:32:59.700
Thank you, freedom.

08:32:59.819 --> 08:33:01.560
Luna said.

08:33:01.619 --> 08:33:04.500
And then she and Dusky pulled on the silk

08:33:04.500 --> 08:33:07.259
and severed the breath of evil from the

08:33:07.259 --> 08:33:08.700
dragonette who'd saved them.

08:33:08.819 --> 08:33:13.259
Chapter 26.

08:33:13.500 --> 08:33:16.560
Soon after they cut the vine.

08:33:16.619 --> 08:33:19.319
Both of the husks on the throne crumbled

08:33:19.319 --> 08:33:19.799
into dust.

08:33:19.860 --> 08:33:23.340
Luna dug down into the dirt around the

08:33:23.340 --> 08:33:25.860
last original piece of the vine that

08:33:25.860 --> 08:33:27.900
cotton mouth had planted so many

08:33:27.900 --> 08:33:28.680
centuries ago.

08:33:28.740 --> 08:33:32.580
She used her flame silk to burn all the

08:33:32.580 --> 08:33:34.919
roots, which stretched far into the

08:33:34.919 --> 08:33:36.840
ground, like burrowing eels.

08:33:36.900 --> 08:33:40.139
The smoke was green and a little dizzying

08:33:40.139 --> 08:33:42.779
but it dissipated quickly, and there was

08:33:42.779 --> 08:33:44.340
nothing left to reach into their brains

08:33:44.340 --> 08:33:45.119
or take them over.

08:33:45.180 --> 08:33:48.540
All the rest of the vines in the room had

08:33:48.540 --> 08:33:51.060
shriveled up, including the ones blocking

08:33:51.060 --> 08:33:51.479
the door.

08:33:51.540 --> 08:33:55.020
Flying up out of the abyss was much

08:33:55.020 --> 08:33:57.180
harder and more tiring than flying down

08:33:57.180 --> 08:33:59.700
into it, especially with Dusky on her

08:33:59.700 --> 08:34:02.159
back, and the disoriented guardian

08:34:02.159 --> 08:34:03.419
cradled in her talons.

08:34:03.479 --> 08:34:07.200
But Luna was so happy to be flying, so

08:34:07.200 --> 08:34:09.599
happy to be out of that throne room, that

08:34:09.599 --> 08:34:10.919
her wings felt like they could keep

08:34:10.919 --> 08:34:11.580
beating forever.

08:34:11.639 --> 08:34:16.020
At the top of the chasm, she found wren

08:34:16.020 --> 08:34:19.619
axolotl, and sky, with the humans who had

08:34:19.619 --> 08:34:20.639
kidnapped Dusky.

08:34:20.700 --> 08:34:22.619
Muna!

08:34:22.740 --> 08:34:25.319
Sky cried, as she rose over the edge.

08:34:25.380 --> 08:34:28.740
Yes, Ren said triumphantly.

08:34:28.799 --> 08:34:30.479
I told you she'd survive.

08:34:30.540 --> 08:34:32.580
You owe me a turtle.

08:34:32.639 --> 08:34:35.220
Hang on, why did I agree to bed in

08:34:35.220 --> 08:34:35.639
turtles?

08:34:35.700 --> 08:34:37.439
Are you all right?

08:34:37.500 --> 08:34:38.400
Sky asked.

08:34:38.459 --> 08:34:39.779
What happened down there?

08:34:39.840 --> 08:34:45.000
It's a long, long story, Luna said.

08:34:45.060 --> 08:34:48.060
She landed, and gently deposited the

08:34:48.060 --> 08:34:49.439
guardian in front of the other humans.

08:34:49.500 --> 08:34:52.860
He pushed himself to his feet, wobbling.

08:34:52.919 --> 08:34:56.099
The one named Raven, gasped, and grabbed

08:34:56.099 --> 08:34:58.259
her friend's arm, and then they both ran

08:34:58.259 --> 08:35:00.720
forward and caught the gaunt, bedraggled

08:35:00.720 --> 08:35:02.220
human before he could topple over.

08:35:02.279 --> 08:35:04.680
Is he back to normal?

08:35:04.740 --> 08:35:06.479
Luna asked Ren.

08:35:06.540 --> 08:35:09.900
Ren said something to Raven in human, and

08:35:09.900 --> 08:35:11.700
then all the humans had a chatter fest

08:35:11.700 --> 08:35:12.240
for a minute.

08:35:12.299 --> 08:35:15.180
Finally, Ren looked up at Luna, grinning.

08:35:15.299 --> 08:35:17.700
They think so, she said.

08:35:17.759 --> 08:35:20.700
That is, he remembers that his name is

08:35:20.700 --> 08:35:22.919
Vol, and he remembers the guardian

08:35:22.919 --> 08:35:25.799
ceremony, but not much after that, except

08:35:25.799 --> 08:35:27.299
being hungry all the time.

08:35:27.419 --> 08:35:29.279
They hope he'll be all right after a lot

08:35:29.279 --> 08:35:29.700
of rest.

08:35:29.759 --> 08:35:33.779
And a bath, Sky suggested.

08:35:33.840 --> 08:35:35.759
Also, a haircut.

08:35:35.819 --> 08:35:37.799
Maybe several more baths.

08:35:37.860 --> 08:35:41.340
Let's go find Cricket and the others, Luna

08:35:41.340 --> 08:35:41.700
said.

08:35:41.759 --> 08:35:44.700
I think the other mind is gone, but I

08:35:44.700 --> 08:35:45.720
want to make sure they're safe.

08:35:45.779 --> 08:35:50.700
Cricket, Axolotl said, in a near perfect

08:35:50.700 --> 08:35:51.540
dragon accent.

08:35:51.599 --> 08:35:54.000
They padded one of the pouches around

08:35:54.000 --> 08:35:56.819
Sky's neck, which Luna recognized as the

08:35:56.819 --> 08:35:58.259
one with the dragon book in it.

08:35:58.380 --> 08:35:59.819
Book friend.

08:35:59.880 --> 08:36:01.979
Axolotl added with a smile.

08:36:02.040 --> 08:36:06.360
Wow, Luna said to them, impressed, very

08:36:06.360 --> 08:36:06.659
good.

08:36:06.720 --> 08:36:08.700
They pointed to her.

08:36:08.759 --> 08:36:11.400
Luna, fire friend.

08:36:11.520 --> 08:36:15.180
We've been practicing, Ren said proudly.

08:36:15.240 --> 08:36:17.279
You were down there for days, you know.

08:36:17.340 --> 08:36:22.560
I am very, very hungry, Luna realized.

08:36:22.619 --> 08:36:24.060
Me too.

08:36:24.119 --> 08:36:25.919
Dusky chirped from her back.

08:36:25.979 --> 08:36:29.040
We can eat after we find the others.

08:36:29.099 --> 08:36:31.439
Do you know how to get to Lake Scorpion

08:36:31.439 --> 08:36:31.740
from here?

08:36:31.860 --> 08:36:33.659
She asked Ren.

08:36:33.720 --> 08:36:36.959
Ren spoke to the abyss humans again, then

08:36:36.959 --> 08:36:39.659
said, Raven says she'll take us there.

08:36:39.720 --> 08:36:41.880
While Mole gets his brother back to the

08:36:41.880 --> 08:36:42.119
village.

08:36:42.180 --> 08:36:45.419
It was strange for Luna to walk through

08:36:45.419 --> 08:36:47.819
the tunnels, with the sharp faced

08:36:47.819 --> 08:36:49.560
feathered human, listening to her

08:36:49.560 --> 08:36:51.900
murmuring voice and conversation with Ren

08:36:51.900 --> 08:36:52.680
and Axolotl.

08:36:52.740 --> 08:36:55.799
This human kidnapping Dusky was the whole

08:36:55.799 --> 08:36:58.740
reason Luna had wound up in the abyss, but

08:36:58.740 --> 08:37:00.180
Luna couldn't bring herself to be angry

08:37:00.180 --> 08:37:00.900
at Raven.

08:37:00.959 --> 08:37:03.840
On the scale of all the things that

08:37:03.840 --> 08:37:05.759
humans and dragons had done to one

08:37:05.759 --> 08:37:08.220
another over the centuries, it was only

08:37:08.220 --> 08:37:10.080
one small, desperate act.

08:37:10.139 --> 08:37:13.139
And continuing the cycle of fury and

08:37:13.139 --> 08:37:14.939
revenge and punishment.

08:37:15.000 --> 08:37:17.639
That was for other dragons, perhaps, but

08:37:17.639 --> 08:37:18.360
not for Luna.

08:37:18.419 --> 08:37:22.139
At least, that's how she felt, when it

08:37:22.139 --> 08:37:23.459
came to present day humans.

08:37:23.520 --> 08:37:27.900
I'm still angry at Cottonmouth, and Queen

08:37:27.900 --> 08:37:28.500
Wasp.

08:37:28.560 --> 08:37:30.840
They were trying to make the world a

08:37:30.840 --> 08:37:32.880
worse place for their own selfish reasons

08:37:32.880 --> 08:37:35.400
and they hurt a lot of dragons.

08:37:35.459 --> 08:37:38.220
And she didn't know what to think yet

08:37:38.220 --> 08:37:39.180
about the hive wings.

08:37:39.240 --> 08:37:41.580
She had a feeling that would depend on

08:37:41.580 --> 08:37:44.279
what they did next, without malevolent

08:37:44.279 --> 08:37:45.659
voices in their heads.

08:37:45.720 --> 08:37:48.659
The sunlight up ahead was so dazzling

08:37:48.659 --> 08:37:51.599
that Luna was blinking, her eyes watering

08:37:51.599 --> 08:37:53.520
long before they reached the cave

08:37:53.520 --> 08:37:54.659
entrance and stepped outside.

08:37:54.720 --> 08:37:57.959
How many days had they been underground?

08:37:58.020 --> 08:38:00.599
How long had she been trapped in the

08:38:00.599 --> 08:38:01.139
abyss?

08:38:01.200 --> 08:38:02.759
She had no idea.

08:38:02.819 --> 08:38:05.340
But it felt as though years had passed

08:38:05.340 --> 08:38:07.080
since the real sun had warmed her

08:38:07.080 --> 08:38:07.439
scales.

08:38:07.500 --> 08:38:10.799
In the mind space vision, the whisper of

08:38:10.799 --> 08:38:12.599
the trees and the leafy scent of the air

08:38:12.599 --> 08:38:14.040
had seemed real enough.

08:38:14.099 --> 08:38:16.439
But now that she could truly breathe them

08:38:16.439 --> 08:38:17.939
in, it was overwhelming.

08:38:18.000 --> 08:38:21.240
She stood in the sunlight with her eyes

08:38:21.240 --> 08:38:24.240
closed for a moment, letting her senses

08:38:24.240 --> 08:38:27.119
and her internal clock realign, feeling

08:38:27.119 --> 08:38:29.939
her real body really here, and nowhere

08:38:29.939 --> 08:38:30.180
else.

08:38:30.240 --> 08:38:33.900
She felt Sky gallop past her yelling

08:38:33.900 --> 08:38:35.759
Pineapple, Kibli.

08:38:35.880 --> 08:38:38.159
And a hubbub of voices came toward them

08:38:38.159 --> 08:38:39.000
through the trees.

08:38:39.060 --> 08:38:42.000
When she opened her eyes, Cricket was

08:38:42.000 --> 08:38:43.619
standing right in front of her, eyes

08:38:43.619 --> 08:38:44.279
shining.

08:38:44.340 --> 08:38:47.099
The other mind is gone, isn't it?

08:38:47.159 --> 08:38:47.939
Cricket asked.

08:38:48.000 --> 08:38:50.459
You did something amazing, didn't you?

08:38:50.520 --> 08:38:53.520
Not just me, Luna said.

08:38:53.580 --> 08:38:54.900
Everyone helped.

08:38:55.020 --> 08:38:57.599
Cricket impulsively threw her wings

08:38:57.599 --> 08:39:00.240
around Luna, and Luna hugged her back

08:39:00.240 --> 08:39:00.900
smiling.

08:39:00.959 --> 08:39:04.919
For the 1st time, this didn't feel like a

08:39:04.919 --> 08:39:06.419
hive wing, hugging her.

08:39:06.479 --> 08:39:09.060
This was Cricket, who was more than her

08:39:09.060 --> 08:39:11.159
scales and her tribe, just like every

08:39:11.159 --> 08:39:11.639
dragon.

08:39:11.700 --> 08:39:15.779
Sundu interrupted, coming up to join

08:39:15.779 --> 08:39:16.020
them.

08:39:16.080 --> 08:39:19.259
Before we get to the Hug Fest, can

08:39:19.259 --> 08:39:21.659
someone tell me what exactly happened?

08:39:21.720 --> 08:39:23.939
One minute, I was locked in a ferocious

08:39:23.939 --> 08:39:26.220
battle, turning every plant I could reach

08:39:26.220 --> 08:39:28.860
into a fearsome weapon, ready to fight to

08:39:28.860 --> 08:39:29.459
the death.

08:39:29.580 --> 08:39:31.020
And the next minute?

08:39:31.139 --> 08:39:34.139
All my foes suddenly fell over, as though

08:39:34.139 --> 08:39:35.880
their bones had turned into ferns.

08:39:35.939 --> 08:39:39.479
I felt that, Pineapple said.

08:39:39.540 --> 08:39:42.720
It was like, that feeling when you're

08:39:42.720 --> 08:39:45.000
holding up a huge bunch of bananas while

08:39:45.000 --> 08:39:47.639
someone saws them free, and then suddenly

08:39:47.639 --> 08:39:50.340
the last fiber is cut, but you weren't

08:39:50.340 --> 08:39:50.819
paying attention.

08:39:50.880 --> 08:39:53.400
So the whole thing plummets out of your

08:39:53.400 --> 08:39:57.840
talons, and it's like, oops, but wow, you

08:39:57.840 --> 08:39:59.340
feel so much lighter.

08:39:59.400 --> 08:40:01.979
Sad about the bananas, though.

08:40:02.040 --> 08:40:03.419
Hmm.

08:40:03.540 --> 08:40:05.880
Maybe that wasn't the best analogy.

08:40:05.939 --> 08:40:08.759
Did you feel them both go?

08:40:08.819 --> 08:40:10.139
Luna asked.

08:40:10.200 --> 08:40:12.599
Cottonmouth, and then the dragon?

08:40:12.659 --> 08:40:14.340
Yes.

08:40:14.400 --> 08:40:15.720
Pineapple said.

08:40:15.840 --> 08:40:18.180
There was an odd in between time.

08:40:18.240 --> 08:40:21.060
When I felt like I was myself, but still

08:40:21.060 --> 08:40:23.700
sort of tethered, maybe?

08:40:23.759 --> 08:40:27.299
And then I felt her and the plant go, and

08:40:27.299 --> 08:40:28.139
I was all me again.

08:40:28.259 --> 08:40:31.439
Her, Sundu demanded.

08:40:31.500 --> 08:40:32.520
Her who?

08:40:32.580 --> 08:40:35.880
I'll tell you the whole story, Luna

08:40:35.880 --> 08:40:36.240
said.

08:40:36.299 --> 08:40:38.700
Everything that happened in the abyss.

08:40:38.819 --> 08:40:42.119
She glanced up at the sun, now slanting

08:40:42.119 --> 08:40:43.560
down toward the western horizon.

08:40:43.619 --> 08:40:47.279
But, can I tell you on the way to Cicada

08:40:47.279 --> 08:40:47.700
Hive?

08:40:47.759 --> 08:40:50.040
There's someone waiting for me in the

08:40:50.040 --> 08:40:50.700
mosaic garden.

08:40:50.759 --> 08:40:54.900
And when they arrived the next morning

08:40:54.900 --> 08:40:57.779
Sortell was there, he really was.

08:40:57.840 --> 08:41:00.240
He was standing on the hills surrounded

08:41:00.240 --> 08:41:03.479
by violets and sunshine, waiting, as

08:41:03.479 --> 08:41:05.580
though he could wait forever, and would

08:41:05.580 --> 08:41:06.959
wait forever for her.

08:41:07.020 --> 08:41:09.659
And when she swooped in through the open

08:41:09.659 --> 08:41:12.240
sky arches, and soared over everyone's

08:41:12.240 --> 08:41:15.060
heads, and crashed into his arms, he

08:41:15.060 --> 08:41:17.340
laughed, as they fell over and they

08:41:17.340 --> 08:41:19.560
rolled through the grass, and it was real

08:41:19.560 --> 08:41:22.139
he was real at last.

08:41:22.200 --> 08:41:24.659
Are you all right?

08:41:24.720 --> 08:41:26.639
She said, finally, sitting up.

08:41:26.700 --> 08:41:29.400
She lifted his eyelids and studied each

08:41:29.400 --> 08:41:33.299
beautiful dark blue pupil. 100% sore

08:41:33.299 --> 08:41:33.659
tail?

08:41:33.720 --> 08:41:36.840
I was all right, he said.

08:41:36.900 --> 08:41:40.439
And then you squished the honey drops.

08:41:40.500 --> 08:41:44.340
Luna squeaked and jumped back, discovering

08:41:44.340 --> 08:41:46.020
a squashed white box under her tail.

08:41:46.139 --> 08:41:49.680
See, he said self righteously.

08:41:49.740 --> 08:41:52.139
I am not the only one who sits on candy

08:41:52.139 --> 08:41:52.619
around here.

08:41:52.680 --> 08:41:57.540
Ah, you got me honey drops, she said

08:41:57.540 --> 08:41:58.319
beaming.

08:41:58.380 --> 08:42:01.020
She scooted the box aside and snuggled

08:42:01.020 --> 08:42:01.619
under his wings.

08:42:01.740 --> 08:42:05.580
Well, he said, what else do you get for

08:42:05.580 --> 08:42:06.959
the dragon who rescued your brain?

08:42:07.080 --> 08:42:09.240
I don't think they covered this in

08:42:09.240 --> 08:42:10.919
manners and proper behavior class.

08:42:10.979 --> 08:42:14.040
They actually did, she said.

08:42:14.099 --> 08:42:15.299
And you know what's weird?

08:42:15.360 --> 08:42:17.340
The answer is honey drops.

08:42:17.400 --> 08:42:20.400
She reached up and patted his snout while

08:42:20.400 --> 08:42:22.500
he laughed, checking again that he was

08:42:22.500 --> 08:42:22.740
real.

08:42:22.799 --> 08:42:25.319
I missed you so much.

08:42:25.380 --> 08:42:28.380
I missed you more, he said.

08:42:28.439 --> 08:42:30.240
Where's Blue?

08:42:30.360 --> 08:42:30.900
she asked.

08:42:30.959 --> 08:42:34.380
In the webs, with Io and your mom's, he

08:42:34.380 --> 08:42:34.619
said.

08:42:34.680 --> 08:42:37.139
He needs a lot of hugs right now.

08:42:37.200 --> 08:42:40.619
On it, Luna said, jumping up.

08:42:40.680 --> 08:42:44.400
Let's get cricket and go hug the antennae

08:42:44.400 --> 08:42:45.180
off that dragon.

08:42:45.240 --> 08:42:48.240
She sprinted back to the sky arches with

08:42:48.240 --> 08:42:50.819
sore tail behind her. outside.

08:42:50.880 --> 08:42:53.520
Cricket and sky and pineapple were flying

08:42:53.520 --> 08:42:56.220
in a circle, waiting for her, with Wren

08:42:56.220 --> 08:42:58.560
on Skye's back, and axolotl on

08:42:58.560 --> 08:42:59.220
pineapples.

08:42:59.279 --> 08:43:01.979
The other dragons had gone to Wasp Hive

08:43:01.979 --> 08:43:03.900
with Sundew, to make sure someone

08:43:03.900 --> 08:43:06.240
imprisoned Queen Wasp, so she could be

08:43:06.240 --> 08:43:07.020
brought to justice.

08:43:07.139 --> 08:43:11.040
Luna beckoned to her friends and led the

08:43:11.040 --> 08:43:13.680
way back to her home in the sunlit, silk

08:43:13.680 --> 08:43:15.540
spun webs full of rainbow colored

08:43:15.540 --> 08:43:16.139
dragons.

08:43:16.200 --> 08:43:18.360
She hadn't been paying attention before

08:43:18.360 --> 08:43:20.939
but now that she looked, there was a

08:43:20.939 --> 08:43:23.759
weird quiet hanging over everything, the

08:43:23.759 --> 08:43:25.979
dragons she could see looked like they

08:43:25.979 --> 08:43:27.840
had all just come out of their cocoons

08:43:27.840 --> 08:43:31.139
disoriented, startled, and potentially

08:43:31.139 --> 08:43:33.479
thrilled, but in a very confused way.

08:43:33.540 --> 08:43:37.799
In fact, she realized, she hadn't seen

08:43:37.799 --> 08:43:39.180
any hive wings at all yet.

08:43:39.240 --> 08:43:42.060
Sore tail, she asked.

08:43:42.119 --> 08:43:43.860
Where did all the hive wings go?

08:43:43.919 --> 08:43:48.000
Home, he said, deep into the hive.

08:43:48.060 --> 08:43:51.180
When the mind control snapped, some of

08:43:51.180 --> 08:43:53.459
them tried to keep ordering us around, but

08:43:53.459 --> 08:43:55.740
most of them just wanted to go home and

08:43:55.740 --> 08:43:57.959
find their families, and be inside their

08:43:57.959 --> 08:43:59.880
own bodies again, in their own space.

08:43:59.939 --> 08:44:03.240
Wasp had been controlling them since she

08:44:03.240 --> 08:44:05.340
brought them to the snarling river, which

08:44:05.340 --> 08:44:07.500
is much, much longer than she'd ever

08:44:07.500 --> 08:44:08.459
stolen their minds before.

08:44:08.520 --> 08:44:10.439
He hesitated.

08:44:10.500 --> 08:44:13.680
I still think they're the worst, and if

08:44:13.680 --> 08:44:15.959
it were up to me, I take every hive wing

08:44:15.959 --> 08:44:18.299
soldier, and merchant, and teacher, and

08:44:18.299 --> 08:44:21.000
snob who was mean to us, and put them on

08:44:21.000 --> 08:44:22.200
misbehavior's way for a year.

08:44:22.319 --> 08:44:25.200
But after having someone in my own head

08:44:25.200 --> 08:44:28.319
like that, I mean, it was pretty

08:44:28.319 --> 08:44:28.919
terrible.

08:44:28.979 --> 08:44:32.159
He looked up at the pale sprays of cloud

08:44:32.159 --> 08:44:34.500
feathered across the sky, then back at

08:44:34.500 --> 08:44:37.919
her, adding quickly, But they still could

08:44:37.919 --> 08:44:39.599
have done something to try and be better

08:44:39.599 --> 08:44:40.439
dragons.

08:44:40.500 --> 08:44:43.439
Like, maybe they could have noticed that

08:44:43.439 --> 08:44:45.360
Queen Wasp was an evil dictator.

08:44:45.419 --> 08:44:47.279
And certainly they could have treated

08:44:47.279 --> 08:44:49.619
silk wings like equal dragons, and

08:44:49.619 --> 08:44:51.000
generally not been jerks.

08:44:51.119 --> 08:44:54.119
So, my go back and forth a bit.

08:44:54.180 --> 08:44:58.319
My brain words, Luna said ruefully.

08:44:58.380 --> 08:45:00.119
He laughed.

08:45:00.180 --> 08:45:01.439
Words of my head.

08:45:01.560 --> 08:45:04.259
I have no idea what's going to happen

08:45:04.259 --> 08:45:07.259
with the hive wings, she said, brushing

08:45:07.259 --> 08:45:08.340
one of his wings with hers.

08:45:08.400 --> 08:45:11.159
But let's do what we can do for right now

08:45:11.159 --> 08:45:12.959
which is take care of Blue.

08:45:13.080 --> 08:45:16.860
She glanced around, and saw Cricket

08:45:16.860 --> 08:45:19.080
hanging back shyly as they approached

08:45:19.080 --> 08:45:19.860
Luna's home.

08:45:19.919 --> 08:45:22.860
Luna wondered if Blue had had a chance to

08:45:22.860 --> 08:45:24.599
tell their moms about the hive wing who

08:45:24.599 --> 08:45:24.959
loved him.

08:45:25.020 --> 08:45:30.299
Burnett, Silverspot, and Io all stood up

08:45:30.299 --> 08:45:31.560
bristling, when they saw her.

08:45:31.619 --> 08:45:34.319
But Luna took one of Cricket's talons in

08:45:34.319 --> 08:45:36.419
hers, and guided her into the silken

08:45:36.419 --> 08:45:36.659
cell.

08:45:36.779 --> 08:45:39.840
Hello all, she said.

08:45:39.900 --> 08:45:41.340
This is Cricket.

08:45:41.400 --> 08:45:43.080
She's part of our family now.

08:45:43.139 --> 08:45:47.040
And then her moms saw the look on Blue's

08:45:47.040 --> 08:45:50.279
face as he saw Cricket, and Luna knew it

08:45:50.279 --> 08:45:51.119
was going to be all right.

08:45:51.180 --> 08:45:54.360
It might take them a moment, the way it

08:45:54.360 --> 08:45:56.939
had taken her a moment, but if Blue loved

08:45:56.939 --> 08:45:59.459
her and Luna trusted her, soon, they

08:45:59.459 --> 08:45:59.939
would too.

08:46:00.000 --> 08:46:03.900
She did not even mind that cricket got to

08:46:03.900 --> 08:46:05.220
wrap her wings around him first.

08:46:05.279 --> 08:46:06.720
That was fine.

08:46:06.779 --> 08:46:09.840
Because her wings fit over crickets, and

08:46:09.840 --> 08:46:12.180
sore tails could go around hers, and they

08:46:12.180 --> 08:46:13.740
were together, and safe.

08:46:13.799 --> 08:46:17.459
Finally, finally, finally.

08:46:17.520 --> 08:46:19.860
Luna knew.

08:46:19.979 --> 08:46:21.720
They had only started to change the

08:46:21.720 --> 08:46:21.959
world.

08:46:22.020 --> 08:46:24.119
There was still a lot to do.

08:46:24.180 --> 08:46:26.340
A lot of dragons who needed help.

08:46:26.400 --> 08:46:30.240
Dragons who needed homes, and dragons who

08:46:30.240 --> 08:46:31.979
needed a new way of looking at the world

08:46:31.979 --> 08:46:33.959
which would be the hardest thing of all.

08:46:34.080 --> 08:46:36.900
But she didn't have to do it by herself.

08:46:36.959 --> 08:46:39.959
She didn't have to be the one great and

08:46:39.959 --> 08:46:42.479
mighty and wonderful flame silk, who set

08:46:42.479 --> 08:46:45.419
the world on fire, and saved everyone, and

08:46:45.419 --> 08:46:47.220
fixed everything all alone.

08:46:47.279 --> 08:46:50.340
And she also didn't have to be the sad

08:46:50.340 --> 08:46:53.040
lost dragon who sat and waited to be

08:46:53.040 --> 08:46:53.400
rescued.

08:46:53.459 --> 08:46:56.220
She only had to be herself.

08:46:56.279 --> 08:46:57.720
Luna.

08:46:57.779 --> 08:47:01.200
Talon in talon with blue and cricket, and

08:47:01.200 --> 08:47:03.779
sore tail, and sundew, and all the

08:47:03.779 --> 08:47:06.419
dragons of the distant kingdoms, and

08:47:06.419 --> 08:47:07.439
hopefully the humans too.

08:47:07.500 --> 08:47:11.580
If each of them tried, even a little bit

08:47:11.580 --> 08:47:14.099
to make the world even a little better

08:47:14.099 --> 08:47:16.439
then maybe there was hope.

08:47:16.500 --> 08:47:19.680
And maybe, things could change.

08:47:19.740 --> 08:47:24.180
Epilogue.

08:47:24.240 --> 08:47:27.599
The sky was full of dragons.

08:47:27.659 --> 08:47:31.259
Luna had made six weavings and was

08:47:31.259 --> 08:47:33.540
halfway through a seventh, but she still

08:47:33.540 --> 08:47:35.040
hadn't managed to capture quite how

08:47:35.040 --> 08:47:37.680
breathtaking it was to see so many colors

08:47:37.680 --> 08:47:40.860
and so many wing shapes, diving and

08:47:40.860 --> 08:47:41.400
soaring together.

08:47:41.459 --> 08:47:44.340
The more visitors flew over from the

08:47:44.340 --> 08:47:46.619
distant kingdoms, the more complicated

08:47:46.619 --> 08:47:47.639
her tapestries got.

08:47:47.700 --> 08:47:51.119
Maybe I don't have the sky color quite

08:47:51.119 --> 08:47:54.659
right yet. she said, holding up her claws

08:47:54.659 --> 08:47:56.639
to frame a piece of the feathery clouds.

08:47:56.759 --> 08:47:59.220
The rain had stopped not long ago.

08:47:59.279 --> 08:48:01.619
And the air felt like wading through

08:48:01.619 --> 08:48:05.220
sunshine, liquid and gold up close, and

08:48:05.220 --> 08:48:07.919
lined with dark gray in the distance, and

08:48:07.919 --> 08:48:10.020
completely impossible to capture in

08:48:10.020 --> 08:48:10.319
silk.

08:48:10.439 --> 08:48:13.319
Or maybe I'll never figure out how to

08:48:13.319 --> 08:48:15.000
convey motion in a tapestry.

08:48:15.060 --> 08:48:17.580
Like pinning down a dragonfly or a

08:48:17.580 --> 08:48:18.240
firefly.

08:48:18.299 --> 08:48:20.159
It's not the same if they're not moving.

08:48:20.220 --> 08:48:23.639
I think your weavings are perfect

08:48:23.639 --> 08:48:25.919
Swordell said contentedly.

08:48:25.979 --> 08:48:30.119
And look at that rainbow, Luna said with

08:48:30.119 --> 08:48:30.779
disgust.

08:48:30.840 --> 08:48:33.419
Nobody would believe it, if I put a

08:48:33.419 --> 08:48:35.340
rainbow that pretty into my tapestry.

08:48:35.400 --> 08:48:38.459
Everyone would be like, oh, sure, Luna.

08:48:38.520 --> 08:48:40.500
I just bet there was also a perfect

08:48:40.500 --> 08:48:42.659
rainbow, and your perfect scene of

08:48:42.659 --> 08:48:44.700
dragons from different tribes getting to

08:48:44.700 --> 08:48:45.119
know each other.

08:48:45.180 --> 08:48:47.580
Very subtle metaphor.

08:48:47.639 --> 08:48:48.240
Well done.

08:48:48.360 --> 08:48:51.599
You could do a tapestry of the silkwing

08:48:51.599 --> 08:48:53.880
assembly, trying to get anything done

08:48:53.880 --> 08:48:55.259
Sortell suggested.

08:48:55.319 --> 08:48:58.380
If you're looking for a less perfect

08:48:58.380 --> 08:48:58.799
scene.

08:48:58.919 --> 08:49:00.900
Ah!

08:49:00.959 --> 08:49:04.020
I love them, but oh my goodness, Luna

08:49:04.020 --> 08:49:04.380
said.

08:49:04.439 --> 08:49:06.779
Oh, sorry.

08:49:06.840 --> 08:49:08.279
Did you have something to say?

08:49:08.340 --> 08:49:12.180
Sortell struck a pose, imitating the silk

08:49:12.180 --> 08:49:13.680
wings had been chosen for the assembly.

08:49:13.740 --> 08:49:16.860
No, no, please, you go ahead.

08:49:16.919 --> 08:49:18.900
Wait, maybe she had an idea?

08:49:18.959 --> 08:49:21.419
Oh, no, I'm sure he was about to speak.

08:49:21.479 --> 08:49:24.659
These are all great suggestions, everybody

08:49:24.659 --> 08:49:25.319
really great.

08:49:25.380 --> 08:49:27.540
Someday, eventually.

08:49:27.599 --> 08:49:29.700
We'll get around to potentially doing

08:49:29.700 --> 08:49:30.900
something about some of them.

08:49:30.959 --> 08:49:32.580
Break for lunch.

08:49:32.700 --> 08:49:34.740
Luna laughed.

08:49:34.799 --> 08:49:36.779
They're lovely, she said.

08:49:36.840 --> 08:49:38.099
They'll figure it out.

08:49:38.159 --> 08:49:40.500
We haven't had a silk wing in charge of

08:49:40.500 --> 08:49:41.939
anything in a really long time.

08:49:42.060 --> 08:49:45.299
And wasp left no descendants from Queen

08:49:45.299 --> 08:49:46.080
Monarch.

08:49:46.139 --> 08:49:48.419
So I think this is a good compromise.

08:49:48.479 --> 08:49:53.459
I think perhaps 200 silk wings in one

08:49:53.459 --> 08:49:56.220
governing body is a few too many.

08:49:56.279 --> 08:49:59.279
Swortell said, rolling his eyes

08:49:59.279 --> 08:50:01.560
especially when Morpho is one of them.

08:50:01.680 --> 08:50:05.099
Io and Tal will sort them out, Luna

08:50:05.099 --> 08:50:05.520
said.

08:50:05.580 --> 08:50:07.740
At least we're not in the mess the hive

08:50:07.740 --> 08:50:08.220
wings are in.

08:50:08.340 --> 08:50:12.479
Wasp was imprisoned in her own Flame Silk

08:50:12.479 --> 08:50:14.639
Cavern, along with all of her sisters.

08:50:14.700 --> 08:50:18.419
Lady Jewel was nominally now queen Jewel

08:50:18.419 --> 08:50:20.459
of the hive wings, but there was a lot of

08:50:20.459 --> 08:50:22.439
rumbling and grumbling and several

08:50:22.439 --> 08:50:24.000
disgruntled factions in the tribe.

08:50:24.060 --> 08:50:27.479
Some hive wings wanted to get far away

08:50:27.479 --> 08:50:29.939
from the hives, and any reminder of what

08:50:29.939 --> 08:50:33.060
wasp had done to them, one, named Tree

08:50:33.060 --> 08:50:36.060
Hopper, had immediately come to find Tao

08:50:36.060 --> 08:50:37.500
and never left.

08:50:37.560 --> 08:50:39.000
Another was Hawker.

08:50:39.060 --> 08:50:41.520
One of the checkpoint soldiers, Luna

08:50:41.520 --> 08:50:43.919
remembered from Cicada Hive, and to

08:50:43.919 --> 08:50:46.799
Luna's surprise and cricket's delight, the

08:50:46.799 --> 08:50:49.560
one they'd rescued on the island, Earwig

08:50:49.560 --> 08:50:51.180
had defected from the hive wings too.

08:50:51.240 --> 08:50:53.759
She'd appeared in the new Silkwing

08:50:53.759 --> 08:50:55.919
encampments, looking for the dragons who

08:50:55.919 --> 08:50:57.060
had left her the map to get home.

08:50:57.119 --> 08:50:59.040
See?

08:50:59.099 --> 08:51:02.099
Cricket had said to Sundo triumphantly, it

08:51:02.099 --> 08:51:03.000
was the right thing to do.

08:51:03.119 --> 08:51:06.060
But not all dragons felt that way.

08:51:06.119 --> 08:51:09.119
There were rather horrifying amount of

08:51:09.119 --> 08:51:12.119
hive wings who wanted Queen Wasp back

08:51:12.119 --> 08:51:14.880
mind control and all, which was the most

08:51:14.880 --> 08:51:16.860
mystifying thing Luna had ever heard.

08:51:16.919 --> 08:51:20.159
She was glad there were other dragons

08:51:20.159 --> 08:51:23.759
leaf wings, mostly, like Belladonna, who

08:51:23.759 --> 08:51:25.080
were happy to grapple with that problem.

08:51:25.139 --> 08:51:28.200
I was sort of hoping we'd fixed

08:51:28.200 --> 08:51:30.419
everything, Luna said to Swordtail.

08:51:30.479 --> 08:51:32.459
We defeated the big bad guy.

08:51:32.520 --> 08:51:35.040
Whoosh, all better, right?

08:51:35.099 --> 08:51:38.520
So why are there still more problems and

08:51:38.520 --> 08:51:39.180
things to fix?

08:51:39.240 --> 08:51:40.560
I don't like it.

08:51:40.619 --> 08:51:42.299
Yeah.

08:51:42.360 --> 08:51:45.180
Sortell said, and they're woobly

08:51:45.180 --> 08:51:45.720
problems.

08:51:45.779 --> 08:51:47.759
All complicated and stuff.

08:51:47.819 --> 08:51:50.700
Blur to you problems, I say.

08:51:50.759 --> 08:51:53.939
I don't know how you reach dragons like

08:51:53.939 --> 08:51:55.740
those hive wings, Luna said.

08:51:55.799 --> 08:51:59.040
Like, how do you help dragons save

08:51:59.040 --> 08:52:01.560
themselves, or teach them to care about

08:52:01.560 --> 08:52:04.139
other dragons, especially ones who don't

08:52:04.139 --> 08:52:04.560
look like them?

08:52:04.619 --> 08:52:07.560
It feels completely impossible.

08:52:07.619 --> 08:52:11.340
She sighed, and Sortell brushed her wing

08:52:11.340 --> 08:52:11.639
with his.

08:52:11.700 --> 08:52:14.580
You know what makes me feel better?

08:52:14.580 --> 08:52:15.240
he said.

08:52:15.299 --> 08:52:18.060
Thinking about the good dragons instead

08:52:18.060 --> 08:52:18.659
of the bad ones.

08:52:18.720 --> 08:52:21.959
I focus on how many dragons are out there

08:52:21.959 --> 08:52:24.060
trying to make the world better instead

08:52:24.060 --> 08:52:25.020
of worse.

08:52:25.080 --> 08:52:25.979
It's not only us.

08:52:26.040 --> 08:52:28.500
Lots of other dragons are trying to fix

08:52:28.500 --> 08:52:29.639
things too, right?

08:52:29.700 --> 08:52:33.060
We all keep going and keep trying and

08:52:33.060 --> 08:52:34.080
keep fixing what we can.

08:52:34.139 --> 08:52:37.259
And if you're tired or sad or need a

08:52:37.259 --> 08:52:38.400
break, that's okay.

08:52:38.459 --> 08:52:40.619
Because it's not all on you.

08:52:40.680 --> 08:52:43.619
There's lots of us doing this together.

08:52:43.680 --> 08:52:47.040
Luna rubbed her eyes and looked up at

08:52:47.040 --> 08:52:47.279
him.

08:52:47.340 --> 08:52:49.799
I get sad sometimes.

08:52:49.860 --> 08:52:51.959
She admitted quietly.

08:52:52.020 --> 08:52:55.740
I know, he said, putting his wing around

08:52:55.740 --> 08:52:55.979
her.

08:52:56.040 --> 08:52:58.619
And when you do, you can tell me.

08:52:58.740 --> 08:53:02.099
She nodded and took a deep breath.

08:53:02.220 --> 08:53:04.979
Most of the time, she was all right.

08:53:05.040 --> 08:53:06.720
Most of the time.

08:53:06.779 --> 08:53:09.240
She could think about her art and the

08:53:09.240 --> 08:53:11.520
dragons she loved, and the sadness would

08:53:11.520 --> 08:53:11.819
lift.

08:53:11.880 --> 08:53:14.279
But sometimes it still found her.

08:53:14.340 --> 08:53:17.639
Sometimes, especially when she thought

08:53:17.639 --> 08:53:19.979
about the hive wings, and how there were

08:53:19.979 --> 08:53:22.139
still so many dragons who didn't care

08:53:22.139 --> 08:53:22.919
about hurting others.

08:53:22.979 --> 08:53:26.220
I kind of wish we could do the same thing

08:53:26.220 --> 08:53:28.500
for them that we did for freedom, she

08:53:28.500 --> 08:53:28.740
said.

08:53:28.799 --> 08:53:31.799
I wish we could link them to our memories

08:53:31.799 --> 08:53:33.900
and let them feel what it's like to be

08:53:33.900 --> 08:53:36.240
someone else for a little while, or show

08:53:36.240 --> 08:53:38.099
them that what we're trying to build is a

08:53:38.099 --> 08:53:40.500
better world for everyone, not just us.

08:53:40.560 --> 08:53:43.439
Sortell bummed her side.

08:53:43.500 --> 08:53:46.500
That's what your weavings are for, he

08:53:46.500 --> 08:53:46.740
said.

08:53:46.799 --> 08:53:49.860
And those stories, cricket and blue, have

08:53:49.860 --> 08:53:50.400
talked about writing.

08:53:50.459 --> 08:53:53.580
He reached into the bag around his neck

08:53:53.580 --> 08:53:55.500
and pulled out the rolled up weaving

08:53:55.500 --> 08:53:56.580
she'd brought for sundew.

08:53:56.700 --> 08:53:59.939
It was one of Luna's visions for the Leaf

08:53:59.939 --> 08:54:02.939
Silk Kingdom, a vast forest of trees

08:54:02.939 --> 08:54:04.560
covering the southern half of the

08:54:04.560 --> 08:54:07.860
continent, with webs of silk and hammocks

08:54:07.860 --> 08:54:10.080
and tree houses, all connected together.

08:54:10.139 --> 08:54:12.900
It looked a little bit like the rain wing

08:54:12.900 --> 08:54:13.200
home.

08:54:13.259 --> 08:54:15.540
But here, half the dragons were green

08:54:15.540 --> 08:54:17.759
with leaf shaped wings, and there were

08:54:17.759 --> 08:54:19.919
gardens in the clearings, and galleries

08:54:19.919 --> 08:54:22.139
full of silk tapestries, and a library

08:54:22.139 --> 08:54:24.119
full of books that told the truth.

08:54:24.180 --> 08:54:27.419
Sortell unrolled it and spread it on the

08:54:27.419 --> 08:54:28.500
grass, smiling.

08:54:28.619 --> 08:54:32.520
You looked at it 5 minutes ago, Luna said

08:54:32.520 --> 08:54:32.939
with a laugh.

08:54:33.000 --> 08:54:35.220
I know, he said.

08:54:35.279 --> 08:54:36.840
Looking at it makes me happy.

08:54:36.900 --> 08:54:39.540
I mean, who doesn't want to live in this

08:54:39.540 --> 08:54:39.659
world?

08:54:39.779 --> 08:54:43.799
Oh, Luna cried. clutching his arm.

08:54:43.860 --> 08:54:45.000
Here they come.

08:54:45.060 --> 08:54:45.840
Here they come.

08:54:45.900 --> 08:54:50.040
Cerulean blue and orange gold black wings

08:54:50.040 --> 08:54:51.180
were descending from the sky.

08:54:51.240 --> 08:54:53.819
The sunlight reflected brightly off

08:54:53.819 --> 08:54:54.840
Cricket's glasses.

08:54:54.900 --> 08:54:57.840
Luna waved at them, as Soritail rolled

08:54:57.840 --> 08:54:59.700
the weaving back up again, and Blue

08:54:59.700 --> 08:55:00.659
veered toward her.

08:55:00.720 --> 08:55:03.900
From Cricket's shoulder, Axolotl waved

08:55:03.900 --> 08:55:04.080
back.

08:55:04.139 --> 08:55:06.959
Did we get here before sundew?

08:55:07.080 --> 08:55:07.919
Cricket called.

08:55:08.040 --> 08:55:09.360
Nope.

08:55:09.419 --> 08:55:12.240
Sundew said cheerfully, bounding up next

08:55:12.240 --> 08:55:13.860
to Luna with Willow beside her.

08:55:13.919 --> 08:55:16.080
She grinned at Blue and Cricket as they

08:55:16.080 --> 08:55:16.319
landed.

08:55:16.439 --> 08:55:19.020
Her smile wavered a bit at the dragons

08:55:19.020 --> 08:55:21.000
right behind them, but everyone had

08:55:21.000 --> 08:55:22.979
already awkwardly met Cricket's parents.

08:55:23.040 --> 08:55:24.959
Katy did, and Malachite.

08:55:25.020 --> 08:55:28.560
Luna had told them how Malachite tried to

08:55:28.560 --> 08:55:30.959
help Kibli, tsunami, and pineapple in

08:55:30.959 --> 08:55:33.540
Wasp Hive, and they'd also heard the

08:55:33.540 --> 08:55:35.520
story of how Malachite had been taken

08:55:35.520 --> 08:55:38.340
away by Queen Wasp when she realized Lady

08:55:38.340 --> 08:55:39.540
Scarab cared about him.

08:55:39.599 --> 08:55:42.659
He was one of the hive wings who hadn't

08:55:42.659 --> 08:55:44.220
been in control of his own body for many

08:55:44.220 --> 08:55:47.880
years, him, and the librarian, and a few

08:55:47.880 --> 08:55:48.240
others.

08:55:48.240 --> 08:55:50.759
Most of them were among those who'd come

08:55:50.759 --> 08:55:52.919
to seek refuge in the Leaf Silk Kingdom.

08:55:52.979 --> 08:55:55.740
It's so beautiful from up there.

08:55:55.860 --> 08:55:58.619
Blue said to Sundew, his eyes shining.

08:55:58.680 --> 08:56:02.040
It's like a huge dragon spread green

08:56:02.040 --> 08:56:04.139
wings all across the dragon tail

08:56:04.139 --> 08:56:04.619
peninsula.

08:56:04.680 --> 08:56:07.080
I can't believe how many more trees there

08:56:07.080 --> 08:56:07.740
are already.

08:56:07.799 --> 08:56:09.419
We were only gone a few days.

08:56:09.479 --> 08:56:12.720
She might tell you that's the magic of

08:56:12.720 --> 08:56:15.599
leaf speak, Willow said, but the tree

08:56:15.599 --> 08:56:17.700
magician will be whoever can get her to

08:56:17.700 --> 08:56:19.799
stop and actually eat something once in a

08:56:19.799 --> 08:56:19.979
while.

08:56:20.040 --> 08:56:23.580
She twined her tail around sundews and

08:56:23.580 --> 08:56:25.080
released Bumblebee into the grass.

08:56:25.139 --> 08:56:28.799
The little hive wing bounded over to hug

08:56:28.799 --> 08:56:31.020
Cricket's leg, her wings vibrating

08:56:31.020 --> 08:56:31.439
happily.

08:56:31.500 --> 08:56:34.259
Axolotl slid down beside her.

08:56:34.319 --> 08:56:36.779
Patted bumblebee's head and gave her a

08:56:36.779 --> 08:56:38.459
carrot to gnaw on.

08:56:38.520 --> 08:56:40.500
The human was staying with cricket for a

08:56:40.500 --> 08:56:43.020
while, to keep studying dragon, and they

08:56:43.020 --> 08:56:44.759
had found the way straight to Bumblebee's

08:56:44.759 --> 08:56:45.419
heart very quickly.

08:56:45.479 --> 08:56:49.919
I eat all the time, Sundu protested.

08:56:49.979 --> 08:56:51.240
I ate a...

08:56:51.240 --> 08:56:54.000
Something, this morning, while we were

08:56:54.000 --> 08:56:56.279
sorting pyrean tree seedlings, didn't I?

08:56:56.400 --> 08:56:57.540
I think I did.

08:56:57.659 --> 08:57:00.479
The seedlings were very noisy, full of

08:57:00.479 --> 08:57:00.900
questions.

08:57:00.959 --> 08:57:03.360
It must be weird to fly across an ocean

08:57:03.360 --> 08:57:04.200
when you're a tree.

08:57:04.200 --> 08:57:06.659
Not a common tree experience, I suspect.

08:57:06.779 --> 08:57:09.779
If you're talking about that talent full

08:57:09.779 --> 08:57:11.759
of cashews, that does not count.

08:57:11.880 --> 08:57:13.259
Willow said.

08:57:13.319 --> 08:57:16.740
Does my cashews.

08:57:16.919 --> 08:57:18.540
Bumblebee announced grumbly.

08:57:18.599 --> 08:57:21.419
Snoodoo in big to a bubble.

08:57:21.479 --> 08:57:24.659
Well, we're having a big feast after this

08:57:24.659 --> 08:57:24.840
right?

08:57:24.900 --> 08:57:26.639
Swordell interjected.

08:57:26.700 --> 08:57:29.040
I was promised a tree planting party.

08:57:29.099 --> 08:57:31.259
Uh, yeah.

08:57:31.319 --> 08:57:32.700
Willow said.

08:57:32.759 --> 08:57:36.060
Sunday's idea of a tree planting party is

08:57:36.060 --> 08:57:38.220
one where we plant trees all day, and

08:57:38.220 --> 08:57:40.680
then look at them and go, well done, us.

08:57:40.740 --> 08:57:42.720
Good night, trees, and that's it.

08:57:42.779 --> 08:57:44.520
That's the whole party.

08:57:44.639 --> 08:57:48.419
Sortell looked outraged, and so did

08:57:48.419 --> 08:57:49.080
Bumblebee.

08:57:49.200 --> 08:57:51.599
Although that was bumblebee's normal face

08:57:51.599 --> 08:57:52.259
much of the time.

08:57:52.319 --> 08:57:54.900
So it was hard to tell how much this

08:57:54.900 --> 08:57:57.240
concept of a party was specifically

08:57:57.240 --> 08:57:57.840
offending her.

08:57:57.900 --> 08:58:01.979
No, no, no, Swartail said.

08:58:02.040 --> 08:58:05.459
A tree planting party is, we plant one

08:58:05.459 --> 08:58:08.279
tree, and then we eat, and dance, and

08:58:08.279 --> 08:58:10.380
flop around, and eat some more, and

08:58:10.380 --> 08:58:12.299
ideally, place charades.

08:58:12.419 --> 08:58:16.439
Turns out Swordtail is weirdly great at

08:58:16.439 --> 08:58:18.299
charades, Luna said.

08:58:18.360 --> 08:58:19.680
This is a new discovery.

08:58:19.740 --> 08:58:21.360
Kibli's fault.

08:58:21.419 --> 08:58:22.680
It may not surprise you to hear.

08:58:22.740 --> 08:58:26.340
Charades are my secret superpower.

08:58:26.459 --> 08:58:29.819
Soratel said, fluffing out his wings.

08:58:29.880 --> 08:58:32.279
Just wait until it's my turn to save the

08:58:32.279 --> 08:58:32.459
world.

08:58:32.580 --> 08:58:35.819
If anyone can save the world with

08:58:35.819 --> 08:58:37.799
charades, it's you.

08:58:37.860 --> 08:58:39.720
Blue said loyally.

08:58:39.779 --> 08:58:42.000
Yes, Luna said.

08:58:42.119 --> 08:58:44.880
When the bad guys get so frustrated

08:58:44.880 --> 08:58:46.919
because you refuse to tell him what

08:58:46.919 --> 08:58:49.200
you're acting out, and the charades never

08:58:49.200 --> 08:58:51.479
end, so he can never enact his evil

08:58:51.479 --> 08:58:51.720
plan.

08:58:51.779 --> 08:58:55.560
I think this party can find some happy

08:58:55.560 --> 08:58:58.200
medium. between planting trees all day

08:58:58.200 --> 08:58:59.880
and infinite charades.

08:58:59.939 --> 08:59:01.619
Willow said with a laugh.

08:59:01.740 --> 08:59:03.479
Did you bring it?

08:59:03.540 --> 08:59:04.919
Can I meet it?

08:59:05.040 --> 08:59:06.900
Sundew asked cricket.

08:59:06.959 --> 08:59:09.659
Cricket's wings shimmered as she reached

08:59:09.659 --> 08:59:10.919
into the large basket.

08:59:10.979 --> 08:59:12.599
Her parents had been carrying between

08:59:12.599 --> 08:59:12.840
them.

08:59:12.959 --> 08:59:16.020
She gently lifted out a ball of roots and

08:59:16.020 --> 08:59:18.540
dirt, out of which grew a tiny, perfect

08:59:18.540 --> 08:59:19.560
tree.

08:59:19.799 --> 08:59:22.979
Tree, Axolotl said with delight.

08:59:23.040 --> 08:59:25.740
Book friend, tree, friend.

08:59:25.799 --> 08:59:28.979
They pointed to Cricket, and then Sundo.

08:59:29.040 --> 08:59:31.439
Bumblebee bonked their hand with their

08:59:31.439 --> 08:59:33.360
snout, and Axolotto laughed.

08:59:33.419 --> 08:59:35.159
Loud friend.

08:59:35.279 --> 08:59:39.000
I can't believe my tree survived while I

08:59:39.000 --> 08:59:40.439
was away, Cricket said.

08:59:40.500 --> 08:59:42.959
I wonder if someone at school was

08:59:42.959 --> 08:59:44.759
secretly watering my terrarium for me.

08:59:44.819 --> 08:59:46.619
Wouldn't that be kind?

08:59:46.680 --> 08:59:48.900
I was so happy to see it again.

08:59:48.959 --> 08:59:50.459
I hope it's all right.

08:59:50.520 --> 08:59:51.959
Can you tell if it's all right?

08:59:52.020 --> 08:59:54.720
I tried to explain to it that it was

08:59:54.720 --> 08:59:56.340
going to a place where it could grow big

08:59:56.340 --> 08:59:58.560
and strong and free in the sunshine.

08:59:58.619 --> 09:00:01.799
I'll let it know, Sundew said.

09:00:01.860 --> 09:00:04.080
Taking the ball of dirt into her talons.

09:00:04.200 --> 09:00:07.139
She touched her snout to the top of the

09:00:07.139 --> 09:00:09.659
miniature leaves and closed her eyes.

09:00:09.720 --> 09:00:12.779
It's a ficus, she whispered.

09:00:12.840 --> 09:00:16.619
It says hello, more or less, in like, a

09:00:16.619 --> 09:00:17.639
tree way, you know.

09:00:17.700 --> 09:00:20.759
It also says, thank you, cricket, for

09:00:20.759 --> 09:00:21.479
keeping it alive.

09:00:21.540 --> 09:00:24.659
I mean, I'm translating, but that's

09:00:24.659 --> 09:00:25.500
essentially what it's saying.

09:00:25.560 --> 09:00:28.500
Would you like to grow bigger, little

09:00:28.500 --> 09:00:28.979
tree?

09:00:29.099 --> 09:00:32.220
She listened for a moment, then nodded.

09:00:32.279 --> 09:00:34.799
All right, let's see.

09:00:34.860 --> 09:00:38.639
Sundu carried the tree over to the hole

09:00:38.639 --> 09:00:40.560
Luna and Sortell had helped to dig

09:00:40.560 --> 09:00:40.979
earlier.

09:00:41.040 --> 09:00:43.860
She tucked the ball of rude sin.

09:00:43.919 --> 09:00:45.959
Like it was a baby dragonette.

09:00:46.020 --> 09:00:49.740
Well, an agreeable baby dragonette, like

09:00:49.740 --> 09:00:50.400
Dusky.

09:00:50.520 --> 09:00:53.040
Not the shrieking hurricane of fury that

09:00:53.040 --> 09:00:55.080
Bumblebee turned into most bedtime.

09:00:55.080 --> 09:00:58.020
She's better when they have sleepovers.

09:00:58.080 --> 09:01:01.259
Luna reminded herself, glancing at the

09:01:01.259 --> 09:01:03.599
little hive wing, who was watching Sundo

09:01:03.599 --> 09:01:04.080
with awe.

09:01:04.139 --> 09:01:07.139
And Dusky loves her fierceness.

09:01:07.259 --> 09:01:09.959
They had found Desky's mother.

09:01:10.020 --> 09:01:13.319
The sweetest dark blue dragon, who had

09:01:13.319 --> 09:01:15.840
cried and cried when she finally got to

09:01:15.840 --> 09:01:17.580
hug her dragonette for the 1st time.

09:01:17.639 --> 09:01:20.520
Luna wasn't worried about him anymore.

09:01:20.580 --> 09:01:23.159
He'd have all the hugs he could possibly

09:01:23.159 --> 09:01:25.919
want, and Luna was close by if he needed

09:01:25.919 --> 09:01:26.459
more.

09:01:26.520 --> 09:01:29.939
Sundew covered the roots, and buried her

09:01:29.939 --> 09:01:30.779
claws in the dirt.

09:01:30.840 --> 09:01:34.139
A few moments later, the trees, leaves

09:01:34.139 --> 09:01:36.540
quivered, then started to stretch

09:01:36.540 --> 09:01:38.040
reaching for the sun.

09:01:38.099 --> 09:01:40.860
The branches spread, and the trunk

09:01:40.860 --> 09:01:42.000
widened as it grew.

09:01:42.119 --> 09:01:46.020
Cricket's parents, and axolotl let out

09:01:46.020 --> 09:01:48.540
matching gasps, and Cricket clapped her

09:01:48.540 --> 09:01:49.680
talons together with delight.

09:01:49.740 --> 09:01:53.520
Soon the tree towered overhead, looking

09:01:53.520 --> 09:01:54.779
enormously proud of itself.

09:01:54.840 --> 09:01:58.680
I love it, Cricket breathed.

09:01:58.740 --> 09:02:01.560
Me too, Bumblebee declared.

09:02:01.619 --> 09:02:04.139
Let's call it Bumblebee Jr.

09:02:04.200 --> 09:02:07.200
You should make a tapestry of this tree

09:02:07.200 --> 09:02:09.900
Sundew said to Luna, the most beautiful

09:02:09.900 --> 09:02:11.099
bumblebee in the world.

09:02:11.159 --> 09:02:12.840
What?

09:02:12.959 --> 09:02:14.580
Bumblebee shrieked.

09:02:14.639 --> 09:02:17.340
Sundew and Willow both cracked up, and

09:02:17.340 --> 09:02:19.080
Bumblebee shook her little fist at them.

09:02:19.139 --> 09:02:22.500
Wait until you see her newest weaving.

09:02:22.560 --> 09:02:25.619
Sortell said happily, pulling out Luna's

09:02:25.619 --> 09:02:26.279
tapestry again.

09:02:26.340 --> 09:02:28.319
I think this is my favorite.

09:02:28.380 --> 09:02:32.099
You say that about every single one, Blue

09:02:32.099 --> 09:02:32.639
pointed out.

09:02:32.759 --> 09:02:34.799
And it's always true.

09:02:34.860 --> 09:02:36.720
Sortell beamed.

09:02:36.779 --> 09:02:39.000
He unfurled the weaving, and they all

09:02:39.000 --> 09:02:39.720
gathered around it.

09:02:39.779 --> 09:02:43.080
Oh, wow, Cricket said.

09:02:43.139 --> 09:02:45.599
All right, this one is my favorite too.

09:02:45.659 --> 09:02:49.979
You also say that about every single

09:02:49.979 --> 09:02:50.459
one.

09:02:50.520 --> 09:02:53.340
Blue observed, and they gave each other

09:02:53.340 --> 09:02:55.080
little starry eyed nudges.

09:02:55.139 --> 09:02:58.319
Cricket, Luna said slowly.

09:02:58.380 --> 09:03:01.139
I've been wondering if I should make some

09:03:01.139 --> 09:03:04.439
tapestries about, Well, about the

09:03:04.439 --> 09:03:06.720
scorching, and freedom's story.

09:03:06.779 --> 09:03:09.479
The real story of all the terrible things

09:03:09.479 --> 09:03:10.200
that happened.

09:03:10.259 --> 09:03:12.119
I don't really want to.

09:03:12.180 --> 09:03:14.880
I feel like they would be awful weavings

09:03:14.880 --> 09:03:18.000
and they'd make everyone sad, which is

09:03:18.000 --> 09:03:19.259
not what I want my silk to do.

09:03:19.319 --> 09:03:21.840
But I have to, don't I?

09:03:21.900 --> 09:03:24.720
Because they'd be true, and everyone

09:03:24.720 --> 09:03:26.459
should know the truth, shouldn't they?

09:03:26.520 --> 09:03:28.439
Yes.

09:03:28.500 --> 09:03:30.779
They should, Cricket said.

09:03:30.840 --> 09:03:32.759
But that's what I'm here for.

09:03:32.819 --> 09:03:34.799
I'll do that for you, Luna.

09:03:34.860 --> 09:03:37.979
I feel like that's my responsibility, and

09:03:37.979 --> 09:03:39.000
something I can do.

09:03:39.060 --> 09:03:42.779
I'll make sure dragons know the truth, and

09:03:42.779 --> 09:03:44.939
that we record history in our books, the

09:03:44.939 --> 09:03:47.880
way it really was, about cotton mouth, and

09:03:47.880 --> 09:03:50.159
this gorching, about the real book of

09:03:50.159 --> 09:03:52.439
Clearsight, and about what humans are

09:03:52.439 --> 09:03:52.740
like now.

09:03:52.799 --> 09:03:55.979
We'll help, said her dad.

09:03:56.040 --> 09:03:58.979
He adjusted his spectacles in exactly the

09:03:58.979 --> 09:04:00.119
way cricket always did.

09:04:00.180 --> 09:04:03.419
Writing was something I loved to do, when

09:04:03.419 --> 09:04:04.080
I was myself.

09:04:04.139 --> 09:04:05.400
When I was little.

09:04:05.459 --> 09:04:07.439
I had this plan that I would write about

09:04:07.439 --> 09:04:09.479
something that happened every day and

09:04:09.479 --> 09:04:11.220
give the story to all my neighbors.

09:04:11.639 --> 09:04:15.419
I did too, Cricket said, wide eyed.

09:04:15.479 --> 09:04:17.400
I had that exact same plan.

09:04:17.459 --> 09:04:21.360
Malachide patted her head tentatively

09:04:21.360 --> 09:04:23.639
like he was still trying out the gestures

09:04:23.639 --> 09:04:25.500
that went with the idea of dad.

09:04:25.619 --> 09:04:28.680
My parents shut that down pretty quick

09:04:28.680 --> 09:04:29.279
I'm afraid.

09:04:29.340 --> 09:04:33.000
Mine too, Cricket said glumly.

09:04:33.119 --> 09:04:35.520
I mean, my grandparents did.

09:04:35.639 --> 09:04:38.639
You wrote the stories for me for a while

09:04:38.639 --> 09:04:38.819
though.

09:04:38.880 --> 09:04:40.560
Katie did reminded her.

09:04:40.619 --> 09:04:43.439
I loved those, the one about the peacock

09:04:43.439 --> 09:04:45.119
that got loose in your school, and ran

09:04:45.119 --> 09:04:46.380
around screaming for a day.

09:04:46.439 --> 09:04:47.459
That was amazing.

09:04:47.520 --> 09:04:51.299
Cricket lit up as though her veins were

09:04:51.299 --> 09:04:52.319
full of flame silk.

09:04:52.439 --> 09:04:56.459
We can do it now, she said to Malachite.

09:04:56.520 --> 09:04:59.159
Together She turned to Luna.

09:04:59.220 --> 09:05:00.599
We'll do that part.

09:05:00.659 --> 09:05:03.119
You let us worry about telling the past

09:05:03.119 --> 09:05:05.520
and you keep making tapestries like this

09:05:05.520 --> 09:05:07.680
about the future we can all hope for.

09:05:07.740 --> 09:05:11.340
She touched the corner of the one sundew

09:05:11.340 --> 09:05:12.000
was inspecting.

09:05:12.060 --> 09:05:13.860
Is it worth it?

09:05:13.919 --> 09:05:15.060
Luna asked.

09:05:15.119 --> 09:05:18.599
Dreaming all these big, wild dreams that

09:05:18.599 --> 09:05:19.740
will probably never come true?

09:05:19.799 --> 09:05:22.860
Sometimes I think I should make my ideas

09:05:22.860 --> 09:05:25.080
smaller and more realistic.

09:05:25.139 --> 09:05:29.520
No, Blue said, taking her talon in his.

09:05:29.639 --> 09:05:32.759
I want the world with big dreams in it.

09:05:32.819 --> 09:05:34.439
Me too.

09:05:34.500 --> 09:05:35.939
Sundu agreed.

09:05:36.000 --> 09:05:38.400
We need dragons who can see the brightest

09:05:38.400 --> 09:05:41.159
futures, so we can try to get there, even

09:05:41.159 --> 09:05:42.720
if it takes longer than we wanted to.

09:05:42.779 --> 09:05:47.220
And even, if some dragons are stupid, and

09:05:47.220 --> 09:05:48.599
make getting there harder than it needs

09:05:48.599 --> 09:05:48.900
to be.

09:05:49.020 --> 09:05:51.419
SoreTail declared.

09:05:51.479 --> 09:05:53.099
Yeah!

09:05:53.220 --> 09:05:56.099
Bumblebee shouted, sound dragon stupid.

09:05:56.220 --> 09:05:58.200
Cricket winced.

09:05:58.259 --> 09:06:01.259
Except we don't use that word, remember?

09:06:01.319 --> 09:06:04.200
she said, giving Sortell a pointed look.

09:06:04.259 --> 09:06:07.560
We tried to use kind words and understand

09:06:07.560 --> 09:06:11.819
each, some dragons very stupid, Bumblebee

09:06:11.819 --> 09:06:14.040
shouted, loud enough that several of the

09:06:14.040 --> 09:06:15.959
dragons in the sky turned to see what the

09:06:15.959 --> 09:06:16.500
noise was.

09:06:16.559 --> 09:06:19.859
The stupidest, brains full of stupid.

09:06:19.919 --> 09:06:20.879
Ha, ha, ha.

09:06:20.940 --> 09:06:24.839
Thank you so much, Cricket said to

09:06:24.839 --> 09:06:27.180
Sortail, as Bumblebee bounded off into

09:06:27.180 --> 09:06:29.940
the grass, pouncing on grasshoppers, and

09:06:29.940 --> 09:06:31.080
yelling insults at them.

09:06:31.139 --> 09:06:34.139
He gave her an innocent shrug, and

09:06:34.139 --> 09:06:36.120
crouched to roll up the tapestry again

09:06:36.120 --> 09:06:37.680
Blue laughed.

09:06:37.739 --> 09:06:40.379
We do try to understand each other.

09:06:40.440 --> 09:06:44.160
Luna thought, looking at her brother, the

09:06:44.160 --> 09:06:46.019
sweetest, most understanding dragon in

09:06:46.019 --> 09:06:48.660
the world, who had still managed to fight

09:06:48.660 --> 09:06:49.680
back when he had to.

09:06:49.739 --> 09:06:52.979
But even if we find a way to understand

09:06:52.979 --> 09:06:55.859
the dragons who hurt us, that doesn't

09:06:55.859 --> 09:06:57.539
mean we have to let them do all the

09:06:57.539 --> 09:06:58.799
terrible things they want to do.

09:06:58.860 --> 09:07:02.160
We can empathize with them, like Blue

09:07:02.160 --> 09:07:06.000
does, and try to stop them, like sundew

09:07:06.000 --> 09:07:08.099
would, all at the same time.

09:07:08.220 --> 09:07:12.059
Well, now that certain little chaos

09:07:12.059 --> 09:07:14.459
monkeys aren't listening, Willow said

09:07:14.459 --> 09:07:16.199
watching Bumblebee charge away.

09:07:16.260 --> 09:07:19.500
Who wants to try the fried bananas Luna

09:07:19.500 --> 09:07:20.160
and I invented?

09:07:20.220 --> 09:07:24.000
But na, na, na, na, na...

09:07:24.000 --> 09:07:25.680
Bumblebee bellowed.

09:07:25.739 --> 09:07:28.499
Skidding around at top speed and hurtling

09:07:28.499 --> 09:07:29.399
back toward Willow.

09:07:29.459 --> 09:07:34.199
I suppose I deserve that, Willow said, as

09:07:34.199 --> 09:07:36.660
the dragonette scaled her leg and threw

09:07:36.660 --> 09:07:38.940
her arms around Willow's neck to yell

09:07:38.940 --> 09:07:40.559
Bananas, in her ear.

09:07:40.620 --> 09:07:42.959
Axolotl laughed.

09:07:43.019 --> 09:07:45.899
Bananas, they tried.

09:07:45.959 --> 09:07:47.220
Stu...

09:07:47.220 --> 09:07:48.120
Oopid?

09:07:48.239 --> 09:07:50.699
Bananas, yes.

09:07:50.760 --> 09:07:52.500
Cricket told them, holding out her

09:07:52.500 --> 09:07:53.040
talent.

09:07:53.099 --> 09:07:54.480
Stupid, no.

09:07:54.540 --> 09:07:57.300
Axolotl climbed up to her shoulder

09:07:57.300 --> 09:07:58.440
looking puzzled.

09:07:58.500 --> 09:08:01.199
Who's got the dream visitor this week?

09:08:01.260 --> 09:08:02.400
Sundu asked.

09:08:02.459 --> 09:08:05.639
Luna raised her talon, and they all

09:08:05.639 --> 09:08:07.620
turned to walk into the forest that

09:08:07.620 --> 09:08:09.660
sundew was growing with her leaf speak.

09:08:09.720 --> 09:08:12.540
Maybe we can see if any of our friends

09:08:12.540 --> 09:08:14.699
are asleep in the distant kingdoms and

09:08:14.699 --> 09:08:15.360
want to say hi.

09:08:15.419 --> 09:08:18.660
Pineapple and Jambu promised to visit

09:08:18.660 --> 09:08:20.099
soon, Luna said.

09:08:20.160 --> 09:08:23.459
And then we'll go there, Sortell said.

09:08:23.519 --> 09:08:26.279
And then they'll come here, and then

09:08:26.279 --> 09:08:29.099
we'll go there, and then there will be

09:08:29.099 --> 09:08:30.359
dragons in all directions.

09:08:30.419 --> 09:08:34.440
Dragons and humans, Cricket offered

09:08:34.440 --> 09:08:36.900
nudging Axolotl's foot affectionately.

09:08:36.959 --> 09:08:39.660
Sure, Swordtail agreed.

09:08:39.720 --> 09:08:42.000
Weird, but mostly dragons.

09:08:42.059 --> 09:08:46.199
Dragons and humans, living in peace after

09:08:46.199 --> 09:08:46.919
all this time.

09:08:46.980 --> 09:08:48.720
Luna said.

09:08:48.839 --> 09:08:51.059
Tilting her head back to watch the

09:08:51.059 --> 09:08:52.139
sunlight through the leaves.

09:08:52.260 --> 09:08:56.220
I can't wait to see what that future is

09:08:56.220 --> 09:08:56.459
like.

09:08:56.519 --> 09:09:02.879
A guide to the dragons of Pentala.

09:09:03.000 --> 09:09:05.279
Hive wings.

09:09:05.339 --> 09:09:06.659
Description.

09:09:06.720 --> 09:09:11.279
Red, yellow, and or orange, but always

09:09:11.279 --> 09:09:13.980
mixed with some black scales, 4 wings.

09:09:14.040 --> 09:09:17.940
Abilities vary from dragon to dragon.

09:09:18.000 --> 09:09:21.120
Examples include deadly stingers that can

09:09:21.120 --> 09:09:23.400
extend from their wrists to stab their

09:09:23.400 --> 09:09:23.819
enemies.

09:09:23.940 --> 09:09:27.540
Venom in their teeth or claws, a

09:09:27.540 --> 09:09:29.879
paralyzing toxin that can immobilize

09:09:29.879 --> 09:09:30.480
their prey.

09:09:30.540 --> 09:09:34.800
Or boiling acid, sprayed from a stinger

09:09:34.800 --> 09:09:35.459
on their tails.

09:09:35.519 --> 09:09:38.759
Queen, Queen Wasp.

09:09:38.879 --> 09:09:42.779
Silk wings, description.

09:09:42.839 --> 09:09:46.079
Silkwing dragonettes are born wingless

09:09:46.079 --> 09:09:49.079
but go through a metamorphosis at age 6

09:09:49.079 --> 09:09:52.379
when they develop 4 huge wings and silk

09:09:52.379 --> 09:09:54.959
spinning abilities, as beautiful and

09:09:54.959 --> 09:09:58.079
gentle as butterflies, with scales in any

09:09:58.079 --> 09:10:01.019
color under the sun, except black.

09:10:01.080 --> 09:10:05.279
Abilities, can spin silk from glands on

09:10:05.279 --> 09:10:07.680
their wrists to create webs or other

09:10:07.680 --> 09:10:10.680
woven articles, can detect vibrations

09:10:10.680 --> 09:10:12.779
with their antennae to assess threats.

09:10:12.839 --> 09:10:16.259
Queen, wasp.

09:10:16.379 --> 09:10:19.679
The last silkwing queen, before the tree

09:10:19.679 --> 09:10:21.779
wars, was Queen Monarch.

09:10:21.839 --> 09:10:24.419
Leaf Wings.

09:10:24.480 --> 09:10:27.900
Description, wiped out during the tree

09:10:27.900 --> 09:10:30.360
wars with the hive wings, but while they

09:10:30.360 --> 09:10:32.580
lived, this tribe had green and brown

09:10:32.580 --> 09:10:35.400
scales and wings shaped like leaves

09:10:35.400 --> 09:10:38.940
abilities, could absorb energy from

09:10:38.940 --> 09:10:40.859
sunlight, and were accomplished

09:10:40.859 --> 09:10:41.339
gardeners.

09:10:41.400 --> 09:10:44.940
Some were rumored to have unusual control

09:10:44.940 --> 09:10:45.900
over plants.

09:10:46.019 --> 09:10:47.879
Queen.

09:10:47.940 --> 09:10:51.000
Last known queen of the leaf wings was

09:10:51.000 --> 09:10:54.900
Queen Sequoia, about 50 years ago, at the

09:10:54.900 --> 09:10:56.099
time of the tree wars.

09:11:20.220 --> 09:11:22.139
This is Shannon McManus.

09:11:22.199 --> 09:11:23.879
We hope that you have enjoyed this

09:11:23.879 --> 09:11:27.899
production of Wings of Fire, Book 15, The

09:11:27.899 --> 09:11:30.659
Flames of Hope, by 2ET Sutherland.

